var DATA = {"Q24071475":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.33517,"wikipedia":{"Dagupan Church":"Santuario de San Juan Evangelista"},"locDesc":null,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Dagupan, Pangasinan","lat":16.04248,"name":"Church of Dagupan","region":"Ilocos Region","address":"Dagupan Church, Zamora Street, Dagupan, Pangasinan","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The Augustinians had charge of the spiritual administration of Dagupan from 1590 to 1713, and the Dominicans from 1713 to the close of the nineteenth century. An early church and a convent were burned in 1660 when Andres Malong's men razed the town. The Rev. Pedro Rama, O.P., rebuilt this church in 1816. In 1895 the Rev. Vicente Iztegui, O.P. rebuilt the facade that the earthquake of March 16, 1892 had destroyed.</p>","title":"Church of Dagupan","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":3456,"hash":"77","file":"Dagupan Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608}}}},"Q54810513":{"lon":120.38925,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Isabelo de los Reyes":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","date":"2003-05-01","lat":17.57368,"name":"Isabelo F. de los Reyes","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Tagapagtatag ng kilusang paggawa sa Pilipinas. Ipinanganak sa Vigan, Ilocos Sur, 6 Hulyo 1864. Dinakip sa hinalang pagiging sangkot sa Himagsikang Pilipino, 1896. Ipinatapon sa Espanya, Enero 1897. Nagtatag ng Union Obrera Democratica de Filipinas, unang kilusang sa paggawa sa Pilipinas, 2 Pebrero 1902. Ipinahayag ang pagtatag ng Iglesia Filipina Independiente, 3 Agosto 1902. Konsehal ng Maynila, 1912–1919. Obispo Pandangal ng Iglesia Filipina Independiente, 1929–1938. Nagtatag ng mga pahayagang El Ilocano (unang pahayagang pangrehiyon sa Pilipinas), El Defensor de Filipinas, Filipinas ante Europa, at La Rendicion del Obrero. May akda ng mga kasulatang tungkol sa kasaysayan at sining ng Pilipinas tulad ng Historia de Ilocos, El Folklore Filipinas, Historia de Filipinas, La Religion de Katipunan at Independencia y Revolucion, at mga kasulatang pangrelihiyon tulad ng Biblia Filipina Divino Oficio at Genesis Cientifico y Moderno. Yumao, 10 Oktubre 1938.</p>","title":"Isabelo F. de los Reyes","subtitle":"(1864–1938)"}}},"address":"1 Calle Crisologo, Vigan, Ilocos Sur"},"Q50384010":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":458,"file":"Agoncillo marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"5e","height":653},"text":{"title":"Felipe Encarnacion Agoncillo at Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo","subtitle":"(1859–1941) (1859–1946)","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ang unang Pilipinong diplomatiko at ang tumahi ng bandila ng Pilipinas na buong pagmamalaking iwinagayway ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo sa Kawit, Cavite noong Hunyo 12, 1898 sa pagpapahayag ng pagsasarili ng Pilipinas, ay maligaya at masayang nanirahan kapiling ang kanilang mga ulirang anak na sina Lorenza, Gregoria, Eugenia, Marcela at Maria.</p>"}}},"address":"2020 M. H. del Pilar Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Felipe Encarnacion Agoncillo at Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo","lat":14.56768,"date":"1990-05-26","macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Felipe Agoncillo":true,"Marcela Agoncillo":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98511},"Q52161871":{"date":"1983-10-24","macroAddress":"Batac, Ilocos Norte","lat":18.05986,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":3693,"file":"Historical Marker Don Mariano Marcos y Rubio.JPG","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":5554,"hash":"29"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Born in Batac, Ilocos Norte, 21 April 1897, to Don Fabian Marcos and Doña Cresencia Rubio. His father was the Justice of the Peace, school teacher and gobernadorcillo of Batac after the Revolution. Married to Josefa Quetulio Edralin, 1916; children: Ferdinand, Pacifico, Elizabeth and Fortuna. </p><p> Primary schooling in the new elementary schools established by the Americans, Ilocos Norte. Secondary education, Manila. Teacher’s course, Philippine Normal School, 1916. </p><p> Principal teacher, 1917; lieutenant, Philippine National Guard, 1918; Laoag School District supervisor, 1919; and teacher, National University, Manila, 1921. Graduated valedictorian in law, University of the Philippines, 1925. </p><p>Representative to the Philippine Assembly, second district, Ilocos Norte, 1925; Chairman, Committee on Style; member, Committees on Library, Public Instruction, Civil Service, Public Lands, Mines and Natural Resources of the Assembly. Appointed by President Manuel L. Quezon as technical assistant and Deputy Governor of Davao to hasten pioneer settlements, 1932. His elder son Ferdinand elected President of the Philippines, 1965, 1969, 1981.</p><p>Died in La Union, March 1945.</p>","subtitle":"(1897–1945)","title":"Don Mariano Marcos y Rubio"}}},"address":"Mariano Marcos State University, Marcos Avenue, Batac, Ilocos Norte","name":"Don Mariano Marcos y Rubio","region":"Ilocos Region","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.5486,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Mariano Marcos":true}},"Q23987469":{"name":"Paco Cemetery","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Completed shortly previous to the cholera epidemic of 1820. Nine of the niches were donated by the City of Manila in grateful acknowledgment of the services of the Dominicans to the victoms of cholera. The mausoleum of Governor General Ramon Solano y Lladeral is inside the mortuary chapel. The remains of the Filipino leader, Dr. José Rizal y Mercado, were interred here from December 30, 1896 to December 29, 1912.</p>","title":"Paco Cemetery","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"af","height":2423,"file":"IJVPacoCemetery1.jpg","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2018}}},"address":"Paco Park, Gen. Luna Street cor. Padre Faura Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","date":"1938","lat":14.58093,"wikipedia":{"Paco Park":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the park’s entrance.","lon":120.98852,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Entrance of Paco Park.jpg","width":3264,"height":2448,"hash":"87"}},"Q54669863":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Tinaguriang “Henerala,” isinilang sa Malibay, 1869. Tumungo sa Cavite pagkaraang sumiklab ang Himagsikang Filipino, Agosto 1896 at sumapi sa himagsikan sa Cavite. Nakilahok at namuno sa isang pangkat ng mga rebolusyonaryo sa Labanan sa Pasong Santol kung saan siya nasawi, 21 Marso 1897.</p>","title":"Marcela Marcelo–Lugo","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Malibay Plaza, Clemente Jose Street cor. Apelo Cruz Street, Malibay, Pasay, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Marcela Marcelo–Lugo","lat":14.53416,"date":"2006","macroAddress":"Pasay, Metro Manila","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":121.00918,"locPhoto":null},"Q25069958":{"wikipedia":{"Bridge of Isabel II":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is installed at the upper portion of a commemorative structure on the balcony on the southbound side of the bridge.","lon":120.94022,"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"1c","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"ImusCavitejf0723 07.JPG","width":4608},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Bridge of Isabel II","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Bridge of Isabel II historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3000,"hash":"bf","height":3239},"text":{"title":"Bridge of Isabel II","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This bridge was constructed shortly before 1857 by the lay Brother Matias Carbonell, A.R. (1806–1861), overseer of the Hacienda de Imus. A silver medal was awarded the builder by Don Ramon Montero, Governor General of the Philippines.</p>"}}},"address":"Bridge of Isabel II, Imus, Cavite","lat":14.43023,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Imus, Cavite"},"Q30129474":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":-118.26048,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Jose Rizal","subtitle":"(1861–1896)","inscription":"<p>Philippine National Hero. Born on 19 June 1861. Doctor, poet, writer, educator, linguist, inventor.</p><p>Authored novels Noli Me Tangere (1887) and El Filibusterismo (1891) which bared colonial oppression of the Filipinos. He advocated nonviolent struggle for freedom but was charged with inciting dissent.</p><p>The living soul of the 1896 Philippine revolution, he was executed on 30 December 1896.</p><p>His martyrdom inspired a sense of nationhood that eventually led to the proclamation of the Philippine Independence in 1898.</p><p>Installed in commemoration of Jose Rizal’s 150<sup>th</sup> birth anniversary.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"José Rizal (Carson, California) historical marker.jpg","width":2304,"hash":"d2","height":3456}}},"address":"801 E. Carson Street, Carson, Los Angeles County, California, United States of America","region":"Overseas","name":"Jose Rizal","lat":33.83206,"macroAddress":"Carson, California, United States","date":"2012-09-29"},"Q52356816":{"address":"Washington Street cor. Dewey Street, Batac, Ilocos Norte","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Teacher, soldier, and patriot, Born here in Batac, Ilocos Norte, to Esteban Ricarte y Faustino and Bonifacia Garcia y Rigonan. Holder of the Bachelor of Arts, San Juan de Letran, and Teacher’s Certificate for Primary Instruction. Principal of the San Francisco de Malabon Primary School in Cavite; Brigadier-General, Magdiwang faction: chosen Captain-General by the Tejeros Convention.</p><p>Captured by the Americans in 1900. Imprisoned and banished to Guam in 1901. Refusing to take the oath of allegiance to the United States Government, he lived abroad. Returned to the Philippines from Japan during World War II. Died in Barrio Nagparaon, Kalinga Mt. Province.</p>","title":"General Artemio Ricarte (Vibora)","subtitle":"20 October 1866 – 31 July 1945"},"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker General Artemio Ricarte.jpg","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3224,"height":4849,"hash":"06"}}},"name":"General Artemio Ricarte (Vibora)","region":"Ilocos Region","macroAddress":"Batac, Ilocos Norte","date":"1966","lat":18.0564,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Artemio Ricarte":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.56555},"Q54370374":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.54417,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"date":"1988-12-17","macroAddress":"Iloilo City","lat":10.6977,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Lider rebolusyonaryo at makabayan. Isinilang sa Molo (dating Parian), Iloilo noong Agosto 17, 1865. Nagkamit ng titulong Batsilyer sa Sining, Ateneo Municipal de Manila, 1883; Titulo de Agrimensor y Perito Tasador de Tierras, 1885 at Lisensiyado sa Medisina, 1890 kapwa sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas. Naging kapitan ng Voluntarios de Ejercito Español ng Molo, 1898; hepe superior ng ekspedisyong rebolusyonaryo na dumaong sa Lipata, Antique, 1898; tinalo ang mga kawal Kastila sa Labanan sa Arevalo, Iloilo; Komandante Heneral ng Hukbong Rebolusyonaryo ng Iloilo at kinatawan ng Hukbo sa Republika ng Visaya, 1898; presidente municipal ng Molo, 1902; punong pangkalusugan ng lalawigan ng Iloilo, 1905–1907; punong sanidad de Panay, 1907–1908; at kagawad ng sangguniang panlalawigan ng Iloilo, 1909. Namatay noong 1943.</p>","title":"Pablo Araneta y Soriano","subtitle":"(1865–1943)"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Araneta soriano historical marker.JPG","width":1449,"height":2155,"hash":"e5"}}},"address":"Molo Convent, San Pedro Street, Molo, Iloilo City","name":"Pablo Araneta y Soriano","region":"Western Visayas"},"Q56051825":{"date":"1993","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","lat":14.58405,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang isang natatanging klub ng mga Kastilang (Hijos del Pais) naninirahan sa Maynila noong 1893. Itinayo ang unang gusali ayon sa disenyo ni Juan Arellano, 1913; pinasinayaan, 1917. Nasira noong Liberasyon ng Maynila, 1945. Pansamantalang nalipat ito sa isang bahay sa panulukan ng Daang Oregon (ngayo’y Apacible) at Daang Perez, Paco. Muling itinayo sa kasalukuyang pook sa pamamagitan ni Ignacio Planas, 1951. Dito ginaganap ang mga mahahalagang pagdiriwang ng Espanya. Sa kasalukuyan, ang klub na ito ay isang buhay na sagisag ng mainit at magandang pagsasamahan ng Pilipinas at Espanya.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Casino Español de Manila"},"photo":{"file":"Casino Espanol de Manila 8.JPG","credit":"Claire Algarme {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1288,"height":1936,"hash":"10"}}},"address":"Casino Español de Manila, 855 Teodoro M. Kalaw Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Casino Español de Manila","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"hash":"84","height":1288,"credit":"Claire Algarme {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Casino Espanol de Manila 9.JPG","width":1936},"lon":120.985,"locDesc":"This historical marker is located on the right wall of the entrance hall.","wikipedia":{"Casino Español de Manila":true}},"Q54849330":{"lon":120.98121,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Andres Bonifacio":"Andrés Bonifacio"},"date":"1997","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","lat":14.59084,"address":"The Life and Heroism of Gat Andres Bonifacio, Padre Burgos Avenue cor. Natividad Almeda-Lopez Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pagpupugay kay Andres Bonifacio, masigasig na tagapagtanggol ng kalayaan, supremo at dakilang ama ng Katipunan. Siya ay ipinanganak sa Tondo, Maynila noong Nobyembre 30, 1863. Dahil sa pag-ibig sa tinubuang lupa, siya ay sumapi sa La Liga Filipina at nagtatag ng Katipunan, isang lihim na samahan na ang layunin ay makamtan ang kasarinlan ng Pilipinas sa rebulusyonaryong pamamaraan. Sumulat ng mga makabayang tula at sanaysay na naging batis ng diwang malaya ng mga Pilipino. Sa kanyang kabayanihan, ang panandang pangkasaysayang ito ay iniaalay ng madlang Pilipino sa kanyang karangalan sa pagdiriwang ng ikasandaang taon ng kanyang kabayanihan.</p>","title":"Memorare","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"name":"Memorare","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q28877414":{"name":"Ang Lumang Bayan ng Dapitan","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","address":"Lawaan Rotonda, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Lumang Bayan ng Dapitan","inscription":"<p>Ipinahayag na Heritage Zone / Historic Center ng pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 24 Mayo 2011 sa bisa ng NHCP Board Resolution No. 3 S. 2011.</p>"},"photo":{"width":472,"file":"Old Town of Dapitan historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","height":351,"hash":"93"}}},"macroAddress":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","date":"2011","lat":8.64714,"wikipedia":{"Dapitan":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal at the center of the rotunda.","locPhoto":{"width":2496,"credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Dapitan City Old Town Marker.JPG","height":2952,"hash":"be"},"lon":123.4218},"Q40318367":{"lon":120.97387,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"José Burgos":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1984","lat":14.592,"name":"Padre Jose A. Burgos","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"59","height":559,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Padre Jose Burgos in Cabildo.jpg","width":414},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Padre Jose A. Burgos","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito nanirahan si Padre Burgos mula noong 1865 hanggang 1872 at nagtrabaho para sa mga pagbabago sa simbahan sa ilalim ng Espanya. Naging kura paroko ng Parroquia del Sagrario, fiscal eclesiastico at pansamantalang canonigo magistral ng Katedral ng Maynila sa Intramoros. Tungkol sa kanya si Kardinal Gonzales, isang Kastila, ay nagwika: “Ang Pilipinas ay mangangailangan pa marahil ng isan-daang taon upang magkaroon ng isang anak na may katalinuhang tulad ni P. Jose A. Burgos.” Kasama sina Padre Gomes at Zamora, siya ay namatay na isang martir sa Luneta noong Pebrero 17, 1872.</p>"}}},"address":"Cabildo Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q54806261":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Elpidio Quirino":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.38722,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3663,"hash":"4d","file":"Elpidio Quirino Historical Marker Vigan.JPG","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2436},"text":{"title":"Elpidio R. Quirino","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Born in Vigan, Ilocos Sur, November 16, 1890. Finished his elementary studies in Aringay, La Union and secondary school course at Manila High School, 1911. Obtained the degree of Bachelor of Laws, University of the Philippines, 1915. Started service in the government as a school teacher in Daparian, Agoo, La Union at the age of 16. Appointed private secretary to President Manuel L. Quezon; Secretary of Finance under Governor General Frank Murphy and Secretary of the Department of Interior. Elected representative of Ilocos Sur, 1919; Senator, 1922, 1931, 1941; Delegate, Constitutional Convention, 1934; and Vice President of the Republic of the Philippines, 1946. Became the President of the Philippines with the death of President Manuel A. Roxas, 1948; elected President of the Republic, 1949. Died, February 29, 1956. His administration was highlighted by economic recovery of the country devastated by the Second World War and the restoration of peace and trust of the citizenry in the government.</p>"}}},"address":"Plaza Salcedo, Quezon Avenue, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","name":"Elpidio R. Quirino","region":"Ilocos Region","date":"1982","macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","lat":17.57559},"Q52161722":{"lat":14.57765,"date":"2007-12-01","macroAddress":"Cainta, Rizal","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Cainta","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni Padre Gaspar Marco, S.J. ang simbahang yari sa bato, 1707. Tinapos ni Padre Joaquin Sanchez, S.J., 1716. Inialay sa Patronato ng Nuestra Señora de la Luz, 1727. Naging simbahang parokyal, 1760. Nasunog kasama ang larawan ng patron noong Digmaang Filipino-Amerikano, 1899. Ipininta ni Fernando Amorsolo ang replika ng larawan ng patron, 1950. Muling ipinatayo ang simbahan at ipinanumbalik ang orihinal na harapan ni Arkitekto Fernando Ocampo, 1966. Pinasinayaan ni Rufino Cardinal Santos, 25 Pebrero 1968.</p>"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Cainta Church historical marker.jpg","height":4608,"hash":"96"}}},"address":"Cainta Church, A. Bonifacio Avenue, Cainta, Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng Cainta","locPhoto":{"file":"Cainta Church facade.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"hash":"c1","height":4608},"lon":121.11562,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the right pilaster base immediately to the right of the main entrance.","wikipedia":{"Cainta Church":"Our Lady of Light Parish Church"}},"Q52387913":{"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Camalaniugan, Cagayan","lat":18.27158,"name":"Church of Camalaniugan","region":"Cagayan Valley","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>The ecclesiastical administration of Camalaniugan was accepted by the Dominicans on June 15, 1596. The Church and the Convent were destroyed by fire in 1719. They were rebuilt but were destroyed again by the typhoon of October 7, 1845. The silk weaving industry received great impetus when the parish priest, Rev. Francisco Rojano, O.P., introduced European looms in 1737.</p>","title":"Church of Camalaniugan","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Camalaniugan Church, Camalaniugan, Cagayan","lon":121.67581,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q54888799":{"locPhoto":{"height":750,"hash":"7c","credit":"Francisco M. Pajares, Jr. {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Panay Church main entrance.jpg","width":900},"lon":122.79391,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade to the right of the main entrance.","wikipedia":{"Panay Church":true},"date":"1997-12-06","macroAddress":"Panay, Capiz","lat":11.55559,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pan-ay, originally called Bamban, was established in 1572. The first church, constructed in 1774 by Fr. Miguel Murguia, was heavily damaged by typhoon in 1875. The present church was constructed in 1884 under the direction of Fr. Jose Beloso who commissioned Don Juan Reina to cast a bell for the church from seventy sacks of coins donated by the townspeople. This bell, the biggest in the Philippines, measures seven feet in diameter, five feet in height, and weighs 10,400 kilograms.</p><p>By virtue of NHI Board Resolution No. 3, S. 1997, this church is declared a National Historical Landmark.</p>","title":"Church of Pan-ay","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":2000,"file":"Church of Pan-ay historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Bukidisarog; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"18","height":2451}}},"address":"Panay Church, Panay, Capiz","name":"Church of Pan-ay","region":"Western Visayas"},"Q37782699":{"locDesc":"The marker is at the base of the statue of Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy located at the left side of the facade of the Tejeros Convention house.","wikipedia":{"Emilio Aguinaldo":true},"locPhoto":{"hash":"eb","height":1080,"width":1920,"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Tejeros Convention House.jpg"},"lon":120.86078,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1155,"file":"Emilio Aguinaldo marker at Site of Tejeros Convention.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":2048,"hash":"5e"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Bayani at unang pangulo ng Pilipinas. Isinilang sa Kawit, Cavite, 22 Marso 1869. Naging Kapitan Munisipal ng Kawit at kasapi ng Katipunan sa pangalang Magdalo, 1895. Naging Pangulo ng pamahalaang rebolusyonaryo sa Tejeros, 22 Marso 1897; at Republika ng Biyak-na-Bato, 2 Nobyembre 1897. Nadestiyero sa Hong Kong, 27 Disyembre 1897. Dito niya itinatag ang Hong Kong Junta at ipinagawa ang bandila ng Pilipinas. Bmalik sa Pilipinas pang ipagpatuloy ang laban para sa kalayaan, 19 Mayo 1898. Itinatag ang pamahalaang diktatoryal, 24 Mayo 1898. Inatasan si Julian Felipe na kumatha ng \"Marcha Filipina Magdalo\" na kalauna'y naging pambansang awit, 4 Hunyo 1898. Ipinahayag ang kalayaan ng Pilipinas sa Espanya sa Kawit, Cavite, 12 Hunyo 1898. Itinatag ang pamahalaang rebolusyonanryo ng Pilipinas, 23 Hunyo 1898. Pinulong ang kongreso ng Malolos sa simbahan ng Barasoain, Bulacan na magbabalangkas ng saligang batas, 15 Setyembre 1898. Hinirang bilang pangul kasabay ng pagtatatag ng Republika ng Pilipinas, 23 Enero 1899. Pinamunuan ang digmaang Filipino laban sa mga Amerikano, 1899-1901. Nadakip sa Palanan, Isabela, 23 Marso 1901. Yumao, 6 Pebrero 1964.</p>","subtitle":"(1869–1964)","title":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy"}}},"address":"General Trias Drive, Rosario, Cavite","name":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Rosario, Cavite","date":"2011","lat":14.40109},"Q52180914":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":120.98962,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Asociacion Feminista Filipina (Philippine Feminist Association) historical marker.jpg","hash":"69","height":4608},"text":{"subtitle":"(Philippine Feminist Association)","title":"Asociacion Feminista Filipina","inscription":"<p>Founded on 30 June 1905 in Manila at the initiative of Concepcion Felix and with the collaboration of Trinidad Rizal, Clemencia Lopez, Bonifacia Delgado de Barretto, Maria Arevalo, Sofia Reyes, Helen C. Wilson, Paz Natividad Vda. de Zulueta, Maria F. de Villamor, Teresa Solis and Agueda and Jacoba Paterno. It was the first woman's club in the Philippines dedicated to the promotion of social welfare and the encouragement of the participation of women in public affairs. The first president was Concepcion Felix; secretary, Trinidad Rizal; treasurer, Bonifacia Delgado de Barrett; and the members of the Board of Directors were Clemencia Lopez, Maria F. de Villamor, Maria Arevalo and Helen C. Wilson.</p><p>The first meeting was held at the home of Paz Natividad Vda. de Zulueta on Salcedo Street (now part of Rizal Avenue).</p>"}}},"address":"NFWC Building, 962 J. Escoda Street cor. San Marcelino Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Asociacion Feminista Filipina","lat":14.5783,"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"1955"},"Q55712996":{"date":"1981","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","lat":14.60028,"name":"Ariston Bautista Lin","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Chinatown Gold Center, 509-11 Ronquillo Street, Plaza Santa Cruz, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Ariston Bautista Lin 1863 - 1928 Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":428,"hash":"ea","height":635},"text":{"subtitle":"1863–1928","title":"Ariston Bautista Lin","inscription":"<p>Manggagamot, pilantropo at makabayan. Siya ay ipinanganak sa pook na ito noong ika-22 ng Pebrero 1863 kina Mariano A. Bautista at Teresa Limpingco. Nag-aral ng medisina sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, 30 Hunyo 1891 at nagtapos na may titulong Lisensiyado at Doktor ng Medisina sa Universidad Central de Madrid, 20 Abril 1892. Kinilalang klinista dahil sa pagbalangkas niya ng orihinal na mga reseta para sa panggagamot ng ketong, kolera at tisis. Naging puno ng kagawarang klinikal ng Kolehiyo ng Medisina ng Pamantasan ng Pilipinas, 1916–1917. Naging unang Pilipinong pangulo ng Lupon ng mga Tagasuri sa Medisina, 1903. Kasama nina Rizal, Luna, del Pilar at Lopez Jaena sa Kilusan ng Pagpapalaganap. Ibinilanggo sa Kutang Santiago, 1896. Naging kagawad ng Kongreso ng Unang Republika ng Pilipinas, 1898. Namatay sa Maynila noong ika-3 ng Marso 1928.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98051,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q28865328":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Pagsanjan","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Historical marker of Pagsanjan.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"hash":"68","height":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Formerly a barrio of Lumbang. Organized into a municipality, 1668. Francisco Umali, first Gobernadorcillo. Became capital of Laguna, 1688–1858. Town gate constructed, 1878–1880; inaugurated, 1984, by Don Pedro A. Paterno. Occupied by the revolutionists, 1896; by the Americans, 1899; by the Japanese, 1942. Liberated, 1945, by the Filipinos, led by Manuel Soriano.</p>","title":"Pagsanjan","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Pagsanjan Arch, J. P. Rizal Street, Pagsanjan, Laguna","lat":14.27328,"macroAddress":"Pagsanjan, Laguna","date":"1953","wikipedia":{"Pagsanjan":true,"Pagsanjan Arch":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.44906},"Q55100868":{"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Malabuyoc","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Malabuyoc","inscription":"<p>Nagsimula bilang visita ng Samboan, 1784 at naging ganap na parokya sa patronato ni San Nicolas de Tolentino, 1834. Itinayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan yari sa korales, 1863. Ginawa ang kumbento batay sa disenyo ni Domingo de Escondrillas, 1881–1885. Ipinagawa ang isang bantayan na yari sa kahoy at korales, malapit sa Kipot ng Tañon, na naging himpilan ng mga nagbibigay babala na may parating na mga pirata noong kalagitnaaan ng ika-9 na siglo.</p>"},"photo":{"height":1079,"hash":"8d","width":1156,"credit":"Tabunon {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Hm churchMalabuyoc (cropped).jpg"}}},"address":"Malabuyoc Church, Malabuyoc, Cebu","lat":9.6512,"macroAddress":"Malabuyoc, Cebu","date":"2017-09-25","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":123.32401,"locPhoto":null},"Q54811181":{"wikipedia":{"Gabriela Silang":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.43469,"name":"Maria Josefa Gabriela Silang","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>In this municipality of Santa, Barrio Canniogan, Ilocos Sur, was born Maria Josefa Gabriela Silang ca. 1723. Wife of Diego Silang, leader of the Ilocos Revolt, she continued with the uprising after his assassination. She was later captured by the Spanish authorities and executed on September 20, 1763. She was the first woman to lead a revolt in the Philippines.</p>","subtitle":"1723–1763","title":"Maria Josefa Gabriela Silang"}}},"address":"Imelda Garden and Park, Santa, Ilocos Sur","date":"1963","macroAddress":"Santa, Ilocos Sur","lat":17.4861},"Q52404834":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Jose Rizal","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3699,"hash":"54","file":"Jose Rizal historical marker at Rizal Capitol.jpg","credit":"Photo: Roel Balingit; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2500},"text":{"title":"Jose Rizal","subtitle":"(1861–1896)","inscription":"<p>Pambansang Bayani ng Pilipinas. Doktor, agrimensor, dalubwika, manunulat, makata, eskultor at pintor. Isinilang sa Calamba, Laguna, 19 Hunyo 1861. May-akda ng Noli me Tangere (1887) at El Filibusterismo (1891), mga nobelang higit pang nagpaalab sa mga Filipino na maghimagsik laban sa Espanya. Dinakip at ipinatapon sa Dapitan, Mindanao, 6 Hulyo 1892. Nagboluntaryo bilang manggagamot ng puwersang Espanyol sa Cuba, 1896, nguni’t muling dinakip habang patungong Espanya sa bintang rebelyon. Binaril sa Bagumbayan (ngayo’y Rizal Park), Maynila, 30 Disyembre 1896. Ipinangalan sa kanya ang bagong tatag na lalawigang Rizal, sa bisa ng Philippine Commission Act Blg. 137, 11 Hunyo 1901. Patuloy na inspirasyon para sa kalayan at pagkabansang Filipino.</p>"}}},"address":"Rizal Provincial Capitol, Sen. L. Sumulong Memorial Circle cor. P. Oliveros Street, Antipolo, Rizal","lat":14.58674,"date":"2012","macroAddress":"Antipolo, Rizal","wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of the Rizal Monument found at the northwest corner of Ynares Center Complex.","locPhoto":{"hash":"bd","height":4160,"width":3120,"file":"Rizal Monument, Rizal Capitol 2.jpg","credit":"Roel Balingit {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"lon":121.1689},"Q40999993":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng Recoletos","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ipinatayo ang simbahan at kumbento ng San Nicolas de Tolentino ng Order of Agustinian Recollects (OAR) sa kagandahang-loob ni Bernardino del Castillo Maldonado, 1608. Nagsilbing pangunahing kumbento ng mga Recoletos sa Pilipinas, Tsina, Hapon at Marianas Islands. Kilala sa pagiging maadorno at sa malaking kampanaryo. Ang simbahan ay napinsala ng lindol, 30 Nobyembre 1645, tuluyang nawasak, 20 Agosto 1658. Muling ipinatayo subalit gumuho dahil sa lindol, 1722; at ipinatayong muli, 1780. Nagtamo ng malubhang pinsala noong Labanan sa Maynila, 1945; tuluyang nagiba, 1959. Idinambana sa simbahaan ang mga imahen ng Nuestro Padre Jesus Nazareno, Virgen de la Salud, San Jose at Santa Lucia. Nanirahan sa kumbento ang naging santo na si Ezekiel Moreno, ang apat na banal na martir ng Hapon, ang banal na si Vicente Soler at ang apat pang martir ng Mortil sa Espanya.</p>"},"photo":{"width":443,"file":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng Recoletos Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"21","height":602}}},"address":"Recoletos Street cor. Muralla Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng Recoletos","lat":14.58861,"date":"2006","macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Province of Saint Ezequiél Moreno":"Augustinian Recollect Province of Saint Ezequiél Moreno"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97871},"Q53707114":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>On this site of this town, Baler, was born Manuel Luis Quezon, 19 August 1878. Indomitable crusader of Philippine independence and social justice, great and fiery statesman, dynamic and far-sighted leader, and true patriot. Son of Lucio Quezon and Maria Molina. Became a soldier in 1899, lawyer, 1903; member, First Philippine Assembly, 1907–1909; Resident Commissioner at Washington, D.C., 1909–1916; President, Philippine Senate, 1916–1935; President, Commonwealth of the Philippines, 1935–1944. Died at Saranac Lake, New York, 1 August 1944.</p>","title":"Birthplace of Manuel Luis Quezon","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":425,"hash":"5c","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"MLQ Birthplace.jpg","width":285}}},"address":"Quezon Park, Quezon Street cor. Aurora Street, Baler, Aurora","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Birthplace of Manuel Luis Quezon","lat":15.75964,"macroAddress":"Baler, Aurora","date":"1948","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Manuel L. Quezon":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.56194},"Q54806683":{"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":1920,"file":"Syquia Mansion plate.JPG","credit":"Oloapsaziracav {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":1080,"hash":"2e"},"text":{"title":"Syquia Mansion","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This is a Heritage House pursuant to Board Resolution No. 1 dated January 18, 2002 of the National Historical Insitute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>"}}},"address":"Quirino Boulevard cor. Salcedo Street, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","name":"Syquia Mansion","region":"Ilocos Region","date":"2002-02-02","macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","lat":17.571,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.3899},"Q46996498":{"lat":14.3857,"macroAddress":"General Trias, Cavite","date":"1992-12-12","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng Heneral Trias","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"0e","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of General Trias historical marker.jpg","width":3456},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Heneral Trias","inscription":"<p>Ang unang kapilya na yari sa magagaang materyal at itinayo ng mga misyonerong Pransiskano nang ang pook na ito ay isang bisita pa lamang ng Kawit noong mga taong 1611. Isinalin sa misyong Heswita ng Cavite Puerto, 1624. Naging nagsasariling parokya, Setyembre 9, 1753. Ang simbahang yari sa bato ay ipinagawa noong 1769 sa pangunguna ni Doña Maria Josepha de Yrizzari y Ursula, Condesa de Lizarraga. Ipinaayos at pinalakihan, 1834; bahagyang napinsala ng lindol, 1880; pinalitan ang harapan o patsada, 1881; pinaganda, 1885; pinalitan ang bubong na tisa ng yero galbanisado, 1892; muling inayos at pinalaki, 1893; ibinalik sa dating anyo, 1989–1991; kinonsagra ng Obispo Felix P. Perez, Hunyo 22, 1991. Sa simbahang ito ininsayo ng Banda Matanda ang Marcha Filipina bago ito tinugtog nang ipahayag ang kalayaan ng Pilipinas sa Kawit, Hunyo 12, 1898.</p>"}}},"address":"General Trias Church, General Trias, Cavite","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.88012,"wikipedia":{"General Trias Church":"St. Francis of Assisi Parish Church (General Trias)"},"locDesc":null},"Q55216921":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1869 1915)","title":"Hen. Baldomero Aguinaldo y Baloy","inscription":"<p>Isinilang noong 28 Pebrero 1869 sa Binakayan, Kawit, Cavite. Anak ni Cipriano Aguinaldo at Silvestra Baloy. Nag-aral sa Ateneo Municipal at Pamantasan ng Sto. Tomas. Directorcillo, Registrador de Titulos at hukom pamayapa ng Kawit; Pangulo, Sangguniang Magdalo ng KKK, Oktubre 1896; Kalihim ng Pananalapi, 1897; isa sa mga lumagda sa Konstitusyon ng Biyak-na-Bato, 1897; Kalihim Pandigma at Gawaing Bayan ng Unang Republika ng Pilipinas, 1898–1899; namumunong heneral sa Timog Luzon noong Digmaang Pilipino at Amerikano, 1899; at tagapagtatag at unang pangulo, Kapisanan ng mga Beterano ng Himagsikang Pilipino mula noong Oktubre 1912 hanggang sa kanyang kamatayan noong Pebrero 1915. Ang maybahay niya ay si Petrona Reyes ng Imus, Cavite at nagkaanak sila ng dalawa, si Leonor na naging asawa ni Dr. Enrique T. Virata at si Aurellano kay Liwanag Virata. Pinsang-buo ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo.</p>"},"photo":{"width":933,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Baldomero Aguinaldo House Marker 2.jpg","height":1206,"hash":"be"}}},"address":"Baldomero Aguinaldo Shrine, Bisita Street, Kawit, Cavite","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Hen. Baldomero Aguinaldo y Baloy","lat":14.44779,"macroAddress":"Kawit, Cavite","date":"1983-06-12","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Baldomero Aguinaldo":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.92351},"Q46993559":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Diosdado Macapagal":true},"lon":120.60037,"locPhoto":null,"address":"President Diosdado P. Macapagal Library and Museum, Lubao, Pampanga","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"AbDiosdado Macapagal.JPG","hash":"fb","height":4608},"text":{"title":"Ang Bahay na Sinilangan ni Pangulong Diosdado Macapagal","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na itong yari sa pawid at kawayan, ang panglimang naging pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas Diosdado Macapagal ay ipinanganak noong ika-28 ng Setyembre 1910. Pangalawa sa apat na anak nina Urbano Macapagal at Romana Pangan. Dito niya ginugol ang mga masasayang unang taon ng kanyang kabataan. Ang pagsasaayos na muli ng bahay na ito ay isinagawa sa pagtutulungan ng mga mamamayan ng Lubao, ng Pamahalaan at ng Kagawaran ng Edukasyon, Kultura at Isports (Rehiyon III).</p>"}}},"name":"Ang Bahay na Sinilangan ni Pangulong Diosdado Macapagal","region":"Central Luzon","date":"1990-02-20","macroAddress":"Lubao, Pampanga","lat":14.93935},"Q30130266":{"date":"2014-03-03","macroAddress":"Tokyo, Japan","lat":35.69686,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"Fujimi, Chiyoda-Ku, Tokyo","title":"Embahada ng Pilipinas","inscription":"<p>Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan sa bisa ng Resolusyon Blg. 1 ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 11 Marso 2013.</p>"},"photo":{"height":2549,"hash":"a6","file":"Embahada ng Pilipinas historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2715}}},"address":"The Kudan, Fujimi, Chiyoda-ku, Tokyo, Japan","name":"Embahada ng Pilipinas","region":"Overseas","locPhoto":{"hash":"37","height":3000,"width":4000,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"The Kudan main gate (3).jpg"},"lon":139.74881,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the exterior wall of the security building beside the main gate of the residence.","wikipedia":{"The Kudan":true}},"Q53087133":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the column to the left of the main door at the church portico.","wikipedia":{"Pateros Church":true},"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"43","credit":"Judgefloro","file":"3253San Roque Santa Marta de Pateros Church Metro Manila 47.jpg","width":3456},"lon":121.06707,"address":"Pateros Church, B. Morcilla Street, Pateros, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Agustino bilang visita ng Pasig, 1572. Naging visita ng Taguig, 1742. Naging parokya sa patronato ni San Roque, 1 Hunyo 1815. Ipinatayo nina Padre Andres Veil at Padre Manuel Pelaes ang simbahan yari sa bato ayon sa disenyo ni Padre Santos Gomez Marañon, 1815. Ipinagawa ni Padre Raymundo Martinez ang kampanang ipinangalan kay San Isidro, 1821. Nasira ng lindol, 1863. Ipinaayos ni Padre Nicolas Gonzales, 1892; ipinatapos ni Padre Tomas Espejo, 1893. Pansamantalang naging kuwartel heneral ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo ang kumbento, 1–2 Enero 1897. Nasira noong Labanan sa Pateros, 14 Marso 1899. Dito ikinulong ng mga Hapon ang mga Pilipinong dinakip sa Pateros, Agosto 1943. Maraming sibilyan ang pinaslang ng mga Hapon sa loob ng simbahan at sa paligid nito, Disyembre 1944.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Pateros"},"photo":{"hash":"6b","height":3678,"file":"Simbahan ng Pateros historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2500}}},"name":"Simbahan ng Pateros","region":"Metro Manila","date":"2015-08-15","macroAddress":"Pateros, Metro Manila","lat":14.54523},"Q44508069":{"lat":14.48099,"date":"1991","macroAddress":"Cavite City, Cavite","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Mababang Paaralang Manuel S. Rojas","address":"Manuel S. Rojas Elementary School, Dra. Salamanca Street, San Roque, Cavite City, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating Paaralang San Roque. Ipinatayo sa istilong Gabaldon na may limang dorikong kulumna noong 1911. Pinangalanang Mababang Paaralang Manuel S. Rojas, Agosto 11, 1972. Bilang parangal at pagkilala sa ama ng batas na nagtatadhana sa pagiging Lungsod ng Cavite o Batas Komonwelt bilang 546, Setyembre 7, 1940. Pinaayos, 1988.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Mababang Paaralang Manuel S. Rojas"},"photo":null}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.90131,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q38818766":{"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Nuestra Señora de Guia","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo noong 1606 na yari sa kawayan, mulawen, at pawid, ang simbahan ng Nuestra Señora de Guia ay makailang nawasak dahil sa lindol. Muling itinayo noong 1810 at nawasak noong 1945 sa Labanan ng Maynila. Ang imahen ng Nuestra Señora de Guia, na nasa Katedral ng Maynila mula pa noong pananakop ng mga Inggles (1762), ay inilipat dito noong 1918. Ang kasalukuyang simbahan ay itinayo noong 1947 sa may pook na di-umano’y kinatagpuan sa Birhen noong 19 Mayo 1571. Kinoronahan ang Birhen noong 16 Mayo 1971 ni Rufino Kardenal Santos. Ang gintong korona ay kaloob ng Papa Paulo VI.</p>","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Nuestra Señora de Guia","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Ang Simbahan ng Nuestra Señora de Guia historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2500,"height":3691,"hash":"09"}}},"address":"Ermita Church, M. H. del Pilar Street cor. A. Flores Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1971","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","lat":14.5788,"wikipedia":{"Ermita Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the facade to the left of the main entrance of the church.","lon":120.97981,"locPhoto":{"file":"Ermita Church historical marker location.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2352,"hash":"c5","height":1807}},"Q53678093":{"lon":121.06112,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Banaue Rice Terraces":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"1940","macroAddress":"Banaue, Ifugao","lat":16.91099,"name":"Ifugao Rice Terraces","region":"Cordillera Administrative Region","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Ifugao Rice Terraces","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The Ifugao Rice Terraces cover an area of nearly 400 square kilometers, and if the walls were placed end to end, they would reach more than half-way around the earth. Those of Banaue, Hapao, and Hungduan are among the oldest in Luzon. Archaeological and historical studies indicate that it took the Ifugaos more than 2,000 years to build them. The stone-walled terraces of Ifugao are the highest, best built, and most extensive in the world. </p><p> A single migrating people is believed to have carried the terrace culture from South China or Indo-China across to Luzon and southern Japan, and southward to Java and the lesser Sunda Islands — which are the only regions where true rice terraces exist. Remains indicate that the first migration was probably in the second millenium B.C., and carried only a material culture of polished stone, copper and bronze; but a second migration, in the latter part of the first millenium B.C., brought also the use of iron, pottery, and woven cloth. The Banaue people represent the oldest native folk; those of central Ifugao are the typical carriers of the terrace culture; and those of the Kiangan district are the latest comers into the region.</p>"}}},"address":"Municipal Tourism Center, Poblacion, Banaue, Ifugao"},"Q37153825":{"lon":120.5896,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":15.13532,"date":"1986","macroAddress":"Angeles","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Bahay ni Angel Pantaleon de Miranda","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Bahay ni Angel Pantaleon de Miranda","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayong yari sa bato at kahoy noong 1824 ni Don Angel Pantaleon de Miranda at kanyang maybahay, Doña Rosalia de Jesus, ang nagtatag ng Angeles (Dating Culiat), Pampanga noong 1796. Minana ng kanilang anak na si Doña Juana Miranda de Henson at pagkaraan ay tinirahan ng mga tagapagmana ni Don Jose P. Henson. Kasalukuyang tahanan ni Don Vicente N. Henson, Sr. Naging tuluyan din ng hukbong rebolusyonaryo ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo noong panahon ng Digmaaang Pilipino–Amerikano, 1899.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Angel Pantaleon de Miranda House, 770 Santo Rosario Street, Angeles"},"Q55072621":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98959,"name":"Asociacion Feminista Filipina","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Kauna-unahang samahang pangkababaihan sa Pilipinas na nagtaguyod sa pagpapalaganap ng kagalingang panlipunan at masugid na paglahok ng mga kababaihan sa kapakanang pambayan. Itinatag sa Maynila, 30 Hunyo 1905. Unang pangulo ng samahan si Concepcion Felix.</p>","subtitle":"(Samahang Feminista ng Pilipinas)","title":"Asociacion Feminista Filipina"},"photo":{"height":3456,"hash":"2b","credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Asociacion Feminista Filipina historical marker.jpg","width":4608}}},"address":"NFWC Building, 962 J. Escoda Street cor. San Marcelino Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"2005-09-21","lat":14.57829},"Q45181046":{"lon":120.97552,"locPhoto":{"width":3000,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Molino Dam historical marker location.jpg","height":4000,"hash":"83"},"wikipedia":{"Molino Dam":"Prinza Dam"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall facing the dam of the river station building on the Las Piñas end of the dam.","macroAddress":"Las Piñas, Metro Manila","date":"2017-12-01","lat":14.43859,"name":"Molino Dam","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinagawa ayon sa disenyo ni Fray Hilario Bernal, OAR upang patubigan ang mga bukirin sa Las Piñas at Bacoor. Isinaayos ni Fray Ezekiel Moreno, OAR upang lubos na matulungan ang mga magsasaka at lunasan ang tagtuyot na nararanasan sa lugar, 1885. Ganap na natapos, 1890. Nagsisilbing tulay sa pagitan ng Las Piñas at Bacoor, Cavite hanggang sa kasalukuyan.</p>","title":"Molino Dam","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":2500,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Molino Dam historical marker.jpg","hash":"85","height":3010}}},"address":"Molino Dam, Florlina dela Cruz Street, Las Piñas, Metro Manila"},"Q28868890":{"date":"1982-02-24","macroAddress":"Calamba, Laguna","lat":14.21397,"name":"Heneral Vicente Lim","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Calamba, Laguna noong Pebrero 24, 1888 kina Jose Lim at Antonia Podico. Kawal, makabayan, isa sa mga nagtatag ng Boy Scouts of the Philippines at unang Pilipinong nag-aral sa United States Military Academy sa West Point, New York. Ikinasal kay Pilar Hidalgo, kilalang edukador at mapagkawanggawa.</p><p>Namumunong heneral, Ika-41 Dibisyon ng Impanteriya noong 1941; nakaligtas sa <u>Death March</u>; nagtatag ng pangkat ng gerilya noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig; nabihag ng patrulyang Hapones sa baybayin ng Mindoro; ibinilanggo sa Kutang Santiago at pagkaraan ay binaril sa Sementeryo ng Intsik noong 1944. </p><p>Pagkaraang mamatay, pinagkalooban ng mga medalyang <u>Distinguished Conduct Star</u>, <u>Distinguished Service Star</u> at <u>Distinguished Long Service Star</u> at ginawaran ng ranggong heneral na may tatlong bituin. Bilang parangal, ang himpilan ng Konstabularya ng Pilipinas sa Canlubang, Laguna ay ipinangalan sa kanya.</p>","subtitle":"(1888–1944)","title":"Heneral Vicente Lim"}}},"address":"M. H. del Pilar Street, Calamba, Laguna","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.16542,"wikipedia":{"Vicente Lim":true},"locDesc":null},"Q24841847":{"name":"Simbahan ng Tanauan","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Tanauan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ang pangangasiwang pansimbahan ng bayan ay tinanggap ng Agustino noong Mayo 5, 1584. Si P. Antonio Roxas ang naging unang kura paroko. Natapos ang unang simbahan na yari sa kahoy at nasa may lawa ng Bombon bago ang taong 1690. Ipinatayo ang simbahang bato, 1732. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang kinalalagyan nito nang ang buong bayan ay lumubog bunga ng pagsabog ng Bulkang Taal, 1754. Muling ipinagawa ni P. Jose Diaz, 1881, ganap na nasira, 1944. Muling ipinagawa ni Monsignor Mariño, 1948.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Tanauan Church.jpg","credit":"Kevin Michael Aguinaldo {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2336,"height":3610,"hash":"c1"}}},"address":"Tanauan Church, Tanauan, Batangas","date":"1991-01-21","macroAddress":"Tanauan, Batangas","lat":14.086,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.15331},"Q23821323":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Liliw Church":"Saint John the Baptist Parish Church (Liliw)"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.43578,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Liliw Church historical marker.jpg","hash":"11","height":4608},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Lilio","inscription":"<p>The ecclesiastical administration of this town belonged to Nagcarlang up to 1605. The Church and the Convent of Lilio were seriously damaged by the earthquakes of 1880. The reconstructed Church and the Convent were partially burned on April 6, 1898.</p>"}}},"address":"Liliw Church, Liliw, Laguna","name":"Church of Lilio","region":"Calabarzon","date":"1939","macroAddress":"Liliw, Laguna","lat":14.13005},"Q43375893":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.01535,"wikipedia":{"Philippine–American War":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":14.60407,"macroAddress":"Santa Mesa, Manila","date":true,"region":"Metro Manila","name":"First Shot in Filipino–American War","address":"Silencio Street cor. Sociego Street, Santa Mesa, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"First Shot in Filipino–American War","inscription":"<p>Here, at 9:00 o’clock in the evening of February 4th, 1899, Private William Grayson of the First Nebraska Volunteers fired the shot that started the Filipino–American War.</p>"},"photo":{"width":640,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"First Shot in Filipino-American War Marker.jpg","height":480,"hash":"87"},"date":"1941"},"tl":{"date":"2004","photo":{"height":400,"hash":"f2","width":392,"file":"Unang Putok sa Digmaang Filipino-Amerikano Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito noong ganap na 9:00 sa gabi ng 4 Pebrero 1899 nagpaputok si Private William Grayson ng First Nebraska Volunteers, putok na nagpasiklab sa Digmaang Filipino–Amerikano.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Unang Putok sa Digmaang Filipino–Amerikano"}}}},"Q23665949":{"lon":123.90494,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Andres Bonifacio":"Andrés Bonifacio"},"locDesc":null,"lat":10.29236,"date":"2013-12-03","macroAddress":"Cebu City","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Andres Bonifacio","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Andres Bonifacio Cebu City historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":1947,"height":2808,"hash":"8c"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Bayani at rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Tondo, Maynila, 30 Nobyembre 1863. Sumapi sa Masoneriya at La Liga Filipina, 1892. Nagtatag ng Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan o Katipunan, isang lihim na kilusan na ang pangunahing adhikain ay mapagkaisa ang lahat ng mga Pilipino at itaguyod ang isang bayang malaya sa pamamagitan ng paghihimagsik, 7 Hulyo 1892. Pinamunuan ang pagsisimula ng malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa mga Espanyol, Agosto 1896. Sumalakay sa San Juan del Monte upang kubkubin ang Polvorin, 30 Agosto 1896. Pinatay sa Maragondon, Cavite, 10 Mayo 1897[.] Kinikilala bilang Supremo ng Katipunan at Ama ng Himagsikan.</p>","title":"Andres Bonifacio","subtitle":"(30 Nobyembre 1863 – 10 Mayo 1897)"}}},"address":"Plaza Independencia, Mariano Jesus Cuenco Avenue, Cebu City"},"Q52145135":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng Pagbilao","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang parokya ng mga Pransiskano sa simbahan noong 1685. Itinayo ang kapilyang yari sa kawayan at kogon, 1688, at naging ministro si Padre Cristobal Mortanchez. Inilipat ang simbahan sa kasalukuyang tayo ng bayan sa pamamatnubay ng Patrona Sta. Catalina de Alexandria, 1730, at naging kura paroko si Padre Francisco Xavier de Toledo. Itinayo ang simbahang bato sa pamamahala ni Padre Victorino Peralija, 1846; at natapos, kasama ang kumbento at tore, 1877, sa pamamahala ni Padre Eugenio Gomez. Nawasak noong Liberasyon, 1945, at muling ipinaayos sa pangangasiwa ni Padre Vicente Urlanda noong 1954.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Pagbilao","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Pagbilao Church, Pan-Philippine Highway cor. General Lucban Street, Pagbilao, Quezon","lat":13.97203,"macroAddress":"Pagbilao, Quezon","date":"1986-07-04","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.68667},"Q31770524":{"date":"1955","macroAddress":"Danao, Bohol","lat":9.95945,"name":"In Memory of Francisco Dagohoy","region":"Central Visayas","address":"Dagohoy Monument, Danao, Bohol","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"In Memory of Francisco Dagohoy","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Filipino patriot, who established an independent government for the island of Bohol during the long and successful rebellion, 1744–1829, on this site, between Inabangan and Talibon.</p>"},"photo":{"height":1083,"hash":"d3","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Dagohoy Monument marker.jpg","width":872}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.18406,"wikipedia":{"Francisco Dagohoy":true},"locDesc":null},"Q55723617":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Castillejos":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.2001,"address":"Castillejos Municipal Hall, Olongapo–Bugallon Road, Castillejos, Zambales","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Castillejos","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Originally the Pueblo de Uguic created in 1743. Present name adopted in 1863 in honor of the Marqués de Castillejos who distinguished himself in the battle of the valley of Castillejos in Spanish Morocco, Africa. A contingent of Castillejos residents joined the Revolutionary forces in capturing the Spanish troops in Zambales in 1896. The guerillas under the command of Ramon Magsaysay dislodged the Japanese soldiers garrisoned at the Castillejos Airstrip on 26 January 1945, in preparation for the liberation of the town four days later.</p>"}}},"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Castillejos","lat":14.9321,"date":"1955","macroAddress":"Castillejos, Zambales"},"Q28942441":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Muhammad Kudarat":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.24599,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Sultan Dipatuan Kudarat","subtitle":"c. 1590–1671","inscription":"<p>Ikapitong Sultan ng Maguindanao. Kilala sa mga tala ng Espanyol bilang Corralat. Namuno mula 1619 hanggang 1671. Pinagbuklod ang mga pinunong Muslim at nakipagkaisa sa Sultanato ng Sulu. Lumaban sa mga Espanyol, 1635–1645. Naging tanging pinuno ng malawak na bahagi ng Mindanao kabilang ang Davao, Cotabato at Zamboanga. Nilagdaan ang kasunduang pangkapayapaan na nagbunga ng ilang taong katiwasayan sa Mindanao, 1645. Kinilala na walang takot na tagapagtanggol ng pananampalatayang Islam at umuusbong na kalayaan ng Pilipinas. Namatay, 1671.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"92","height":699,"width":535,"file":"Sultan Kudarat historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"address":"Tantawan Park, Sinsuat Avenue, Cotabato City","name":"Sultan Dipatuan Kudarat","region":"Soccsksargen","macroAddress":"Cotabato City","date":"2004-12-19","lat":7.22146},"Q47087017":{"lat":14.13142,"macroAddress":"Nagcarlan, Laguna","date":"1981-10-24","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Sementeryo sa Ilalim ng Lupa ng Nagcarlan","inscription":"<p>Ang naiiba at nag-iisang sementeryong ito sa Pilipinas ay itinayo ng mga misyonerong Pransiskano sa pangangasiwa ni Padre Vicente Velloc noong 1845, kasabay ng pagtatayong-muli ng pinalaking Simbahan ni San Bartolome at pagtatayo ng kumbento.</p><p>Dito nagpulong nang palihim ang mga pinuno ng Himagsikan sa Laguna noong 1896. </p><p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973, na sinusugan ng Kautusan Bilang 1505, Hunyo 11, 1978. Ang sementeryong ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"77","height":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Nagcarlan Underground Cemetery historical marker.jpg","width":3456}}},"address":"Nagcarlan Underground Cemetery, Nagcarlan–Rizal Road, Nagcarlan, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Sementeryo sa Ilalim ng Lupa ng Nagcarlan","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.41519,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Nagcarlan Underground Cemetery":true}},"Q45058955":{"lon":123.41629,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":8.63917,"date":"2017-07-13","macroAddress":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","name":"Dr. Jose Rizal Memorial Hospital","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Batas Blg. 2663 na ipinasa noong 19 Hunyo 1916, itinatag ang Rizal Memorial Hospital sa Casa Comandancia. Dito nanirahan si Jose Rizal nang siya ay ipatapon sa Dapitan noong 1892. Isinaayos, 1927–1931. Naging ospital ng mga sundalo noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Naging Rizal Memorial District Hospital, 1982. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan nito, 1991. Naging Dr. Jose Rizal Memorial Hospital, 30 Hulyo 1996.</p>","title":"Dr. Jose Rizal Memorial Hospital","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Dr. Jose Rizal Memorial Hospital, National Road, Lawaan, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte"},"Q46519998":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.71245,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Daraga Church":true},"date":"2008-10-16","macroAddress":"Daraga, Albay","lat":13.15,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng mga paring Pransiskano na yari sa bato, 1773. Dito lumipat ang mga mananampalataya ng Cagsawa matapos masira ang kanilang simbahan sa pagsabog ng Mayon, 1814. Inialay sa patronato ni Nuestra Señora de la Porteria, 1854. Ginamit na himpilan ng mga Hapones at nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1945. Muling ipinaayos, 1971–1973. Halimbawa ng istilong Baroque ayon sa kahusayan ng mga manggagawang Filipino noong panahon ng mga Espanyol.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Daraga"},"photo":{"height":6016,"hash":"fc","file":"Historical Marker at the Simbahan ng Daraga.JPG","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4000}}},"address":"Daraga Church, Santa Maria Street, Daraga, Albay","name":"Simbahan ng Daraga","region":"Bicol Region"},"Q54806821":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.44845,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"07","height":2696,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Isabelo Abaya historical marker.jpg","width":1901},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Lider rebolusyonaryo at martir ng Digmaang Pilipino–Amerikano. Isinilang sa Candon, Ilocos Sur, Enero 1866, tagapagtatag ng Katipunan sa Candon na tinaguriang Estrella del Sur kasama si Fernando Guirnalda, Enero 1898. Namuno sa pag-aalsa sa Candon at itinatag ang Republic Filipina Katipunan sa Kumbento ng Candon, 25 Marso 1898. Namuhay kasama ng mga Igorot matapos mabawi ng Hukbong Espanyol ang Candon, 27 Marso 1898. Muling sumama sa Hukbong Rebolusyonaryo, 15 Agosto 1898. Nag-organisa at nanguna sa puwersang Igorot na dumalo sa inagurasyon ng Republic Filipina sa Malolos, Bulacan, 23 Enero 1899, at lumaban sa mga Amerikano sa Caloocan, 5 Pebrero 1899. Komandante, Katimugang Hukbo ng Ilocos, 1899–1900. Hinuli at pinatay ng mga Amerikano matapos ang Labanan sa Pasoñgan (bahagi ng Galimuyod, Ilocos Sur), at inilantad sa publiko ang bangkay sa Plaza ng Candon, 3 Mayo 1900.</p>","subtitle":"1866–1900","title":"Isabelo Abaya"}}},"address":"Candon City Plaza, Candon, Ilocos Sur","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Isabelo Abaya","lat":17.19303,"date":"2016-03-29","macroAddress":"Candon, Ilocos Sur"},"Q46880345":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":122.69477,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Guho ng Kapilya ng Ermita","inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayo ang kapilya yari sa nipa nang gawing sentro ng pagmimisyon sa Panay ang Araut (ngayo’y Dumangas) ni Padre Juan de Alva, O.S.A., 1569. Ipinatayo ang simbahan at kumbento na yari sa bato sa patronato ni San Agustin, 1572. Nasunog, 1628. Muling ipinatayo ngunit nasira ng lindol, 1787. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 28 Agosto 1989.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Ermita Chapel, Dumangas, Iloilo","name":"Guho ng Kapilya ng Ermita","region":"Western Visayas","date":"2014-03-13","macroAddress":"Dumangas, Iloilo","lat":10.817},"Q54087651":{"wikipedia":{"Jose P. Laurel Residence":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.04529,"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Jose P. Laurel residence","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Raani Paranas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jose P. Laurel residence in Mandaluyong historical marker.jpg","width":2252,"hash":"a7","height":3002},"text":{"title":null,"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This building was erected in the year 1957 as a residence for Jose P. Laurel, President of the Second Philippine Republic, who was born in Tanauan, Batangas on March 9, 1891, and died in Mandaluyong, Rizal, on November 6, 1959, after a lifetime of dedicated service to his country.</p>"}}},"address":"515 Shaw Boulevard cor. S. Laurel Street, Mandaluyong, Metro Manila","lat":14.58832,"date":"1965","macroAddress":"Mandaluyong, Metro Manila"},"Q23677500":{"macroAddress":"Cebu City","date":"1941","lat":10.29354,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"The Cross of Magellan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>From time immemorial this spot has been set aside to commemorate the erection of a Cross in Cebu by the expedition of Magellan, when King Humabon of Cebu and his Queen, son and daughters, together with some 800 of their subjects were baptized by Father Pedro Valderrama. This hallowed site was improved in 1735 by Rev. Juan Albarran, Prior of San Agustin and in 1834 by Rt. Rev. Santos Gomez Marañon, Bishop of Cebu. The image of the Santo Niño found by the expedition of Legaspi in a house near the present site of the Cathedral of Cebu is venerated by the faithful in the nearby Church of San Agustin.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2112,"credit":"Photo: Josh Lim (Sky Harbor); perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","file":"20170812160609!Magellan's Cross historical marker.jpg","height":2130,"hash":"a5"}}},"address":"Magellan's Cross, Cebu City","name":"The Cross of Magellan","region":"Central Visayas","locPhoto":{"credit":"Kingphoto23 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Magellan's Cross Cebu.jpg","width":864,"height":576,"hash":"05"},"lon":123.90193,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located above the southern entrance of the building housing the cross.","wikipedia":{"Magellan's Cross":true}},"Q41735715":{"name":"Lunsod ng San Carlos","region":"Ilocos Region","address":"Malong Street, San Carlos, Pangasinan","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"SaintDominicdeGuzmanParishChurchjf278.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"8b"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating Binalatogan, ang unang bayan ng Pangasinan na itinatag ng mga paring Dominikano sa Abagbagan noong 1587. Dito itinatag ang unang misyon ng mga Dominikano sa lalawigan at ginanap ang unang pagdiriwang ng kapitulo probinsiyal ng Orden ng mga Dominikano noong 1617. Naging sentro ng pag-aalsa nina Andres Malong, 1660–1661; Juan Caragay, 1718–1719; at ng paghihimagsik ni Juan dela Cruz Palaris, 1762–1764. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang pook at pinanganlang San Carlos ayon sa atas ng Hari ng Espanya matapos ang paghihimagsik ni Palaris noong 1764. Ipinatayo ang casa tribunal, 1820. Naging lungsod sa bisa ng Batas Republika Bilang 4487, Hunyo 17, 1965.</p>","title":"Lunsod ng San Carlos","subtitle":null}}},"date":"1988","macroAddress":"San Carlos, Pangasinan","lat":15.92568,"wikipedia":{"San Carlos":"San Carlos, Pangasinan"},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.34734,"locPhoto":null},"Q37309666":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.90312,"wikipedia":{"Andres Bonifacio":"Andrés Bonifacio"},"locDesc":null,"date":"1963","macroAddress":"Indang, Cavite","lat":14.20002,"name":"Ang Pagdakip kay Bonifacio","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ng Limbon, Indang, nagsagupa ang mga pangkat ni Andres Bonifacio at ng Pamahalaan noong ika-28 ng Abril 1897. Ipinadakip ng Pangulong Aguinaldo si Bonifacio dahil sa himaton ni Pio del Pilar na nagbabangon ng ibang pamahalaang mapanghimagsik ang Supremo. Sa sagupaan ay napatay si Ciriaco at nasugatan si Andres.</p>","title":"Ang Pagdakip kay Bonifacio","subtitle":"(1897)"},"photo":null}},"address":"Bonifacio Shrine, Pangil Road, Indang, Cavite"},"Q43247430":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Emiliano Riego de Dios","address":"Col. E. Riego de Dios Street, Maragondon, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Maragondon, Kabite, noong Setyembre 7, 1864 sa mag-asawang Sotero Riego de Dios at Jorga Loyola. Naging Katipunero noong 1896 at nakilaban na kasama ang mga kapatid na sina Koronel Vicente (1868–1936) at Heneral Mariano (1875–1935). Nahalal na Ministrong Pandigma sa Kumbensiyon ng Teheros, Marso 22, 1897; gobernador militar ng Kabite, 1898; at pangalawang tagapangulo ng Hunta ng Hongkong, Nobyembre, 1898. </p><p>Namatay noong Pebrero 14, 1926.</p>","title":"Emiliano Riego de Dios","subtitle":"(1864–1926)"},"photo":null}},"lat":14.27283,"date":"1975","macroAddress":"Maragondon, Cavite","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":120.73695,"locPhoto":null},"Q52773904":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Corregidor","address":"Gen. Jonathan M. Wainright Memorial Park, Bottomside, Corregidor, Cavite City, Cavite","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Derived its name from Corregimiento or municipal district. About 1225 the island became a stronghold for Chinese pirates until the latter were driven by the Moros. Became Spanish possession, 1570, when Spaniards arrived in Manila from Panay. Occupied by the Dutch, 1600. Recaptured by the Spaniards as a fortification besides being used as lighthouse, dockyard, naval convalescent hospital, penal colony, and checking point for ships to have their papers corrected. Surrendered without resistance to Admiral Dewey, May 6, 1898. First occupied by the Americans as a convalescent hospital, November 14, 1904, and first garrison, the 35th Company, C.A.C., commanded by Captain C.E. Kilbourne, arrived, May 8, 1908. Became the seat of the government of the Commonwealth of the Philippines during World War II and the scene of President Quezon’s taking oath of office on his second term. President Quezon and his family sought shelter at Malinta Tunnel, December 24, 1941. Occupied by the Japanese, May 6, 1942; retaken by the Americans, March 2, 1945. Turned over to the Republic of the Philippines, October 12, 1947.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Corregidor"},"photo":null}},"lat":14.38635,"macroAddress":"Cavite City, Cavite","date":"1949","wikipedia":{"Corregidor":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.58853,"locPhoto":null},"Q53997707":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of the statue of José Ignacio Paua.","wikipedia":{"José Ignacio Paua":true},"lon":120.97569,"locPhoto":{"hash":"e3","height":4272,"file":"General Jose Ignacio Paua.JPG","credit":"Joy Merced {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2848},"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"80","width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Jose Ignacio Paua historical marker in Silang, Cavite.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa nayon ng Laona, Lamwua, Fookien, Tsina, Abril 29, 1872. Dumating sa Pilipinas, 1890. Umanib sa Himagsikang Pilipino. Inatasan ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo sa pamamahala’t pagtatag ng isang arsenal at pagawaan ng armas sa Imus. Buong giting na nakipaglaban sa iba’t ibang labanan sa Cavite, Bulacan, Pampanga, Pangasinan at Tarlac. Tanging Tsino na lumagda sa Konstitusyon ng Biyak-na-Bato, 1897. Itinalagang mangingilak ng pondo sa Kabikolan noong Labanang Filipino–Amerikano. Sumuko, Marso 24, 1900. Nakulong sa Kutang Santiago; pinalaya, Hunyo 21, 1900. Bumalik sa Manito, Albay, kung saan siya nahalal na presidente municipal. Namatay, Mayo, 24, 1896.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Heneral Jose Ignacio Paua"}}},"address":"Aguinaldo Highway cor. J.P. Rizal Street, Silang, Cavite","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Heneral Jose Ignacio Paua","lat":14.24416,"macroAddress":"Silang, Cavite","date":"1991"},"Q29018590":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Maasin Cathedral":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.83816,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Maasin Church historical marker.jpg","width":560,"height":796,"hash":"ea"},"text":{"title":"Katedral ng Maasin","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ang pook na ito ay itinatag ng mga misyonerong Heswita noong 1700. Isang pansamantalang simbahan ang ipinatayo subalit ito ay nasira nang sumalakay ang mga Moro noong 1754. Ang Maasin ay naging bayan nang sumunod na taon. Noong 1768 ang pangasiwaan ng simbahan ay inilipat sa mga paring Agustino. Ang simbahan ay muling ipinatayo noong 1771 subalit muling sinira ng mga Moro noong 1784. Sa pangangasiwa ni Padre Serapio Gonzales isang simbahang bato ang itinayo. Ito ay muling nagiba. Noong 1839 si Padre Jose Paco ay nagpatayo ng bagong simbahan na nasunog noong 1882. Muling ipinagawa. Ito ay naging katedral nang maging sede ng bagong Diyosesis ang Maasin noong Agosto 14, 1968. Patrona nito ang Nuestra Señora de la Asuncion.</p>"}}},"address":"Maasin Cathedral, Iglesia Street cor. Rosales Street, Maasin, Southern Leyte","region":"Eastern Visayas","name":"Katedral ng Maasin","lat":10.13255,"macroAddress":"Maasin, Southern Leyte","date":"1983"},"Q55327054":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.62042,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Lucena","date":null,"lat":13.94947,"name":"Manuel S. Enverga","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Makabayan at lingkod-bayan. Isinilang sa Mauban, Quezon, 1 Enero 1909. Nagtapos ng Abogasya sa Philippine Law School, 1938. Master of Laws sa Universidad ng Sto. Tomas, 1948. Ginawaran ng Doctor of Laws ng Universidad Central de Madrid, 1950. Nagtatag ng Luzonian Colleges, ngayo’y Manuel S. Enverga University Foundation, 11 Pebrero 1947. Nahalal na kinatawan ng unang distrito ng Quezon, 1953–1969. Nagpanukala ng pagtatatag ng Philippine Coconut administration, 1954. Naging tagapangulo ng House Committee on Education, 1958–1961, House Committee on Foreign Affairs, 1961–1969. Napiling Outstanding Congressman ng mga pahayagan sa Pilipinas bilang pangunahing tagapagmungkahi ng panukalang-batas para sa pagbubukas ng kalakalan sa pagitan ng Pilipinas at ng mga bansang komunista, 1966. Yumao, 14 Hunyo 1981.</p>","subtitle":"(1909–1981)","title":"Manuel S. Enverga"}}},"address":"Enverga University, Enverga Boulevard, Brgy. Ibabang Dupay, Lucena"},"Q25080039":{"wikipedia":{"Casa Hacienda de Naic":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the main entrance of the building.","lon":120.76354,"locPhoto":{"file":"NaicChurchjf9481 10.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608,"hash":"75","height":3456},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Casa Hacienda de Naic","address":"Casa Hacienda de Naic, Naic, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3566,"hash":"cb","width":2500,"file":"Casa Hacienda de Naic historical marker (corrected).jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa mismong gusaling ito, ngayo'y Mababang Paaralan ng Naic, isinagawa at isinakatuparan noong Abril 19, 1897 ang Acta de Naic o Naic Military Agreement, isang kasunduan nina Bonifacio at ng kanyang mga kapanalig na salungat sa mga panuntunan na pinagkasunduan ng mga manghihimagsik sa Kumbensiyon ng Tejeros, na ginanap noong Marso 22, 1897.<br />Dito rin binuo ni Pangulong Emilio Aguinaldo, makaraan ang mahal na araw nang taon ding yaon ang kanyang 'Cabinet of Reconciliation,\" o ang pagsasaayos ng gabinete ng kanyang pamahalaan na hindi nabuo sa Kumbensiyon ng Tejeros.</p>","title":"Casa Hacienda de Naic","subtitle":null}}},"lat":14.32046,"date":"1998","macroAddress":"Naic, Cavite"},"Q53625913":{"region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Labanan sa Pasong Balete","address":"Dalton Pass, Brgy. Tactac, Santa Fe, Nueva Vizcaya","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Battle of Balete Pass historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"91"},"text":{"title":"Labanan sa Pasong Balete","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Pinangyarihan ng labanan sa pagitan ng mga Amerikano at mga Hapon upang makontrol ang Cagayan Valley, 21 Pebrero hanggang Mayo 1945. Sinalakay ng magkakasamang puwersa ng ika-25 Dibisyon ng Estados Unidos, mga gerilyang Pilipino na kasapi ng Luzon Guerilla Forces (LGAF) sa ilalim ni Kolonel Robert Lapham, at mga Tsino, at naitaboy ang pangkay ng Shobu ng mga Hapon na pinamunuan ni Heneral Tomoyuki Yamashita. Umurong ang nalalabing Hukbong Hapon sa Pasong Balete at nagtungo sa Gitnang Cordillera. Dumating ang unang patrulya ng mga Amerikano sa Pasong Balete, 9 Mayo 1945. Idineklarang bukas sa Allied Forces, 13 Mayo 1945. Pinanganlang Pasong Dalton bilang parangal kay Brigadyer Heneral James L. Dalton II na napatay ng isang sniper noong 16 Mayo 1945 habang nagsasagawa ng ibayong pagsisiyasat sa Pasong Balete makaraan ang labanan.</p>"}}},"lat":16.13325,"macroAddress":"Santa Fe, Nueva Vizcaya","date":"2005-05-13","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting at the center of the view deck entry way.","lon":120.92999,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Battle of Balete Pass view deck entry way with the historical marker.jpg","height":3456,"hash":"ef"}},"Q53754382":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade on the buttress immediately to the left of the nave entrance.","wikipedia":{"Mahatao Church":"San Carlos Borromeo Church (Mahatao)"},"lon":121.94716,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"file":"Mahatao Church 08.JPG","credit":"KisekiLacroix {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"1c","height":2592},"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo sa ilalim ng patronahe ni San Carlos Borromeo, 1787. Nasira ng bagyo, 1872. Muling itinayo ni P. Cresencio Polo, O.P., 1873. Itinaas ng mga Katipunero ang bandila ng Katipunan sa kampanaryo, 19 Setyembre 1898. Pinalitan ng bubong na yero, ika-20 siglo. Tinanggal ang koro, noong mga taong 1990. Ipinahayag ng Pambansang Museo bilang Yamang Pangkalinangan, 31 Hulyo 2001.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Mahatao","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":2592,"hash":"69","credit":"KisekiLacroix {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Mahatao Church historical marker.jpg","width":4608}}},"address":"National Road, Mahatao, Batanes","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Simbahan ng Mahatao","lat":20.41565,"macroAddress":"Mahatao, Batanes","date":"2000"},"Q55229998":{"date":"2011","macroAddress":"Taytay, Rizal","lat":14.57224,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Jose Rizal historical marker at Taytay Elementary School, Rizal.jpg","credit":"Roel Balingit {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3120,"height":4160,"hash":"7f"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pambansang Bayani ng Pilipinas. Doktor, agrimensor, dalubwika, manunulat, makata, eskultor at pintor. Isinilang sa Calamba, Laguna, 19 Hunyo 1861. May-akda ng Noli me Tangere (1887) at El Filibusterismo (1891), mga nobelang higit pang nagpaalab sa mga Filipino na maghimagsik laban sa Espanya. Dinakip at ipinatapon sa Dapitan, Hilagang Mindanao, 6 Hulyo 1892. Nagboluntaryo bilang manggagamot ng puwersang Espanyol sa Cuba, 1896, nguni’t muling dinakip habang patungong Espanya sa bintang rebelyon. Binaril sa Bagumbayan (ngayo’y Liwasang Rizal), Maynila, 30 Disyembre 1896. Patuloy na inspirasyon para sa kalayaan at pagkabansang Filipino.</p>","subtitle":"(1861–1896)","title":"Jose Rizal"}}},"address":"Taytay Elementary School, L. Wood Street, Taytay, Rizal","name":"Jose Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","lon":121.13722,"locPhoto":{"file":"Jose Rizal monument at Taytay Elementary School.jpg","credit":"Roel Balingit {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3120,"hash":"66","height":4160},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the monument pedestal inside the campus.","wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true}},"Q54942036":{"lon":120.69747,"locPhoto":{"height":768,"hash":"92","width":1024,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Purugganan Ancestral House.jpg"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the house facade on Puruganan Street near the street corner.","wikipedia":null,"macroAddress":"Dingras, Ilocos Norte","date":null,"lat":18.10417,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"83","height":4608,"file":"PurugananHouse2.jpg","credit":"Eric Jam {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3456},"text":{"title":"Tahanan ng Angkang Puruganan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo nina Don Cirilo Peralta Puruganan at kanyang maybahay, Doña Ynocencia Peralta Parado. Ginamit na gusali ng pamahalaang bayan noong panahon ng Kastila at pagkaraan bahay-tagpuan ng mga pinunong manghihimagsik, kabilang sina Gregorio Puruganan at Gregorio Aglipay, na nadakip dito ng Hukbo ng Estados Unidos noong 1899. Magkakasunod ding ginamit ng Hukbong Imperyal ng Hapones at ng pangkat ng tagapagtanggol Pilipino–Amerikano at, pagkatapos ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, ng mga pinuno ng ika-13 Hukbong Panghimpapawid ng Estados Unidos. Pinangalagaan ng apo ng Don Emilio Puruganan at kanyang maybahay, Doña Maria Rivera Puruganan, at ngayo’y pag-aari ng apo sa tuhod, Gregorio Rivera Puruganan, dating Floor Lider at Kinatawan ng Konstitusyonal Konbensyon ng 1971.</p>"}}},"address":"Medina Street cor. Puruganan Street, Brgy. Madamba, Dingras, Ilocos Norte","name":"Tahanan ng Angkang Puruganan","region":"Ilocos Region"},"Q34125673":{"wikipedia":{"Felix Manalo":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":121.07949,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Pook na Sinilangan ni Felix Y. Manalo","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"5c","height":956,"width":692,"file":"Felix Y. Manalo birthplace historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito sa Bo. Calsada, Tipas, Rizal isinilang si Felix Y Manalo, 10 Mayo 1886. Nagtatag at unang tagapamahalang pangkalahatan ng mga kongregasyon ng Iglesia ni Cristo sa Pilipinas. Unang ipinangaral ang Iglesia ni Cristo sa Punta, Sta. Ana, Maynila, at opisyal na ipinarehistro bilang isang samahang pangrelihiyon, 27 Hulyo 1914. Naglathala ng babasahing Pasugo na naglalaman ng mga doktrina ng Iglesia ni Cristo na hango sa Bibliya, 1939. Nagtayo ng mga simbahan ng Iglesia ni Cristo sa iba’t ibang panig ng Pilipinas at buong mundo. Yumao, 12 Abril 1963. Ipinahayag ang pook na kanyang sinilangan bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, Enero 1986.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Pook na Sinilangan ni Felix Y. Manalo"}}},"address":"Felix Y. Manalo National Historical Landmark, Felix Y. Manalo Street, Calzada<nobr>–<nobr>Tipas, Taguig, Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Taguig, Metro Manila","date":"2007-07-27","lat":14.53353},"Q56055118":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.85474,"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Pardo","address":"Pardo Church, Cebu South Road, Pardo, Cebu City","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Pardo","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang parokya ng Diyosesis ng Cebu sa patronato ni Santo Tomas de Villanueva at ipinatayo ang unang simbahan yari sa tabique at nipa sa panahon ni Padre Domingo Sanchez, 1866. Napinsala ng lindol, 1877. Ipinatayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan yari sa bato ayon sa disenyo ni Domingo de Escondrillas sa panahon ni Padre Manuel Ibeas, 1880–1893. Muling ipinaayos ni Padre Venerando Reynes, 1912. Napinsala ng lindol ang bahagi, 2013; inayos, 2015–2016.</p>"},"photo":null}},"lat":10.2794,"date":"2016-07-11","macroAddress":"Cebu City"},"Q25160366":{"lat":10.70183,"date":"2010","macroAddress":"Iloilo City","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Old Capitol Building of Iloilo","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating Casa Real na yari sa kahoy at bato noong panahon ng mga Espanyol. Naging kapitolyo nang itinatag ang Pamahalaang Sibil ng lalawigan ng Iloilo, 11 Abril 1901. Martin T. Delgado, Rebolusyonaryo, Unang Gobernador, 1901-1904. Ginamit ng mga pwersang Hapones noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1942-1945. Isinaayos ang ilang bahagi ng gusali, mga taong 1960's. Muling ipinaayos matapos masunog ang gusali, 4 Nobyembre 1998. Naging sentro sa pagtataguyod ng lalawigan ng Iloilo, 1901-2001.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Old Capitol Building of Iloilo"},"photo":{"hash":"74","height":1600,"width":1160,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Old Capitol Building of Iloilo historical marker.jpg"}}},"address":"Old Capitol Building of Iloilo, City Proper, Iloilo City","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.569,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q28928492":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Taluksangay Mosque","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Unang Mosque sa Peninsula ng Zamboanga na ipinatayo ni Hadji Abdullah Maas Nuno noong mga taong 1885. Ito ang unang sentrong Islam na kinilala ng ibang bansa tulad ng Turkey, Saudi Arabia, India, Malaysia, Indonesia at Borneo. Itinuturo dito ang mga tuntunin, kautusan at hurisprudensiya ng Islam na nagbunga ng mabilis na paglaganap ng Islam sa Peninsula ng Zamboanga, Basilan at kapuluan ng Sulu.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Taluksangay Mosque, Brgy. Taluksangay, Zamboanga City","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","name":"Taluksangay Mosque","lat":6.95075,"macroAddress":"Zamboanga City","date":"1992","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Taluksangay Mosque":true},"lon":122.18137,"locPhoto":null},"Q55317924":{"lat":10.31668,"date":"2008","macroAddress":"Cebu City","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Kapitolyo ng Cebu","address":"Cebu Provincial Capitol, Osmeña Boulevard cor. N. Escario Street, Cebu City","details":{"ceb":{"text":{"title":"Kapitolyo sa Sugbo","subtitle":null,"inscription":""},"photo":null},"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Kapitolyo ng Cebu","inscription":"<p>Unang itinayo sa harapan ng kasalukuyang Plaza Independencia. Sinakop ng mga Pilipinong rebolusyonaryo, 1898, at ng mga Amerikanong militar, 1899. Sinimulang ipatayo ang kasalukuyang gusali ng pamahalaang panlalawigan ayon sa disenyo ni Arkitekto Juan Arellano, Disyembre 1936. Pinasinayaan ni Pangulong Manuel Quezon, 14 Hunyo 1938. Natatanging halimbawa ng gusaling pampamahalaan at arkitektura ng unang bahagi ng ikadalawampung dantaon. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 9 Hulyo 2008.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":{"height":564,"hash":"af","file":"Cebu Provincial Capitol entrance facade.jpg","credit":"Ara Mae Nacario {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1647},"lon":123.89073,"wikipedia":{"Cebu Provincial Capitol":true},"locDesc":"The historical markers are located on the facade on both sides of the center doorway with the Cebuano marker to the left and the Tagalog marker to the right."},"Q28877396":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Replica of the house constructed in Talisay by Rizal. He lived here from March 1893 to 31 July 1896 while in exile at Dapitan.</p>","title":"Jose Rizal","subtitle":"1861–1896 National Hero of the Philippines"},"photo":{"width":2848,"file":"Jose Rizal historical marker in Rizal Shrine Dapitan.jpg","credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":4288,"hash":"41"}}},"address":"Jose Rizal Memorial Protected Landscape, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","name":"Jose Rizal","lat":8.66805,"date":"1962","macroAddress":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.41665},"Q55365894":{"lat":14.94903,"macroAddress":"San Antonio, Zambales","date":"1950","region":"Central Luzon","name":"San Antonio","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Explored and settled by Ilocano pioneers from Paoay, Ilocos Norte, 1830. Named Barrio Pamisaraoan, 1836. Became a municipality, 12 May 1849. Witnessed the surrender of the Zambales Spanish forces to the Philippine Revolutionary Army at Annaoangen mountain, June, 1898, and their rout march to the plaza in front of the first Casa Tribunal located on this spot. Occupied by the Japanese, 1942. Liberated by the XI Corps of the Allied Armed Forces that landed at Ua, 29 January 1945.</p>","title":"San Antonio","subtitle":"<i>(Pamisaraoan)</i>"}}},"address":"San Antonio Central School, National Highway, San Antonio, Zambales","lon":120.0883,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"San Antonio":"San Antonio, Zambales"},"locDesc":null},"Q30087446":{"lat":14.60462,"macroAddress":"San Juan, Metro Manila","date":"1972-08-30","region":"Metro Manila","name":"El Deposito","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"El Deposito NHCP historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2004,"height":2610,"hash":"ba"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito itinayo ng mga Kastila ang tinggalan ng tubig na may lawak na dalawang ektarya at may lalim na dalawandaang talampakan. Dito naganap ang labanan noong ika-30 ng Agosto, 1886. Ginamit hanggang noong panahon ng Amerikano nang itayo ang tinggalan ng tubig sa San Juan at ang salaan ng tubig sa Balara na pinamahalaan ng dating Metropolitan Water District.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"“El Deposito”"}}},"address":"Pinaglabanan Shrine, San Juan, Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"width":2511,"file":"El Deposito historical marker in Pinaglabanan Shrine, San Juan City.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","height":3136,"hash":"88"},"lon":121.03054,"wikipedia":{"El Deposito":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main steps of the Pinaglabanan Shrine."},"Q55339602":{"wikipedia":{"Majayjay Church":"Saint Gregory the Great Parish Church (Majayjay)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade, below the pilaster to the right of the main entrance.","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Majayjay,Lagunajf8982 07.JPG","width":3456,"hash":"c9","height":4608},"lon":121.47132,"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng Majayjay","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Majayjay Church historical marker (cropped).JPG","width":2341,"hash":"ae","height":3481},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Majayjay","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayong yari sa kawayan at pawid sa Sitio May-it ng mga misyonerong Agustino matapos ang pamamayapa sa katutubo ni Salcedo, 1571; nasunog, 1576. Muling ipinatayo ng mga Pransiskano sa panahon ni P. Juan de Plasencia, 1578; muling nasunog, 1606. Ipinatayo ang kasalukuyang simbahang bato 1616–1649; bahagyang nasunog, 1660; pinaayos, 1707. Pinalaki ni P. Jose de Puertollano noong mga taong 1839, 1842 at 1848 dahil sa pinsala ng bagyo. Naging himpilan ng mga Amerikano noong Digmaang Pilipino–Amerikano. Isinaayos, 1912.</p>"}}},"address":"Majayjay Church, Majayjay, Laguna","lat":14.14653,"date":"1993","macroAddress":"Majayjay, Laguna"},"Q54006014":{"address":"Glowmoon Hotel, Martelino Street, Kalibo, Aklan","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"1855–1927","title":"Victorino Mapa","inscription":"<p>Born in Kalibo, Aklan, on 25 February 1855.</p><p>Legal adviser to the Philippine Revolutionary Government, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court 1901–1913; Secretary of Finance and Justice, 1913–1920; Chief Justice of the Supreme Court, 1920–1921.</p><p>Died in Manila 12 April 1927.</p>"}}},"region":"Western Visayas","name":"Victorino Mapa","lat":11.71001,"date":"1954","macroAddress":"Kalibo, Aklan","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Victorino Mapa":true},"lon":122.36407,"locPhoto":null},"Q39024392":{"wikipedia":{"Pío Valenzuela":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete wall at the corner of the property of the Valenzuela house.","locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"7958Valenzuela City Metro Manila Roads Landmarks 26.jpg","width":4608,"height":3456,"hash":"45"},"lon":120.94515,"name":"Dr. Pio Valenzuela","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Dr. Pio Valenzuela Street cor. Kabesang Pino Street, Pariancillo Villa, Valenzuela, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang si Pio Valenzuela sa Polo, Bulakan, noong Hulyo 11, 1869. Bunsong anak nina Kapitan Francisco Valenzuela at Lorenzana Alejandrino. Umanib sa Katipunan noong Hulyo 15, 1892 na ang ginamit na sagisag ay Madlang-Away. Bilang sugo ng Katipunan, nakipagkita kay Jose Rizal sa Dapitan at isinangguni ang napipintong paghihimagsik laban sa mga Kastila na hindi sinang-ayunan nitong huli dahil sa kakulangan ng sandata. Sa bisa ng dekreto ni Gobernador-Heneral Ramon Blanco noong Agosto 30, 1890, si Dr. Valenzuela ay nahatulang mabilanggo sa Fuerza Santiago kasama si Antonio Luna at iba pa. Nakalaya pagkatapos ng Kasunduan sa Paris, Disyembre 10, 1898. <BR><BR>Naging punong-bayan ng Polo, Setyembre 6, 1899; gobernador ng Bulakan, 1919 at 1922. <BR><BR>Nakipag-isang dibdib kay Marciana de Castro, Oktubre 9, 1900. Yumao noong ika-6 ng Abril 1956 sa Polo, Bulakan.<BR><BR>Bilang parangal kay Don Pio ang ngalang Polo ng kanyang bayan ay pinalitan ng Valenzuela.</p>","title":"Dr. Pio Valenzuela","subtitle":"1869–1956<br>Dakilang Katipunero at Lingkod ng Bayan"},"photo":{"width":2000,"file":"Dr. Pio Valenzuela historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","hash":"06","height":3146}}},"date":"1966","macroAddress":"Valenzuela, Metro Manila","lat":14.70855},"Q52144871":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Pransiskano noong 1578 at naging regular na parokya at bayan noong 1595. Nang panahong ito ipinatayo ang unang simbahan sa patronato ni San Luis Obispo at unang gobernadorsilyo si Marcos Tigla.</p><p>Noong 1629, ang bayan ay inilipat sa kasalukuyang kinalalagyan nito. Ipinatayo ang bahay pamahalaan na yari sa apog at bato noong 1703 na tinupok ng apoy noong Setyembre 9, 1859. Ang kasalukuyang bahay pamahalaan ay itinayo matapos ang malaking sunog noong Hunyo 13, 1968. </p><p>Noong panahon ng Kastila, ng Amerikano at ng Hapon, maraming anak ng Lukban ang nakipaglaban sa kalayaan at karapatan ng mga Pilipino. Nanguna sa kilusang ito si Apolinario de la Cruz, kinikilalang dakilang anak ng bayan at ng bansa.</p>","title":"Lucban","subtitle":"(1578–1978)"},"photo":{"width":3456,"file":"LucbanMunicipalHalljf8677 14.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":4608,"hash":"be"}}},"address":"Lucban Municipal Hall, Quezon Avenue cor. Lucban–Sampaloc Road, Lucban, Quezon","name":"Lucban","region":"Calabarzon","date":"1978-05-14","macroAddress":"Lucban, Quezon","lat":14.11433,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal at the northwestern corner of the municipal hall.","wikipedia":{"Lucban":true},"lon":121.55475,"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"39","file":"LucbanMunicipalHalljf8677 15.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456}},"Q24816583":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the museum.","wikipedia":{"Marcela Agoncillo":true},"locPhoto":{"width":1286,"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Marcela Agoncillo Historical Landmark entrance.jpg","height":834,"hash":"e9"},"lon":120.91815,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Taal 24 Hunyo 1859; nag-aral sa Kolehiyo ng Santa Catalina; Asawa ni Felipe Agoncillo at siya niyang matapat na katulong sa kanyang gawaing makabayan; ipinagbili ang kanyang mga hiyas upang magugol ng asawa sa misyon nito sa ibang bansa sa kapakanan ng pagsasarili ng Pilipinas. Sa panahon ng kanilang pagkapatapon sa Hong Kong, ay tinahi niya ang unang bandilang Pilipino na buong pagmamalaking iwinagayway ni Heneral Emelio Aguinaldo sa Kawit noong 12 Hunyo 1898 sa pagpapahayag ng Pagsasarili ng Pilipinas. Namatay sa Taal 30 Mayo 1946.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo 1859–1946"},"photo":{"width":1161,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo historical marker.jpg","hash":"45","height":1782}}},"address":"Marcela Mariño and Felipe Agoncillo Museum, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Marcela Mariño de Agoncillo 1859–1946","lat":13.87843,"macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","date":"1955-06-24"},"Q24049388":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.9852,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Quiapo, Manila","date":"1973","lat":14.59671,"name":"El Renacimiento","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito itinatag ni Martin Ocampo ang makabayang pahayagang <u>El Renacimiento</u> na ang unang bilang ay lumabas noong Setyembre 3, 1901. Naging patnugot sina Rafael Palma (1901–1903), Fernando Ma. Guerrero (1903–1907), at Teodoro M. Kalaw (1907–1909). Natalo sa usaping libelo at ang mga kasangkapan ng pahayagan ay ipinagbili upang mabayaran ng ₱60,000 danyos ang Kalihim-Panloob Dean C. Worcester. Ito ang ikinamatay ng pahayagan.</p>","title":"El Renacimiento","subtitle":"1901"},"photo":{"width":3000,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"El Renacimiento historical marker.jpg","hash":"5f","height":4000}}},"address":"Gunao Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q55100819":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":754,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Naval Base of Subic Bay historical marker 03.jpg","height":1030,"hash":"a1"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isang sentro ng kalakalan bago dumating ang mga Espanyol. Idineklarang daungang pandagat ng Hari ng Espanya, 1884. Sinimulan ang pagpapatayo ng arsenal at istasyong pandagat, 1885. Pansamantalang nakuha ng puwersang Pilipino, 1898. Ngunit napasailalim sa mga Amerikano, 1899. Nasakop ng mga Hapon, 1941 at nabawi ng Amerikano, 1945. Muling pinamahalaan ng mga Amerikano alinsunod sa Military Bases Agreement ng Pilipinas at Estados Unidos, 1947–1991. Nasalanta sa pagputok ng bulkang Pinatubo, 1991. Tuluyang nilisan ng mga Amerikano nang hindi pinagtibay ng Senado ang bagong Military Bases Agreement, 1992. Naging Special Economic and Freeport Zone sa pamamahala ng Subic Bay Metropolitan Authority, 13 Marso 1992.</p>","title":"Himpilang Pandagat ng Look ng Subic","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Subic Spanish gate, Sampson Road cor. Dewey Avenue, Olongapo","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Himpilang Pandagat ng Look ng Subic","lat":14.81749,"macroAddress":"Olongapo","date":"2013-11-26","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Naval Base Subic Bay":"U.S. Naval Base Subic Bay"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.28344},"Q55736332":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.48486,"wikipedia":{"Corregidor":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Mariveles, Bataan","date":"1949","lat":14.4317,"name":"Corregidor","region":"Central Luzon","address":"Bonifacio Street cor. P. Monroe Street, Brgy. Poblacion, Mariveles, Bataan","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Corregidor","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Derived its name from Corregimiento or municipal district. About 1225 the island became a stronghold for Chinese pirates until the latter were driven by the Moros. Became Spanish possession, 1570, when Spaniards arrived in Manila from Panay. Occupied by the Dutch, 1600. Recaptured by the Spaniards as a fortification besides being used as lighthouse, dockyard, naval convalescent hospital, penal colony, and checking point for ships to have their papers corrected. Surrendered without resistance to Admiral Dewey, May 6, 1898. First occupied by the Americans as a convalescent hospital, November 14, 1904, and first garrison, the 35th Company, C.A.C., commanded by Captain C.E. Kilbourne, arrived, May 8, 1908. Became the seat of the government of the Commonwealth of the Philippines during World War II and the scene of President Quezon’s taking oath of office on his second term. President Quezon and his family sought shelter at Malinta Tunnel, December 24, 1941. Occupied by the Japanese, May 6, 1942; retaken by the Americans, March 2, 1945. Turned over to the Republic of the Philippines, October 12, 1947.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"e6","height":4608,"file":"0501jfBalon Poblacion Manila Bay Halls Mariveles Bataanfvf 25.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro","width":3456}}}},"Q36597581":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Tondo Church main door.jpg","width":2464,"hash":"44","height":1607},"lon":120.96711,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located just to the left of the main door of the church.","wikipedia":{"Tondo Church":true},"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","lat":14.60779,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"ChurchofTondojf1245 01.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3359,"height":3547,"hash":"b1"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The first Catholic minister of Tondo was the Rev. Alonso de Alvarado, O.S.A. Tondo was the residence of Lakan-Dula who was baptized by the Rev. Martin de Rada, O.S.A. In the early days its ecclesiastical jurisdiction extended up to Pasig, Cainta and Taytay. Tondo was an active center of Catholic activities among the Chinese. The former convent was demolished in 1662 by Governor Sabiniano Manrique de Lara as a military precaution against the expected attack on Manila by Kue-Sing. The present church was built by the Rev. Manuel Diez, O.S.A., and the Rev. Casimiro Herrero, O.S.A., in the second half of the 19th century. Since the early days the traditional fluvial procession of Sto. Niño has attracted thousands of visitors to Tondo.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Tondo"}}},"address":"Tondo Church, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Church of Tondo","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q23886446":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.45618,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Our Lady of Guadalupe Parish Church":"Our Lady of Guadalupe Parish Church (Pagsanjan)"},"lat":14.27271,"macroAddress":"Pagsanjan, Laguna","date":"1953","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"cf","height":768,"width":576,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker of Pagsanjan Church.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Church of Pagsanjan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Founded, 1687. Father Agustin de la Magdalena, first curate. Original chapel of bamboo and nipa reconstructed, 1690, under the direction of Miguel Guan-co and Alguacil Mayor Alonso Garcia. Improved, 1853 by Fr. Joaquin de Coria. Transept added, 1872 by Fr. Serafin Linares and Fr. Cipriano Bac. Damaged during World War II.</p>"}}},"address":"Our Lady of Guadalupe Parish Church, Pagsanjan, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Church of Pagsanjan"},"Q37659579":{"name":"Simbahan ng Tagig","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Agustino ang parokya sa pamamatnubay ng patronang si Sta. Ana at ipinatayo ng unang kura paroko P. Diego Alvarez, ang unang simbahang bato noong 1587. Nasira ng lindol, 1645, at muling ipinatayo ni P. Andres Diaz, 1848. Nasirang muli ng lindol, 1882, at muling ipinatayong yari sa bato ni P. Giullermo Diaz, 1886–1896. Ipinaayos ni Rt. Rev. Msgr. Augurio I. Juta, 1980–1985, at ni Msgr. Emmanuel V. Sunga, 1985–1987. Inihandog sa Panginoon ng Kagalang-Galang Obispo Bruno Torpigliani, Apostoliko Nunsiyo sa Pilipinas, sa pagdiriwang ng ika-400 taong pagkatatag ng parokya, Hulyo 25, 1987.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Tagig"},"photo":{"hash":"72","height":3072,"width":2304,"credit":"Raani Paranas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Simbahan ng Taguig.JPG"}}},"address":"Taguig Church, 41 Liwayway Street, Sta. Ana, Taguig, Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Taguig, Metro Manila","date":"1987-07-25","lat":14.52673,"wikipedia":{"Taguig Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall just to the right of the main entrance of the church.","locPhoto":{"file":"Taguig Church main entrance.jpg","credit":"Ronaldbunag {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1530,"height":1110,"hash":"47"},"lon":121.07423},"Q55724524":{"lat":14.87037,"macroAddress":"Hermosa, Bataan","date":"1948","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Bataan and Democracy","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3371,"hash":"3a","width":2200,"file":"Bataan and Democracy historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The little mountainous peninsula of Bataan saved democracy and the whole world from the evil hands of the devil. </p><p>(From the radio broadcast of President Franklin Delano Roosevelt, January 5, 1945.)</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Bataan and Democracy"}}},"address":"Prado Bridge, Km. 96 Jose Abad Santos Avenue, Brgy. Balsic, Hermosa, Bataan","locPhoto":{"hash":"be","height":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jf9393Pampanga Bataan Democracy Welcome Archfvf 20.JPG","width":4608},"lon":120.49953,"wikipedia":{"Bataan":true,"World War II":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting a few meters from the north side of the road."},"Q24033369":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.69871,"wikipedia":{"Dingras Church":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":18.10274,"date":"1987","macroAddress":"Dingras, Ilocos Norte","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Guho ng Simbahang Katoliko ng Dingras","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Guho ng Simbahang Katoliko ng Dingras","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Bakas ng isang magandang simbahang sinira ng lindol at apoy, 1913. May bubong na yero, malaki at matibay na pader. Ang simbahan na may habang 90 hakbang at lapad na 20 hakbang ay isa sa pinakamalaki sa Pilipinas. Nagsimulang visita ng Batac, ginawang parokya ng mga Agustino at inialay sa patrong San Jose; Si Padre Bartolome Conrado ang unang kura, 1598. Ibinalik sa pagkavisita, 1603. Naging parokyang muli bilang sentro ng misyon, 1605. Nasira ng lindol, 1619; Muling ipinagawa bagong nasunog, 1838 at nasira ng kidlat, 1853. Huling ipinatayo ni Padre Ricardo Deza sa paggawa ng 2 polistas buhat sa bawat isa ng 58 cabecerias sa halagang $28, 649.31 piso ng Mehiko, sa tulong ni Alkalde Mayor Camilo Millan, 1879-1893.</p>"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Eric Jam {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"DingrasChurchMarker1.JPG","height":4608,"hash":"76"}}},"address":"Dingras Church, Dingras, Ilocos Norte"},"Q47004026":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"Lucban, Quezon","title":"Labanan sa Baryo Piis","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito naganap ang labanan sa pagitan ng USAFFE 1<sup>st</sup> Infantry ng 1<sup>st</sup> Regular Division kasama ang 2<sup>nd</sup> Platoon Company C, 194<sup>th</sup> Tank Batallion at pwersang Hapones na galing sa Mauban, 26 Disyembre 1941. Tumagal ang labanan mula umaga hanggang hapon at nakaabot sa sangang-daang Mauban at Lucban kung saan dumating ang tatlong daang Philippine Scouts upang tumulong sa USAFFE. Nanaig sa labanan ang pwersang Hapones, subali’t naantala nito ang pagsulong sa Maynila.</p>"}}},"address":"Kilometer 134, Lucban–Sampaloc Road, Lucban, Quezon","name":"Labanan sa Baryo Piis","region":"Calabarzon","date":"2011-05-02","macroAddress":"Lucban, Quezon","lat":14.14867,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":121.59587,"locPhoto":null},"Q54152845":{"name":"Felipe Sonsong","region":"Central Luzon","address":"Macabebe Church, Poblacion, Macabebe, Pampanga","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Macabebe, Pampanga, 1 Mayo 1611. Lumahok sa Pag-aalsang Maniago, 1660. Naglingkod sa Orden ng mga Misyonerong Agustino sa Pampanga at Misyonerong Dominikano sa Maynila. Napabilang sa Orden ng mga Heswita bilang donado sa Isla ng Marianas, 1668. Nakibahagi sa paggawa ng mga simbahan at bahay ng mga katutubo. Naging tagapagpayo sa mga nangangailangan ayon sa turo ng Diyos. Malubhang nasugatan matapos ang paglusob ng mga rebeldeng katutubo, 23 Hulyo 1684. Nanatili sa Isla ng Marianas hanggang yumao, 11 Enero 1686.</p>","title":"Felipe Sonsong","subtitle":"(1611–1686)"},"photo":{"width":2871,"file":"Felipe Sonsong historical marker (cropped).jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","hash":"54","height":4055}}},"macroAddress":"Macabebe, Pampanga","date":"2011-05-01","lat":14.90788,"wikipedia":{"Felipe Songsong":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting at the center of the Macabebe Church patio.","lon":120.7153,"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"fd","width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Macabebe Church patio monuments.jpg"}},"Q23805082":{"macroAddress":"Cavinti, Laguna","date":"1938","lat":14.24531,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":3000,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Cavinti historical marker.jpg","hash":"40","height":3030},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The ecclesiastical administration of Cavinti belonged to Lumbang until 1619. The first stone Church and convent were built about 1621, but both were seriously damaged during the Chinese uprising of 1939. The present Church was partially, and the convent totally, destroyed by the earthquakes of 1824; both were rebuilt before 1851. The tower collapsed during the earthquakes of 1880, and the walls were badly cracked during the earthquakes of 1880 and 1937.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Cavinti"}}},"address":"Cavinti Church, Cavinti, Laguna","name":"Church of Cavinti","region":"Calabarzon","lon":121.50741,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Cavinti Church":true}},"Q39696558":{"locPhoto":{"file":"4081Maysan Road Malinta, Valenzuela City 04.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":4608,"hash":"f2","height":3456},"lon":120.96877,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting beside a historic cannon.","wikipedia":{"Harry C. Egbert":true},"lat":14.69413,"date":"2013-04-22","macroAddress":"Valenzuela, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Naganap ang sagupaan ng mga sundalong Pilipino at Amerikano hindi kalayuan sa Simbahan ng Malinta, kung saan napaslang ang ilang kawal ng 22<sup>nd</sup> U.S. Infantry kabilang si Col. Harry C. Egbert, 26 Marso 1899. Bagaman nadepensahan ng mga Pilipino sa unang bahagi ang kanilang posisyon sa Malinta, kalauna’y napilitan silang umatras pahilaga sa paglusob ng dagdag na kawal ng puwersang Amerikano.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Malinta","subtitle":"26 Marso 1899"},"photo":{"file":"Labanan sa Malinta historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","width":1058,"height":1282,"hash":"9b"}}},"address":"Maysan Road, Valenzuela, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Labanan sa Malinta"},"Q28855086":{"wikipedia":{"Bernardino Jalandoni Museum":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":122.97731,"locPhoto":null,"region":"Western Visayas","name":"Bernardino-Ysabel Jalandoni Ancestral House","address":"Bernardino Jalandoni Museum, Silay, Negros Occidental","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"d2","height":695,"width":1107,"credit":"ClaireMRA {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Bernardino-Ysabel Jalandoni Ancestral House historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>This is a Heritage House pursuant to Board Resolution no. 3 dated April 6, 1993 of the National Historical Institute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Bernardino-Ysabel Jalandoni Ancestral House"}}},"lat":10.80186,"date":"1993","macroAddress":"Silay, Negros Occidental"},"Q37705570":{"locPhoto":{"file":"Battle of Alapan Monument in Imus Heritage Park.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3000,"height":4000,"hash":"83"},"lon":120.91516,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Alapan":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of a monument of a lady brandishing the Philippine Flag at a battle. The monument is at the western portion of the park.","lat":14.40373,"macroAddress":"Imus, Cavite","date":"2014","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Labanan sa Alapan","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa Alapan","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ng Alapan, Imus, Kabite, noong 28 Mayo 2898, naipagtagumpay ang kaunaunahang labanan sa mga hangganan ng Kawit nang muling magbangong-lakas laban sa Espanya ang himagsikan itinatag ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo. Ang labanang ito ang naging palatandaan ng ating matagumpay na pagpupunyaging maibagsak ang paghahari ng mga Kastila at ng pagsilang ng unang Republika ng Pilipinas. Sa pook din ito unang iwinagayway ang bandilang Pilipino.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Battle of Alapan Historical Marker at Imus Heritage Park.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3043,"height":3864,"hash":"55"}}},"address":"Shrine of the National Flag, Bucandala-Alapan Road, Imus, Cavite"},"Q24702174":{"address":"Atimonan Church, Quezon Street, Atimonan, Quezon","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of Atimonan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The first Church here and the town were burned by the Dutch in 1640. The second Church, built of stone in 1643, was partially destroyed by fire in 1648. The third Church, rebuilt in 1650, likewise was destroyed by earthquakes. The present Church and the Convent were constructed between 1687 and 1700, but were seriously damaged by the earthquake of August 20, 1937.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Our Lady of the Angels Parish Marker in Atimonan, Quezon.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2592,"hash":"21","height":1944}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Church of Atimonan","lat":14.00164,"macroAddress":"Atimonan, Quezon","date":"1939","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.92139},"Q31440620":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.88035,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Sandugo":true},"date":"1941","macroAddress":"Tagbilaran, Bohol","lat":9.62714,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":1346,"file":"Blood Compact Between Sikatuna and Legaspi historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","hash":"b1","height":1497},"text":{"inscription":"<p>About the middle of March 1565, Captain General Miguel Lopez de Legaspi’s fleet anchored along this shore. Shortly thereafter, Legaspi manifesting trust and confidence in the islanders, entered into a blood compact with Datu Sikatuna for the purpose of insuring friendly relations between the Spaniards and the natives. A few drops of blood drawn from a small incision in the arm of each of the two chiefs were placed in separate cups containing wine, and in the presence of the followers of both, each chief drank the potion containing the blood of the other. Thus, during this period of colonization, a bond was sealed in accordance with native practice, the first treaty of friendship and alliance between Spaniards and Filipinos.</p>","title":"Blood Compact Between Sikatuna and Legaspi","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Tagbilaran, Bohol","name":"Blood Compact Between Sikatuna and Legaspi","region":"Central Visayas"},"Q55231219":{"lat":14.84423,"date":"1990-06-11","macroAddress":"Malolos, Bulacan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Casa Real","address":"Casa Real, Bank of Commerce Road cor. Paseo del Congreso, Malolos, Bulacan","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Casa Real","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayong yari sa kawayan at kogon, 1580; pinaayos sa kahoy at nipa noong ika-16 na dantaon. Ipinagawang yari sa bato, 1767; ng ladrilyo at mortar, 1786. Pamuling ipinatayo, 1843. Pinaganda at nagkaroon ng balkonahe, 1918. Naging tanggapan ng gobernadorcillo noong panahon ng Kastila; tesoreriya ng pamahalaang Kastila noong panahon ng pananakop ng mga Ingles sa Maynila; dito nilimbang ang La Independencia, El Heraldo de la Revoluccion, Kalayaan, at Kaibigan ng Bayan. Nasira sa kalaunan at mula sa nalalabing pader at haligi, pinasimulang ayusin at papanumbalikin sa dating kaayusan ang makasaysayang gusaling ito 1980.</p>"},"photo":{"width":570,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"CasaReal HistoricalMarker MalolosCity.jpg","height":879,"hash":"5f"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.81149,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q54586401":{"wikipedia":{"Antonio Luna":true,"Philippine–American War":true,"First Philippine Republic":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the far left end of the building facade facing MacArthur Highway.","locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"6017Valenzuela railway station 12.jpg","height":3456,"hash":"16"},"lon":120.96025,"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Punong Himpilan ng Operasyong Militar sa Maynila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"e8","height":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"6017Valenzuela railway station 07.jpg","width":4608},"text":{"title":"Punong Himpilan ng Operasyong Militar sa Maynila","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito naghimpil si Hen. Antonio Luna, pinuno ng operasyong militar ng Republika ng Pilipinas laban sa Hukbong Amerikano sa Maynila, 5 Pebrero 1899. Kinontrol ng hukbo ni Luna ang Ferrocarril de Manila a Dagupan upang hadlangan ang pag-abante ng Hukbong Amerikano patungong hilaga. Nilisan matapos ang Labanan sa Polo, 25 Marso 1899. Nakatulong ang pananatili rito ng hukbo ni Luna upang maantala ang pagkubkob ng mga Amerikano sa Malolos, Bulacan, kabisera ng Republika, at nabigyan ng sapat na panahon si Pangulong Emilio Aguinaldo na lumipat patungong San Isidro, Nueva Ecija, ang napiling bagong kabisera ng Pamahalaang Pilipino.</p>"}}},"address":"MacArthur Highway cor. G. Lazaro Street, Dalandanan, Valenzuela, Metro Manila","lat":14.70862,"date":"2015-04-15","macroAddress":"Valenzuela, Metro Manila"},"Q54810448":{"wikipedia":{"Marcelino Crisólogo":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.38637,"region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Mena Crisologo","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"0c","height":3219,"width":4841,"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker Mena Crisologo.JPG"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Vigan, Ilocos Sur, noong Nobyembre 11, 1844. Notario eclesiastico, Diyosesis ng Nueva Segovia. Isa sa mga lumagda sa Konstitusyon ng Malolos, 1899. Unang gobernador ng Ilocos Sur, 1901. Kagawad, Lupon ng mga Gobernador na ipinadala sa Pandaigdig na Eksposisyon, St. Louis, E.U., 1904. Pagkatapos ng kanyang panunungkulan bilang gobernador, inilaan niya ang kanyang panahon sa pagpapalaganap ng mga sining at panitikang Iloko at pagbuo ng mga orkestra at banda. Ang kanyang mga komedya at sarsuela ay patuloy na itinatanghal tuwing pista sa Ilocos. Namatay noong Hulyo 5, 1927.</p>","subtitle":"(1844–1927)","title":"Mena Crisologo"}}},"address":"Plaza Vicente Singson Encarnacion, Calle Burgos, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","lat":17.57545,"macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","date":"1983-07-05"},"Q54802580":{"date":"1999-11-12","macroAddress":"Bayambang, Pangasinan","lat":15.8102,"name":"Luklukan ng Pamahalaang Panghimasikan ng Pilipinas","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bayang ito, noong Nobyembre 12, 1899, itinatag ng Pangulong Emilio Aguinaldo ang sentro ng Pamahalaang Panghimagsikan ng Pilipinas. Tinipon ang isang sanggunian na nagpasiyang lansagin ang Hukbong Pilipino. Napilitang gumamit ng pamamaraang gerilya sa pakikipaglaban sa mga Amerikano. Nilisan nang sumunod na araw, Nobyembre 13, 1899.</p>","title":"Luklukan ng Pamahalaang Panghimasikan ng Pilipinas","subtitle":"Bayambang, Pangasinan"}}},"address":"Bayambang Municipal Hall, Roxas Street, Poblacion, Bayambang, Pangasinan","locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"09","file":"Bayambang Pangasinan Municipal Hall facade.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608},"lon":120.45622,"wikipedia":{"Revolutionary Government of the Philippines":"Revolutionary Government of the Philippines (1898–1899)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the facade of the municipal hall building, below the balcony."},"Q46993548":{"date":"1990","macroAddress":"Lubao, Pampanga","lat":14.93936,"name":"Diosdado P. Macapagal","region":"Central Luzon","address":"President Diosdado P. Macapagal Library and Museum, Lubao, Pampanga","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Diosdado P. Macapagal","inscription":"<p>5th President of the Republic of the Philippines, a native son of Lubao, Pampanga, with deliberate patience, liberated himself from and transcended all the shackling obstacles adherent to the poverty of his birth on September 28, 1910.</p><p>Working his way through school, partly with the support of philantrophist Honorio Ventura, he earned the degrees of Bachelor of Laws, Master of Laws, Doctor of Laws and Doctor of Economics from the University of Santo Tomas. He topped the bar examination in 1936.</p><p>In 1949, he was elected Congressman for the first district of Pampanga, after two terms in Congress, he was elected Vice President of the Philippines in 1957 and was chosen as President of the Liberal Party. In 1961, he was elected President of the Republic of the Philippines.</p><p>As President, he had two objectives: to fight mass poverty and to strengthen and maturize democracy in the Philippines. On August 8, 1963, he enacted the Agricultural Land Reform Code, which abolished the centuries-old tenancy in the Philippines. After his retirement from politics in 1965, he was elected delegate to the 1971 Constitutional Convention which elected him as its president. </p><p>Diosdado Macapagal’s service to his people and country is characterized by his personal virtues of honesty, commitment and integrity and by a deep love and fear of God. All these manifestations of his idealism are shared by his wife, Evangelina <nobr>Macaraeg–Macapagal</nobr>, and his children Cielo <nobr>Macapagal–Salgado,</nobr> Arturo Macapagal, Gloria <nobr>Macapagal–Arroyo</nobr> and Diosdado Macapagal, Jr.</p>"}}},"lon":120.60034,"locPhoto":{"file":"Diosdado Macapagal historical marker in Lubao.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3456,"hash":"98","height":4608},"wikipedia":{"Diosdado Macapagal":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal holding the bust of Macapagal."},"Q55383208":{"lat":14.84235,"date":"1966","macroAddress":"Olongapo","region":"Central Luzon","name":"City of Olongapo","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"City of Olongapo","inscription":"<p>Subic Bay, Zambales became a U.S. Naval Station, 1901. Designated as a military reservation was the adjacent land from where a portion of the area grew the community of Olongapo and administered by the U.S. navy officials. Administration of Olongapo was turned over to the Republic of the Philippines by the United States Government, December 7, 1959. By virtue of Executive Order No. 366, Olongapo became a municipality and its local officials appointed.</p><p>The desire and aspirations of the citizens of Olongapo led by Mayor James L. Gordon became a fulfillment when Congressman Ramon Magsasaysay, Jr. sponsored H.B. No. 983 converting the municipality of Olongapo into a City. Approved by President Ferdinand E. Marcos, June 1, 1966 as Republic Act No. 4645, and the incumbent elective officials as the first city officials.</p><p>James L. Gordon<br><small>Mayor</small> </p><p>Jaime Guevara<br><small>Vice-Mayor</small></p><p><u>Councilors</u><br>Remigio Tierro<br>Alfredo de Perio, Jr.<br>Marciano Solis<br>Floro Cruz<br>Cornelio O. Cardenas<br>Leonoro Pardo<br>Agustin Elane<br>Hector Ruiz (appointed)<br>Vice Macario Macaraeg (deceased)</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Olongapo City Hall, Rizal Avenue, Olongapo","lon":120.28764,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Olongapo":true},"locDesc":null},"Q28149890":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.03726,"wikipedia":{"Balmis Expedition":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Muntinlupa, Metro Manila","date":"2004-04-15","lat":14.40925,"name":"Ang Espedisyong Balmis","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Binuo sa panahon ni Haring Carlos IV noong 1 Setyembre 1803. Ang espedisyong pinamunuan ng doktor na si Francisco de Balmis ang nagpasimula ng bakuna laban sa bulutong sa mga kolonya ng Espanya. Naglayag ang Espedisyong Balmis mulang La Coruña, Espanya noong 30 Nobyembre 1803 at dumating sa Filipinas kasama ang dalawampu't limang batang Mehikanong taglay ang bakuna noong 15 Abril 1805. Bilang pagtanaw ng utang-na-loob sa dulot na pansagip laban sa salot ng bulutong, isang bantayog ni Haring Carlos ang ipinatayo at inihandog ng Lungsod ng Maynila sa Intramuros noong 1824.</p>","title":"Ang Espedisyong Balmis","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Ang Espedisyong Balmis historical marker 1.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2928,"hash":"ac","height":3697}}},"address":"Research Institute for Tropical Medicine, Alabang, Muntinlupa, Metro Manila"},"Q24844845":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Sixto López":true},"lon":120.73597,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak, Abril 6, 1863 sa Balayan, Batangas kina Natalio Lopez at Maria Castelo. Nagsimulang mag-aral sa pampublikong paaralan ng Balayan, 1875; pagkaraan, Ateneo Municipal, Manila; pagkatapos ay sumailalim siya sa pagtuturo ni Dr. Cipriano Gonzales; San Juan de Letran, 1882; at sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, kung saan ay nagtapos siya ng sekundaryang edukasyon noong 1884. Tagahanga at kaibigan ni Dr. Jose Rizal. Naging kalihim ni Ambassador Plenipontentiary Felipe Agoncillo. Isa sa ilang Pilipino na di sumumpa ng katapatan sa Estados Unidos. Kusang ipinatapon ang sarili sa Estados UNidos sa loob ng 25 taon. Ginugol ang nalalabing buhay sa kanyang bukid sa Balayan namatay, Marso 3, 1947.</p>","title":"Sixto Castelo Lopez","subtitle":"(1863–1947)"}}},"address":"Balayan, Batangas","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Sixto Castelo Lopez","lat":13.9405,"macroAddress":"Balayan, Batangas","date":"1993-03-13"},"Q28923100":{"date":"2012","macroAddress":"Pikit, Cotabato","lat":7.06124,"name":"Fort Pikit","region":"Soccsksargen","address":"Fort Pikit, Pikit, Cotabato","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Fort Pikit","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Kabilang sa mga kutang ipinatayo ng Pamahalaang Espanyol upang sakupin ang Mindanao at magapi ang mga Morong patuloy na nagtaguyod ng kanilang kalayaan mula sa pamahalaang kolonyal, 1893. Ginamit ng mga sundalong Amerikano at Philippine Constabulary na binubuo ng mga Pilipinong Kristiyano at Muslim. Inokupahan ng mga puwersang Hapon, 1942-1945. Binawi ng puwersang Amerikano para sa pagpapalaya ng silangang bahagi ng Mindanao, Abril 1945. Naging himpilan ng Philippine Marine Corps hanggang 2005. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 24 Abril 2012.</p>"}}},"lon":124.67795,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q24835341":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Luz–Katigbak Ancestral House","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":1002,"hash":"e8","file":"Luz katigbak House historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP), a government agency","width":1386},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Luz–Katigbak Ancestral House","inscription":"<p>This is a heritage house pursuant to the Board Resolution No. 4, series of 1996 of the National Historical Institute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>"}}},"address":"Casa de Segunda, Jose P. Rizal Street, Lipa, Batangas","lat":13.93897,"macroAddress":"Lipa, Batangas","date":"1996-10-20","wikipedia":{"Casa de Segunda":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.16179},"Q41329465":{"lon":121.41742,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":14.27553,"date":"2015-08-28","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ang Gusaling Pamahalaan ng Laguna","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng Pamahalaang Panlalawigan ng Laguna sa ilalim ni Gobernador Juan Cailles ayon sa disenyo ni Arkitekto William E. Parsons, 1907. Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at ipinaayos sa pamamagitan ng U.S.–Philippine Rehabilitation Act of 1946 at natapos, 1949. Muling ipinaayos, 2012, at nananatiling sento ng pamamahala sa lalawigan.</p>","title":"Ang Gusaling Pamahalaan ng Laguna","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Old Laguna Provincial Capitol Building, Pedro Guevarra Avenue, Santa Cruz, Laguna"},"Q44816101":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Ambrosio Rianzares Bautista":true},"lon":121.0844,"locPhoto":null,"address":"Biñan Cultural Center, A. Bonifacio Street, Biñan, Laguna","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1830–1903)","title":"Ambrosio Rianzares Bautista","inscription":"<p>Unang tagapayo ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo noong 1898. May-akda ng Pagpapahayag ng Kalayaan ng Pilipinas (ika-12 ng Hunyo 1898), at masigasig na makabayan at tagapagpalaganap. Siya ay ipinanganak sa Biñan, Laguna noong ika-7 Disyembre 1830 kina Gregorio Enriquez Bautista at Silvestra Altamira. Nagtapos siya ng panimulang pag-aaral sa Biñan at ng pag-aaral sa batas sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas noong 1865.</p><p>Nagsanay siya sa pagkamanananggol sa Maynila at naging kilala sa pagkakaloob ng walang bayad na paglilingkod sa mahihirap na may usapin. Isang masigasig na kagawad ng La Liga Filipina, Cuerpo de Compromisarios, at La Propaganda. Siya ay dinakip ng mga maykapangyarihang Kastila at ipiniit sa Kutang Santiago nang magsiklab ang himagsikan noong 1896. Siya ay pinalaya pagkaraang ipagtanggol niya nang buong ningning ang kanyang sarili.</p><p>Siya ay inihalal na Ikalawang Pangulo ng Kongresong Panghimagsikan sa Tarlak noong ika-14 ng Hulyo 1899. Itinalaga siya bilang hukom ng Hukumang Unang Dulugan sa Pangasinan. Siya ay namatay sa Maynila noong ika-4 ng Disyembre 1903.</p>"},"photo":null}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ambrosio Rianzares Bautista","lat":14.33864,"date":"1980","macroAddress":"Biñan, Laguna"},"Q54535640":{"lon":120.98985,"locPhoto":{"width":2448,"file":"Miguel de Benavides Monument, UST.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"32","height":3264},"wikipedia":{"University of Santo Tomas":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the backside of the pedestal of the Miguel de Benavides Monument in Benavides Park in front of UST Main Building.","lat":14.60947,"date":"2012-01-25","macroAddress":"Sampaloc, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"University of Santo Tomas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang itinatag sa Intramuros bilang seminaryo ng Colegio de Nuestra Señora del Santisimo Rosario ni Arsobispo Miguel de Benavides, O.P., 28 Abril 1611. Pinangalanang Colegio de Santo Tomas bilang pag-alaala kay Santo Tomas de Aquino, 1625. Naging unibersidad 1645. Ginawaran ng titulong Real ni Haring Carlos III, 1785. Tagapangasiwa ng mga paaralan sa Pilipinas, 1865. Isinara noong pangalawang bahagi ng Rebolusyong Pilipino laban sa Espanya at Digmaang Filipino–Amerikano, 1898–1899. Muling binuksan, 1899. Binigyan ng titulong Pontifical University ni Papa Leo XIII, 1902. Tumanggap ng mga mag-aaral na babae, 1924. Inilipat sa Hacienda Sulucan sa Sampaloc; pinasinayaan ang pangunahing gusali na dinesensyo ni Padre Roque Ruaño, O.P., 1927. Ginamit ng mga Hapon bilang piitan ng mga Amerikanong sibilyan at iba pang mga bihag na kaalyado ng Estados Unidos, 1942–1945. Ginawaran ni Papa Pio XII ng titulong Catholic University of the Philippines, 1947. Kabilang sa mga nag-aral dito ang mga itinanghal na santo at martir ng simbahan, at mga bayaning Pilipino tulad nina Jose Rizal, Emilio Jacinto, Marcelo H. del Pilar at Apolinario Mabini; at mga naging pangulo ng Pilipinas na sina Manuel L. Quezon, Sergio Osmeña, Jose P. Laurel at Diosdado Macapagal. Ipinahayag na pambansang palatandaang pangkasaysayan, 24 Mayo 2011, sa bisa ng NHCP Board Resolution No. 5, s. 2011.</p>","title":"University of Santo Tomas","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"f1","height":1939,"file":"University of Santo Tomas Marker (Benavides Monument) (cropped).jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1604}}},"address":"University of Santo Tomas, España Boulevard, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q52774187":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Mindanao Garden of Peace","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"Corregidor Island","title":"Mindanao Garden of Peace","inscription":"<p>Nagsilbing kampo sa pagsasanay ng mga kabataang Moro bilang isang lihim na pangkat na pinamunuan ng ilang tauhan ng Hukbong Katihan ng Pilipinas. Nagsimula ang pagsasanay sa Simunul (ngayo’y bayan sa Lalawigan ng Tawi-Tawi), 17 Disyembre 1967. Inilipat sa Corregidor, 3 Enero 1968. Ang mga ulat ng pagpaslang sa ilang kasapi noong 18 Marso 1968 ay nagsilbing mitsa ng mga sigalot sa Mindanao na humantong sa pambansang krisis ng dekada 1970. Ang pangalang Mindanao Garden of Peace ay sumasagisag sa kabutihang loob ng mga Pilipino na makamit ang kapayapaan at kaunlaran sa ating bansa.</p>"}}},"address":"South Shore Road, Tailside, Corregidor, Cavite City, Cavite","lat":14.39131,"macroAddress":"Cavite City, Cavite","date":"2015-03-18","wikipedia":{"Jabidah massacre":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.60786},"Q43245232":{"lon":120.87079,"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"f2","width":4608,"file":"13Cavitejf0322 07.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"wikipedia":{"Thirteen Martyrs of Cavite":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on an inclined pedestal to the left of the southern stairway of the monument.","lat":14.2809,"macroAddress":"Trece Martires, Cavite","date":"1997","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Labintatlong Martir ng Cavite","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Labintatlong Martir ng Cavite historical marker.jpg","width":2500,"height":3587,"hash":"37"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Mga kilalang mamamayan ng Cavite na dinakip sa salang pakikipagsabwatan sa mga Katipunero kaugnay ng naganap na pag-aalsa sa Cavite noong Agosto 31, 1896. Bagaman at walang kasalanan sa krimeng ibinibintang sa kanila sila ay hinatulan ng kamatayan sa komisyong militar na lumitis sa kanila. Binaril noong hapon ng Setyembre 12, 1896 sa Kutang San Felipe, Lungsod ng Cavite, ang mga martir na ito ay sina:</p><p>Luis Aguado<br>Eugenio Cabezas<br>Feliciano Cabuco<br>Agapito Conchu<br>Maximo Inocencio<br>Maximo Gregorio<br>Jose Lallano<br>Severino Lapidario<br>Victoriano Luciano<br>Alfonso de Ocampo<br>Francisco Osorio<br>Hugo Perez<br>Antonio San Agustin</p>","title":"Labintatlong Martir ng Cavite","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Governor’s Drive cor. City Hall Road, Trece Martires, Cavite"},"Q24034676":{"region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Simbahan ng Sta. Maria","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1789,"file":"Historical Marker Simbahan ng Sta. Maria.jpg","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"65","height":2690},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Sta. Maria","inscription":"<p>Orihinal na itinayo ng mga paring Agustino bilang kapilya ng Narvacan. Naging isang parokya noong 1769 na ang patrona ay Nuestra Senora de la Asuncion. Muling ginawa at nilagyan ng tore noong 1810. Naging pansamantalang tuluyan ng mga misyonerong nagtutungo sa Abra. Binago noong 1863 at ang dalusdos ay pinaligiran ng malalaking bato. Muling ipingawa ni Padre Lorenzo Rodriguez ang simbahang bato.\nSa Bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974 at bilang 1515, 11 Hunyo, 1978, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palantandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"}}},"address":"Our Lady of the Assumption Church, Santa Maria, Ilocos Sur","lat":17.36678,"macroAddress":"Santa Maria, Ilocos Sur","date":"1982","wikipedia":{"Our Lady of the Assumption Church":"Santa Maria Church"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.48309},"Q54460999":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.02446,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":11.89235,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Culion, Palawan","region":"Mimaropa","name":"Fort Culion","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Fort Culion","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Fort Culion was constructed about 1740 by the Recollect Agustinians. It was built of stone, square in form, with four bastions.</p>"}}},"address":"Fort Culion, Brgy. Libis, Culion, Palawan"},"Q44453303":{"lat":15.34896,"date":"2002","macroAddress":"Capas, Tarlac","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Capas Concentration Camp","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2438,"file":"Capas Concentratrion Camp historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"20","height":3226},"text":{"title":"Capas Concentration Camp","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag noong 1940 bilang Camp O’Donnell. Nagsilbing bilangguan ng mahigit na 40,000 kawal Pilipino at 9,000 kawal Amerikano na bihag ng digma na dumanas ng Death March. Humigit-kumulang sa 30,000 ang namatay sa kampong ito sanhi ng sakit at ibayong pahirap mula Abril hanggang Hunyo 1942. Inilibing sa iisang hukay ang mga nasawing bayani. Nakilala sa pangalang Capas Concentration Camp. Naging bahagi ng Clark Air Base Military Reservation makaraan ang Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Ibinalik sa Republika ng Pilipinas 9 Abril 1982. Ipinahayag na isang Pambansang Dambana 9 Oktubre 1991.</p>"}}},"address":"Capas National Shrine, Km. 112 Tarlac–Zambales Road, Brgy. Aranguren, Capas, Tarlac","lon":120.54525,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"CapasNationalShrinev1jf4301 09.JPG","hash":"07","height":3456},"wikipedia":{"Capas National Shrine":true,"Camp O'Donnell":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is attached to the base of one of the legs of the obelisk-like structure."},"Q46571641":{"macroAddress":"Altavas, Aklan","date":"1992","lat":11.53837,"name":"Altavas","region":"Western Visayas","address":"Altavas Municipal Hall, Altavas, Aklan","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Naging visita ng Batan na dating kilala sa pangalang Laguing Banwa. Natatag bilang bayan, 1862 at pinanganlang Jimeno bilang parangal kay P. Romualdo Jimeno, Obispo ng Cebu. Bahagi ng bagong tatag ng bayang New Washington, 1903; Isang nagsasariling bayang tinawag na Altavas, bilang pagkilala kay Senador Jose Cortez Altavas, isa sa awtor ng batas para mahiwalay ang bayang ito sa New Washington, 1918. Naging kabisera ng lalawigan ng Capiz noong pananakop ng mga Hapon. Nahiwalay sa Capiz, 1956.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Altavas"}}},"lon":122.48759,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Altavas":true},"locDesc":null},"Q46864313":{"wikipedia":{"Museo Sugbo":true},"locDesc":"The Tagalog historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of the museum while the Cebuano marker is located to the right.","locPhoto":{"height":1536,"hash":"c8","credit":"Ringer {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Museo Sugbo.jpg","width":2048},"lon":123.90645,"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Carcel de Cebu","address":"Museo Sugbo, M. J. Cuenco Avenue, Cebu City","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2448,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Carcel de Cebu historical marker (Tagalog).jpg","hash":"94","height":3264},"text":{"title":"Carcel de Cebu","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ang mga gusali yari sa korales ayon sa disenyo ni Domingo Escondrillas bilang Bilangguan ng Distrito ng Visayas, 1870. Naging Cebu Provincial Jail noong panahon ng mga Amerikano at dinagdagan ang ilang gusali ng ikalawang palapag. Ginamit ang mga gusali sa harap bilang Cebu City Jail, 1946–1976. Naging Cebu Provincial Detention and Rehabilitation Center mula 1976 hanggang paglipat nito sa mas malawak na bilangguan sa Brgy. Kalunasan, Cebu City, 2004. Pinasinayaan bilang Museo Sugbo, ang Museo ng Lalawigan ng Cebu, 2008.</p>"}},"ceb":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Gitukod ang mga edipisyong binuhat sa mga batong gasang subay sa mugna ni Domingo de Esconrillas isip Bilangguan sa Distrito sa Kabisayaan, 1870. Nahimong Cebu Provincial Jail sa panahon sa mga Amerikano ug gipun-an ang ubang edipisyo og ikaduhang andana. Gigamit pod ang atubangang bahin isip Cebu City Jail, 1946–1976. Nahimong Cebu Provincial Detention and Rehabilitation Center gikan sa tuig 1976 hangtod sa pagbalhin niini ngadto sa mas hamugaway nga bilangguan sa Brgy. Kalunasan, Cebu City, 2004. Gisubhan isip Museo Sugbo, Ang Museo sa Lalawigan sa Sugbo, 2008.</p>","title":"Karsel sa Sugbo","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Carcel de Cebu historical marker (Cebuano).jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2448,"height":3264,"hash":"39"}}},"lat":10.3038,"date":"2009-08-13","macroAddress":"Cebu City"},"Q52153517":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Hilongos","subtitle":null,"inscription":""}}},"address":"Hilongos Church, R.V. Villaflores Street, Hilongos, Leyte","name":"Simbahan ng Hilongos","region":"Eastern Visayas","macroAddress":"Hilongos, Leyte","date":"1994-12-22","lat":10.37305,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the frontage wall of the church.","wikipedia":null,"lon":124.74792,"locPhoto":{"height":378,"hash":"d7","width":651,"credit":"GinaD {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Hilongos Church frontage with historical marker.jpg"}},"Q54006790":{"lat":11.53805,"date":"2018-01-25","macroAddress":"Altavas, Aklan","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"1877–1952","title":"Jose Cortes Altavas","inscription":"<p>Makabayan at mambabatas. Isinilang sa Capiz, ngayo’y Lungsod ng Roxas, Capiz, 11 Setyembre 1877. Naglingkod sa Hukbong Rebolusyonaryo sa Capiz at naging tagapamagitan ng mga Capiznon at nga mga hukbong ekspedisyonaryo na ipinadala ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo mula sa Luzon, 1898. Kinatawan ng ikalawang distrito ng Capiz sa Asamblea Filipina, 1907, at senador ng Pilipinas, 1916. Naging delegado sa kumbensiyong nagbalangkas sa Saligang Batas ng 1935. Yumao, 21 Agosto 1952.</p>"},"photo":{"width":678,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jose Cortes Altavas NHCP Historical Marker.png","hash":"e9","height":873}}},"address":"Katimawaan’t Jimeno Park, PC Barracks Road, Altavas, Aklan","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Jose Cortes Altavas","lon":122.4872,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q44455814":{"address":"Priscilla Building, 770 Rizal Avenue cor. Claro M. Recto Avenue, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"c4","height":4608,"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Asociacion Feminista Filipina site historical marker in Santa Cruz 2.jpg"},"text":{"title":null,"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>In a building on this site was organized the Asociacion Feminista Filipinas on 30 June, 1905.</p>"}}},"name":"Founding site of the Asociacion Feminista Filipina","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","date":"1955","lat":14.60332,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98209},"Q36031375":{"lat":14.56921,"date":"1937","macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Church of Malate","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Malate","inscription":"<p>This section of the city dates back to 1588. The titular patroness of this church is Nuestra Señora de los Remedios whose statue was brought from Spain in 1624 by Rev. Juan Guevara, O.S.A. The British landed their troops near these shores in 1762 and used the church of Malate for protection for their rear-guard in the capture of Manila. This church was greatly damaged by the earthquake of June 3, 1863 and was rebuilt by Rev. Francisco Cuadrado, O.S.A. The parish has been under the successive administration of the Augustinians, the secular clergy, the Redemptorists, and the Columbans.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Church of Malate historical marker 2.jpg","width":2000,"hash":"1c","height":2155}}},"address":"Malate Church, Marcelo H. del Pilar Street cor. Remedios Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"height":1580,"hash":"41","width":2175,"file":"Church of Malate historical marker vicinity.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"lon":120.98432,"wikipedia":{"Malate Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the extreme left of the main entrance of the church."},"Q43301560":{"locPhoto":{"file":"09708jfSanto Niño de Pandacan Parish Church Manila Schools Landmarksfvf 05.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":4608,"hash":"3f","height":3456},"lon":121.00392,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the church.","macroAddress":"Pandacan, Manila","date":"1976-07-13","lat":14.59308,"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Pandakan","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":2984,"hash":"0f","width":2500,"file":"Ang Simbahan ng Pandakan historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo noong 1732 ng paring Francisco del Rosario, O.F.M., ang simbahan at kumbento ay nayari noong 1760. Nasiraan dahil sa lindol ng 1852 at ng 1937. Ipinaayos ng paring Francisco Teodoro. Ang kasalukuyang simbahan ay itinayo sa pamamahala ng paring Victor R. Serrano at binasbasan ng arsobispo Jaime L. Sin noong ika-31 ng Marso, 1974.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Pandakan"}}},"address":"Pandacan Church, 833 Jesus Street cor. Pandacan Street, Pandacan, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q56164863":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98943,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"University of Santo Tomas":true},"macroAddress":"Manila","date":"1935","lat":14.60989,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3264,"hash":"4b","file":"University of Santo Tomas Marker (Main Building).jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2448},"text":{"inscription":"","subtitle":null,"title":"University of Santo Tomas"}}},"address":"Main Building, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"University of Santo Tomas","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q24247737":{"lat":14.59891,"date":"1988","macroAddress":"Quiapo, Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2229,"file":"Gregorio Araneta y Soriano historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","height":3292,"hash":"d2"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1869–1930)","title":"Gregorio Araneta y Soriano","inscription":"<p>Hurista, makabayan at matapat na lingkod bayan. Isinilang sa Molo; (dating Parian), Iloilo noong Abril 16, 1869. Nagkamit na titulong Batsilyer sa Sining, sobresaliente, Ateneo Municipal de Manila, 1884; titulo de agrimensor y perito tasador de tierras, 1886; at lisensiyado sa hurispundensiya, 1891, sobresaliente, Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas. Naging Nanunungkulang Piskal ng Audiencia de Manila, 1894–1895; Sekretaryo Heneral ng Republika ng Malolos, 1898; kasapi sa komite na bumalangkas ng Konstitusyon ng Malolos, katulong na mahistrado ng Kataas-taasang Hukuman, 1899; Solisitor Heneral ng pamahalaang sibil, 1900; unang Pilipinong Abogado Heneral, 1905 at Kalihim ng Katarungan at Pananalapi, 1908. Propesor ng batas sibil sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, 1916–1930[.] Namatay noong Marso 9, 1930.</p>"}}},"address":"Nazarene Catholic School, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Gregorio Araneta y Soriano","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98737,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Gregorio S. Araneta":true}},"Q54550946":{"lon":120.98031,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Santa Cruz Church":"Santa Cruz Church (Manila)"},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","date":"1937","lat":14.59951,"name":"Church of Santa Cruz","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"ChurchofSantaCruzjf0162 03.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"hash":"97","height":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>This church was built and administered by the Jesuits up to 1768. Adjoining was the Jesuit College of San Ildefonso, founded by Governor Alfonso Fajardo de la Tenza on January 9, 1724. The titular Patroness of the church is Nuestra Señora del Pilar, whose satue was brought from Spain prior to 1763. The confraternity of Nuestra Señora del Pilar was canonically founded in this church in 1743. On the surrounding plaza the British returned the City of Manila to Simon de Anda y Salazar in 1764.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Santa Cruz"}}},"address":"Santa Cruz Church, Plaza Santa Cruz, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q52684188":{"region":"Bicol Region","name":"Jesse M. Robredo","address":"Jesse Robredo Museum, J. Miranda Avenue cor. Taal Avenue, Naga, Camarines Sur","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Punong Lungsod ng Naga, Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Interyor at Lokal na Pamahalaan, at Pangulo ng League of Cities of the Philippines.</p><p>\nIsinilang sa Lungsod ng Naga, Camarines Sur noong ika-27 ng Mayo 1958. Nagsimula siya sa serbisyo publiko bilang Program Director ng Bicol River Basin Development Program noong 1986. Nahalal siya bilang Punong Lungsod ng Naga noong 1988 at nagsilbi nang 19 taon, mula 1988–1998 at 2001–2010. Bilang isang lingkod-bayan, ginawaran siya ng Ramon Magsaysay Award para sa kaniyang pagsulong ng aktibong pakikilahok ng taumbayan sa pamamahala. Itinalaga siya bilang Kalihim ng Interyor at Pamahalaang Lokal noong 2010. Bilang kalihim, ipinatupad niya ang Full Disclosure Policy upang tiyaking tapat at wasto ang paggamit ng lokal na pamahalaan sa pera ng bayan. Pumanaw siya noong ika-18 ng Agosto 2012. Bilang pagkilala sa kanyang natatanging nagawa sa mabuting pamamahala, ipinagkaloob sa kaniya ang Lehiyong Pandangal ng Pilipinas na may ranggong Punong Komandante at ang Krus ng Serbisyo ni Quezon, ang pinakamataas na karangalang maigagawad ng Republika.</p>","title":"Jesse M. Robredo","subtitle":"1958–2012"},"photo":null}},"lat":13.62856,"date":"2017-08-18","macroAddress":"Naga, Camarines Sur","wikipedia":{"Jesse Robredo":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.19721},"Q41231668":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Bayani ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Isinilang sa Laoag, Ilocos Norte, 9 Agosto 1906. Nagtapos sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas ng Pilosopiya, 1929, at ng Abogasya, 1930; pumasa sa pagsusulit sa bar ng taon ding iyon. Inihalal na gobernador ng Ilocos Norte, 1937 at 1941. Kasama si Tenyente Feliciano Madamba, binuo ang Ablan-Madamba Guerilla Group of Northern Luzon, Enero 1942. Nanguna sa mga labanan kabilang ang matagumpay na Labanan sa Pampanniki, Solsona, Ilocos Norte, 8 Nobyembre 1941. Huling nakita sa Labanan sa Bumitalag, Piddig, 5 Pebrero 1943.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Roque B. Ablan"},"photo":{"credit":"Eric Jam {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Gov. Roque Ablan Sr. Shrine2.JPG","width":450,"height":600,"hash":"3e"}}},"address":"Roque Ablan Shrine, A. Bonifacio Street, Laoag, Ilocos Norte","name":"Roque B. Ablan","region":"Ilocos Region","macroAddress":"Laoag, Ilocos Norte","date":"2006","lat":18.19222,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the Roque Ablan monument.","wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Eric Jam {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Gov. Roque Ablan Sr. Shrine3.JPG","width":450,"hash":"09","height":600},"lon":120.59885},"Q53618835":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.76491,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Cabagan, Isabela","lat":17.42619,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Former site of Fort Cabagan, described in an official report of 1736 to 1739 as built of stone and mortar and triangular in design. The fort was damaged by earthquake and transferred to Cavincunga.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Fort Cabagan"}}},"address":"Balay na Maguili, Rizal Avenue, Cabagan, Isabela","name":"Fort Cabagan","region":"Cagayan Valley"},"Q30131050":{"lat":48.84667,"date":"1959","macroAddress":"Paris, France","region":"Overseas","name":"José Rizal","address":"124 Rue de Rennes, 6th arrondissement, Paris, Île-de-France, France","details":{"fr":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>[Rizal] vécut dans cette maison en 1883.</p>","title":"José Rizal","subtitle":"1861–1896 Héros National des Philippines"}}},"lon":2.32642,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locDesc":null},"Q46995384":{"region":"Western Visayas","name":"Nazaria Lagos","address":"Dueñas, Iloilo","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":1376,"hash":"73","width":1087,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Nazaria Lagos historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1851–1945)","title":"Nazaria Lagos","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa baryo ng Burongan, ngayo’y Jaguimit, Dueñas, Iloilo noong 28 Agosto 1851. Makabayan, at ulirang nars ng mga sugatang Pilipino noong panahon ng himagsikan sa Kabisayaan. Tinahi niya ang bandilang Pilipino na iwinagayway sa Dueñas noong 12 Hunyo 1899, unang anibersaryo ng pagpapahayag ng kalayaan ng Pilipinas. Namatay noong 27 Enero 1945.</p>"}}},"lat":11.06503,"macroAddress":"Dueñas, Iloilo","date":"1973","wikipedia":{"Nazaria Lagos":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":122.61849,"locPhoto":null},"Q22262589":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Manila":"Battle of Manila (1899)","San Juan River Bridge":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.02029,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa tulay na ito, noong 29 Enero 1899, nagtagpo sina Kol. Luciano San Miguel, Filipinong komandante sa pook na iyon, at Col. John Stotsenburg, Commander, First Nebraska Volunteer Infantry, U.S. Army, upang ilatag ang hangganang sakop ng mga puwersang Filipino at Amerikano. Pagkaraang sumiklab ang Digmaang Filipino-Amerikano sa panulukan ng Sociego at Silencio, Sta. Mesa, Maynila noong 4 Pebrero 1899, naglabanan ang dalawang puwersa sa tulay na ito, 5 Pebrero 1899.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Tulay ng San Juan"},"photo":{"file":"Tulay ng San Juan 10.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1280,"hash":"97","height":1575}}},"address":"San Juan River Bridge, San Juan, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Tulay ng San Juan","lat":14.60159,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"San Juan, Metro Manila"},"Q24702458":{"name":"Tayabas","region":"Calabarzon","address":"Tayabas, Quezon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2388,"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Tayabas Historical Marker.jpg","hash":"1c","height":3340},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Pransiskano noong 1578, naging kabisera ng lalawigan noong 1605 na dati ay nasa Kalilayan (ngayo'y Unisan). Inilipat sa Lucena, ika-10 ng Marso, 1901. Noong ika-23 ng Oktubre, 1841, sa pamumuno ni Apolinario de la Cruz, isang labanan ang namagitan sa kanyang mga tauhan at sa pangkat ng mga Kastila sa baryo Isabang. Ang mga manghihimagsik ay nagwagi sa labanang iyon at napatay ang gobernador ng Kastila. Isa pang labanan ang naganap noong ika-1 ng Nobyembre sa Alitao kung saan nadakip si Hermano Puli at binitay sa karatig na bulwagang bayan ng Tayabas noong ika-4 ng Nobyembre. Siya ay ipinagbunyi bilang unang bayani ng lalawigan ng Tayabas at hari ng mga Tagalog.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Tayabas"}}},"macroAddress":"Tayabas, Quezon","date":"1978-01-15","lat":14.02517,"wikipedia":{"Tayabas":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the facade of Tayabas municipal  hall.","locPhoto":{"width":4608,"file":"Tayabasjf0310 07.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":3456,"hash":"34"},"lon":121.59256},"Q55724208":{"lat":14.72152,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Abucay, Bataan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Church of Abucay","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Abucay","inscription":"<p>The spiritual ministration of Abucay was entrusted to the Dominicans in 1588. A fierce battle between the Dutch invaders and the Pampango defenders was fought in this court on June 23, 1647. Nearly two hundred Pampangos were put to death and forty others, together with the Spanish Alcalde Mayor and two Dominican priests were taken prisoners to Batavia. The present Church was badly damaged by the earthquake of September 16, 1852. One of the earliest printing presses in the Philippines was operated in this town, where as early as 1610 Rev. Francisco Blancas de San Jose, O.P., and Don Tomas Pinpin printed several books in Spanish and Tagalog.</p>"},"photo":{"height":3456,"hash":"41","file":"Abucay's St. Dominic Church historical marker in Bataan.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608}}},"address":"Abucay Church, Abucay, Bataan","lon":120.53517,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"ParishChurchofSt.DominicdeGuzmanjf3734 04.JPG","hash":"4e","height":3456},"wikipedia":{"Abucay Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade, on the column to the right of the main entrance."},"Q46484367":{"macroAddress":"Naic, Cavite","date":"2014-01-21","lat":14.31985,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Biñan, Laguna, 15 Hunyo 1819. Nag-aral ng teolohiya sa Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas. Nagsilbing kura paroko ng Paombong, Bulacan, 1851–1854, kura rektor ng Katedral ng Maynila, 1855–1857, at kura paroko ng Naic, Cavite, 1857–1864. Tinaguriang “Ama ng Prosang Tagalog.” Kabilang sa kanyang mga akda: ang Platicas Doctrinales, Novena de San Isidro Labrador, Novena del Apostol Santiago at Exposicion de las Siete Palabras. May-akda ng Urbana at Felisa, na nagsilbing gabay ng kagandahang-asal at pakikipagkapwa-tao noong panahong iyon, 1864. Yumao, 21 Enero 1864.</p>","title":"Padre Modesto de Castro","subtitle":"1819–1864"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Urbanroamer {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Naic Church and Convent 8.JPG","hash":"ee","height":5184}}},"address":"Naic Church, Naic, Cavite","name":"Padre Modesto de Castro","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.76406,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q55915397":{"wikipedia":{"University of the Philippines":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.06488,"name":"University of the Philippines","region":"Metro Manila","address":"University of the Philippines Diliman, University Avenue, Diliman, Quezon City, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"University of the Philippines","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Founded on June 18, 1908 under Act No. 1870 of the First Philippine Legislature. Commemorated the U.P. Diamond Jubilee Year on June 18, 1983 to reassert the University’s role as fountain of learning and source of leadership of the Filipino people. Proclamation No. 2147 of His Excellency Ferdinand E. Marcos, President of the Republic of the Philippines, created a Presidential Commission on the U.P. Diamond Jubilee composed of:</p><p>Cesar E.A. Virata<br><small>Chairman</small></p><p>Onofre D. Corpus<br><small>Co-Chairman</small></p><p>Edgardo J. Angara<br><small>Vice-Chairman</small></p><p><small>Members</small><br>Manuel S. Alba<br>Roberto S. Benedicto<br>Francisco Tantuico, Jr.<br>Simeon Datumanong<br>Muss Isquierdo<br>Juan Ponce Enrile<br>Maria Kalaw Katigbak<br>Emil Q. Javier</p><p>Oscar M. Alfonso<br><small>Secretary</small></p><p>Dedicated on the 77th Foundation Day, June 18, 1985.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"7d","height":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"University of the Philippines Diamond Jubilee historical marker.jpg","width":4608}}},"macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","date":"1985","lat":14.65492},"Q52923028":{"name":"Simbahan ng Angeles","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating bisita ng San Fernando. Pinasinayaan ang unang kapilya sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora del Rosario, 1812. Naging ganap na parokya, 1829. Ipinatayo ang simbahang yari sa bato ayon sa disenyo ni Antonio de la Camara, 1877–1896. Dinaluhan ng libo-libong Pilipino ang misang isinagawa dito na sinundan ng talumpati ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo bilang bahagi ng pagdiriwang ng unang anibersaryo ng Proklamasyon ng Kalayaan ng Pilipinas, 12 Hunyo 1899. Ginamit ng hukbong Pilipino ang kampanaryo bilang bantayan laban sa hukbong Amerikano, 1899. Nagsilbing ospital at himpilan ng mga Amerikano ang simbahan at kumbento, 1900–1902. Ginamit ng mga Hapon bilang garahe ng mga sasakyang pandigma, 1942. Muling ipinaayos ang loob ng simbahan, 1962.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Angeles"}},"pam":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating bisitas ning San Fernando. Mibuklat ya ing mumunang kapilya kang Nuestra Señora del Rosario, 1812. Megin ganap yang parokya, 1829. Mitalakad ya ing pisamban a yari king batu agpang king disenyu nang Antonio dela Camara, 1877–1896. Tegunan de ring libu-libung Pilipinu ing meganap a misa keti na petukyanan ning metung a talumpati nang Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo antimong metung a dake ning pamagmasusi king mumunang anibersaryu ning Proklamasyun ning Pangatimawa ning Pilipinas, 12 Hunyu 1899. Ginamit de ring ukbung Pilipinu ing kampanaryu antimong batiawan laban karing ukbung Amerikanu, 1899. Megsilbing ospital at himpilan de ring Amerikanu ing pisamban at kumbentu, 1900–1902. Ginamit de ring Hapon bilang garahi karing saken dang pandigma, 1942. Pasibayu yang misamamas ing kilub ning pisamban, 1962.</p>","subtitle":"(Pisamban ning Angeles)","title":"Pisamban Maragul"}}},"address":"Santo Rosario Street, Angeles","macroAddress":"Angeles","date":"2017-08-17","lat":15.13469,"wikipedia":{"Angeles Church":"Holy Rosary Parish Church (Angeles)"},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.59057,"locPhoto":null},"Q22082854":{"date":"1937","macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","lat":14.56244,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Fort of San Antonio Abad","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The origin of this fort dates from 1584. It was captured by the British in 1762 and rebuilt at the beginning of the nineteenth century, when it was called La Polvorista because it was used as powder magazine. The first battalion of the First Colorado Regiment, under the command of Lt. Col. McCoy, took possession of this fort and hoisted the American flag over it on August 13, 1898.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"de","height":1406,"width":1500,"file":"Fort of San Antonio Abad - historic plaque.JPG","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"address":"Fort San Antonio Abad, Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas Complex, Roxas Boulevard, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Fort of San Antonio Abad","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"height":1574,"hash":"08","width":1260,"file":"Fort of San Antonio Abad - historical marker vicinity.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"lon":120.98689,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall below a statue of St. Anthony the Great and to the right of the southern entrance of the fort.","wikipedia":{"Fort San Antonio Abad":true}},"Q28933123":{"wikipedia":{"Douglas MacArthur":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":124.66431,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Macabalan Wharf","region":"Northern Mindanao","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng mga Espanyol sa Cagayan de Misamis ika-labinsiyam na siglo. Nagsilbing daungan ng mga sasakyang pandagat mula Maynila, Cebu, Maribojoc, Iloilo at Romblon. Naging kutang tanggulan ng mga Cagayanon upang pigilan ang pagsakop ng mga Amerikano sa Cagayan de Misamis, Enero-Marso 1900. Nasakop ng mga Amerikano, 25 Abril 1900. Dito dumaong sina Hen. Douglas MacArthur at pamilya mula Corregidor, 13 Marso 1942. Tumungo sa Del Monte Airfield, Bukidnon at lumpipad patungong Australya, 17 Marso 1942.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Macabalan Wharf"}}},"address":"Macabalan Wharf, Cagayan de Oro","macroAddress":"Cagayan de Oro","date":"2008-03-13","lat":8.50114},"Q43222507":{"wikipedia":{"Philtranco":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the entrance to the Philtranco Transport Heritage Museum.","lon":123.41653,"locPhoto":{"file":"Philtranco Transport Heritage Museum.jpg","credit":"Free2barredo {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4128,"height":3096,"hash":"f7"},"name":"Philtranco Service Enterprises, Inc.","region":"Bicol Region","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Philtranco Service Enterprises, Inc.","inscription":"<p>Unang pinanganlang Albert Louis Ammen Transportation Company (ALATCO). Ang unang kompaniya na pampasaherong bus ng mga Amerikano sa Pilipinas na itinatag noong 1914 ni A.L. Ammen, isang sundalong Amerikano, at ang punong himpilan ay sa Iriga, Camarines Sur. Ang pook na ito ay ginamit na garison ng Hukbong Imperyal na Hapon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig na nagbunga sa pansamantalang pagtigil ng paglilingkod na pambayan nito. Nagpasimulang muli noong 1945 sa Tabaco, Albay. Binili ng D. Tuason, Inc., noong 1949 at naging simula ng pagiging isa nitong korporasyong pag-aari ng mga Pilipino. Binili nito nang taong ding yaon ang Bicol Transportation Company (BITRANCO). Ang Consolidated Auto Lines (CAL) at Mindoro Transportation Company (MINTRANCO) noong 1954. Nakasanib ang Eastern Tayabas Bus Company (ETBCO), 1968. Binili ng Mantrade Group of Companies noong 1971 at pinanganlang Pantranco South Express Incorporated. Binigyan ng bagong pangalang Philtranco Services Enterprises, Inc., 1985.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ringer {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Philtranco Marker.jpg","width":2448,"hash":"b3","height":3264}}},"address":"Philtranco Transport Heritage Museum, Iriga–Baao Road, Iriga, Camarines Sur","macroAddress":"Iriga, Camarines Sur","date":"2000","lat":13.42681},"Q50383807":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.99063,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Honoria Acosta-Sison":true},"lat":14.5723,"date":"1988-12-20","macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Honoria Acosta Sison","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Unang babaeng doktor na Pilipino, siyentipiko at nanguna sa pananaliksik sa obstetrisya. Isinilang sa Calasiao, Pangasinan, Disyembre 30, 1888. Nagkamit ng titulong Doktor sa Medisina, Women’s Medical College of Pennsylvania, Estados Unidos, 1909. Ginawaran ng titulong Doktor sa Agham, Philippine Women’s University, 1940 at Women’s Medical College of Pennsylvania, 1950, kapwa honoris causa. Nagtatag at unang pangulo ng Asociacion de Damas de Filipinas at ng Philippine Obstetrical and Gynecological Society; kagawad, Philippine National Research Council at Philippine Historical Society; at isa sa mga nagtatag at unang pangalawang pangulo ng Philippine Academy of Science and Humanities. Tumanggap ng mga Medalyang Pampangulo para sa kanyang mga pananaliksik sa panggagamot, 1951 at Gawad Pampangulo dahil sa kanyang kontribusyon sa Kilusang Kababaihan ng Pilipinas, 1955. Itinalagang professor emeritus sa obstetrisya at hinekolohiya ng Lupon ng mga Rehente ng University of the Philippines, 1955. Namatay, 1970.</p>"},"photo":{"height":608,"hash":"f9","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"HonoriaAcostaSison HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg","width":417}}},"address":"1906 Taft Avenue, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Honoria Acosta Sison"},"Q54455521":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa bisa ng Kautusang Tagapagpaganap Blg. 35 ng pamahalaang Amerikano, 22 Agosto 1904. Nakarating dito ang unang grupo ng 365 na may sakit na Hansen mula sa Bisayas, 27 Mayo 1906. Ipinatupad ang Batas Blg. 1711 na tinipon ang mga may sakit sa Culion, 12 Setyembre 1907. Naging pinakamalaki at modelong leprosaryo sa buong mundo at sentro ng pananaliksik sa sakit, dekada 1920. Simula 1927, bumaba ang bilang ng mga ipinatapon sa Culion sa pagbukas ng mga pagamutan para sa sakit sa mga rehiyon. Noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, kinumpiska ng mga Hapon ang pagkaing naimbak sa isla, kaya’t higit sa 2,000 pasyente ang namatay sa gutom at iba’t ibang sakit. Ang dating ospital ng Culion ay naging Culion Sanitarium and General Hospital, 2009.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Culion Leper Colony"},"photo":null}},"address":"Culion Sanitarium and General Hospital, Brgy. Libis, Culion, Palawan","name":"Culion Leper Colony","region":"Mimaropa","macroAddress":"Culion, Palawan","date":"2014-07-26","lat":11.89181,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Culion Leper Colony":"Culion leper colony"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.02359},"Q52263930":{"macroAddress":"San Fernando, La Union","date":"1958","lat":16.61825,"address":"F. Ortega Highway, San Fernando, La Union","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Converted into a mountain bastion, Bacsil Ridge constituted the east flank of the Japanese line established in mid-January 1945 at the northern suburb of San Fernando. Subjected to several concerted attacks by elements of the 121st Infantry USAFIP NL, Bacsil Ridge was finally seized on 19 March 1945 and three days later the liberation of the entire town-port of San Fernando was effected.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Bacsil Ridge"},"photo":null}},"name":"Bacsil Ridge","region":"Ilocos Region","lon":120.36325,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Bacsil Ridge":true}},"Q36172767":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97238,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Teodora Alonzo":"Teodora Alonso Realonda"},"macroAddress":"San Nicolas, Manila","date":"2014","lat":14.59888,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pook na Kinamatayan ni Teodora Alonso","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito namatay si Teodora Alonso, ina ni Jose Rizal, noong 16 Agosto 1911.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"08","height":425,"file":"Pook na Kinamatayan ni Teodora Alonso.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":464}}},"address":"San Fernando Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Pook na Kinamatayan ni Teodora Alonso","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q28912870":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":125.03575,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Leyte":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Dulag, Leyte","date":"2008","lat":10.95269,"name":"Pagdaong sa Dulag, Leyte","region":"Eastern Visayas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Pagdaong sa Dulag, Leyte","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Dumaong sa dalampasigan ng bayang ito ang US 24<sup>th</sup> Corps, sa ilalim ni Maj. Gen. John R. Hodge, 20 Oktubre 1944, kasabay ng pagdaong sa Palo, Leyte ng 10<sup>th</sup> Corps bilang unang hakbang ng mga Amerikano sa pagbawi ng Pilipinas mula sa mga pwersang Hapones. Sa tulong ng mga gerilya ng 9<sup>th</sup> Military District sa pamumuno ni Col. Ruperto Kangleon, nabawi ang Dulag Airstrip. Nasagip ang limang daang sibilyan sa Lambak ng Leyte, at muling nabuksan ang San Juanico at Panaon Straits.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Pagdaong sa Dulag, Leyte historical marker.jpg","width":880,"height":1202,"hash":"1b"}}},"address":"Dulag, Leyte"},"Q46515773":{"wikipedia":{"Magellan–Elcano circumnavigation":"Timeline of the Magellan–Elcano circumnavigation","Battle of Mactan":true,"Ferdinand Magellan":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the back side of the pedestal inside an open building on the eastern side of the Mactan Shrine.","locPhoto":{"hash":"f0","height":1998,"width":3024,"credit":"Rabosajr {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Lapu-lapuShrine05.jpg"},"lon":124.01551,"name":"Ferdinand Magellan’s Death","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>On this spot Ferdinand Magellan died on April 27, 1521, wounded in an encounter with the soldiers of Lapulapu, Chief of Mactan Island. One of Magellan’s ships, the Victoria, under the command of Juan Sebastian Elcano, sailed from Cebu on May 1, 1521, and anchored at San Lucar de Barrameda on September 6, 1522, thus completing the first circumnavigation of the earth.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ferdinand Magellan’s Death"},"photo":{"width":3024,"file":"Lapu-lapuShrine05.jpg","credit":"Rabosajr {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":1998,"hash":"f0"}}},"address":"Mactan Shrine, Punta Engaño Road, Lapu-Lapu","macroAddress":"Lapu-Lapu","date":"1941","lat":10.31081},"Q22284212":{"lat":13.94106,"macroAddress":"Lipa, Batangas","date":"1939","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Cathedral of Lipa","inscription":"<p>The parish of Lipa was administered by the Augustinians from 1605 to the end of the nineteenth century. Lipa, which was located formerly on the shore of Bombon Lake, was destroyed by the eruption of Taal Volcano in 1754, but was reconstructed on the present site. This Church was built under the supervision of the Rev. Benito Varas, O.S.A., parish priest from 1865 to 1894. The Diocese of Lipa was created by Pope Pius X on April 10, 1910. The Augustinians encouraged the extensive cultivation of cacao and coffee.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"a3","height":2280,"width":2252,"credit":"Photo: RaMmpage18; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Cathedral of Lipa historical marker.jpg"}}},"address":"Lipa Cathedral, Lipa, Batangas","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Cathedral of Lipa","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.16368,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Lipa Cathedral":true}},"Q54572741":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"San Nicolas de Tolentino marker.jpg","width":548,"hash":"41","height":684},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Kapilya ni San Nicolas de Tolentino","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayong yari sa tisa at bato ng mga paring Agustino noong 1776 sa karangalan ni San Nicolas de Tolentino. Ginamit bilang barracks at imbakan ng mga gamit pandigma ng mga kawal Kastila noong panahon ng Himagsikan. Inayos, 1958–1960; muling inayos, pinaganda at pinalamutian ng mga mananampalataya ng La Huerta, 1993–1995. Sa kapilyang ito nagkaroon ng buhay ang makulay na pagdiriwang ng tradisyong sunduan at caracol na ngayo’y hinahangaan ng mga turistang dayuhan at lokal.</p>"}}},"address":"San Nicolas de Tolentino Chapel, San Nicolas Street, La Huerta, Parañaque, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Kapilya ni San Nicolas de Tolentino","lat":14.49999,"date":"1995-05-07","macroAddress":"Parañaque, Metro Manila","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.99355},"Q37727427":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Baler":"Baler, Aurora"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.5629,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Baler Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":996,"height":1471,"hash":"03"},"text":{"title":"Bayan ng Baler","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Lumang pamayanan sa barrio Sabang, bago dumating ang mga Espanyol. Itinatag bilang misyon ng mga paring Pransiskano, 1609. Nasira ng malalaking alon, 27 Disyembre 1735. Lumikas pansamantala ang mga mamamayan sa burol ng Ermita bago lumipat sa kasalukuyang pook. Naging kabisera ng distrit ng El Principe (ngayo’y Aurora), 1856. Pook na sinilangan ni Manuel Luis Quezon, 19 Agosto 1878. Sumiklab ang himagsikan, Iktubre 1897. Naganap sa simbahan ang pagkubkob ng mga rebolusyonaryo sa puwersang Espanyol, 27 Hunyo 1898 – 2 Hunyo 1899, na kinilala bilang mga kaibigan ng bisa ng dekreto ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo, 20 Hunyo 1899. Naging bahagi ng Tayabas (ngayo’y Quezon), 12 Hunyo 1902. Naging kabisera ng sub-province ng Aurora, 1951, at ng lalawigan ng Aurora, 1979.</p>"}}},"address":"Baler Municipal Hall, San Luis Street, Baler, Aurora","name":"Bayan ng Baler","region":"Central Luzon","date":"2009","macroAddress":"Baler, Aurora","lat":15.75908},"Q28973743":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.23237,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Fidel V. Ramos":"Fidel Ramos","Narciso Ramos":true,"Leticia Ramos-Shahani":true},"date":"1995","macroAddress":"Lingayen, Pangasinan","lat":16.0292,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":586,"hash":"b0","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Ramos House historical marker in Lingayen, Pangasinan (cropped).jpg","width":415},"text":{"inscription":"<p>For many years on this site was located the rented family house of Narciso Ramos (lawyer, journalist, statesman and diplomat) and Angela Valdez (former English supervisor of Pangasinan Vocational High School).</p><p>It was here that their eldest child Fidel, and first daughter Leticia, were born, raised and spent their formative years: Fidel, former Chief of Staff of the Armed Forces of the Philippines, former Secretary of National Defense and in 1992 elected 12th President of the Republic of the Philippines, Leticia Ramos Shahani, ambassador, senator and Senate President Pro-Tempore. Gloria Ramos da Rodda, their third child and a Philippine consul, was born in the Pangasinan Provincial Hospital in Dagupan.</p><p>The house was destroyed during World War II and the present structure, which now houses family mementos, was constructed in January 1995 through the donations of the Ramos Foundation and the Agpoon family.</p>","subtitle":"Lingayen, Pangasinan","title":"Ramos House"}}},"address":"Lingayen, Pangasinan","name":"Ramos House","region":"Ilocos Region"},"Q34999670":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Alburquerque Church":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.95751,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1059,"file":"Alburquerque Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","height":1495,"hash":"61"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nagsimula bilang bisita ng Baclayon sa ilalim ng patronato ni Santa Monica. Unang ipinatayo yari sa kahoy at kawayan sa kanlurang bahagi ng liwasan, 1842. Isang matibay at malawak na simbahan ang ipinatayo sa silangang bahagi, 1856. Humiwalay ang kinatatayuan sa bayan ng Baclayon at tinawag na Alburquerque, 1861. Pormal na pinasinayaan bilang parokya, 1869, at sumailalim sa pamamahala ng mga Rekoleto hanggang 1898. Sinimulan ni Padre Manuel Muro ang pagpapatayo ng simbahang bato, 1885. Ipinagawa ang itaas na bahagi ng pader at tore, dekada, 1920. Ipininta ni Ray Francia ang mga larawan sa kisame ng simbahan, 1932. Ang lagusang may nakahanay na mga arko ang nagdurugtong sa simbahan at kumbento na bukod-tangi sa Bohol.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Alburquerque"}}},"address":"Alburquerque Church, Alburquerque, Bohol","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Alburquerque","lat":9.61102,"macroAddress":"Alburquerque, Bohol","date":"2014"},"Q41080609":{"lat":14.59121,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"2000","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":743,"hash":"72","width":453,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"First Diocesan Seminary site historical marker in Manila.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Pook na Kinatatayuan ng Unang Seminaryong Diyosesano ng Pilipinas","inscription":"<p>Unang itinatag sa bisa ng dekreto ng Haring Felipe V na ipinalabas noong Abril 28, 1702 bilang seminaryong konsilyar na kaugnay ng Simbahang Metropolitan ng Maynila para sa walong katutubong seminarista. Ang seminaryo ay ipinatayo sa pamamahala ng Gobernador Heneral Domingo Zabalburu de Echavarri (1701–1709) at Don Diego Camacho y Avila, Arsobispo ng Maynila (1697–1706), sa dating tirahan ni Don Manuel Suarez de Oliveira sa likod ng Palasyo ng Gobernador Heneral subalit inilipat sa tapat ng Palasyo ng Arsobispo na pinagpagawaan ng isang malaking gusali. Ang seminaryo na pinangalang Real Colegio Seminario de San Clemente sa karangalan ng Papa Clemente XI ay pinasinayaan noong 1705 at ginamit ng 80 mag-aaral kabilang na yaong nagbuhat sa ibang mga bansa sa Asya.</p><p>Ipinasara ng hari noong 1706 dahil sa paglabag sa mga itinatadhana ng kanyang Dekreto ng 1702. Binigyan ng bagong pangalang Seminario de San Felipe noong Disyembre 31, 1712. Ang seminaryong ito ang pinagsimulan ng kasalukuyang Seminaryong Diyosesano ng San Carlos ng Arkidiyosesis ng Maynila. </p><p> Inalisan ng tabing noong yubileo ng mga seminarista, Setyembre 23, 2000.</p>"}}},"address":"Arzobispo Street cor. Postigo Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Ang Pook na Kinatatayuan ng Unang Seminaryong Diyosesano ng Pilipinas","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97241,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"San Carlos Seminary":true}},"Q40314230":{"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1990-08-04","lat":14.58743,"name":"Cuartel de Santa Lucia","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Cuartel de Santa Lucia, Santa Lucia Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Cuartel de Santa Lucia","subtitle":"(Santa Lucia Barracks)","inscription":"<p>On this site, Cuartel de la Artilleria de Montaña was built by Thomas Sanz, engineer of the Army during the administration of Governor General Jose Basco y Vargas, 1781. Used as barracks by the Philippine Constabulary, 1901. Became the Philippine Officers School, February 17, 1905. Here, the newly appointed Constabulary officers, studied a three-month course of instruction in law and Spanish language, in addition to military drill and constabulary administration. Transferred to Baguio City, 1908. Destroyed during World War II and from the remaining walls, the Philippine Constabulary reconstructed this barracks.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"b0","height":4608,"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Santa Lucia Barracks historical marker in Intramuros, Manila.jpg"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97481,"wikipedia":{"Cuartel de Santa Lucia":true},"locDesc":null},"Q55836839":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pook na Unang Pinaglibingan kay Heneral Artemio Ricarte (Vibora)","inscription":"<p>Dito unang inilibing ang mga labi ni Heneral Artemio Ricarte. Pinuno ng Katipunan. Unang kapitan heneral ng Hukbong Pilipino at kilala sa bansag na “Vibora.” Yumao, 31 Hulyo 1945. Hinukay at itinago sa isa sa mga yungib ng Hunduan, 1954; inilipat, 19 Setyembre 1977; inilibing sa Libingan ng mga Bayani, 22 Marso 1978. Muling hinukay, sinunog ang mga labi at hinati. Inilagay ang kalahati ng mga abo sa Libingan ng mga Bayani, 22 Marso 1977. Ang kalahati sa Pambansang Dambanang Ricarte, Batac, Ilocos Norte, 23 Marso 1997.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Hungduan Municipal Hall, Poblacion, Hungduan, Ifugao","name":"Pook na Unang Pinaglibingan kay Heneral Artemio Ricarte (Vibora)","region":"Cordillera Administrative Region","date":"2002","macroAddress":"Hungduan, Ifugao","lat":16.83847,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Artemio Ricarte":true},"lon":121.00542,"locPhoto":null},"Q37978616":{"lat":20.37428,"macroAddress":"Ivana, Batanes","date":"2014","address":"National Road, Ivana, Batanes","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Andres Bonifacio","subtitle":"(30 Nobyembre 1863 – 10 Mayo 1897)","inscription":"<p>Bayani at rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Tondo, Maynila, 30 Nobyembre 1863. Sumapi sa Masoneriya at La Liga Filipina, 1892. Nagtatag ng Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan o Katipunan, isang lihim na kilusan na ang pangunahing adhikain ay mapagkaisa ang lahat ng mga Pilipino at itaguyod ang isang bayang malaya sa pamamagitan ng paghihimagsik, 7 Hulyo 1892. Pinamunuan ang pagsisimula ng malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa mga Espanyol, Agosto 1896. Sumalakay sa San Juan del Monte upang kubkubin ang Polvorin, 30 Agosto 1896. Pinatay sa Maragondon, Cavite, 10 Mayo 1897. Kinikilala bilang Supremo ng Katipunan at Ama ng Himagsikan.</p>"},"photo":null}},"region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Andres Bonifacio","lon":121.91592,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Andres Bonifacio":"Andrés Bonifacio"}},"Q44504751":{"lat":14.59452,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"2014","region":"Metro Manila","name":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands","details":{"es":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"La Cámara de Comercio de las Islas Filipinas","inscription":"<p>Fundada como la Cámara de Comercio de Manila con el fin de promover el comercio y la industria en el país, 9 de Abril de 1886. Establecida de nuevo y registrada como la de Cámara de Comercio Filipina, 1903; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands, 1919; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippines, 1946; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippines Foundation Inc., 1979; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands, 2011. El actual edificio fue construido segun lo diseñado por Juan Arellano, 1937.</p>"},"photo":{"width":1232,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands Historical Marker (Spanish).jpg","height":2048,"hash":"95"}},"tl":{"photo":{"height":2048,"hash":"62","width":1232,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands Historical Marker (Filipino).jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang Camara de Comercio de Manila, 9 Abril 1886 upang mapaunlad ang komersyo at industriya sa bansa. Muling itinatag at itinala bilang korporasyon ng Camara de Comercio Filipina, 1903; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands, 1919; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippines, 1946; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippines Foundation Inc., 1979; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands, 2011. Itinayo ang kasalukuyang gusali na idinisenyo ni Juan Arellano, 1937.</p>","title":"Ang Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands","subtitle":null}},"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands","inscription":"<p>Founded as the Camara de Comercio de Manila to promote commerce and industry in the country, 9 April 1886. Reestablished and registered as a corporation of the Camara de Comercio Filipina, 1903; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands, 1919; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippines, 1946; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippines Foundation Inc., 1979; Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands, 2011. Present building constructed following the design of Juan Arellano, 1937.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"8a","height":2048,"file":"The Chamber of Commerce of the Philippine Islands Historical Marker (English).jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1232}}},"address":"3 Magallanes Drive, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.9762,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q23540785":{"lat":14.56613,"macroAddress":"Makati, Metro Manila","date":"1937","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":477,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Makati church marker.jpg","hash":"1f","height":515},"text":{"title":"San Pedro Macati","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The Franciscans were the first missionaries here in 1578. The Jesuits built this church in 1620 and administered it until 1768. Adjoining were the novitiate for the Jesuits and a house of retreat. Both the church and novitiate were dedicated to San Pedro in memory of the Rev. Pedro de los Montes, builder of the church, and of Captain Pedro de Britto, Regidor of Manila, who donated the site called Buenavista in 1607 and endowed the novitiate.</p>"}}},"address":"Makati Church, 5539 D.M. Rivera Street, Makati, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"San Pedro Macati","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.03134,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Makati Church":"San Pedro Macati Church"}},"Q24849237":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Malabrigo Lighthouse","inscription":"<p>Known as the Faro de Punta de Malabrigo, designed by Guillermo Brockman as cylindrical brick tower with metal staircase, adjacent pavilion and machine room, 1891. Built by the Chinese conractor Jose Garcia, 1896. An outstanding work of architecture from the Spanish colonial period, it has served as beacon to sea vessels at Verde Island Passage. Declared as National Historical Landmark, 27 November 2006.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Malabrigo Point Lighthouse, Brgy. Malabrigo, Lobo, Batangas","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Malabrigo Lighthouse","lat":13.59882,"date":"2007","macroAddress":"Lobo, Batangas","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.26247},"Q54670729":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Ladislao Bonus","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2304,"file":"Ladislao Bonus Historical Marker.JPG","credit":"Raani Paranas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"77","height":3072},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang “Ama ng Operang Pilipino”, dalubhasang musiko, kompositor at guro sa musika. Si Ladislao Bonus ay isinilang sa pook na ito noong ika-27 ng Hunyo 1854, kina Pedro Bonus at Maria Mariano. Maykatha ng unang operang Pilipino ang “Sandugong Panaginip” ni Pedro A. Paterno, naglapat ng tugtugin sa “Recuerdos a la Patria” ni Dr. Jose Rizal, at maykatha pa rin ng maraming tugtugin sa Sarsuelang Pilipino, misa, rosaryo kantada, gozo at mga kantahing-bayan na naging dahilan upang ang Pandacan ay kilalaning “Munting Italya ng Pilipinas.”</p><p> Siya ay namatay noong ika-28 ng Marso, 1908.</p>","subtitle":"(1854–1908)","title":"Ladislao Bonus"}}},"address":"1141 Teodoro San Luis Street, Pandacan, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59204,"macroAddress":"Pandacan, Manila","date":"1980","wikipedia":{"Ladislao Bonus":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the lower portion of the monument of Ladislao Bonus on the concrete fence of the residential property.","locPhoto":{"hash":"d0","height":3072,"file":"Birthplace of Ladislao Bonus in Pandacan.JPG","credit":"Raani Paranas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2304},"lon":121.00331},"Q28937459":{"lat":7.06462,"date":"2012","macroAddress":"Davao City","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"City Government of Davao","file":"Davao City Hall historical marker.jpg","width":709,"hash":"b0","height":960},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Davao City Hall","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo bilang gusaling munisipal ng Davao, 1926. Nilagdaan ni Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon ang Commonwealth Act No. 51 na bumuo sa Karta ng Lungsod ng Davao, 16 Oktubre 1936. Pinasinayaan ni Kalihim Elpidio Quirino ang Karta sa harapan ng gusali, 1 Marso 1937. Nasira nong panahon ng digmaan, 1945. Muling ipinatayo ayon sa orihinal na disenyo, 1947. Sentro ng pamahalaan sa pagtaguyod ng Davao bilang pangunahing lungsod sa silangang bahagi ng Mindanao noong panahon ng mga Amerikano.</p>"}}},"address":"Davao City Hall, San Pedro Street, Davao City","region":"Davao Region","name":"Davao City Hall","lon":125.60793,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Davao City":true}},"Q51168711":{"lon":120.9633,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lat":14.95816,"macroAddress":"San Rafael, Bulacan","date":"1997-11-30","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa San Rafael","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito naganap noong ika-30 ng Nobyembre 1896 ang isa sa pinakamadugong labanan sa lalawigan ng Bulakan sa pagitan ng mga Katipunero na pinamumunuan ni Heneral Anacleto Enriquez (Matanglawin) at ng mga kawal na Kastila sa pamumuno naman ni Tinyente Koronel Lopez Arteaga. Sa pagkapawi ng usok ng putukan, tinatayang may 800 katao sa panig ng mga Pilipino ang sinamang-palad na namatay kabilang na rito si Matanglawin at iba pang mga Katipunero na nakipaglaban para sa kalayaan hanggang sa huling sandali.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"d6","height":741,"file":"Battle of San Rafael (Bulacan) historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":618}}},"address":"San Juan de Dios Church, San Rafael, Bulacan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Labanan sa San Rafael"},"Q26709080":{"wikipedia":{"Noli Me Tángere":"Noli Me Tángere (novel)","José Rizal":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":8.75882,"name":"José Rizal","region":"Overseas","details":{"de":{"text":{"subtitle":"1861–1896 Nationalheld der Philippinen","title":"José Rizal","inscription":"<p>[Rizal] verfasste den letzten Teil seines Romans “Noli Me Tangere” in diesem Haus, während er Gast von Pfarrer Ullmer war 1886</p>"},"photo":{"height":3681,"hash":"42","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"José Rizal historical marker in Wilhelmsfeld.jpg","width":2573}}},"address":"José-Rizal-Straße 17, Wilhelmsfeld, Rhein-Neckar, Baden-Württemberg, Germany","macroAddress":"Wilhelmsfeld, Germany","date":"1960-01-04","lat":49.47027},"Q54667416":{"lat":14.54208,"macroAddress":"Pasay, Metro Manila","date":"1961","region":"Metro Manila","name":"School for the Deaf and the Blind","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1907)","title":"School for the Deaf and the Blind","inscription":"<p>Pioneer school for the handicapped in the Philippines. Planned by Dr. David P. Barrows, Director of Education; organized by Miss Delia Delight Rice, principal teacher (1907–1923). It was established in the City of Manila where it remained until it was transferred to its present site in Pasay City, June 1923.</p><p>Leading institution for the education of the deaf and the blind in the Philippines.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"2620 F.B. Harrison Street, Pasay, Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.99537,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q43325425":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Punong Himpilan ng Hukbong Pampulisya ng Maynila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Punong Himpilan ng Hukbong Pampulisya ng Maynila NHCP Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1729,"hash":"ed","height":2577},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang unang pulisyang sibil ng Maynila sa bisa ng proklamasyon ni Gobernador William H. Taft, 5 Agosto 1901. Nagsilbing mga punong himpilan ang Escuela Municipal, Intramuros, 1901–1904; Bulwagang Lungsod ng Maynila, 1904–1946; Lumang Kulungan ng Bilibid, 1946–1949; at ang kasalukuyang himpilan mula 1949. Itinayo ang gusaling ito bilang South Police Station bago ang Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig; pinagkublian ng hukbong Hapones at naging lugar ng matinding labanan, 14–20 Pebrero 1945; at isinaayos sa pamamagitan ng Philippine Rehabilitation Act at itinalagang punong himpilan ng Hukbong Pampulisya ng Maynila, 1949.</p>","title":"Punong Himpilan ng Hukbong Pampulisya ng Maynila","subtitle":null}}},"address":"United Nations Avenue cor. San Marcelino Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.58339,"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"2017-08-07","wikipedia":{"Manila Police District":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98646},"Q46573020":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Jaime Sin":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.43162,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang kina Juan Sin at Maxima Lachica sa New Washington, Aklan, 31 Agosto 1928. Itinalagang pari, 3 Abril 1954; naglingkod bilang paring misyonero, Diyosesis ng Capiz, 1954–1957; unang rektor, St. Pius X Seminary, Roxas City, 1957–1967; Obispong Auksilyar ng Jaro, 1967; Arsobispo ng Jaro, 1972; Arsobispo ng Maynila, 1974, at Kardenal, 1976. Nagsilbing lider ispiritwal at tagapagtaguyod ng demokrasya sa Pilipinas noong panahon ng batas militar. Isa sa mga nanguna sa People Power ng 1986 at 2001. Ginawaran ng pamahalaang Pilipinas ng Legion of Honor, 1992; Order of Sikatuna, 1999; at Order of Lakandula, 2003. Nagretiro, 15 Setyembre 2003. Yumao, 21 Hunyo 2005.</p>","subtitle":"(1928–2005)","title":"Jaime Cardinal Sin"}}},"address":"M.A. Roxas Avenue cor. Oming Venus Avenue, New Washington, Aklan","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Jaime Cardinal Sin","lat":11.65106,"date":"2007","macroAddress":"New Washington, Aklan"},"Q54554882":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Amado Hernandez y Vera","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Tundo, Maynila, 13 Setyembre 1903. Makatang laureado, manunulat, mamamahayag at lider ng mga manggagawa. Ibinilanggo dahil sa bintang na rebelyon, 1951; pinawalang sala ng Kataas-taasang Hukuman, 1964. Mga katangi-tanging akda: <u>Isang Dipang Langit</u>, <u>Bayang Malaya</u>, <u>Mga Ibong Mandaragit</u>, at <u>Luha ng Buwaya</u>, na pawang isinulat samantalang nasa bilangguan. Ginawaran: Commonwealth Literary Awards, Palanca Awards (dalawang ulit), Journalism Award (NPC–ESSO), Republic Cultural Heritage Award, at Balagtas Award. Mga postumong gawad: Doktor sa Humanidad, <u>honoris causa</u>, U.P. at Tanglaw ng Lahi, Ateneo University. Pinarangalan bilang Pambansang Alagad ng Sining, 1973. Namatay, 24 Marso 1970.</p>","title":"Amado Hernandez y Vera","subtitle":"(1903–1970)"},"photo":{"hash":"07","height":3456,"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"AmadoV.Hernandezjf1214.JPG"}}},"address":"Plaza Hernandez, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.60754,"date":"1982","macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","wikipedia":{"Amado V. Hernandez":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96684},"Q48764447":{"locPhoto":{"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"975jfPampanga+Provincial Monuments Capitolfvf 08.JPG","hash":"90","height":4608},"lon":120.68722,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is installed upright in front of the bust of Hilario which is located to the right of the main entrance of the capitol building.","lat":15.02405,"date":"1982","macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Zoilo J. Hilario y Sangalang","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3456,"hash":"92","width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Zoilo J. Hilario historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Mambabatas, makata at tagapagtaguyod ng kagalingang panlipunan. Ipinanganak sa San Juan, San Fernando, Pampanga, 27 Hunyo 1892. Nag-aral para sa titulong batsilyer sa sining, Liceo de Manila, at batsilyer sa batas, Escuela de Derecho. Makatang laureado sa Kastila sa kanyang tulang “Alma Española”, 1917; at makatang laureado sa wikang Pampango sa kanyang tulang “Ing Babai”, 1918. Naglathala ng mga aklat ng tula: <u>Adelfas</u>, <u>Patria y Redencion</u>, <u>Himnos y Arengas</u> at <u>Bayung Sunis</u>. May-akda: <u>Ilustres Varones Filipino</u>s at ng unang “Tenancy Law”, 1932. Kagawad: Philippines Historical Committee at Institute of National Language. Nagharap ng pinakamaraming bilang ng mga panukalang batas na pinagtibay ng Lahislatura ng Pilipinas, 1931–1934. Hinirang na isa sa Sampung Katangi-tanging Mababatas, 1933, at Hukom ng Unang Dulungan, 1951. Namatay, 13 Hunyo 1963.</p>","title":"Zoilo J. Hilario y Sangalang","subtitle":"1892–1963"}}},"address":"Pampanga Provincial Capitol, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga"},"Q55276521":{"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Simbahan ng Baler","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":588,"hash":"cb","width":400,"file":"Baler Church in Aurora province historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayo sa nipa at kawayan ng mga paring Pransiskano sa Tibag (ngayo’y Sabang) sa pagtatangkilik ni San Luis Obispo de Tolosa, 1611. Inilipat sa pamamahala ng mga Rekoletos, 1658; muling ibinalik sa mga Pransiskano, 1703. Nawasak ng daluyong, Disyembre 27, 1735; inilipat sa kasalukuyag kinatatayuan at isang bagong simbahang yari sa bato ang naitayo. Dito, Si Manuel Luis Quezon, unang Pangulo ng Komonwelt ng Pilipinas ay bininyagan, 1878. Isang may 54 kataong garison ng mga Kastila ang kinubkub ng mga Pilipinong rebolusyonaryo, Hunyo 27, 1898 hanggang Hunyo 2, 1899. Napasailalim ng pamamahala ng mga sekular, 1899; muling ipinagawa ng Pangulo at Ginang Quezon, 1939; inilipat sa mga Karmelitas, 1947 at muling ibinalik sa mga sekular, 1983. </p><p> Ipinahayag na isang Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan Pebrero 29, 2000 sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973, na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974 at Bilang 1505, Hunyo 11, 1978.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Baler"}}},"address":"Baler Church, Rizal Street, Poblacion, Baler, Aurora","lat":15.75895,"macroAddress":"Baler, Aurora","date":"2000","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the left side of the church facade.","locPhoto":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Church facade in Baler, Aurora.jpg","width":2592,"hash":"37","height":1944},"lon":121.56226},"Q48370942":{"date":"2017-12-11","macroAddress":"Bautista, Pangasinan","lat":15.81022,"name":"Pook Kung Saan Sinulat ang “Filipinas”, Liriko ng Pambansang Awit","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito sinulat si Jose Palma y Velasquez ang tulang “Filipinas” na naging liriko sa wikang Espanyol ng Himno Nacional Filipina, ngayo’y pambansang awit ng Pilipinas. Nalathala sa pahayagang La Independecia, 3 Setyembre 1899. Ang nasabing pook ay itinatag bilang Munisipalidad ng Bautista noong 1900.</p>","title":"Pook Kung Saan Sinulat ang “Filipinas”, Liriko ng Pambansang Awit","subtitle":"Bautista, Pangasinan"},"photo":null}},"address":"Bautista, Pangasinan","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.47628,"wikipedia":{"Lupang Hinirang":true,"José Palma":true},"locDesc":null},"Q24849479":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.731,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":14.1903,"macroAddress":"Mauban, Quezon","date":"1939","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Church of Mauban","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>The town, successfully located at the Pinagbayanan, Balaybalay, and Soledad, was transferred to this site in 1647. The first church and the first convent, constructed in 1647, were demolished in 1769. The second church and the second convent were completed in 1773. The convent were badly damaged in the earthquake of 1830 and rebuilt between 1836 and 1945. The old church collapsed during the earthquakes of July, 1880. The present church was built in 1891. The belfry, constructed in 1773, was seriously damaged during the earthquakes of 1880 and the portion of which remained was partially destroyed again by the earthquake of August 20, 1937.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Mauban"}}},"address":"Mauban Church, Mauban, Quezon"},"Q46575606":{"lon":122.67928,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":10.74259,"date":"2003","macroAddress":"Buenavista, Guimaras","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Roca Encantada","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 14 August 2002</p>","title":"Roca Encantada","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Roca Encantada, Buenavista, Guimaras"},"Q52021836":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Claro M. Recto":true},"lon":120.99332,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Makabayan, estadista, hurista, parlamentaryo at manunulat kung saan ginugol ang pinakamahulugang bahagi ng kanyang buhay na naging huwaran ng kadakilaan, karangalan at pagpipitagan sa sariling kakayahan ng sambayanang Pilipino.</p>","title":"Tumira Dito si Claro Mayo Recto","subtitle":"(1890–1960)"},"photo":null}},"address":"1750 Leveriza Street cor. Fresno Street, Pasay, Metro Manila","name":"Tumira Dito si Claro Mayo Recto","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Pasay, Metro Manila","date":null,"lat":14.5588},"Q43633671":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97096,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"43","file":"Simon Tecson historical marker in San Miguel, Bulacan.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Koronel ng Hukbong Rebolusyonaryo sa Bulacan. Isinilang sa San Miguel de Mayumo, Bulacan, 5 Pebrero 1861. Lumagda sa Konstitusyon ng Biyak-na-Bato, 1897. Inatasan ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo na pamunuan ang pagkubkob ng puwersang Espanyol sa Simbahan ng Baler (ngayo’y sakop ng lalawigan ng Aurora), 1899. Lumagda sa kasunduan ng pagsuko ng mga Espanyol sa pangunguna ni Martin Cerezo, 2 Hunyo 1899. Lumaban sa Digmaang Filipino–Amerikano, 1899; sumuko, 12 Pebrero 1901. Ipinatapon sa Guam dulot ng hindi pagkilala sa pamahalaang Amerikano, 16 Hunyo 1901; nakabalik sa Pilipinas, Setyembre 1902. Yumao, 15 Nobyembre 1903.</p>","subtitle":"(1861–1903)","title":"Simon Tecson"}}},"address":"Rizal Street, San Miguel, Bulacan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Simon Tecson","lat":15.13866,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"San Miguel, Bulacan"},"Q43442579":{"macroAddress":"San Miguel, Bulacan","date":"1963-06-20","lat":15.14055,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang si Nicanor Abelardo sa pook na ito ng San Miguel, Bulakan, noong ika-7 ng Pebrero, 1893, anak na panganay nina Valentin Abelardo at Placida Sta. Ana. Nagtapos ng musika sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas noong 1921 at sa Chicago Musical College noong 1932. Sa bisa ng kanyang matitimyas na kundiman at mga himig na naglalarawan ng katutubong tanawin, si Abelardo ay tinaguriang “Makata ng Tugtugin” at kinikilalang pinakadakilang mangangatha ng tugtugin sa Pilipinas. Sa kanyang mga tugtugin ay lalong natampok ang “Nasaan ka Irog” at “Mutya ng Pasig.”</p><p> Yumao noong ika-21 ng Marso, 1934, sa Maynila.</p>","title":"Nicanor Abelardo at Sta. Ana","subtitle":"(1893–1934)"}}},"address":"146 Payawal Street, San Miguel, Bulacan","name":"Nicanor Abelardo at Sta. Ana","region":"Central Luzon","lon":120.97562,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Nicanor Abelardo":true}},"Q47721120":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.68679,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","lat":15.02468,"address":"Governor Macario Arnedo Park, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":635,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"HonorioVentura HistoricalMarker SanFernandoCityPampanga.jpg","height":831,"hash":"58"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pilantropo at lingkod bayan. Isinilang sa Bacolor, Pampanga, 30 Hulyo 1887. Nagtapos ng abogasya sa Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas, 1909; hinirang na gobernador ng lalawigan ng Pampanga, 1914. Nahalal nang dalawang termino bilang gobernador ng Pampanga, 1916–1919 at 1919–1921. Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Panloob matapos ng panunungkulan ni Felipe Agoncillo, 1925–1933. Nagpaaral ng mahihirap na mga mag-aaral kabilang si Diosdado P. Macapagal naging Pangulo ng Pilipinas (1961–1965). Yumao, 3 Setyembre 1940.</p>","subtitle":"(1887–1940)","title":"Honorio Ventura"}}},"name":"Honorio Ventura","region":"Central Luzon"},"Q29018378":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa Catubig","inscription":"<p>Dito nakipaglaban ang mga gerilyang Filipino sa puwersang Amerikano, 15-18 Abril 1900. Pinaligiran ng mga Filipino ang destakamento ng kalaban hanggang mapatalsik ang mga ito. Marami ang napatay samantalang tumakas ang naiwan hanggang nailigtas ng ibang pwersang Amerikano. Isa sa matagumpay na labanang naganap sa kasaysayan ng pambansang pagkilos para sa kalayaan noong panahon ng Digmaang Filipino-Amerikano.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Catubig, Northern Samar","name":"Labanan sa Catubig","region":"Eastern Visayas","macroAddress":"Catubig, Northern Samar","date":"2007","lat":12.40759,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Siege of Catubig":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":125.0545},"Q24845880":{"lat":13.94053,"macroAddress":"Balayan, Batangas","date":"2013-02-08","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1872–1963)","title":"Clemencia Castelo Lopez","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Balayan, Batangas, 23 Nobyembre 1872. Kasama ang kapatid na si Sixto, nagtungo sa Estados Unidos bilang panauhin ng American Anti-Imperialist League, 1902-1903. Nanawagan kay Pangulong Theodore Roosevelt para sa pagpapalaya ng kanyang mga kapatid at pagsalungat sa hindi makatarungang pagdakip sa mga ito, Marso 1902. Nagbigay ng testimonya sa Senado ng Estados Unidos upang tutulan ang pagsakop sa Pilipinas, 15 Marso 1902. Nagtalumpati sa pulong ng New England Women Suffrage Association, 29 Mayo 1902. Bumalik sa Pilipinas, 1904. Isa sa mga nanguna sa pagtatag ng Asociacion Feminista Filipina, 30 Hunyo 1905. Tagapagtaguyod ng karapatan ng mga kababaihan sa Pilipinas. Yumao 4 Hunyo 1963.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Balayan, Batangas","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Clemencia Castelo Lopez","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.73597,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q45312720":{"name":"Ladislao Diwa","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Ladislao Diwa","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Makabayan, anak nina Mariano Diwa at Cecilia Nocon. Ipinanganak sa San Roque, 27 Hunyo 1863. Kaanib sa Liga Filipina. Kasama nina Andres Bonifacio at Teodoro Plata sa pagtatatag ng Katipunan, 6 Hulyo 1892. Namuno sa isang sangay ng himagsikan, 1896, sa ilalim ni Heneral Mariano Trias. Nabilanggo sa Puersa Santiago; nakalaya matapos lagdaan ang kasunduan sa Biak-na-Bato, 1897. Nahalal na gubernador ng Kabite sa panahon ng unang Republika ng Pilipinas 1898. Namatay dito sa Karidad, Lunsod ng Kabite, 12 Marso 1930.</p>"}}},"address":"Ladislao Diwa Shrine, Cabuco Street cor. de Guzman Street, Caridad, Cavite City, Cavite","macroAddress":"Cavite City, Cavite","date":"1964-06-27","lat":14.47926,"wikipedia":{"Ladislao Diwa":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.89264,"locPhoto":null},"Q54860599":{"lon":120.9768,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"San Miguel Church":"San Miguel Arcangel Church (San Miguel, Bulacan)"},"lat":15.14067,"macroAddress":"San Miguel, Bulacan","date":"2018-05-03","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Agustino sa patronato ni San Miguel Arkanghel bilang visita ng Candaba, 1607. Naging visita ng Gapan at Macabebe, 1726–1872. Sinimulang itinayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan yari sa bato at ladrilyo sa panunungkulan ni Padre Juan Manuel Tombo, 1848 at natapos sa panahon ni Padre Francisco Arriola, 1869. Naging hiwalay na parokya, 1872. Dito nagkuta ang mga kawal na Espanyol sa ilalim ni Tenyente Telesforo Carrasco noong kasagsagan ng Labanan ng San Miguel de Mayumo, Mayo 1898. Sumuko sila sa mga Rebolusyonaryong Pilipino na pinamunuan ni Koronel Pablo Tecson sa plaza ng simbahan, 1 Hunyo 1898. Napinsala noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at isinaayos sa pangunguna ni Padre Honorio Resurreccion, 1941–1948. Muling kinumpuni, 2003.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng San Miguel de Mayumo"}}},"address":"San Miguel Church, Libertad Street cor. Victor Street, San Miguel, Bulacan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Simbahan ng San Miguel de Mayumo"},"Q28871691":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.14091,"wikipedia":{"San Joaquin Church":"San Joaquin Church (Iloilo)"},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"San Joaquin, Iloilo","date":"1980","lat":10.58593,"name":"Makasaysayang Simbahan ng San Joaquin","region":"Western Visayas","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1662,"file":"Simbahan ng San Joaquin historical marker.JPG","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"29","height":2149},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng pagpapatibay ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan noong Setyembre 22,1977 na binigyan ng karapatan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo ng Pilipinas bilang 260, Agosto 1,1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Makasaysayang Simbahan ng San Joaquin"}}},"address":"San Joaquin Church, San Joaquin, Iloilo"},"Q55717904":{"lat":14.625,"macroAddress":"Orion, Bataan","date":"2015-03-27","address":"Balagtas Park, Sitio Pag-asa, Brgy. Wawa, Orion, Bataan","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Francisco C. Baltazar (Balagtas)","subtitle":"1788–1862","inscription":"<p>Makata at manunulat ng ika-19 na siglo. Isinilang sa Panginay, Bigaa (ngayo’y Balagtas), Bulacan, 2 Abril 1788. May-akda ng “Florante at Laura,” 1838 at “Orosman at Zafira,” 1867–1870. Nagbigay inspirasyon sa mga bayani katulad nina Jose Rizal at Apolinario Mabini. Naging kawani ng lokal na huwes sa Maynila, 1840, bago lumipat sa Bataan bilang katulong ng kawani ng korte. Naging unang tenyente at tagapamahala ng taniman at pag-aani sa bayan ng Orion. Yumao, 20 Pebrero 1862.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2400,"file":"Francisco C. Baltazar (Balagtas) historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","height":3354,"hash":"c4"}}},"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Francisco C. Baltazar (Balagtas)","lon":120.58627,"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"6c","width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"09929jfDaang Fields Halls Balagtas Poblacion Orion Bataanfvf 08.JPG"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the monument pedestal of Francisco Baltazar facing Manila Bay.","wikipedia":{"Francisco Balagtas":true}},"Q28858156":{"lon":120.99945,"locPhoto":{"hash":"31","height":972,"file":"Justo Takayama monument and historical marker at Plaza Dilao.jpg","credit":"noel Gonong (Wikipedia Takes Manila participant) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1340},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the southwest of the Takayama monument.","wikipedia":{"Dom Justo Takayama":true,"Plaza Dilao":true},"date":"1992","macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","lat":14.5808,"address":"Plaza Dilao, Quirino Avenue Extension, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"80","height":640,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Takayama Marker.jpg","width":480},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pinuno ng unang pangkat ng mga maharlikang Hapon na Kristiyano na ipinatapon sa Pilipinas noong 1614, nang ipinagbawal ng Hapon ang Kristiyanismo. Mahigit sa 100 kagawad ng maharlikang angkan ng Hapon na naging Kristiyano, kabilang ang Lord Juan Tokuan Naito, at ang mga kagawad ng unang Kongregasyong Katoliko ng kababaihan sa Hapon sa pangunguna ni Priyora Julia Naito, ay malugod na tinanggap sa Maynila ng magigiliw na pilipino na kanilang nakasama sa ilalim ng isang bigkis ng kapatirang Kristiyano. Ang mga Kristiyanong Hapon ay nanatili sa Pilipinas hanggang sa sila ay lubusang mapabilang sa madlang Pilipino. </p><p> Ang Liwasang Dilao na kinatatayuan ng bantayog na ito ay gumugunita sa bayan ng Dilao (ngayo'y Paco), ang unang purok ng Hapon sa Maynila.</p>","title":"Lord Justo Ukon Takayama","subtitle":"(1552–1615)"}}},"name":"Lord Justo Ukon Takayama","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q50413542":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Siquijor","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang parokya ng mga paring sekular sa patronato ni San Francisco de Asis noong Pebrero 1, 1783. Inilipat sa mga paring Rekoleto noong 1793. Sinimulan ni P. Setten, isang sekular, ang pagpapatayo ng simbahang bato na pinangasiwaan ni P. Alonso de los Dolores noong 1795–1831. Ipinagawa ang kumbento na katulad ng isang kuta upang malabanan ang madalas na pagsalakay ng mga tulisang-dagat.</p>"}}},"address":"Siquijor Church, Santa Fe Street, Siquijor","name":"Simbahan ng Siquijor","region":"Central Visayas","macroAddress":"Siquijor, Siquijor","date":"1984-05-19","lat":9.21539,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.51397},"Q23821137":{"wikipedia":{"Palacio del Gobernador":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.97274,"locPhoto":null,"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Former Palace of the Governors General","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Historical marker Palacio del Gobernador.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":960,"hash":"e3","height":720},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Former Palace of the Governors General","inscription":"<p>This site was formerly occupied by the stately residence of Captain Manuel Estacio Venegas, Secretary to Governor General Diego Fajardo. Venegas died on March 7, 1660, a prisoner at Fort Santiago. His residence was confiscated and became the Palace of the Governors of the Philippine Islands until its destruction by the earthquake of June 3, 1863. These foundations, intended for the new gubernatorial palace, were abandoned when it was decided to make Malacañan the permanent residence of the Governors General.</p>"}}},"address":"Palacio del Gobernador, General Luna Street cor. Andres Soriano Jr. Avenue, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59185,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1936"},"Q41079362":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97248,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Manila":"Battle of Manila (1945)"},"date":"1989-02-03","macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","lat":14.59101,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ang Pagpapalaya ng Maynila","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ang paglunsad ng hukbong Amerikano sa Lingayen Enero 3, 1945 ang simula ng paglaya ng Maynila at mga karatig pook sa Gitnang Luzon. Pinangunahan ng ika-37 Impanteriya na pinalakas ng Unang Kabalyaria at mga gerilyang Pilipino ang pagsalakay sa Maynila noong Pebrero 3, 1945. Ang madugong labanang naganap ay naging sanhi ng pagkamatay ng libu-libong mamamayan at pagkasira ng maraming gusali sa Intramuros at sa ibang panig ng lunsod.</p>"},"photo":{"width":1472,"file":"Pagpapalaya sa Maynila historical marker (cropped).jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"0c","height":2053}}},"address":"Postigo Street cor. Arzobispo Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Ang Pagpapalaya ng Maynila","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q52266526":{"region":"Ilocos Region","name":"The Battle of San Fernando","address":"San Fernando City Plaza, MacArthur Highway cor. F. Ortega Highway, San Fernando, La Union","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":3456,"file":"SanFernandoCityLaUnionjf9870 12.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"55","height":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The Battle of San Fernando began with assault on the Japanese position along the south bank of the Baroro River, Bacnotan, La Union, by the 121st Infantry USAFIP, NL, on 4 January 1945, followed by the seizure of enemy strongholds south of Baroro and the concerted attack on enemy strong points situated along Oaig Creek where it crossed the San Fernando–Camansi Road, on Reservoir Hill and Insurrecto Hill and on the Bacsil–Apaleng Range on the second week of February. By 24 March 1945 the entire San Fernando area was secured and enabled the establishment at Poro Peninsula the headquarters of U.S. Army Base M, Build-up area for the projected invasion of Japan.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"The Battle of San Fernando"}}},"lat":16.61617,"date":"1959","macroAddress":"San Fernando, La Union","wikipedia":{"Battle of Luzon":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal facing away from the highway.","locPhoto":{"file":"SanFernandoCityLaUnionjf9870 15.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"c1"},"lon":120.31685},"Q46546191":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":124.19542,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Escuela Pia ng Prieto–Diaz","inscription":"<p>Itinayo na gawa sa kurales sa ilalim ng mga Kastila ayon sa arkitektura ng Escuela Pia noong ikalabinsiyam na dantaon. Ipinagpatuloy bilang paaralang pambayan noong panahon ng mga Amerikano at ngayo’y kabilang sa mga gusali ng Prieto–Diaz Central School. Isinaayos nang masira ng Bagyong Reming, 2006 ng GMA Kapuso Foundation Inc., bilang bahagi ng programang “Unang Hakbang sa Kinabukasan,” 2007.</p>"}}},"address":"Prieto Diaz Central School, Prieto Diaz, Sorsogon","name":"Ang Escuela Pia ng Prieto–Diaz","region":"Bicol Region","macroAddress":"Prieto Diaz, Sorsogon","date":"2002","lat":13.03975},"Q55507213":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":118.73722,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":9.74005,"macroAddress":"Puerto Princesa","date":"2011","region":"Mimaropa","name":"Higinio A. Mendoza","address":"Mendoza Park, Rizal Avenue cor. H. Mendoza Street, Puerto Princesa","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker of Higinio Mendoza.JPG","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2265,"height":3405,"hash":"59"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1898–1944)","title":"Higinio A. Mendoza","inscription":"<p>Lingkod bayan at manggagamot. Isinilang sa Puerto Princesa, Palawan, 27 Hulyo 1898. Naglingkod bilang gobernador ng Palawan, 1931–1937. Nagtatag ng Mendoza Guerilla Unit, 21 Enero 1942. Tumulong sa paglikas ng mga taong-bayan at nakipaglaban sa mga Hapon. Dinakip ng mga Hapon sa Tinitian, Puerto Princesa (ngayo’y bayan ng Roxas), 6 Enero 1944. Hinatulong mamatay sa Canigaran, Puerto Princesa, 24 Enero 1944.</p>"}}}},"Q41326209":{"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"LagunaAjf9944 21.JPG","height":3456,"hash":"47"},"lon":121.45621,"wikipedia":{"Conrado Benitez":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located in front on the Benitez House along Gen. Taino Street.","lat":14.27385,"macroAddress":"Pagsanjan, Laguna","date":"1982","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Conrado Benitez y Francia","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Conrado Benitez historical marker in Pagsanjan, Laguna.jpg","hash":"ee","height":4608},"text":{"title":"Conrado Benitez y Francia","subtitle":"(1889–1971)","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Pagsanjan, Laguna, 26 Nobyembre 1889. Unang dekanong Pilipino, Kolehiyo ng Malalayang Sining, University of the Philippines, 1918; tagapagtatag, Philippine Columbian Association, 1909; unang patnugot, The Philippine Herald, 1920. May-akda at tagapaglathala History of the Philippines, tagapagtatag at dekano, Kolehiyo ng Pamahalaang Pangalakal, U.P., 1926. Kinatawan ng Laguna at isa sa pitong pantas na bumalangkas sa Konstitusyon ng Pilipinas, 1935; at konsehal, Lungsod ng Quezon, 1959. Tumanggap ng Gawad Rizal Pro Patria at Knight Grand Cross of Rizal, 1969. Namatay, 4 Enero 1971.</p>"}}},"address":"Gen. Taino Street, Pagsanjan, Laguna"},"Q30097887":{"macroAddress":"Cabanatuan, Nueva Ecija","date":"1990","lat":15.48652,"address":"Lazaro Francisco Elementary School, Zulueta Street, Cabanatuan, Nueva Ecija","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":4128,"hash":"e4","file":"Lazaro Francisco historical marker.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3096},"text":{"subtitle":"(1898–1980)","title":"Lazaro Francisco","inscription":"<p>Makabayan, pangunahing nobelista sa Panitikang Pilipino. Isinilang sa Orani, Bataan, Pebrero 22, 1898. Lumaki sa Cabanatuan at nagsulat ng nobela sa bayang ito mula 1925. Mahalagang bahagi ng kanyang panulat ang pakikisangkot sa mga suliraning tumutukoy sa kapakanan ng bansa. Tagapagtatag ng Kapatiran ng mga Alagad ng Wikang Pilipino (KAWIKA), 1958. Tampok sa mga tinanggap niyang gawad: Republic Cultural Heritage Award, 1970; Patnubay ng Kalinangan, Maynila, 1975; Dangal ng Lahi, Lungsod ng Quezon, 1976; Tanglaw ng Lahi, Ateneo de Manila, 1979. Sa kanyang alaala ang Cabanatuan West Central School ay pinangalanan noong 1987 ng \"Paaralang Elementaryang Lazaro Francisco.\" Namatay noong Hunyo 17, 1980.</p>"}}},"name":"Lazaro Francisco","region":"Central Luzon","lon":120.95902,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Lazaro Francisco":"Lázaro Francisco"}},"Q52861421":{"lon":120.99117,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"MendiolaStreetjf2529 14.JPG","width":3456,"hash":"e1","height":4608},"wikipedia":{"Mendiola Street":true,"First Quarter Storm":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is attached to a concrete pedestal facing the street intersection.","lat":14.6002,"date":"2012","macroAddress":"San Miguel, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Kalye Mendiola","address":"Mendiola Street cor. Claro M. Recto Avenue and B. Legarda Street, San Miguel, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinangalan kay Enrique Mendiola, abogado’t edukador, itinalagang direktor ng Instituto Burgos, sekundaryang paaralan ng Republikang Malolos. Naging simbolo ng kilusang protesta laban sa paniniil sa iba’t-ibang panahon ng kasaysayang pangkasalukuyan, pinakatampok ang labanan sa Mendiola, 30 Enero 1970, at ang paglaban sa Batas Militar, 1972–1986, na karaniwang binuwag ng bomba ng tubig at tear gas. Sinarhan sa ilalim ng Batas Militar. Nabuksan ng pag-aalsa ng mamamayan, binaklas ang tinikang kawad, 25 Febrero 1986. Nananatiling lansangan ng protestang bayan.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Kalye Mendiola"},"photo":{"file":"Mendiola Street historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"97"}}}},"Q22342220":{"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Pila, Laguna","lat":14.23396,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Pila historical marker.jpg","width":2500,"height":2729,"hash":"14"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Rev. Juan de Florencia, O.F.M. was the first priest to minister to this town in 1578.The first Church and the first Convent were completed 1616. The town was transferred from Pagalangan to the present site in 1800 to avoid frequent floods. The present Church was built at the beginning of the 19th century and the Convent was completed in 1849, both having been seriously damaged by the earthquakes of 1880. A rest-house for the sick Franciscan Missionaries was maintained in this town from 1618 to 1673. The Franciscans established here in 1606 a printing press under the printers Tomas Pinpin and Domingo Loag.</p>","title":"Church of Pila","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Pila Church, Pila, Laguna","name":"Church of Pila","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"71","file":"PilaChurchjf3816 03.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608},"lon":121.3644,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the columns immediately to the right of the main entrance of the church.","wikipedia":{"Pila Church":"San Antonio de Padua Parish Church (Pila)"}},"Q40176326":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Site of the Proclamation of Philippine Independence","inscription":"<p>On June 12, 1898, Philippine independence was proclaimed from the center window of the original house of the family of General Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy, President of the First Philippine Republic and leader of the revolution against Spain and America. Through the reading of the Acta de la proclamacion de la independencia del pueblo Filipino by Ambrosio Rianzares Bautista. During this occasion, the Philippine flag made in Hongkong by Doña Marcela Marino de Agoncillo was officially unfurled as the band of San Francisco de Malabon proudly played the Marcha Nacional Filipina (now the Philippine National Anthem) composed by Julian Felipe.</p><p>This historical marker is installed by the grateful Filipino people in observance of the centennial of the proclamation of Philippine independence. Unveiled by His Excellency President Fidel Valdez Ramos on June 12, 1998.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Site of the Proclamation of Philippine Independence historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2500,"hash":"5b","height":3688}},"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Noong Hunyo 12, 1898. Buhat sa gitnang bintana ng orihinal na tahanan ng mga Aguinaldo ipinahayag ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy, pangulo ng unang Republika ng Pilipinas at puno ng himagsikan laban sa Espanya at sa Amerika, ang kasarinlan ng Pilipinas sa pamamagitan ng pagbasa ng Acta de la proclamacion de la independencia del pueblo Filipino na sinulat ni Ambrosio Rianzares Bautista. Sa pagkakataong ito, ang watawat ng Pilipinas na tinahi ni Donya Marcela Marino de Agoncillo sa Hongkong ay opisyal na iwinagayway habang buong pagmamalaking tinutugtog ng banda ng San Francisco de Malabon ang Marcha Nacional Filipina (ngayo’y Pambansang Awit ng Pilipinas) na kinatha ni Julian Felipe.</p><p>Ang tandang pangkasaysayang ito ay iniaalay ng Sambayanang Pilipino sa pagdiriwang ng ikasandaang taon ng pagpapahayag ng kasarinlan ng Pilipinas. Inalisan ng tabing ng Kagalang-galang na Pangulong Fidel Valdez Ramos noong Hunyo 12, 1898.</p>","title":"Pook ng Pagpapahayag ng Kasarinlan ng Pilipinas","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":3692,"hash":"89","file":"Pook ng Pagpapahayag ng Kasarinlan ng Pilipinas historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2500}}},"address":"Aguinaldo Shrine, Kawit Loop Road, Kawit, Cavite","name":"Site of the Proclamation of Philippine Independence","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Kawit, Cavite","date":"1998-06-12","lat":14.44511,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Aguinaldo Shrine":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.90661},"Q55739838":{"macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","date":"1967","lat":15.02646,"name":"Death March","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"photo":{"file":"DeathMarch HistoricalMarker SanFernandoCityPampanga.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":397,"hash":"c9","height":446},"text":{"tl":{"title":null,"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa himpilang daang-bakal na ito ng San Fernando, ang mga bihag ng dimang kawal Pilipino at Amerikano, matapos piliting maglakad mula Bataan hanggang Pampanga sa pinaka-nakapanghihilakbot na paglalakbay sa kasaysayan ng daigdig, ay sala-salansang isinakay sa mga bagon ng tren ng masahol pa sa mga hayop. Marami ang hindi na nakarating sa patutunguhan at nangamatay sa daan.</p>"},"en":{"inscription":"<p>At this railroad station of San Fernando, the Filipino and American prisoners of war who had been marched all the way from Bataan to Pampanga, in one of the ghastliest forced marches in history, were loaded like cattle on boxcars, where, because every compartment was packed to the limit, many suffocated or were crushed to death during the trip to Capas.</p>","title":"Death March","subtitle":"April 1942"}}},"address":"Brgy. Santo Niño, San Fernando, Pampanga","lon":120.68672,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Bataan Death March":true},"locDesc":null},"Q43302099":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the facade to the right of the main entrance of Malcolm Hall.","wikipedia":{"University of the Philippines College of Law":true},"lon":121.07214,"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"e6","file":"UPDilimanjf2829 06.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608},"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Inorganisa sa inisyatiba ni George A. Malcolm sa tulong ng mga Young Men’s Christian Association, 1910. Itinatag sa bisa ng resolusyon ng Lupon ng mga Rehente ng Unibersidad ng Pilipinas, 12 Enero 1911. Sherman Moreland, dekano, 1911; George Malcolm, dekano, 1911–1917. Jorge Bocobo, unang Pilipinong dekano, 1917–1934. Nagsara noong digmaan, 13 Disyembre 1941; muling nagbukas, 6 Agosto 1945. Inilipat sa Diliman Campus, 1948.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"University of the Philippines College of Law"},"photo":{"hash":"7b","height":3395,"width":2500,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"University of the Philippines College of Law historical marker.jpg"}}},"address":"University of the Philippines College of Law, Osmeña Avenue cor. F. Ma. Guerrero Street, Diliman, Quezon City, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"University of the Philippines College of Law","lat":14.65642,"date":"2012","macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila"},"Q24081292":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1946,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Simbahan ng San Carlos historical marker.jpg","height":2786,"hash":"3d"},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng San Carlos","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ang simbahang gawa sa ladrillo ay sinimulang itatag noong 1770 sa pamamahala ni P. Ausina, sa pook na ito kung saan inilipat ang kabayanang Binalatongan, na pinangalanang San Carlos noong 1764. Pinakamalaking simbahan sa Pilipinas sa panahong iyon. Napinsala ng lindol noong 1789, 1796 at 1799. Ang pagtatayo ng kampanaryo at pagsasagawa ng mga pagbabago ay pinamahalaan ni Padre Alvarez Carrozal, 1878-1890.</p>"}}},"address":"Saint Dominic de Guzman Parish Church, San Carlos, Pangasinan","name":"Simbahan ng San Carlos","region":"Ilocos Region","macroAddress":"San Carlos, Pangasinan","date":"1989-08-08","lat":15.92594,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Saint Dominic de Guzman Parish Church":"Saint Dominic de Guzman Parish Church (San Carlos)"},"lon":120.34719,"locPhoto":null},"Q43282120":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.83924,"region":"Mimaropa","name":"Maharlikang Tahanan ni Kapitan Piroco","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Maharlikang Tahanan ni Kapitan Piroco","inscription":"<p>Ari ng Kapitan Munisipal Pedro Lardizabal, lalong kilala sa taguring Kapital Piroco. Dito nakipagpanayam si William H. Taft, tagapangulo ng Komisyon ng Pilipinas, sa mga tanyag na mamamayan noong ika-13 ng Marso, 1901. Sa pamamagitan ni Eduardo Nepomuceno, tagapagsalita, hiniling nilang ang Marinduque ay maging hiwalay na lalawigan. Ang pamahalaang sibil ng lalawigan ay itinatag dito ni Ricardo Paras, Sr., ang unang gobernador. Itinalaga siya sa tungkulin ni W. H. Taft.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"house of Pedro Lardizabal, Governor D. Reyes Street cor. Magsaysay Drive, Boac, Marinduque","lat":13.44835,"macroAddress":"Boac, Marinduque","date":"1973-02-23"},"Q28919950":{"lat":8.47626,"date":"2000","macroAddress":"Cagayan de Oro","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinagawa noong 1882 na yari sa ladrilyong inangkat sa Timog Tsina ni Sia Ygua noong Enero 10, 1899. Nagtipun-tipon sa harapan ng bahay na ito ang mga kalahok sa maringal na parada sa Cagayan de Misamis bilang pagkilala sa pamahalaang rebolusyonaryo ni Heneral Aguinaldo. Sinakop at inokupahan ng ika-40 rehimiyento ng mga boluntaryo ng Estados Unidos. Nilusob ng batalyong Mindanao sa pamumuno ni Heneral Nicolas Capistrano na nagtangkang palayain ang Cagayan de Misamis noong Abril 7, 1900. Maraming Pilipinong manghihimagsik ang napatay sa bahay na ito noong labanan sa Cagayan de Misamis at inilibong sa likod bahay nito.</p>","title":"Casa del Chino Ygua","subtitle":"(Balay nga Bato)"},"photo":{"file":"Casa del Chino Ygua Marker.JPG","credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1764,"height":2332,"hash":"ff"}}},"address":"Casa del Chino Ygua, Cagayan de Oro","region":"Northern Mindanao","name":"Casa del Chino Ygua","locPhoto":null,"lon":124.64412,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q23677499":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.90243,"wikipedia":{"Bank of the Philippine Islands":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":10.29353,"macroAddress":"Cebu City","date":"2010-12-02","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Bank of the Philippine Islands (BPI)","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":1366,"hash":"e4","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Bank of the Philippine Islands Cebu historical marker 2 (cropped).jpg","width":1102},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa panulukan ng Calle Jakosalem at Cuenco sa Lungsod ng Cebu bilang pangatlong sangay ng B.P.I. sa labas ng Maynila, 1924. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang gusali na ipinatayo ayon sa disenyo ni Juan M. Arellano, 1941. Isinailalim sa pamamahala ng mga puwersang Hapones noong panahon ng digmaan, 1942–1945. Ipinaayos, 1947. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 24 Setyembre 1991.</p>","title":"Bank of the Philippine Islands (BPI)","subtitle":null}}},"address":"BPI Cebu Main branch, Cebu City"},"Q43227562":{"wikipedia":{"Horacio de la Costa":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":121.07691,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Horacio de la Costa, S.J.","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2500,"file":"Horacio de la Costa, S.J. historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","hash":"6d","height":3642},"text":{"subtitle":"1916–1977","title":"Horacio de la Costa, S.J.","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Mauban, Quezon, 9 Mayo 1916. Nagtapos ng kursong Batsilyer ng Sining sa Ateneo de Manila, summa cum laude, 1935, at ng Doktorado sa Pilosopiya sa Harvard University, 1951. Nagsilbing unang dekano ng Kolehiyo ng Sining at Agham ng Ateneo de Manila, 1953–1955, unang Pilipinong puno ng Society of Jesus sa Pilipinas, 1964–1970, at katulong pangkalahatan at tagapayo ng mga Heswita sa Roma, 1970–1975. Dahil sa mga akdang pangkasaysayan, ginawaran ng Republic Cultural Heritage Award, 1965. Kagawad ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan, 1967–1977. Yumao, 20 Marso 1977.</p>"}}},"address":"Ateneo School of Humanities, University Road, Quezon City, Metro Manila","date":"2017","macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","lat":14.64007},"Q56065902":{"lon":123.61957,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lat":10.01694,"macroAddress":"Sibonga, Cebu","date":"2010","address":"Sibonga Church, National Road cor. R. Bacaltos Street, Sibonga, Cebu","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang visita ng Carcar ng mga misyonerong Agustino, 1690. Naging parokya sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora del Pilar de Zaragoza, 1830. Ipinagawa ang unang simbahan yari sa kahoy at nipa, ayon sa disenyo ni Obispo Santos Gomez Marañon ng Cebu. Ipinatayo ni Padre Prospero Puerto ang kumbento yari sa bato at korales, 1839, at sinimulan ang pagpapatayo ng kasalukuyang simbahan yari sa bato at korales sa arkitekturang Neo-Gothic, 1866. Ipinagpatuloy nina Padre Juan Alonso, 1868–1881; Enrique Magaz, 1881–1890; Emiliano Diez, 1890–1898. Muling ipinaayos ang simbahan ni Padre Francisco Latorre at pinasinayaan ni Arsobispo Jeremias Harty ng Maynila, 17 Nobyembre 1907. Ginawa ni Raymundo Francia ng Cebu ang mga obrang bibliko at trompe l’oeil sa kisame ng simbahan, 1924.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Sibonga","subtitle":null}}},"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Sibonga"},"Q55299857":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BayChurchjf4044 11.JPG","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"d1"},"lon":121.28435,"wikipedia":{"St. Augustine Parish Church":"San Agustin Parish Church (Bay, Laguna)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade to the left of the main entrance.","date":"1985-08-28","macroAddress":"Bay, Laguna","lat":14.18085,"name":"Simbahan ng Bay","region":"Calabarzon","address":"St. Augustine Parish Church, Jose Rizal Avenue cor. J. Tanaleda Street, Bay, Laguna","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni Reb. P. Martin de Rada, paring Agustino, sa Aplaya noong 1571 sa ilalim ng patronato ni San Agustin. Naging parokya noong Abril 30, 1578. Inilipat ang pangangasiwa sa mga paring Pransiskano at naging unang kura paroko si Reb. P. Domingo Martorel, 1737. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan sa Poblacion sa pamamahala ni Reb. P. Geronimo Hervas at Reb. Pedro Moya, 1804. Nasira ang batong simbahan noong pananakop ng mga Hapon, 1944–1945. Muling ipinatayo ni Reb. Alejandro Vermorel, 1953. Nasakupan ng Diyosesis ng San Pablo mula noong Abril 16, 1967.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Bay"},"photo":{"height":575,"hash":"84","width":432,"file":"Ba-y Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}}},"Q24012063":{"lat":14.48121,"date":"2014-02-28","macroAddress":"Las Piñas, Metro Manila","address":"Las Piñas Church, P. Diego Cera Avenue, Las Piñas, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":2656,"hash":"a6","file":"Simbahan ng Parokya ng San Jose, Las Piñas historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2804},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan sa bisa ng Resolusyon Blg. 08 ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 15 Hulyo 2013.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Parokya ng San Jose, Las Piñas"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Simbahan ng Parokya ng San Jose, Las Piñas","locPhoto":{"width":3000,"file":"Simbahan ng Parokya ng San Jose, Las Piñas historical marker location.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"48","height":4000},"lon":120.98155,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the church.","wikipedia":{"Las Piñas Church":true}},"Q52984975":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Mansyong Pamintuan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni Mariano Pamintuan noong mga taong 1890. Naging punong himpilan ng Tanggulan ng Republika ng Pilipinas laban sa puwersang Amerikano, Mayo 1899. Nagsilbing pansamantalang tanggapan ni Pangulong Emilio Aguinaldo habang inihahanda ang Tarlac bilang kabisera ng Republika, Hunyo 1899. Sa tapat nito idinaos ang paradang militar noong bisperas ng unang anibersayo ng Proklamasyon ng Kalayaan ng Pilipinas, 1899. Naging himpilan ni Heneral Arthur MacArthur, Agosto 1899. Tahanan ng mga Pilipinong kamikaze ng hukbong panghimpapawid ng Hapon, 1944–1945. Pinaupahan bilang Angeles Hotel, 1948. Binili ni Pedro Tablante mula sa pamilyang Pamintuan, 1959. Naging ekstensiyon ng bahay-pamahalaan ng Angeles, 1964. Binili ng Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas ang lote habang ipinagkaloob ng pamilyang Tablante ang bahay upang ayusin ng pamahalaan, 1981. Isinalin sa Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 17 Hunyo 2010. Pinasinayaan ang Museo ng Kasaysayang Panlipunan ng Pilipinas, 24 Agosto 2015.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2034,"file":"Mansyong Pamintuan historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","height":3000,"hash":"71"}}},"address":"Pamintuan Mansion, Santo Entierro Street cor. Miranda Street, Angeles","name":"Mansyong Pamintuan","region":"Central Luzon","macroAddress":"Angeles","date":"2017-08-17","lat":15.13561,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a post at the entrance gate to the museum.","wikipedia":null,"lon":120.59127,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"1405Pamintuan Mansion Angeles, Pampanga 36.jpg","hash":"fa","height":3456}},"Q24702505":{"address":"Lucban Church, Lucban, Quezon","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":2592,"credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"St. Louis Bishop Parish Marker Lucban, Quezon.JPG","height":1944,"hash":"15"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Lucban","inscription":"<p>The first church, built in 1595, was ruined in 1629. The second church was constructed between 1630 and 1640, but was seriously damaged by fire in 1733. The present church was completed in 1738 and the convent in 1743.</p>"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Church of Lucban","lat":14.11503,"macroAddress":"Lucban, Quezon","date":"1939","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Lucban Church":true},"lon":121.55397,"locPhoto":null},"Q51924068":{"date":"1974-12-27","macroAddress":"Antipolo, Rizal","lat":14.58719,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1874–1942)","title":"Juan M. Sumulong","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Antipolo, Rizal noong ika-27 ng Disyembre 1874.</p><p>Kalihim sa Morong ng mga naghihimagsik laban sa Kastila, manunulat at manananggol. Naipanalo ang usapin ng El Renacimiento sa sakdal na libelo ng mga Amerikanong militar. Itinatag ang Lalawigan ng Rizal dahil sa pagkakapagtibay sa kanyang panukala na ang dating lalawigan ng Morong at ang ilang bayan ng Maynila ay pagsamahin at gawing isang lalawigan. Hukom sa Pagtatala ng Lupa (1908); Kagawad ng Komisyon ng Pilipinas (1909–1913); nahalal na Senador, 1925–1931 at 1934–1935, at Kagawad ng Komisyon sa Kalayaan, 1930–1931. Utak ng oposisyon na ang patakaran ay ang pagsasabi ng totoo, at pagtatapat sa bayan.</p><p>Namatay noong ika-9 ng Enero, 1942.</p>"},"photo":{"width":1822,"file":"Juan Sumulong historical marker 02 (cropped).jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":2185,"hash":"1e"}}},"address":"Sumulong Park, M. L. Quezon Street, Antipolo, Rizal","name":"Juan M. Sumulong","region":"Calabarzon","lon":121.17592,"locPhoto":{"hash":"c1","height":3264,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Juan Sumulong Monument.jpg","width":2448},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of a statue of Juan M. Sumulong facing M.L. Quezon Street.","wikipedia":{"Juan Sumulong":true}},"Q26111317":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the extreme left of the main entrance of the church.","wikipedia":{"Taytay Church":"St John the Baptist Church (Taytay, Rizal)"},"lon":121.13232,"locPhoto":{"hash":"df","height":1176,"width":1962,"file":"Taytay Church historical marker location.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"address":"Taytay Church, J. Sumulong Street, Brgy. San Isidro, Taytay, Rizal","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Taytay","inscription":"<p>Dating yari sa mahihinang kagamitan na ipinatayo ng mga misyonerong Pransiskano malapit sa baybayin ng Laguna de Bay, 1579. Nahiwalay bilang Visita ng Santa Ana de Sapa, 1583. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang pook ni P. Pedro Chirino, S.J., 1591 at bininyagan ang bayan ng pangalang San Juan del Monte. Ipinagawa ang unang simbahang bato sa labas ng Maynila. Muling ipinagawa ang pangalawang simbahang bato na higit na malaki ni P. Juan de Salazar, 1630. Nasira ang bubungan ng malakas na bagyo, 1632; ipinaayos sa pamamahala ng mga sekular, 1768; at sa mga Agustinong-Rekoletos, 1864. Muling nasunog noong Digmaang Filipino-Amerikano, 1899; pinalaki para matugunan ang lumalaking populasyon noong mga unang taon nang 1970's.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"d5","height":3550,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Simbahan ng Taytay historical marker.jpg","width":2500}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng Taytay","lat":14.57102,"date":"1992","macroAddress":"Taytay, Rizal"},"Q29018520":{"lon":125.07034,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"date":"1987","macroAddress":"Basey, Samar","lat":11.2811,"name":"Simbahan ng Basey","region":"Eastern Visayas","address":"Basey Church, Basey, Samar","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Basey","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Dating parokya ng mga Heswita sa ilalim ng Obispado ng Cebu noong 1591 at ng tahanan ng Dagami noong 1656. Ipinatayong may matibay na pundasyon ng mga Heswita at inialay kay San Miguel de Archangel. Inilipat sa mga Agustino, 1768, at sa mga Pransiskano, 1795; ngunit pinamusesyonan noong 1804. Ipinaayos at ipinagawa ang tore at kumbentong bato at kubales kasama ang sementeryo at kapilya ni Padre Domingo de Madrid, 1845, sinira ng bagyo, 1880. Pinalitan ang bubungan ng yerong galbanisado ni Padre Vicente Gutierrez, 1894-1896. Naging punong himpilang pangmisyon, sentro ng pagtuturo ng \"Doctrina Christiana, at kuta - panahon ng Kastila; bulwagang pulungan at dulaan — nang pananakop ng Hapon; at pook likasan — noong Liberasyon.</p>"}}}},"Q35096899":{"name":"Simbahan ng Tubigon","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Tubigon","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Heswita bilang bisita ng Calape at inilipat sa pamamahala ng mga Rekoleto, 1768. Naging parokya sa patronato ni San Isidro Labrado, 1852. Ipinagpatuloy ni Padre Felix Guillen (1887–1893) ang pagpapatayo ng kasalukuyang simbahan. Pinangasiwaan ng mga paring sekular, 1899. Isinagawa ni Ray Francia ang mga larawan sa kisame ng simbahan, dekada 1920 at 1930. Nasira ng lindol, 15 Oktubre 2013.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Tubigon Church, Tubigon, Bohol","date":"2015","macroAddress":"Tubigon, Bohol","lat":9.95045,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":123.96282,"locPhoto":null},"Q43354402":{"lat":16.41054,"macroAddress":"Baguio","date":"1940","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>This is the site of the building where the Philippine Commission held its first session in Baguio from April 22 to June 11, 1904, inclusive, officially initiating use of Baguio as the Philippines’ summer capital. The Commission was composed of Governor General Luke E. Wright, President, and Commissioners Henry C. Ide, Dean C. Worcester, T. H. Pardo de Tavera, Benito Legarda, Jose R. de Luzuriaga, James F. Smith and W. Cameron Forbes. In this session, 74 acts and 273 Resolutions were approved.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Philippine Commission’s First Session in Baguio"},"photo":{"hash":"30","height":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Philippine Commission session site in Baguio historical marker 01.jpg","width":3456}}},"address":"Governor Pack Road, Baguio","region":"Cordillera Administrative Region","name":"Philippine Commission’s First Session in Baguio","lon":120.5988,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Taft Commission":true}},"Q55001963":{"date":"1954","macroAddress":"Puerto Princesa","lat":9.74472,"name":"Iwahig Penal Colony","region":"Mimaropa","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Originally named Iuhuit Penal Settlement, this colony was established by the Philippine Commission, 16 November 1904. The site was selected by a committee composed of G.N. Wolfe, W.S. Lyon and Arlington Pond, created by an Executive Order of Gov. Gen. Luke E. Wright. The first Superintendent was an American, R.J. Shields. The early policy of sending the worst prisoners to the place was abandoned after the mutiny of thirty-three prisoners on 20 September 1905. Prisoners of good conduct were sent and given lands, tools and other supplies and in certain areas their families were allowed to live with them. </p><p>Ramon Victorio, first Filipino Superintendent, 1921.</p>","title":"Iwahig Penal Colony","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Iwahig Prison and Penal Farm, Km. 17 Puerto Princesa South Road, Brgy. Iwahig, Puerto Princesa","lon":118.66098,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Iwahig Prison and Penal Farm":true},"locDesc":null},"Q47005963":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.02197,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Tanauan, Batangas, ika-5 ng Disyembre 1859. Anak nina Eusebio Gonzales at Leocadia Lantin. Nagtapos sa Kolehiyo ng San Juan de Letran at nag-aral sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas. Nahalal na gobernandor ng Tanauan, 1894–1897; namuno bilang koronel sa Batalyon Makiling sa ilalim ng pangangasiwa ni Heneral Miguel Malvar. Nakasama nina Heneral Juan Cailles at Heneral Pio del Pilar sa pangkat ng mga manghihimagsik na nagwagi sa Lipa, Batangas, at sa Santa Cruz, Laguna. Nataas sa tungkuling brigadyer, 1901; naging gobernador ng Batangas, ika-16 ng Oktubre 1916 hanggang ika-31 ng Oktubre 1919. Tinaguriang Bundok ng Gonzales ng mga Amerikano ang pook ng Banawan bilang alaala sa kanyang pagkahimpil doon. Namatay sa Tanauan, Batangas, ika-5 ng Hulyo 1923.</p>","title":"Heneral Nicolas Gonzales at Lantin","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":718,"hash":"c8","width":489,"file":"Heneral Nicolas Gonzales at Lantin.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"address":"People's Park in the Sky, Tagaytay, Cavite","name":"Heneral Nicolas Gonzales at Lantin","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Tagaytay, Cavite","date":"1958-12-05","lat":14.14299},"Q46155194":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.87959,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"General Trias, Cavite","lat":14.38528,"name":"Bahay na Tinigilan ni Andres Bonifacio","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"GeneralTrias,Cavitejf2987 12.JPG","hash":"88","height":4608},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Bahay na Tinigilan ni Andres Bonifacio","inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na ito pansamantalang tumigil sina Andres Bonifacio, tagapagtatag ng Katipunan at mga kapatid na sina Ciriaco at Procopio nang pumunta sa Cavite sa paanyaya ng konsehong panlalawigan ng Magdiwang, Disyembre 1896–Abril 1897. Naging pag-aari ni Estefania Potente, pagkaraa’y nabili ni Emilio P. Virata, kinatawan ng Cavite, 1919–1922. Hanggang sa mabili ng mag-asawang Dr. Jose at Martha Rodriguez, 1975, at tinirahan. Kabilang sa mga naging panauhin dito sina Pangulong Emilio Aguinaldo, Manuel Luis Quezon, Sergio Osmeña, Manuel Roxas at Elpidio Quirino.</p>"}}},"address":"96th Street cor. Corregidor Street, General Trias, Cavite"},"Q28973983":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.23264,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Fidel V. Ramos":"Fidel Ramos","Narciso Ramos":true,"Leticia Ramos-Shahani":true},"macroAddress":"Lingayen, Pangasinan","date":"1993","lat":16.02951,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3814,"hash":"02","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Ramos house 2 historical marker.JPG","width":2898},"text":{"title":"Ramos House","subtitle":"Lingayen, Pangasinan","inscription":"<p>On this site has stood for years the house of the couple Narciso Ramos, lawyer, journalist, statesman and diplomat, and Angela Valdez, one-time English supervisor of the Pangasinan Vocational High School. In this house were born and raised their children: Leticia Ramos Shahani, ambassador and senator; Fidel, AFP Chief of Staff, Secretary of the Department of National Defense and eighth President of the Republic of the Philippines; and Gloria Ramos-Rodda.</p><p>This marker was made possible through the initiative of Kaluyagan Nen Palaris and daughters of Princess Urduja Executive Committee headed by Justice and Mrs. Porfirio V. Sison.</p>"}}},"address":"The President Hotel, Lingayen, Pangasinan","name":"Ramos House","region":"Ilocos Region"},"Q44452718":{"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Lazi","address":"Lazi Church, Lazi, Siquijor","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Lazi","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ang parokyang ito ay itinatag ng mga paring Agustino Rekoleto sa ilalim ng patronato ni San Isidro Labrador noong 1857. Ang simbahan at kumbento ay ipinatayo sa pangangasiwa ng P. Toribio Sanchez, O.A.R. Yari sa mga batong-dagat at matitigas na kahoy, ang simbahan ay tinapos ng mga Pilipinong artesano nong 1884 at ang kampanaryo pagkalipas ng isang taon. Ang maluwang na kumbento ay sinimulan noong 1887 at binasbasan noong 1891. May sukat na 42 sa 38 metro, ang kumbentong ito ay isa sa pinakamalaki sa Pilipinas. </p><p> Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan Bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974, at Bilang 1505, 11 Hunyo 1978, ang simbahan at kumbento ay ipinahayag na mga Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Lazi Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":834,"height":1214,"hash":"ba"}}},"lat":9.12765,"macroAddress":"Lazi, Siquijor","date":"1984-05-19","wikipedia":{"Lazi Church":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":123.6335,"locPhoto":null},"Q22298034":{"lon":120.97329,"locPhoto":{"file":"Manila Cathedral Facade.JPG","credit":"H.abanil {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3088,"height":2056,"hash":"78"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the cathedral.","wikipedia":{"Manila Cathedral":true},"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1958","lat":14.59175,"address":"Manila Cathedral, Sto. Tomas Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Roman Catholic Cathedral of Manila","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>First cathedral built in 1581, damaged by a typhoon, 1582 and destroyed by fire, 1583. Second cathedral built of stone in 1592 and partially destroyed by earthquake, 1600. Third cathedral built of stone in 1614 and destroyed by the earthquake of 1645. Fourth cathedral magnificently built in 1654-1671 by Archbishop Miguel Poblete and destroyed by the earthquake ofv3 June 1863. Fifth cathedral built in 1870-1879 under architects Luciano Oliver, Vicente Serrano Salaverria and Eduardo Lopez Navarro and solemnly blessed in December 1879. The center of the cross on the dome is a reference point of astronomical longitudes of Manila in 1945. Sixth cathedral reconstruction 1954-1958; under the direction of Archbishop Rufino J. Santos of Manila mainly with the support of the people. Fernando Ocampo, architect.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Roman Catholic Cathedral of Manila historical marker (corrected).jpg","width":2000,"height":3291,"hash":"55"}}},"name":"Roman Catholic Cathedral of Manila","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q54944140":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":120.59488,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Church of San Nicolas","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Founded 1584 by the Agustinian missionaries. Original chapel was of masonry with a thatch roof. Reconstructed 1811–1830. Father Victoriano Garcia Alonso erected the tower, 1895–1897. Occupied by revolutionists, 1898; by American forces, 1899; and Philippine Independent Church, 1900–1901.</p>","title":"Church of San Nicolas","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker Church of San Nicolas.jpg","width":1687,"height":2537,"hash":"e1"}}},"address":"Manila North Road cor. Doña Josefa Llanes Escoda National Highway, Poblacion, San Nicolas, Ilocos Norte","date":"1952","macroAddress":"San Nicolas, Ilocos Norte","lat":18.17411},"Q55739330":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Bataan Death March":true},"lon":120.49098,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ika-9 ng Abril, 1942, ang pagbagsak ng Bataan ay naging luksang kabanata sa kasaysayan ng Bansang Pilipino. Nguni’t para sa mahigit na 70,000 kawal ng USAFFE na naging labi ng digma sa Bataan, ang mariing dagok na ito ay hindi nagwakas ng araw na yaon. Mula sa larangan ng digmaan, sila’y inilikas ng mga Hapones bilang mga bilanggo ng digma, at dito nila dinanas ang libong hirap at pagtitiis sa paglalakbay na natitik sa kasaysayan ng bansa sa bansag na “Death March”.</p><p>Nagsimula sa dalawang pook ang “Death March” mula sa Mariveles noong ika-10 ng Abril, at mula sa Bagac noong ika-11 ng Abril. Araw at gabi’y pinaglakad ang mga kawal na Pilipino’t Amerikano, sa nakapapasong init ng araw o sa lamig ng gabi, pasuray-suray sa mga bayan ng Cabcaben, Limay, Orion, Pilar at Balanga, sila’y pinagpahingang sandali at pinainom nang kaunti. Buhat sa Balanga ang mga bilanggo ng digma ay pinagpangkat-pangkat mula sa 100 hanggang 200 bawa’t pangkat at isinailalim sa mga tanod habang naglalakad sa mga lansangan ng Abukay, Samal, hanggang Orani at doon ibinukod ang mga bilanggong Amerikano sa mga bilanggong Pilipino at magkahiwalay na pinaglakad. Ang marahas na pagpapalakad ay nagpatuloy pahilaga patungong Abukay, Samal, Hermosa hanggang sangandaan ng Layac, pagkatapos pasilangan patungong Pampanga sa pamamagitan ng Lubao, Guagua na dito pinagpahinga at binigyan ng kaunting pagkain sa bakuran ng National Development Company, Bacolor at San Fernando. </p><p>Laganap ang daing ng mga kawal Pilipino at Amerikano na duhagi na sa pakikibaka ay pagod pa sa paglalakad. Ano mang karamdaman o sakit ng katawan ay hindi dahilan upang makapagpahinga, sapagka’t ang pagtigil ay malaking sagabal na nangangahulugan ng lalong malupit na parusang igagawad ng walang-awang mga kaaway. Libo-libong buhay ang hindi na nakarating sa paroroonan. Salamat sa mga mamamayang naglakasloob sumuong sa panganib, makapag-abot lamang ng pagkain at inumin; may mapapalad pa ring tumanggap ng pangtawid-buhay. </p><p> Sa San Fernando ay higit na makahayop ang pakikitungong tinanggap ng mga bilanggo ng digma nang sila’y sala-salansang isakay sa bagon ng tren. Ibayong dami ng buhay ang nakitil, at mabibilang ang nakarating ng buhay sa Capas. Mula sa Capas, ang mga nalalabi’y muling pinalakad hanggang Kampo O’Donnel, isa sa mga kulungang maituturing na impiyerno sa ibabaw ng lupa noong panahon ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig.</p>","title":null,"subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":3246,"hash":"15","file":"Death March Tagalog historical marker in Mariveles (cropped).JPG","credit":"Judgefloro","width":1215}},"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Immediately after the Fall of Bataan on April 9, 1942, the USFIP forces were evacuated by the Japanese from the field of battle as prisoners of war. The more than 70,000 Filipino and American troops who had survived the Battle of Bataan underwent, in this evacuation, the ordeal that history knows as the Death March. </p><p> The Death March started from two points in Bataan: on April 10 from Mariveles, on April 11 from Bagac. The Filipino and American troops were marched day and night, under the blistering sun or cold night sky, staggering through Cabcaben, Limay, Orion, Pilar and Balanga, where they were given a brief rest and some water. From Balanga, the prisoners of war were organized into groups of 100 to 200 and under guard marched on through Abucay, Samal and Orani, where the Americans were segregated from the Filipino prisoners of war and marched separately. The march continued northward through Hermosa, to Layac, through Lubao, Guagua, where the prisoners rested and given little food at the National Development Company Compound, Bacolor and San Fernando. </p><p>Already suffering from battle fatigue, the Filipino and American troops were strained to utter exhaustion by this long march on foot. Many were ill, most were feverish, but none might rest, for the enemy was brutal with those who lagged behind. Thousands fell along the way. Townspeople on the roadside risked their lives by slipping food and drink to the Death Marchers as they stumbled by. </p><p>In San Fernando, the Death March became a Death Ride by cargo train when the prisoners were packed so densely into boxcards that many of them perished from suffocation. Those who arrived alive in Capas had still to walk the last and most agonized miles of the Death March: the 6 kilometers to Camp O’Donnell, which was to become of the most hellish of the concentration camps of World War II.</p>","title":"The Death March of Filipino and American Prisoners of War from Mariveles and Bagac to Camp O’Donnell, Capas, Tarlac","subtitle":"April 1942"},"photo":{"width":1267,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Death March English historical marker in Mariveles (cropped).JPG","hash":"56","height":3308}}},"address":"World War II Death March Memorial Shrine, National Road, Brgy. Poblacion, Mariveles, Bataan","name":"The Death March of Filipino and American Prisoners of War from Mariveles and Bagac to Camp O’Donnell, Capas, Tarlac","region":"Central Luzon","date":"1967","macroAddress":"Mariveles, Bataan","lat":14.43591},"Q55861802":{"name":"Lumang Simbahan ng Sablayan","region":"Mimaropa","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang parokya ng mga Rekoleto, 1843. Itinayo ang simbahan at kumbento na yari sa bato sa panahon ni Padre Jacinto Perez de San Agustin, 1861–1866. Napinsala ng tsunami, 1877. Ipinanumbalik sa ilalim ng panunungkulan ni Padre Simeon Mendaza V. de Ibernalo, 1877–1879. Kinumpuni matapos mapinsala ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1954. Muling isinaayos ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 2017–2018.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Lumang Simbahan ng Sablayan"}}},"address":"San Sebastian Street, Brgy. Poblacion, Sablayan, Occidental Mindoro","macroAddress":"Sablayan, Occidental Mindoro","date":"2018-07-12","lat":12.83078,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.76758},"Q24814491":{"locPhoto":{"hash":"11","height":3456,"file":"Taal,Batangasjf2457 08.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608},"lon":120.92372,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the main entrance of the building.","lat":13.8805,"macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","date":"1991-01-22","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Escuela Pia","address":"Escuela Pia, Taal, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isang paaralang pinangasiwaan ng simbahan at ipinangalan sa orden ng Escuela Pia, isang kongregasyong na itinatag ni San Jose ng Calasanz noong ika-17 daantaon. Itinatag ng mga paring agustino noong 1839, ang kumbento ng mga ito ang nagsilbing paaralan para sa mahihirap at iniwang kabataan ng Taal. Ang kasalukuyang gusali at ipinatayo ni P. Aniceto Aparicio, 1885. Naging paaralang sentral noong panahon pananakop ng mga Amerikano. Ang restorasyon ng lumang gusali, na isa sa mga pinakamatandang institusyong edukasyonal sa Pilipinas, ay sinumulan ng Taal Arts and Culture Movement, Inc. sa pakikipag-ugnayan sa pambansang suriang pangkasaysayan. Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga kautusang bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974, at bilang 1505, 11 Hunyo 1978, ang paaralang ito ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","title":"Escuela Pia","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"69","height":3819,"file":"Escuela Pia historical marker 2.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2538}}}},"Q44643834":{"macroAddress":"Puerto Princesa","date":"2014-12-08","lat":9.74059,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"San Ezekiel Moreno","subtitle":"1848–1906","inscription":"<p>Paring Agustino Rekoleto at santo. Isinilang sa La Rioja, Espanya, 9 Abril 1848. Dumating sa Maynila, 10 Pebrero 1870. Naordenahang pari sa Katedral ng Maynila, 2 Hunyo 1871. Kabilang sa mga nagtatag ng bayan ng Puerto Princesa bilang unang misyonero, kapelyan ng mga militar at ng colonya penal, 4 Marso 1872. Mula 1873 hanggang 1885, naging kura paroko ng Calapan (Mindoro), Las Piñas, Santo Tomas (Batangas), Sta. Cruz (Maynila) at tagapamahala ng Hacienda ng Imus. Yumao sa Espanya sa sakit na kanser, 19 Agosto 1906. Idineklarang santo ni Papa Juan Pablo II dahil sa ipinakitang kabanalan, kapuri-puring halimbawa, at taospusong pagsilbi sa mga kapuspalad at mga maysakit sa Pilipinas, Espanya at Colombia, 11 Oktubre 1992. Itinuturing na santo at patron ng mga may kanser.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Immaculate Conception Cathedral, Rizal Avenue, Puerto Princesa","name":"San Ezekiel Moreno","region":"Mimaropa","lon":118.72988,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Ezequiél Moreno y Díaz":true}},"Q52144815":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal several meters in front of the monument to Recto.","wikipedia":{"Claro M. Recto":true},"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"b8","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"CMRectoTiaongjf0271 19.JPG","width":4608},"lon":121.32446,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Claro M. Recto historical marker in Tiaong, Quezon.jpg","height":4608,"hash":"4d"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1890–1960)","title":"Claro Recto y Mayo","inscription":"<p>Makabayan, estadista, parlamentaryan, hukom, mambabatas, awtor at orador. Isinilang sa Tiaong, Quezon, noong Pebrero 8, 1890. Nagtapos ng A.B. sa Ateneo de Manila, 1909; LL.B. at LL.M., Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, 1913 at 1914; LL.D. Honoris Causa, Pamantasan ng Maynila, 1936, at Pamantasan ng Arellano, 1940, Kinatawan ng Batangas, at Lider ng Minorya ng Mababang Kapulungan. Senador, at pansamantalang Pangulo at Lider Mayorya ng Senado ng Pilipinas. Pangulo, Konstitusyonal Kumbensyon at Ama ng Saligang Batas ng Pilipinas, 1934–1935.</p><p> Kasapi sa Bar ng Kataas-taasang Hukuman ng Estados Unidos at Katulong na Mahistrado ng Kataas-taasang Hukuman ng Pilipinas, may akda ng tulang Bajo los Cocoteros, dulang Solo Entre las Sombras, at maraming aklat pambatas at pangkasaysayan. Namatay sa Roma noong Oktubre 2, 1960.</p>"}}},"address":"Pan-Philippine Highway cor. Recto Mayo Street, Tiaong, Quezon","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Claro Recto y Mayo","lat":13.95873,"macroAddress":"Tiaong, Quezon","date":"1984-02-08"},"Q37324123":{"locPhoto":{"file":"IJVPacoChurch3.jpg","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3872,"hash":"8c","height":2592},"lon":120.99492,"wikipedia":{"Paco Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main entrance of the church.","date":"1936","macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","lat":14.57933,"name":"Church of Dilao–Paco","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The first chapel built in 1599–1601, and damaged during the Chinese uprising of 1603, was repaired by Archdean Francisco Gomez Arellano. The chapel gave way to a church built in 1809–1914 under the supervision of Bernardo de la Concepcion Perdigon, O.F.M., afterward Bishop of Nueva Caceres. The church was damaged by the earthquakes of 1852 and 1881, and destroyed by fire on February 5, 1899. The present church was solemnly blessed on April 29, 1934.</p>","title":"Church of Dilao–Paco","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":2133,"hash":"f6","width":2054,"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"San Fernando de Dilao Church, Paco historical marker (English) (cropped).jpg"}}},"address":"Paco Church, 1521 Paz Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q36141914":{"address":"Lavezares Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>This house was occupied by Dr. Pio Valenzuela together with Ulpiano Fernandez and Faustino Duque, Filipino printers who turned out for Dr. Valenzuela and Emilio Jacinto 2,000 copies of the newspaper entitled \"Ang Kalayaan,\" giving Yokohama as the place of publication to evade suspicion. The first issue was dated January 18, 1896, but was not circulated until the middle of March. The second issue, in preparation, was seized by the Spanish authorities when the revolution broke out that year. </p><p><small> Original house destroyed February 1945, in the battle of Liberation of Manila in the Second World War.</small></p>","title":"Where “Ang Kalayaan” Was Printed","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Where Ang Kalayaan was Printed.jpg","width":528,"height":651,"hash":"83"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Where “Ang Kalayaan” Was Printed","lat":14.59889,"macroAddress":"San Nicolas, Manila","date":"1941","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Pío Valenzuela":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96791},"Q28927631":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.92189,"name":"San Ramon Prison and Penal Farm","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"San Ramon Prison and Penal Farm","inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa patronato ni San Ramon Nonato Colonia Penitenciaria Agricola upang palawakin ang agrikultura sa paggawa ng mga bilangong manggagawa, 31 Agosto 1870. Piitan ng mga nahatulang kalaban ng pamahalaang Espanyol. Kalauna’y dito itinapon ang mga nagkasalang Kristiyano at Muslim. Nasunog ang mga gusali sa labanan ng Pilipino at Espanyol, 1899. Ipinagpatuloy ng mga Amerikano ang pamamahala dito, 1901. Pinamunuan ng Moro Province, 1911, ng Department of Mindanao and Sulu, 1914, at ng Bureau of Prisons, 1915. Ginamit ng mga Hapon bilang piitan noong ikalawang digmaang pandaigdig. Isa sa mga unang kolonyang penal sa bansa.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"San Ramon Prison and Penal Farm, Sitio San Ramon, Brgy. Talisayan, Zamboanga City","date":"2014","macroAddress":"Zamboanga City","lat":6.99399},"Q37707492":{"wikipedia":{"Tejeros Convention":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the right facade of the convention house.","lon":120.86072,"locPhoto":{"height":1080,"hash":"eb","width":1920,"file":"Tejeros Convention House.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"The Tejeros Convention","address":"General Trias Drive, Rosario, Cavite","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>A revolutionary assembly was held March 22, 1897 in the building known as the Casa Hacienda of Tejeros. That once stood on this site. Presided over by Andress Bonifacio. Toward the end of the session, the assembly decided to establish a central revolutionary government and elected Emilio Aguinaldo, president; Mariano Trias, vice president; Artemio Ricarte, captain general;; Emiliano Riego de Dios, Director of War; and Andres Bonifacio, Director of the Interior. Certain events arising in the convention caused Bonifacio to bolt its action.</p>","title":"The Tejeros Convention","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":1427,"file":"Tejeros Convention Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"be","height":1155}}},"lat":14.40119,"macroAddress":"Rosario, Cavite","date":"1941"},"Q55279104":{"address":"Baler Church, Rizal Street, Poblacion, Baler, Aurora","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>A Spanish garrison of four officers and fifty men was besieged in this Church by Filipino insurgents from June 27, 1898, to June 2, 1899. Offers of peace and demands for surrender were refused on five occasions. From newspapers dropped into the court by an emissary of General Rios on May 29, the garrison learned for the first time that the Philippines had been lost to Spain and that for many months there had been no Spanish flag in Luzon, except the one waving over Baler Church. Broken by starvation and tropical diseases, the depleted command arranged a truce with the insurgents and marched out of this Church across the mountains to Manila on June 2, 1899. Of the original garrison, two officers, the priest and twelve men had died from disease; two men had been killed by insurgent bullets; two men had been executed; two officers and fourteen men had been wounded; six men had deserted. The fortitude of the garrison was praised by General Aguinaldo in a public document issued at Tarlac on June 20, 1899. Upon their return to Spain the survivors were rewarded by the Queen Regent in the name of Alfonso XIII and the Spanish nation.</p>","title":"Siege of the Church of Baler","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":493,"file":"Siege of Church of Baler.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":495,"hash":"f4"}}},"name":"Siege of the Church of Baler","region":"Central Luzon","date":"1939","macroAddress":"Baler, Aurora","lat":15.75897,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade, to the left of the main entrance.","wikipedia":{"Siege of Baler":true},"locPhoto":{"hash":"37","height":1944,"width":2592,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Church facade in Baler, Aurora.jpg"},"lon":121.56234},"Q35008459":{"date":"2010","macroAddress":"Loon, Bohol","lat":9.79863,"name":"Simbahan ng Loon","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Loon","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Heswita, 1753. Inilipat sa pamamahala ng mga Augustinian Recollects, 1768. Nasunog ang unang simbahan maliban ang harapan, 1850's. Kasama ang harapan ng dating gusali, muling ipinatayo ayon sa disenyo ni Domingo Escondrillas, 1855-1864. Ginamit ng mga pwersang Amerikano bilang garison sa kanilang kampanya laban sa mga Filipinong gerilya, 1901. Isinagawa ni Ray Francia, Cebuanong pintor, ang mga pintadong obra sa loob ng simbahan, 1938. Pangunahing patron ang Nuestra Señora de la Luz o Birhen sa Kasilak at pangalawang patron si St. Joseph the Worker. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 2010.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Loon Church historical marker.jpg","width":497,"height":687,"hash":"7c"}}},"address":"Loon Church, Loon, Bohol","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.79285,"wikipedia":{"Loon Church":true},"locDesc":null},"Q55710363":{"wikipedia":{"Katipunan":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96813,"name":"Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":2009,"hash":"55","file":"Marker KKK foundation.jpg","credit":"Nikond80 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1444},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito sa #72 Azcarraga, Tondo, Maynila, itinatag ang K.K.K.N.M.A.N.B. ni Andres Bonifacio kasama sina Ladislao Diwa, Teodoro Plata, Deodato Arellano, Valentin Diaz, at Jose Dizon, 7 Hulyo 1892. Pangunahing adhikain ng lihim na samahan ang mapagkaisa ang lahat ng mga Filipino at itaguyod ang isang bayang malaya sa pamamagitan ng paghihimagsik. Nagtatag ng mga Sangguniang Bayan at Hukumang Balangay sa iba’t ibang bahagi ng kapuluan. Ang Kartilya ni Emilio Jacinto ang nagsilbing gabay ng mga kasapi. Bilang Supremo pinamunuan ni Bonifacio ang Sigaw sa Pugadlawin, bilang hudyat sa malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa Espanyol, 23 Agosto 1896.</p>","title":"Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan","subtitle":"(K.K.K.N.M.A.N.B)"}}},"address":"Claro M. Recto Avenue cor. Elcano Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"2008","macroAddress":"San Nicolas, Manila","lat":14.60318},"Q53997782":{"lon":120.97323,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"macroAddress":"Silang, Cavite","date":"2016-09-07","lat":14.21887,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Silang, Cavite, 15 Hunyo 1857. Naglingkod bilang tenyente mayor, cabeza de barangay, kalihim tribunal, at gobernadorcillo. General de brigada ng Sangguniang Bayang Magdalo at isa sa mga nanguna sa pag-aaklas sa Silang, 1896. Lumagda sa Konstitusyon ng Biak-na-Bato, 1 Nobyembre 1897. Kalihim ng Digma sa Biak-na-Bato at kabilang sa mga lider na kusang nagpatapon sa Hong Kong, Disyembre 1897. General de division ng Hukbong Rebolusyonaryo, 25 Hunyo 1898. Kinatawan ng Batanes, Kongresong Rebolusyonaryo, Setyembre 1898. Itinalaga ni Emilio Aguinaldo bilang punong komandante ng Albay at hepe ng mga hukbo sa Camarines Norte, Camarines Sur at Sorsogon, 29 Oktubre 1898. Nakipaglaban sa puwersa ni Hen. William Kobbe noong Digmaang Pilipino–Amerikano sa Albay, 1900–1901. Sumuko sa mga Amerikano, 4 Hulyo 1901. Yumao, 14 Hulyo 1933.</p>","subtitle":"1857–1933","title":"Vito Belarmino"},"photo":null}},"address":"J.P. Rizal Street cor. M.H. del Pilar Street, Silang, Cavite","name":"Vito Belarmino","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q44814882":{"region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Servando Castro","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1861–1946)","title":"Servando Castro","inscription":"<p>Isinilang noong Oktubre 23, 1861 sa Batac, Ilocos Norte. Nag-aral ng pagpapari at nagturo sa Seminaryo ng Vigan. Naglingkod ng 12 taon sa Diyosesis ng Nueva Segovia. Sumapi sa Iglesia Filipina Independiente at naging isa sa mga lumagda sa Doctrina y Reglas Constitucionales. Pansimbahang Gobernador ng Laguna, Obispo ng Rehiyon ng Ilocos, Obispo Maximo Emeritus at Decano de los Obispos. Sumulat para sa La Vanguardia. Kinatawan ng Ilocos Norte sa 1934 Konstitusyunal Kumbensiyon at kagawad ng Komite sa Tungkulin ng Mamamayan. Namatay noong Disyembre 6, 1946.</p>"}}},"address":"Sabas Street cor. Asuncion Street, Batac, Ilocos Norte","lat":18.05225,"date":"1983-12-06","macroAddress":"Batac, Ilocos Norte","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.56547},"Q53360187":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.72512,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"JC San Jacinto 5.jpg","width":1680,"hash":"93","height":2520},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo ng mga Dominikano noong 1604 sa karangalan ni San Jacinto. Muling itinayo ni Fray Bernabe de la Magdalena at pinasinayaan noong Agosto 16, 1724. Dito itinatag at ipinag-utos ni Don Joseph Arzadun de Rebolledo ng <u>Audiencia Real de Manila</u> ang pondong pampamayanan at alituntunin sa mamamayan ng Cagayan noong 1739. Pinalamutihan ng mga mamamayan sa pamamatnubay ni Gobernadorsilyo Domingo Balino at pinanganlang <u>Hermita de Piedra de San Jacinto</u> noong 1772. Ginamit na kuwartel ng mga manghihimagsik at kanlungan ng mga sundalong Amerikano noong Digmaang Pilipino–Amerikano. Kasalukuyang pinamamahalaan ng <u>St. Paul Sisters</u>.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Kapilya ng San Jacinto"}}},"address":"Mabini Street cor. Legazpi Street, Tuguegarao, Cagayan","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Kapilya ng San Jacinto","lat":17.61666,"date":"1982","macroAddress":"Tuguegarao, Cagayan"},"Q28855130":{"wikipedia":{"Balay Negrense":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.97316,"region":"Western Visayas","name":"Victor Fernandez Gaston Ancestral House","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Victor Fernandez Gaston Ancestral House","inscription":"<p>This is a Heritage House pursuant to Board Resolution no. 1 dated March 8, 1994 of the National Historical Institute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker Victor Fernandez Gaston Ancestral House.JPG","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4752,"hash":"a8","height":3168}}},"address":"Balay Negrense, Silay, Negros Occidental","lat":10.80005,"macroAddress":"Silay, Negros Occidental","date":"1994"},"Q54555425":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ni Dr. Rebecca Parish bilang Dispensaria Betaña sa gusali ng Bible School for Women sa Santa Cruz, Maynila, 1906. Naging pagamutan at paaralan ng nursing, 1907. Sa pook na ito ipinatayo ang unang gusali ng pagamutan mula sa donasyon ni Daniel S.B. Johnston at pinanganlang Mary Johnston Hospital sa alaala ng kanyang yumaong misyonerong asawa, 1908. Muling ipinatayo matapos masunog, 1911. Ginamit na pagamutan ng pamahalaang Hapon, 1942. Nasunong noong Labanan sa Maynila, 1945. Pinasinayaan ng Pangulong Elipidio Quirino ang bagong gusali, 1950. Dito binuksan ang unang klinika ng isterilisasyon sa bansa, 1975. Tumanggap ng Gawad Apolinario Mabini sa kategoryang Rehabilitation Volunteer Group mula sa Philippine Foundation for the Rehabilitation of Disabled, 1987. Ginawaran ng plake ng pagkilala ng Kagawaran ng Kalusugan at ng National Institutes of Health bilang Outstanding Newborn Screening Facility and Exemplary Newborn Screening Facility sa kategoryang Private Tertiary Hospital, Oktubre 2005.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Mary Johnston Hospital"},"photo":{"file":"Mary Johnston Hospital marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":381,"hash":"d0","height":551}}},"address":"1221 Juan Nolasco Street, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Mary Johnston Hospital","lat":14.60915,"macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","date":"2006-12-08","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the right post of the main hospital entrance.","wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":{"hash":"b2","height":3456,"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Mary Johnston Hospital facade (Tondo).jpg"},"lon":120.96631},"Q55843907":{"lat":10.82753,"date":"2012","macroAddress":"Santa Barbara, Iloilo","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo sa pangangasiwa ni Padre Francisco Aguerria, OSA, sa patronato ni Santa Barbara Virgen y Martir 1849; ipinagpatuloy ni Padre Mateo Rodriguez, 1855–1873; natapos sa pamumuno ni Padre Calixto Fernandez, 1878. Ginamit bilang himpilan ng “Ejercito Libertador” na pinamunuan ni Hen. Martin Teofilo Delgado nang itinatag ang Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo sa Visayas, 17 Nobyembre 1898. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan sa bisa ng NHI Resolusyon Blg. 1, 6 Hulyo 1990.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng Santa Barbara"},"photo":{"width":798,"file":"Santa Barbara Church and Convent Heritage Marker.jpg","credit":"Franz Miko G. Verzon {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":1200,"hash":"2c"}}},"address":"Santa Barbara Church, General Martin Teofilo Delgado Street, Santa Barbara, Iloilo","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng Santa Barbara","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.53217,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Santa Barbara Church":true}},"Q55721532":{"macroAddress":"Iba, Zambales","date":"1989","lat":15.32747,"name":"Ramon Magsaysay","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"52","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Ramon Magsaysay historical marker at Iba, Zambales.jpg","width":3456},"text":{"subtitle":"(1907–1957)","title":"Ramon Magsaysay","inscription":"<p>‘Idolo ng Masa.’ Kilala sa tawag na ‘The Guy.’ Isinilang noong Agosto 31, 1907 sa Iba, Zambales. Nagkamit ng BSC, Jose Rizal College, Mandaluyong, Rizal. Pangkalahatang puno, Zambales Military District, 1942; panghukbong punong-lalawigan ng Zambales at itinaas sa pagka-medyor ni Heneral Douglas MacArthur, 1945; kinatawan, 1946–1950; Pangulo ng Pilipinas, 1953–1957, isa sa mga nagsikap upang mapagtibay ang Rogers Bill para sa mga beteranong Filipino at nagdala nito sa Pilipinas mula sa E.U. Sumupil ng mga Hukbalahap. Nagtatag ng President’s Action Committee (PCAC), National Rehabilitation and Resettlement Administration (NARRA), National Marketing Corporation (NAMARCO), at Land Tenure Administration (LTA). Namatay noong Marso 17, 1957.</p>"}}},"address":"Magsaysay Avenue, Iba, Zambales","locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"91","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Ramon Magsaysay Monument at Iba.jpg","width":3456},"lon":119.97699,"wikipedia":{"Ramon Magsaysay":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the bust pedestal of Ramon Magsaysay, by the sidewalk."},"Q24189287":{"lat":13.62801,"macroAddress":"Naga, Camarines Sur","date":"1939","region":"Bicol Region","name":"Cathedral of Naga","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Cathedral of Naga historical marker.jpg","width":3120,"hash":"3b","height":4160},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Erected of Padi-an when the Diocese of Nueva Caceres was created by a Papal bull of 14 August 1595. Destroyed by fire, 1768. Construction of present cathedral in Spanish-Romanesque style began by Bishop Bernardo de la Concepcion, 1808. Finished and blessed by Mons. Tomas Ladron de Guevara, 1843. Damaged by typhoon, October, 1856; restored by the Very Reverend Fray Francisco Gainza, 1862-1879. Damaged by earthquake, 1887; repaired by Obras Publicas under the direction of Bishop Arsenio Campo and engineer Ricardo Ayuso, 1890.</p>","title":"Cathedral of Naga","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Naga Cathedral, Elias Angeles Street, Naga, Camarines Sur","lon":123.18718,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Naga Cathedral":true},"locDesc":null},"Q23336728":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"EDSA People Power","inscription":"<p>Nagtipon ang libu-libong mamamayan bilang tugon sa panawagan ng Arsobispo ng Maynila, Jaime Cardinal Sin[,] upang bigyan proteksyon sina Juan Ponce Enrile, Ministro ng Tanggulang Pambansa; Ten. Heneral Fidel V. Ramos, pangalawang pinuno ng Hukbong Sandatahan ng Pilipinas at ang mga rebeldeng sundalong kabilang sa Reform the Armed Forces Movement, na tumiwalag sa administrasyon ni Pangulong Ferdinand E. Marcos at nagkanlong sa Kampo Crame at Aguinaldo, 22–25 Pebrero 1986. Nanumpa si Ginang Corazon C. Aquino bilang Pangulo ng Pilipinas sa Club Filipino, San Juan, Metro Manila, 25 Pebrero 1986. Kinagabihan ng araw ding iyon nilisan ng pamilyang Marcos ang Malacañang, kasama ang ilang tagasunod. Ito ang naging katapusan ng 20 taong rehimeng Marcos at kulminasyon ng mahabang panahong pakikibaka upang ibalik at pairaling muli ang demokrasya sa bansa.</p><p>Inalisan ng tabing ng Kagalang-galang na Pangulong Benigno S. Aquino, III, 25 Pebrero 2011 bilang paggunita sa ika-25 anibersaryo ng mapayapang People Power EDSA Revolution.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"EDSA People Power historical marker.jpg","width":513,"hash":"fe","height":763}}},"address":"People Power Monument, EDSA cor. White Plains Avenue, Quezon City, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"EDSA People Power","lat":14.60002,"macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","date":"2011-02-25","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"People Power Revolution":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.05996},"Q24711215":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.61681,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Malagonlong Bridge":true},"date":"2004-11-26","macroAddress":"Tayabas, Quezon","lat":14.01312,"address":"Malagonlong Bridge, Tayabas, Quezon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"7b","height":1939,"file":"Malagonlong Bridge Historical Marker.JPG","credit":"Ramiltibayan {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2585},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Tulay Malagonlong","inscription":"<p>Ginawa noong 1840 sa ilalim ng pangagasiwa ng kura paroko ng Tayabas, si P. Antonio Mateos, at natapos noong 1850. Isa sa mga nalalabing tulay na bato sa bansa na ipinagawa sa panahon ng pananakop ng mga Espanyol.</p>"}}},"name":"Tulay Malagonlong","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q39021856":{"lat":14.57877,"date":"2018","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Gusaling Army and Navy Club","inscription":"<p>Dinisenyo ni William E. Parsons bilang bahagi ng balangkas ni Daniel Burnham para sa Lungsod ng Maynila. Pinasinayaan, 19 Abril 1911. Nagsilbing clubhouse ng Samahang Pang-Hukbong Katihan at Pandagat ng Maynila (Army and Navy Club of Maynila) mula 1911–1942 at 1946–1980. Matinding napinsala noong labanan sa Maynila, 1945. Muling isinaayos sa pagtutulungan ng U.S. Army Engineering Corps at U.S. Navy Construction Battallion (Seabees), 1945. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 26 Abril 1991. Muling isinaayos, 2014–2017. Pinasinayaan bilang Rizal Park Hotel ni Pangulong Rodrigo Roa Duterte, 26 Hulyo 2017.</p>"},"photo":null},"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Designed by William E. Parsons as part of Daniel Burnham’s plan for the City of Manila. Inaugurated, 19 April 1911. Served as the clubhouse of the Army and Navy Club of Manila, 1911–1942 and 1946–1980. Sustained heavy damage during the battle for Manila, 1945. Reconstructed through the joint effort of the U.S. Army Engineering Corps and U.S. Navy Construction Battallion (Seabees), 1945. Declared a National Historical Landmark, 26 April 1991. Underwent rehabilitation, 2014–2017. Inaugurated as the Rizal Park Hotel by President Rodrigo Roa Duterte, 26 July 2017.</p>","title":"Army and Navy Club Building","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Rizal Park Hotel, South Drive, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Army and Navy Club Building","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97624,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Army and Navy Club Building":"Manila Army and Navy Club Building"}},"Q41645242":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the southern main door of the church.","wikipedia":{"Barasoain Church":true},"locPhoto":{"hash":"9d","height":603,"width":877,"file":"Historical markers on the facade of Barasoain Church.jpg","credit":"Shubert Ciencia {CC BY 2.0}"},"lon":120.81255,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Simbahan ng Barasoain historical marker.jpg","width":2500,"height":2255,"hash":"cb"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Barasoain","inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"}}},"address":"Barasoain Church, Paseo del Congreso cor. Don Antonio Bautista Street, Malolos, Bulacan","name":"Simbahan ng Barasoain","region":"Central Luzon","macroAddress":"Malolos, Bulacan","date":"1976","lat":14.84623},"Q24068386":{"lat":16.61572,"date":"1949","macroAddress":"San Fernando, La Union","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Church of San Fernando, La Union","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of San Fernando, La Union","inscription":"<p>Chapel made of stone and thatch erected, 1764 by Fr. Francisco Romero and Santiago Holarte at Barrio San Vicente formerly known as Pindangan after which San Fernando was first called. Moved to Tanque, then to Kabaroan, and afterwards to its present site where it was built of stone and brick by Fr. Juan Sorolla, Simon Guillermo and Pedro Fernando, 1773–1786. Damaged by earthquake, 1892. Occupied by the revolutionists under Col. Blas Villamor, 1898, when they overwhelmed the Spanish forces that sought shelter therein. Destroyed during the liberation, 26 February 1945. Reconstructed by the residents through the efforts of Bishop Santiago C. Sancho, 1947–1949. Rededicated, 10 February 1949.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"San Fernando, La Union historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"hash":"8d","height":4608}}},"address":"Cathedral of St. William the Hermit, San Fernando, La Union","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.31753,"wikipedia":{"Cathedral of St. William the Hermit":"San Fernando Cathedral (La Union)"},"locDesc":null},"Q29018351":{"wikipedia":{"Agustin Sumuroy":"Agustín Sumuroy"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":125.11505,"region":"Eastern Visayas","name":"Agustin Sumuroy","address":"Palapag, Northern Samar","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Palapag, Samar. Namuno sa pag-aalsa laban sa mga Espanyol bilang protesta sa sapilitang paggawa at mga pang-aabuso sa mga katutubo, 1 Hunyo 1649. Lumaganap ito sa lalawigan ng Cebu, Masbate at Bohol sa Kabisayaan; Iligan, Hilangang Mindanao at Zamboanga sa Mindanao; at Sorsogon at Albay sa Luzon. Ito ay kinikilala bilang unang malawakang paghihimagsik ng mga katutubo. Pinagkanulo at pinaslang ng sariling mga tauhan, 1650.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Agustin Sumuroy"},"photo":{"hash":"4a","height":400,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Agustin Sumuroy historical marker.jpg","width":318}}},"lat":12.54553,"macroAddress":"Palapag, Northern Samar","date":"2008"},"Q41743750":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall on the westernmost portion of the church facade.","wikipedia":{"Meycauayan Church":true},"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"89","width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"MeycauayanChurchBulacan 08.JPG"},"lon":120.95705,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Meycauayanchurchjf1238 06.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608,"height":3456,"hash":"2f"},"text":{"title":"Church of Meycauayan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The first Church was destroyed by a typhoon in 1588. The construction of the present Church was started shortly after 1668, when the town was moved from Lagolo to the present site. Rev. Francisco Gascueña, O.F.M., who built the belfry in 1800, preached the Gospel in China for six years, and on being exiled from that kingdom out of opposition to his religious teachings returned to Meycauayan. He served this parish for 31 years and died here on November 18, 1831. The Convent was built from 1731 to 1759. Both Convent and Church were seriously damaged by the typhoon of 1882.</p>"}}},"address":"Meycauayan Church, Marcos Ira Street, Meycauayan, Bulacan","name":"Church of Meycauayan","region":"Central Luzon","macroAddress":"Meycauayan, Bulacan","date":"1939","lat":14.73481},"Q28933707":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":123.84558,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Women’s Auxilary Service","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this site, May 18, 1943 was adopted the constitution and by-laws of the Women’s Auxiliary Service led by Josefa Borromeo Capistrano which assisted the Tenth Military District under Col. Wendell W. Fertic, army of the United States, in resisting the Japanese invaders. Dedicated to the courageous women of Misamis Occidental who volunteered and risked their lives for freedom.</p>"}}},"address":"La Purisima Street corner Jose P. Rizal Avenue, Ozamiz, Misamis Occidental","region":"Northern Mindanao","name":"Women’s Auxilary Service","lat":8.14225,"macroAddress":"Ozamiz, Misamis Occidental","date":null},"Q55730700":{"lat":14.59906,"macroAddress":"Bagac, Bataan","date":"2017-09-22","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Pinagsimulan ng Death March","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Mahigit 70,000 sundalong Pilipino at Amerikanong mga bihag ng digmaan noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig ang nagsimulang magmartsa sa utos ng mga sundalong Hapones mula Mariveles, Bataan, 10 Abril 1942, at Bagac, Bataan, 11 Abril 1942. Nakaranas ng pagmamalupit, matinding pagod, gutom at uhaw ang mga bihag. Marami ang namatay at ang iba ay nagkasakit. Pagdating sa San Fernando, Pampanga, isinakay sila sa tren patungong Capas, Tarlac. Ikinasawi ng marami ang kawalan ng hangin bunga ng pagsisiksikan sa mga bagon. Nakarating ang mga natirang buhay sa Capas, Tarlac at muling pinaglakad ng anim na kilometro hanggang sa bilangguan ng Camp O’Donnell, 15 Abril 1942. Kinikilala sa kasaysayan bilang Death March.</p>","title":"Pinagsimulan ng Death March","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Camacho Street, Brgy. Bagumbayan, Bagac, Bataan","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.39468,"wikipedia":{"Bataan Death March":true},"locDesc":null},"Q55285497":{"lon":121.621,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"GeneralNakar,QuezonHalljf0200 04.JPG","width":4608,"hash":"bb","height":3456},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting beside the statue of Gen. Guillermo Nakar in front of the municipal hall.","wikipedia":null,"lat":14.75686,"macroAddress":"General Nakar, Quezon","date":"2012","address":"General Nakar Municipal Hall, Brgy. Anoling, General Nakar, Quezon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pinuno ng 1<sup>st</sup> Batallion ng 71<sup>st</sup> Infantry Division ng USAFFE na lumaban sa puwersang Hapon sa Hilagang Luzon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Isinilang sa Barrio Anoling, Infanta, Tayabas (ngayo’y Quezon), 10 Hunyo 1906. Nagtapos sa Philippine Military Academy at naging kapitan sa Philippine Constabulary nang sumiklab ang digmaan, 1941. Nadakip sa Minuri, Jones, Isabela. Tumangging makipagtulungan sa mga Hapon. Dinala sa Maynila kung saan siya binitay, Setyembre 1942. Ginawaran ng ranggong brigadier general ni Pangulong Elpidio Quirino, 21 Hulyo 1949. Ipinangalan sa kanya ang bagong bayan na Gen. Nakar, Quezon, 1949 at ang Southern Luzon Command sa Lucena bilang Kampo Heneral Guillermo Nakar.</p>","title":"Guillermo Peñamante Nakar","subtitle":"(1906–1942)"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"GeneralNakar,QuezonHalljf0200 05.JPG","hash":"f9","height":4608}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Guillermo Peñamante Nakar"},"Q28927583":{"lat":6.90391,"date":"1969","macroAddress":"Zamboanga City","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"79","height":1256,"file":"City Hall of Zamboanga historical marker 10.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":848},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo noong 1905–1907 ng Pamahalaang Pederal ng Estados Unidos. Ang gusaling ito ang naging luklukan ng Pamahalaan ng Lalawigang Muslim noong panahon ng mala-militar na pananakop ng mga Amerikano, 1903–1913; ng Kagawaran ng Mindanao at Sulu noong panahon ng sibil na pananakop ng mga Amerikano, 1914–1920; ng Lalawigan ng Zamboanga, 1921–1945; at ng Lungsod ng Zamboanga mula noong 1937 hanggang sa kasalukuyan.</p>","subtitle":"(Dating Panlalawigang Kapitolyo ng Zamboanga)","title":"Bahay-Pamahalaan ng Lungsod ng Zamboanga"}}},"address":"Zamboanga City Hall, N.S. Valderrosa Street, Zamboanga City","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","name":"Bahay-Pamahalaan ng Lungsod ng Zamboanga","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.07628,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Zamboanga City Hall":true}},"Q44514157":{"name":"Simbahan ng Las Piñas","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Las Piñas Church, P. Diego Cera Avenue, Las Piñas, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang pueblo, 1762. Inihiwalay sa parokya ng Parañaque, 1775. Itinalagang unang naninirahang kura paroko si P. Diego Cera dela Virgen del Carmen, Disyembre 26, 1795. Ipinatayo niya ang simbahang bato, 1797–1819 at ang organong yari sa 902 tubong kawayan at 129 tubong lata, 1816–1824. Bahagyang nasira ng lindol, 1828 at 1863. Dahil sa magkakasunod na paglindol noong 1880, ito ay hindi na pinagdausan ng misa. Ipinakumpuni noong 1883 subalit hindi ito ganap na naisaayos. Ginamit na kampo ng mga bihag noong panahon ng pananakop ng mga Hapon at bilang pagamutan noong liberasyon. Ibinalik sa dating kaayusan sa pamamagitan ng magkasamang pagpupunyagi ng parish community at ng Historical Conservation Society, 1962–1977.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Las Piñas"},"photo":{"hash":"58","height":3609,"width":2230,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Simbahan ng Las Piñas historical marker.jpg"}}},"date":"1995-07-27","macroAddress":"Las Piñas, Metro Manila","lat":14.48117,"wikipedia":{"Las Piñas Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of the church.","lon":120.98159,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Las Piñas Church entrance and historical marker.jpg","width":4000,"hash":"e2","height":3000}},"Q22296143":{"lat":14.63779,"macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","date":"1936","address":"Santuario de San Pedro Bautista, 69 San Pedro Bautista Street, Barangay Damayan, San Francisco del Monte, Quezon City, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Church of San Francisco del Monte historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2500,"hash":"85","height":2915},"text":{"title":"Church of San Francisco del Monte","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The site was donated to the Franciscans on February 17, 1590, by Governor Santiago de Vera in the name of King Philip II. Chapels were built of thatch and bamboo in 1590, of wood in 1593, and of volcanic tuff in 1599. The last was badly damaged in the Chinese uprising of 1639. Present church built from 1696 to 1699, through the generosity of Tomas de Endaya. To this site retired for prayer and recollection several Franciscans who sufferred martyrdom in Japan in the XVII Century and others who lead missionary expeditions to Japan, China and Cambodia. The Escuela Serafica or Probation School for Filipino applicants to the Franciscan order was opened here July 16, 1931.</p>"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Church of San Francisco del Monte","lon":121.01262,"locPhoto":{"hash":"ef","height":853,"width":1280,"file":"The former facade of the San Francisco del Monte Church or San Pedro Bautista Shrine in Quezon City.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the former doorway at the original facade of the church (eastern side).","wikipedia":{"Santuario de San Pedro Bautista":true,"Martyrs of Japan":true}},"Q36178435":{"address":"Quipayo Church, Calabanga, Camarines Sur","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"b6","height":3653,"file":"Quipayo Church National Historical Institute marker.jpg","credit":"Jun pasa {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2432},"text":{"title":"Simbahang Parokya ng Quipayo","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Isa sa pinakamatatandang simbahan sa Kabikolan. Ito ay itinatag noong 1578 ng mga misyonerong Pransiskano na sina Prayle Pablo de Jesus at Bartolome Ruiz. Pinakaulo ng mga naunang misyon, ang bayan ay sumakop sa mga bisita ng Ligmanan (Libmanan), Bangon (Siruma), Calabangan (Calabanga) at Bombon hanggang sa ang mga ito ay nagsarili noong mga taong 1586, 1687, at 1749, ayon sa pagkakabanggit. Mula noong 1902 hanggang sa kasalukuyan, ang Quipayo ay naging parokyang baryo ng bayan ng Calabanga. </p><p> Buhat sa orihinal na nipa at kahoy ang kasalukuyang simbahang tisa ay ipinatayo sa pamamahala ni Prayle Francisco Gaviria noong 1616. Gayunman, ang harapan ng simbahan ay nagiba nong 1949 dahil sa malakas na pag-ulan. Patrona ng parokya ay ang Birhen ng Imakulada Konsepsiyon. Noong 1659, naging pangalawang patron nito si San Roque.</p>"}}},"name":"Simbahang Parokya ng Quipayo","region":"Bicol Region","macroAddress":"Calabanga, Camarines Sur","date":"1979","lat":13.69911,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":123.20126,"locPhoto":null},"Q23920517":{"locDesc":"The marker is located on the wall immediately to the left of the main entrance of the church.","wikipedia":{"Laoag Cathedral":true},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Oloapsaziracav {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Laoag Church main entrance.jpg","width":917,"height":792,"hash":"7c"},"lon":120.59323,"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of Laoag","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Chapel of wood and thatch built on this site when the Augustinian friars founded the parish, 1580. Replaced by this church of Italian Renaissance; foundation laid, 1612. Looted by the Chieftain Almazan who took possession of Virgin Mary's crown and proclaimed himself king, 1661. Damaged by fire, 1843; Repaired by Obras Publicas under Engineer Antonio de la Camara and Fray Santiago Muniz, 1873-1880. Occupied by Revolutionists, 1898; by American forces, 1899. Ownership contested by Aglipayans, 1901. Scene of Diocesan Marian Congress, 1932 and 1949.</p>"},"photo":{"height":4104,"hash":"37","width":2582,"credit":"Photo: Eric Jam; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Church of Laoag historical marker.jpg"}}},"address":"Laoag Cathedral, Laoag, Ilocos Norte","name":"Church of Laoag","region":"Ilocos Region","macroAddress":"Laoag, Ilocos Norte","date":"1950","lat":18.19402},"Q47073005":{"lat":15.02465,"date":null,"macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"08635jfProvincial Capitol Boulevard San Fernando City Pampangafvf 30.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":3456,"hash":"52","height":4608},"text":{"title":"Maximino H. Hizon","subtitle":"(1870–1901)","inscription":"<p>Heneral ng Himagsikan, kagawad ng Kongreso ng Malolos at makabayan. Ipinanganak sa Parian, Mexico, Pampanga noong Mayo 9, 1870. Umanib sa Katipunan, 1896. Dinakip at ipinatapon sa Jolo nang matuklasan ang lihim na samahan noong Agosto 19, 1896. Pinalaya pagkaraang lagdaan ang Kasunduan sa Biak-na-Bato. Hinirang na Komandante Heneral ng Pampanga at pagkaraan brigadyer heneral, 1898. Hinirang na kinatawan ng lalawigan ng Sorsogon sa Kongreso ng Malolos. Naging kilala sa madugong labanan sa Caloocan noong Pebrero 23, 1899, at sa mga pagsalakay sa mga pangkat ng Amerikano hindi lamang sa Pampanga kungdi sa Bataan, Zambales, Tarlac at Pangasinan. Nasugatan sa labanan sa Dumandan. Malapit sa Porac noong Enero 17, 1900, nabihag sa San Jose, Malino, Mexico noong Hunyo 19, 1900. Ipinatapon sa Guam na pook na na kanyang kinamatayan noong Setyembre 1, 1901.</p>"}}},"address":"Governor Macario Arnedo Park, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Maximino H. Hizon","lon":120.68721,"locPhoto":{"width":3456,"file":"PampangaProvincialCapitoljf67.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":4608,"hash":"ba"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is installed upright in front of the equestrian statue of Maximino Hizon.","wikipedia":null},"Q50426496":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"León Kilat":true},"lon":123.29514,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Pantaleon Villegas “Leon Kilat”","subtitle":"(1873–1898)","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Bacong, Negros Oriental, 27 Hulyo 1873. Sumanib sa Katipunan habang nasa Maynila matapos paslangin ang mga mandaragat mula sa Kabisayaan sa Calle Camba, Binondo, Setyembre 1896. Dinakip at ikinulong ng mga Espanyol, nakatakas at sumanib sa puwersang Rebolusyonaryo sa Cavite, 1897. Inatasan ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo na palawakin ang kilusang Rebolusyonaryo sa Cebu, 1897. Pinamunuan ang pag-aalsa ng Tres de Abril sa Lungsod ng Cebu, 1898. Pinaslang sa Carcar, Cebu, 8 Abril 1898. Ibinalik ang mga labi sa bayan ng Bacong, Negros Oriental, 2 Agosto 1926.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Leon Kilat Park, Dumaguete South Road, Bacong, Negros Oriental","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Pantaleon Villegas “Leon Kilat”","lat":9.24511,"date":"2000","macroAddress":"Bacong, Negros Oriental"},"Q54810400":{"date":"1983-07-05","macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","lat":17.57543,"name":"Leon C. Pichay","region":"Ilocos Region","address":"Plaza Vicente Singson Encarnacion, Calle Burgos, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker Leon Pichay.JPG","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":5268,"hash":"0a","height":3503},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Manunulat, makata. Isinilang noong Hunyo 27, 1902 sa Vigan, Ilocos Sur. Nag-aral sa Seminario de Vigan, Mataas na Paaralan ng La Union at University of Manila. Sumulat ng ilang maikling kuwento, tula at nobela sa wikang Iloko, kasaping manunulat ng The Ilocano Times; kalihim-pangkalahatan ng Romanceros Nacionales; kagawad, Unyon ng mga Patnugot at Tagapaglathala at Academia Ilocana. Mahahalagang isinulat; Puso ti Ina, Pananakadingpel ni Dr. Jose A. Burgos, Daelang ti Amianan, Sarming ti Biag at Ladingit. Namatay noong Agosto 11, 1970.</p>","subtitle":"(1902–1970)","title":"Leon C. Pichay"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.38645,"wikipedia":{"Leon Pichay":"Leon C. Pichay"},"locDesc":null},"Q25906814":{"wikipedia":{"Quiapo Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main entrance of the church at the base of the left tower.","lon":120.98361,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"0208jfQuiapo Central Church Plaza Manila Bridge Riverfvf 09.jpg","hash":"86","height":3456},"name":"Church of Quiapo","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":2635,"hash":"58","file":"Church of Quiapo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2384},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Governor General Santiago de Vera founded the District of Quiapo August 29, 1586. Franciscan missionaries built the first Church, of bamboo and nipa, that was burned in 1639. Rebuilding and repairs at intervals gave the parish the stronger edifice that the earthquake of 1863 partially destroyed. The next Church, completed in 1899, was the work of Rev. Eusebio de Leon and Rev. Manuel Roxas, the latter raising ₱40,000.00 in contributons. A fire on October 30, 1929, left the Church only its scarred walls and belfry, and a parish committee headed by Doña Encarnacion Nakpil de Orense raised the funds for its reconstruction. Juan F. Nakpil, architect, drafted the plans for the reconstructed building. A famous image of Christ bearing the Cross, called the Nazarene, is the center of intense Friday devotions througout the year.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Quiapo"}}},"address":"Quiapo Church, Plaza Miranda, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","date":"1939","lat":14.59849},"Q24702612":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.10028,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"macroAddress":"Gumaca, Quezon","date":"1981-03-17","lat":13.92294,"address":"Lakan Bugtali Boulevard, Gumaca, Quezon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1944,"credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Kutang San Diego Marker Gumaca, Quezon.JPG","height":2592,"hash":"e5"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Yari sa tinabtab na bato at may bubong na tisa, ang kutang ito ang tanging nalalabi sa ipinatayo ng mga Kastila sa pangangasiwa ng mga paring Pransiskano noong huling bahagi ng ika-18 siglo upang ipagtanggol ang bayan laban sa pagsalakay ng mga tulisang-dagat. Sa pagitan ng dalawang moog, si P. Francisco Costa ay nagpatayo noong 1850 ng matibay na pader na yari sa apog at bato upang ipangsanggalang ang bayan buhay sa hanging mula sa hilagang-silangan.</p>","title":"Kutang San Diego","subtitle":"Gumaca, Quezon"}}},"name":"Kutang San Diego","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q50377948":{"lat":14.3366,"date":"1958","macroAddress":"Biñan, Laguna","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Rizal in Biñan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>In this town of Biñan in 1871, Dr. Jose Rizal received his first formal schooling under Maestro Justiniano Cruz, who later advised him to study in a higher school in Manila.﻿</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Gen. M. Capinpin Street, Biñan, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Rizal in Biñan","lon":121.08353,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true}},"Q52799929":{"lon":120.98841,"locPhoto":{"height":1920,"hash":"e0","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Gota de Leche 09.jpg","width":1280},"wikipedia":{"Gota de Leche":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of the building.","lat":14.60279,"macroAddress":"Sampaloc, Manila","date":"1977-10-17","region":"Metro Manila","name":"La Proteccion de la Infancia, Inc.","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"La Proteccion de la Infancia.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1280,"hash":"eb","height":1539},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa lupang ipinagkaloob ng mapagkawanggawang si Teodoro R. Yangco noong 1907 upang sugpuin ang mga sakit na pumapatay ng maraming bata. Nang taon ding yaon ay itinatag ng samahan ang <u>La Gota de Leche</u> na namahagi ng sariwang gatas ng baka sa mga anak mahihirap. Itinayo rin ng samahan, sa pamamagitan ng Hukom Natividad Almeda Lopez, ang Manila Children’s Hospital na ngayo’y Manila Children’s Lying-in Hospital sa Taft Avenue, Maynila.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"La Proteccion de la Infancia, Inc."}}},"address":"Gota de Leche Building, 859 Sergio H. Loyola Street, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q54810308":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.44844,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"macroAddress":"Candon, Ilocos Sur","date":"2016-03-29","lat":17.193,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"a7","height":2114,"width":1770,"file":"Sigaw ng Candon historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"title":"Sigaw ng Candon","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito nagwagi ang mga Rebolusyonaryo sa pamumuno ni Isabelo Abaya at isinigaw ang kalayaan mula sa mga Espanyol, 25 Marso 1898. Binihag ng mga Rebolusyonaryo ang mga opisyal at prayleng Espanyol. Sa Kumbento ng Candon idineklara ang Republic Filipina Katipunan. Nabawi ng mga Espanyol ang Candon at nalansag ang Republika, 27 Marso 1898</p>"}}},"address":"Candon City Plaza, Candon, Ilocos Sur","name":"Sigaw ng Candon","region":"Ilocos Region"},"Q52144727":{"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"NasugbuBatangasjf0339 38.JPG","hash":"ad","height":3456},"lon":120.62502,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal at the rear part of the monument inside a portion modeling a boat.","wikipedia":{"Battle of Luzon":true},"date":"2007","macroAddress":"Nasugbu, Batangas","lat":14.07124,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"3e","height":4608,"file":"NasugbuBatangasjf0339 39.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456},"text":{"title":"Pagdaong sa Nasugbu","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito dumaong ang mga sundalo ng Unang Batalyon at 188<sup>th</sup> Glider Infantry ng 11<sup>th</sup> Airborne Division sa pangunguna ni Lt. General Robert Eichelberger, 31 Enero 1945. Nagsilbing kabalikat ng hukbong Amerikano ang mga gerilyang Filipino na pinangunahan ni Tenyente Koronel Marcelo Castillo at Koronel Eleuterio L. Adevoso.</p>"}}},"address":"Apacible Boulevard, Nasugbu, Batangas","name":"Pagdaong sa Nasugbu","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q35093587":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.01206,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":9.60099,"date":"2004","macroAddress":"Loay, Bohol","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Santisima Trinidad ng Loay","address":"Loay Church, Loay, Bohol","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"a7","height":495,"width":396,"file":"Loay Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang Loay bilang Barrio Santisima Trinidad sa ilalim ng Parokya ng San Pedro Apostol ng Loboc noong ika-18 dantaon. Naging parokya sa pangangasiwa ng mga misyonerong Rekoletos, 1799. Itinayo ang simbahan, 1822; ang kumbento, 1838; ang kampanaryo, 1865. Naglingkod dito si Padre Leon Inchausti, martir ng digmaang sibil sa Espanya (1936-1939) na kinanonisa bilang santo noong 1999. Mahalagang halimbawa ng arkitekturang Pilipino-Espanyol. Inihayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 18 Agosto 2003.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Santisima Trinidad ng Loay","subtitle":null}}}},"Q55347047":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located below a coffee mug sculpture.","wikipedia":{"Amadeo":"Amadeo, Cavite"},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pahimis Monument in Amadeo Municipal Hall in Cavite.jpg","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"f6"},"lon":120.92204,"address":"Amadeo Municipal Hall, A. Mabini Street, Amadeo, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Bayan ng Amadeo","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Dating Barrio ng Silang na tinawag na Gitnang Pulo, nakilala nang lumaon bilang Masilao, nagsarili noong Hulyo 15, 1872 at pinanganlang Amadeo bilang parangal sa Haring Amadeo ng Espanya. Inihiwalay sa parokya ng Silang at isinailalim sa patronahe ni Santa Maria Magdalena sa bisa ng Kautusan Blg. 424 ni Reb. P. Pedro Payo, Arsobispo ng Maynila, Mayo 1, 1884. Isinanib sa Silang sa pamamagitan ng Batas Blg. 947 ng Komisyon ng Pilipinas, Oktubre 15, 1903. Muling itinatag bilang hiwalay at nagsasariling bayan, 1915. Unang hinirang at inihalal na alkalde si Jeronimo Bayot.</p>"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"AmadeoHallComplexjf9966 32.JPG","hash":"66","height":4608}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Bayan ng Amadeo","lat":14.17022,"date":"1992","macroAddress":"Amadeo, Cavite"},"Q54803647":{"lon":121.73477,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Iguig":true},"lat":17.7504,"macroAddress":"Iguig, Cagayan","date":"1939","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of Iguig","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The town of Iguig was founded by the Rev. Ambrosio de la Madre de Dios, O.P., on December 28, 1607. The Church and the Convent were built by the Rev. Pedro de San Pedro, O.P., parish priest from 1765 to 1787.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Iguig Church, Ajat, Iguig, Cagayan","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Church of Iguig"},"Q24033367":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.52112,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Paoay Church":true},"lat":18.06161,"date":"1950","macroAddress":"Paoay, Ilocos Norte","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Parish founded by Augustinian missionaries, 1593. Cornerstone of church laid, 1704; of convent, 1707; of tower, 1793. Used before completion and kept in repair by the people under the joint auspices of the Church and the town officials. Inauguration ceremonies, 28 February 1896. Church damaged by earthquake, 1706 and 1927. Tower used as observation post by Katipuneros during the Revolution, by Guerrilleros during the Japanese Occupation.</p>","title":"Church of Paoay","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"02","height":4028,"width":2678,"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker at the Church of Paoay.jpg"}}},"address":"Paoay Church, Paoay, Ilocos Norte","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Church of Paoay"},"Q41323794":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.43713,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Sambat":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":14.26403,"macroAddress":"Pagsanjan, Laguna","date":"1988-09-20","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Labanan sa Sambat","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"ec","height":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Battle of Sambat historical marker.jpg","width":3456},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sukdulan ng unang labanan sa Laguna ng Katipunan, Sangay Maluningning, at ng lakas Kastila. Napaurong sa dami ng nasawi sa Sta. Cruz noong Nobyembre 15, 1896 ng mga casadores na may mga riple at artileriya ang 3,000 na may mga itak, sibat at ilang baril na rebulusyonaryong buhat sa Pagsanjan, Lumban, Paete, Pakil, Siniloan, Cavinte, Sta. Cruz, Magdalena at mga karatig-bayan na pinamumunuan ni Hen. Severino Taino. Huling napuksa sa tatlong oras na sagupaan sa pook na ito noong Nobyembre 16 ng Southern Expeditionary Force kasama ang 70th Infantry Regiment ni Heneral Jaramillo buhay sa Batangas ang panlikod na hanay ni Kol. Francisco Abad at ng mga cuadrilleros ng Bay. Napatay ang 'Bayani ng Sambat' at daan-daang mga katipunero sa dalawang araw na mabangi at madugong paghahamok.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa Sambat"}}},"address":"F.T. San Luis Street, Pagsanjan, Laguna"},"Q23421195":{"lat":14.55586,"macroAddress":"Makati, Metro Manila","date":"1996","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Nielson Tower","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"NielsonTower HistoricalMarker MakatiCity.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":503,"hash":"86","height":653},"text":{"title":"Nielson Tower","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo noong 1937 sa lupaing pag-aari ng mga Ayala at Cia. Ang Nielson Tower ay nagsilbing himpilang pampasahero at sentro ng pamamahala ng Paliparang Nielson. Ginamit mula 1937 hanggang 1947. Ang paliparang ito ang unang makabago at komersyal na paliparang pandaigdig sa bansa at sa magkahiwalay na panahon, ito ay naging punong himpilan ng kapwa hukbong sandatahan ng Hapon at ng Estados Unidos. Sa muling pagsasaayos ng gusali, pinanatili ng Ayala Group of Companies ang orihinal na arkitektura nito bago magkadigma upang magsilbing tagapagpagunita sa pangunguna nito sa larangan ng transportasyon at komunikasyon.</p><p>Ngayon, ang gusaling ito ang kinalalagyan ng Filipinas Heritage Library at nagsisilbing kawing ng bansa sa daigdig sa pamamagitan ng ugnayang pangkaalaman.</p>"}}},"address":"Nielson Tower, Ayala Triangle, Makati Avenue, Makati, Metro Manila","lon":121.02464,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Nielson Tower":true},"locDesc":null},"Q46865828":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.89481,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Cebu City","date":"2013","lat":10.30584,"name":"Bradford Memorial Church","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nagsimula bilang Cebu Mission Station sa Lungsod ng Cebu ng mga misyonerong Presbitero sa pangunguna ni Paul Frederic Jansen upang ipalaganap ang Protestantismo sa lalawigan ng Cebu, 1902. Sa pagtataguyod ng maybahay ni Dwight H. Day, ipinatayo ang gusaling ito, 1912 at itinalaga, 26 Oktubre 1913, bilang alaala sa inang si Matilda R.L. Bradford ng Fifth Avenue Presbyterian Church, New York City. Naging bahagi ang Bradford Memorial Church ng United Church of Christ in the Philippines simula 1948.</p>","subtitle":"1913","title":"Bradford Memorial Church"},"photo":{"width":2448,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical marker of Bradford Memorial Church.jpg","hash":"f8","height":3264}}},"address":"Matilda L. Bradford Memorial Church, 85 Osmeña Boulevard, Cebu City"},"Q24846678":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.72864,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Balayan Church":"Immaculate Conception Parish Church (Balayan)"},"lat":13.93783,"date":"1986-12-09","macroAddress":"Balayan, Batangas","address":"Balayan Church, Balayan, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Balayan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayong yari sa mahihinang kagamitan ng mga paring Pransiskano sa ilalim ng pamamahala ni Padre Francisco de Santa Maria noong 1579. Inilipat ang pamamahalang espiritwal ni Padre Juan de Oliver sa mga Heswita sa pamumuno ni Padre Pedro Chirino, 1591. Ipinatayong yari sa bato noong 1748, muling inilipat ang pamamahala ng parokya sa mga paring sekular na Kastila, 1753. Pagkaraan sa mga Rekoletos, 1876. Isinalin sa mga paring sekular na Pilipino sa ilalim ng Arsidiyosesis ng Maynila, 1908. Napalipat ang pangangasiwa sa Diyosesis ng Lipa at ang pari ay si Padre Benigno Gamez.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"79","height":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BalayanAcademyChurchjf0400 29.JPG","width":4608}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng Balayan"},"Q41212768":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.18617,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":13.62442,"date":"1972","macroAddress":"Naga, Camarines Sur","region":"Bicol Region","name":"Simbahan ng San Francisco","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"5b","height":6016,"width":4000,"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical Marker at the San Francisco Church in Naga City.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng San Francisco","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Kauna-unahang simbahan sa Naga at isa sa pinakamatanda sa Kabikulan na itinayo noong 1578. Naging tirahan ng misyonaryong Pransiskano. Pinalaki noong 1883; nasira noong 1915 at nanatiling hindi ginagamit hanggang sa maitayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan noong 1957. Sa pook ding ito sumuko sa mga Pilipino ang huling gobernador ng Ambos Camarines noong 18 Setyembre 1898.</p>"}}},"address":"Saint Francis of Assisi Parish Church, Peñafrancia Avenue, Naga, Camarines Sur"},"Q24054361":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall of St. Rita College facing the street and near the vehicular entrance to San Sebastian Church.","wikipedia":{"Beaterio de Terciarias Agustinas Recoletas":true},"lon":120.98967,"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"f1","file":"09587jfBeaterio Terciarias Agustinas Recoletas Quiapo Manilafvf 05.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3456},"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>This Beaterio dates from 1719. The religious habit was given to the first two Religious Sisters Dionisia and Cecilia Talampas Constancia by the Rev. Diego de San Jose, O.R.S.A., on July 16, 1725. The Beaterio became a teaching institution in June, 1907. The congregations of Madres Recoletas in Labrea, Brazil, and Catequistas Agustinas de Cristo Rey in Kweitehfu, China, are affiliated with it by decrees of the Holy See.</p>","title":"Beaterio de Terciarias Agustinas Recoletas","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Beaterio de Terciarias Agustinas Recoletas historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2162,"hash":"0c","height":2228}}},"address":"Saint Rita College, Pasaje del Carmen Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Beaterio de Terciarias Agustinas Recoletas","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Quiapo, Manila","date":"1939","lat":14.59943},"Q24702488":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.07707,"wikipedia":{"Pasig Cathedral":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":14.56054,"macroAddress":"Pasig, Metro Manila","date":"1937","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Church of Pasig","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"7c","height":3173,"file":"Church of Pasig historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ronaldbunag; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2198},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The first Catholic Missionary of Pasig was Rev. Alonso de Alvarado, companion of Villalobos in his expedition in Moluccas. The first church was built in 1575. The present one was used by the British for military purposes in their campaign against the military forces of Simon de Anda y Salazar.</p>","title":"Church of Pasig","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Pasig Cathedral, A. Luna Street cor. Caruncho Avenue, Pasig, Metro Manila"},"Q54152737":{"lat":14.90822,"macroAddress":"Macabebe, Pampanga","date":"2016-06-03","address":"Macabebe Municipal Hall, Poblacion, Macabebe, Pampanga","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pinamunuan ang mahigit 2,000 mandirigmang Moro buhat sa Macabebe, Hagonoy at iba pang bahagi ng Pampanga para palayasin ang mga Espanyol sa Luzon, 31 Mayo 1571. Hinimok si Lakan Dula ng Tondo na sumama sa kanyang kampanya, ngunit nakapanumpa na ito ng katapatan sa mga Espanyol, kasama sina Raha Matanda at Raha Soliman ng Maynila. Tinanggihan ang alok ni Gob. Hen. Miguel Lopez de Legazpi na pakikipagkaibigan at hinamon ito sa isang labanan sa wawa ng Ilog Bangkusay, Tondo, Look ng Maynila. Napaslang sa naturang labanan, kasama ng 300 iba pang Moro, 3 Hunyo 1571.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Kabataang Pinuno ng Macabebe"}}},"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Ang Kabataang Pinuno ng Macabebe","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.71519,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Bankusay Channel":true}},"Q44820798":{"wikipedia":{"Juan Luna":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.47691,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Birthplace of Juan Luna y Novicio","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":413,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Juan Luna historical marker in Badoc.jpg","height":612,"hash":"40"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Birthplace of Juan Luna y Novicio","inscription":"<p>Patriot and foremost Filipino painter. Born in Badoc, Ilocos Norte, 24 October 1857; son of Joaquin Luna de San Pedro and Laureana Novicio. Studied in the Ateneo Municipal, Escuela de Bellas Artes and Escuela Nautica in Manila; became a licensed pilot at 17. Pupil of Lorenzo Guerrero, noted Filipino painter. Went to Spain, 1877, studied in the Academia de Bellas Artes de San Fernando, Madrid. Painted in Rome his first famous work, “The Death of Cleopatra”. Won gold medal for his Spoliarium at the International Painting Exposition, 1884, in Madrid. Won other medals and honors in Europe. Among his other notable paintings were “The Battle of Lepanto”, “The Blood Compact”, “People and Kings”. Co-worker of Rizal, Lopez–Jaena, del Pilar and other Filipino reformers in Europe; was in the Diplomatic Service of the First Philippine Republic. Died in Hongkong, 7 December 1899.</p>"}}},"address":"Juan Luna Shrine, Rizal Street, Badoc, Ilocos Norte","date":"1957","macroAddress":"Badoc, Ilocos Norte","lat":17.92725},"Q55358996":{"lat":14.48185,"date":"1972","macroAddress":"Cavite City, Cavite","address":"Samonte Park, Judge Ibañez Street, San Roque, Cavite City, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa Lungsod na ito, noong ika-20 ng Enero 1872, nag-aklas ang mga 200 Pilipino, sa pamumuno ni Sarmento la Madrid, bilang pagtutol sa pagpapairal sa kanila ng pagbabayad ng buwis at sa pagpuwing sa kanilang karapatang mataliwas sa sapilitang paglilingkod. Bunga ng pag-aaklas ay ang pagpaparakip, paglilitis, at pagbitay sa mga paring Jose Burgos, Jacinto Zamora, at Mariano Gomez noong ika-17 ng Pebrero 1872, sa Bagumbayan, ngayo’y Rizal Park, Maynila.</p>","title":"Ang Pag-aaklas sa Kabite ng 1872","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"a6","height":4608,"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Cavite Mutiny of 1872 historical marker in Cavite City.jpg"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ang Pag-aaklas sa Kabite ng 1872","lon":120.9086,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"1872 Cavite mutiny":true}},"Q53997835":{"lon":120.97425,"locPhoto":{"width":2048,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Silang Church facade - 3.jpg","height":1536,"hash":"da"},"wikipedia":{"Silang Church":"Our Lady of Candelaria Parish Church (Silang)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting in front of the left side of the church facade.","lat":14.22378,"date":"2008","macroAddress":"Silang, Cavite","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng Silang","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Silang","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang parokya ng mga Pransiskano, 3 Pebrero 1595. Nasunog, 30 Agosto 1603. Nagtayo ng bagong simbahan ang mga Pransiskano sa patronato ni San Diego de Alcala. Inilipat sa mga Heswita, 1611. Itinayo ang simbahang yari sa bato ni Juan de Salazar, S.J., 1637–1639. Inialay sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora de Candelaria, mga taong 1640. Naging kuta ng mga guwardiya sibil nang kubkubin at itaboy sila ng mga Filipinong manghihimagsik na pinamunuan ni Hen. Vito Belarmino, 5–6 Setyembre 1896. Pinamahalaan ng mga paring sekular nang pinaalis ang mga Heswita, 1788. Inilipat sa mga Recoletos sa pamamagitan ng Real Orden, 9 Marso 1849. Ibinalik sa mga sekular, 1868. Inilipat sa mga paring Congregation of the Immaculate Heart of Mary (CICM), 1910; sekular, 1913; Columbans, 1936; at sekular muli, 1978 hanggang sa kasalukuyan. Hilambawa ng arkitekturang kolonyal na may mga retablong idinisenyo sa estilong Rococo. Nasira ng lindol ang pinakamataas na palapag ng kampanaryo, 1880. Isinaayos, 1989.</p>"},"photo":{"width":3456,"file":"Silang Church in Cavite province historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":4608,"hash":"99"}}},"address":"Silang Church, J.P. Rizal Street, Silang, Cavite"},"Q55718778":{"address":"590 Dr. Gonzalez Street, Poblacion, Baliuag, Bulacan","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":1944,"hash":"e4","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Joaquin Gonzalez historical marker in Baliuag.png","width":2096},"text":{"title":"Joaquin Gonzalez","subtitle":"(1853–1900)","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Baliwag, Bulacan, 22 Hulyo 1853. Nagkamit ng titulong Lisensiyado sa Medisina, Universidad de Valladolid at Doktor sa Medisina, Universidad Central de Madrid, rector, Universidad Cientifica Literaria de Filipinas, 1898. Kinatawan ng Pampanga sa Kongresong Mapanghimagsik at kagawad ng komite na bumalangkas sa Konstitusyon ng Malolos. Tagapangulo ng Lupon ng Serbisyo Sibil noong panahon ng Amerikano. Namatay, 21 Setyembre 1900.</p>"}}},"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Joaquin Gonzalez","lat":14.95536,"macroAddress":"Baliuag, Bulacan","date":"1982","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting on the sidewalk.","wikipedia":{"Joaquin Gonzalez":"Joaquín González (politician)"},"lon":120.90258,"locPhoto":{"hash":"41","height":1944,"width":2592,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Baliuag, Bulacan (71).jpg"}},"Q37593057":{"wikipedia":{"Andres Bonifacio":"Andrés Bonifacio"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the southern face of the pedestal of a statue of Andres Bonifacio at the middle of the plaza.","locPhoto":{"width":3456,"file":"Statue of Andrés Bonifacio at Liwasang Bonifacio, Manila.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":4608,"hash":"a9"},"lon":120.9794,"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Andres Bonifacio","address":"Liwasang Bonifacio, Padre Burgos Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"c6","height":3417,"width":2341,"credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","file":"Andrés Bonifacio historical marker at the Liwasang Bonifacio, Manila.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Bayani at rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Tondo, Maynila, 30 Nobyembre 1863. Sumapi sa Masoneriya at La Liga Filipina, 1892. Nagtatag ng Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan o Katipunan, isang lihim na kilusan na ang pangunahing adhikain ay mapagkaisa ang lahat ng mga Pilipino at itaguyod ang isang bayang malaya sa pamamagitan ng paghihimagsik, 7 Hulyo 1892. Pinamunuan ang pagsisimula ng malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa mga Espanyol, Agosto 1896. Sumalakay sa San Juan del Monte upang kubkubin ang Polvorin, 30 Agosto 1896. Pinatay sa Maragondon, Cavite, 10 Mayo 1897[.] Kinikilala bilang Supremo ng Katipunan at Ama ng Himagsikan.</p>","title":"Andres Bonifacio","subtitle":"30 Nobyembre 1863 – 10 Mayo 1897"}}},"lat":14.59453,"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"2013"},"Q56062323":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Sergio Osmeña":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.90367,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":2912,"credit":"Paolobon140 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Sergio Osmeña's birthplace Cebu Philippines.jpg","height":4368,"hash":"67"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>In a house on this site, Sergio Osmeña, Sr., was born 9 September 1878. </p><p>Served as provincial fiscal of Cebu and Negros Oriental (1905); provincial governor of Cebu (1904, 1906–1907); member and first speaker of the Philippine Assembly (1907–1922); senator (1922–1935); vice-president of the Philippine Commonwealth (1935–1944); president of the Philippine Commonwealth (1944–1946).</p>","title":"Birthplace of Sergio Osmeña, Sr.","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Osmeña Boulevard cor. Lapulapu Street, Cebu City","name":"Birthplace of Sergio Osmeña, Sr.","region":"Central Visayas","macroAddress":"Cebu City","date":"1959","lat":10.29381},"Q28944815":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":125.38564,"address":"Balangiga Church, Balangiga, Eastern Samar","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Balangiga Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":899,"height":1600,"hash":"8c"},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Balangiga","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinagawang yari sa bato sa loob ng kutang patyo na may apat na baluarte ng mga paring Heswita noong mga ika-17 na dantaon sa patronato ni San Lorenzo. Muling ipinagawa ni P. Cristobal Miralles, 1653. Visita ng Guian, 1773. Ipinaayos ni P. Manuel Valverde, 1850. Naging isang bayan, Abril 3, 1854; parokya, Setyembre 27, 1859. Dito ang mag manghihimagsik ay nagtipon-tipon para hintayin ang pagtunog ng kampana na siyang hudyat sa pagsisimula ng pag-aaklas sa Balangiga laban sa mga Amerikano, Setyempre 28, 1901. Muling ipinagawa, 1927; inayos at pinaganda, 1962-1993.</p>"}}},"name":"Simbahan ng Balangiga","region":"Eastern Visayas","macroAddress":"Balangiga, Eastern Samar","date":"1993","lat":11.10939},"Q28919864":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.84671,"address":"Fort of the Conception and Triumph, Ozamiz–Cotta Road, Ozamiz, Misamis Occidental","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayong yari sa korales sa hugis-parihaba na may apat na balwarte: San Fernando, San Jose, Santigo at San Ignacio, 1756. Punong Himpilan ng Konstabularya ng Pilipinas noong Panahon ng mga Amerikano at mga Hapon. Giniba ng lindol, 1955. Dito idinambana ang Inmaculada Concepcion na kilala rin sa tawag na Santa Mariang Birhen, Virgen sa Cota, na pinagpipitaganan at dinadayo ng mga deboto tuwing Hulyo 16. Isinaayos, 2002. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Panandang Pangkasaysayan, 13 Marso 2002.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Fuerte de la Concepcion y del Triunfo"},"photo":{"width":1093,"file":"Fuerte De La Concepcion Y Del Triunfo historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","hash":"48","height":1324}}},"name":"Fuerte de la Concepcion y del Triunfo","region":"Northern Mindanao","date":"2002","macroAddress":"Ozamiz, Misamis Occidental","lat":8.14045},"Q43267842":{"name":"Pilar Hidalgo Lim","region":"Mimaropa","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Pilar Hidalgo Lim","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Boac, Marinduque, 24 Mayo 1893. Balediktoryan, Manila High School, 1910. Unang babaeng nagtapos nang may karangalan, UP, 1913. Mga titulong pandangal: K.S. sa Gawaing Panlipunan, CEU, 1949; Doktor sa Pagtuturo, DLSC, 1964, at PWU, 1967. Maybahay ng bayaning si Hen. Vicente Lim. Nanguna, pagboto ng mga babae at rehabilitasyon ng mga salanta. Pangulo: NFWC, 1931–41; GSP, 1957–63; PFRD, 1949–51, 1953–57; CEU, 1953–73. Tumanggap ng pinakatanging gawad: Alumna, UP 1955; Ina, NFWC, 1960; Dakilang Guro, 1968; Anak ng Boac, Marinduque, 1973. Namatay, 10 Disyembre 1973.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Boac Municipal Hall, Boac, Marinduque","macroAddress":"Boac, Marinduque","date":"1982-05-24","lat":13.44684,"wikipedia":{"Pilar Hidalgo-Lim":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.84169},"Q38348252":{"lon":120.98128,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José P. Laurel":true},"lat":14.57292,"macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","date":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Jose P. Laurel","subtitle":"(1891–1959)","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Tanauan, Batangas, 9 Marso 1891. Naging Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Interyor, 9 Pebrero–17 Hulyo 1923; Senador, 1925–1931; Kinatawan, Kumbensyon Konstitusyonal, 10 Hulyo 1934–23 Marso 1935; Mahistrado (Associate Justice) ng Korte Suprema, 29 Pebrero 1936–1941; Kalihim ng Katarungan at pansamantalang Punong Mahistrado, Disyembre 1941–Enero 1942; Komisyoner para sa Kagawaran ng Katarungan (23 Enero) at Kagawaran ng Interyor (2 Disyembre), Komisyong Tagapagpaganap, 1942; at Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas, 14 Oktubre 1943–17 Agosto 1945. Tinanggihan ang lubos na kulaborasyon sa mga Hapon, kabilang ang tuwirang pagdeklara ng digmaan laban sa Estados Unidos, at sa gayon nailigtas ang mga Filipino sa ibayong pagdurusa, muling naging Senador, 1951. Yumao, 6 Nobyembre 1959.</p>"},"photo":{"height":539,"hash":"cc","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jose P. Laurel (1891 - 1959) Roxas blvd.jpg","width":381}}},"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Pedro Gil Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Jose P. Laurel"},"Q38250202":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.9723,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Antonio Luna":true},"lat":14.59829,"date":"1967-10-29","macroAddress":"San Nicolas, Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":533,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Sinilangang Pook ni Heneral Antonio Luna 1866-1899.jpg","hash":"40","height":875},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na ito, 843 Urbiztondo, isinilang si Antonio Luna noong ika-29 ng Oktubre, 1866. Anak nina Joaquin Luna de San Pedro at Laureana Novicio at kapatid ni Juan Luna, ang pintor. Parmasyutko at kimiko. Bantog na manunulat ng <u>La</u> <u>Solidaridad</u>, isang pahayagang Pilipino. Napaghinalaan ng mga Kastilang kasapi sa Katipunan, kaya ipinatapon sa Madrid noong 1897. Sa kanyang pagbabalik sa Pilipinas noong 1898, ay hinirang siyang katulong na Kalihim ng Digma; hinirang na punong komandante ng Hukbo ng Republika ng Pilipinas noong Pebrero 1899. Pinatay sa Kabanatuan, Nueva Ecija, noong ika-5 ng Hunyo, 1899.</p>","subtitle":"1866–1899","title":"Sinilangang Pook ni Heneral Antonio Luna"}}},"address":"457 Urbiztondo Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Sinilangang Pook ni Heneral Antonio Luna"},"Q54134796":{"wikipedia":{"Pililla Church":"Saint Mary Magdalene Parish Church (Pililla, Rizal)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade, to the right of the main entrance.","locPhoto":{"hash":"39","height":3072,"width":2304,"credit":"Raani Paranas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Pililla Church.JPG"},"lon":121.30666,"name":"Simbahan ng Pililla","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2304,"credit":"Raani Paranas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Marker of Pililla Church.JPG","hash":"37","height":3072},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dumating ang mga unang paring misyonero noong 1572 sa pook na ito. Unang simbahang kawayan at kogon ay ipinagawa ng mga paring Pransiskano noong 1585 sa ilalim ng patrona Santa Maria Magdalena. Naging simbahang tabla at pawid noong 1599. Nasunog noong 1632 ang simbahang bato at muling itinayo noong 1670–1673.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Pililla"}}},"address":"Pililla Church, Imatong, Pililla, Rizal","date":"1977","macroAddress":"Pililla, Rizal","lat":14.48021},"Q54665306":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the building facade, to the left of the main entrance.","locPhoto":{"width":3872,"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Associacion de Damas de Filipinas Settlement House driveway.jpg","hash":"a9","height":2592},"lon":120.9985,"name":"Asociacion de Damas de Filipinas, Inc.","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Asociacion de Damas de Filipinas Settlement House, 1451 Quirino Avenue Extension, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3872,"hash":"91","width":2592,"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Associacion de Damas de Filipinas historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang Asociacion de Damas de Filipinas, Inc. ay itinatag noong Setyembre 26, 1913 ng mga maybahay ng mga nangunang kasapi ng Philippine Columbian Club bilang kababaihang pantulong o auksilyar ng samahan na ang unang pangulo ay si Dr. Honoria Acosta. Ang mga unang pagpupunyagi nito ay upang makalikom ng pondo para sa pamayanan ng mga may ketong sa Culion, iba’t ibang bahay-ampunan, mga nasunugan at mga mahihirap na nagpapasusong ina. Noong 1919 itinatag nito ang panirahan sa isang paupahang gusali sa Abenida Rizal, Maynila upang magsilbing pansamantalang kanlungan para sa mga sanggol, mga bata, hindi kasal na mga ina at mga matatanda. Inilipat sa Daang Benavides sa Santa Cruz noong 1926 at sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan nito sa Daang Canonigo, Paco noong 1927.</p><p>Ang panirahan ay naging kanlungan ng mga nagsisilikas. Naging pagamutan at klinika para sa mga mamamayan noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, pagkatapos ng digmaan, ang gusali ay sumailalim sa pagbabagong-ayos. Isang dagdag na gusali na may mga makabagong kagamitan ang ipinatayo mula 1955 hanggang 1963. Ang aklatan at paaralan para sa mga bata ay pinasinayaan noong 1997. Ang saligang batas nito ay sinusugan noong Enero 15, 1998 upang ibilang ang mga karagdagang interes.</p>","title":"Asociacion de Damas de Filipinas, Inc.","subtitle":"Settlement House"}}},"date":"1998-09-26","macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","lat":14.58136},"Q24816799":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Felipe Agoncillo y Encarnacion 1859–1941","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Abogado, estadista, at makabayan. Ipinanganak sa Taal 26 Mayo 1859. Batsilyer sa Artes, Ateneo Municipal de Manila; Lisensiyado sa Batas, Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas. Masiglang kagawad ng Lupong Pilipino ng Himagsikan sa Hong Kong. Ministro ng Plenipotensiyaryo noong unang Republika ng Pilipinas. Caballero dela Cruz Roja Española, iginawad ng Pamahalaang Kastila. Diputado ng unang purok ng Batangas sa Asamblea Pilipina, 1907–09. Kalihim Panloob ng gabinete ni Gobernador Wood, 1924–25. Pangulo sa loob ng anim na sunud-sunod na taon ng Colegio de Abogados de Filipinas. Pangulo ng Unang Kongreso ng Pilipinas sa Pagsasarili, Maynila, 22–26 Pebrero 1930. Namatay sa Maynila 29 Setyembre 1941.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2500,"file":"Felipe Agoncillo y Encarnacion historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"9d","height":3848}}},"address":"Don Gregorio Agoncillo Mansion, Palico-Balayan-Batangas Road cor. Calle Felipe Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas","name":"Felipe Agoncillo y Encarnacion 1859–1941","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","date":"1955","lat":13.87818,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located beneath a statue of Felipe Agoncillo that is erected at the front lawn of the Don Gregorio Agoncillo Mansion.","wikipedia":{"Felipe Agoncillo":true},"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Taaljf2115 13.JPG","hash":"db","height":3456},"lon":120.92528},"Q43304094":{"locDesc":"The historical markers are located on opposite sides of the pedestal for the statue of Juan Luna.","wikipedia":{"Juan Luna":true},"lon":120.97865,"locPhoto":{"hash":"ed","height":2294,"width":1536,"file":"Juan Luna Monument.jpg","credit":"Nikond80 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"JuanLunajf0501 03.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"hash":"04","height":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Painter, patriot and diplomat. Born on October 24, 1857 in Badoc, Ilocos Norte. Studied at Ateneo Municipal de Manila, Escuela de Bellas Artes and Escuela Nautica, Manila; and Academia de Bellas Artes de San Fernando, Madrid, Spain. Painted in Rome the famous “The Death of Cleopatra,” 1881 and “Spoliarium,” 1884, and “The Battle of Lepanto,” “The Blood Compact,” “People and Kings” and others. Associate of Jose Rizal, Graciano Lopez Jaena and Marcelo H. del Pilar in the Propaganda Movement. Diplomatic agent of Gen. Emilio Aguinaldo, Paris, 1898. Died in Hongkong on December 7, 1899.</p><p>By virtue of Presidential Decree No. 260, 1 August 1973, as amended by Presidential Decree No. 375, 14 January 1974, and No. 1505, 11 June 1978. This monument is declared a National Historical Monument.</p>","subtitle":"(1857–1899)","title":"Juan Luna y Novicio"}},"tl":{"text":{"title":"Juan Luna y Novicio","subtitle":"(1857–1899)","inscription":"<p>Pintor, makabayan at diplomat. Isinilang noong Oktubre 24, 1857 sa Badoc, Ilocos Norte. Nag-aral sa Ateneo Municipal de Manila, Escuela de Bellas Artes at Escuela Nautica, Maynila; at Academia de Bellas Artes de San Fernando, Madrid, Espanya. Ipininta sa Roma ang kilalang “The Death of Cleopatra,” 1881, at “Spoliarium,” 1884; at “The Battle of Lepanto,” “The Blood Compact,” “People and Kings,” atbp.. Kasama nina Jose Rizal, Graciano Lopez Jaena at Marcelo H. del Pilar sa Kilusang Propaganda. Sugong pandiplomatiko ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo, Paris, 1898. Namatay sa Hongkong noong Disyembre 7, 1899.</p><p> Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Blg. 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan ng Pangulo Blg. 375, 14 Enero 1974, at Blg. 1505, 11 Hunyo 1978, ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Bantayog Pangkasaysayan.</p>"},"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"4e","width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Juan Luna historical marker in Intramuros.jpg"}}},"address":"Padre Burgos Avenue cor. General Luna Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Juan Luna y Novicio","region":"Metro Manila","date":"1985-12-14","macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","lat":14.58532},"Q22236932":{"lat":14.57816,"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"1984","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Manuel S. Guerrero","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"d4","height":354,"width":455,"file":"Manuel S. Guerrero (1877 - 1919).jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"title":"Manuel S. Guerrero","subtitle":"(1877–1919)","inscription":"<p>Ama ng pag-aaral ng beriberi sa mga sanggol sa Pilipinas. Ipinanganak sa Ermita, Maynila, Enero 8, 1877. Nagtapos ng A.B. sa Ateneo Municipal, 1894, at Doktor sa Medicina sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, 1902. Sumulat para sa Republica Filipina, La Independencia at La Patria. Kagawad ng patnugutan, Manila at Revista Filipina de Medicina y Farmacia. Kagawad, Colegio Medico-Farmaceutico, Asamblea de Medicos y Farmaceuticos de Filipinas at Sanggunian ng Kalusugan. Isa sa mga nagtatag ng Liga Nacional Filipina para la Proteccion de la Infancia at La Gota de Leche. Pinagkalooban ng mga medalyang pilak ng Louisiana Purchase Exposition at Panama Pacific International Exposition. Namatay, Enero 4, 1919.</p>"}}},"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Plaza Nuestra Señora de Guia Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.9785,"wikipedia":{"Manuel S. Guerrero":true},"locDesc":null},"Q55743859":{"lat":15.51084,"date":"2003","macroAddress":"Cabanatuan, Nueva Ecija","address":"Camp Pangatian Memorial Shrine, Km. 124 Nueva Ecija–Aurora Road, Brgy. Pangatian, Cabanatuan, Nueva Ecija","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Raid at Cabanatuan Memorare English historical marker (cropped).JPG","credit":"Judgefloro","width":2348,"hash":"fa","height":2799},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Memorare","inscription":"<p>On the night of January 30, 1945, Filipino guerillas under Captains Juan Pajota and Eduardo Joson effectively prevented Japanese reinforcements at Pangatian Concentration Camp in Cabanatuan. The blockade at Bangad resulted in the liberation of 516 Allied prisoners of war. The joint operation of the guerillas, Alamo Scouts and the U.S. 6th Ranger Battalion was under Lt. Col. Henry Mucci. This event is considered one of the most successful rescue missions of its type in the annals of U.S. military history.</p>"}},"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Raid at Cabanatuan Memorare Filipino historical marker (cropped).jpg","width":2179,"height":2544,"hash":"31"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Memorare","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito, noong gabi ng 30 Enero 1945, matagumpay na hinadlangan ng mga gerilyang Filipino, sa pamumuno nina Kapitan Juan Pajota at Eduardo Joson, ang pagdating ng mga kawal at kagamitan sa Pangatian Concentration Camp sa Cabanatuan. Nagbunga ang labanan sa Tulay Cabu at pagbabarikada sa Bangad sa pagpapalaya ng 516 bihag ng digmaan. Pinamunuan ang magkasanib na operasyon ng mga gerilya, mga Alamo Scouts at ng 6th Ranger Battalion ng Estados Unidos ni Tenyente Koronel Henry Mucci. Itinuturing ito na isa sa pinakamatagumpay na misyon ng pagliligtas sa kasaysayan militar ng Estados Unidos.</p>"}}},"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Memorare","lon":121.04353,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Raid at Cabanatuan":true}},"Q24188594":{"lon":123.18786,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Universidad de Sta. Isabel":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Naga, Camarines Sur","lat":13.62833,"name":"Colegio de Santa Isabel","region":"Bicol Region","address":"Universidad de Sta. Isabel, Elias Angeles Street, Naga, Camarines Sur","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"39","height":2686,"file":"Colegio de Santa Isabel historical marker.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito; perspective correction: Ervin Malicdem (schadow1) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2729},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Colegio de Santa Isabel","inscription":"<p>The Rt. Rev. Francisco C. Gainza, O.P., Bishop of Nueva Caceres (1862-1879), was the promoter and founder of this college named in honor of Saint Isabel, Queen of Hungary. It was solemnly blessed and opened September 18, 1870. By a royal decree of January 11, 1872, it became the first normal school for girls in the Philippines. During its existence from 1877 to 1898, three hundred students were graduated.</p>"}}}},"Q41972059":{"lon":120.97708,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"RizalParkjf8267 04.JPG","hash":"ef","height":3456},"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locDesc":"The Tagalog and English historical markers are located on a granite mounting at the entrance to the execution site.","lat":14.58234,"date":"1996","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Rizal’s Execution Site","address":"Rizal Park, Roxas Boulevard cor. Padre Burgos Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Jose Rizal y Mercado, Filipino physician, propagandist, writer, and patriot was executed within these hallowed grounds at exactly 7:03 in the morning of December 30, 1896 by an eight-man squad of Filipino riflemen from the 70th Infantry Regiment, the ‘Magallanes’, of the Spanish colonial army.</p><p>Those who witnessed Rizal’s public execution included Lt. Luis Taviel de Andrade, his legal defender during his trial for alleged treason against Spain, and the two Jesuit priests, Fr. Jose Villaclara, S.J. and Fr. Estanislao March, S.J. who accompanied Rizal during his final walk before his execution.</p><p>Rizal’s martyrdom fanned the flames of the Filipino Revolution of 1896 and inspired the Filipinos in their resolute and epic fight for freedom.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Rizal’s Execution Site"},"photo":{"height":3475,"hash":"bc","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Rizal's Execution Site historical marker.jpg","width":2500}},"tl":{"text":{"title":"Pook ng Pinagbarilan kay Rizal","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Si Jose Rizal y Mercado, manggagamot na Pilipino, propagandista, manunulat, at makabayan ay binaril sa banal na pook na ito noong ganap na ika-7:03 nang umaga ng Disyembre 30, 1896 ng iskwad na binubuo ng walong Pilipinong mamamaril buhat sa ika-70 Rehimyento, ang Magallanes, ng hukbong kolonyal ng mga Kastila.</p><p>Kabilang sa madlang nakasaksi sa pagbaril kay Rizal sina Tinyente Luis Taviel de Andrade, ang kanyang manananggol sa paglilitis sa bintang na pagtataksil sa Espanya, at ang dalawang paring Heswita, sina P. Jose Villaclara at P. Estanislao March, na sumama kay Rizal sa kanyang huling paglakad bago siya binaril. </p><p> Ang kanyang kamatayan bilang martir ang nagpalagablab sa apoy ng Himagsikang Pilipino noong 1896 at nagbigay-sigla sa mga Pilipino sa kanilang walang takot at dakilang pakikipaglaban para sa kalayaan.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pook na Pinagbarilan kay Rizal historical marker.jpg","width":2500,"height":3750,"hash":"fc"}}}},"Q52664972":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Elpidio Quirino","subtitle":"(1890–1956)","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Vigan, Ilocos Sur, noong Nobyembre 19, 1890. Unang nagtrabaho sa gulang na 16 na taon bilang guro sa Baryo Caparia-an. Naging Pangulo ng Pilipinas nang mamatay ang Pangulong Manuel Roxas noong Abril 15, 1948. Inihalal bilang Pangulo ng Pilipinas noong Nobyembre 1949. Namatay noong Pebrero 29, 1956.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Kilometer 247, MacArthur Highway, Caba, La Union","name":"Elpidio Quirino","region":"Ilocos Region","macroAddress":"Caba, La Union","date":"1983-11-16","lat":16.4279,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Elpidio Quirino":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.35},"Q55085958":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"University of the Philippines Cebu":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.89834,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"University of the Philippines Cebu College","inscription":"<p>Nagsimula na Junior College of Liberal Arts sa dating Warwick Barracks; Dr. Lawrence Wharton, unang dekano, 1918. Inilipat sa pook ng Parian at pinangalanang Junior College of the University of the Philippines (U.P.); Dr. Jose Mirasol, unang Filipinong dekano, 1922; at sa Fort San Pedro, 1925. Ipinagkaloob ng Lalawigan ng Cebu ang kampus sa Lahug at pinasinayaan ang pangunahing gusali, 1929. Ginamit ng pwersang Hapones bilang piitan, 1942–1945l ng U.S. Navy General Engineering at muling binuksan bilang paarlan, 1945. Ipinaayos sa tulong ng U.S.–Philippine War Damage Commission, 1946. Ipinasara ng pamahalaan at inupahan ng mga Heswita bilang Berchmans College, 1950. Ibinalik sa U.P., 1963. Naging bahagi ng University of the Philippines Visayas (UPV), 1986–2010. Pinagkalooban ng U.P. Board of Regents ng autonomiya bilang U.P. Cebu College sa ilalim ng Tanggapan ng Pangulo ng Unibersidad, 24 Setyembre 2010.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"3c","height":3264,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"UP Cebu historical marker.jpg","width":2448}}},"address":"University of the Philippines Cebu, Gorordo Avenue, Cebu City","region":"Central Visayas","name":"University of the Philippines Cebu College","lat":10.32233,"macroAddress":"Cebu City","date":"2010-12-02"},"Q39773891":{"lat":14.56372,"macroAddress":"Makati, Metro Manila","date":"2008-09-02","address":"Ayala Avenue Extension cor. Kamagong Street, Makati, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Philippine Dental Association","inscription":"<p>Umiral ang pagdedentista sa Pilipinas sa panahong prekolonyal ayon sa ebidensyang arkeolohikal. Itinuro bilang bahagi ng edukasyong medikal sa panahon ng mga Espanyol. Itinatag bilang isang legal na propesyon, 10 Enero 1903. Binuo ang unang kalupunan ng mga tagasulit Dr. Robert T. Oliver, unang pangulo. Itinatag ang Sociedad Dental de Filipinas upang itaas ang antas ng propesyong dental, Escolta, Manila, 11 Hulyo 1908; Dr. Bonifacio Arevalo, unang pangulo. Itinatag ang National Dental Association, 1925; Dr. Francisco Tecson, unang pangulo. Pinag-isa ang dalawang samahan at naging Philippine Dental Association, 12 Agosto 1945; Dr. Joaquin C. Ladao, unang pangulo. Pinasinayaan, 7 Setyembre 1945.</p>"},"photo":{"width":503,"file":"PDA marker, Makati.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"05","height":745}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Philippine Dental Association","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.01586,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q54086773":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Leonor Rivera":"Leonor Rivera–Kipping","Concordia College":"Concordia College (Manila)","José Rizal":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.00261,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Concordia College Marker 2.jpg","width":368,"height":408,"hash":"09"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa kolehiyong ito, na itinatag ni Donya Margarita Roxas de Ayala noong 1868 at pinangasiwaan ng Daughters of Charity, nag-aral ang tatlong butihing kapatid ng pambansang bayaning si Dr. Jose Rizal na sina Saturnina, Soledad at Olympia. Dito nakilala ni Rizal ang kanyang unang pag-ibig sa katauhan ni Segunda Katigbak gayundin si Leonor Rivera na pinag-ukulan niya ng tunay na pagmamahal at binigyang buhay sa kanyang walang kamatayang nobelang \"Noli Me Tangere.\"</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Concordia College"}}},"address":"Concordia College, 1739 Pedro Gil Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Concordia College","lat":14.5812,"macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","date":"1996"},"Q35096799":{"lat":10.15097,"date":"2015","macroAddress":"Talibon, Bohol","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Katedral ng Talibon","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Heswita bilang parokya, 1722. Nagsimula ang pagtatayo ng simbahang gawa sa bato sa ilalim ng ma Rekoleto, 1852, sa pangangasiwa ni Lorenzo Mayor, 1851–1861. Idinagdag ang kampanaryo sa panahon ni Jose Sanchez, 1868–1875. Nagsilbing sentro ng Katolisismo sa hilagang Bohol. Naging katedral sa patronato ng Santisima Trinidad at luklukan ng Diyosesis ng Talibon, 1986.</p>"}}},"address":"Talibon Cathedral, Talibon, Bohol","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Katedral ng Talibon","locPhoto":null,"lon":124.32616,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q24702389":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"The Cathedral of Palo","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Constructed, 1596 under the direction of the Jesuits who founded Palo. Used for some time as their residence. Taken over by the Augustinians, 1768; by the Franciscans, 1843. Repaired by Fr. Agustin de Consuegra, who built the two towers, 1850; by Fr. Pantaleon de la Fuente, who installed a clock on the facade, 1896. Proclaimed a cathedral, 25 March 1938. Msgr. Manuel Mascariñas, first bishop. Used as hospital, October, 1944 to March, 1945, by American Liberation forces.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"The Cathedral of Palo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Jojit Ballesteros; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2000,"hash":"f3","height":3056}}},"address":"Palo Cathedral, Palo, Leyte","name":"The Cathedral of Palo","region":"Eastern Visayas","macroAddress":"Palo, Leyte","date":"1954","lat":11.15926,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Palo Cathedral":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.99163},"Q30087463":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main steps of the Pinaglabanan Shrine.","wikipedia":{"Pinaglabanan Shrine":true},"lon":121.03047,"locPhoto":{"width":4000,"file":"Pinaglabanan Shrine NHCP historical marker vicinity.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"4d","height":3000},"address":"Pinaglabanan Shrine, San Juan, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Pinaglabanan Shrine NHCP historical marker.jpg","width":1471,"hash":"3d","height":1773},"text":{"title":"Pang-alaalang Dambana ng Pinaglabanan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ginawang Pambansang Dambana sa bisa ng Utos Pampangulo Blg. 260, Agosto 1, 1973.</p><p>Ang pook at bantayog ay sinimulang itayo ng Pang-alaalang Komisyon ng Pinaglabanan na itinatag sa bisa ng Utos Tagapagpaganap Blg. 394. Inilipat sa Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan noong Pebrero 4, 1974.</p>"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Pang-alaalang Dambana ng Pinaglabanan","lat":14.60475,"date":"1976-08-30","macroAddress":"San Juan, Metro Manila"},"Q54553120":{"name":"Monte de Piedad and Savings Bank","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":501,"file":"MonteDePiedad HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":819,"hash":"0c"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Oldest savings bank in the Philippines. Founded by Fr. Felix Huertas (de Huerta) of the Franciscan Order with the funds of the Obras Pias. Inaugurated 2 August 1882. Originally located at the ground floor of Santa Isabel College, corner of Arzobispo and Anda Streets, Intramuros. Transferred to Monte de Piedad Building (now Roman Santos Building) Plaza Goiti, 1894. President Manuel L. Quezon was at one time employed as clerk. Moved to present site 1938. Edifice destroyed during Liberation of Manila 1945. Rebuilt 1946 and resumed operation 1947. Administered by Archbishop of Manila until 1949 when it was incorporated. Patron saint is Santo Cristo del Tesoro, whose feast day is celebrated 14th September.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Monte de Piedad and Savings Bank"}}},"address":"Monte de Piedad Building, Ronquillo Street cor. Ongpin Street, Plaza Santa Cruz, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1959","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","lat":14.60011,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":120.98016,"locPhoto":null},"Q55299427":{"macroAddress":"Mauban, Quezon","date":"1982","lat":14.18984,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Horacio de la Costa, S.J.","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Mauban, Quezon, noong 9 Mayo 1916. Paring iskolar at mananalaysay. Natamo ang titulong Doktor sa Pilosopiya sa Harvard University, 1951. May akda: The Jesuits in the Philippines, 1581–1768. Readings in Philippine History, Background of Nationalism, Asia and the Philippines at ilang sanaysay. Unang Pilipinong puno ng mga Heswita sa bansa, 1964; katulong na pangkalahatan at tagapayo ng Padre Heneral ng mga Heswita sa Roma, 1971; kagawad ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan. Namatay noong 20 Marso 1977.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Plaridel Street cor. San Buenaventura Street, Mauban, Quezon","name":"Horacio de la Costa, S.J.","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.73147,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Horacio de la Costa":true}},"Q43301970":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.92214,"address":"Iskong Bantay, Iskong Bantay Street cor. Angeles Street, Atimonan, Quezon","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>The only observation and defense tower existing of the seven built around 1752 in Atimonan, Quezon (Tayabas), to guard the sea coast against pirates. Repaired, 1948–1951 by the Municipality of Atimonan, naming it in memory of Francisco Tandas, popularly called Iskong Bantay, chief defender of the town in the raid of 1872.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Iskong Bantay"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Iskong Bantay","lat":14.00278,"macroAddress":"Atimonan, Quezon","date":"1952"},"Q44820670":{"macroAddress":"Badoc, Ilocos Norte","date":"1977","lat":17.92722,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Bahay ni Luna","inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Resolusyon Bilang 3, Oktubre 7, 1976 ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan na binigyan ng karapatan ng Seksyon 4 ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973, na sinusugan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974 ang gusali at pook na ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"47","height":922,"width":691,"file":"Bahay ni Luna historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"address":"Juan Luna Shrine, Rizal Street, Badoc, Ilocos Norte","name":"Bahay ni Luna","region":"Ilocos Region","lon":120.47696,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Juan Luna":true}},"Q28865725":{"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Henson-Hizon House","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 27 January 2003.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Henson-Hizon House"},"photo":null}},"address":"Henson-Hizon House, V. Tiomico Street, San Fernando, Pampanga","lat":15.0262,"macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","date":"2003","wikipedia":{"Henson-Hizon House":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.69013},"Q28942505":{"lat":7.38406,"date":"2014-04-02","macroAddress":"Parang, Maguindanao","address":"Camp Brigadier General Salipada K. Pendatun, Parang, Maguindanao","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Salipada K. Pendatun (1921–1985)","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Pikit, Cotabato, 3 Disyembre 1912. Nagtapos ng abogasya sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas at pumasa sa Philippine Bar, 1938. Hinirang bilang kasapi ng Lupong Panlalawigan ng Cotabato, 1938; nahalal, 1940. Nakomisyon bilang 3rd Lieutenant, Philippine Army Reserve Force at napabilang sa USAFFE bago sumiklab ang Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Kasama si Datu Udtog Matalam, nagtatag ng isang puwersang gerilya laban sa mga Hapon sa Cotabato. Hinirang bilang Gobernador ng Cotabato pagkatapos ng digmaan. Nahalal bilang senador, 1946-1949; tagapayo, administrasyong Quirino, 1950-1953; kinatawan ng lalawigan ng Cotabato sa Kongreso, 1958-1961; 1962-1965; 1966-1969; 1970-1972; Speaker Pro Tempore, 1962-1967; kinatawan ng Maguindanao sa Regular Batasang Pambansa at Speaker Pro Tempore, 1984-1985. Yumao, 27 Enero 1985.</p>"}}},"region":"Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao","name":"Salipada K. Pendatun (1921–1985)","lon":124.25707,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Salipada Pendatun":true}},"Q43282847":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.84185,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dambana ng Banal na Ina ng Biglang Awa na itinayo noong 1792. Naniniwala ang mga tao na siya ang nagligtas sa pagsalakay ng mga Moro noong ika-18 dantaon. Dito binindisyunan ang bandila ng himagsikan na dala ni Canuto Vargas noong 1899. Ang pari ng parokya, Saturnino Trinidad, ay tumulong kay Kapitan H. H. Bandholtz, U.S.A. sa pagpapasuko kay Koronel Maximo Abad at sa 300 manghihimagsik.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Boac","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Boac Cathedral, Boac, Marinduque","region":"Mimaropa","name":"Simbahan ng Boac","lat":13.44856,"macroAddress":"Boac, Marinduque","date":"1972"},"Q24702224":{"date":"1952","macroAddress":"Lucena","lat":13.93581,"address":"Manuel Quezon Avenue, Lucena","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Lucena historical marker.jpg","width":2750,"height":4619,"hash":"eb"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating nayon ng Tayabas na sunod-sunod na pinangalanang Buenavista, Oroquieta at Cotta bago tinawag na bayang Lucena, 1 Hunyo 1882, na siyang pangalan ng bayang sinilangan sa Espanya ni P. Mariano Granja, unang paroko. Faustino Enriquez, unang punong-bayan.</p>","title":"Lucena","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Lucena","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.61311,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Lucena":"Lucena, Philippines"}},"Q24727862":{"address":"Clark Freeport Zone, Angeles","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3105,"hash":"bc","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Death Place of Roxas historical marker.jpg","width":2000},"text":{"title":"Death Place of Roxas","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this Base, at then official residence of the Commanding General of the United States 13th Air Force, Manuel Roxas, First President of the Republic of the Philippines, soldier, statesman and exponent of Philippine–American friendship, died on 15 April 1948.</p>"}}},"name":"Death Place of Roxas","region":"Central Luzon","macroAddress":"Angeles","date":"1955","lat":15.179,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Manuel Roxas":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.51867},"Q36011972":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"The Aristocrat","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nagsimula sa isang lumang sasakyang ginamit ni Engracia Cruz-Reyes o Aling Asiang bilang tindahan ng meryenda na lumilibot sa Luneta at iba pang kalapit pook sa Maynila, Hulyo 1936. Dito itinatag ang unang gusaling kinilalang The Admiral Dewey at kinalauna’y pinangalanang The Aristocrat, 1939. Isa sa mga tanyag na kainang nagtampok ng mga lutuing Pilipino.</p>","title":"The Aristocrat","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":303,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"The Aristocrat.jpg","height":363,"hash":"56"}}},"address":"423 San Andres Street cor. Roxas Boulevard, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.56834,"macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","date":"2013-07-04","wikipedia":{"Engracia Cruz-Reyes":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98363},"Q54669717":{"lat":14.55054,"macroAddress":"Pasay, Metro Manila","date":"1986-11-24","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"","subtitle":"(1895–1986)","title":"Eduardo A. Quisumbing"},"photo":null}},"address":"327 College Road, Pasay, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Eduardo A. Quisumbing","lon":120.99908,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Eduardo Quisumbing":true}},"Q52261152":{"wikipedia":{"Battle of Tres de Abril":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.88874,"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Ang Madugong Linggo ng Palaspas","address":"Tres de Abril Street cor. V. Rama Avenue, Cebu City","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2448,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Tres de Abril historical marker.jpg","hash":"71","height":3264},"text":{"subtitle":"1898","title":"Ang Madugong Linggo ng Palaspas","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito, noong ika-3 ng Abril, 1898 nagbalikwas ang mga taga-Sebu, sa pamumuno ni Hen. Pantaleon Villegas, laban sa mga Kastila. Naging madugo ang labanan kaya’t ang araw ng paglalabanan ay tinawag na madugong Linggo ng Palaspas.</p>"}}},"lat":10.29679,"date":"1966","macroAddress":"Cebu City"},"Q42931575":{"address":"Pulang Lupa Historical and Ecotourism Park, Brgy. Bolo, Torrijos, Marinduque","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito naganap ang madugong labanan ng Hukbong Pilipino sa pamumuno ni Tenyente–Koronel Maximo Abad at Hukbong Amerikano sa pamumuno ni Kapitan Devereux Shields noong Setyembre 13, 1900. Nagtagumpay ang mga Pilipino sa labanang ito. </p><p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 1505, Hunyo 11, 1978, ang pook na ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan noong Setyembre 24, 1991.</p>","title":"Ang Labanan sa Pulang Lupa","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"region":"Mimaropa","name":"Ang Labanan sa Pulang Lupa","lat":13.35847,"macroAddress":"Torrijos, Marinduque","date":"2000-09-13","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Pulang Lupa":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.09186},"Q31764159":{"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Dauis Church Complex","address":"Dauis Church, Dauis, Bohol","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3648,"hash":"51","credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","file":"Dauis Church Complex historical marker.jpg","width":2736},"text":{"title":"Dauis Church Complex","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Binubuo ng simbahan, kumbento, bantayan at kampanaryo na pawang yari sa korales. Itinatag ng mga paring Heswita bilang visita ng Baclayon ay naging parokya sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora de Asuncion, 1697. Ipinatayo ni Padre Joseph Nepomuceno, S.J. ang kumbento na naging opisyal na tirahan ng mga Heswita mula sa Loboc, 1753-1768. Isinailalim sa mga paring Recoletos, 1768. Ipinatayo ni Padre Santiago del Corazon de Jesus, O.A.R., and kampanaryo, 1774. Pinatibay ang bakuran bilang depensa sa pagsalakay ng mga piratang Moro, 1885. Inumpisahang ipatayo ni Padre Julio Saldaña, O.A.R. ang kasalukuyang simbahan, 1863-1879. Tinapos ni Padre Natalio del Mar na may pintadong obra ni Ray Francia at Canuto Avila, 1919-1923. Pinasinayaan ni Monsignor Juan Gorordo ng Cebu, 23 Agosto 1923. Naging kanlungan ng mga madre ng Holy Spirit ng Tagbilaran ang kumbento noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Itinalaga bilang Shrine of Our Lady of Assumption, 15 Agosto 2004. Halimbawa ng arkitekturang Neo-Gothic at Neo-Classic. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 2009.</p>"}}},"lat":9.62623,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"Dauis, Bohol","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.86522},"Q28937488":{"lat":7.41277,"date":"1956","macroAddress":"Braulio E. Dujali, Davao del Norte","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Davao Penal Colony","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Established 21 January 1932 under Act 3732 of the Philippine Legislature on a site reserved by Proclamation no. 414 issued by Governor-General Dwight F. Davis on 7 October 1931; first penal colony founded under the administration of a Filipino Director of Prisons, Lt. Col. Paulino Santos. First superintendent, Pablo I. Norona, later assistant director of prisons. The official and prisoners of the colony were transferred by the Japanese forces to Iwahig Penal Colony, 8 November 1942; served as evacuation center for residents of Davao city during the early part of World War II; used as concentration camp for American prisoners of war; Colony was reopened 2 August 1946.</p>"}}},"address":"Davao Prison and Penal Farm, Sitio Dapecol, Brgy. Tanglaw, Braulio E. Dujali, Davao del Norte","region":"Davao Region","name":"Davao Penal Colony","locPhoto":null,"lon":125.623,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Davao Prison and Penal Farm":true}},"Q31766805":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.86509,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Dauis","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Heswita bilang visita ng Baclayon; Naging parokya sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora de Asuncion, 1697. Ipinamahal sa mga paring Recoletos, 1768. Inumpisahang ipatayo ni Padre Julio Saldaña, O.A.R. ang kasalukuyang simbahan, 1863-1879. Ipinagpatuloy ni Padre Natalio del Mar, 1919-1923. Isinagawa ni Ray Francia at Canuto Avila ang mga pintadong obra sa loob ng simbahan. Pinasinayaan ni Monsignor Juan Gorordo ng Cebu, 23 Agosto 1923. Itinalaga bilang Shrine of Our Lady of Assumption, 15 Agosto 2004. Halimbawa ng arkitekturang Neo-Gothic at Neo-Classic. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 2009.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Dauis church historical marker.jpg","width":768,"hash":"b3","height":1024}}},"address":"Dauis Church, Dauis, Bohol","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Dauis","lat":9.62549,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"Dauis, Bohol"},"Q53165353":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the front side of the pedestal of the monument sculpture.","lon":121.0732,"locPhoto":{"width":2592,"file":"Monument to the Heroes of 1896, Quezon City.JPG","credit":"Diosa Marie Aguila {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"6a","height":3888},"name":"Monumento sa mga Bayani ng 1896","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Vinzons Hall, Roxas Avenue cor. Shuster Avenue, University of the Philippines Diliman, Diliman, Quezon City, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Monumento sa mga Bayani ng 1896","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinayo sa Balintawak, noo’y sakop ng Kalookan, 27 Agosto 1911, bilang pag-alaala sa mga bayani ng Himagsikang Filipino ng 1896. Nilikha ni Ramon Martinez y Lazaro. Pinasinayaan, 3 Setyembre 1911. Inilipat sa Bulwagang Vinzons, Unibersidad ng Pilipinas, Diliman, Lungsod Quezon, 29 Nobyembre 1968.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Monumento sa mga Bayani ng 1896 historical marker (corrected).jpg","width":2500,"height":3089,"hash":"76"}}},"macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","date":"2011","lat":14.6543},"Q36987290":{"lon":120.96686,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","date":"1992","lat":14.61,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Propagandista, makabayan at martir. Ipinanganak sa Mambusao, Capiz, Agosto 4, 1856. Nagkamit ng Perito Mercantil certificate, Ateneo Municipal; nag-aral ng notariado sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, kung saan ay nakilala niya at naging kaibigan si Jose Rizal. Naging unang pangulo ng La Liga Filipina, Hunyo 1892, at pangulo ng Cuerpo de Compromisarios, 1894. Dinakip ng mga Kastila, dahilan sa pagsapi sa Katipunan, Setyembre 19, 1896. Ikinulong sa Kutang Santiago at pinahirapan ng may tatlong buwan; binaril sa pamamagitan ng firing squad kasama ang labindalawang mga makabayang Filipino sa Bagumbayan, Enero 11, 1897.</p>","title":"Domingo Franco y Tuason","subtitle":"(1856–1897)"},"photo":{"width":1672,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Domingo Franco y Tuason historical marker.jpg","height":2180,"hash":"9c"}}},"address":"Plaza Moriones, Moriones Street cor. Franco Street, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Domingo Franco y Tuason","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q52027139":{"macroAddress":"Pasig, Metro Manila","date":"1954-08-29","lat":14.56064,"name":"Pang-alaalang Bantayog","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":857,"file":"Pang-alaalang Bantayog.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"5a","height":482},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pang-alaalang Bantayog","inscription":"<p>Ang bantayog na ito ay sa karangalan ng mga anak ng Pasig na nangamatay nang Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig upang tayong nangabubuhay ay makakuhang-uliran sa kanila. Ang mga kagamitan at salaping ginugol dito ay buhat sa mga butihing mamamayan ng Pasig at mga kalapit-bayan. Ang namanihala sa pagbabangon ay ang Pasig Civic League. Pinasinayaan noong ika-29 ng Agosto, 1954.</p>"}}},"address":"Pasig World War II Memorial Monument, Caruncho Avenue, Pasig, Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"hash":"08","height":3456,"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"01430jfBarangays Bridges River Avenues Center Buildings Pasig Cityfvf 09.jpg"},"lon":121.0783,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the monument."},"Q34998485":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ang Sandugo","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa look ng Hinawanan, Loay, naganap ang sandugo sa pagitan nina Miguel Lopez de Legazpi at Datu Sikatuna ng Bohol sa loob ng barkong San Pedro ng Espanya, 25 Marso 1565. Isinagawa sa pamamagitan ng pag-inom ng alak na inihalo sa dugo mula sa hiwa sa dibdib ng dalawang pinuno. Naging simula ng pagkakaibigan ng mga Espnayol at mga Boholano at Kristiyanisasyon ng Pulo.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Ang Sandugo historical marker.jpg","width":822,"hash":"34","height":949}}},"address":"Loay, Bohol","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Ang Sandugo","lat":9.60579,"macroAddress":"Loay, Bohol","date":"2006","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Sandugo":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.99882},"Q25079737":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Bonifacio Trial House":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.73702,"address":"Maragondon, Cavite","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Where Bonifacio was Court-Martialled","inscription":"<p>In this house, erected in 1889, by its owner, Teodorico Reyes, Andres Bonifacio, founder of the Katipunan, was tried with his brother, Procopio, May 1897, by a court-martial headed by Brigadier-General Mariano Noriel. He was shot, May 10, 1897, at Mt. Buntis.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2684,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Bonifacio court-martial location historical marker.jpg","hash":"53","height":3735}}},"name":"Where Bonifacio was Court-Martialled","region":"Calabarzon","date":"1948","macroAddress":"Maragondon, Cavite","lat":14.27426},"Q53997849":{"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Baras, Rizal","lat":14.52279,"name":"Church of Baras","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The Franciscans built the first Church in 1595. The town was transferred to Ibayo in 1636 but returned to the present site in 1682. The Jesuits administered this parish from 1616 to 1679. The present church was completed in 1686.</p>","title":"Church of Baras","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Baras Church (Rizal) historical marker.jpg","height":3456,"hash":"e6"}}},"address":"Baras Church, San Jose Street, Brgy. San Juan, Baras, Rizal","locPhoto":{"hash":"79","height":4608,"width":3456,"file":"BarasChurchjf6091 08.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"lon":121.26757,"wikipedia":{"Baras Church":"St. Joseph Church (Baras, Rizal)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade, on the pillar immediately to the left of the nave entrance."},"Q43304785":{"date":"2006","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","lat":14.58484,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng San Juan Bautista de Bagumbayan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ipinatayo ang unang simbahan at kumbento ng Order of Augustinian Recollects (OAR) sa Patronato ni San Juan Bautista. Dating tahanan ni Gobernador Heneral Pedro de Acuña, ito ay nabili at pinasinayaan ng mga Recoletos sa pangunguna ni Fr. Juan de San Jeronimo, 10 Setyembre 1606. Giniba sa atas ni Gobernador Heneral Sebastian Hurtado de Corcuera, 1644; muling ipinatayo subalit tuluyang nawasak noong panahon ng pananakop ng mga Ingles sa Maynila, 1764. Ang simbahan ay nagsilbing provincial curia at bahay-sanayan ng mga Recoletos para sa kanilang unang misyon sa Zambales, Mindanao, Calamianes Islands at Mindoro.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Marker church and convent of San Juan Bautista de Bagumbayan.jpg","credit":"Nikond80 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1536,"hash":"26","height":2294}}},"address":"Rizal Park, Padre Burgos Avenue cor. Maria Y. Orosa Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Simbahan at Kumbento ng San Juan Bautista de Bagumbayan","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97911,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q23848774":{"locPhoto":{"file":"Paete church,laguna.jpg","credit":"Leoviernes1 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2868,"hash":"93","height":1920},"lon":121.4815,"wikipedia":{"Paete Church":"Saint James the Apostle Parish Church (Paete)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the extreme right of the church's entrance.","date":"1939","macroAddress":"Paete, Laguna","lat":14.36449,"name":"Church of Paete","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Paete was founded in 1580 by the Rev. Juan de Plasencia. Its stone Church and its Convent, built in 1646, were ruined before 1717. The Rev. Francisco de la Fuente, O.F.M., constructed a stronger Church in 1717, which was later destroyed by the earthquake of 1880. The Church which the Rev. Pedro Galiano, O.F.M., built in 1884, was destroyed by the earthquake of August 20, 1937.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Paete"},"photo":{"width":720,"credit":"xtintina {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Paete historical marker.jpg","hash":"b5","height":540}}},"address":"Paete Church, Paete, Laguna"},"Q50562154":{"name":"Jose Rizal sa Dumaguete","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Jose Rizal sa Dumaguete","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Nagwakas ang pagkakatapon ni Rizal sa Dapitan, Mindanao nang pahintulutang manilbihan bilang siruhano sa hukbong Espanyol sa Cuba. Nilisan ang Dapitan patungong Maynila, kasama sina Josephine Bracken, at kapatid na si Narcisa, at iba pa, lulan ng barkong España, hatinggabi ng 31 Hulyo 1896. Pansamantalang tumigil sa Dumaguete ang barko, bukang-liwayway, 1 Agosto. Dito nakipagkita si Rizal kina Gobernador Emilio Regal, punong lalawigan ng Negros Oriental, at Faustino Herrero Regidor, dating kamag-aral. Kinahapunan, inopera sa mata ang kapitan ng konstabularya ng lalawigan. Nilisan ang Dumaguete mulang sakay ng España, ika-10 ng gabi ng araw ring iyon.</p>"}}},"address":"Quezon Park, Gov. Perdices Street, Dumaguete, Negros Oriental","date":"2012-02-07","macroAddress":"Dumaguete, Negros Oriental","lat":9.30554,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.30823},"Q52212836":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Eugenio Daza y Salazar","subtitle":"(1870–1954)","inscription":"<p>Guro, rebolusyonaryo, mambabatas. Ipinanganak, Nobyembre 15, 1879, Borongan, Eastern Samar. Nagkamit ng titulo sa edukasyon, Escuela Normal de Maestro, Maynila, 1888. Makaraang makatapos ng edukasyon, siya ay nagturo sa Borongan Municipal School at pagkaraan ng limang taon ay nagtatag ng sariling paaralan sa ilalim ng pamamahala ng mga Kastila. Sumapi sa kilusang himagsikang sa Samar sa pagsiklab ng Himagsikang Pilipino. Itinalaga ni Heneral Vicente Lukban na maging pangkalahatang punong-hukbo ng Silangang Samar. Isa sa mga naging kasangkapan sa tagumpay ng isang makasaysayang pangyayaring naganap sa Balangiga noong Setyembre 28, 1901. Nahalal na kinatawan ng ikatlong-distrito ng Samar sa Unang Asemble ng Pilipinas, 1907. Namatay Disyembre 16, 1954, Calamba, Laguna.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Borongan–Guiuan Road cor. Rawis Road, Borongan, Eastern Samar","region":"Eastern Visayas","name":"Eugenio Daza y Salazar","lat":11.6039,"macroAddress":"Borongan, Eastern Samar","date":"1992-08-11","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":125.4403,"locPhoto":null},"Q31440656":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.03158,"wikipedia":{"Loboc Church":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":9.63656,"macroAddress":"Loboc, Bohol","date":"1999","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Church of San Pedro Apostol","address":"Loboc Church, Loboc, Bohol","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of San Pedro Apostol","inscription":"<p>In May 1597, Fr. Juan de Torres, S.J., established the mission of Loboc, which was canonically established as a parish dedicated to San Pedro Apostol[.] In 1602, the present church, built on foundations of the early church which was destroyed by the fire, was started in 1670 and completed in 1734. The convent annexed to the church in a three-storey structure, was the central residence of the Jesuit Missions. In 1768, the Recollects were assigned the former missions in Bohol; they built the octagonal bell tower separate from the main church structure. Sometime in 1858, Fray Aquilino Bon, O.A.R., built the portico in front of the church façade and the octagional mortuary chapel at the gospel flank of the church.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2736,"file":"Loboc Church historical marker.JPG","credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","hash":"7a","height":3648}}}},"Q56070586":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pinunong rebolusyonaryo, at mangangalakal. Isinilang sa Binondo, Manila, 20 Mayo 1849. Itinatag ang Hacienda Vallehermoso sa Guihulngan, 1881. Hinirang bilang heneral ng brigada ng Hukbong Rebolusyonaryo ng Pilipinas, Nobyembre 1898. Nanguna sa pagpapalaya ng mga bayan sa Hilagang Negros at sa bayan ng Dumaguete, 24 Nobyembre 1898. Nahalal at naglingkod bilang delegado ng Digmaan ng Zona Militar ng Katimugang Negros, 25 Nobyembre – 15 Mayo 1899. Bumalik sa pagsasaka matapos maglingkod sa Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo, sa pamamagitan ng kanyang pagsisikap naging hiwalay na bayan ang Vallehermoso, 1 Enero 1913. Yumao, 27 Marso 1920.</p>","subtitle":"(1849–1920)","title":"Diego de la Viña"}}},"address":"J. Burgos Street, Vallehermoso, Negros Oriental","name":"Diego de la Viña","region":"Central Visayas","macroAddress":"Vallehermoso, Negros Oriental","date":null,"lat":10.33581,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":123.32647,"locPhoto":null},"Q41082313":{"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1968-12-08","lat":14.59402,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinangalan sa Reyna Isabela II, ang pintong ito ay nakaharap sa Ilog Pasig at nasa pagitan ng Kuta ng San Gabriel sa silangan at ng dating Kuta ng Sto. Domingo sa kanluran. Itong huli ang dati’y nakapaligid sa noo’y gusali ng adwana (ngayo’y Bangko Sentral). Ang makitid na bahagi ng lupa sa pagitan ng ilog at ng mga pader ay siyang dating pook ng ikalawang parian na naging Paseo de Magallanes at muelle. Sa pagitan ng mga kutang nabanggit ay may 20 malalaking silid na ginagamit na pintungan at ang dakong itaas ay balwarteng nakaharap sa ilog. Ang pintong ginawa at binuksan noong 1861 ay lumalagos sa Daang San Juan de Letran sa pagitan ng Kolehiyo ng San Juan de Letran at ng dating Beateryo ng Sta. Catalina noong kapanahunan ni Gobernador Jose Lemery. Nasira noong 1945 dahil sa digmaan; muling ginawa ng Intramuros Restoration Committee noong 1968 sa tulong ng abuloy ng Research Foundation in Philippine Anthropology and Archaelogy, Inc., at iba pa, ng pambansang pamahalaan at ng Lungsod ng Maynila.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Pintong Isabela II"},"photo":{"hash":"01","height":3328,"width":2072,"credit":"Photo: Josh Lim (Sky Harbor); perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pintong Isabela II historical marker.jpg"}}},"address":"Magallanes Drive, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Pintong Isabela II","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97618,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Gates of Intramuros":true}},"Q28923408":{"lat":8.94768,"date":"1999-01-19","macroAddress":"Butuan","region":"Caraga","name":"The Raising of the Philippine Flag in Mindanao","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>In this place on January 17, 1899, Governor Wenceslao Gonzales of the Tercio Distrito of Surigao, Fr. Francisco Nebot, S.J. and the principal residents of Butuan formally lowered the Vatican flag and officially raised the Philippine flag accompanied by the playing of the Himno Nacional de Filipinas by the local bands of Butuan, Tubay and Cabadbaran. The event marked the formal establishment of the authority of the Philippine Revolutionary Government in Mindanao.</p>","title":"The Raising of the Philippine Flag in Mindanao","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Guingona Park, Jose S. Aquino Avenue cor. Ester Luna Street, Butuan","lon":125.54342,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Revolutionary Government of the Philippines":"Revolutionary Government of the Philippines (1898–1899)","flag of the Philippines":"Flag of the Philippines"},"locDesc":null},"Q24045081":{"date":"1934","macroAddress":"Quiapo, Manila","lat":14.59946,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Designed by Genaro Palacios. The structural metal of which this church is uniquely built was manufactured in Belgium and erected here by Belgian engineers. The church was solemnly blessed August 16, 1891. Earlier churches built on this site by Recollect friars since 1611 were destroyed by earthquake in 1859, 1863 and 1880.</p>","title":"San Sebastian Church","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"San Sebastian Church (Manila) historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2437,"height":2281,"hash":"26"}}},"address":"San Sebastian Church, Pasaje del Carmen Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"San Sebastian Church","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"San Sebastian Basilica main entrance.jpg","width":3000,"hash":"12","height":1424},"lon":120.98924,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main entrance of the church.","wikipedia":{"San Sebastian Church":"San Sebastian Church (Manila)"}},"Q55716666":{"lat":14.95531,"macroAddress":"Bustos, Bulacan","date":"1960","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Mabuhay ang mga Bayani","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa patyong ito sa paligid ng tribunal nuong ika-16 ng Hunio, 1897, nagkatipon ang may isang libong lalaking taga Bustos na pawang sandatahan sa pangunguna nina Kap. Bindoy at Andres upang mahigpit na tutulan ang paghuhulog ng “Juez de Cuchillo”, sa bayang ito. Pinagkasunduan nila na kundi pakikinggan ang kanilang pagtutol ay pagsusunggabanan na lamang nila at sukat ang mga baril at bayoneta ng may apat na raang kasadores na sa kanila ay nakapaligid, at ang palatandaan ng pagsasagawa nito ay ang pagyapos ng mga Kapitang Municipal na taga Bustos sa mga opisyal na Kastila na kanilang kausap sa bulwagan ng tribunal.</p>","title":"Mabuhay ang mga Bayani","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":849,"hash":"68","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"MabuhayAngMgaBayani HistoricalMarker Bustos.jpg","width":562}}},"address":"Bustos Church, C.L. Hilario Highway, Poblacion, Bustos, Bulacan","lon":120.90976,"locPhoto":{"height":3264,"hash":"42","file":"Bellsjf.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2448},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the Church Bell of Bustos pedestal in the church patio."},"Q40316780":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Manila massacre":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96961,"address":"Fort Santiago, Santa Clara Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"In Memory of the Victims at Fort Santiago","inscription":"<p>On this site lie the mortal remains of approximately 600 Filipinos. Their bodies were found inside a nearby dungeon where victims of the atrocities perpetrated by the Japanese Imperial Foces were imprisoned during the last days of February 1945. </p><p>The memory of all these unknown victims of Japanese atrocities will live forever in the hearts and minds of the Filipino people.</p>"},"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"d7","width":3456,"file":"WWII Victims at Fort Santiago historical marker, Manila.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"In Memory of the Victims at Fort Santiago","lat":14.59486,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1995"},"Q52024197":{"lon":121.07639,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":14.55983,"date":"1937","macroAddress":"Pasig, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Colegio de Madres Agustinas","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":960,"hash":"b2","width":659,"file":"Colegio de Madres Agustinas.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Colegio de Madres Agustinas","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This College was founded in 1740 by Rev. Felix Trillo, O.S.A. with the assistance of Pedro and Rita Quijano, for the education of girls. The building was occupied by the British after the expulsion of the Spanish forces. It was greatly damaged by the earthquakes of 1880.</p>"}}},"address":"Colegio del Buen Consejo, A. Luna Street cor. R. Jabson Street, Pasig, Metro Manila"},"Q28855047":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 04 September 2009</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Mercado Mansion"},"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Historical Marker of Mercado Mansion.jpg","width":840,"height":775,"hash":"2c"}}},"address":"Mercado Mansion, Jose Rizal Street, Carcar, Cebu","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Mercado Mansion","lat":10.10451,"date":"2010-05-29","macroAddress":"Carcar, Cebu","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Mercado Mansion":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.64139},"Q56089708":{"wikipedia":{"Kuta Church ruins":"Kuta Church Ruins"},"locDesc":null,"lon":121.51501,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Mga Guho ng Simbahang Kuta","region":"Mimaropa","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Mga Guho ng Simbahang Kuta","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Unang napahayag sa Libro de Registros ng mga Rekoleto noong 1737 ang misyon ng Bongabong. Nagsilbing Plaza de Armas kung saan ang mga mamamayan ng misyon ay nagkubli tuwing panahon ng pananalakay. Nasira ang mga ito noong 1753 at 1754 noong sumalakay ang mga Muslim dahil sa kanilang patuloy na pagtutol sa pananakop ng mga dayuhang Espanyol. Halimbawa ang mga guho ng pagsasama-sama ng katangiang simbahan at kuta. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 25 Hunyo 2012.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Kuta Church ruins, Sitio Cuta, Brgy. Anilao, Bongabong, Oriental Mindoro","date":"2013-05-08","macroAddress":"Bongabong, Oriental Mindoro","lat":12.72199},"Q51921881":{"lon":121.17639,"locPhoto":{"file":"Antipolo Shrine (Antipolo, Rizal).jpg","credit":"Shubert Ciencia {CC BY 2.0}","width":800,"hash":"7c","height":600},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the southern corner of the cathedral facade.","wikipedia":{"Our Lady of Peace and Good Voyage":true},"lat":14.58757,"macroAddress":"Antipolo, Rizal","date":"1937","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"OLOfGoodVoyage HistoricalMarker AntipoloCity.jpg","width":451,"height":533,"hash":"c7"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje","inscription":"<p>The statue of Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje was brought from Mexico to Manila by Governor Juan Niño de Tavora in 1626 and at his death in 1632 was turned over to the Jesuits for the Church of Antipolo. Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje was proclaimed Patroness of the galleons. The statue crossed the Pacific, and returned, eight times on board the galleons of Acapulco: in 1641, 1643, 1645–46 on the San Luis; 1648–1649 on the Encarnacion; in 1650 on the San Diego; in 1851–1853 on the San Javier; in 1659–1662 on the San Jose and in 1746–1748 on the Nuestra Señora del Pilar. The statue of Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje was canonically crowned on November 26, 1926, by the Most Rev. Michael J. O’Doherty, Archbishop of Manila, on the Luneta, Manila, in the presence of at least one hundred thousand people.</p>"}}},"address":"Antipolo Cathedral, P. Oliveros Street, Antipolo, Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje"},"Q37977096":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"lon":121.96878,"locPhoto":null,"address":"National Road, Basco, Batanes","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1861–1896)","title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Pambansang Bayani ng Pilipinas. Doktor, agrimensor, dalubwika, manunulat, makata, eskultor at pintor. Isinilang sa Calamba, Laguna, 19 Hunyo 1861. May-akda ng Noli me Tangere (1887) at El Filibusterismo (1891), mga nobelang higit pang nagpaalab sa mga Filipino na maghimagsik laban sa Espanya. Dinakip at ipinatapon sa Dapitan, Hilagang Mindanao, 6 Hulyo, 1892. Nagboluntaryo bilang manggagamot ng puwersang Espanyol sa Cuba, 1896, ngunit muling dinakip habang patungong Espanya sa bintang na rebelyon. Binaril sa Bagumbayan (ngayo’y Liwasang Rizal), Maynila, 30 Disyembre 1896. Patuloy na inspirasyon para sa kalayan at pagkabansang Filipino.</p>"}}},"region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Jose Rizal","lat":20.44932,"date":"2014","macroAddress":"Basco, Batanes"},"Q56063373":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":123.71936,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3008,"hash":"93","width":2000,"file":"Heritage Marker of Bantayan Church.JPG","credit":"Sherlock S. Sison {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang simbahang ito na inialay sa Nuestra Señora de la Asuncion ay ipinatayo ng mga paring Agustino noong ika-11 ng Hunyo 1580. Pagkaraan, naging patron ng simbahan si San Pedro Apostol at lumawak ang sakop ng parokya hanggang Maripipi, Panamao at Limangcawayan sa Leyte. Sinunog ng mga mananalakay na Muslim noong 1600, ito ay muling ipinatayo noong taon ding iyon at inilipat sa pamamahala ng mga sekular.</p><p> Ang kasalukuyang gusali ay sinimulang gawin noong 1839 at natapos noong 1863.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Bantayan"}}},"address":"Bantayan Church, M.L. Quezon Street, Bantayan, Cebu","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Ang Simbahan ng Bantayan","lat":11.16672,"macroAddress":"Bantayan, Cebu","date":"1980"},"Q43302605":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Paul de la Gironière":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.32136,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Manlalakbay na Pranses na dumating sa Maynila noong 1820. Nanirahan sa Pilipinas sa loob ng dalawampung taon at binuo ang asyendang Jala-Jala sa Morong, ngayo’y Lalawigang Rizal. Pinaunlad ang pag-aalaga ng baboy, pagtatanim ng indigo, tubo at kape at nakapagtanim ng kapeng may 60,000 puno sa ikalawa nitong pag-aani. Dahil dito siya ay tumanggap ng karangalan buhat sa <u>La Real Sociedad Economica de Amigos del Pais de Filipinas</u> noong Hunyo 27, 1837. Sinulat ang salaysay ng kanyang buhay at paglalakbay sa kapuluan na pinamagatang <u>Vingt Annees aux Philippines</u> (Dalawampung Taon sa Pilipinas). Nagbalik sa Pransiya at binawian ng buhay noong 1865.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Paul P. de la Gironiere"},"photo":{"width":3456,"file":"Paul de la Gironière Estate historical marker 2.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"21","height":4608}}},"address":"Jalajala, Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Paul P. de la Gironiere","lat":14.3538,"macroAddress":"Jalajala, Rizal","date":"1978"},"Q24813802":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.13267,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Ibaan Church":true},"macroAddress":"Ibaan, Batangas","date":"1941","lat":13.81873,"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Ibaan","inscription":"<p>In 1874 a chapel was built at Matala, but fire destroyed the convent in 1801. Constituted as a town in 1804, Ibaan had it's first church in 1817. In 1832, it was under Rev. Manuel Grijalbo, O.S.A., afterward Bishop of Nueva Caceres. Constructed by Rev. Manuel Diez Gonzales, O.S.A., in 1854, the present church was completed by Rev. Bruno Laredo, O.S.A., in 1869. Rev Vicente Maril, O.S.A., erected the towers and rebuilt the facade in 1876..</p>"},"photo":{"height":3012,"hash":"5e","file":"Ibaan Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2890}}},"address":"Ibaan Church, Ibaan, Batangas","name":"Church of Ibaan","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q28861668":{"date":"1960","macroAddress":"Sampaloc, Manila","lat":14.60838,"name":"Jose Rizal","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Arch of the Centuries, España Boulevard, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"es":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Jose Rizal, Alumno de la Real y Pontificia Universidad de Santo Tomas de Manila, Filipinas, 1877–1882.</p>","subtitle":"1861–1896","title":"Jose Rizal"},"photo":{"height":3264,"hash":"e6","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jose Rizal historical marker at the Arch of the Centuries UST.jpg","width":2448}}},"lon":120.9908,"locPhoto":{"width":640,"credit":"Ms.popsie21 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Arch of the Centuries- University of Santo Tomas.jpg","height":426,"hash":"5d"},"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the left post of the arch looking from España Boulevard."},"Q55480494":{"macroAddress":"Noveleta, Cavite","date":"1964-08-31","lat":14.42724,"name":"Tribunal ng Nobeleta","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"e4","height":4608,"width":3456,"file":"Noveleta Old Town Hall historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Tribunal ng Nobeleta","subtitle":"Kabite"}}},"address":"Gen. Antonio Street, Noveleta, Cavite","locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Noveleta,Cavitejf1648 08.JPG","hash":"02","height":3456},"lon":120.88071,"wikipedia":{"Philippine Revolution":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a low memorial wall in front of the right side of the building facade."},"Q30130018":{"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1861–1896)","title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Philippine National Hero. Born on 19 June 1861. Doctor, poet, writer, educator, linguist, inventor.</p><p>Authored novels Noli Me Tangere (1887) and El Filibusterismo (1891) which bared colonial oppression of the Filipinos. He advocated nonviolent struggle for freedom but was charged with inciting dissent.</p><p>The living soul of the 1896 Philippine revolution, he was executed on 30 December 1896.</p><p>His martyrdom inspired a sense of nationhood that eventually led to the proclamation of the Philippine Independence in 1898.</p>"}}},"address":"Rizal Park, Anthony Drive, Rosemeadow, City of Campbelltown, Sydney, New South Wales, Australia / Rizal Park, Anthony Drive, Rosemeadow, City of Campbelltown, Sydney, City of Sydney, Australia / Rizal Park, Anthony Drive, Rosemeadow, City of Campbelltown, Sydney, Australia","name":"Jose Rizal","region":"Overseas","macroAddress":"Sydney, New South Wales, Australia","date":"2012-10-26","lat":-34.10127,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"lon":150.79218,"locPhoto":null},"Q28927601":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Kinatatayuan ng pamayanan ni Sultan Untung na nakubkob ng puwersang Espanyol, 1887. Tinayuan ng Kuta ng Alfonso XIII, 1890; natapos, 1891. Pook ng rebelyon laban sa Espanya, Setyembre 1896 at Oktubre 1898, at pook-pinagbitayan sa mga rebeldeng sundalong Pilipino sa Mindanao, Enero 1897. Tinayuan ng pamayanang Muslim matapos iwan ng mga Espanyol, 1899. Naging garison ng hukbong Amerikano, 1900-1912, at ng Philippine Constabulary, 1902-1903. Sentro ng Tukuran-Lintogup Telephone Line ng U.S. SIGNAL Corps, ang pangunahing linya ng komunikasyon sa Mindanao, 1 Enero 1901. Himpilan ng distritong militar, 1912-1918, at distritong munisipal ng Tukuran, 1918-1921. Tuluyang inabandona dulot ng patuloy na pagsalakay ng mga Moro, 1921. Naging Barangay Militar, Tukuran, Zamboanga del Sur.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Mga Guho ng Kuta ng Tukuran"},"photo":null}},"address":"Km. 1650 Pan-Philippine Highway, Brgy. Militar, Tukuran, Zamboanga del Sur","name":"Mga Guho ng Kuta ng Tukuran","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","macroAddress":"Tukuran, Zamboanga del Sur","date":"2014-10-28","lat":7.84445,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":123.5849,"locPhoto":null},"Q40176443":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ang Bahay ni Aguinaldo","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3209,"hash":"87","width":2500,"file":"Ang Bahay ni Aguinaldo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo:Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Ang Bahay ni Aguinaldo","subtitle":"1849","inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na ito, na itinayo noong 1849, ipinanganak si Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo noong Marso 22, 1869. Sa durungawang nakaharap sa daan ipinahayag ni Aguinaldo ang kasarinlan ng Pilipinas noong Hunyo 12, 1898. Ipinagkaloob ang bahay sa Pamahalaang Pilipino bilang alaala sa mga nakihamok upang makamtan ang kalayaan. Inilibing siya sa loteng kinatatayuan ng bahay noong Pebrero 16, 1964.</p>"}}},"address":"Aguinaldo Shrine, Kawit Loop Road, Kawit, Cavite","lat":14.44516,"macroAddress":"Kawit, Cavite","date":"1971","wikipedia":{"Aguinaldo Shrine":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.90692},"Q56062655":{"macroAddress":"Carcar, Cebu","date":"2017-09-25","lat":10.10594,"address":"Carcar Church, Santa Catalina Street, Carcar, Cebu","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Carcar","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Agustino sa patronato ng Mahal na Birhen ng Bisitasyon, 1599. Naging visita ng Santo Niño, 1599–1610, at San Nicolas de los Naturales de Cebu, 1610–1617. Naging parokya sa patronato ni Santa Catalina de Alejandria, 1617. Sinimulang itayo ang simbahan yari sa bato ni Padre Antonio Manglano, 1860; ipinagpatuloy ni Padre Gabriel Gonzalez, 1865; at natapos kasama ang kumbento ni Padre Manuel Fernandez, 1875. Pinapintahan at muling ipinaayos ni Padre Anastacio del Corro, 1901–1948.</p>"},"photo":null}},"name":"Simbahan ng Carcar","region":"Central Visayas","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.64045,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q23797154":{"wikipedia":{"University of the Philippines Los Baños College of Agriculture":"University of the Philippines Los Baños College of Agriculture and Food Sciences"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.24213,"name":"College of Agriculture","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"bc","height":1512,"width":985,"file":"UPLB College of Agriculture historical marker.jpg","credit":"Mjuadiong {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag upang magsagawa ng pananaliksik at pag-aaral sa agrikultura, 6 Marso 1909. Binuksan sa mga mag-aaral, 14 Hunyo 1909. Dr. Edwin B. Copeland, unang dekano 1909-1917. Itinayo ang pangunahing gusali, 21 Mayo 1911. Itinanghal na pangunahing kolehiyo ng agrikulturang tropikal sa Pilipinas ng University of Illinois, 1923. Bienvenido Ma. Gonzalez, unang Filipinong Dekano 1927-1939. Nagsilbing himpilan ng mga Hapon, 1941, at naging piitan ng mga banyagang bihag. Muling nagbukas, 25 Hulyo 1946. Naging bahagi ng bagong Unibersidad ng Pilipinas Los Baños sa Bisa ng P.D. No. 58, 20 Nobyembre 1972. Ginawaran ng Ramon Magsaysay Award, 1977. Naging sentro ng karunungang pang-agrikultura sa Asya.</p>","title":"College of Agriculture","subtitle":null}}},"address":"University of the Philippines Los Baños, Pedro R. Sandoval Avenue cor. Harold Cuzner Royal Palm Avenue, Los Baños, Laguna","date":"2010","macroAddress":"Los Baños, Laguna","lat":14.16552},"Q44354771":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.94291,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Tomás Mascardo":true},"lat":14.42393,"date":"1973-12-17","macroAddress":"Imus, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pinangalanang Tulay Tomas Mascardo bilang pagkilala sa kanyang mga nagawa nang siya'y naging heneral ng 1896 Himagsikan at gobernador ng lalawigan ng Kabite (1910-1912)</p>","title":"Tulay Tomas Mascardo","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Tomás Mascardo Bridge, Emilio Aguinaldo Highway, Imus, Cavite","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Tulay Tomas Mascardo"},"Q44807646":{"wikipedia":{"Battle of Bataan":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.53027,"region":"Central Luzon","name":"The Fall of Bataan","address":"Bataan Provincial Capitol, Capitol Drive, Balanga, Bataan","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"The Fall of Bataan","subtitle":"9 April 1942","inscription":"<p>[The fall of Bataan] sealed in blood the permanent ties of friendship and cooperation between the Philippines and the United States. This marker is dedicated, 9 April 1952, to the memory of the gallant Filipino and Americans soldiers as well as civilians, who fought and died side by side in the defense of Democracy.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"52","height":3641,"width":2500,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"The Fall of Bataan historical marker.jpg"}}},"lat":14.67589,"date":"1952-04-09","macroAddress":"Balanga, Bataan"},"Q24817240":{"wikipedia":{"Galicano Apacible":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.72936,"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Galicano C. Apacible","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Manggagamot, propagandista, diplomatiko, mambabatas at makabayan. Ipinanganak sa Balayan, Batangas 24 Hunyo 1864. Kasama si Dr. Jose Rizal at iba pang mga mag-aaral na Filipino, itinatag sa Maynila ang El Compañerismo. Isang lihim na samahang pulitikal noong 1880. Isa sa mga nagtatag ng pahayagang propagandistang La Solidaridad noong 1889. Pangulo ng Asociacion Solidaridad Filipina sa Barcelona noong 1888 at ng komite sentral ng mga Filipino sa Hong Kong noong 1898. Tagapayo ng mataas na konseho ng mga rebolusyonaryong Filipino at kinatawan ng Republika ng Pilipinas sa Tsina, 1898-1899. Natatanging sugo sa Amerika at Europa, 1900-1901. Isa sa mga tagapagtatag ng Lapiang Nacionalista, 1906. Gobernador ng Batangas, 1908-1909; Kinatawan ng Batangas sa Asamblea ng Pilipinas, 1910-1916: Kalihim ng Pagsasaka at Likas na Yaman, 1917-1921. Yumao 22 Marso 1949.</p>","subtitle":"(1864–1949)","title":"Galicano C. Apacible"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Galicano Apacible marker at his monument in Balayan,Batangas.jpg","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"07"}}},"address":"Balayan, Batangas","lat":13.93814,"macroAddress":"Balayan, Batangas","date":"2003"},"Q50881819":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.86881,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":10.09638,"macroAddress":"Himamaylan, Negros Occidental","date":"1993-05-17","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Pascual V. Ledesma","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pinuno ng Himagsikan, unang flag-officer in command ng Hukbong Dagat ng Pilipinas. Ipinanganak sa Himamaylan, Negros Occidental, Mayo 17, 1843. Nagsimula bilang kapitan ng isang commercial marine company, 1863. Sumapi sa Katipunan, 1894; tumulong sa pagpapalaganap ng mga adhikain at aral ng K.K.K. sa Maynila at karatig na mga lalawigan. Hinirang ni Aguinaldo bilang patnugot pandagat at pangkalakal na may ranggong komandante heneral, 1899–1901. Namalagi sa Hapon, Tsina at Indotsina. Nagbalik sa Pilipinas, 1905. Isa sa mga nagtatag ng Lapiang Nacionalista at samahan ng mga beterano ng Himagsikan. Namatay, Hunyo 6, 1917.</p>","title":"Pascual V. Ledesma","subtitle":"(1843–1917)"},"photo":null}},"address":"Negros South Road, Poblacion, Himamaylan, Negros Occidental"},"Q54554030":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":120.98259,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"08","height":603,"width":414,"file":"Honorio Lopez (1875 - 1958) Avenida.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Mamamahayag, mandudula, tagalathala, propagandista at isa sa pinakabatang tenyente koronel ng impanteriya ng Hukbong Panghimagsikan ng Pilipinas. Ipinanganak, Disyembre 30, 1875 Sta. Cruz, Maynila. Nagkamit ng Batsilyer sa mga Sining, San Juan de Letran; Agronomiya, Instituto Filipino at Batsilyer sa mga Batas, Academia de Jurisprudencia ng Colegio de Filipino, 1908. Sumapi sa Himagsikan bilang sarhento; naging ayuda de kampo ni Heneral Artemio Ricarte at pagkaraan, tenyente koronel sa ilalim ni Heneral Mariano Trias. Tagapagtatag, Academia Tagala. Unang naglathala ng kalendaryong Tagalog, ang Dimasalang: Kalendaryong Tagalog ni Honorio Lopez. Tagapagtatag, unang kumpanya ng mga sarswelang Tagalog. Patnugot, seksyong Tagalog ng mga pahayagang Libre la Patria at La Consolidacion. Nahalal na konsehal ng Maynila 1916. Katulong na teknikal nina Pangulong Ramon Magsaysay at Carlos P. Garcia. Namatay, Hulyo 3, 1958.</p>","subtitle":"(1875–1958)","title":"Honorio Lopez"}}},"address":"2875 Rizal Avenue, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Honorio Lopez","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","date":"1991-09-02","lat":14.62921},"Q54670620":{"macroAddress":"San Miguel, Manila","date":"2012","lat":14.59884,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag alinsunod sa Batas Commonwealth Blg. 184 na nilagdaan ni Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon bilang Surian ng Wikang Pambansa (SWP) na may pangunahing layunin na pumili mula sa iba’t ibang wika sa Pilipinas bilang batayan sa pagbabablangkas ng pambansang wika, 13 Nobyembre 1936. Binuo ang Lupon ng mga Pinuno, 13 Enero 1937. Jaime C. de Veyra, unang direktor. Unang nakahimpil sa Gusali ng Kongreso ng Pilipinas at nailipat sa iba’t ibang pook. Inilipat ang pangangasiwa sa Kagawaran ng Pagtuturo, 4 Oktubre 1947. Naging Linangan ng mga Wika sa Pilipinas (LWP) sa ilaim ng Kautusang Tagapagpaganap Blg. 117 ni Pangulong Corazon C. Aquino, Enero 1987. Naging Komisyon sa Wikang Filipino (KWF) sa bisa ng Batas Republika Blg. 7104, 14 Agosto 1991. Inatasang magsagawa ng pananaliksik, pagpapaunlad, pagpapalaganap at preserbasyon ng Filipino at iba pang wika sa Pilipinas.</p>","title":"Komisyon sa Wikang Filipino","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Watson Building, 1610 J.P. Laurel Street, San Miguel, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Komisyon sa Wikang Filipino","region":"Metro Manila","lon":120.99746,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Commission on the Filipino Language":true}},"Q40999278":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa pook na ito bilang Colegio de Santisimo Rosario noong Abril 28, 1611, bilang pamana ni Miguel Benavides, O.P., ang ikatlong Obispo ng Maynila. Pagkaraan pinangalanang Colegio de Sto. Tomas sa alaala ni Santo Tomas de Aquino. Binigyan ng kapangyarihang magkaloob ng titulo sa sining, pilosopiya at teolohiya, 1624. Itinaas ang antas bilang pamantasan ni Papa Innocent X, 1645. Ginawaran ng titulong “Real” ni Carlos III, 1785. Ipinahayag na “Pamantasang Pontipikal” ni Papa Leo, 1902, at “Pamantasang Katoliko ng Pilipinas” ni Papa Pius XII, 1947. Binuksan ang mga pinto sa kababaihan, 1924. Inilipat ang karamihan sa mga kolehiyo nito sa Sampaloc, Maynila, 1927. Ang orihinal na pangunahing gusali ay ganap na nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandigdig. Ang liwasang ito ay nagsilbing patio ng orihinal na pamantasan. Kabilang sa mga nag-aaral dito ay ang mga bayani at mga makabayang tulad nina Jose Rizal, Jose Burgos gayundin ang mga pangulo ng Pilipinas, sina Manuel L. Quezon, Sergio Osmeña, Jose P. Laurel at Diosdado P. Macapagal.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas"},"photo":{"file":"USTFoundationSite HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":391,"height":579,"hash":"c8"}}},"address":"Sto. Tomas Street cor. Solana Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas","lat":14.59291,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"2002","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"University of Santo Tomas":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97466},"Q52438247":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>This Heritage House of the Infante Family is registered with the National Historical Institute, pursuant to NHI Board Resolution No. 1, S. 2001.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Infante Heritage House"},"photo":null}},"address":"Infante Heritage House, La Carlota, Negros Occidental","name":"Infante Heritage House","region":"Western Visayas","macroAddress":"La Carlota, Negros Occidental","date":"2001-12-12","lat":10.45106,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":122.93469,"locPhoto":null},"Q54539767":{"date":"1935","macroAddress":"Sampaloc, Manila","lat":14.60325,"address":"Sampaloc Church, Jose Figueras Street, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Site donated to the Franciscans in 1613 by Pedro de Chaves. First chapel built in honor of Our Lady of Loreto in 1613 and set on fire during the Chinese uprising of 1639. Second chapel built under the supervision of Andres de Puertellano O.F.M. Present church built in 1666 under the direction of Francisco de Santa Catalina O.F.M. Associated with the Convent of Sampaloc, there functioned here from 1692 to 1808 one of the best printing presses of Manila.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Sampaloc"},"photo":{"credit":"Urbanroamer {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Sampaloc, Manila - Our Lady of Loreto Church historical marker.jpg","width":5184,"hash":"df","height":3456}}},"name":"Church of Sampaloc","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.99343,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Sampaloc Church":true}},"Q28865543":{"lat":15.02669,"macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","date":"2003","address":"Hizon-Singian House, Consuji, San Fernando, Pampanga","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Hizon-Singian House","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute, 27 January 2003</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"72","height":825,"file":"Hizon-SingianHouse HistoricalMarker SanFernandoCityPampanga.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":942}}},"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Hizon-Singian House","lon":120.69188,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Hizon-Singian House":true}},"Q44454498":{"wikipedia":{"Bataan Death March":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is attached to a large white triangular-shaped stone at Kilometer 106 of the Death March route.","locPhoto":{"width":4608,"file":"002jfSanto Domingo Death March Marker Capas Tarlacfvf 07.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":3456,"hash":"77"},"lon":120.59417,"name":"Death March","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"text":{"tl":{"title":null,"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa himpilang daang-bakal na ito ng Capas, ang mga bihag ng digmang kawal Pilipino at Amerikano na himalang nakaligtas sa makahayup na paglalakbay mula San Fernando, ay muling pinaglakad gayong mga nag-aagaw buhay, hanggang Kampo O’Donnell na may 6 kilometro ang layo. Sa impiyernong kulungang yaon, sila’y naging bilanggo.</p>"},"en":{"subtitle":"April 1942","title":"Death March","inscription":"<p>At this railroad station of Capas, the Filipino and American prisoners of war who survived the horrendous trip from San Fernando, during which so many smothered to death in the densely crowded cars, were unloaded and force, although on the point of collapse to march the 6 kilometers to Camp O’Donnell, where they were concentrated.</p>"}},"photo":{"width":2500,"file":"Death March April 1942 historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","hash":"c0","height":2810}},"address":"Capas, Tarlac","macroAddress":"Capas, Tarlac","date":"1967","lat":15.34484},"Q53996688":{"lat":10.13281,"macroAddress":"Maasin, Southern Leyte","date":"2018-04-17","region":"Eastern Visayas","name":"Oppus Ancestral House","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Oppus Ancestral House","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 06 October 2005</p>"},"photo":{"width":1420,"credit":"Juca Munda {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Oppus Ancestral House (Southern Leyte Provincial Library) (cropped).jpg","height":1287,"hash":"c7"}}},"address":"Oppus House, Tomas Oppus Street, Brgy. Abgao, Maasin, Southern Leyte","lon":124.84202,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Juca Munda {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Façade of the Oppus Ancestral House in Maasin.jpg","width":4032,"height":3024,"hash":"f4"},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the building facade, to the right of the entry door."},"Q43363516":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Tomas Claudio","address":"Tomas Claudio Street cor. Tupas Street, Morong, Rizal","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"28","height":1260,"width":903,"credit":"Hannachiever07 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Tomas Claudio (1892-1918) historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1892–1918)","title":"Tomas Claudio","inscription":"<p>Bayani ng Unang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Ipinanganak, Mayo 7, 1892, Morong, Rizal. Nagtapos ng Komersiyo, Clark Healds Business College, Sparks, Nevada, 1916. Umanib sa Hukbo ng Estados Unidos, Nobyembre 2, 1917; nagtungo sa Pransya bilang kasapi ng ika-41 Dibisyon, Disyembre 15, 1917. Lumipat sa ika-28 Rehimeng Impanteriya, Unang Dibisiyon at buong tapang na nakibaka sa madugong Labanan ng Cantigny, Pransya, Mayo 28. Namatay bunga ng tinamong sugat, Hunyo 29, 1918. Ibinalik ang mga labi sa Pilipinas at inilibing nang may karampatang seremonya sa Cementerio del Norte, 1921. Bilang parangal, ang Tomas Claudio Memorial School ay itinatag sa bisa ng Batas Lehislatura Blg. 1281, noong 1921.</p>"}}},"lat":14.51273,"date":"1992-05-07","macroAddress":"Morong, Rizal","wikipedia":{"Tomas Claudio":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.23859},"Q54866680":{"lon":123.82096,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Manila galleon":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"2006","macroAddress":"Magallanes, Sorsogon","lat":12.81856,"name":"Ang Astilyero sa Isla ng Bagatao","region":"Bicol Region","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito na dating kilala bilang Calaguimi, itinatag ang Real Astillero de Bagatao sa panahon ni Gobernador-Heneral Juan de Silva, 1610. Dito ginawa ang ilang mga barko para sa Kalakalang Galyon ng Manila–Acapulco kabilang ang pinakamalaki at tanyag na Santisima Trinidad na sa kasamaang palad ay nakuha ng mga Ingles noong 1762. Sinalakay ng mga pirata noong 1616, kung saan maraming Pilipino ang nasawi at mga paring Espanyol ang nadakip. Muling sinalakay noong 1627 at 1635. Ang Astilyero ng Bagatao ay tumagal ng 140 taon.</p>","title":"Ang Astilyero sa Isla ng Bagatao","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Sitio Pansod, Brgy. Behia, Bagatao Island, Magallanes, Sorsogon"},"Q54497342":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting at the base of the Philippine flag pole, in the center of the shrine.","wikipedia":{"Melchora Aquino":true},"locPhoto":{"hash":"c2","height":853,"width":1280,"file":"Tandang Sora Shrine 02.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"lon":121.04542,"address":"Tandang Sora Shrine, Banlat Road cor. Melchora Aquino Street, Banlat, Quezon City, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"45","height":1792,"width":1280,"file":"Tandang Sora Shrine 01.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Baryo Banlat, Kalookan ngayo’y Banlat, Lungsod Quezon, 6 Enero 1812. Tinaguriang Ina ng Himagsikan dahil sa pagtulong sa mga Katipunero na pinamumunuan ni Gat Andres Bonifacio sa pamamagitan ng pagpapakain at pag-aalaga sa mga sugatan. Dinakip ng mga Espanyol at ipinatapon sa Guam, 1896. Pinalaya ng mga Amerikano at nagbalik sa Pilipinas, 1903. Yumao, 19 Pebrero 1919 at inilibing sa Mausoleo de los Veteranos de la Revolucion, Manila North Cemetery. Inilipat ang mga labi sa Himlayang Pilipino, 6 Enero 1970.</p>","title":"Melchora Aquino","subtitle":"(Tandang Sora)"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Melchora Aquino","lat":14.68316,"macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","date":"2007"},"Q41995081":{"wikipedia":{"Gregorio del Pilar":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal for the statue of del Pilar.","locPhoto":{"file":"Gregoriojf.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"hash":"73","height":4608},"lon":120.8755,"name":"Birthplace of General Gregorio H. del Pilar","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Birthplace of General Gregorio H. del Pilar historical marker.jpg","width":1686,"height":2846,"hash":"b1"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Site in the town of Bulacan where General Gregorio H. del Pilar was born November 14, 1875. Fifth child of Ferrnando H. del Pilar and Felipa Sempio. Intrepid, valiant and youngest Filipino General. Figured most prominently in the defense of Kakaron, Attack of Paombong, Liberation of Bulacan, and in the Battle of Tirad Pass where he died “a soldier and a gentleman,” December 2, 1899.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Birthplace of General Gregorio H. del Pilar"}}},"address":"Birthplace of General Gregorio del Pilar Historical Landmark, Camino Real Street, Bulakan, Bulacan","macroAddress":"Bulakan, Bulacan","date":"1948","lat":14.79633},"Q29018562":{"lon":125.07496,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"First Mass in the Philippines":true},"date":"1950","macroAddress":"Limasawa, Southern Leyte","lat":9.90785,"address":"Limasawa Shrine, Brgy. Magallanes, Limasawa, Southern Leyte","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"First Mass in the Philippines","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Celebrated here on Easter Sunday, 31 March 1521, when Magellan landed on this island of Limasawa on his voyage around the world. Early in the morning, Magellan sent ashore priest Pedro de Valderrama with men to prepare a mass and to inform Rajah Kolambu, through an interpreter that he and his men would land to attend. The rajah showed consent by sending gifts. As Magellan and his men approached the shore, a salvo of six guns was fired as a sign of peace. Rajahs Kolambu and Si-Agu each embraced Magellan, flanked him and together with the sailors, they marched to the place of worship. During the mass the rajahs remained on their knees with clasped hands. At the elevation the ships fired all their artillery in response to musket signal from the shore.</p>"},"photo":null}},"name":"First Mass in the Philippines","region":"Eastern Visayas"},"Q42699840":{"lon":120.89233,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Ladislao Diwa":true},"macroAddress":"Cavite City, Cavite","date":"1964-11-30","lat":14.47703,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>To the memory of Ladislao Diwa, patriot, educator, one of the founders of the Katipunan in 1892, one of the signers of the Proclamation of the Philippine Independence on 12 June 1898, first civil governor of Cavite and a leader in the Philippine Revolution. </p><p> Born in San Roque, Cavite on 27 June 1863. Died in Caridad, Cavite on 12 March 1930.</p><p> This monument was erected and dedicated by patriotic citizens and teachers on 30 November 1964, the day this school was renamed in his honor.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ladislao Diwa Elementary School"}}},"address":"Ladislao Diwa Elementary School, Padre Burgos Avenue cor. Crisostomo Street, Caridad, Cavite City, Cavite","name":"Ladislao Diwa Elementary School","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q43357307":{"region":"Cordillera Administrative Region","name":"Dominican Hill and Retreat House","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"60","height":1944,"file":"Diplomat Hotel Marker.JPG","credit":"Ramiltibayan {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1457},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo bilang bahay bakasyunan ng mga Dominikano sa Dominican Hill sa Baguio, 1913–1915. Idinisenyo ni Fr. Roque Ruaño , O.P.; pinasinayaan, 1915. Ginawang paaralan at pinangalanang Colegio del Santissimo Rosario, 1915–1918. Nagsilbing kanlungan ng mga pamilya at paring Dominikano noong panahon ng Hapon, 1942–1945. Ginamit ng mga Hapon bilang huling tanggulan, 1945. Binomba ng mga sundalong Amerikano, Abril 1945; ipinaayos, 1945–1947. Ginawang Diplomat Hotel, 1973–1987. Inilipat ang pagmamamay-ari sa Lungsod ng Baguio, 2005.</p>","subtitle":"(1915)","title":"Dominican Hill and Retreat House"}}},"address":"Dominican Hill Retreat House, Dominican Hill Road, Baguio","lat":16.40402,"macroAddress":"Baguio","date":"2014-09-01","wikipedia":{"Dominican Hill Retreat House":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.58659},"Q41998118":{"macroAddress":"Bulakan, Bulacan","date":"2012-01-17","lat":14.79754,"name":"Birthplace of Marcelo H. del Pilar","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3636,"hash":"ad","credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"JC Marcelo Shrine 16.JPG","width":2586},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Born in Barrio San Nicolas, town of Bulacan on August 30, 1850 to Julian H. del Pilar and Blasa Gatmaytan. Marcelo H. del Pilar, patriot, writer and editor of La Solidaridad, a newspaper of the Propaganda Movement published in Spain. Died in Barcelona, July 4, 1896.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Birthplace of Marcelo H. del Pilar"}}},"address":"Marcelo H. del Pilar Shrine, Barangay San Nicolas Street, Bulakan, Bulacan","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.86896,"wikipedia":{"Marcelo H. del Pilar":true},"locDesc":null},"Q55339960":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Naging enkomiyenda noong ika-14 ng Nobyembre, 1571. Si Gaspar Osorio ang unang punong bayan noong 1594. Sa bayang ito nagkasakit at namatay si Emilio Jacinto, “Ang Utak ng Katipunan,” habang pinamumunuan ang mga Pilipino laban sa mga Amerikano noong ika-16 ng Abril, 1899.</p>","title":"Mahayhay","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Majayjay Church, F. Blumentritt Street, Majayjay, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Mahayhay","lat":14.14597,"macroAddress":"Majayjay, Laguna","date":"1971","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Emilio Jacinto":true,"Majayjay":true},"lon":121.47142,"locPhoto":null},"Q25070568":{"lat":14.26271,"macroAddress":"Maragondon, Cavite","date":"1953","address":"Bonifacio Shrine and Eco-Tourism Park, Maragondon, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Noong Mayo 10, 1897, sa pook na itong tinatawag na Nagpatong, malapit sa Bundok Buntis, Maragondon, ang Supremo Andres Bonifacio at ang kanyang kapatid na si Procopio ay binaril alinsunod sa pasiya ng hukumang militar ng Pamahalaang Mapanghimagsik.</p>","title":"Bundok Nagpatong","subtitle":"Maragondon, Kabite"},"photo":{"width":1072,"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Bundok Nagpatong Historical Marker.jpg","height":1430,"hash":"1b"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Bundok Nagpatong","lon":120.7176,"locPhoto":{"width":1920,"file":"Andres Bonifacio Mount Nagpatong Park.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":1372,"hash":"f2"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of a small obelisk at the western portion of the park.","wikipedia":{"Andres Bonifacio":"Andrés Bonifacio","Procopio Bonifacio":true}},"Q54486817":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the left corner of the portico of the main entrance of the complex.","wikipedia":{"Hospicio de San Jose":true},"locPhoto":{"hash":"e8","height":3264,"credit":"Roel Balingit {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Hospicio de San Jose historical marker - location.jpeg","width":1836},"lon":120.98764,"address":"Hospicio de San Jose, San Miguel, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1836,"file":"Hospicio de San Jose historical marker.jpeg","credit":"Roel Balingit {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":3264,"hash":"65"},"text":{"title":"Hospicio de San Jose","subtitle":"(1782)","inscription":"<p>Itinatag noong 1782 ng mag-asawang Francisco Gomez Enriquez para sa mahihirap at mahihina ang isip. Mula sa Pandakan ay inilipat sa Intramuros, pagkatapos ay sa Binundok, at katapus-tapusa'y sa munting pulong ito noong 1835–40. Ang institusyong ito ay kumakalinga sa mahihirap at sa walang mag-aruga. Ang pagkalinga sa mga sanggol ay sinimulan noong 1905. Mula noong 1905 hanggang 1917, ang mga batang may pagkakasalang nagawa ay ipinadadala dito ng pamahalaan. Mula noong 1865, ang mga <u>Sisters of Charity</u> ay siya nang namahala sa institusyong ito.</p>"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Hospicio de San Jose","lat":14.59078,"macroAddress":"San Miguel, Manila","date":"1977"},"Q52167811":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.91517,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"San Jose de Ivana Church":true},"lat":20.36631,"date":"2008","macroAddress":"Ivana, Batanes","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo bilang kapilya, 1787. Ipinagawa ang simbahang bato ni P. Francisco de Paula Esteban, O.P., 1795; ang kampanaryo ni P. Jose Fausto de Cuevas, O.P., 1814–1817. Pinaliit ang simbahan matapos lumisan ang mga mamamayan ng Sabtang, 1844. Ipinaayos ang harapan ng simbahan ni P. Fabian Martin, O.P., 1866–1869. Itinaas ng mga Katipunero ang bandila ng Katipunan sa kampanaryo ng simbahan, 18 Setyembre 1898. Nasira ng lindol, 2000. Isinaayos ni P. Gumersindo Hernandez, O.P., 2001.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Ivana"}}},"address":"San Jose de Ivana Church, National Road, Ivana, Batanes","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Simbahan ng Ivana"},"Q56239887":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Ellinwood Malate Church","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng Presbyterian Mission sa boys dormitory na ipinangalan kay Rev. Dr. Francis F. Ellinwood sa Daang Wright na ngayo’y Antonio Vasquez sa Malate; Rev. George Wright, unang pastor, 1907. Inilipat sa Tooker Hall ng Union High School, 1919. Rev. Catalino Paulino, unang Filipinong pastor, 1921. Ipinatayo ang unang kongkretong santuaryo at pinangalanang Ellinwood Malate Church, 1932. Dito itinago ang mga electro-type plates na ginamit sa paglimbag ng bibliya mula sa American Bible Society noong Labanan sa Maynila, 1945. Itinatag dito ang United Church of Chrsit in the Philippines, 1948. Ipinatayo ang kasalukuyang santuaryo, 1956. Pinagdausan ng Kumbensiyong Konstitusyonal ng UCCP, 1972. Halimbawa ng modernong arkitektura noong unang bahago ng siglo-20 na naglalarawan ng estilong hango sa Romanesko at Gotiko.</p>"}}},"address":"Ellinwood Malate Church, 1661 Antonio Vasquez Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Ellinwood Malate Church","lat":14.57489,"date":"2007","macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":120.98728,"locPhoto":null},"Q54613357":{"macroAddress":"Binondo, Manila","date":"1977","lat":14.59883,"name":"Patricio Mariano","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Mandudula, mamamahayag, makata, at nobelista na ipinanganak sa Sta. Cruz, Maynila, noong ika-17 ng Marso, 1877, anak ng mag-asawang Petronilo Mariano at Dionisia Geronimo. Naging kanang kamay ni Ambrosio Rianzares Bautista, unang tagapayo ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo. Naging kagawad ng pasulatan ng mga pahayagang <u>Heraldo de la Revolucion</u>, <u>Kaibigan nang Bayan</u>, <u>El Renacimiento</u>, <u>El Renacimiento Filipino</u>, at naging patnugot ng mga pahayagang <u>Ang Paggawa</u> at <u>Ang Lunas ng Bayan</u>.</p><p> Namatay sa Maynila noong ika-25 ng Enero, 1935.</p>","subtitle":"(1877–1935)","title":"Patricio Mariano"},"photo":{"hash":"b1","height":3342,"file":"Patricio Mariano historical marker (cropped).JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2843}}},"address":"Estero de la Reina, Banquero Street corner Escolta Street, Binondo, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97974,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"file":"0011jfSanta Cruz Recto Avenue Binondo Streets Manilafvf 11.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"8d","height":3456},"wikipedia":{"Patricio Mariano":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting by the river wall."},"Q38446821":{"lat":14.57171,"date":"2007","macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","details":{"text":{"tl":{"title":"Ramon Magsaysay","subtitle":"(1907–1957)","inscription":"<p>Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas</p>"},"en":{"inscription":"<p>President of the Republic of the Philippines (1953–1957)</p>","title":"Ramon Magsaysay","subtitle":"(1907–1957)"}},"photo":{"file":"Ramon Magsaysay (1907 - 1957) Roxas blvd.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":485,"hash":"53","height":462}},"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Dr. J. Quintos Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Ramon Magsaysay","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98191,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Ramon Magsaysay":true}},"Q55157479":{"lon":122.75207,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Manuel Roxas":true},"lat":11.58316,"date":"2011","macroAddress":"Roxas, Capiz","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Manuel Acuña Roxas","subtitle":"(1892–1948)","inscription":"<p>Patriot, statesman and soldier. Fifth President of the Republic of the Philippines, 1946–1948. Born in Capiz, Capiz (now Roxas City), 1 January 1892. Obtained Bachelor of Laws, University of the Philippines; Bar topnotcher, 1913. Governor of Capiz, 1919–1922. Representative of Capiz and Speaker of the House, 1922–1934; headed the Philippine Independence Mission to the United States with Sergio Osmeña known as Os–Rox Mission, 1931–1933. Delegate to the Constitutional Convention, 1935; Secretary of Finance, 1938; Senator, 1941; President of the Senate, 1945–1946. Became major during World War II, 1941; and brigadier–general, 1945. Died, 15 April 1948.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Hughes Street cor. Rizal Street, Roxas, Capiz","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Manuel Acuña Roxas"},"Q28937549":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":124.27848,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":399,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Notre Dame Archdiocesan Seminary historical marker.jpg","height":517,"hash":"2f"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ni Arsobispo Gerard Mongeau, OMI, DD, sa Kidapawan, 1960. Fr. William McGrath, OMI, unang rector. Inilipat sa Rebuken, Sultan Kudarat, Maguindanao, 1963. Binasbasan ni Rufino J. Cardinal Santos, 1964. Kilala rin bilang Nuling Seminary. Makaraan ang \"missionary era\" nagpatuloy na tumulong upang makapagpatapos ng mga lokal na pari na maglilingkod sa Archdiocese of Cotabato, Diocese of Kidapawan at sa iba pang panig ng mundo. Naging instrumento sa pagpapalaganap ng Kristiyanismo at pagkakawanggawa sa mga maralita sa Mindanao.</p>","title":"Notre Dame Archdiocesan Seminary","subtitle":"Archdiocese of Cotabato"}}},"address":"Notre Dame Archdiocesan Seminary, Quezon Avenue, Cotabato City","region":"Soccsksargen","name":"Notre Dame Archdiocesan Seminary","lat":7.25867,"macroAddress":"Cotabato City","date":"2010"},"Q54810531":{"wikipedia":{"Leona Florentino":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.38925,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Leona Florentino","region":"Ilocos Region","address":"1 Calle Crisologo, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Leona Florentino","inscription":"<p>Foremost Ilocano poetess, subtle satirist and playwright. Born in Vigan, Ilocos Sur 19 April 1849. Daughter of Marcelino Florentino and Isabel Florentino mother of the late Isabelo de los Reyes. Distant cousin of Rizal. A poet at the age of ten. Her works in Spanish and Ilocano were later exhibited in the “Exposicion General de Filipinas,” Madrid, 1887 and in the “Exposition Internationale,” Paris, 1889. Her name with a list of some of her works appeared in the “Bibliotheque Internationale des Ouveres des Femmes” edited by madame Andzia Wolkska, 1889. Died 4 October 1884.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"b4","height":3400,"file":"Historical Marker Leona Florentino.jpg","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2261}}},"macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","date":"1959-04-19","lat":17.57363},"Q24817348":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.92106,"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Goco Ancestral House","address":"Goco Ancestral House, Calle Hermenegildo del Castillo cor. Calle Gliceria Marella, Taal, Batangas","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Goco Ancestral House","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This heritage house of the Goco family is registered with the National Historical institute, pursuant to NHI Board Resolution No. 03, S. 2000.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"c9","height":1820,"width":1972,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Goco Ancestral House historical marker.jpg"}}},"lat":13.88013,"macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","date":"2001"},"Q55097169":{"wikipedia":{"Agueda Kahabagan":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.415,"name":"Agueda Kahabagan","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Agueda Kahabagan","inscription":"<p>Rebolusyonaryo at heneral ng Hukbo ng Republika ng Pilipinas. Isinilang sa Santa Cruz, Laguna. Isa sa mga babaeng lumahok sa rebolusyon sa Laguna at sa digmaan laban sa mga Amerikano. Pinamunuan ang isang pulutong ng kawal ni Brigadyer Heneral Severino Taiño, Mayo 1897. Binansagang “henerala” dahil sa kanyang galing at kasanayan sa pamumuno sa ilang mga labanan sa Laguna, isa na rito ang sa San Pablo, Oktubre 1897. Iminungkahi ni Heneral Pio del Pilar kay Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo na kilalanin bilang heneral, 6 Abril 1899. Inihalal sa katungkulan at naging kaisa-isang babaeng heneral sa talaan ng Hukbong Pilipino, 1899. Dinakip ng pwersang Amerikano, Enero 1902.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Pio Valenzuela Street, Santa Cruz, Laguna","date":"2016-03-14","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Laguna","lat":14.28159},"Q40311869":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Manila massacre":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97441,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":960,"hash":"21","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical marker Memorare Manila 1945.jpg","width":720},"text":{"inscription":"<p>This monument is erected in memory of the more than 100,000 defenseless civilians who were killed during the Battle for the Liberation of Manila between February 3 and March 3, 1945. They were mainly victims of heinous acts perpetrated by the Japanese Imperial Forces and the casualties of the heavy artillery barrage by the American forces. </p><p>The Battle for Manila at the end of World War II was one of the most brutal episode in the history of Asia and the Pacific. </p><p>The non-combatant victims of that tragic battle will remain forever in the hearts and minds of the Filipino people.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Memorare – Manila 1945"}}},"address":"Gen. Luna Street cor. Anda Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Memorare – Manila 1945","region":"Metro Manila","date":"1995","macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","lat":14.59028},"Q54864143":{"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Heneral Isidoro D. Torres","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"ce","height":4608,"file":"General Isidoro D. Torres historical marker.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":3456},"text":{"title":"Heneral Isidoro D. Torres","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Isinilang noong ika-10 Abril 1866 sa baryo ng Matimbo, Malolos; anak nina Florencio Torres at Maria Dayao; nagtapos ng segunda enseñanza sa Kolehiyo ng San Juan de Letran at pagka Batsilyer sa Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas; naging Cabeza de Barangay sa loob ng tatlong taon, 1890–1892; umanib sa Katipunan, 1892, at kilala sa taguring “Matang Lawin”; nakihamok sa iba’t ibang madugong labanan sa Tulay ng Bagbag, Kalumpit, San Rafael, Binakod, at Barasoain, 1896–1899; naging Koronel sa Republika ng Biyak-na-Bato, 1897; kasapi sa Kongreso ng Malolos, 1898; naging Gobernador Militar de la Plaza sa tungkuling Brigadyer, 1898; nagtatag ng gerilya nang ang Malolos ay mapasakamay ni Heneral Arthur MacArthur, ika-31 ng Marso, 1899; juez de paz ng San Antonio, Nuweba Esiha, 1909–1912. Namatay noong ika-5 ng Disyembre, 1928.</p>"}}},"address":"Barangay Matimbo Road, Matimbo, Malolos, Bulacan","lat":14.81801,"date":"1956-09-15","macroAddress":"Malolos, Bulacan","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal at end of an open area marking the birthplace.","locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"General Isidoro D. Torres Monument.jpg","hash":"a3","height":3456},"lon":120.83616},"Q55383578":{"lon":119.981,"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"3a","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"IbaCapitoliojf9075 04.JPG","width":3456},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the Provincial Capitol lobby, to the right of the main staircase.","date":"1939","macroAddress":"Iba, Zambales","lat":15.32581,"name":"Provincial Building of Zambales","region":"Central Luzon","address":"Zambales Provincial Capitol, Iba, Zambales","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>This building was constructed by the Spanish Civil Government in the years 1875–1878. The molave and yacal posts were cut in the forest near Dirita. Used as a provincial prison during the Spanish regime, it became the general headquarters of the Revolutionary Government of Zambales in 1899. A portion of the building has, ever since, been utilized as the seat of the Provincial Government. The front part was reconstructed in 1939.</p>","title":"Provincial Building of Zambales","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"cc","height":3271,"width":3059,"file":"Provincial Building of Zambales historical marker (cropped).JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}}},"Q50385026":{"lon":120.98188,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"The Manila Grand Opera House historical marker location.jpg","width":1577,"height":1176,"hash":"0e"},"wikipedia":{"Manila Grand Opera House":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the corner of the landscaping at the entrance of the hotel’s parking area.","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","date":"1948","lat":14.60575,"name":"The Manila Grand Opera House","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Manila Grand Opera Hotel & Casino, 925 Doroteo Jose Street cor. Rizal Avenue, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":2142,"hash":"57","width":2182,"file":"The Manila Grand Opera House historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ryomaandres; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Erected on this site, and the scene of the inauguration of the First Philippine Assembly, was burned November 16, 1943. This new building was erected and inaugurated April 11, 1947.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"The Manila Grand Opera House"}}}},"Q44702634":{"wikipedia":{"Ramon Magsaysay":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the front side of the pedestal for the bust of Ramon Magsaysay.","locPhoto":{"hash":"5c","height":768,"width":1024,"credit":"Nmcast {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pres. Ramon Magsaysay monument in Mt. Manunggal, Balamban, Cebu.jpg"},"lon":123.81407,"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Ramon Magsaysay","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ramon Magsaysay","subtitle":"(1907–1957)","inscription":"<p>Idolo ng masa, kilala sa tawag na “The Guy.” Isinilang noong Agosto 31, 1907 sa Iba, Zambales. Nagkamit ng BSC, Jose Rizal College, Mandaluyong, Rizal. Pangkalahatang puno, Zambales Military District, 1942; panghukbong punong-lalawigan ng Zambales at itinaas sa pagka-medyo ni Heneral Douglas MacArthur, 1945; Kinatawan, 1946–1950; Kalihim ng National Defense, 1950; pangatlong Pangulo ng Pilipinas, 1953. Kumuha ng Rogers Bill sa Estados Unidos para sa mga beteranong Pilipino at sumupil ng mga Hukbalahap. Nagtatag ng President’s Action Committee (PCAC), National Rehabilitation and Resettlement Administration (NARRA), National Marketing Corporation (NAMARCO), at Land Tenure Administration (LTA). Namatay nang bumagsak ang sinasakyang Mt. Pinatubo sa pook na ito, noong Marso 17, 1957.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Mount Manunggal, Brgy. Sunog, Balamban, Cebu","lat":10.45047,"macroAddress":"Balamban, Cebu","date":"1988"},"Q55367346":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Penyaranda","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pamamagitan ng kautusán ng Gobernador Henerál noong 1851, ang nayong Mapisong ng Gapáng ay nagíng munisipyo ng Penyaranda bilang parangál kay José María Peñaranda, inhinyero sibil. Ang mga unang alkalde sa ilalim ng ibá ibáng pamamahala: Basilio Padilla, 1851, panahon ng Kastila; Ponciano Abesamis, 1898–1899, Repúbliká Pilipina; Ambrosio Legaspi, 1900, panahón ng Amerikano; Casiano M. Abes, 1935, Komonwelt; Casiano M. Abes, 1945, Pagkápalaya; Aquilino H. Aberin, 1946, Repúblika ng Pilipinas; Amado B. Ramos, kasalukuyang Alkalde.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"23","height":4608,"file":"Peñaranda (Nueva Ecija) historical marker.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":3456}}},"address":"Peñaranda Municipal Hall, Brgy. Sinasajan, Peñaranda, Nueva Ecija","name":"Penyaranda","region":"Central Luzon","date":"1951","macroAddress":"Peñaranda, Nueva Ecija","lat":15.36519,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Peñaranda":"Peñaranda, Nueva Ecija"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.01429},"Q56072024":{"lat":15.68691,"date":"1987-09-25","macroAddress":"Camiling, Tarlac","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Carlos P. Romulo","address":"Camiling Park, Quezon Avenue, Camiling, Tarlac","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1899–1985)","title":"Carlos P. Romulo","inscription":"<p>Bantog na diplomatiko, edukador, mamamahayag at manunulat. Ipinanganak sa Camiling, Tarlac noong Enero 14, 1899. Nagkamit ng A.B., University of the Philippines, 1918; M.A., Columbia University, New York, 1921; at 71 pang pandangal na titulo. Patnugot ng Taliba–La Vanguardia–Tribune, 1931; isa sa mga nagtatag, Boy Scouts of the Philippines, 1936; at tagapaglathala ng Debate–Mabuhay–Herald–Monday Mail, 1937. May-akda ng “Rizal A Chronicle Play,” “The Magsaysay Story,” at atbp. Kasama ni Hen. Douglas MacArthur sa Leyte Landing, 1944. Unang Asyanong Pangulo, United Nations General Assembly, 1949; tatlong beses na Pangulo U.N. Security Council; at 20 beses na pinuno ng delegasyon ng Pilipinas, U.N. General Assembly. Kalihim ng Kabatiran at Kaugnayang Publiko, Embahador at Tanging Sugo sa U.S.A., Pangulo ng U.P. at Kalihim ng Pagtuturo, at Ministro ng Suliraning Panlabas. Tumanggap ng Pulitzer Prize sa Pamamahayag, Silver Star, Purple Heart, Legion of Honor, Presidential Unit Citation at Presidential Medal of Freedom sa U.S.A. at 65 pang medalya at karangalan. Namatay noong Disyembre 15, 1985.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.4145,"wikipedia":{"Carlos P. Romulo":true},"locDesc":null},"Q32093140":{"name":"Zapote Battlefield","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Zapote Battlefield","inscription":"<p>On this site the Filipino revolutionary forces fought two decisive battles: one against the Spanish forces, 17 February 1897, in which Filipino General Edilberto Evangelista was killed; the other, against the American forces, 13 June 1899, led by General H. W. Lawton, who later was killed in San Mateo, Rizal, by Filipino General Licerio Geronimo.</p>"},"photo":{"height":3640,"hash":"4a","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Zapote Battlefield historical marker.jpg","width":2378}}},"address":"Zapote Bridge, Aguinaldo Highway, Bacoor, Cavite","date":"1952","macroAddress":"Bacoor, Cavite","lat":14.46388,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Zapote River":true,"Battle of Zapote Bridge":"Battle of Zapote Bridge (1897)","Edilberto Evangelista":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of a monument at the southern end of Zapote Bridge that is depicting General Edilberto Evangelista.","lon":120.96625,"locPhoto":{"width":1536,"file":"Zapote Battlefield Monument.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":2048,"hash":"cd"}},"Q43302185":{"locPhoto":{"height":1877,"hash":"f1","width":1610,"file":"Morong Museum entrance (2).jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"lon":121.23887,"wikipedia":{"Morong":"Morong, Rizal"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located immediately to the left of the main entrance of the old Morong municipal hall.","date":"1971","macroAddress":"Morong, Rizal","lat":14.51285,"name":"Morong","region":"Calabarzon","address":"Tupas Street, Morong, Rizal","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"d9","height":2361,"width":1839,"file":"Morong Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Hannachiever07 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang bayan ng Morong noong 1578 at naging kabisera nang itatag ang Distrito Politico-Militar ng Morong noong 1853. Ang distrito ay naging lalawigan ng Rizal noong 1901. Ang gusaling ito na kilala sa tawag na \"Commandancia\" ay itinayo noong 1880–1881, sa panahon ni G. Mauricio Mata Cruz, gobernadorsilyo ng bayan.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Morong"}}}},"Q24702138":{"macroAddress":"Balangiga, Eastern Samar","date":"1982","lat":11.10959,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Balangiga Massacre","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa bayang ito, noong ika-28 ng Setyembre 1901, nilusob ng mga Pilipinong nasasandatahan ng gulok ang Kumpanya “C”, ika-9 na Impanteriya ng E.U. Napatay nila halos lahat ang lahat ng mga sundalong Amerikano. Bilang ganti ay naglunsad ang mga Amerikano ng may anim na buwang “pagpatay at pagsunog,” ang bayan ay nagmistulang “humahagulgol na kagubatan.” Dahil sa kanilang kalupitan, sina Brig. Hen. Jacob H. Smith at Medyor Littleton W. T. Waller ay nilitis ng hukumang militar at itiniwalag.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Jojit Ballesteros {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical marker at the foot of Valeriano Abanador statue.JPG","width":2448,"hash":"7a","height":3696}}},"address":"Balangiga, Eastern Samar","name":"Balangiga Massacre","region":"Eastern Visayas","lon":125.3861,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Balangiga massacre":true}},"Q55721704":{"lat":14.9375,"date":"2002","macroAddress":"Castillejos, Zambales","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Tahanan ng mga Magsaysay","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na ito ginugol ni Ramon Magsaysay, ikapitong Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas at kilala sa taguring “The Guy,” ang mabungang taon ng kanyang buhay. Ipinamana niya ang mga katangian ng masikap na paggawa, pananagutang sibiko para sa pangkaraniwang tao at makabayang gawain para sa bayan at mga mamamayan. </p><p>Muling ipinagawa ng mga inapo ng Pangulong Magsaysay, 1990. Napinsala nang malaki nang pumutok ang Bundok Pinatubo, Hunyo 1991, muling isinaayos ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan, 1999.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"2a","height":4608,"width":3456,"file":"Ramon Magsaysay Home historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"address":"President Ramon Magsaysay House, National Highway, Brgy. Sta. Maria, Castillejos, Zambales","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Tahanan ng mga Magsaysay","lon":120.19614,"locPhoto":{"hash":"ff","height":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"RamonMagsaysayjf7462 02.JPG","width":4608},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the left of the main door of the house.","wikipedia":{"Ramon Magsaysay":true}},"Q53447898":{"locPhoto":{"hash":"16","height":1029,"file":"Department of Health Central Office - main entrance of main building.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":863},"lon":120.98207,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the left of the main entrance of the main building.","wikipedia":{"Department of Health":"Department of Health (Philippines)"},"macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","date":"1994-09-28","lat":14.61546,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Kagawaran ng Kalusugan.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":391,"hash":"d8","height":599},"text":{"title":"Kagawaran ng Kalusugan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang Lingkuran ng Kalusugang Pambayan at Lupon ng Kalusugan ng Lungsod ng Maynila sa Bisa ng Pangkalahatang Kautusan Blg. 15, Setyembre 29, 1898. Naging Lupon ng Kalusugan sa pamamagitan ng Batas Blg. 157 ng Komisyon ng Pilipinas, Hulyo 1, 1901, Kawanihan ng Kalusugan, 1905 at Lingkurang Pangkalusugan ng Pilipinas, 1915 at muling pinanganlang Kawanihan ng Kalusugan. Isinama sa Tanggapan ng Komisyuner ng Kalusugan at Kagalingang Pambayan sa ilalim ng Kagawaran ng Pagtuturong Pambayan, 1932. Itinaas bilang kagawaran, 1941 at naging hiwalay na kagawaran, 1947. Ilang mga yunit ang itinatag sa ilalim nito: Laboratoryo sa Pananaliksik ng Kalusugang Pambayan, 1950; mga Tanggapang Pangrehiyon ng Kalusugan, 1958. Lingkurang Pangkalusugan at Medikal ay pinagsama-sama, 1982. Panrehiyong Tanggapan ng Kalusugan sa NCR at pinagbukod-bukod ang mga tanging pagamutan sa mga Pambansang Sentro ng Medikal at mga tanging sentro sa pananaliksik, 1987; at ang mga pangunahing lingkuran ng kalusugan ay isinalin sa mga local na yunit ng pamahalaan, 1991.</p>"}}},"address":"Department of Health Central Office, Rizal Avenue cor. Tayuman Street, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Kagawaran ng Kalusugan","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q55313864":{"locPhoto":{"hash":"40","height":1783,"credit":"Ramiltibayan {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Entrance to Catalino Rodriguez House.JPG","width":2366},"lon":121.52508,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the house facade on Daliz street, to the left on the entry door.","wikipedia":{"Don Catalino Rodriguez Ancestral House":true},"macroAddress":"Sariaya, Quezon","date":"2008-05-14","lat":13.96287,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a heritage house by the National Historical Institute 14 May 2008</p>","title":"Rodriguez House","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Don Catalino Rodriguez Ancestral House, Daliz Street cor. Quezon Avenue, Sariaya, Quezon","name":"Rodriguez House","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q53861712":{"wikipedia":{"Sofia de Veyra":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.51624,"region":"Western Visayas","name":"Sofia Reyes de Veyra","address":"Villa Arevalo Plaza, Osmeña Street cor. Yulo Drive, Arevalo, Iloilo City","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"9c","height":2141,"width":1923,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Sofia Reyes de Veyra historical marker.JPG"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Arevalo, Iloilo ika-30 ng Setyembre ng taong 1876. Namuno sa mahahalagang kilusang sibiko at sa mga adhikaing pangkababaihan ng bansa. Tampok sa larangan ng paghubog sa puso at isipan ng mga mag-aaral.</p><p>Naging Pangalawang Pangulo ng Pamantasang Centro Escolar mula noong 1934 hanggang 1953, taon ng kanyang kamatayan.</p>","title":"Sofia Reyes de Veyra","subtitle":"(1876–1953)"}}},"lat":10.68863,"date":"1976-09-30","macroAddress":"Iloilo City"},"Q56220007":{"lon":120.99614,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":14.64649,"date":"1982","macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Jorge Pineda","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Jorge Pineda","subtitle":"1879–1946","inscription":"<p>Realistikong pintor. Ipinanganak sa Sta. Cruz, Maynila 26 Hulyo 1879. Nag-aral sa Academia de Dibujo y Pintura. Disenyador, <u>Renacimiento Filipino</u>; litograpo, Carmelo & Bauermann; at karikaturista, <u>Philippine Free Press.</u> Ilan sa kanyang mga pintura ay ang “Sungka,” “Siklot,” “Panguingue,” at “Kakawate.” Ang “Las Buyeras” ay nagkamit ng pangatlong gantimpala sa Pandaigdig na Eksposisyon sa St. Louis, E.U., 1904. Unang Pilipinong pintor na nagsalarawan sa tula ni Rizal, ang “Ultimo Adios” sa oleo at akwarela sa 14 na kanbas. Namatay 12 Setyembre 1946.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"11 J. Pineda Street, Barangay Pag-ibig sa Nayon, Balintawak, Quezon City, Metro Manila"},"Q46993491":{"wikipedia":{"Jose Rizal Monument":"First José Rizal Monument (Daet)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the monument.","locPhoto":{"hash":"6a","height":2896,"width":1944,"credit":"Firehorse {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Oldest Jose Rizal Monument in Daet, Camarines Norte by Gina Meneses.jpg"},"lon":122.95455,"region":"Bicol Region","name":"First Rizal Monument","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>First Rizal Monument in the Philippines. Erected by voluntary contributions of the People of Camarines Norte, led by Lt. Col. Ildefonso Alegre and Lt. Col. Antonio Sanz of the Revolutionary Army. Unveiled on 30 December 1898.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Rizal Park, Magallanes Iraya Street cor. Justo Lukban Street, Daet, Camarines Norte","lat":14.11319,"date":"1961","macroAddress":"Daet, Camarines Norte"},"Q41328550":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the pedestal of the monument of Juan Cailles.","wikipedia":{"Juan Cailles":true},"lon":121.41722,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Monument to Juan Cailles in Laguna Provincial Capital, Philippines.jpg","width":3456,"hash":"92","height":4608},"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1871–1951)","title":"Juan Cailles","inscription":"<p>Makabayan, Rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Nasugbu, Batangas, 10 Nobyembre 1871. Nagkamit ng Teacher's Diploma, Paaralang Normal ng mga Heswita, 1890. Nagturo sa baryo Amaya, Tanza, Cavite hanggang sa pagsiklab ng Himagsikang Filipino, 1896. Umanib sa hukbo ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo at naging brigadyer heneral, 1897. Isa sa mga lumagda sa pagpapahayag ng Kalayaan ng Pilipinas, 12 Hunyo 1898. Itinalaga sa Laguna, 1899. Tinalo ang mga Amerikano sa Labanan ng Mabitac, 17 Setyembre 1900. Sumuko sa mga Amerikano, 24 Hunyo 1901. Hinirang na Gobernador Sibil, 1902-1910 at nahalal na Gobernador ng Laguna, 1915-1925; naging kinatawan ng Lalawigan ng Mountain Province, 1926-1931; muling nahalal na Gobernador ng Laguna, 1932-1938; pangalawang tagapangulo ng Board of Pensions for Veterans, 1940. Inspektor Heneral ng Philippine Veterans Administration, 1941. Yumao 28 Hunyo 1951.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2500,"file":"Juan Cailles historical marker, Laguna, Philippines.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"00","height":3622}}},"address":"Old Laguna Provincial Capitol Building, Pedro Guevarra Avenue, Santa Cruz, Laguna","name":"Juan Cailles","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Laguna","date":"2013","lat":14.27549},"Q28855210":{"date":"1993","macroAddress":"Silay, Negros Occidental","lat":10.80198,"name":"Manuel Severino Hofileña Ancestral House","region":"Western Visayas","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":387,"hash":"9a","width":520,"file":"Hofileña Ancestral House 03.JPG","credit":"Claire Algarme {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>This is a Heritage House pursuant to Board Resolution no. 3 dated April 6, 1993 of the National Historical Institute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Manuel Severino Hofileña Ancestral House"}}},"address":"Hofileña Ancestral House, Silay, Negros Occidental","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.97427,"wikipedia":{"Hofileña Ancestral House":true},"locDesc":null},"Q25080050":{"name":"Simbahan ng Dasmariñas","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating kapilya sa baryo ng Imus. Itinatag ang Parokya ng Camarin de Piedra ng mga paring Rekoleto noong 1867. Ipinatayo ang simbahang bato sa patronato ng La Immaculada Concepcion at naging unang kura paroko si Padre Valentin Diaz. Nagsilbing luklukan ng pamahalaang sibil ng mga Kastila ang kumbento: naganap dito ang madugong labanan ng magapi ng hukbong Kastila ang mga rebolusyonaryo sa pamumuno ni Kapitan Placido Campos at kanyang kalihim Francisco Barzaga, Pebrero 25, 1897. Ipiniit rin dito ng mga Hapon ang mga mamamayan noong Disyembre 17, 1944 at 17 sa kanilang pinatay ang nalibing sa iisang hukay.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Dasmariñas"},"photo":{"width":2500,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Simbahan ng Dasmariñas historical marker.jpg","hash":"3c","height":3392}}},"address":"Immaculate Conception Parish Church of Dasmariñas, Dasmariñas, Cavite","macroAddress":"Dasmariñas, Cavite","date":"1986-10-02","lat":14.32693,"wikipedia":{"Immaculate Conception Parish Church of Dasmariñas":"Immaculate Conception Parish Church (Dasmariñas)"},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.93583,"locPhoto":null},"Q28869091":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Luneta Hotel","address":"Luneta Hotel, 414 Kalaw Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"8c","height":2994,"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Luneta Hotel historical marker.jpg","width":2500},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Idinisenyo ni Salvador Farre. Binuksan bilang isang otel, 1919. Dito namalagi ang mga kalahok sa XXXIII International Eucharistic Congress, 1937. Ginawang Noncommissioned Officer’s Club ng mga Amerikano, Hulyo 1941. Isa sa mga naunang mataas na kongkretong gusali sa Maynila noong pangalawang dekada ng ika-20 dantaon. Halimbawa ng istilong French Renaissance.</p>","title":"Luneta Hotel","subtitle":null}}},"lat":14.58,"date":"2014-05-09","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","wikipedia":{"Luneta Hotel":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall between the two main doorways of the hotel.","lon":120.9781,"locPhoto":{"height":1936,"hash":"5d","width":2850,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Luneta Hotel main entrance.jpg"}},"Q46872637":{"name":"Silva House","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 04 September 2009</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Silva House"},"photo":null}},"address":"Silva House, Jose Rizal Street, Carcar, Cebu","date":"2010-05-29","macroAddress":"Carcar, Cebu","lat":10.10457,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main door of the house.","lon":123.64113,"locPhoto":{"width":2448,"file":"Silva Residence.jpeg","credit":"Pinoeana {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":3264,"hash":"df"}},"Q50384107":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Engracia Cruz Reyes","subtitle":"(1892–1975)","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak, Navotas, Rizal, Abril 16, 1892. Nanguna sa industriya ng restaurant, tagapagtaguyod ng pagkaing Pilipino at ng baro’t saya; feminista. Nagsimula sa negosyo sa pamamagitan ng pagbubukas ng kantinang ‘Lapu-Lapu’ na nagsisilbi ng mga popular na pagkaing Pilipino sa Marquez de Comillas, Maynila, 1928. Sinundan ito ng travelling store na pinanganlang ‘Aristocrat,’ 1936; itinatag ang Aristocrat Restaurant sa Dewey Boulevard (ngayo’y Roxas Boulevard), 1939; sumapi sa Suffragette Movement, 1937; nagkamit ng gawad pagkilala bilang Mother of the Outstanding Family of the Year; Republic Day Award, 1955; Most Oustanding Woman Award sa marketing ng Philippine Marketing Association, 1967. Sa kanyang karangalan, Ang Gintong Ina Award para sa Outstanding Mother of the Year ay itinatag ng Pambansang Kabataang Barangay, 1982. Namatay, Hulyo 5, 1975.</p>"},"photo":{"height":578,"hash":"ad","width":396,"file":"Engracia Cruz Reyes (1892–1975) historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"address":"Plaza Rajah Sulayman, Roxas Boulevard cor. San Andres Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Engracia Cruz Reyes","lat":14.56866,"date":"1992-07-12","macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Engracia Cruz-Reyes":true},"lon":120.9839,"locPhoto":null},"Q44949419":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Villa Escudero":true},"lon":121.34222,"locPhoto":null,"address":"Villa Escudero, Kilometer 91, Pan-Philippine Highway, Tiaong, Quezon","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Villa Escudero","inscription":""},"photo":null},"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Villa Escudero","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sumasakop sa malawak na lupaing bahagi ng lungsod ng San Pablo sa Laguna at mga bayan ng Tiaong at Dolores sa Quezon. Nabili noong 1880 ni Placido Escudero, isang Kastilang asawa ni Claudia Marasigan. Dito niya kinupkop ang mga manghihimagsik laban sa mga Kastila at Amerikano noong 1897–1901. Dito rin pinatuloy ni Arsenio, kanyang anak at asawa ni Rosario Adap, ang maraming kawal Pilipino at Amerikano nang umurong buhat timog noong 1941 at tumungo sa Bataan; gayundin ang marami sa kanila nang tumalilis sa Bataan. Dito pa rin binuo ni Arsenio ang isang pulutong ng mga gerilya laban sa Hapon noong 1942. Sa pagkupkop ng mag-ama sa mga sundalo sila’y dinakip at pinahirapan ng kani-kanilang kaaway. Isang makasaysayang villa ng kalayaan noong panahon ng Kastila, Amerikano at Hapon.</p>"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Villa Escudero","lat":13.99521,"macroAddress":"Tiaong, Quezon","date":"1984-06-03"},"Q24736360":{"lat":13.87761,"macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","date":"1991-01-22","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ananias Diokno","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ananias Diokno","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Kilala sa taguring Heneral ng Karagatan. Ipinanganak sa Taal, Batangas, Enero 22, 1860. Naging kalihim ng Digma sa pamahalaang pangkagawaran ng Batangas, 1898: Namumunong Heneral ng hukbong ekspedisyunaryo ng Panay; matagumpay na nakipaglaban sa balwarte ng mga Kastila sa Aklan, Antique, Capiz at Lungsod ng Iloilo: Gobernador pampulitiko-militar ng Capiz. Lumahok sa pakikipaglaban ng mga gerilya noong Digmaang Pilipino at Amerikano sa Capiz, 1898. Nakipaglaban at nadakip ng mga Amerikano sa may bundok Makawiwili, Aklan, 1901. Namatay sa Arayat, Pampanga, Nobyembre 2, 1922.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Ananias Diokno historical marker.jpg","width":1156,"height":1768,"hash":"3d"}}},"address":"Calle Ramon Diokno, Taal, Batangas","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.91758,"wikipedia":{"Ananias Diokno":true},"locDesc":null},"Q36483228":{"date":"1991-02-16","macroAddress":"San Pablo, Laguna","lat":14.07147,"name":"Mansiyong Fule–Malvar","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Mansiyong Fule–Malvar","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo sa istilong Romantic Classicism ng mag-asawang Eusebia Fule at Potenciano Malvar, 1915; Grand old man ng San Pablo; pinunong mediko, Digmaang Pilipino-Amerikano; Kinatawan, Asamblea ng Pilipinas, 1909-1912; Gobernador ng Laguna, 1912-1914; at kauna-unahang nahirang na punong lungsod ng San Pablo, 1940. Naging pansamantalang tuluyan ng mga kilalang panauhin ng San Pablo kagaya nina Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon, Sergio Osmeña, atbp. Ipinamana ng mag-asawang Malvar sa kanilang mga pamangkin na siyang nagbili ng mansiyong ito sa National Life Insurance Company, 1966. Nabili ng Philippine American Life Insurance Company, 1988, na siyang gumawa ng pagsasaayos, 1990.</p>"},"photo":{"width":1994,"credit":"Ian Lopez (Ianlopez1115)","file":"Fule Malvar Mansion historical marker.jpg","hash":"5a","height":2617}}},"address":"Fule–Malvar Mansion, Jose Rizal Avenue, San Pablo, Laguna","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.32257,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q55230875":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the building main entrance.","lon":120.81044,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Meralco Malolos branch main entrance.jpg","width":1955,"height":1752,"hash":"6d"},"name":"Pook ng Gobierno Militar de la Plaza","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pook na kinatayuan ng kuwartel ni Heneral Isidoro Torres noong itinalaga ang Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo at Unang Republika ng Pilipinas hanggang sa Digmaang Filipino–Amerikano, 1898–1899. Dito ipinatayo ang bahay ng mag-asawang Ygnacio Adriano at Gregoria Vasquez, 1916. Hanggang sa mabili ng Meralco bilang sangay sa Malolos, 1995. Isinaayos at pinasinayaan, 21 Mayo 1997. Halimbawa ng estilong Art Nouveau noong unang bahagi ng ikadalawampung dantaon at konserbasyon ayon sa konsepto ng Adaptive Re-use.</p>","title":"Pook ng Gobierno Militar de la Plaza","subtitle":"Malolos, Bulacan"},"photo":{"file":"Pook ng Gobierno Militar de la Plaza historical marker.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":2832,"height":3963,"hash":"5b"}}},"address":"Pariancillo Street, Brgy. Sto. Niño, Malolos, Bulacan","macroAddress":"Malolos, Bulacan","date":"2008","lat":14.84308},"Q55216957":{"date":"2005-06-30","macroAddress":"Baler, Aurora","lat":15.73952,"name":"Dikaloyungan","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Dikaloyungan historical marker.jpg","width":2448,"height":3264,"hash":"a7"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito noong 3 Setyembre 1897 nagpunit ng sedula ang mga Katipunerong kinabibilangan nina Teodorico Luna Novicio, Antero Amatorio, Norberto Valenzuela, Isabelo Palispis at iba pa at lumagda sa isang manipestong nagpapahayag ng kanilang pagsalungat sa kapangyarihan ng España. Sa pangyayaring ito nagsimula ang Himagsikang Filipino sa Distrito ng Principe (Aurora ngayon). Nagsilbi rin itong himpilan ng Kilusang Rebolusyonaryo sa Baler.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Dikaloyungan"}}},"address":"Brgy. Zabali, Baler, Aurora","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.57108,"wikipedia":{"Philippine Revolution":true},"locDesc":null},"Q52025927":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.07639,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"Pasig, Metro Manila","lat":14.5602,"name":"Colegio del Buen Consejo","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Colegio del Buen Consejo, A. Luna Street cor. R. Jabson Street, Pasig, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"cc","height":847,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Colegio del Buen Consejo.jpg","width":661},"text":{"title":"Colegio del Buen Consejo","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa pook na dating Beaterio de Santa Rita de Pasig sa pamumuno ni Madre Superyor Consuelo Barcelo, O.S.A. at ipinamahala sa mga Filipinong madre sa pangunguna ni Sor Teresa de Jesus Andrada, O.S.A., 10 Marso 1909. Pinasinayaan sa patronato ni Nuestra Señora del Buen Consejo, 26 Abril 1909. Naging kanlungan ng mga mamamayan noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig; nasira noong Labanan sa Maynila, 1945. Muling ipinaayos, 1948.</p>"}}}},"Q41105872":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.71546,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"macroAddress":"Piddig, Ilocos Norte","date":"1958","lat":18.16616,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":3120,"file":"Claro Caluya historical marker 2.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"d5","height":4160},"text":{"title":"Claro Caluya","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Foremost vernacular poet and dramatist in Ilocos Norte. Born 22 June 1868. Son of Rafael Caluya and Norberta Pasion. Studied n his hometown; later went to a higher school in Laoag 1882; became Cabeza de Barangay, 1890 and Capitan Municipal, 1893-1896; Joined the Revolutionary Forces, 1896-1897; distinguished himself in the Filipino-American war; served as Municipal President of his town, 1903-1905. Under his administration, the first public market was built and several primary schools were opened. Founded civic and cultural organizations. Wrote many plays and poems in Ilocano, including a translation of Rizal's Ultimo Adios, which is considered as the most lyrical Ilocano version of the poem. Married to Sabina Aquino. Died 14 December 1914.</p>"}}},"address":"Don Claro Caluya Green Garden, Estella Street, Piddig, Ilocos Norte","name":"Claro Caluya","region":"Ilocos Region"},"Q47092288":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dalubhasa sa batas, estadista, makabayan, martir. Ipinanganak sa San Fernando, Pampanga, 19 Pebrero 1886. Itinalaga bilang kinatawan ng Pangulo ng Komonwelt ng Pilipinas noong mga unang araw ng pananakop ng mga Hapon. Binaril sa Malabang, Lanao, 2 Mayo 1942, dahil sa pagtangging manumpa ng katapatan sa Imperyong Hapon.</p>","title":"Jose Abad Santos","subtitle":"(1886–1942)"},"photo":{"height":3456,"hash":"a8","file":"08685jfProvincial Capitol Boulevard San Fernando City Pampangafvf 01.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":4608}}},"address":"Governor Macario Arnedo Park, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Jose Abad Santos","lat":15.02476,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of a statue of José Abad Santos.","wikipedia":{"José Abad Santos":true},"lon":120.68763,"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"2c","width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"08685jfProvincial Capitol Boulevard San Fernando City Pampangafvf 08.jpg"}},"Q52778432":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the facade to the right of the main door of the church.","wikipedia":{"Knox United Methodist Church":true},"lon":120.98226,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"KUMCManilajf7761 30.JPG","height":3456,"hash":"44"},"address":"Knox United Methodist Church, 960 Rizal Avenue cor. Lope de Vega Street, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Nagkakaisang Metodistang Simbahang Knox (Knox United Methodist Church) (Itinatag 1899).jpg","width":720,"hash":"fd","height":960},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito nagsimula ang unang pamayanan ng Protestanteng simbahang ebanghelikal sa Pilipinas, nang isang misyonerong Amerikano ng Simbahang Metodista, si Obispo James W. Thoburn, ay bumigkas ng unang sermong ebanghelikal sa bansa, noong Marso 5, 1899. Bago matapos ang taon si Nicolas Zamora ay inordenang unang ministrong Protestante na Pilipino at naglingkod sa “Unang Simbahang Metodista” dito sa Pilipinas. Isang pansamantalang kapilya ang ipinatayo dito hanggang sa isang permanenteng gusali ang ipinagawa noong 1906 sa pamamagitan ng donasyon ng isang kilalang manggagawa ng sumbrero sa Lungsod ng Nuweba York. At bilang alaala sa kanya, ang simbahan ay tinagurian sa kanyang pangalan. Ito ay muling ipinaayos nang naaayon sa makabagong arkitektura noong 1952.</p>","subtitle":"(Knox United Methodist Church)<br>(Itinatag 1899)","title":"Nagkakaisang Metodistang Simbahang Knox"}}},"name":"Nagkakaisang Metodistang Simbahang Knox","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","date":"1979-10-28","lat":14.60625},"Q54943720":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.90915,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"19","height":4608,"file":"Porta Vaga Church historical marker in Cavite City.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating kapilya na yari sa kahoy na itinayo para sa Nuestra Señora de la Soledad de Porta Vaga noong mga taong 1667. Opisyal na iniluklok, Abril 12, 1692. Pagkaraan ng maraming taong pagkukumpuni at muling pagsasaayos, isang simbahan na yari sa bato ang itinayo noong 1787. Muling ipinaayos 1848. Iginuho ng lindol 1863. Muling ipinagawa noong taong din yaon. Muling kinumpuni, 1880. Pinaganda ni P. Pedro Lerena, 1932. Ganap na nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig kung kaya’t ang itinatanging imahen ng Virgen de la Soledad de Porta Vaga, ang patrona ng mga galyon at pinakamatandang naitalang pinta ng Birhen Maria sa Pilipinas ay inilipat sa Simbahan ng San Roque, Cavite, 1945.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ermita de Porta Vaga"}}},"address":"Samonte Park, Plaza Soledad Street, San Roque, Cavite City, Cavite","name":"Ermita de Porta Vaga","region":"Calabarzon","date":"1991-11-17","macroAddress":"Cavite City, Cavite","lat":14.48228},"Q55233733":{"wikipedia":{"First Philippine Republic":true,"Revolutionary Government of the Philippines":"Revolutionary Government of the Philippines (1898–1899)"},"locDesc":"The historical markers are located on the western end of the facade of the convent, beside the cathedral facade.","lon":120.81155,"locPhoto":{"hash":"ac","height":4608,"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"J1887cMalolosCathedralfvfjr 17.JPG"},"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Philippine Republic","details":{"es":{"text":{"title":"Republica Filipina","subtitle":"1898–1901","inscription":"<p>En este convento se estableció la Presidencia de la Republica Filipina cuyo Presidente fué Don Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy y lo ocupó desde el 10 de Septiembre de 1898 hasta el 29 de Marzo de 1899.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"8b","height":4608,"width":3456,"file":"MalolosCathedraljf0606 02.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}},"tl":{"photo":{"file":"MalolosCathedraljf0606 03.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608,"hash":"c8","height":3456},"text":{"title":"Republika Pilipina","subtitle":"1898–1901","inscription":"<p>Sa kumbentong ito itinatag ang Presidensiya ng Unang Republika Pilipina na pinanguluhan ng Kgg. Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy at dito’y nanatili mula noong ika-10 ng Setyembre 1898 hanggang ika-29 ng Marso 1899.</p>"}},"en":{"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"2b","width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Bulacanjf0591 03.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":"1898–1901","title":"Philippine Republic","inscription":"<p>In this convent, General Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy as President of the First Philippine Republic held office from 10 September 1898 to 29 March 1899.</p>"}}},"address":"Malolos Cathedral, Pariancillo Street cor. Estrella Street, Malolos, Bulacan","lat":14.84283,"macroAddress":"Malolos, Bulacan","date":"1956"},"Q50562657":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"St. Paul Sisters of Chartes":"St. Paul Sisters of Chartres"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.30982,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dumating ang mga unang kawani ng Saint Paul of Chartres sa paanyaya ni Monsignor Frederic Z. Rooker, Obispo ng Jaro, Iloilo upang tumulong sa edukasyon ng mga kabataan ng pulo ng Negros, 1904. Dumaong ang mga unang madre ng SPC sa Dumaguete, 29 Octubre 1904. Silay ay sina Mo. Marthe de St. Paul Legendre, Sr. Marie Louise du Sacre Coeur Nivou, Sr. Anna de la Croix Anne, Sr. Ange Marie Bannier (Pranses); Sr. Marie Josephine Rappeport (Amerikano); Sr. Catherine de Genes Gutteres (Portugues) at Sr. Charles Aho (Tsino). Si Maria Echavez (Sr. Ambroisine) ang unang Pilipinang kawani, 1904. Nagbukas ang Instituto de San Pablo (St. Paul Academy), 9 Enero 1905. Si Mo. Marie Madeleine Denoga ang unang Pilipinang superyora ng kongregasyon, 1965. Tinatag at pinamahalaan ng Kongregasyong Sisters of St. Paul of Chartres ang mahigit na 60 paaralan, pagamutan, at iba pang mapagkawang gawang institusyon sa Pilipinas.</p>","title":"Sisters of St. Paul of Chartres","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Rizal Avenue, Dumaguete, Negros Oriental","name":"Sisters of St. Paul of Chartres","region":"Central Visayas","macroAddress":"Dumaguete, Negros Oriental","date":"2004-10-28","lat":9.30802},"Q28927264":{"region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","name":"José Rizal at Dapitan Church","address":"Dapitan Church, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","details":{"photo":{"width":1177,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Saint James Church historical marker.jpg","height":1600,"hash":"27"},"text":{"en":{"title":null,"subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this spot of Saint James Church constructed by the Jesuits in 1871, Jose Rizal stood while hearing mass every Sunday during his exile in Dapitan in 1892–1896.</p>"},"tl":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ng Simbahan ng San Jaime na ipinagawa ng mga Heswita noong 1871, tumayo si Jose Rizal tuwing Linngo upang makinig ng misa sa buong panahon ng kanyang pagkapatapon sa Dapitan, 1892–1896.</p>","title":null,"subtitle":null}}},"lat":8.6546,"macroAddress":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","date":"1989","wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.42497},"Q56051780":{"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"f3","width":3456,"file":"742Adamson University Museum Manila 12.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"lon":120.98555,"wikipedia":{"Adamson University":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal at the base of the left column of the portico of St.Vincent Building.","lat":14.5858,"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"2007-02-08","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Adamson University","address":"Adamson University, 900 San Marcelino Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Adamson University","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ni George Lucas Adamson bilang Adamson School of Industrial Chemistry sa Santa Cruz, Maynila, 1932. Inilipat sa San Miguel, Maynila, 1933. Naging Adamson School of Industrial Chemistry and Engineering, 1936. Tanging bumuo ng ROTC Chemical Warfare Service Unit sa bansa, 1936. Inilipat sa Intramuros, 1939. Naging Adamson University, 1941. Ginamit ng puwersang Hapon, 1942. Sinunog noong Labanan sa Maynila, 1945. Muling binuksan sa dating Congregation of the Mission Central House sa Daang San Marcelino, Ermita, Maynila, 1946. Naging pag-aari ng Congregation of the Mission, 1964. Pinalawak ang kampus nang mabili ang Gusaling Meralco, 1968, ang lupa ng Tabacalera, 1974, at ang St. Theresa’s College, 1977.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"b0","height":537,"width":395,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Adamson university marker.jpg"}}}},"Q24733593":{"locPhoto":{"width":3696,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Taal, Batangas (50).jpg","height":2448,"hash":"4b"},"lon":120.92436,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located immediately to the left of the main door of the basilica.","wikipedia":{"Taal Basilica":true},"lat":13.88042,"date":"1986-12-08","macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang itinayo ni Padre Diego Espina noong 1575 sa ngayon ay San Nicolas na dating bahagi ng Balangon. Nagiba noong 1754 nang pumutok ang bulkan. Ipinagawa sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan noong 1755 at iginuho ng lindol. Noong 1849, kinikilalang pinakamalaking simbahang Katoliko sa dakong silangan, ang kasalukuyang simbahan ay sinimulan noong 1756 ayon sa ibinalangkas ni Luciano Oliver, isang arkitektong. Pinasinayaan ito nooong 1865.</p>","title":"Ang Basilika ng Taal","subtitle":"(1575)"},"photo":{"width":1274,"file":"Ang Basilika ng Taal historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","height":1598,"hash":"9c"}}},"address":"Taal Basilica, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ang Basilika ng Taal"},"Q46574680":{"lat":10.91353,"macroAddress":"Patnongon, Antique","date":"2008-02-25","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Ang Lumang Simbahan at Kumbento ng Patnongon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Lumang Simbahan at Kumbento ng Patnongon","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni P. Manuel Asensio, OSA sa patronato ni San Agustin, 1860 at natapos sa pangangasiwa ni P. Eustaquio Heria, 1895. Idinisenyo ni P. Joaquin Fernandez ang patio, 1896. Inilipat ang pamamahala ng parokya sa Mill Hill Fathers ng Inglatera, 1906. Isinaayos dulot ng pinsala noong Himagsikang Filipino, 1896 – 1899. At noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1941 – 1945. Inilagak sa gusali ng kumbento ang Akademya ng San Agustin, 1962.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Patnongon, Antique","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.99369,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q56065992":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.43477,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Dumanjug","subtitle":null,"inscription":""}}},"address":"Dumanjug Church, Fr. H. Villa Street, Dumanjug, Cebu","name":"Simbahan ng Dumanjug","region":"Central Visayas","macroAddress":"Dumanjug, Cebu","date":null,"lat":10.05766},"Q24831810":{"lat":13.94006,"macroAddress":"Lipa, Batangas","date":"1984-05-03","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa lungsod ng Lipa, Batangas, noong Mayo 3, 1878. Nagtapos ng A.B., Colegio de San Juan de Letran, 1895 at B.S. Phar. Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas, 1902. Patnugot ng La Vanguardia at El Renacimiento. Nagbunyag ng mga katiwalian ng pamahalaang Amerikano sa kanyang editorial na “Aves de Rapina”, na pumukaw sa pambansang kamalayan. Kinatawan, Asambleya ng Pilipinas, 1912, at unang Pilipinong direktor , Kawanihan ng Pangangalakal at Industriya, 1918–1929. Nagkaloob ng lote sa lungsod ng Lipa para sa kaunaunahang SOS Children's Village sa Pilipinas. Namatay Setyembre 10, 1967.</p>","title":"Fidel A. Reyes","subtitle":"(1878–1967)"},"photo":{"file":"Fidel Reyes Monument, Lipa City.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1944,"height":2592,"hash":"1f"}}},"address":"Lipa, Batangas","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Fidel A. Reyes","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.16278,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q56035702":{"macroAddress":"Bacoor, Cavite","date":"1972-08-05","lat":14.45964,"address":"Bacoor Church, Gen. Evangelista Street cor. F.L. Pagtakhan Street, Bacoor, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3558,"hash":"b9","file":"Padre Mariano Gomez historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2750},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Naging kura paroko ng bayang ito sa loob ng 48 taon. Isinilang sa Sta. Cruz, Maynila noong Agosto 2, 1799. Nagtanggol sa karapatan ng mga paring Pilipino. Isinangkot sa pag-aalsa sa Kabite noong Enero 20, 1872 at ipinapatay noong Pebrero 17, 1872 na kasama nina Padre Jose Burgos at Jacinto Zamora.</p>","title":"Padre Mariano Gomez","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Padre Mariano Gomez","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"72","width":4608,"file":"4296Bacoor West City Cavite Landmarks Roads 30.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"lon":120.93975,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the entrance to the parish office building.","wikipedia":{"Mariano Gómez":true}},"Q44755886":{"locPhoto":{"height":3240,"hash":"7a","file":"Calle Real, Iloilo City 2.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4320},"lon":122.57048,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a pedestal in front of the Eusebio Villanueva Building.","wikipedia":null,"date":"2014-08-08","macroAddress":"Iloilo City","lat":10.69461,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sentro ng komersyo sa Iloilo na nagbigay daan sa pagbubukas ng daungang nagpaunlad ng pandaigdigang kalakalan at industriya ng asukal noong ika-19 dantaon. Napanatili ang arkitektura ng mga gusaling itinayo noong ika-20 dantaon. Ipinahayag na Pook Pamana ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas sa bisa ng Kapasyahan ng Lupon Bilang 3, 16 Hunyo 2014.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Distritong Pangkomersyo ng Lungsod ng Iloilo bilang Pook Pamana"},"photo":{"height":2654,"hash":"4b","credit":"Photo: Ryomaandres; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Distritong Pangkomersyo ng Lungsod ng Iloilo bilang Pook Pamana historical marker.jpg","width":1844}}},"address":"Iloilo City Central Business District, J. M. Basa Street cor. Aldeguer Street, City Proper, Iloilo City","name":"Distritong Pangkomersyo ng Lungsod ng Iloilo bilang Pook Pamana","region":"Western Visayas"},"Q37625398":{"lon":120.97441,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"09500jfElpidio Quirino Monument Grandstand Rizal Parkfvf 02.jpg","height":3456,"hash":"f3"},"wikipedia":{"Elpidio Quirino":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of a bust of Elpidio Quirino near the southern end of the Quirino Grandstand.","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"1990","lat":14.57955,"name":"Elpidio R. Quirino","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Quirino Grandstand, Parade Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Elpidio Quirino (Quirino Grandstand) historical marker.JPG","credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","width":2008,"hash":"0d","height":2997},"text":{"subtitle":"(1890–1956)","title":"Elpidio R. Quirino","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Vigan, Ilocos Sur, Nobyembre 16, 1890. Nagtapos ng elementarya sa Aringay, La Union at sekondarya sa Manila High School, 1911. Nagkamit ng Titulo sa Batas, Pamantasan ng Pilipinas, 1915. Nagsimulang maglingkod sa bayan bilang guro sa Caparian, Agoo, La Union sa gulang na 16. Nahirang na pribadong kalihim ng Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon, Kalihim ng Pananalapi sa ilalim ng panunungkulan ng Gobernador Heneral Frank Murphy at Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Interyor. Nahalal na kinatawan ng Ilocos Sur, 1919; senador 1922, 1931, 1941; delegado sa Kumbensiyong Konstitusyonal, 1934; at pangalawang pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas, 1946. Naging pangulo sa pagkamatay ni Pangulong Manuel A. Roxas, 1948; nahalal na pangulo, 1949. Namatay, Pebrero 29, 1956. Ang kanyang panunungkula’y kinatampukan ng muling pagpapayabong sa ekonomiya ng bansa na sinira ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at pagpapanumbalik ng kapayapa’t muling pananalig ng mamamayan sa pamahalaan.</p>"}}}},"Q50385359":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The First Philippine Assembly was inaugurated here on October 16, 1907, by United States Secretary of War William Howard Taft in the presence of thousands of people, including Governor General James F. Smith, members of the Philippine Commission, Justices of the Supreme Court, representatives of foreign governments, officers of the United States Army and Navy, ecclesiastical dignitaries, and ranking officials of the insular, provincial, and municipal governments. Of the 80 duly elected delegates, 79 were present. The first Filipino bishop of Nueva Caceres, the Right Reverend Jorge Barlin, pronounced the invocation.</p>","title":"Inauguration of the First Philippine Assembly","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"9f","height":2726,"width":2500,"file":"Inauguration of the First Philippine Assembly historical marker (corrected).jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"address":"Manila Grand Opera Hotel & Casino, 925 Doroteo Jose Street cor. Rizal Avenue, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Inauguration of the First Philippine Assembly","lat":14.60531,"date":"1940","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a marble mounting to the right of the main hotel entrance.","wikipedia":{"1st Philippine Legislature":true,"Philippine Assembly":true},"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"74","file":"ManilaOperaHousejf7591 28.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608},"lon":120.98166},"Q28937921":{"lat":6.498,"date":"2013","macroAddress":"Koronadal, South Cotabato","region":"Soccsksargen","name":"Pook na Pinaglibingan ng Labimpitong Pilipinong Martir sa Koronadal","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Pook na Pinaglibingan ng Labimpitong Pilipinong Martir sa Koronadal","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sinalakay ng mga sundalo ng USAFFE, 24 Nobyembre 1942, na pinamumunuan ni Lt. Alfredo Garingo, ang mga Hapong nakahimpil sa kamalig ng National Land Settlement Administration. Nasawi ang isa sa mga sundalong Hapon at bilang paghihiganti, pinaslang ng mga Hapon ang mga Pilipino. Dito sila inilibing, 1942.</p>"}}},"address":"Koronadal Central Elementary School I, Rizal Street, Koronadal, South Cotabato","locPhoto":{"width":640,"credit":"City Government of Cotabato","file":"Seventeen Martyrs of Koronadal historical marker.jpg","hash":"aa","height":960},"lon":124.8409,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the front of the memorial obelisk."},"Q52878121":{"lon":116.28982,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Paduka Pahala":true},"macroAddress":"Dezhou, Shandong, China","date":null,"lat":37.47069,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>The Eastern King of Sulu, known in Chinese records as Pa-tu-ko Pa-ta-la or Pa-tu Ko Pa-ha-la. Travelled to China in 1417 during the reign of Emperor Yongle with an entourage of more than 340 persons, and presented to the emperor a tribute consisting of a letter in golden script, pearls and other precious gifts. Acknowledging the king as a true ruler, Emperor Yongle gave him official seals, commissions, and other imperial gifts as a sign of great respect and admiration. Enroute to his homeland after 27 days in China, the Sulu chief fell ill and died in Dezhou, Shandong Province. Buried in Dezhou, two of his sons stayed behind to honor and guard their father’s tomb. Their descendants, with the surnames An and Wen, continue to live today in Dezhou. </p><p> In honor of the strong bond of friendship and goodwill forged together by the early rulers of Sulu and China this historical marker is dedicated by the National Historical Institute of the Philippines and the Katipunang Gatrizal in cooperation with the Sultanate of Sulu.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Paduka Batara"}}},"address":"Su Lu Wang Mu, Lingnan Road, Decheng District, Dezhou, Shandong, People's Republic of China","name":"Paduka Batara","region":"Overseas"},"Q53354770":{"locDesc":"The historical markers in English and Filipino are both located below the left niche on the church facade.","wikipedia":{"Tumauini Church":true},"lon":121.80712,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Cabajar {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Tumauini Church.jpg","width":4320,"hash":"dd","height":3240},"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayong yari sa kahoy ni Padre Francisco Nuñez, O.P., at inialay sa patronato ni San Matias, 1702. Nahiwalay sa Cabagan at naging isang ganap na bayan, 1751. Ang simbahang bato na may pabilog na kampanaryo, ang kaisa-isang uri nito sa Pilipinas ay ipinatayo ni Padre Domingo Forto, 1783 at ganap na natapos 1805. Naging kabisera ng Isabela sa loob na maikling panahon, 1880’s. Bahagyang nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at ipinaayos ng mga tapat na mananampalataya ng Tumauini. </p><p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973, na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan Bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974, at Bilang 1505, Hunyo 11, 1978. Ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 24 Pebrero 1989.</p>","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Tumauini","subtitle":null},"photo":null},"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>First built of light materials by Fray Francisco Nuñez, O.P. and dedicated to the patron saint San Matias, 1707. Separated from Cabagan and became a regular parish, 1751. The church of stone with a unique cylindrical bell tower, the only of its kind in the Philippines was constructed by Father Domingo Forto, 1783 and completed, 1805. Became the capital of Isabela for sometime in 1880’s. Partly damaged during World War II and repaired into its original form by the faithful of Tumauini. </p><p> By virtue of Presidential Decree No. 260, 1 August 1973, as amended by Executive Order Nos. 375, 14 January 1974, and No. 1505, 11 June 1976. This church was declared a National Historical Landmark, 24 February 1989.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Tumauini"},"photo":{"width":2248,"credit":"Cabajar {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Tumauini Church Marker (cropped).jpg","hash":"d9","height":3344}}},"address":"Tumauini Church, Tumauini, Isabela","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Church of Tumauini","lat":17.27501,"date":"1989-02-24","macroAddress":"Tumauini, Isabela"},"Q37776237":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Elpidio Quirino":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98507,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Vigan, Ilocos Sur, Nobyembre 16, 1890. Nagtapos ng elementarya sa Aringay, La Union at sekondarya sa Manila High School, 1911. Nagkamit ng Titulo sa Batas, Pamantasan ng Pilipinas, 1915. Nagsimulang maglingkod sa bayan bilang guro sa Caparian, Agoo, La Union sa gulang na 16. Nahirang na pribadong kalihim ng Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon, Kalihim ng Pananalapi sa ilalim ng panunungkulan ng Gobernador Heneral Frank Murphy at Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Interyor. Nahalal na kinatawan ng Ilocos Sur, 1919; senador 1922, 1931, 1941; delegado sa Kumbensiyong Konstitusyonal, 1934; at pangalawang pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas, 1946. Naging pangulo sa pagkamatay ni Pangulong Manuel A. Roxas, 1948; nahalal na pangulo, 1949. Namatay, Pebrero 29, 1956. Ang kanyang panunungkula’y kinatampukan ng muling pagpapayabong sa ekonomiya ng bansa na sinira ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at pagpapanumbalik ng kapayapaan at muling pananalig ng mamamayan sa pamahalaan.</p>","title":"Elpidio R. Quirino","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. President Quirino Avenue, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Elpidio R. Quirino","lat":14.56459,"macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","date":"1994-03-01"},"Q46570505":{"wikipedia":{"Ananias Diokno":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.42786,"name":"Pagdakip kay Heneral Ananias Diokno","region":"Western Visayas","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito sa Altavas sa Aklan (dati’y Jimeno at noo’y bahagi ng Capiz) dinakip si Ananias Diokno ng mga Amerikano, 1901. Kilala sa taguring “Heneral Pandagat,” namuno sa hukbong ekspedisyon ng Panay, Agosto 1898; matagumpay na nakipaglaban sa mga Espanyol sa pulo ng Panay. Itinalagang gobernador politiko-militar ng Capiz at lumahok sa pakikipaglaban ng mga gerilya sa Digmaang Pilipino–Amerikano, 1899.</p>","title":"Pagdakip kay Heneral Ananias Diokno","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Brgy. Dalipdip, Altavas, Aklan","date":"2013-08-30","macroAddress":"Altavas, Aklan","lat":11.52824},"Q24702677":{"address":"Mauban, Quezon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2520,"credit":"Photo: Lawrence Ruiz (Epi Fabonan III); perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Manuel S. Enverga historical marker (cropped).jpg","hash":"af","height":3745},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Makabayan at lingkod-bayan. Isinilang sa Mauban, Quezon, 1 Enero 1909. Nagtapos ng Abogasya sa Philippine Law School, 1938. Master of Laws sa Universidad ng Sto. Tomas, 1948. Ginawaran ng Doctor of Laws ng Universidad Central de Madrid, 1950. Nagtatag ng Luzonian Colleges, ngayo’y Manuel S. Enverga University Foundation, 11 Pebrero 1947. Nahalal na kinatawan ng unang distrito ng Quezon, 1953–1969. Nagpanukala ng pagtatatag ng Philippine Coconut administration, 1954. Naging tagapangulo ng House Committee on Education, 1958–1961, House Committee on Foreign Affairs, 1961–1969. Napiling Outstanding Congressman ng mga pahayagan sa Pilipinas bilang pangunahing tagapagmungkahi ng panukalang-batas para sa pagbubukas ng kalakalan sa pagitan ng Pilipinas at ng mga bansang komunista, 1966. Yumao, 14 Hunyo 1981.</p>","title":"Manuel S. Enverga","subtitle":"(1909–1981)"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Manuel S. Enverga","lat":14.18808,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"Mauban, Quezon","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the statue of Manuel Enverga.","wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":{"width":3456,"file":"Enverga Statue.jpg","credit":"Lawrence Ruiz (Epi Fabonan III) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":4608,"hash":"02"},"lon":121.73264},"Q54401768":{"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Simbahan ng Obando","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Obando Church historical marker.jpg","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"50"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Obando","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng mga paring Pransiskano sa pangunguna ni Reb. P. Manuel de Olivencia, unang kura ng Obando, noong 29 Abril 1754. Ipinagawa ang pangalawang simbahang bato na may magandang krusero ng mga naninirahan buhat sa buwis na nasingil sa loob ng dalawang taon. Iginuho ng malakas na panganganyon noong Liberasyon ng 1945. Muling ipinagawa ang simbahan at kumbento ng mga taga parokya sa pangunguna ni Reb. P. Marcos C. Punzal sa loob ng dalawang taon. Pinag-ibayo ang pagsasaayos sa pangangasiwa ni D. Reb. Mons. Rome R. Fernandez, H.P. Ipinagdiriwang ang kapistahan ng bayan tuwing ika-17, 18, at 19 ng Mayo bilang parangal kina San Pascual de Bailon, kabilang ang pagsasayaw upang magkaanak; Santa Clara, patrona ng mga naglilihing ina; at Nuestra Señora Virgen de Salambao, patrona ng mga mangingisda at magbubukid.</p>"}}},"address":"Obando Church, Obando, Bulacan","lat":14.71039,"macroAddress":"Obando, Bulacan","date":"1984","wikipedia":{"Obando Church":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.93676,"locPhoto":null},"Q54370455":{"lat":10.69426,"macroAddress":"Iloilo City","date":"1981","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Nicholas Loney","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2550,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Nicolas Loney historical marker.JPG","height":3188,"hash":"cb"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Plymouth, Devonshire, Inglaterra noong 1826, siya ay nagtungo sa Maynila bilang mangangalakal noong 1851. Itinalaga siya bilang unang Bise-Konsul na Ingles sa Iloilo noong 1856 pagkaraang ipahayag na ito’y isang pandaigdig na daungan. Malaki ang naitulong niya sa pagpapaunlad ng Panay at Negros, lalo na sa industriya ng asukal, sa pamamagitan ng paggamit ng mga makabagong iluhan ng tubo at pagbibigay ng tulong na pananalapi sa mga magtatanim ng tubo. Ang kanyang bahay-kalakal, ang Loney and Company ang kaunaunahagang kompanya ng dayuhan sa Iloilo. Pinagbuti niya ang mga kaluwagang pandaungan at nagsagawa ng unang tuwirang eksportasyon ng asukal buhat sa Iloilo noong 1859. Lubhang nawiwili sa pagpapaunlad ng pangangalakal at industriya. Sinimulan niya ang ilang pagbabago buhat sa pamahalaang Kastila. Siya ay namatay noong Abril 22, 1869 at inilibing sa Iloilo.</p>","subtitle":"(1826–1869)","title":"Nicholas Loney"}}},"address":"Muelle Loney Street cor. Ortiz Street, City Proper, Iloilo City","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.57356,"wikipedia":{"Nicholas Loney":true},"locDesc":null},"Q54943626":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Makata ng Ilokandia, lider at manggagawang panlipunan, ipinanganak Hunyo 15, 1882 sa Dingras, Ilokos Norte. Kalihim, Dingras Women’s Club, 1918; Tagasiyasat, Rural Credit Association ng Northern Luzon, 1919; Kinatawan, Infant Mortality Conference sa Maynila, 1920. Pangalawang Pangulo, Ilokos Norte Women’s Club, 1922; Tagapagtatag, puericulture centers ng Northern Luzon at Pangulo, Provincial Women’s Club of Ilokos Norte, 1923–1938; Nagharap sa Pambansang Kumbensiyon ng Women’s Club ng panukulang magkaroon ng Araw ng mga Ina at kasamang nagtaguyod sa Lehislatura ng karapatan ng kababaihan sa pagboto. Namatay noong Abril 29, 1940.</p>","title":"Enriqueta de Peralta","subtitle":"(1882–1940)"}}},"address":"Doña Josefa Llanes Escoda National Highway cor. Peralta Street, Brgy. Albano, Dingras, Ilocos Norte","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Enriqueta de Peralta","lat":18.10114,"date":null,"macroAddress":"Dingras, Ilocos Norte","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.69998},"Q23974922":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Manila Metropolitan Theater","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2648,"file":"MMManilajf2189 02.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":3817,"hash":"53"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nagsimula bilang isang Pambansang Tanghalan ayon sa disenyo ni Arkitekto Juan Arellano. Pinasinayaan noong 1931. Naging tanghalan ng mga artistang Pilipino at banyaga. Nagpalabas ng mga opera, pageant, at dulang Kastila at Ingles na isinalin sa Tagalog para sa mga Filipino noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Nasira nang bahagya noong 1945. Ang gumuhong gusali ay naging tirahan ng mga squatter at pinangalanang Besa Boxing Arena. Ibinalik sa dating maringal na anyo noong 1978 ng Komisyon ng Kalakhang Maynila.</p>","title":"Manila Metropolitan Theater","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Manila Metropolitan Theater, Padre Burgos Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59422,"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"1988","wikipedia":{"Manila Metropolitan Theater":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98032},"Q28912690":{"region":"Eastern Visayas","name":"Bantayan ng Biliran","address":"Biliran Watchtower, Leyte–Biliran Road, Biliran","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Bantayan ng Biliran","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo sa burol na ito ni Padre Gaspar Ignacio de Guevara kasama ang simbahan at kuta ng nagsilbing santuaryo ng mga mananampalataya, 1765 - 1774. Tanging natira nang sunugin ng mga piratang moro ang pook, 1774. Ginamit sa pagpapalaganap ng relihiyong komyunal sa Biliran, Leyte at Samar. Halimbawa ng arkitektura na yari sa korales at bato noong panahon ng mga Espanyol. Ipinaayos, 2000.</p>"},"photo":{"height":1600,"hash":"82","width":1345,"file":"Biliran Watchtower historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"lat":11.46394,"macroAddress":"Biliran, Biliran","date":"2008","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.47981},"Q23886432":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.41738,"wikipedia":{"Nagcarlan Church":"San Bartolome Apostol Parish Church (Nagcarlan)"},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Nagcarlan, Laguna","date":"1938","lat":14.13656,"name":"Church of Nagcarlang","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"NagcarlanChurchjf4012 01.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608,"hash":"d2","height":3456},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The first church, which was of light materials, was built by Rev. Tomas de Miranda, O.F.M., who was assigned to this town in 1583 as resident priest. The second church, of brick and stone, was built in 1752, but was partly destroyed by fire in 1781. A choirloft was added to the reconstructed church in 1845 by Rev. Vicente Velloc, who built the Nagcarlang Cemetery and its underground crypt. Rev. Tomas de Miranda was pioneer in the successful cultivation of wheat in the uplands of Nagcarlang.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Nagcarlang"}}},"address":"Nagcarlan Church, Nagcarlan, Laguna"},"Q46790914":{"address":"Casa Gorordo, Lopez Jaena Street cor. Ballesteros Street, Cebu City","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Casa Gorordo","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The house was built in the mid-19th century by Alejandro Reynes y Rosales and bought by Juan Isidro de Gorordo, a Spanish merchant, in 1863. Four generations of the Gorordo Family lived in this house, including Juan Gorordo, first Filipino Bishop of Cebu 1910–1932. Acquired in 1980 by the Ramon Aboitiz Foundation, Inc. It was restored and later opened as a public museum. Casa Gorordo has been declared a National Historical Landmark by virtue of National Historical Institute Board Resolution No. 4 dated September 24, 1991.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Casa Gorordo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2448,"hash":"0c","height":3264}}},"name":"Casa Gorordo","region":"Central Visayas","date":"1998-08-21","macroAddress":"Cebu City","lat":10.29997,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.90488},"Q47092331":{"name":"Diosdado Macapagal","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ika-9 na Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas, 1961–1965. Isinilang sa San Nicolas, Lubao, Pilipinas, 28 Setyembre 1910. Nagtapos ng Associate in Arts sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas, 1932, abogasya (1936), Master of Laws (1941), Doctor of Civil Law (1947); at Doctor of Economics (1957) sa Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas. Unang pangulo ng Philippine Lawyers Association, 1947. Kinatawan ng unang distrito ng Pampanga sa Pangalawa at Pangatlong Kongreso ng Pilipinas, 1949–1957; may akda ng Foreign Service Act ng 1952. Pangalawang Pangulo ng Pilipinas, 1957–1961; Pangulo ng Liberal Party, 1958–1961; 1964–1966. Itinakda ang pagdiriwang ng Araw ng Kalayaan ng Pilipinas tuwing ika-12 ng Hunyo, 1964. Nagpasimula ng pagtatatag ng MAPHILINDO upang palakasin ang ugnayan ng Malaysia, Philippines at Indonesia, 1963; nilagdaan ang Agricultural Land Reform Code, 1963. Pangulo ng 1971 Constitutional Convention. Ama ni Gloria Macapagal Arroyo, ika-14 na Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas (2004–2010). Yumao, 21 Abril 1997.</p>","title":"Diosdado Macapagal","subtitle":"(1910–1997)"},"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Diosdado Macapagal historical marker (Pampanga Provincial Capitol).jpg","width":4608,"hash":"74","height":3456}}},"address":"Pampanga Provincial Capitol, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","date":"2009","lat":15.02408,"wikipedia":{"Diosdado Macapagal":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is installed upright in front of the bust of Macapagal which is located to the left of the main entrance of the capitol building.","locPhoto":{"hash":"51","height":4608,"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"08586jfProvincial Capitol Boulevard San Fernando City Pampangafvf 35.jpg"},"lon":120.68735},"Q54996691":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Bosoboso Church":true},"lon":121.23829,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo ang unang simbahan nang maorganisa ng mga paring Pransiskano ang mga Dumagat ng Lanatin at Linotan sa kabundukan ng Tanay, lalawigan ng Tondo, ngayo’y Rizal, 1669. Tinawag na Misyon ng San Andres de Lanatin ng mga paring Pransiskano, 1670. Tinawag na Bosoboso nang ituloy ng mga paring Heswita ang misyon, kasabay ng pagiging bayan nito, 1741. Isinalin sa mga paring sekular, 1768. Nawasak ng lindol, 1880. Inabandona dahil pinalipat ang mga taga-rito sa Bagong Bosoboso sa ilalim ng Antipolo, Rizal, matapos isama sa Marikina Watershed Reservation, 1911. Naging himpilan ng Hunters ROTC Guerrilla ang mga guho nito, 1942. Muling isinaayos ng mga mananampalataya at ng mga paring Kamilyano, 1995. Itinalagang patron ang Nuestra Señora de la Anunciata at muling naging parokya ng Diyosesis ng Antipolo sa pangangasiwa ng mga paring Kamilyano, 2004.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Lumang Bosoboso","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Bosoboso Church, Boso-Boso Road, Sitio Old Boso-Boso, Brgy. San Jose, Antipolo, Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng Lumang Bosoboso","lat":14.63955,"macroAddress":"Antipolo, Rizal","date":"2018-06-14"},"Q24817337":{"lat":13.88022,"date":"1985-12-08","macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":2154,"hash":"a3","width":1650,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Gliceria Marella de Villavicencio historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1852–1929)","title":"Gliceria Marella de Villavicencio","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Taal, Batangas, 13 Mayo 1852. Tinawag na Aling Eriang at itinuring na isang bayani ng himagsikan noong 1896, dahil sa kanyang tulong na moral at materyal sa mga manghihimagsik. Ang kanyang bahay ay nagsilbing punong himpilan noong panahon ng himagsikan. Ipinagkaloob niya ang kanyang karapatan sa sasakyang pandagat na \"Bulusan\" na ginawang sasakyang pandigma ng mga manghihimagsik. Namatay 28 Setyembre 1929.</p>"}}},"address":"Casa Villavicencio, 33 Calle Gliceria Marella, Taal, Batangas","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Gliceria Marella de Villavicencio","lon":120.92104,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Gliceria Marella de Villavicencio":true}},"Q54806690":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":120.38991,"locPhoto":null,"address":"Quirino Boulevard cor. Salcedo Street, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","details":{"es":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Construída en 1830 por Don Justo Angco y dada en dote a su hija Estefanía, al casarse con Gregorio R. Syquia, honrado por el Gobierno español con las encomiendas de Isabel la Catolica y Carlos III. Fué casa solariega de Don Tomás Syquia, padre de Doña Alicia, que vino a ser esposa del Presidente Elpidio Quirino, entonces representante, primer distrito de Ilocos Sur, y en 1921, residencia de los esposos Quirino<nobr>–<nobr>Syquia.</p>","title":"Mansion Syquia","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"b2","height":1920,"credit":"Oloapsaziracav {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Syquia Mansion marker.JPG","width":1080}}},"region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Mansion Syquia","lat":17.57103,"date":"1951","macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur"},"Q28942696":{"address":"Patio Victoria Baluarte, San Jose, Tacloban","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Built by the Japanese Imperial Forces during World War II as part of the fortification against the Allied Liberation Forces lead by Gen. Douglas MacArthur on D-Day, 20 October 1944. The United States Marines captured and used it as shelter from aerial bombardments by Japanese planes. As war relic, the Dio Island Resort has maintained and preserved it for posterity.</p>","title":"Japanese Pillbox Whitebeach, San Jose, Tacloban City","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"region":"Eastern Visayas","name":"Japanese Pillbox Whitebeach, San Jose, Tacloban City","lat":11.2073,"date":"1979","macroAddress":"Tacloban","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Leyte":true},"lon":125.02763,"locPhoto":null},"Q55383636":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Iba","inscription":"<p>Originally the village of Paynaven; founded 1611 by the Recollect Missionaries Fr. Rodrigo de San Miguel and Fr. Andres del Espiritu Santo; formerly situated near Fort Playa Honda; transferred in 1680 by the Dominicans to this site and renamed Iba; later became capital of Zambales. Hometown of Juan Manday, member of Malolos Congress; Silverio Apostol, Acting Secretary of Agriculture, 1922; Gregorio Anonas, representative, 1928–33, manager, Metropolitan Water District, 1934–38 and NDC, 1938–46. </p><p><i>Birthplace of</i> RAMON MAGSAYSAY, <i>President of the Philippines, 1953–·</i></p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Iba historical marker.jpg","width":3456,"hash":"a1","height":4608}}},"address":"Zambales Provincial Capitol, Iba, Zambales","name":"Iba","region":"Central Luzon","macroAddress":"Iba, Zambales","date":"1956","lat":15.32586,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the Provincial Capitol lobby, to the left of the main staircase.","wikipedia":{"Ramon Magsaysay":true,"Iba":"Iba, Zambales"},"lon":119.981,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"IbaZambalesjf9191 08.JPG","width":4608,"hash":"5d","height":3456}},"Q28913903":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Douglas MacArthur":true,"Sergio Osmeña":true},"lon":125.00426,"locPhoto":null,"address":"Price Mansion, Tacloban","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Provisional Capitol","inscription":"<p>Constructed, 1910, and enlarged, 1936. This edifice, owned by Mr. and Mrs. Walter S. Price, sheltered Gen. Douglas Macarthur, who escaped injury, 20 October 1944, when Japanese bomb penetrated the roof over his room. Served as provisional Capitol 20–23 October 1944, upon the reconstitution of the Commonwealth of the Philippines, for President Sergio Osmeña.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"f0","height":1600,"width":1200,"file":"Provisional Capitol historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"}}},"name":"Provisional Capitol","region":"Eastern Visayas","macroAddress":"Tacloban","date":"1950","lat":11.24392},"Q28927638":{"lon":122.01367,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Mindanao":true,"Jens A. Doe":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"1952","macroAddress":"Zamboanga City","lat":6.92748,"name":"Zamboanga Beach","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"f7","height":1200,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Zamboanga Beach historical marker 01.jpg","width":810},"text":{"title":"Zamboanga Beach","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Here on the 10th of March, 1945 the 41st Division, U.S. Army under the command of Maj. Gen. Jens A. Doe landed in order to liberate the City of Zamboanga from the Japanese Forces. Liberation completed on the 12th of March, 1945.</p>"}}},"address":"Zamasco, Zamboanga West Coastal Road, Brgy. Sinunuc, Zamboanga City"},"Q54666933":{"lon":121.00056,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"date":"1984","macroAddress":"Pasay, Metro Manila","lat":14.54967,"name":"Unang Paaralang Bayan ng Pasay","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Padre Burgos Elementary School, 509 P. Burgos Street, Pasay, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan Bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974 at Bilang 1505, 11 Hunyo 1978, ang Paaralang ito ay ipinahayag na pambansang palatandaang makasaysayan, 21 Setyembre 1984.</p>","title":"Unang Paaralang Bayan ng Pasay","subtitle":null},"photo":null}}},"Q52399087":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":2520,"hash":"79","width":1680,"credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"JC Tuguegarao 1.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang mga Paring Dominiko ay dumating sa Cagayan Valley noong 1600 at sinimulan ang kanilang misyon sa Tuguegarao noong 9 Mayo 1604. Unang bikaryo si P. Tomas Villa, O.P. Ang simbahan na may kampanaryo ay ipinagawa ni Reb. Antonio Lobato, O.P. simula noong 1761 hanggang 1767 sa tulong ng mga mananampalataya. Ito ang pinakamalaking simbahan sa Cagayan. </p><p>Ang diyosesis ay itinatag ng Papa Pio X noong 10 Abril 1910 at itinalaga ni Mons. Mauricio P. Foley bilang unang obispo nito noong 6 Disyembre 1911. </p><p>Nagiba noong panahon ng pagpapalaya noong 1945. Ang katedral ay muling ipinatayo ni Mons. Constance Jurgens. Ang nasirang kampanaryo ay muling isinaayos ng mga mananampalataya at ng Knights of Colombus.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Katedral ng Tuguegarao"}}},"address":"Tuguegarao Cathedral, Rizal Street cor. Gomez Street, Tuguegarao, Cagayan","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Ang Katedral ng Tuguegarao","lat":17.61313,"macroAddress":"Tuguegarao, Cagayan","date":"1982-07-15","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Tuguegarao Cathedral":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.73051},"Q28858149":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.8581,"wikipedia":{"Carlos P. Garcia Heritage House":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"Tagbilaran, Bohol","lat":9.6414,"name":"Carlos P. Garcia House","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":2137,"file":"Carlos P. Garcia House historical marker.JPG","credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","height":1886,"hash":"0e"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute, 04 September 2009</p>","title":"Carlos P. Garcia House","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Carlos P. Garcia Heritage House, Tagbilaran, Bohol"},"Q44504205":{"locPhoto":{"width":3000,"file":"Entrance to the Mansion House.jpg","credit":"Francisco M. Pajares, Jr. {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":1993,"hash":"62"},"lon":120.6204,"wikipedia":{"The Mansion":"The Mansion (Baguio)"},"locDesc":"The historical markers are located on the pillars of the main gate to the compound. The Tagalog marker is on the second pillar from the north, the English on the third pillar, and the Ilocano on the last pillar.","lat":16.41361,"macroAddress":"Baguio","date":"2008","region":"Cordillera Administrative Region","name":"Mansion House","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Mansion House","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni William Cameron Forbes ayon sa disenyo ni William E. Parsons, 1908, bilang bahagi ng Burnham Plan ng Baguio at ng City Beautiful Movement. Dito ginanap ang special session ng Pangalawang Lehislatura ng Pilipinas, 1910. Nasira noong panahon ng Liberasyon, 1945. Ipinaayos, 1947. Dito ginanap ang pangalawang pagpupulong ng U.N. Economic Commission of Asia and the Far East (ECAFE), 1947; U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO), 1948; at unang pagpupulong ng Southeast Asian Union (SEAU) na kilala bilang Baguio Conference of 1950. Bahay bakasyunan ng mga Amerikanong gobernador-heneral, 1908–1935 at ng mga Pangulo ng Pilipinas mula kay Manuel L. Quezon hanggang sa kasalukuyan.</p>"},"photo":null},"ilo":{"photo":{"width":1504,"credit":"Irvin Parco Sto. Tomas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Mansion House NHI marker Ilokano.JPG","height":2256,"hash":"88"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Naipatakder kas improponer ni William Cameron Forbes nga naitutop iti disenyo ni William E. Parsons, 1908, kas parte ti Plano ti Burnham ti Baguio, naengganyo iti Napintas nga Biag ti Siyudad. Naaramid ditoy ti naipangpangruna a sesyon ti Maikadua a Lehislatura ti Pilipinas, 1910. Nadadael kabayatan ti Liberasyon, 1945. Naisubli iti sigud a kasasaad, 1947. Naaramid ditoy ti maikadua a gimong ti U.N. Economic Commission of Asia ken ti Far East (ECAFE), 1947; U.N. Food and Organization (FAO), 1948; ken ti umuna a gimong ti Southeast Asian Union (SEAU) nga nabigbig kas Baguio Conference of 1950. Balay a pagbakasyunan dagiti gobernador heneral nga Amerikano, 1908–1935 ken dagiti Presidente ti Pilipinas manipud kenni Manuel L. Quezon agingga iti agdama.</p>","title":"Mansion House","subtitle":null}},"en":{"text":{"title":"Mansion House","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Constructed at the instance of William Cameron Forbes following the design of William E. Parsons, as part of the Burnham Plan for Baguio, 1908, inspired by the City Beautiful Movement. Venue of the special session of the Second Philippine Legislature, 1910. Destroyed during the War, 1945. Rehabilitated, 1947. Venue of the U.N. Economic Commission of Asia and the Far East (ECAFE), 1947; The U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO), 1948; and the first meeting of the Southeast Asian Union (SEAU) known as the Baguio Conference of 1950. Summer residence of American governors-general, 1908–1935 and later of Philippine presidents from Manuel L. Quezon to the present.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"f9","height":2256,"width":1504,"file":"Mansion House NHI marker English.JPG","credit":"Irvin Parco Sto. Tomas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"address":"The Mansion, V.L. Romulo Drive, Baguio"},"Q55718188":{"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Orion, Bataan","lat":14.62152,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"8d","height":3110,"width":3675,"file":"Church of Orion historical marker.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"text":{"title":"Church of Orion","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The spiritual ministration of Orion belonged formerly with Abucay. Orion became an independent missionary center in 1667. Its first minister was the Rev. Domingo Perez. The Church and the Convent were badly damaged by the earthquakes of September 16, 1852, and were repaired in 1854. The Rev. Ulpiano Herrero constructed the beautiful sacristy and the marble altars. In this town Cayetano Arellano, eminent Filipino jurist and statesman and first Filipino Chief Justice of the Supreme Court, was born on March 2, 1847. Francisco Baltazar Balagtas, author of Florante at Laura, lived in this town from July 22, 1842 to February 20, 1862.</p>"}}},"address":"Orion Church, National Road cor. M. Santos Street, Orion, Bataan","name":"Church of Orion","region":"Central Luzon","lon":120.57658,"locPhoto":{"file":"9112Town Proper Orion San Vicente Bataan 10.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"be"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the  church facade, on the column immediately to the left of the left niche.","wikipedia":{"Orion Church":true,"Francisco Balagtas":true,"Cayetano Arellano":true}},"Q55100931":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.53548,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":9.7625,"date":"2004-10-03","macroAddress":"Dalaguete, Cebu","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng San Guillermo de Aquitania","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Tabunon {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Hm dalagueteChurch.jpg","width":453,"hash":"84","height":604},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng San Guillermo de Aquitania","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang visita ng Carcar, 1690. Naging parokya, 1711. Sinimulan ang kasalukuyang simbahan, 1802. Natapos 1825; ang kumbento, 1832; at ang kampanaryo, 1860. Itinalaga sa pagtangkilik ni San Guillermo de Aquitania. Ang simbahan at bantayan sa harapan ay ginamit bilang tanggulan laban sa pananalakay ng mga pirata noong unang bahagi ng ika-19 dantaon. Kinumpuni ang nabe, 1868. Gawa ni Canuto Avila ang mga larawan sa kisame ng simbahan, 1935. Mahalagang halimbawa ng arkitekturang Filipino–Espanyol at isa sa mga natitira at katangitanging church–fortress complex sa bansa. Inihayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 16 Abril 2004.</p>"}}},"address":"Dalaguete Church, San Guillermo Street, Dalaguete, Cebu"},"Q22340995":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.16747,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"date":"1960","macroAddress":"Calamba, Laguna","lat":14.21375,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Jose Rizal historical marker at Calamba Church.jpg","width":2500,"height":3466,"hash":"69"},"text":{"subtitle":"1861–1896","title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Si José Rizal ay bininyagan ni P. Rufino Collantes sa pabinyagang ito ng Simbahan ng Calamba, noong ika-22 ng Hunyo ng 1861, at naging inaama sa binyag si P. Pedro Casañas.</p>"}}},"address":"Calamba Church, Jose Rizal Street, Calamba, Laguna","name":"Jose Rizal","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q55223581":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the rear side of the monument pedestal, facing Vinzons Hall.","lon":121.07323,"locPhoto":{"file":"Monument to the Heroes of 1896 rear view.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608,"height":3456,"hash":"9f"},"name":"New site of the Monument of the Cry of Pugad Lawin","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Vinzons Hall, Roxas Avenue cor. Shuster Avenue, University of the Philippines Diliman, Diliman, Quezon City, Metro Manila","details":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Sigaw ng Pugad Lawin marker.jpg","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"07"},"text":{}},"date":"1968","macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","lat":14.6543},"Q28877481":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni Padre Pablo Pastells, S.J. kaagapay si Padre Juan Terricabras, S.J. Yari sa kahoy, korales at bato, 1877. Natapos ang simbahan at naging parokya sa patronato ni San Juan Savador Del Mundo,1884. Nagsilbing sentro ng misyon ng mga Heswita sa pagtatag ng mga pueblo at pagpalaganap ng ebanghelyo sa silangang bahagi ng Mindanao noong panahon ng mga Espanyol. Ipinamahala sa mga pari ng Foreign Mission of Quebec, 1939; Maryknoll Missioners, 1961; Diyosesis ng Tagum,1978; at Diyosesis ng Mati, 1984.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Caraga","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":492,"hash":"b4","file":"San Salvador Del Mundo Church National Historical Site Marker.jpg","credit":"Olan214 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":550}}},"address":"Caraga Church, San Salvador Street, Caraga, Davao Oriental","name":"Simbahan ng Caraga","region":"Davao Region","macroAddress":"Caraga, Davao Oriental","date":"2012","lat":7.32754,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Caraga Church":"San Salvador del Mundo Church"},"lon":126.56588,"locPhoto":null},"Q54088778":{"locDesc":"The historical markers are located on the facade of the house on Santo Sepulcro Street, with the Filipino marker to the left of the entry door and the English marker to the right.","wikipedia":{"Jose P. Laurel Ancestral House, Manila":"Jose P. Laurel Ancestral House (Manila)"},"lon":120.99721,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"0425jfPeñafrancia Street Jose P. Laurel Ancestral House Paco Manilafvf 11.jpg","height":3456,"hash":"e7"},"address":"1515 Peñafrancia Street cor. Santo Sepulcro Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayo noong 1861, ang tahanang ito ay binili ni Jose P. Laurel noong 1926. Nanirahan siya rito nang may 29 na taon (1926–1955) kasama ang kanyang maybahay na si Paciencia Hidalgo at ang kanyang mga anak. </p><p>Ang ari-ariang ito ay minana ng kanyang ikatlong anak, si Sotero H. Laurel, na nag-kaloob nito sa Jose P. Laurel Memorial Foundation at nanguna sa pagpapanumbalik nito sa ayos bilang parangal sa kanyang ama na buong giting, may matibay na paniniwala at walang pag-iimbot na dedikasyon na naglingkod sa kanyang bayan.</p><p> Pinasinayaan ng kagalang-galang na Pangulong Fidel V. Ramos noong Marso 8, 1998, bisperas ng pagdiriwang ng ika-107 kaarawan ni Jose P. Laurel, at bilang pakikiisa sa pagdiriwang ng Sentenyal ng Pilipinas (1898–1998).</p>","subtitle":"Pangulo, Ikalawang Republika ng Pilipinas<br>(1943–1945)","title":"Tahanan ni Jose P. Laurel"}},"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Residence of Jose P. Laurel","subtitle":"President, Second Philippine Republic<br>(1943–1945)","inscription":"<p>Originally built in 1861, this house was purchased in 1926 by Jose P. Laurel. He lived her for 29 years (1926–1955) with his wife Paciencia Hidalgo and children. </p><p>This property was inherited by his third son, Sotero H. Laurel who donated it to the Jose P. Laurel Memorial Foundation and spearheaded its restoration in tribute to his father who served his country with dauntless courage, unwavering conviction, and selfless dedication. </p><p> Inaugurated on March 8, 1998 by His Excellency President Fidel V. Ramos on the eve of the 107th Birth Anniversary of Jose P. Laurel and on the occasion of the Philippine Centennial (1898–1998).</p>"}}},"name":"Residence of Jose P. Laurel","region":"Metro Manila","date":"1998-03-08","macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","lat":14.57963},"Q28933167":{"lat":8.47579,"macroAddress":"Cagayan de Oro","date":"2000-04-07","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Labanan sa Cagayan de Misamis","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Bago magbukang-liwayway noong Abril 7, 1900, ang lakas panghimagsikan ng batalyong Mindanao sa pamumuno ni Heneral Nicolas Capistrano ay nagsagawa ng isang biglaang pagsalakay sa ika-40 rehimiyento na binubuo ng mga boluntaryo ng Estados Unidos sa pamumuno ni Medyor James Case. Sa pagtatanggol sa kanilang minamahal na bansa. Ilang daang magigiting na Pilipinong manghihimagsik ang namatay sa labanang ito. </p><p> Ang panandang pangkasaysayang ito ay buong pusong iniaalay ng sambayanang Pilipino sa magigiting na tagapagtanggol ng kalayaan ng Cagayan de Misamis sa paggunita sa ikasandaang taon ng makasaysayang labanang ito.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Cagayan de Oro","region":"Northern Mindanao","name":"Labanan sa Cagayan de Misamis","lon":124.6419,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Cagayan de Misamis":true}},"Q31440688":{"macroAddress":"Tagbilaran, Bohol","date":"1953","lat":9.63949,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"40","height":4032,"width":3024,"credit":"Malou Buenconsejo {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Tagbilaran Church Plaque.JPG"},"text":{"title":"Church of Tagbilaran","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>One of the six parishes founded in Bohol by the Jesuit Missionaries, 1595. Turned over to the Recollects, 1768. Original church built by the Jesuits on this spot was burned, 23 December 1798. Reconstructed and enlarged by Fr. Valero de San Pascual, 1839-1855; Fr. Lucas Corominas built the convent, 1872; Fr. Jose Sancho the tower, 1884-1888. Father Escolastico Enciso improved the premises by placing iron cornices, tile flooring and chandeliers, 1884-1894.</p>"}}},"address":"Tagbilaran Church, Tagbilaran, Bohol","name":"Church of Tagbilaran","region":"Central Visayas","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.85593,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q43590262":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Maximo Sison Viola":"Máximo Viola"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96779,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"32","width":3456,"file":"Maximo Viola historical marker.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Here in Barrio Sta. Rita, San Miguel, Bulacan, was born Maximo Viola, friend and traveling companion in Europe of Jose Rizal, who advanted the money needed for the printing of Rizal’s novel NOLI ME TANGERE. </p><p> Dr. Viola and Dr. Rizal toured Europe together, May–June, 1887, visiting various cities in Germany, Austria, Hungary and Switzerland. One of the places they visited was Leitmeritz, Austria, hometown of Professor Ferdinand Blumentritt.</p>","subtitle":"1857–1933","title":"Dr. Maximo Viola"}}},"address":"Cagayan Valley Road cor. Viola Street, San Miguel, Bulacan","name":"Dr. Maximo Viola","region":"Central Luzon","date":"1962-10-17","macroAddress":"San Miguel, Bulacan","lat":15.14013},"Q54069098":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.71511,"wikipedia":{"Vicente Manansala":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"1984","macroAddress":"Macabebe, Pampanga","lat":14.90836,"name":"Vicente S. Manansala","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3058,"file":"Vicentejf (cropped).JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"06","height":2530},"text":{"title":"Vicente S. Manansala","subtitle":"(1910–1981)","inscription":"<p>Bantog na pintor at miyuralista. Isinilang sa Macabebe, Pampanga, noong Enero 22, 1910. Nagtapos ng Fine Arts sa Pamantasan ng Pilipinas, 1930. Tagaguhit at lay-out artist ng Philippines Herald, Photo News, Liwayway at Saturday Evening News, Nagwagi ng unang gantimpala ang kanyang \"Pounding Rice,\" 1940, at \"Barung-Barong No. 1,\" 1950. Tumanggap ng Outstanding U.P. Alumni Award, 1957; Republic Cultural Heritage Award, 1963; at Araw ng Maynila Patnubay ng Kalinangan Award, 1970. Gumuhit ng miyural \"Freedom of the Press,\" \"Stations of the Cross,\" \"Agham at Humanidad,\" atba. Ginawaran pagkamatay bilang isang National Artist, 1981. Namatay noong Agosto 22, 1981.</p>"}}},"address":"Macabebe Municipal Hall, Poblacion, Macabebe, Pampanga"},"Q37963698":{"lon":120.98908,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"date":"1957","macroAddress":"San Miguel, Manila","lat":14.59189,"address":"Goldenberg Mansion, General Solano Street, San Miguel, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Goldenberg Mansion","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Built by the Eugster Family from whom it was acquired by the Oidor de la Audiencia, Jose Moreno Lacalle; successively occupied by Admiral Patricio Montojo of the Spanish Navy, 1897–1898, later by the Spanish Royal Navy Club, 1898. Home and Headquarters of General Arthur McArthur, 1899. Became the Offices of the Philippine Preliminary Exposition to the International Exposition, St. Louis, Mo., U.S.A., 1903–1904. Housed the Philippine School of Commerce, 1908. The First Philippine Senate held its sessions here, Oct. 16, 1916. Bought and occupied by Michael Goldenberg, 1950.</p>"},"photo":null}},"name":"Goldenberg Mansion","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q50377908":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Philippine Post Office","inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang Tanggapan ng Koreo sa Maynila, 1767; itinaas bilang Distritong Pangkoreo ng Espanya, 1779; nagpanibagong-tatag , 5 Disyembre 1837; naging pangunahing sentrong pangkoreo, 1838. Naging kasapi ng Universal Postal Union, 1877. Itinatag bilang Lingkurang Pangkoreo sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulong Emilio Aguinaldo, 1898. Muling itanatag bilang kawanihan sa ilalim ng Kagawaran ng Pangangalakal sa bisa ng Batas ng Komisyon ng Pilipinas Blg. 426, 15 Setyembre 1902. Itinayo ang kasalukuyang gusali na may arkitekturang neo-klasiko, 1926. Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig; muling ipinatayo, 1946. Pinangalanang Postal Services Office sa pangangasiwa ng Kagawaran ng Transportasyon at Komunikasyon sa bisa ng Kautusang Pampangasiwaan Blg. 125, 13 Abril 1987; at Philippine Postal Corporation sa bisa ng Batas ng Republika Blg. 7354, 3 Abril 1992.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"48","height":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"ManilaCentralPostOfficejf1446 15.JPG","width":3456}}},"address":"Manila Central Post Office, Magallanes Drive, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Philippine Post Office","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"1994-06-02","lat":14.59533,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Manila Central Post Office":true,"Philippine Postal Corporation":true},"lon":120.9791,"locPhoto":null},"Q29017572":{"lat":8.47617,"macroAddress":"Cagayan de Oro","date":"2015-01-13","region":"Northern Mindanao","name":"Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Cagayan de Misamis","address":"Cagayan de Oro","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinaas ang watawat ng Pilipinas sa Casa Real ng Cagayan de Misamis (ngayo'y Cagayan de Oro) bilang sagisag ng pagkilala sa Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo, 10 Enero 1899. Tinawag ni Gobernador Jose Roa y Casas ng lalawigan ng Misamis ang pagdiriwang na yaon bilang \"La Fiesta Nacional\" sa kanyang liham kay Hen. Aguinaldo, 26 Enero 1899. Tanda ito ng masiglang pagdiriwang ng mamamayan sa kalayaan ng Pilipinas.</p>","subtitle":"10 Enero 1899","title":"Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Cagayan de Misamis"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.6417,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q24708066":{"name":"Basilika Menor ng Inmaculada Concepcion","region":"Calabarzon","address":"Minor Basilica of the Immaculate Conception, M.H. del Pilar Street cor. Natividad Street, Batangas City, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Basilika Menor ng Inmaculada Concepcion","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ang unang simbahan ni P. Diego Mojica, pastor na Augustino ng Calapan, Mindoro, noong 1581 at inialay sa Immaculada Concepcion de Nuestra Señora bilang parokya. Inilagay noong 1601 ang pundasyong bato ng ikalawang simbahan na ipinagawa ng mga pari noong 1682-1721. Idinagdag noong 1693 ang kumbentong may artileriya upang maitaboy ang mga tulisang-dagat. Giniba pagkaraan ng 179 na taon at muling ipinatayo ni P. Pedro Cuesta noong 1851. Binasbasan noong Pebrero 2, 1857, itinalaga bilang Basilika Menor noong Pebrero 13, 1948 at nagdiwang ng ikasandaang taon noong 1957.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Basilika Menor ng Inmaculada Concepcion historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3000,"height":4150,"hash":"1f"}}},"date":"1984-01-15","macroAddress":"Batangas City, Batangas","lat":13.75434,"wikipedia":{"Minor Basilica of the Immaculate Conception":"Minor Basilica of the Immaculate Conception (Batangas City)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade, between the main entrance and left aisle entrance.","lon":121.05922,"locPhoto":{"hash":"14","height":2083,"file":"Batangas Basilica historical marker location.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1828}},"Q56055061":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"f6","height":3264,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Cebu Cathedral historical marker.jpg","width":2448},"text":{"title":"Katedral ng Cebu","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinayo ang unang katedral gawa sa kahoy at nipa, at naging sentro ng Diyosesis ng Cebu, 1595. Itinanghal na Arsobispado ang Cebu, at naging Metropolitan Cathedral, 1934. Tanging ang harapan, kampanaryo at palibot na pader ng simbahan ang nanatiling nakatayo matapos masira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Muling binuo sa panahon ni Arsobispo Julio Kardinal Rosales, 1950.</p>"}}},"address":"Cebu Metropolitan Cathedral, P. Burgos Street, Cebu City","name":"Katedral ng Cebu","region":"Central Visayas","date":"2016-11-23","macroAddress":"Cebu City","lat":10.29566,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Cebu Metropolitan Cathedral":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.90306},"Q28869059":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Lazatin House":true},"lon":120.69049,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute, 27 January 2003</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Lazatin House"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"LazatinHouse HistoricalMarker SanFernandoCityPampanga.jpg","width":454,"height":427,"hash":"51"}}},"address":"Lazatin House, S. Lazatin Street cor. Consunji Street, San Fernando, Pampanga","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Lazatin House","lat":15.02567,"macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","date":"2003"},"Q55001092":{"date":"1993-04-16","macroAddress":"Taytay, Palawan","lat":10.82802,"name":"Kutang Santa Isabel","region":"Mimaropa","address":"Fort Santa Isabel, Rizal Street, Poblacion, Taytay, Palawan","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":799,"credit":"Jimaggro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Fort Sta. Isabel Marker.JPG","hash":"c2","height":1200},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayo na yari sa kahoy ng mga misyonerong Rekoleto, 1667. Himpilan ng kampanyang pangkapayapaan ng mga Kastila sa Paragua (Palawan). Sa pagsusumikap ni Gobernador Fernando Manuel de Bustillo, muling ipinatayo na yari sa bato at may apat na tanggulan na nagpaparangal kina Santo Toribio, San Miguel, San Juan at Santa Isabel. Noong unang sangkapat ng ika-18 dantaon, pinangsiwaan ni Don Fernando Velez de Arce at natapos noong kalagitnaan ng dantaong ding iyon. Ang kutang ito ay nagsilbing matibay na muog na nagmamatyag sa mga sasakyang pandagat na pangkalakal at sumasalakay na mga tulisang dagat.</p>","subtitle":"(Taytay)","title":"Kutang Santa Isabel"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":119.51777,"wikipedia":{"Fort Santa Isabel":true},"locDesc":null},"Q55731887":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Bataan Death March":true},"lon":120.49096,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pinagsimulan ng Death March","inscription":"<p>Mahigit 70,000 sundalong Pilipino at Amerikanong mga bihag ng digmaan noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig ang nagsimulang magmartsa sa utos ng mga sundalong Hapones mula Mariveles, Bataan, 10 Abril 1942, at Bagac, Bataan, 11 Abril 1942. Nakaranas ng pagmamalupit, matinding pagod, gutom at uhaw ang mga bihag. Marami ang namatay at ang iba ay nagkasakit. Pagdating sa San Fernando, Pampanga, isinakay sila sa tren patungong Capas, Tarlac. Ikinasawi ng marami ang kawalan ng hangin bunga ng pagsisiksikan sa mga bagon. Nakarating ang mga natirang buhay sa Capas, Tarlac at muling pinaglakad ng anim na kilometro hanggang sa bilangguan ng Camp O’Donnell, 15 Abril 1942. Kinikilala sa kasaysayan bilang Death March.</p>"}}},"address":"World War II Death March Memorial Shrine, National Road, Brgy. Poblacion, Mariveles, Bataan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Pinagsimulan ng Death March","lat":14.43583,"date":"2017-03-23","macroAddress":"Mariveles, Bataan"},"Q43217957":{"wikipedia":{"Balanga Cathedral":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.54062,"locPhoto":null,"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Church of Balanga","address":"Balanga Cathedral, Aguirre Street cor. J.P. Rizal Street, Balanga, Bataan","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The spiritual ministration of Balanga formerly belonged to Abucay. Balanga became an independent missionary center in 1739. Rev. Benito Rivas, O.P., strengthened this church by fortifying its wall. Rev. Juan Antonio Vicente, O.P., roofed it with galvanized iron and decorated the interior. Rev. Fernaldo Ma. Miñano, O.P., from 1838–45 constructed the arch of the choir loft and made the baptismal font out of granite from Mariveles. The parochial ministration under the Filipino clergy started with Rev. Mariano Sarili, June 2, 1898.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Balanga"},"photo":{"width":2500,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Balanga historical marker.jpg","hash":"ff","height":2787}}},"lat":14.67934,"macroAddress":"Balanga, Bataan","date":"1940"},"Q41743198":{"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1991","lat":14.592,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":501,"hash":"a9","width":347,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jose P. Laurel (1891 - 1959).jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Kilalang hurista, estadista, lehislador, pilosopong moral at pulitikal, edukador, makabayan at kampeon ng mga karapatang pantao at katarungang panlipunan. Isinilang sa Tanauan, Batangas, Marso 9, 1891. Nagkaloob ng katangi-tanging paglilingkod sa tatlong sangay ng pamahalaan: Kalihim Panloob, 1923; Senador, 1925–1931; Kinatawan, 1934 Kumbensiyong Konstitusyonal; Mahistrado ng Kataas-taasang Hukuman, 1936–1941; Punong Mahistrado at kasabay nito, Kalihim ng Katarungan, 1941–1942; Pangulo ng Ikalawang Republika ng Pilipinas, 1943–1945; Senador, 1951–1957. Namatay, Nobyembre 6, 1959.</p>","title":"Jose P. Laurel","subtitle":"(1891–1959)"}}},"address":"Lyceum of the Philippines University, Muralla Street cor. Real Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Jose P. Laurel","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97801,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José P. Laurel":true}},"Q48316511":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":123.75285,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Labanan sa Legazpi","region":"Bicol Region","address":"Quezon Avenue cor. Rizal Street, Legazpi, Albay","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa Legazpi","inscription":"<p>Sa bayang ito, noong Enero 23, 1900, buong giting na nakipaglaban sa mga sundalong Amerikano ng Ikatlong Batalyon ng ika-47 Impanterya, mga boluntaryo ng E.U. na pinamumunuan ni Brig. Hen. William A. Kobie, ang humigit-kumulang na 800 manghihimagsik na Pilipino sa pamumuno ni Kom. Antonio Reyes. Ang pambobomba sa trintsera ng nagtatanggol na mga Pilipino sa baybayin ng Legazpi ang sapilitang nagpaurong sa kanila sa noon ay tulay ng San Rafael. Dito sila buong tapang na nakipaglaban nang dikitan (mano-mano) sa tumutugis na mga Amerikano. May mga 200 nagtatanggol, kabilang na si Kom. Reyes, ang buong kabayanihang nasawi sa labanang ito.</p>"},"photo":null}},"date":null,"macroAddress":"Legazpi, Albay","lat":13.1473},"Q54608612":{"lat":14.59856,"macroAddress":"Binondo, Manila","date":"1993-02-26","region":"Metro Manila","name":"William J. Burke","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2736,"credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","file":"William J. Burke historical marker.JPG","hash":"0f","height":3648},"text":{"title":"William J. Burke","subtitle":"(1873–1946)","inscription":"<p>Kardiyolohiya, pilantropo. Ipinanganak noong Pebrero 18, 1873 sa San Miguel, Maynila. Nagkamit ng titulong Doktor sa Medisina, University of Dublin, Ireland. Bumalik sa Maynila para magpraktika ng propesyon, 1900. Nagpasimula at naglagay ng unang electrocardiograph sa Pilipinas. Tumanggap ng mga gawad pontipikal dahilan sa kanyang mga mapagkawanggawang gawain mula sa mga kilalang ospital, kumbento at kongregasyon sa bansa. Namatay noong Hulyo 23, 1946.</p>"}}},"address":"Burke Building, Escolta Street corner Burke Street, Binondo, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.97919,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Burke Building, Escolta, Manila (Escolta side).jpg","width":3456,"hash":"09","height":4608},"wikipedia":{"William J. Burke":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the right end of the building facade on Escolta Street."},"Q54732011":{"date":"1994-08-20","macroAddress":"San Miguel, Manila","lat":14.59275,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Sabino B. Padilla","subtitle":"(1894–1986)","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak, Agosto 21, 1894, San Miguel, Maynila. Nagkamit ng titulong Batsilyer sa Sining, Ateneo de Manila, 1911; Batsilyer sa Batas, University of the Philippines, 1915; nagpakadalubhasa sa batas, Columbia University, New York, 1917. Ginawaran ng Doctor in Jure Civile, University of Santo Tomas, 1937; Doktorado sa Batas, University of Manila, 1969. Humawak ng matataas na katungkulan sa pamahalaan, kabilang ang pagiging Attorney General, 1919; auxiliary judge, CFI–Jolo, Sulu, 1929; district judge, CFI–Nueva Ecija, 1933; presiding judge CFI–3rd Branch Manila, 1936; naging Katulong na Mahistrado ng Hukuman ng Paghahabol at Kataas-taasang Hukuman ng Pilipinas, 1946; Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Katarungan, 1948; muling naglingkod sa Korte Suprema bilang Katulong na Mahistrado, 1948–1964. Pangulo, Asociacion de los Veteranos de la Revoluccion, 1962–1986. Tumanggap ng maraming gawad at karangalan sa loob at labas ng bansa, natatangi rito ang Legion of Honor na may Ranggong Komander mula kay Pangulong Diosdado Macapagal, 1964. Namatay, Hunyo 15, 1986.</p>"},"photo":{"height":3264,"hash":"a9","file":"Sabino Padilla historical marker.jpeg","credit":"Roel Balingit {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1836}}},"address":"785 Nicanor Padilla Street, San Miguel, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Sabino B. Padilla","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"width":1836,"file":"Sabino Padilla historical marker - location.jpeg","credit":"Roel Balingit {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":3264,"hash":"f7"},"lon":120.9889,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the property wall.","wikipedia":null},"Q21529486":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Lichauco House","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Declared a heritage house by the National Historical Commission of the Philippines 21 July 2010</p>"},"photo":{"width":2751,"file":"Lichauco Heritage House marker (cropped).jpg","credit":"Zernan2014 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"da","height":2602}}},"address":"Lichauco Heritage House, 2315 Pedro Gil Street, Santa Ana, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Lichauco House","region":"Metro Manila","date":"2010","macroAddress":"Santa Ana, Manila","lat":14.58132,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the wall adjoining to the left of the main gate of the house.","wikipedia":{"Lichauco Heritage House":true},"locPhoto":{"width":3179,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"0246jfPedro Gil Street Plaza Calderon Santa Ana Manila Schools Landmarksfvf 12.jpg","hash":"d1","height":3364},"lon":121.01108},"Q55938921":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","subtitle":null,"title":"Pagpupulong sa Bacoor"}}},"address":"Plaza de Padre Mariano A. Gomez, Gen. Evangelista Street cor. F.L. Pagtakhan Street, Bacoor, Cavite","name":"Pagpupulong sa Bacoor","region":"Calabarzon","date":"2018-08-01","macroAddress":"Bacoor, Cavite","lat":14.45946,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Philippine Revolution":true},"lon":120.94021,"locPhoto":null},"Q24838207":{"date":"1952","macroAddress":"Lemery, Batangas","lat":13.88367,"address":"Lemery, Batangas","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Municipality of Lemery","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The town of Lemery was founded in 1862 during the administration of Governor General Jose Lemery. Jose Cabrera was it's first Gobernadorcillo. Others were Miguel Agoncillo, Eleno Aniversario, Basilio Gatachalian, Mariano Generoso, Perpetuo Ilustre, Mariano Marella, Juan Medina, Brigido Morales, Ramon M. Mitra, Ramon Noble, Victoriano Noble, Agapito Panganiban, and Pioquinto Reyes.</p><p>Lemery was annexed to the municipality of Taal in 1904.</p><p>Again became a municipality in 1907 with Perpetuo de Joya as Municipal President.</p><p>The eruption of nearby Taal volcano in January 1911 killed hundreds of its inhabitants.</p><p>Occupied by the Japanese imperial army in 1942, One third of the town was burnt by enemy artillery when it was liberated by the Americans aided by Filipino Guerillas on 6 March 1945.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Municipality of Lemery historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"ae"}}},"name":"Municipality of Lemery","region":"Calabarzon","lon":120.914,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Lemery":"Lemery, Batangas"}},"Q55401414":{"region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Ang Paglunsad","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Ang Paglunsad","subtitle":"(1945)","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito lumunsad si Heneral Carlos P. Romulo noong ika-10 ng Enero, 1945, isang araw matapos lumunsad si Heneral Douglas MacArthur, ang Kataas-taasang Pinuno ng Hukbong Magkasanib sa Pilipinas at Pasipiko, sa kampanya ng pagpapalaya sa Luzon. Si Heneral Romulo na noon ay Residente Komisyonado sa Estados Unidos ay siyang ayuda-de-kampo ni Heneral MacArthur.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Ang Paglungsad historical marker.JPG","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2210,"hash":"d1","height":2469}}},"address":"Pangasinan Provincial Capitol, Lingayen, Pangasinan","lat":16.03444,"date":"1975-03-15","macroAddress":"Lingayen, Pangasinan","wikipedia":{"Battle of Luzon":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the south side of a simple concrete war memorial near the World War II memorabilia site.","locPhoto":{"width":3872,"file":"IJVPaglulunsad1.jpg","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":2592,"hash":"e2"},"lon":120.23122},"Q35000752":{"name":"Simbahan ng Baclayon","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"3b","height":4000,"width":3000,"file":"Baclayon Church Marker Baclayon, Bohol.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Baclayon","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito pormal na itinayo nina Padre Juan de Torres at Padre Gabriel Sanchez, mga paring Heswita, ang unang misyon ng Kristiyanismo sa Bohol, Nobyembre 17, 1596. Ang unang simbahan na yari sa kahoy ay parangal sa Birheng Immaculada Concepcion. Naging ganap na parokya, 1717. Ipinatayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan yari sa korales, 1727. Pinamahalaan ng mga Agustinong Recolectos, 1768. Idinagdag ang pilak na tabernakulo sa pangunahing dambana, 1810; ginawa ang binyagan at sakristiya, 1852. Nagsagawa ng mga ilang pagbabago at pagsasaayos ngunit ang orihinal na arkitekturang Neo-Klasiko sa paggamit ng arkong Romano at templo ay napanatili hanggang sa kasalukuyan. </p><p> Sa bisa ng kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng mga kautusan bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974 at bilang 1505, Hunyo 11, 1978, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan noong Hulyo 27, 1994.</p>"}}},"address":"Baclayon Church, Baclayon, Bohol","macroAddress":"Baclayon, Bohol","date":"1995","lat":9.62243,"wikipedia":{"Baclayon Church":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":123.91215,"locPhoto":null},"Q40314993":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97176,"wikipedia":{"Fort Santiago":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1934","lat":14.59269,"name":"Fort Santiago","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Fort Santiago, Santa Clara Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Fort Santiago","inscription":"<p>Built of Guadalupe Volcanic Tuff By Governor Gomez Perez Dasmariñas 1590–1593 In Place of the Wooden Palisade of Raja Matanda</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"67","height":500,"file":"Historical marker Fort Santiago.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":471}}}},"Q55332205":{"lon":120.939,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":14.09559,"date":null,"macroAddress":"Tagaytay, Cavite","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ika-41 Dibisyon Hukbong Katihan ng Pilipinas (USAFFE)","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"1 Setyembre – 25 Disyembre 1941","title":"Ika-41 Dibisyon Hukbong Katihan ng Pilipinas (USAFFE)","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito nagtipon ang ika-41 Dibisyon, Hukbong Katihan ng Pilipinas (USAFFE) na tinawag sa paglilingkod sa pamamahala ni Brig. Hen. Vicente P. Lim, noong 28 Agosto 1941, sa bisa ng utos militar ng Pangulong Franklin D. Roosevelt noong 26 Hulyo 1941 at ng Proklamasyong Bilang 740 ng Pangulong Manuel L. Quezon noong 10 Agosto 1941.</p><p>Sinanay noong 1937 at 1938, ang mga sundalong panlaan ng Dibisyon ang bumuo ng ika-4 na Pook Militar ng Hukbong Katihan ng Pilipinas na may punong-himpilan sa Lipa, Batangas. Itinalaga sa tungkulin ng USAFFE noong 1 Setyembre 1941, ang ika-41 at 42 Impanterya Rehimyento, sa tulong ng ibang pangkat ng Hukbong Sandatahan, ay itinaliba upang ipagtanggol ang mga baybayin mula Looc, Kabite hanggang Lemery, Batangas noong 17 Nobyembre 1941, at itinalaga ang ika-43 Rehimyento na reserba sa Tagaytay.</p><p> Dahil sa pagsalakay ng Hukbong Hapones sa Mauban, Tayabas noong 22 Disyembre, naging mapanganib ang katayuan ng militar, at ang buong pangkat ay inatasang tumungo noong ika-24–25 ng Disyembre 1941 mula Batangas hanggang sa Bataan upang itindig ang hanay ng depensang Abucay–Morong sa Bataan. Ang pangkat ay isa sa mga gumawa ng huling pagtatanggol sa makasaysayang Labanan sa Bataan hanggang ika-9 Abril 1942.</p>"}}},"address":"Km. 59 Emilio Aguinaldo Highway, Tagaytay, Cavite"},"Q54152501":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.94731,"address":"272 General Luna Street, Concepcion, Malabon, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3456,"file":"Concepcion Church Malabon historical marker.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","hash":"63","height":4608},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Concepcion","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Agustino bilang visita ng Tambobong, ngayo’y Malabon, sa patronato ng La Purisima, 1607. Itinayo ang unang kapilya sa bato at tisa 1866. Nasira ng lindol, 1880. Ipinatayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan, 1886. Ginamit ng Iglesia Filipina Independiente bilang simbahan, 26 Nobyembre 1902. Ibinalik sa Simbahang Romano Katoliko alinsunod sa utos ng Korte Suprema ng Pilipinas, 24 Nobyembre 1906. Naging simbahang parokyal, 8 Setyembre 1907. Pinagtibay ng Santo Papa Juan Paolo II ang koronasyong kanoniko ng lumang imahen ng La Inmaculada Concepcion ng Malabon, 16 Setyembre 1986. Ginanap ang koronasyon sa pangunguna ni Jaime Cardinal Sin, Arsobispo ng Maynila, 7 Disyembre 1986.</p>"}}},"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Concepcion","region":"Metro Manila","date":"2007-09-08","macroAddress":"Malabon, Metro Manila","lat":14.66897},"Q55334440":{"lat":14.23078,"macroAddress":"Santa Rosa, Laguna","date":"2005","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Kuwartel ng Santo Domingo","address":"Fort Santo Domingo, Santa Rosa–Tagaytay Road, Brgy. Santo Domingo, Santa Rosa, Laguna","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Bahagi ng asyenda ng mga Dominikano sa Santa Rosa na itinayo bilang himpilan ng mga Guwardiya Sibil, 1877. Nagsilbing tipunan at tinggalan ng mga munisyon at gamit ng pangkat ni Hen. Jose Lachambre nang kanilang salakayin ang mga manghihimagsik na Pilipino sa Silang at Dasmariñas, Cavite, 1897. Ginamit ng Hukbong Sandatahan ng Pilipinas, 1957–1990, at ng Pambansang Pulisya ng Pilipinas mula noong 1992. Mahalaga at natatanging halimbawa ng arkitekturang Filipino–Espanyol at isa sa mga makasaysayang pook sa lalawigan ng Laguna. Inihayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 21 Hulyo 2005.</p>","title":"Kuwartel ng Santo Domingo","subtitle":null}}},"lon":121.05001,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Cuartel de Santo Domingo":true},"locDesc":null},"Q52801279":{"name":"La Gota de Leche","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Gota de Leche Building, 859 Sergio H. Loyola Street, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":1824,"hash":"10","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Gota de Leche.jpg","width":1280},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Mapagkawanggawang proyekto ng La Proteccion de la Infancia na nagbibigay ng gatas sa mga sanggol. Pinasinayaan sa Daang San Pedro, ngayon Daang Evangelista, Quiapo, 1907. Nagpatayo ng bagong gusali sa Sampaloc, 1914. Dinisenyo ni Arcadio at Juan Arellano batay sa Ospedale Degli Innocenti ni Brunelleschi sa Florence, Italya. Binuksan, 1915. Inayos, 2002.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"La Gota de Leche"}}},"date":"2003","macroAddress":"Sampaloc, Manila","lat":14.60284,"wikipedia":{"Gota de Leche Building":true,"Gota de Leche":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the building.","locPhoto":{"hash":"e0","height":1920,"credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Gota de Leche 09.jpg","width":1280},"lon":120.98844},"Q56071625":{"date":"2009","macroAddress":"Talibon, Bohol","lat":10.09189,"name":"Carlos P. Garcia","region":"Central Visayas","address":"President Carlos P. Garcia Ancestral Park, Sitio Loy-a, Barangay San Agustin, Talibon, Bohol","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1896–1971)","title":"Carlos P. Garcia","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Talibon, Bohol, 4 Nobyembre 1896. Naging guro sa pampublikong paaralan, Kinatawan ng Ikatlong Distrito ng Bohol sa 7<sup><small>th</small></sup> at 8<sup><small>th</small></sup> Philippine Legislature (1925–1931); kumatawan sa Bohol sa Constitutional Convention (1934–1935); Punong Lalawigan ng Bohol (1934–1941); Senador (1941–1953); Pangalawang Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas at Kalihim ng Ugnayang Panlabas (1953–1957); Pangulo ng Pilipinas (1957–1960). Itinaguyod ang “Filipino First Policy” upang makilala ang mga gawang Filipino at tangkilikin ang mga produkto nito. Pangulo ng 1971 Constitutional Convention, 14 Hunyo 1971.</p>"},"photo":null}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.33183,"wikipedia":{"Carlos P. Garcia":true},"locDesc":null},"Q54867455":{"lon":120.77258,"locPhoto":{"hash":"c6","height":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Saint Pedro Apostol Parish Church, Apalit, right bell tower.jpg","width":3456},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade, to the right of the main entrance at the bottom of the right bell tower.","lat":14.95327,"macroAddress":"Apalit, Pampanga","date":"1939","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Church of Apalit","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of Apalit","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The Catholic Community of Apalit dates from 1590. The former church, built of brick, was destroyed by the earthquake of 1863. The present Church was constructed by Mariano Santos, of Guagua, under the supervision of the Rev. Antonio Redondo, O.S.A., between 1876 and 1880. Its towers were finished in 1896 by the Rev. Toribio Fanjul, who purposely made them low to minimize the effects of earthquakes.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"13","height":3456,"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Saint Pedro Apostol Parish Church, Apalit, historical marker.jpg"}}},"address":"Apalit Church, Gonzales Avenue cor. Reyes Street, San Juan, Apalit, Pampanga"},"Q54555376":{"macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","date":"1934","lat":14.60699,"address":"Tutuban Railway Station, Claro M. Recto Avenue, Tutuban, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Manila Railroad Company","inscription":"<p>Preparation of general plan for railroad on Luzon authorized by Royal Decree June 26, 1875. Royal approval of Don Eduardo Lopez Navarro’s plan May 11, 1883. Concession for the Manila Dagupan line awarded to Don Edmundo Sykes, January 21, 1887, and later transferred to the Manila Railroad Company Ltd. of London. Corner Stone of the main station building at Tutuban laid July 31, 1887. Entire Manila Dagupan line, 195 Kilometers long, completed and service inaugurated November 24, 1892.</p>"},"photo":{"height":2976,"hash":"6f","width":3968,"file":"Historical Marker of the old Tutuban Railway Station.JPG","credit":"Joannerfabregas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"name":"Manila Railroad Company","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97225,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Philippine National Railways":true}},"Q25069494":{"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Battle of Alapan Historical Marker in Alapan Elementary School.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":639,"hash":"2c","height":888},"text":{"title":"Battle of Alapan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this site, on May 28, 1898, between 10:00 A.M. to 3:00 P.M., a bloody encounter ensued between Filipino Revolutionary forces and approximately 270 Spanish Marines, this battle, which resulted in the triumph of Filipino Forces, was taken as a glorious occasion for General Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy to display the Philippine flag for the first time at Cavite Nuevo.</p>"}}},"address":"Alapan I Elementary School, Alapan Street, Imus, Cavite","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Battle of Alapan","lat":14.41572,"date":"1998-05-28","macroAddress":"Imus, Cavite","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the monument of a lady brandishing the Philippine flag on top of a rocky ground with three stars depicting Luzon, Mindanao and Panay.","wikipedia":{"Battle of Alapan":true},"lon":120.91866,"locPhoto":{"height":1920,"hash":"d0","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Battle of Alapan Monument.jpg","width":1371}},"Q28912789":{"lat":11.25056,"date":"1950","macroAddress":"Tacloban","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"John Martin PERRY {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Capitol Building of the Philippines, 1944-1945 historical marker.jpg","width":1067,"height":1600,"hash":"bc"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Capitol Building of the Philippines, 1944–1945","inscription":"<p>On the steps of this Capitol Building of Leyte was formally installed, 23 October 1944, Sergio Osmeña as President of the Commonwealth of the Philippines by Gen. Douglas Mac Arthur in the presence of Cabinet men, Liberation Forces and many other grateful people. Henceforth, until 27 February 1945, this edifice served as the Capitol of the Philippines.</p>"}}},"address":"Leyte Provincial Capitol, Senator Enage Street cor. Magsaysay Boulevard, Tacloban","region":"Eastern Visayas","name":"Capitol Building of the Philippines, 1944–1945","locPhoto":null,"lon":125.00359,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Sergio Osmeña":true}},"Q54578333":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the far right end of the concrete fence of the house.","lon":120.99253,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"4641Elpidio Quirino Avenue Parañaque City Landmarks 05.jpg","height":3456,"hash":"1f"},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Manuel Bernabe y Hernandez","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"251Parañaque City Bridge River Landmarks 42.jpg","hash":"51","height":3456},"text":{"title":"Manuel Bernabe y Hernandez","subtitle":"(1890–1960)","inscription":"<p>Makatang laureado. Ipinanganak sa Parañaque, Rizal, noong Pebrero 17, 1890. Nagtapos ng AB, balediktoryan, Ateneo de Manila, at Batas, Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas. Peryodista ng La Democracia at La Vanguardia. Sumulat ng tulang Cantos del Tropico, kalakip ang kanyang isinaling Rubaiyat of Omar Khayyam, ng Perfil de Cresta at ng himnong No Mas Amor Que el Tuyo. Kongresista, unang purok ng Rizal, 1928 at katulong na tekniko ng pagsasamang Pilipino–Kastila–Amerikano, 1943. Kasapi, Real Academia Española, 1930. Tumanggap ng dekorasyon ng El Yugo y Las Flechas, 1940, at Orden de Isabela la Catolica, 1953, mula sa Espanya. Namatay noong Nobyembre 29, 1960.</p>"}}},"address":"5381 M.H. del Pilar Street cor. Callejon Luna, La Huerta, Parañaque, Metro Manila","lat":14.50121,"macroAddress":"Parañaque, Metro Manila","date":"1983-11-29"},"Q24709070":{"lat":13.82818,"date":"1990","macroAddress":"San Juan, Batangas","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng San Juan","address":"San Juan, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayong yari sa pawid at kawayan sa Pinagbayanan, 1843. Nahiwalay sa Rosario, 1848. Ipinagawa ang simbahang bato ni Padre Damaso Mojica, unang kura paroko sa tulong ng mga Principales ng bayan sa pamumuno ni Gobernadorsilyong si Felipe Salud, 1845. Lumubog sa tubig, 1883. INilipat sa kasalukuyang pook, 1890: at pinasinayaan ang ngayo'y simbahang bato, sa tangkilik ni Padre Celestino Yoldi, Rekoletos, 1894. Pansamantalang pinamahalaan ng mga paring Kaputsino, 1904. Pinalitan ng San Juan de Bocboc ng Bolboc sa pamamagitan ng batas bilang 2390, 1914. Naging San Juan de Nepomuceno ng mga unang taon ng 1920.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng San Juan","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"San Juan Church (Batangas) historical marker.jpg","height":4608,"hash":"20"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.39486,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q56063110":{"address":"Argao Church, J.P. Rizal Street, Argao, Cebu","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating visita ng Carcar at naging hiwalay na parokya sa patronato ni San Miguel Arkanghel, 1733. Padre Ignacio de Olalde, unang kura paroko, 1735–1740. Sa inisyatibo ni Padre Francisco Espina at tulong ng taumbayan, itinayo ang unang simbahan, 1788. Sa pamamahala ni Padre Mateo Perez ipinagawa ang kasalukuyang simbahan, 1803–1836. Kasunod na itinayo ang kampanaryo sa panahon ni Obispo Santos Gomez Marañon, 1830. Nasira ng bagyo ang simbahan at kumbento, 1876. Isinaayos at nilakihan ang simbahan, 1904. Muling isinaayos para sa ika-200 anibersaryo, 1987–1988. Napinsala ng lindol, 2013; kinumpuni, 2016.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Argao"},"photo":null}},"name":"Simbahan ng Argao","region":"Central Visayas","date":"2016-07-11","macroAddress":"Argao, Cebu","lat":9.88194,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Argao Church":true},"lon":123.60815,"locPhoto":null},"Q24189973":{"lon":123.18659,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Holy Rosary Minor Seminary":true},"lat":13.62812,"date":"1988","macroAddress":"Naga, Camarines Sur","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1526,"credit":"Jun Pasa {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Holy Rosary Minor Seminary NCHP Marker.jpg","height":2211,"hash":"48"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Holy Rosary Seminary","inscription":"<p>Dating Casa de Clerigos na itinatag ni Obispo Andres Gonzales, O.P., sirka 1700. Ipinatayo ni Obispo Juan Antonio de Orbigo, O.F.M., ang bagong bahay seminaryo, 1785; Pinanganlang Seminario Conciliar de Nueva Caceres. Pinasinayaan ni Obispo Domingo Collantes, O.P., 1793; Natapos noong 1845. Nasira ng bagyo, 1856; at tinupok ng apoy, 1860. Muling ipinatayo at pinalaki ni Obispo Francisco Gainza, O.P., 1862; Inilipat ang pamamahala sa Vincentian Fathers, 1865. Pinanganlang Seminario del Santisimo Rosario ni Obispo Francisco Reyes, 1925. Bahagyang nasira nang bombahin ng mga sundalong Hapon, 1945, at ipinaayos ni Arsobispo Pedro Santos. Pinanganlang Holy Rosary Seminary sa ilalim ng klerikong Diyosesano, 1964. Malubhang napinsala ng bagyo, ipinaayos ni Arsobispo Teopisto Alberto, 1970. Bukod sa ilang pambansang bayani, mga martir at rebulusyonaryo, 19 sa mga obispo na kasalukuyang nakatalaga sa iba't ibang bahagi ng kapuluan ang katangi-tanging kontribusyon ng seminaryong ito. </p><p> Sa bisa ng kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugna ng mga Kautusan bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974, at bilang 1505, 11 Hunyo 1978, ang seminaryong ito ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"}}},"address":"Holy Rosary Minor Seminary, Elias Angeles Street, Naga, Camarines Sur","region":"Bicol Region","name":"Holy Rosary Seminary"},"Q36151172":{"macroAddress":"Los Baños, Laguna","date":"2014","lat":14.16757,"address":"Church Among the Palms, Jose R. Velasco Avenue, Los Baños, Laguna","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"e2","height":1324,"width":915,"file":"Church among the palms historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"title":"Church Among the Palms","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sinimulang ipangaral ng Iglesia Presbiteriana ang Protestantismo sa College of Agriculture at School of Forestry sa Los Baños, Laguna (ngayo'y University of the Philippines Los Baños), at tinawag na Los Baños College Church, 1911. Kinilala bilang nagsasariling kongregasyon ng Manila Presbytery, 1914. Pinasinayaan ang simbahan, Marso 1917; Rev. Charles R. Hamilton, unang pastor. Sinimulang tawaging Church Among the Palms, mga taong 1928. Sumapi sa United Evangelical Church, 1929, at nang lumaon sa United Church of Christ in the Philippines, 1948. Inilipat sa mga Pilipino ang pamamahala ng simbahan mula 1961.</p>"}}},"name":"Church Among the Palms","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.24037,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q28927495":{"date":"1981","macroAddress":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","lat":8.66735,"address":"Jose Rizal Memorial Protected Landscape, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":4288,"hash":"a2","width":2848,"file":"Visit of Pio Valenzuela historical marker.jpg","credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Noong Hunyo 1896, si Dr. Pio Valenzuela, kilalang kasapi ng Katipunan ay ipinadala sa Dapitan (ngayon ay isang Lungsod sa Zamboanga del Norte) kung saan ipinatapon si Dr. Jose Rizal. Ipinabatid niya sa bayani ang mga balak ng Katipunan subalit tinutulan nito ang isang sandatahang himagsikan sapagkat ito ay “mapaminsala at nagbubunga ng kamatayan.”</p><p> Ipinabatid din ni Valenzuela kay Rizal na binabalak ng mga manghihimagsik na siya ay itakas sa Hapon buhat sa Dapitan na lulan ng isang sasakyang-dagat. Tinanggihan ni Rizal ang alok at nagpayong “para sa kaligtasan ng bayan, hindi na kailangan ang balikan pa ang isang tao lamang.” Sinabi din ni Rizal na “ang mamatay at makalupig ay nakakasiya, subalit ang mamatay at malupig ay napakasakit.”</p><p> Pagkaraang tumigil ng magdamag sa Dapitan, si Valenzuela ay nagbalik sa Maynila at iniulat kay Bonifacio at sa iba pang mga pinuno ng Katipunan ang kinahinatnan ng kanyang misyon.</p>","title":"Ang Pagdalaw ni Valenzuela sa Dapitan","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Ang Pagdalaw ni Valenzuela sa Dapitan","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.41693,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Pío Valenzuela":true,"José Rizal":true,"Katipunan":true,"Philippine Revolution":true}},"Q54337966":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.54797,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lat":10.69221,"macroAddress":"Iloilo City","date":"1973","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3000,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Rosendo Mejica historical marker.JPG","height":4000,"hash":"8f"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa pook na ito ng Molo, Lungsod ng Iloilo noong ika-1 ng Marso 1873. Isa sa mga unang manlilimbag at tagalathala sa Hiligaynon, mamamahayag, edukador. Pinuno ng mga manggagawa at kilalang pilantropo sa lalawigan ng Iloilo. Napatampok bilang dekano ng mga mamamahayag na Bisaya. </p><p>Namatay noong ika-24 ng Pebrero, 1956.</p>","title":"Rosendo Mejica","subtitle":"(1873–1956)"}}},"address":"Lopez Jaena Street, Molo, Iloilo City","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Rosendo Mejica"},"Q55356146":{"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"91","width":4608,"file":"TarlacCityjf4085 01.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"lon":120.5884,"wikipedia":{"Corazon Aquino":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the monument pedestal of Corazon Aquino.","date":"2010","macroAddress":"Tarlac City, Tarlac","lat":15.48713,"name":"Corazon C. Aquino","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Corazon C. Aquino","subtitle":"(1933–2009)","inscription":"<p>Ikalabing-isa at unang babaeng Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas, 1986–1992. Isinilang sa Maynila, 25 Enero 1933. Maybahay ni Senador Benigno “Ninoy” Aquino na pinaslang nang bumalik sa Pilipinas matapos ang tatlong taong pamamalagi sa Estados Unidos upang magpagamot, 21 Agosto 1983. Naging pangulo pagkatapos ng 1986 EDSA People Power Revolution. Pinagtibay ang Saligang Batas ng 1987; Family Code ng 1987; Administrative Code ng 1987; at Local Government Code ng 1991. Nilagdaan ang Comprehensive Agrarian Reform Law, 1988. Nalampasan ang ilang pagtatangkang mapabagsak ang kanyang pamahalaan. Yumao, 1 Agosto 2009.</p>"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Corazon Aquino historical marker in Tarlac City.jpg","hash":"ac","height":4608}}},"address":"P. Burgos Street cor. F. Tañedo Street, Tarlac City, Tarlac"},"Q40319282":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97801,"wikipedia":{"Fernanda Balboa":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":14.58682,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"2002","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Fernanda Balboa","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"6d","height":2273,"file":"Fernanda Balboa historical marker (cropped).jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1607},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Lider sibiko at ina ng batas na nagtatag ng Women’s and Minor’s Bureau. Ipinanganak, 8 Oktubre 1902, kina Marcelino Salcedo at Maria Pilar del Pindo. Nagtatag ng Home for Convalescent Soldiers sa Sampaloc, Maynila at community kitchen sa Antipolo, Rizal, noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Pangulo, League of Women Voters of the Philippines, Inc., 1947-1957. Yumao, Mayo 24, 1999.</p>","title":"Fernanda Balboa","subtitle":"1902–1999"}}},"address":"Muralla Street cor. Gen. Luna Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q47141810":{"name":"Benigno S. Aquino, Jr. “Ninoy”","region":"Central Luzon","address":"Pampanga Provincial Capitol, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Ninoy HistoricalMarker SanFernandoCityPampanga.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":492,"hash":"c9","height":666},"text":{"title":"Benigno S. Aquino, Jr.<br>“Ninoy”","subtitle":"(1932–1983)","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Concepcion, Tarlac, 27 Nobyembre 1932. Cub reporter, The Manila Times, 1949. Correspondent sa Digmaan sa Korea, 1950–1951. Ginawaran ng Philippine Legion of Honor ni Elpidio R. Quirino, 1951; at Pangulong Ramon F. Magsaysay, 1954. Negosyador sa muling pagsailalim sa batas ni Hukbalahap Supremo Luis Taruc, 1954. Punong bayan ng Concepcion, Tarlac, 1955. Pangalawang punong lalawigan ng Tarlac, 1959; punong lalawigan, 1961. Senador, 1967. Ibinilanggo matapos ideklara ang Martial Law ni Pangulong Ferdinand E. Marcos, 23 Setyembre 1972. Hinatulan ng kamatayan ng hukumang militar sa salang subersiyon, ilegal na pag-iingat ng sandata at pagpatay, 1977; pinahintulutang magtungo sa Estados Unidos upang magpagamot. 1980; pinaslang nang bumalik sa Pilipinas, 21 Agosto 1983.</p>"}}},"macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","date":"2009","lat":15.0243,"wikipedia":{"Benigno Aquino, Jr.":"Benigno Aquino Jr."},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.68657},"Q42889907":{"lat":14.88585,"date":"1961","macroAddress":"Plaridel, Bulacan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Simbahan ng Quingua","address":"Santiago Apostol Church, Gov. Padilla Road cor. P. Vergel de Dios Street, Plaridel, Bulacan","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ito ang kauna-unahang simbahang itinayo sa Lumang Bayan ng mga paring Agustino sa pamahala ni Reb. P. Pedro Vasquez nang mga taong 1580–1595. Inilipat dito sa kabayanan noong 1605 sa pamamahala ni Reb. P. Diego Pardo. Muling ipinaayos nang taong 1722. Ang kauna-unahang kura parokong Pilipino ay si Reb. P. Victorino Lopez, na sumama sa kilusan ng Himagsikan, bilang isang pinuno, sa ilalim ni Kapitan Jose Serapio ng Santa Maria. Ang simbahan at kumbento ay ginawang pagamutang hukbo at kuwartel ng mga Amerikano, 1899.</p>","subtitle":"(Plaridel, Bulacan)","title":"Simbahan ng Quingua"},"photo":{"hash":"61","height":4608,"width":3456,"file":"Quinga Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.85978,"wikipedia":{"Santiago Apostol Church":"Santiago Apostol Church (Plaridel)"},"locDesc":null},"Q44503063":{"address":"Binondo Church, Quitin Paredes Road, Binondo, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito itinatag ng mga paring Dominikano ang misyon para sa mga Intsik noong 1587 at naging parokya noong 1596. Nasira nang pumasok ang mga Ingles noong 1762. Inilipat sa paring sekular noong 1769 at ibinalik sa Dominikano noong 1822. Ibinalik sa mga paring sekular noong 1898. Ang simbahan at bagong kumbento ay inayos noong 1946–1971.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Binondo"},"photo":{"height":804,"hash":"62","width":621,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BinondoChurch HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg"}}},"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Binondo","region":"Metro Manila","date":"1971-05-14","macroAddress":"Binondo, Manila","lat":14.59991,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Binondo Church":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97443},"Q51923657":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The first Missionaries of Antipolo were Franciscans. The Jesuits administered the Church from 1591 to 1768. Built by Rev. Juan de Salazar, S.J., the church was ready for Nuestra Señora de la Paz y Buen Viaje in 1632. The church was greatly damaged during the Chinese uprising of 1639 and in the earthquakes of 1645, 1824 and 1863. For three centuries now, this church has been the object of religious pilgrimages all over the Philippines. The famous historians PP. Pedro Chirino, S.J., and Pedro Murillo Velarde, S.J., ministered in Antipolo.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Antipolo"},"photo":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"AntipoloChurchjf5277 05.JPG","hash":"f3","height":3456}}},"address":"Antipolo Cathedral, P. Oliveros Street, Antipolo, Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Church of Antipolo","lat":14.58778,"macroAddress":"Antipolo, Rizal","date":"1937","locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the northern corner of the cathedral facade.","wikipedia":{"Antipolo Cathedral":true},"locPhoto":{"hash":"38","height":4608,"width":3456,"file":"AntipoloChurchjf5277 04.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"lon":121.1764},"Q53637639":{"lat":16.51862,"date":"2011-06-18","macroAddress":"Bayombong, Nueva Vizcaya","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pambansang Bayani ng Pilipinas. Doktor, agrimensor, dalubwika, manunulat, makata, eskultor at pintor. Isinilang sa Calamba, Laguna, 19 Hunyo 1861. May-akda ng Noli me Tangere (1887) at El Filibusterismo (1891), mga nobelang higit pang nagpaalab sa mga Filipino na maghimagsik laban sa Espanya. Dinakip at ipinatapon sa Dapitan, Hilagang Mindanao, 6 Hulyo 1892. Nagboluntaryo bilang manggagamot ng puwersang Espanyol sa Cuba, 1896, nguni’t muling dinakip habang patungong Espanya sa bintang rebelyon. Binaril sa Bagumbayan (ngayo’y Liwasang Rizal), Maynila, 30 Disyembre 1896. Patuloy na inspirasyon para sa kalayaan at pagkabansang Filipino.</p>","title":"Jose Rizal","subtitle":"(1861–1896)"},"photo":null}},"address":"Bangan Hill National Park, Brgy. Casat, Bayombong, Nueva Vizcaya","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Jose Rizal","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.14171,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true}},"Q41760038":{"locPhoto":{"height":2592,"hash":"02","file":"IJVTanayChurch4.jpg","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3872},"lon":121.28475,"wikipedia":{"Tanay Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the right corner buttress of the church facade.","date":"1939","macroAddress":"Tanay, Rizal","lat":14.49849,"name":"Church of Tanay","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3039,"hash":"3a","width":3000,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Tanay historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Tanay","inscription":"<p>The ecclesiastical administration of Tanay belonged to Pililla up to 1606 when the first church was built. The town moved to San Antonio in 1620 but was transferred to this site in 1640. The present Church was completed in 1783.</p>"}}},"address":"Tanay Church, M. H. Del Pilar Street, Tanay, Rizal"},"Q47069817":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Pampanga":true},"lon":120.68726,"locPhoto":null,"address":"Governor Macario Arnedo Park, Capitol Boulevard, San Fernando, Pampanga","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"34","height":4608,"file":"PampangaProvincialCapitoljf56.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pinanahanan ng mga Indo–Malayo ang dakong itaas na pampang, ang pook ay ginalugad ng mga paring Agustino noong 1571. Naging encomienda noong 1576. Dahil pinakamaunlad, pinakamaganda at pinakamasagana, ito ay naging tagatustos ng bigas noong panahon ng Kastila. Nag-alsa laban sa pagmamamlupit ng mga Kastila, minsan noong ika-16 na dantaon at tatlong ulit noong ika-17 dantaon. Ang mga Pampango ay pinangunahan ni Francisco Maniago sa isang nasasandatahang pag-aalsa laban sa sapilitang paggawa at labis-labis na pagpataw ng buwis. Isinalin ang 8 bayan nito sa Bataan, 5 sa Nuweba Esiha at 4 sa Tarlak (na ibinalik pagkaraan). Ang Bakolor ay naging kabisera ng Pilipinas sa ilalim ng Espanya noong 1762–64. Noong panahon ng Amerikano, ang unang pamahalaang sibil ay itinatag sa lalawigan na binubuo ng 22 bayan noong Pebrero 13, 1901. Ang San Fernando ay naging kabisera noong 1904. Masidhing pakikipaglaban ng mga Pampango sa Hapon ang naranasan noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Ang pinakamalaking himpilan ng Hukbong Panghimpapawid ng Amerika sa Asya ay matatapuan sa Lungsod ng Angeles.</p>","title":"Lalawigan ng Pampanga","subtitle":null}}},"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Lalawigan ng Pampanga","lat":15.02431,"date":"1982-12-11","macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga"},"Q41141358":{"lat":14.45962,"date":"1956","macroAddress":"Bacoor, Cavite","address":"Cuenca Ancestral House, Bacoor, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa tahanang ito ng mag-asawang Juan Cuenca at Candida Chaves inilipat ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo ang Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo buhat sa bayan ng Kabite noong ika-15 ng Hulyo, 1898, upang malapit sa mga kalaban sa Maynila. Nanatili rito hanggang sa malipat sa Malolos, Bulakan noong ika-10 ng Setyembre 1898 noong ika-23 ng Enero 1899 ay itinatag doon ang Unang Republika Pilipina.</p>","subtitle":"Bakoor, Kabite","title":"Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo"},"photo":{"file":"Cuenca Ancestral House Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2047,"height":2728,"hash":"7d"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo","lon":120.94281,"locPhoto":{"height":3024,"hash":"d7","width":4032,"file":"Cuenca Ancestral House.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the northern main door of the house.","wikipedia":{"Philippine Revolution":true}},"Q54858021":{"name":"Pagdaong sa Talisay","region":"Central Visayas","address":"Talisay, Cebu","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pagdaong sa Talisay","inscription":"<p>Dito dumaong ang Americal Division ng U.S. 8<sup>th</sup> Army na pinamunuan nina Com. Gen. William H. Arnold at Capt. Albert T. Sprague, sa tulong ng mga Filipinong gerilya ng 8<sup>th</sup> Military District sa pangunguna ni Lt. Col. James M. Cushing, 26 Marso 1945. Ang pagdaong ay bahagi ng Operasyong Victor II na ipinatupad ni Gen. Douglas MacArthur upang mabawi ang mga lalawigan ng Cebu, Bohol at Negros. Ito ay nagbigay-daan sa paglaya ng Lungsod ng Cebu, 27 Marso 1945; at pagsuko ng mga Hapones sa lalawigan, 28 Agosto 1945.</p>"},"photo":null}},"date":"2009","macroAddress":"Talisay, Cebu","lat":10.24198,"wikipedia":{"Battle for Cebu City":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":123.84883,"locPhoto":null},"Q28942530":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.01664,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"First Battle of Bud Dajo":true},"macroAddress":"Jolo, Sulu","date":"2004","lat":6.05122,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Labanan sa pagitan ng mga Muslim at hukbong Amerikano mula 6 Marso hanggang 8 Marso 1906, bilang pagtutol ng mga Muslim sa pamamalakad at pagpataw ng buwis ng mga Amerikano. Nang matapos ang labanan, may isang libong mandirigmang Muslim ang napatay kabilang ang mga babae at bata samantalang 21 ang napatay sa panig ng mga Amerikano. Dito nagtapos ang serye ng mga labnana na nagsimula noong 1903 sa pamumuno ni Panglima Hassan, pagpapatunay ng pagmamahal ng mga Muslim sa kalayaan.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa Bud Dajo"},"photo":null}},"address":"Capitol Site, Jolo, Sulu","name":"Labanan sa Bud Dajo","region":"Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao"},"Q56149343":{"lat":14.59733,"date":"2018-08-14","macroAddress":"Binondo, Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Gusaling Calvo","inscription":"<p>Itinayo ayon sa disenyo ni Fernando Ocampo sa lupang pag-aari ng mag-asawang Angel Calvo at Emiliana Mortera, 1938. Naging opisina ng mga kumpanyang pangnegosyo at pangkabuhayan, 1938–1944. Pansamantalang ginamit ng Japanese Imperial Forces, Nobyembre 1944. Nasira noong Labanan sa Maynila, 1945. Ipinaayos, 1946. Itinatag ang Museo ng Gusaling Calvo sa ikalawang palapag, 1994. Isa sa mga nananatiling gusaling itinayo noong mga unang bahagi ng siglo 20 sa Daang Escolta.</p>"}}},"address":"Calvo Building, 266 Escolta Street, Binondo, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Gusaling Calvo","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97808,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Calvo Building":true}},"Q54086892":{"name":"Concordia College for Girls","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Concordia College, 1739 Pedro Gil Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":null,"inscription":"<p>Concordia College for Girls founded in 1868 by Da. Margarita Roxas de Ayala on her La Concordia estate and administered by the Sisters of Charity.</p>"},"photo":{"height":480,"hash":"61","width":640,"file":"Concordia College Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"date":"1934","macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","lat":14.58119,"wikipedia":{"Concordia College":"Concordia College (Manila)"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.00257},"Q55774782":{"wikipedia":{"José Cojuangco":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.81265,"name":"Jose C. Cojuangco","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1896–1976)","title":"Jose C. Cojuangco","inscription":"<p>Mambabatas at mangangalakal. Isinilang sa Malolos, Bulacan, 3 Hulyo 1896. Nagtapos ng abogasya sa Escuela de Derecho, ngayo’y Manila Law College, 1920. Konsehal ng Paniqui, Tarlac, 1922–1925. Kinatawan ng Tarlac sa Lehislatura ng Pilipinas, 1934–1947. Nagtatag at naging tagapangulo ng Philippine Bank of Commerce, 1938. Tumanggap ng American Medal for Freedom mula kay Presidente Harry S. Truman para sa kanyang konstribusyon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 16 Agosto 1947. Pinangasiwaan ang Hacienda Luisita, 1959–1976. Yumao sa bayan ng Tarlac, 21 Agosto 1976.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"df","height":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Jose Cojuangco historical marker at his house in Malolos, Bulacan.jpg","width":3456}}},"address":"540 Paseo del Congreso, Malolos, Bulacan","macroAddress":"Malolos, Bulacan","date":"2008","lat":14.84501},"Q22341197":{"lat":14.38101,"macroAddress":"Pakil, Laguna","date":"1988","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang unang pamayanan ni San Pedro Bautista, O.F.M., 1588. Naging baryo ng Paete, 1602; Naging bayan, 1676 at hinirang na unang kapitan si Diego Jorge. Ipinatayo ang casa tribunal at unang paaralang bayan, 1800. Ibinalik sa pagiging baryo ng Paete, Oktubre 12, 1903 at inilipat sa pagiging baryo ng Pangil, Nobyembre 25, 1903. Mula ng mapaanib ang bayang ito sa Pangil, apat na taga-Pakil ang naging Presidente Municipal. Naging ganap na bayan, Oktubre 1, 1927 sa Bisa ng Utos Pampangasiwaan bilang 77, Setyembre 9, 1927, na sinusugan ng Utos Pampangasiwaan bilang 91. Disyembre 5, 1927. Nang panahon ng pananakop ng mga Hapon, ang mamamayan ng bayang ito ay buong giting na nakipaglaban. Lumaya, Abril 5, 1945.</p>","title":"Ang Bayan ng Pakil","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":3120,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical marker of Pakil.jpg","height":4160,"hash":"3b"}}},"address":"Pakil Municipal Hall, Pakil, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ang Bayan ng Pakil","locPhoto":{"hash":"6f","height":4608,"width":3456,"file":"Pakil,Lagunajf6670 20.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"lon":121.47871,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the left side of the main entrance of the municipal hall.","wikipedia":{"Pakil":"Pakil, Laguna"}},"Q55711022":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97094,"name":"Mababang Paaralang Pedro Guevara","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng pamahalaang militar ng Amerika noong 1898 bilang isa sa mga unang paaralang primarya sa Maynila. Naging unang mga guro nito ang mga sundalong Amerikano. Matatagpuan sa kinatatayuan ng mga komisaryo na dating pamilihan ng mga seda na buhat sa Tsina. Ang Alcaiceria de San Ferando. Nakilala bilang Paaralang Primarya ng San Nicolas. Si Dr. Walter William Marquardt ang naging unang superbisor nito at si Tranquilino Buenaventura naman ang unang Filipinong punong-guro. Itinayo ang Paaralang Intermedya ng San Nicolas noong Hunyo 1917. Pinagsama ang mga paaralang primarya at intermedya at kinilala bilang Paaralang Elementarya ng San Nicolas noong 1930. Binigyan ng bagong pangalang Mababang Paaralang Pedro Guevara noong 1938. Ang pangunahing gusali ay ginawang garison ng mga Hapon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Ipinaayos at nagpatayo ng mga bagong gusali pagkaraan ng digmaan.</p>","title":"Mababang Paaralang Pedro Guevara","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Pedro Guevara Elementary School, San Fernando Street cor. Numancia Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila","macroAddress":"San Nicolas, Manila","date":"1998-09-01","lat":14.59758},"Q23927292":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"Magalhães","file":"Basilica Minore del Santo Niño entrances and historical marker.jpg","width":1355,"hash":"f9","height":893},"lon":123.90215,"wikipedia":{"Minor Basilica of the Holy Child":"Basilica del Santo Niño"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the entrance to the convent which is located to the left of the main entrance of the basilica.","macroAddress":"Cebu City","date":"1941","lat":10.29424,"name":"Church and Convent of Santo Niño","region":"Central Visayas","address":"Minor Basilica of the Holy Child, Osmeña Boulevard, Cebu City","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The Church and Convent erected by the Augustinian Fathers under the Rev. Andres Urdaneta in 1565 were the first established in the Philippines. Both were burned down on November 1, 1566. The second Church was likewise destroyed by fire in March of 1628, but rebuilt soon after (1628–1629) under the administration of the historian Rev. Juan de Medina, O.S.A. The present massive Church was designed and constructed during the Priorship of Rev. Juan Albarran O.S.A., (1735–1737). The Santo Niño, venerated in this Church since the time of Legaspi, is the center of intense devotion and religious pilgrimages through out the Visayas.</p>","title":"Church and Convent of Santo Niño","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"3e","height":2300,"width":2229,"file":"Church and Convent of Santo Niño historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Nickrds09; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY 3.0}"}}}},"Q41646542":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Bayan ng Obando","inscription":"<p>Unang nakilala sa tawag na Baryo Catangalan sakop ng Meycawayan. Naging sakop ng Polo nang ang huli ay humiwalay sa Meycawayan noong 1623. Naging bayan ng Obando noong Mayo 14, 1753, sa bisa ng kautusang inilagda ni Gobernador Heneral Jose Francisco de Obando y Solis. Lubusang nahiwalay sa bayan ng Polo noong 1754 nang sang-ayunan ang pagiging bayan nito nina Francisco Morales y Mozarabe, gobernador ng Lalawigang Bulakan at Kamahal-mahalang Reberendo Alejandro Ferrer, ministrong panlalawigan. Si Padre Manuel de Olivencia ang unang kura paroko at si Diego San Diego ang naging unang alkalde. Ang kapistahan ay tuwing ika 17–18 ng Mayo.</p>"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Ang Bayan ng Obando Historical marker.jpg","hash":"33","height":4608}}},"address":"J. P. Rizal Street, Obando, Bulacan","name":"Ang Bayan ng Obando","region":"Central Luzon","macroAddress":"Obando, Bulacan","date":"1973-05-19","lat":14.70934,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the concrete pedestal commemorating the Obando Fertility Dance Festival in front of Obando Municipal Hall.","wikipedia":{"Obando":"Obando, Bulacan"},"lon":120.9373,"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Fertilityobandojf.JPG","hash":"05","height":3456}},"Q55088727":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Central Philippine University":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.54923,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":2048,"hash":"8b","credit":"Inaudita {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Central Philippine University Plaque.JPG","width":1536},"text":{"subtitle":"(1905–1980)","title":"Central Philippine University","inscription":"<p>Dating <u>Jaro Industrial School</u> na itinatag noong 1905 ng <u>American Baptist Foreign Mission Society</u> sa pangunguna ni Dr. William O. Valentine, ang unang naging punong-guro.</p><p>Ito ang unang paaralan sa Pilipinas na ang mag-aaral ay nagtrabaho para sa kanilang edukasyon. Nagtatag ng unang pamahalaan ng mga mag-aaral sa bansa noong 1906.</p><p>Naging <u>Central Philippine College</u> noong 1923 at pamantasan noong 1953.</p><p>Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Muling binuksan matapos palayain ang Lungsod ng Iloilo noong 1945.</p><p>Si Dr. Rex D. Drilon ang naging unang Pilipinong pangulo noong 1966. Noong 1969 ipinagkaloob sa mga Pilipino ng mga <u>American Baptist Foreign Mission Society</u> ang buong ari-arian ng pamantasan.</p>"}}},"address":"Central Philippine University, Jaro, Iloilo City","name":"Central Philippine University","region":"Western Visayas","date":"1980-09-19","macroAddress":"Iloilo City","lat":10.73149},"Q55842725":{"name":"Heneral Martin Teofilo Delgado","region":"Western Visayas","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1858–1918)","title":"Heneral Martin Teofilo Delgado","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa bayang ito noong Nobyembre 11, 1858. Nag-aral sa paaralang pambayan ng Sta. Barbara at sa <u>Ateneo Municipal de Manila</u>.</p><p> Naging pangkalahatang puno ng mga rebolusyonaryo sa Kabisayaan at Mindanaw noong Himagsikan ng 1898 at noong Digmaang Pilipino–Amerikano, 1899–1901.</p><p> Sumuko sa mga Amerikano noong Pebrero 1901 matapos makipaglaban nang buong kagitingan. Kauna-unahang gobernador ng Iloilo noong panahon ng mga Amerikano (1901–1903). Naging alkalde ng Sta. Barbara noong (1905–1906).</p><p> Namatay noong Nobyembre 12, 1918.</p>"}}},"address":"Santa Barbara Park, Magalona Street, Santa Barbara, Iloilo","date":"1973","macroAddress":"Santa Barbara, Iloilo","lat":10.82701,"wikipedia":{"Martin Teofilo Delgado":"Martín Teófilo Delgado"},"locDesc":null,"lon":122.53182,"locPhoto":null},"Q36172984":{"date":"1960","macroAddress":"San Nicolas, Manila","lat":14.59888,"name":"Ang Tahanan ng Kaanak ni Rizal","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":500,"hash":"51","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Ang Tahanan ng Kaanak ni Rizal 1903 Daang San Fernando, Maynila.jpg","width":279},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Si Teodora Alonzo, ina ni Rizal, ay namatay noong ika-16 ng Agosto ng 1911 sa isang bahay na nakatayo sa pook na ito (ngayo'y Blg. 476-478) at ari ni Gng. Luisa Lichauco.</p>","title":"Ang Tahanan ng Kaanak ni Rizal","subtitle":"1903 Daang San Fernando, Maynila"}}},"address":"San Fernando Street, San Nicolas, Manila, Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97236,"wikipedia":{"Teodora Alonzo":"Teodora Alonso Realonda"},"locDesc":null},"Q54555769":{"lon":120.97033,"locPhoto":{"file":"WTMP DinoBrinas DSC 0032.jpeg","credit":"Dino Briñas (Wikipedia Takes Manila participant) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4310,"hash":"9d","height":2868},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a granite mounting on the southeastern side of the roundabout facing towards the general direction of Juan Luna Street.","lat":14.62716,"date":"1984-09-06","macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Vicente L. del Fierro","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"JoRitchChT (Wikipedia Takes Manila participant) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Vicente L. Del Fierro historical marker at the Gagalangin Circle in Manila.jpg","width":2048,"height":1536,"hash":"b4"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1903–1960)","title":"Vicente L. del Fierro","inscription":"<p>Tinaguriang “Del Fire”—isang haligi at tagapagtanggol ng kalayaan ng pamamahayag sa Pilipinas. Ipinanganak noong Disyembre 15, 1903 sa Castillejos, Zambales, at nanirahan ng 30 taon sa Gagalangin, Tondo, Maynila. Nagtapos ng A.B. Journalism sa Pamantasan ng Pilipinas, 1924. Patnugot, Philippine Collegian; mamahayag, Tribune at Philippines Herald; unang patnugot, Herald Mid-Week Magazine at Monday Mail; at tagalathala at patnugot, Zambales Reporter at Star Reporter. Pinagkalooban ng National Press Club ng Gawad ng Katangitanging Paglilingkod sa Pamamahayag, 1958. Namatay noong 28 Agosto 1960.</p>"}}},"address":"Plaza Vicente del Fierro, Vicente del Fierro Street, Gagalangin, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q54888960":{"region":"Western Visayas","name":"Birthplace of Manuel Acuña Roxas","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>On this site of this town Capiz, was born President Manuel A. Roxas, 1 January 1892. Fiery orator, dignified statesman, realistic economist, and true patriot. Third son of Gerardo Roxas and Rosario Acuña. Became a lawyer in 1913; town concilor, 1917; provincial governor, 1919; Speaker, House of Representatives, 1922–1934; Secretary of Finance, 1938; President, Philippine Senate, 1945–1946; last President of the Commonwealth and first President of the Republic of the Philippines, 1946–1948. Died of heart attack after an impassioned speech in defense of democracy at Clark Field, Pampanga, as guest of Major General Eugene L. Eubank, C.G., U.S.A. 13th Airforce, 15 April 1948.</p>","title":"Birthplace of Manuel Acuña Roxas","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Roxas Avenue cor. Zamora Street, Roxas, Capiz","lat":11.58295,"date":"1958","macroAddress":"Roxas, Capiz","wikipedia":{"Manuel Roxas":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":122.74982,"locPhoto":null},"Q55002863":{"macroAddress":"Corcuera, Romblon","date":"1983-04-30","lat":12.78412,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ama ng Local Autonomy Bill. Ipinanganak noong Setyembre 13, 1893 sa Capiz (Roxas City), Capiz. Nagtamo ng A.B., balediktoryan, sa Instituto Filipino, 1911, at LL.B. sa Escuela de Derecho (Manila Law College), 1918. Hukom ng Jones, Romblon, 1918–1920; Gobernador ng Romblon, 1928–1934; Kinatawan sa Konstitusyonal Kumbensyon at kagawad sa Executive Power Committee, 1935; at hukom ng mga Hukumang Pampurok ng Jones–Corcuera–Concepcion, 1939–1958. Tumulong para matatag ang Corcuera, 1931, at ng Magdiwang, 1933. Namatay noong Pebrero 1, 1973.</p>","subtitle":"(1893–1973)","title":"Manuel T. Albero y Azores"}}},"address":"Corcuera Municipal Hall, J. Fajilago Street, Poblacion, Corcuera, Romblon","name":"Manuel T. Albero y Azores","region":"Mimaropa","lon":122.04752,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q55346594":{"locPhoto":{"width":4608,"file":"AmadeoChurchjf0160 04.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"3c","height":3456},"lon":120.9217,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete wall at the devotional area, immediately outside the right side of the church.","lat":14.17012,"macroAddress":"Amadeo, Cavite","date":"1984","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Parokya ni Santa Maria Magdalena","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"AmadeoChurchjf0160 07.JPG","width":3456,"hash":"68","height":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Inihiwalay sa Silang ni Arsobispo Pedro Payo, O.P. noong Mayo 1, 1884 ang Parokya ng Amadeo sa ilalim ng patronato ni Sta. Maria Magdalena. Naging unang kura paroko si P. Inocencio Honorio ng Bulakan. Ipinatayo ang simbahang bato ni P. Agapito Ichogoyen noong 1889. Nagsilbing bilangguan ng mga gerilya na kung saan 19 sa kanila ang pinatay ng mga Hapon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Pinalaki ni P. Eugenio Marcelo noong 1954 at binasbasan ni Arsobispo Rufino D. Santos noong Abril 19, 1959. Ipinagdiwang ang ikasandaang taon ng parokya at bayan ngayong 1984.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Parokya ni Santa Maria Magdalena"}}},"address":"Saint Mary Magdalene Church, A. Mabini Street cor. G. Bayot Street, Amadeo, Cavite"},"Q23935031":{"date":"1954","macroAddress":"Santa Ana, Manila","lat":14.58175,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":1996,"hash":"09","file":"Felipe G. Calderon historical marker.jpg","credit":"Zernan2014 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1385},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Felipe G. Calderon","inscription":"<p>Pedagogue, lawyer, writer, scholar and patriot. Drafted the Constitution of the first Philippine Republic. Founder of the Colegio de Abogados de Filipinas and the Escuela de Derecho de Manila, 1899. First president, Asociacion de Tagalistas, 1904. Organizer, Asociacion Historica de Filipinas, 1905. Son of Jose Gonzales Calderon and Manuela Roca born 4 April 1868 in (Santa Cruz de Malabon) Tanza, Cavite. Lived in the district of Santa Ana. Died 6 June 1908.</p>"}}},"address":"Plaza Calderon, Pedro Gil Street, Santa Ana, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Felipe G. Calderon","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"height":4288,"hash":"88","width":2848,"credit":"Zernan2014 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Plaza Calderon, Sta Ana Manila.jpg"},"lon":121.01288,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located beneath a bust of Felipe G. Calderon near the eastern end of Plaza Calderon facing the Santa Ana Church.","wikipedia":{"Felipe Calderón":"Felipe Calderón (Filipino politician)"}},"Q43360070":{"locPhoto":{"width":1425,"credit":"Raani Paranas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Baguio City Hall, a heritage site.JPG","height":1900,"hash":"3f"},"lon":120.5915,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the second column from the left of the building facade.","wikipedia":null,"date":"2009-09-02","macroAddress":"Baguio","lat":16.41376,"address":"Baguio City Hall, City Hall Drive, Baguio","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3935,"hash":"96","width":3038,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Baguio City Hall NHCP Historical Marker.png"},"text":{"title":"Baguio City Hall","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo na yari sa kahoy at yero noong panunungkulan ni E.W. Reynolds, unang punong lungsod, 1910. Sentro ng pamahaalang lokal sa pagtataguyod ng Baguio bilang Summer Capital ng Pilipinas. Sergio Bayan, unang Filipinong punong lungsod, 1937–1939. Dito itinaas ang watawat ng bansang Hapon tanda ng pagsakop sa lungsod, 27 Disyembre 1941. Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1945. Muling ipinatayo na yari sa konkreto, 1949–1950. Pinasinayaan ni Pangulong Elpidio Quirino, Mayo 1950. Ipinaayos, 1997–1999. Pinasinayaan, 15 Pebrero 1999.</p>"}}},"name":"Baguio City Hall","region":"Cordillera Administrative Region"},"Q50085885":{"lon":120.59592,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Corregidor":true},"lat":14.46244,"date":"1977","macroAddress":"Mariveles, Bataan","address":"Bataan Provincial Highway cor. Cabcaben Road, Brgy. Townsite, Mariveles, Bataan","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Cabcaben","subtitle":"Mariveles, Bataan","inscription":"<p>Ang limang buwang walang humpay na pagsalakay ng ma Hapon sa Hukbong Pilipino–Amerikano noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig ay nagwakas sa isang bahay sa lupang ito sa ganap na ika-5 ng hapon, Mayo 6, 1942 nang bumagsak ang Korehidor at sumuko si Tenyente-Heneral Jonathan M. Wainright ng USAFFE kay Tenyente-General Masaharu Homma, puno ng ika-14 na pangkat ng Hukbong Hapon.</p>"}}},"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Cabcaben"},"Q28933375":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.60974,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Makahambus Hill":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"2000-06-07","macroAddress":"Cagayan de Oro","lat":8.37887,"name":"Labanan sa Burol ng Makahambus","region":"Northern Mindanao","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa Burol ng Makahambus","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito, Hunyo 4, 1900, ang hukbong panghimagsikan ng batalyong Mindanao sa pangunguna ni Tenyente Cruz Taal na nasa ilalim ng pamumuno ni Kol. Apolinar Velez y Ramos ay nagwagi sa kanilang madugong pakikipaglaban sa mga sundalong Amerikano na kabilang sa ika-40 impanteryang pinamumunuan ni Kapitan Thomas Miller at ng dagdag na pangkat na pinangungunahan ni Kapitan Walter B. Elliot. Ang pagkatalong ito ng mga Amerikano sa labanan sa Makahambus ay bunga ng mahusay na pamamaraan at disiplina sa sarili ng mga nagtantanggol na mga rebolusyonaryong Pilipino. Umani ang mga Pilipino ng paghanga mula sa mga Amerikano, dahil sa kanilang ginawang pakikitungo sa mga bihag ng digma.</p>"}}},"address":"Macahambus Cave, Cagayan de Oro"},"Q52170111":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2592,"file":"Sabtang Church 04.JPG","credit":"KisekiLacroix {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"2d","height":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo bilang kapilya ng mga Dominikano, 1785. Napabayaan nang sapilitang pinalipat ang mga mamamayan sa Ivana matapos ang pag-aaklas ni Aman Dangat, 1791. Ginawa sa apog at bato sa ilalim ni P. Antonio Vicente, O.P., 1844. Ipinaayos ni P. Gumersindo Hernandez, O.P. ang kampanaryo matapos masira ng bagyo, 1956. Isinaayos ang loob ng simbahan ni P. Rafael Carpintero, O.P., 1983–1984.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Sabtang","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Sabtang Church, National Road, Sabtang, Batanes","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Simbahan ng Sabtang","lat":20.33446,"date":"2008","macroAddress":"Sabtang, Batanes","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Sabtang Church":true},"lon":121.87241,"locPhoto":null},"Q54878361":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang bisita ng Carcar ng mga Agustino noong 1599. Naging isang nagsasariling parokya sa pagtatangkilik ng Nuestra Señora de Patrocinio, 1690. Inilipat sa pamamahala ng mga Heswita, 1737; ibinalik sa mga Agustino, 1747. Natupok ng apoy ang unang simbahang gawa ng mga Agustino, 1782; ipinatayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan ni Padre Ambrosio Otero, OSA, 1783; ipinagpatuloy ni Padre Manuel Cordero, OSA, 1794; ganap na natapos sa panahon ng panunungkulan ni Padre Leandro Moran, OSA, 1920–1948. Napasailalim sa pamamahala ng mga sekular noong mga sumunod na taon. </p><p>Ipinahayag na isang Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan, Disyembre 15, 1999 sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974 at Bilang 1505, Hulyo 11, 1978.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Boljoon","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"1d","height":5312,"file":"Plaque on Boljoon Church -1599 Augustinians.jpg","credit":"Jessicashawledesma {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2988}}},"address":"Boljoon Church, Cebu South Road, Boljoon, Cebu","name":"Simbahan ng Boljoon","region":"Central Visayas","date":"2000-06-25","macroAddress":"Boljoon, Cebu","lat":9.63001,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Boljoon Church":true},"lon":123.47976,"locPhoto":null},"Q24702493":{"lon":121.59183,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"date":"1988-09-20","macroAddress":"Tayabas, Quezon","lat":14.02578,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Kilalang Casa Tribunal na ipinatayong yari sa mahihinang kagamitan ni Gobernadorsilyo Francisco Lopez, 1776; nagsilbing bulwagang pambayan at bahay tuluyan ng mga manlalakbay. Muling ipinatayong yari sa bato ni Gobernadorsilyo Diego Enriquez, 1831; pinasinayaan at pinanganlang Casa de Comunidad, 1835; natapos at pinalamutian ng mga magagandang dekorasyon at mamahaling kasangkapan ni Gobernador de La O, 1855 at nasunog, 1877. Binalak na muling ipatayo bilang ayuntamiento, 1890, ngunit hindi naisakatuparan sa kakulangan ng pundo. Ginawang paaralang sentral noong panahon ng mga Amerikano at muling nasunog noong panahon ng pagpapalaya, 1945, sa mga naiwang pader sinimulan ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan ang huling pagpapaayos ng dati’y isa sa pinakamagandang tribunal sa buong kapuluan.</p><p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan Bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974, at 1505, 11 Hunyo 1978, ang gusaling ito ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan.</p>","title":"Casa de Comunidad de Tayabas","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":3216,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Casa Comunidad de Tayabas historical marker.jpg","height":4812,"hash":"bf"}}},"address":"Casa Comunidad of Tayabas, Gen. Antonio Luna Street cor. J.P. Rizal Street, Tayabas, Quezon","name":"Casa de Comunidad de Tayabas","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q55506318":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.83984,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"date":"2014","macroAddress":"Boac, Marinduque","lat":13.44608,"name":"Tanda ng Ika-Sandaang Taong Pagkakatatag","region":"Mimaropa","address":"Marinduque National High School, Boac, Marinduque","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Tanda ng Ika-Sandaang Taong Pagkakatatag","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Nagsimula bilang Boac High School, 1913. Nanguna sa pagtataguyod ng sekondaryang edukasyon sa Marinduque. Kalauna’y tinawag na Marinduque High School at Marinduque Provincial High School. Nagsilbing garison ng mga Hapon. Sinunog ng mga gerilya at mga sundalong Amerikano noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Naging Marinduque National High School, 1982.</p>"},"photo":null}}},"Q24927356":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.92351,"wikipedia":{"Baldomero Aguinaldo Shrine":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"1983-06-12","macroAddress":"Kawit, Cavite","lat":14.44774,"name":"Ang Bahay ni Heneral Baldomero Aguinaldo","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"19","height":889,"width":1014,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Baldomero Aguinaldo House Marker 1.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Bahay ni Heneral Baldomero Aguinaldo","inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na ito na ipinatayo noong 1906 nanirahan si Heneral Baldomero Aguinaldo at kanyang mag-anak. Unang ipinatayo na yari sa narra at molave, ang bahay ay pinanumbalik ng Intramuros Administration. Noong 1982 ito ay ipinagkaloob ng Punong Ministro Cesar E.A. Virata sa Pamahalaan ng Pilipinas.</p>"}}},"address":"Baldomero Aguinaldo Shrine, Bisita Street, Kawit, Cavite"},"Q41217073":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":450,"credit":"Eric Jam {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Anastacia Giron Tupas Marker 1.JPG","height":600,"hash":"a6"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1890–1972)","title":"Anastacia Giron–Tupas","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Laoag, Ilocos Norte, Agosto 26, 1890. Rehistradong Nars, PGH, 1912. Nagtamo ng Certificate of Public Nursing, University of Pennsylvania, at B.S.E., M.S. (Edukasyon) at M.A. (Narsing), U.P. Unang Pilipinong punong nars at superintendente, PGH School of Nursing, 1917–1923. Nagtatag at unang superintendente, Southern Island Hospital School of Nursing (Lungsod ng Cebu), 1919–1928. Pangulo ng komiteng tagabalangkas ng Batas 2808 ng Narsing, 1919. Nanguna, Philippine Nurses Association (PNA), 1922. Nagtatag at unang direktor, U.P. School of Public Health Nursing. Puno at pagkaraan dekana emeritus, PWU College of Nursing. May-akda ng The History of Nursing in the Philippines, 1952. Tumanggap ng Pinakatanging Gawad, Philippine Association of Board of Examiners, 1951; Presidential Medal of Merit, 1959; at postumong gawad ng PNA bilang tagapagtatag nito at bilang “Dekana ng Narsing sa Pilipinas,” 1981. Sa kanyang ala-ala, ang “Outstanding Achievement Award” ng PNA ay pinanganlang “Anastacia Giron Tupas Award” noong 1975. Namatay, Setyembre 28, 1972.</p>"}}},"address":"Tupas Street, Laoag, Ilocos Norte","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Anastacia Giron–Tupas","lat":18.19448,"macroAddress":"Laoag, Ilocos Norte","date":"1985","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":120.59211,"locPhoto":null},"Q41657997":{"name":"Bulacan Military Area","region":"Central Luzon","address":"Gen. Alejo G. Santos Highway, Poblacion, Bustos, Bulacan","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BMA HistoricalMarker Bustos.jpg","width":465,"hash":"8b","height":681},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Binuo sa ilalim ng East Central Luzon Guerilla Area (ECLGA) ang Bulacan Military District mula sa apat na rehimento ng puwersang gerilya na kumakatawan sa lalawigan ng Bulacan sa utos ni Maj. Edwin P. Ramsey, 14 Setyembre 1943. Capt. Alejo S. Santos, District Commander. Pinangalanang Bulacan Military Area ni Capt. Bernard L. Anderson ng USAFFE Luzon Guerilla Armed Forces, 21 Disyembre 1943. Ang apat na rehimento ng BMA ay naging sampung rehimento, 1944. Tumulong sa pakikipaglaban sa puwersang Hapon sa mga lalawigan ng Nueva Vizcaya, Pangasinan, Pampanga, Ifugao, at Rizal. Nakipaglaban sa mga Hapones hanggang mapalaya sa mga Hapon ang lalawigan ng Bulacan, Hulyo 1945.</p>","title":"Bulacan Military Area","subtitle":null}}},"date":"2012-08-02","macroAddress":"Bustos, Bulacan","lat":14.95277,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.91839},"Q35007957":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":124.36982,"locPhoto":null,"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Jagna","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Heswita sa patronato ni San Miguel Arkanghel, 1631. Inilipat sa pamamahala ng mga Rekoleto, 1768. Sinimulang ipatayo ang simbahang bato ni Fray Felix Blas de las Mercedes, 1808; natapos 1867. Pinangasiwaan ng mga paring sekular, 1868. Nakaligtas ang simbahan at kumbento matapos sunugin ng puwersang Amerikano ang bayan ng Jagna, 1901. Isinagawa ni Ray Francia ang mga larawan sa kisame ng simbahan, dekada 1920 at 1930. Isinaayos ang simbahan, 1968. Nasira ng lindol, 8 Pebrero 1990.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Jagna"}}},"address":"Jagna Church, Jagna, Bohol","lat":9.65218,"macroAddress":"Jagna, Bohol","date":"2015"},"Q41081703":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Gates of Intramuros":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97224,"address":"Postigo Street cor. Sta. Lucia Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Pintong Postigo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2500,"hash":"4f","height":4014},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ito ang ikatlong pintong nakaharap sa Look ng Maynila at tinatawag na “Puerta Postigo del Governador” na malapit sa likuran ng Palasyo ng Gobernador noong panahon ng Kastila. Muling itinayo noong 1783 sa kinadoroonan ng ikalawang pinto ng inhinyero ng hukbo na si Thomas Sanz noong panahon ni Gobernador Jose Basco at Vargas. Sa pintong ito nagdaan si Dr. Jose Rizal nang siya’y dalhin ng mga kawal na Kastila buhat sa Kuta ng Santiago hanggang Bagumbayan (ngayo’y bahagi ng Rizal Park) upang barilin noong ika-30 ng Disyembre 1896. Sa silid ng mga opisyal ng pintong iyan ikinulong si Tenyente Manuel L. Quezon noong 1902 matapos sumuko sa mga Amerikano. Nasira ang bahagi ng pinto noong 1945 dahil sa digmaan; muling ginawa ng Intramuros Restoration Committee noong 1968 sa tulong ng abuloy ng Inner Wheel Club ng Maynila, ng pambansang pamahalaan, at ng Lungsod ng Maynila.</p>","title":"Pintong Postigo","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Pintong Postigo","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1968","lat":14.59092},"Q38167195":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Santuario del Santo Cristo":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.03054,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":2394,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of San Juan del Monte historical marker.jpg","height":3000,"hash":"9c"},"text":{"title":"Church of San Juan del Monte","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The Church and Convent were built in 1602–1604 by the Dominican Province of the Most Holy Rosary on a site donated by Captain Julian de Cuenca. Both buildings were burned during the Chinese uprising of 1639. The new Church and Convent, constructed in 1641, were set on fire in July 1763 during the British occupation of Manila. The present Church and Convent, constructed in 1774, were used by the insurgent forces of the revolution of 1898. This Sanctuary is the seat of the Cofraternity of Santisimo Cristo de San Juan del Monte approved by Pope Innocent X on March 4, 1648.</p>"}}},"address":"Santuario del Santo Cristo, 183 F. Blumentritt Street, San Juan, Metro Manila","name":"Church of San Juan del Monte","region":"Metro Manila","date":"1937","macroAddress":"San Juan, Metro Manila","lat":14.59819},"Q55339137":{"macroAddress":"Luisiana, Laguna","date":"1998","lat":14.18538,"name":"Luisiana","region":"Calabarzon","address":"Luisiana Municipal Hall, Rizal Street cor. Mabini Street, Luisiana, Laguna","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Luisiana (Laguna) historical marker.jpg","height":4608,"hash":"3c"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Luisiana","inscription":"<p>Unang nakilala sa pangalang Nasunog, dating sitio ng Majayjay noong 1678. Naging visita noong 1837. Sibil na inihiwalay noong 1848 at tinaglay ang bagong pangalang Luisiana bilang parangal kina Don Luis Bernardo, ang unang tiniente absoluto, at kanyang maybahay na si Doña Ana. Pinagkalooban ng eklesiastikal at ganap na pagsasarili sa bisa ng isang dikreto buhat sa pamahalaang kolonyal ng Espanya, Abril 3, 1854. Napanatili hanggang sa kasalukuyang ang katatagan at kaunlaran mula nang pagsasarili nito noong 1854.</p>"}}},"lon":121.50962,"locPhoto":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Luisiana,Lagunajf8355 28.JPG","height":4608,"hash":"10"},"wikipedia":{"Luisiana":"Luisiana, Laguna"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the building facade, on a column of the building entrance."},"Q46995411":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.93704,"wikipedia":{"Licerio Topacio":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":14.42925,"macroAddress":"Imus, Cavite","date":"1991-11-16","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Heneral Licerio Topacio y Cuenca","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"10","height":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Licerio Topacio historical marker.jpg","width":3456},"text":{"subtitle":"(1839–1925)","title":"Heneral Licerio Topacio y Cuenca","inscription":"<p>Makabayan, rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa pook na ito noong Agosto 27, 1839. Isa sa mga unang naging kasapi ng Katipunan sa Kabite. Naging Ministro de Fomento ng Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo. Nagplano at nagpatayo ng portipikasyon ng makasaysayang tulay ng Zapote. Isa sa mga lumagda sa Konstitusyon ng Biak-na-Bato, 1897; kagawad ng Kongreso ng Malolos, 1899; pinunong bayan ng Imus, 1888–89; 1890–91; 1903. Namatay noong Abril 19, 1925.</p>"}}},"address":"F. Tirona Street, Imus, Cavite"},"Q52333650":{"name":"Katedral ng Borongan","region":"Eastern Visayas","address":"Borongan Cathedral, Borongan, Eastern Samar","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Katedral ng Borongan","inscription":"<p>Ang orihinal na simbahan na yari sa eskombro ay ipinatayo ni Padre Francisco Diez noong mga taong 1710 bilang parangal sa Mahal na Birhen ng Natividad. Ang pamamahala sa simbahan ay inilipat ng mga paring Heswita sa mga paring Pransiskano noong 1768. Tinupok ng apoy noong 1773 at muling ipinatayo at pinalaki sa pangangasiwa ng Padre Roque de Osma noong 1781. Noong 1853 isang bilog na kampanaryo ang idinagdag ni Padre Juan Navarette. Ang disenyo ng sibahan ay ginawang hugis krus ni Padre Antonio Sanchez noong 1873. Noong 1887, ang bubong ay binago at pinalitan ng sink o metal ni Padre Arsenio Figueroa. </p><p>Noong 1939, inilipat ang pangangasiwa sa simbahan ng mga paring Pransiskano sa unang Pilipinong kura paroko na si Padre Francisco Palomeras na nagdagdag ng ikalawang palapag sa kampanaryo. Ang ikatlong palapag ay ipinagawa ni Padre Potenciano Ortega noong 1950.</p><p>Naging Katedral ng Borongan noong 1961. Ito ay nagkaroon ng malawakang pagbabago at pagpapalaki noong 1962 sa pamamagitan ng Kapita-pitagang Reberendo Vicente P. Reyes, D.D., unang obispo ng Borongan. Sa kasalukuyan ang bilog na kampanaryo ang tanging bahagi ng lumang simbahan na nananatili.</p>"}}},"date":"1998-09-07","macroAddress":"Borongan, Eastern Samar","lat":11.6074,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":125.43249},"Q43302121":{"lon":121.09568,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Kapitan Moy Residence":true},"lat":14.63071,"date":"1970-04-16","macroAddress":"Marikina, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na ito, na naging paaralan, ipinanganak si Laureano Guevara (Kapitan Moy), pangunahing manggagawa ng sapatos sa Marikina. Anak nina Jose Emiterio Guevara at Matea Mariquita Andres, nagsimulang gumawa ng sapatos nang mga huling araw ng taong 1887 sa tulong nina Tiburcio Eustaquio, Ambrosio Santa Ines, Gervasio Carlos, at iba pa. Nakatuklas sila ng mga wastong pamamaraan sa paggawa ng sapatos. Ang kanilang patuloy na pananagumpay sa gawaing ito ang nagbunsod sa kapulungang-bayan na magpatibay ng isang resolusyon noong Hulyo 2, 1968 upang gawing isang museo ang bahay na ito.</p>","title":"Unang Pagawaan ng Sapatos sa Marikina","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Marikina First Shoe Factory historical marker.jpg","height":4608,"hash":"b6"}}},"address":"Kapitan Moy Residence, J. P. Rizal Street cor. Deguangco Street, Marikina, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Unang Pagawaan ng Sapatos sa Marikina"},"Q54593296":{"lon":121.04591,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Philippine Expeditionary Forces to Korea":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":14.52486,"date":"2015-06-25","macroAddress":"Taguig, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Philippine Expeditionary Force to Korea","address":"Philippine–Korea Friendship Center, Bayani Road, Taguig, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinadala ng Pamahalaang Pilipinas sa Timog Korea bilang tugon sa panawagan ng United Nations na pigilan ang pag-abante ng hukbo ng Hilagang Korea, 1950–1955. Binuo ng 2<sup>nd</sup>, 10<sup>th</sup>, 14<sup>th</sup>, 19<sup>th</sup>, at 20<sup>th</sup> Battalion Combat Teams ng mga beteranong sundalo ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at bihasa sa labanang gerilya. Dumating ang unang grupo sa Pusan, 19 Setyembre 1950. Sumabak sa mga Labanan sa Miudong at Singye (1950), Yuldong (1951), Hill Eerie (1951–1952), at Christmas Hill (1953). Mahigit sandaang Pilipino ang nasawi, 300 ang sugatan at 40 ang naging bilanggo ng digmaan. Matagumpay na bumalik sa Pilipinas ang huling grupo 17 Mayo 1955.</p>","title":"Philippine Expeditionary Force to Korea","subtitle":"(PEFTOK)"}}}},"Q43302397":{"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"40","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Morong Church Adoration Chapel gate.jpg","width":4608},"lon":121.23772,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the Adoration Chapel entrance  adjacent to the right of the church.","wikipedia":{"Morong Church":true},"macroAddress":"Morong, Rizal","date":"1939","lat":14.51427,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3456,"hash":"ad","file":"MorongChurchjf0263 21.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The Town dates from 1578. A resident Priest was assigned to it in 1586. A fire in 1612 destroyed the town and its first church. Shortly afterwards, the present Church was constructed. Its frontispiece and the belfry were built by Bartolome Palatino, of Paete, between 1850 and 1853.</p>","title":"Church of Morong","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Morong Church, Turentigue Street, Morong, Rizal","name":"Church of Morong","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q39772690":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.01584,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"dentistry in the Philippines":"Dentistry in the Philippines"},"macroAddress":"Makati, Metro Manila","date":"1961","lat":14.56366,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>In 1850 professional dentistry began in the Philippines when M. Fertri, a French dentist from Hongkong, established a clinic in Manila at corner Barbosa and R. Hidalgo, Quiapo, first Filipino to practice dentistry was Jose Arvealo, better known as Capitan Chencheng, 1852; his daughter Catalina Arevalo Mejia was first Filipino woman dentist. First dental association, Sociedad Dental de Filipinas, organized at corner Escolta and Soda, Manila, by several dentists headed by Dr. G.R. Mateo and inaugurated February 1908; first recognized dental college, Colegio Dental del Liceo de Manila, 12 June 1912, later renamed Philippine Dental College; first dental publication, Journal of the Philippine Dental Association published January 1948. </p><p><small>Compliments of Dr. G. Eraña</small></p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Dental Profession in the Philippines"},"photo":{"height":858,"hash":"83","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"PDA marker, Makati 2.jpg","width":532}}},"address":"Ayala Avenue Extension cor. Kamagong Street, Makati, Metro Manila","name":"Dental Profession in the Philippines","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q54565290":{"date":"2015-02-12","macroAddress":"Parañaque, Metro Manila","lat":14.50482,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Benigno S. Aquino, Jr.<br>“Ninoy”","subtitle":"(1932–1983)","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Concepcion, Tarlac, 27 Nobyembre 1932. Cub reporter, The Manila Times, 1949. Correspondent sa Digmaan sa Korea, 1950–1951. Ginawaran ng Philippine Legion of Honor ni Elpidio R. Quirino, 1951; at Pangulong Ramon F. Magsaysay, 1954. Negosyador sa muling pagsailalim sa batas ni Hukbalahap Supremo Luis Taruc, 1954. Punong bayan ng Concepcion, Tarlac, 1955. Pangalawang punong lalawigan ng Tarlac, 1959; punong lalawigan, 1961. Senador, 1967. Ibinilanggo matapos ideklara ang Martial Law ni Pangulong Ferdinand E. Marcos, 23 Setyembre 1972. Hinatulan ng kamatayan ng hukumang militar sa salang subersiyon, ilegal na pag-iingat ng sandata at pagpatay, 1977; pinahintulutang magtungo sa Estados Unidos upang magpagamot. 1980; pinaslang nang bumalik sa Pilipinas, 21 Agosto 1983.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"c7","height":3661,"file":"Benigno S. Aquino, Jr. historical marker (Parañaque).jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2500}}},"address":"Ninoy Aquino Avenue, Santo Niño, Parañaque, Metro Manila","name":"Benigno S. Aquino, Jr. “Ninoy”","region":"Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"91","credit":"Judgefloro","file":"6415NAIA Road Santo Niño, Parañaque City 38.jpg","width":4608},"lon":121.00018,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of the Benigno S. Aquino, Jr. monument at the center island.","wikipedia":{"Benigno Aquino, Jr.":"Benigno Aquino Jr."}},"Q46869441":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":123.64272,"locPhoto":null,"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Balay na Tisa","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 04 September 2009</p>","title":"Balay na Tisa","subtitle":"(Sarmiento–Osmeña House)"}}},"address":"Sarmiento–Osmeña House, Santa Catalina Street cor. P. Del Rosario Street, Carcar, Cebu","lat":10.10201,"date":"2010-05-29","macroAddress":"Carcar, Cebu"},"Q37330895":{"lon":120.99492,"locPhoto":{"file":"IJVPacoChurch3.jpg","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3872,"hash":"8c","height":2592},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main entrance of the church.","wikipedia":{"Paco Church":true},"lat":14.57929,"macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","date":"1999-08-22","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":2514,"hash":"31","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"IJVPacoChurch2 (cropped).jpg","width":1729},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng San Fernando de Dilao ng Paco","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ang unang simbahan na yari sa bato ay ipinatayo ni Fray Juan de Garrovillas, OFM, sa patronahe ng La Purificacion de Nuestra Señora, 1599–1601. Sumailalim sa ilang serye ng pagtatayong-muli bunga ng ilang malalaking pangyayari: ang pag-aalsa ng mga Intsik noong 1603, ang pagsalakay ng mga Ingles noong 1762, ang lindol noong 1852 at 1881, ang bagyo noong 1892 at ang sunog noong 1899. Inilipat sa pangangasiwa ng mga paring Belga ng Congregatio Immaculatie Cordis Mariae, 1900. Ang kasalukuyang simbahan na ipinatayo ni P. Godofredo Aldenhuijsen, CICM, ay binasbasan noong Abril 29, 1934. Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig at muling ipinagawa ng mga taga-parokya noong 1948. Hinalinhan ng mga paring sekular na Filipino noong 1984. Katulong ang mga taga-parokya, patuloy nilang isinasagawa ang pagpapaayos at pagpapaganda sa kasalukuyang simbahan ayon sa mga espesipikasyon ng Ikalawang Konseho ng Vatican. </p><p> Binasbasan ng Kanyang Kabunyian Jaime Cardinal L. Sin noong Agosto 22, 1999. Bilang pagtatampok sa ikaapat na raan ng pagkakatayo ng unang simbahang bato ng Dilao-Paco.</p>"}}},"address":"Paco Church, 1521 Paz Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Simbahan ng San Fernando de Dilao ng Paco"},"Q24702080":{"date":"1973-11-13","macroAddress":"Gumaca, Quezon","lat":13.92144,"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Gumaca","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Supermakel {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Gumaca Cathedral historical marker.jpg","width":333,"hash":"f4","height":500},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang itinayo sa pook na ito noong 1582 at inilipat sa silanga, sakop ng pulo ng Alabat noong 1638. Sinunog ng mga Olandes noong 1655. Muling itinayo ang simbahan dito noong 1690 at natapos noong 1747. Ang gusali at kombento ay inayos at pinaganda noong 1846. Kinikilalang pinakamalaki at pinakamatandang simbahang Katoliko sa buong lalawigan ng Tayabas, ngayo’y Quezon.</p>","subtitle":"(1582)","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Gumaca"}}},"address":"Gumaca Cathedral, Gumaca, Quezon","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.09942,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q55335479":{"lon":121.43196,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Mabitac":true},"macroAddress":"Mabitac, Laguna","date":null,"lat":14.42619,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito naganap ang isang madugong labanan ng Hukbong Pilipino sa pamumuno ni Heneral Juan Cailles at Hukbong Amerikano sa pamumuno ni Kolonel Cheatham noong Setyembre 17, 1900. Nagtagumpay ang mga Pilipino sa labanang ito.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Mabitac","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BattleofMabitacjf1336 14.JPG","width":4608,"hash":"8f","height":3456}}},"address":"Mabitac, Laguna","name":"Labanan sa Mabitac","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q44303134":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Agustino bilang visita ng Tondo, 1575. Ipinatayo ang simbahang parokyal at kumbento sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora de la Asuncion, 1578. Sinakop at sinunog ng mga Ingles, 1762. Muling ipinatayo, 1812. Ipinagawa ang kampanaryo, 1877. Nasira ng lindol, 1863, 1869, at 1880. Ipinaayos sa disenyong Neo-Byzantine, 1884–1885. Natapos ang kampanaryo, 1889. Dito lihim na ipinamahagi ni Gregorio H. del Pilar ang mga polyeto sa panulat ng kanyang amaing si Marcelo H. del Pilar noong panahon ng Propaganda laban sa mga Kastila. Ipinanumbalik at ipinaayos ang simbahan, 1955–1975.</p>","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Bulacan","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":1920,"file":"Bulacan Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"85","height":2880}}},"address":"Our Lady of Assumption Church, Bulakan, Bulacan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Ang Simbahan ng Bulacan","lat":14.79499,"date":"2007","macroAddress":"Bulakan, Bulacan","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Our Lady of Assumption Church":"Our Lady of Assumption Church (Bulakan)"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.87942},"Q43276986":{"wikipedia":{"Salvador del Mundo":"Salvador del Mundo (chemist)"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.84153,"name":"Salvador del Mundo","region":"Mimaropa","address":"Boac Municipal Hall, Boac, Marinduque","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Salvador del Mundo","subtitle":null}}},"macroAddress":"Boac, Marinduque","date":"1982-05-24","lat":13.44676},"Q54500698":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Ang Dambana ni Melchora (Tandang Sora) Aquino","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito inilipat ang mga labi ni Melchora Aquino mula sa Himlayang Pilipino bilang paggunita sa ika-200 taong anibersaryo ng kanyang kapanganakan, 6 Enero 2012. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Dambana sa bisa ng NHCP Board Resolution Blg. 4, 24 Enero 2012.</p>","subtitle":"(6 Enero 1812–19 Pebrero 1919)","title":"Ang Dambana ni Melchora (Tandang Sora) Aquino"},"photo":{"height":1549,"hash":"f9","width":1280,"file":"Tandang Sora Shrine 09.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"address":"Tandang Sora Shrine, Banlat Road cor. Melchora Aquino Street, Banlat, Quezon City, Metro Manila","lat":14.68297,"macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","date":"2012-03-03","wikipedia":{"Melchora Aquino":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the tomb of Melchora Aquino.","locPhoto":{"file":"Tandang Sora Shrine 04.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1280,"hash":"a6","height":1920},"lon":121.04538},"Q28942492":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.25709,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lat":7.38447,"date":"1991","macroAddress":"Parang, Maguindanao","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Camp Brigadier General Salipada K. Pendatun","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Formerly Camp Parang, renamed after Brig. Gen. Salipada K. Pendatun by House Bill no. 53 of the Regional Legislative Assembly of the Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao (ARMM) and the General Order no. 1472 of the Commanding General of the PNP dated October 25, 1991. Hero of the Second World War, founder of the Bolo Battalion in Cotabato Basin, later, Bukidnon-Cotabato Force, proponent of national unity, freedom and liberty. This camp is dedicated in his honor.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Camp Brigadier General Salipada K. Pendatun, Parang, Maguindanao","region":"Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao","name":"Camp Brigadier General Salipada K. Pendatun"},"Q28922986":{"macroAddress":"Cotabato City","date":"2004","lat":7.18353,"name":"Simbahang Inmaculada Concepcion ng Tamontaka","region":"Soccsksargen","address":"Tamontaka Church, Cotabato City","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayo ng mga paring Heswita sa pampang ng panlahatan sa ilog Tamontaka noong 1872 bilang bahagi ng misyong Tamontaka upang pangalagaan ang kapakanan ng mga kabataan at palaganapin ang ebanghelyo sa rehiyon ng Cotabato. Ipinatayo ang paaralan para sa mga kabataang lalaki sa pangangasiwa ng mga Heswita at paaralan para sa mga kabataang babae sa pangangalaga ng mga Beata ng San Ignacio (ngayo'y Religious of the Virgin Mary o RVM). Inilipat sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan nito, 1879 at naging sentro ng misyong Heswita. Nilisan ng mga paring Heswita, 1899 at inilagay sa pangangalaga ng mga Heswita ng Zamboanga. Pinangasiwaan ng mga paring Oblates of Mary Immaculate at naging bahagi ng kanilang misyon sa Cotabato, 1939. Nasira ng lindol, 17 Agosto 1976. Muling itinayo,, 1978. Nasunog, 11 Mayo 1994, at isinaayos nang taon ding iyon. Ipinahayag ang pook na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 19 Hulyo 2004.</p>","title":"Simbahang Inmaculada Concepcion ng Tamontaka","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Church of the Immaculate Conception of Tamontaka Seal.JPG","credit":"Erichmercado {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1088,"hash":"28","height":1582}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.22226,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q55713585":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Hagonoy":"Hagonoy, Bulacan","Hagonoy Church":"National Shrine of Saint Anne"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.73389,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Hagonoy","inscription":"<p>Ang bayan ay itinatag ng mga paring Agustino noong 1581. Yari sa magagaang kagamitan, ang unang simbahan ay ipinagawa sa ilalim ng patronang si Santa Ana. Unang pari nito si Padre Diego Ordoñez Vivar. Pagkaraan, ang simbahan ay binago at ginamitan ng mga bato at ladrilyo, sina Padre Joaquin Martinez Zuñiga, kilalang mananalaysay na Agustino, at Padre Mariano Sevilla, isang malikhaing manunulat na Tagalog, ay naging mga kura paroko ng bayang ito. </p><p>Ang simbahan ay ipinaayos noong 1936–1963; binago noong 1968 at inihandog sa Panginoon noong ika 25 ng Hulyo 1970.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"0b","height":2984,"width":2220,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Church of Hagonoy historical marker (cropped).jpg"}}},"address":"Hagonoy Church, Poblacion, Hagonoy, Bulacan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Simbahan ng Hagonoy","lat":14.83486,"macroAddress":"Hagonoy, Bulacan","date":"1981-04-05"},"Q31440586":{"lon":123.79026,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Punta Cruz Watchtower":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":9.73506,"macroAddress":"Maribojoc, Bohol","date":"2009","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Bantayan ng Punta Cruz","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Bantayan ng Punta Cruz","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng mga paring Recoletos sa Patronato ni San Vicente Ferrer laban sa pagsalakay ng mga piratang moro, 1796. Yari sa korales na may hugis tatsulok as unang palapag at heksagonal sa ikalawang palapag. Naligtas sa pagkasira noong digmaang Filipino-Amerikano at ikalawang digmaang pandaigdig nang sunugin ng mga puwersang Hapones ang bayan ng Maribojoc, 1944. Halimbawa ng arkitekturang militar noong panahon ng mga Espanyol at bantayog sa kahusayan ng mga lokal na artisano. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 2009.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Punta Cruz Watchtower historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":291,"hash":"9c","height":350}}},"address":"Punta Cruz Watchtower, Maribojoc, Bohol"},"Q53997691":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Arevalo":"Arevalo, Iloilo City"},"lon":122.51613,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2379,"file":"Villa Arevalo historical marker.JPG","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":3757,"hash":"a9"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ni Gobernador Ronquillo de Peñalosa noong 1581 at pinangalanang “La Villa Rica de Arevalo,” sa ilalim ng pangasiwaan ng Oton. Ito ay naging kabisera ng lalawigan noong 1582. Sentro ng pagawaan ng mga sasakyang-dagat. Ito ay nilusob ng mga British noong 1588. Dahil sa mga pananalakay ng mga Muslim noong 1600 at ng mga Olandes noong 1609, 1614, at 1616, ang kabisera ay inilipat sa Punta, ang kasalukuyang Lungsod ng Iloilo. Ito ay ginawang ikaapat na uring bayan noong 1827. Simula noong Hulyo 16, 1937, hanggang sa kasalukuyan, ito ay isa sa mga distritong bumubuo sa lungsod.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Villa de Arevalo"}}},"address":"Villa Arevalo Plaza, Osmeña Street cor. Yulo Drive, Arevalo, Iloilo City","name":"Villa de Arevalo","region":"Western Visayas","date":"1981-12-11","macroAddress":"Iloilo City","lat":10.68744},"Q55719191":{"lat":14.95676,"macroAddress":"Baliuag, Bulacan","date":"1953","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Mariano Ponce","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito ipinanganak noong ika-23 ng Marso, 1863 si Mariano Ponce. Makabayan, mananalaysay, diplomatiko. Kasama nina Rizal, Del Pilar, Lopez–Jaena at iba pa sa Europa sa pagpapalaganap ng mga mithiin ng Pilipinas, 1887–1895. Pasugo ng Pilipinas sa Hapon, 1898. Kinatawan, Kapulungang Bayan, 1909–1912. Namatay sa Hongkong, Mayo 23, 1918.</p>","title":"Mariano Ponce","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"5b","height":2135,"file":"Mariano Ponce historical marker (cropped).jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1298}}},"address":"Mariano Ponce Street, Brgy. Tibag, Baliuag, Bulacan","lon":120.90296,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"09048jfBaliuag Mariano Ponce Houses Subic Bulacanfvf 17.JPG","width":4608,"height":3456,"hash":"29"},"wikipedia":{"Mariano Ponce":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a memorial obelisk in the front yard."},"Q54812276":{"macroAddress":"Tagudin, Ilocos Sur","date":"1958","lat":16.93383,"name":"The Base Hospital","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":2500,"file":"The Base Hospital historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","hash":"b0","height":3856},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The Base Hospital was transferred to this town on 27 May 1945, bringing it closer to the frontline where the battle casualties and medical cases were tremendously heavy. Headquarters was installed at the municipal hall, while big tents set up on the town plaza, and on the market site as well as the big residential houses bordering the town plaza, were utilized as hospital wards. Manned at the height of the campaign by 881 military and civilian personnel, this hospital was biggest installation of its kind in the country during the Philippine liberation campaign.</p>","title":"The Base Hospital","subtitle":"USAFIP, NL"}}},"address":"Tagudin Town Plaza, San Antolin Street, Tagudin, Ilocos Sur","locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Tagudin Municipal Hall, Base Hospital Marker, Sundial.jpg","hash":"ae","height":3456},"lon":120.445,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Luzon":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting across the Tagudin Town Hall."},"Q24702203":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.59105,"wikipedia":{"Tayabas Basilica":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Tayabas, Quezon","date":"1978","lat":14.02583,"name":"Ang Simbahan ng Tayabas","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang unang simbahan na yari sa kawayan, nipa at anahaw ay ipinatayo ng mga prayleng Pransiskano noong 1585 sa ilalim ng patronato ni San Miguel Arkanghel. Ito ay muling ipinaayos ni san Juan Bautista noong 1590. Noong 1600 isang simbahang yari sa tisa ang ipinatayo subalit ito ay giniba ng lindol noong 1743. Nang sumunod na mga taon ang simbahan ay muling ipinagawa at pinalakihan. Ito ay higit pang pinalaki noong 1856 sa pamamagitan ng pagpapagawa ng transepto at kupola. Ang bubong na tisa ng transepto ay pinalitan ng gabanisadong yero noong 1894. Ang simbahang ito ay isa sa pinakamagandang simbahan sa Pilipinas.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Tayabas"},"photo":{"hash":"35","height":1985,"width":1627,"credit":"Ramiltibayan {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Tayabas Basilica Historical Marker.JPG"}}},"address":"Tayabas Basilica, Tayabas, Quezon"},"Q46867382":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.64123,"wikipedia":{"León Kilat":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Carcar, Cebu","date":"2001","lat":10.10487,"name":"Pantaleon Villegas “Leon Kilat”","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Bacong, Negros Oriental, 27 Hulyo 1873. Sumanib sa Katipunan habang nasa Maynila matapos paslangin ang mga mandaragat mula sa Kabisayaan sa Calle Camba, Binondo, Setyembre 1896. Dinakip at ikinulong ng mga Espanyol, nakatakas at sumanib sa puwersang Rebolusyonaryo sa Cavite, 1897. Inatasan ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo na palawakin ang kilusang Rebolusyonaryo sa Cebu, 1897. Pinamunuan ang pag-aalsa ng Tres de Abril sa Lungsod ng Cebu, 1898. Pinaslang sa Carcar, Cebu, 8 Abril 1898. Ibinalik ang mga labi sa bayan ng Bacong, Negros Oriental, 2 Agosto 1926.</p>","title":"Pantaleon Villegas “Leon Kilat”","subtitle":"(1873–1898)"}}},"address":"Santa Catalina Street, Poblacion, Carcar, Cebu"},"Q55285105":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.28493,"wikipedia":{"Tanay":"Tanay, Rizal"},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Tanay, Rizal","date":"1939","lat":14.49806,"name":"Town of Tanay","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Town of Tanay","inscription":"<p>A small village on Monte Tan-ay, now Inalsan under the jurisdiction of Pililla from 1573. Tanay became an independent parish under San Ildefonso in 1606. In 1620 it was transferred to San Antonio (Pantay). When San Antonio was burned in 1639, the people moved to the present site and founded the town in 1640. </p><p>The first stone church in this town was finished in 1680. The present church was built in 1773–1783. Two irrigation dams were built in 1790–1808. A school for boys and a school for girls were opened in 1821. A stone bridge, built across the Tanay River in 1854–1856, was destroyed by the typhoon and flood of September 27, 1864, but rebuilt in 1877. A municipal building was erected in 1888 and a school house in 1893. These public improvements were achieved largely by voluntary contribution. </p><p> Rawang Pass and Kalinawan Plateau in the mountains of this town were strongholds of the Filipinos in the Revolution against Spain and in the Filipino–American War. In April–May, 1900, the American forces occupied this town with the establishment of the Civil Government in 1901. The town became a part of the province of Rizal.</p>"},"photo":[{"height":903,"hash":"fb","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Tanay marker 1.jpg","width":892},{"height":900,"hash":"90","width":886,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Tanay marker 3.jpg"},{"file":"Tanay marker 2.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":893,"hash":"03","height":901}]}},"address":"M.H. del Pilar Street, Plaza Aldea, Tanay, Rizal"},"Q55194981":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni Mariano Villanueva noong ikalabinsiyam na dantaon at kinilala bilang isa sa mga pinakamalaking bahay sa bayan ng Tabaco. Naging pag-aari ng Smith, Bell & Co. at ginamit bilang sangay ng kumpanya sa Tabaco, Albay hanggang sa mabili ni Angela Manalang Gloria, 1965, at tinirahan ng pamilya. Natatanging halimbawa ng bahay na bato noong panahon ng mga Espanyol sa Albay.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Bahay-Kalakal ng Smith, Bell & Co. Tabaco, Albay"},"photo":{"width":717,"credit":"Tabunon {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Hm bahayKalakal.jpg","hash":"8e","height":960}}},"address":"Smith, Bell and Company House, Rizal Street cor. J. B. Berces Street, Tabaco, Albay","region":"Bicol Region","name":"Bahay-Kalakal ng Smith, Bell & Co. Tabaco, Albay","lat":13.35985,"macroAddress":"Tabaco, Albay","date":"2007","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Smith, Bell and Company House":true},"lon":123.73168,"locPhoto":null},"Q28878079":{"name":"Andres Bonifacio","region":"Davao Region","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":1398,"hash":"24","file":"Historical marker of Andres Bonifacio in Davao City.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":1002},"text":{"title":"Andres Bonifacio","subtitle":"(30 Nobyembre 1863 – 10 Mayo 1897)","inscription":"<p>Bayani at rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Tondo, Maynila, 30 Nobyembre 1863. Sumapi sa Masoneriya at La Liga Filipina, 1892. Nagtatag ng Kataastaasan Kagalanggalang na Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan o Katipunan, isang lihim na kilusan na ang pangunahing adhikain ay mapagkaisa ang lahat ng mga Pilipino at itaguyod ang isang bayang malaya sa pamamagitan ng paghihimagsik, 7 Hulyo 1892. Pinamunuan ang pagsisimula ng malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa mga Espanyol, Agosto 1896. Sumalakay sa San Juan del Monte upang kubkubin ang Polvorin, 30 Agosto 1896. Pinatay sa Maragondon, Cavite, 10 Mayo 1897[.] Kinikilala bilang Supremo ng Katipunan at Ama ng Himagsikan.</p>"}}},"address":"Agton Street, Toril, Davao City","macroAddress":"Davao City","date":"2013","lat":7.01882,"wikipedia":{"Andres Bonifacio":"Andrés Bonifacio"},"locDesc":null,"lon":125.49742,"locPhoto":null},"Q53824021":{"wikipedia":{"Panay Liberation Day":true,"Battle of the Visayas":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.368,"name":"Panay Landing","region":"Western Visayas","address":"Iloilo–Antique Road cor. Parara–Jamog Road, Tigbauan, Iloilo","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>On these shores landed, 18 March 1945, the 40th Infantry Division, 8th U.S. Army under Major General Rapp Brush. The Filipino forces under Colonel Macario Peralta, Jr. met them and jointly started operations for liberating Panay Island.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Panay Landing"},"photo":{"file":"Panay Landing historical marker.JPG","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1512,"height":2211,"hash":"97"}}},"macroAddress":"Tigbauan, Iloilo","date":"1954","lat":10.67261},"Q44821150":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.47503,"address":"Badoc Church, Soriano Street, Badoc, Ilocos Norte","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"f2","height":3648,"credit":"KisekiLacroix {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Simbahan ng Badoc historical marker.jpg","width":2736},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo ng mga paring Agustino. Dating kapilya ng Sinait noong 1591. Naging paroko noong 1714 sa pagtataguyod ni San Juan Bautista. Ang simbahan at ang kumbento na kapwa yari sa bato at tisa ay matibay at artistikong naitayo sa pangangasiwa ni Reb. P. Valentin Blovide. Ang simbahang ito ay isa sa mga bahay-dalanginan na nilooban ng mga Sambal noong panahon ng paghihimagsik ni Andres Malong noong 1660–1661.</p><p>Si Juan Luna (1857–1899) ang pangunahing pintor na Pilipino ay bininyagan sa simbahang ito noong ika-27 ng Oktubre 1857. Ang kanyang mga kapatid na sina Laureana at Manuel Andres ay kapwa bininyagan sa simbahang ding ito.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Badoc"}}},"region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Ang Simbahan ng Badoc","lat":17.92783,"macroAddress":"Badoc, Ilocos Norte","date":"1980"},"Q28864749":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the extreme eastern end of the building facade facing the town plaza.","wikipedia":{"Pagsanjan Municipal Hall":true},"lon":121.45581,"locPhoto":{"hash":"ba","height":3456,"width":4608,"file":"Pagsanjan,LagunaTownhaloljf4416 02.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":2274,"file":"Pagsanjan Municipal Building historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"14","height":3500},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Originally constructed in the middle of the nineteenth century and housed the “Tribunal del Gremio de Naturales”; Occupied by the Filipino Revolutionary forces in 1898 and by the American Expeditionary Forces in 1899–1903; served as the first public high school in Laguna 1903–1907; housed the municipal elementary school until 1911; later became the seat of the Municipal government. Destroyed on 20 March 1945; rehabilitated and reconstructed in 1951 and completed in 1955.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Pagsanjan Municipal Building"}}},"address":"Pagsanjan Municipal Hall, J. P. Rizal Street cor. Gen. Taino Street, Pagsanjan, Laguna","name":"Pagsanjan Municipal Building","region":"Calabarzon","date":"1956","macroAddress":"Pagsanjan, Laguna","lat":14.27255},"Q54806714":{"details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"20","height":3367,"file":"Historical Marker Site of the Diocese of Nueva Segovia.jpg","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2239},"text":{"title":"Site of the Diocese of Nueva Segovia","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Founded in Lal-lo, Cagayan, 14 August 1595, with Fr. Miguel de Benavides as first bishop, by the Bull of Pope Clement VIII, through the efforts of Bishop Domingo de Salazar in Madrid. Transferred to Vigan, 1758, occupying a building which escaped capture by the rebels when Diego Silang, who defeated the Bishop's forces, was assassinated by Vicos, 1763. Present building constructed, 1783–1790, repaired, 1824–1826, also housed the Ecclestiastical Court until 1890. Occupied by the Revolutionists who imprisoned Bishop Jose Hevia Campomanes, 1896. Used as garrison by the American Forces under Lt. Col. James Parker, 1899.</p>"}}},"address":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","name":"Site of the Diocese of Nueva Segovia","region":"Ilocos Region","macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","date":"1949","lat":17.57549,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Archdiocese of Nueva Segovia":"Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Nueva Segovia"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.38839},"Q24764629":{"lat":13.78967,"macroAddress":"Bauan, Batangas","date":"1939","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Church of Bauan","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Bauan","inscription":"<p>The parish of Bauan was administered by the Augustinians from 1596 to the end of the nineteenth century. The church built in the eighteenth century, remodelled and improved by the Rev. Hipolito Huerta and the Rev. Felipe Bravo in the nineteenth century was destroyed by fire on July 13, 1928. The eminent botanist Father Blanco was pastor of this church from 1816 to 1828. Under his administration great impetus was given to the home industries of weaving and dyeing. The Museum of Natural History and the Library of Rare Books collected by Father Bravo were destroyed during the insurrection of 1898.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Bauan Church in Batangas historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608,"hash":"12","height":3456}}},"address":"Bauan Church, Bauan, Batangas","lon":121.00781,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Bauan Church":true},"locDesc":null},"Q54943331":{"macroAddress":"Iloilo City","date":"1997-03-18","lat":10.74195,"name":"Battle of Balantang","region":"Western Visayas","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The bloodiest battle fought by the Panay Guerilla Forces led by Colonel Macario Peralta, Jr., occured in these hollowed grounds of Balantang and its vicinity from February 6 up to the Liberation of Iloilo City on March 20, 1945. Though outnumbered, the Filipino forces stood still in their post, repulsing the seven suicidal attacks of the Japanese Imperial Forces, thus enabling the Allied 40th Infantry Division of the U.S. Army under Major General Rapp Brush to land peacefully at Tigbauan, Parara Beach, Iloilo on March 18, 1945 and join the guerilla forces of Col. Peralta in their mopping-up operation to liberate Panay Islands from the Japanese. </p><p>This monument is dedicated to the Freedom Fighters of Panay and Romblon who gave their lives for the cause of freedom and democracy.</p>","title":"Battle of Balantang","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Balantang Memorial Cemetery National Shrine, Jaro, Iloilo City","lon":122.56383,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q53680751":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Japanese occupation of the Philippines":true,"Tomoyuki Yamashita":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.08522,"address":"Kiangan Central School, Poblacion, Kiangan, Ifugao","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Surrender of General Yamashita","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this site, General Tomoyuki Yamashita together with his staff, surrendered to the elements of the U.S. 6th Army in the morning of September 2, 1945. The final surrender ceremony took place the following day at the High Commissioner’s Residence, Camp John Hay, Baguio City.</p>"}}},"name":"Surrender of General Yamashita","region":"Cordillera Administrative Region","date":"1995-09-02","macroAddress":"Kiangan, Ifugao","lat":16.77698},"Q55333575":{"lat":14.47058,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Santa Maria, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Church of Santa Maria","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Santa Maria, Laguna historical marker.jpg","hash":"5b","height":3456},"text":{"title":"Church of Santa Maria","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The town of Santa Maria de Caboan was founded in 1602 and called San Miguel till 1613. Its first minister was the Rev. Antonio de la Llave. A church built in 1613 by the Rev. Geronimo Vasquez, was destroyed in the Chinese uprising of 1639. Another church, completed in 1669, succumbed to earthquakes in 1880. In 1891 the Rev. Leopoldo Arellano reerected the church, but it was destroyed by the earthquake of August 20, 1937.</p>"}}},"address":"Santa Maria Church, P. Burgos Street, Poblacion, Santa Maria, Laguna","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.42334,"wikipedia":{"Santa Maria Church":"Nuestra Señora de los Angeles Parish Church (Santa Maria)"},"locDesc":null},"Q54503102":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98566,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lat":14.58539,"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"1935","address":"Adamson University, 959 San Marcelino Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The chapel built here in 1883 was used as parish church of Paco from 1898 to 1909. Parish of San Vicente de Paul erected in 1909. Present church built of concrete in 1912 to commemorate the fiftieth anniversary of the arrival of the Vincentians and Sisters of Charity in the Philippines.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of San Vicente de Paul"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"St. Vincent de Paul Church historical marker, Ermita, Manila.jpg","hash":"33","height":4608}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Church of San Vicente de Paul"},"Q38348379":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Orador. estadista, ekonomista, at makabayan. Ipinanganak sa Capiz (ngayo’y Roxas City), Capiz, Enero 1, 1892. Nagtapos ng sekondaryang edukasyon, Manila High School, 1910; Batsilyer sa Batas, Pamantasan ng Pilipinas, 1913. Gobernador, 1919, at kinatawan ng Capiz sa Lehislatura, 1922; delegado ng Kumbenston Konstitusyonal, 1935: Kalihim ng Pananalapi, 1938; Senador, 1941. Noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, naging Medyor, 1941; at Brigadyer Heneral, 1945, ng Hukbong Katihan ng Pilipinas. Senador, 1945–1946; Pangulo ng Pilipinas, 1946–1948. Namatay Abril 15, 1948.</p>","title":"Manuel Acuña Roxas","subtitle":"(1892–1948)"},"photo":{"hash":"d0","height":495,"file":"Manuel Acuña Roxas (1892 - 1948) Roxas blvd marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":340}}},"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Pedro Gil Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Manuel Acuña Roxas","region":"Metro Manila","date":"1989","macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","lat":14.5734,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Manuel Roxas":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98105},"Q56070804":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.32706,"wikipedia":{"Carlos P. Garcia":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":10.15053,"date":"1972-11-04","macroAddress":"Talibon, Bohol","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Carlos P. Garcia","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito sa Talibon, Bohol, ipinanganak si Carlos P. Garcia noong Nobyembre 4, 1896. Guro sa paaralang bayan, estadista, Kinatawan ng Ikatlong Purok ng Bohol (1925–1931); Gobernador ng Bohol (1934–1941); Senador (1941–1953); Pangalawang Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipinas at Kalihim Panlabas (1953–1957); ikaapat na Pangulo ng Republika ng Pilipnas (1957–1961); at Delegado ng Bohol sa 1971 Kombensiyong Pansaligang-Batas. Namatay noong Hulyo 14, 1971, tatlong araw makaraang mahalal na pangulo ng naturang kombensiyon.</p>","subtitle":"1896–1971","title":"Carlos P. Garcia"}}},"address":"Carlos P. Garcia Avenue, Talibon, Bohol"},"Q55694506":{"name":"La Liga Filipina","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"La Liga Filipina","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa lugar na ito itinatag ni Jose Rizal ang La Liga Filipina, 3 Hulyo 1892, upang gawing buo, masigasig at nagkakaisa ang bayan; alagaan ang mga nais at pangangailangan ng mga tao; ipagtanggol ang bayan laban sa lahat ng uri ng karahasan at kawalang katarungan; pasiglahin ang edukasyon, agrikultura at kalakal; at pag-aralan at iangkop ang mga pagbabago sa lipunan. Humina ang samahan matapos arestuhin at ipatapon si Rizal sa Dapitan, Hulyo 1892. Muling inorganisa ang samahan nina Domingo Franco, Andres Bonifacio, Apolinario Mabini at iba pa, Abril 1893. Tuluyang nabuwag ang samahan, Oktubre 1893.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"La Liga Filipina NHCP Historical Marker.png","width":2226,"height":3102,"hash":"bd"}}},"address":"Plaza Liga Filipina, Raja Matanda Street cor. Ilaya Street, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","date":"2015","lat":14.60668,"wikipedia":{"La Liga Filipina":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96807},"Q44989612":{"wikipedia":{"Tomás del Rosario":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.5299,"name":"Tomas Guillermo T. del Rosario","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Tomas Guillermo T. del Rosario","inscription":"<p>Masigasig na tagapagtaguyod ng karapatan sa malayang pagsamba at ng pagkakahiwalay ng simbahan at estado. Isinilang kina Cipriano del Rosario at Severina Tongco sa Binondo, Maynila, 10 Pebrero 1857. Nagtapos ng Bachiller en Artes sa Ateneo Municipal, 1875; at Licenciado en Derecho sa Unibersidad ng Santos Tomas, 1886. Naglingkod bilang juez de paz, promotor fiscal, at juez de primera instancia ng Maynila, 1888–1896. Ipinatapon sa Cueta, Aprika sa pagkakasangkot sa himagsikan 1896–1897. Nagbalik sa Pilipinas at nahirang sa delegado sa Kongreso ng Malolos bilang kinatawan ng Surigao, 1898. Nahalal na gobernador ng Bataan, 1904–1906; at kinatawan sa Philippine Assembly, 1909–1912. Yumao, 4 Hulyo 1913.</p>"},"photo":{"height":3751,"hash":"86","file":"Tomas Guillermo T. del Rosario historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2500}}},"address":"Bataan Provincial Capitol, Capitol Drive, Balanga, Bataan","macroAddress":"Balanga, Bataan","date":"2007","lat":14.67582},"Q30133244":{"macroAddress":"Chicago, Illinois, United States","date":"1993","lat":41.95452,"name":"Dr. Jose Rizal","region":"Overseas","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>National hero of the Philippines arrived in Chicago, Illinois on May 11, 1888 at 8:14 a.m. He visited places of interest and left the city at 8:25 p.m.</p>","title":"Dr. Jose Rizal","subtitle":"(1861–1896)"},"photo":null}},"address":"1332 West Irving Park Road, Chicago, Cook County, Illinois, United States of America","lon":-87.6634,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locDesc":null},"Q30138745":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Battle of Pinaglabanan","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito naganap ang makasaysayang labanan ng mga Pilipino at Kastila noong 30 Agosto 1896. Dito unang sumalakay ang mga Katipunero sa pamumuno ni Andres Bonifacio at Emilio Jacinto. Sa labanang ito, na kinasawian ng 153 Katipunero, ipinakilala ng mga Pilipino na handa silang mag-alay ng kanilang buhay alang-alang sa kalayaan ng Inang Bayan.</p>"},"photo":{"width":555,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pinaglabanan HistoricalMarker SanJuanCity.jpg","height":805,"hash":"8b"}}},"address":"N. Domingo Street corner Pinaglabanan Road, San Juan, Metro Manila","name":"Battle of Pinaglabanan","region":"Metro Manila","date":"1969-08-29","macroAddress":"San Juan, Metro Manila","lat":14.60753,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of San Juan del Monte":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.02681},"Q55190092":{"lon":121.0022,"locPhoto":{"file":"FvfPenarandaNE0190 19.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"hash":"e9","height":4608},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located near the leftmost end of the church facade.","date":"1951","macroAddress":"Peñaranda, Nueva Ecija","lat":15.35354,"name":"Simbahan ng Penyaranda","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3456,"hash":"de","file":"JfSaintFrancisChurchPenarandaNuevaEcijafvf 08.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4608},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Penyaranda","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinayo noong 1869 ni P. Florentino Samonte; ipinagpatuloy ni P. Isidoro Prada ang pagpapagawa, 1873–1875, at ni P Candido San Miguel 1879–1881; at tinapos ni P. Santos Vega, 1887–1889. Ang kumbento na yari sa tisa at kahoy ay itinayo ni P. Valentin Gato de la Fuente, 1889–1891. Ang unang simbahan ay may atip na kugon at pader na bato na itinayo ni P. Alvaro Calleja.</p>"}}},"address":"Rizal Street, Peñaranda, Nueva Ecija"},"Q43248095":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the facade, on the buttress to the right of the nave entrance.","wikipedia":{"Maragondon Church":true},"lon":120.73364,"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"57","width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"MaragondonChurchjf0031 06.JPG"},"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ng mga paring Heswita sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora de la Asuncion, 1618. Naging simbahang parokyal, 1627. Ipinatayo at ipinalaki ang bagong simbahan, 1630–1633. Ipinagiba upang iwasang maging kuta ng mga Olandes, 1646–1649. Muling ipinatayo na gawa sa kahoy, 1650. Inayos ang kumbento, 1666–1672. Ginawa sa bato, 1714. Inilipat sa pangangasiwa ng mga paring sekular, 1768, at ng mga Rekoletos, 1860. Ginamit na tanggulan ng mga rebolusyonaryo nang gawing punong himpilan ang Maragondon ng mga puwersa ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo, Mayo 1897. Muling pinangasiwaan ng mga paring sekular noong ikadalawampung dantaon. Natatanging halimbawa ng disenyo at arkitekturang kolonyal. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Yamang Pangkalinangan ng Pambansang Museo, 31 Hulyo 2001.</p>","title":"Ang Simbahan ng Maragondon","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":2485,"hash":"fb","file":"Simbahan ng Maragondon Marker.JPG","credit":"Ramiltibayan {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1860}}},"address":"Maragondon Church, Maragondon, Cavite","name":"Ang Simbahan ng Maragondon","region":"Calabarzon","date":"2007","macroAddress":"Maragondon, Cavite","lat":14.27399},"Q54814795":{"lon":120.53328,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Gregorio Aglipay":true,"Philippine Independent Church":true},"lat":17.94879,"macroAddress":"Pinili, Ilocos Norte","date":"1998-11-07","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Formerly a barrio of Badoc, Kul-labeng used to serve as the refuge of Monsignor Gregorio Aglipay, revolutionary leader and vicar general castrence of the Filipino Revolutionary Government. This barrio was the scene of encounters between Filipino Revolutionary forces and the Americans during the Filipino–American War, including one which resulted in the routing of 50 American soldiers and the death of an American captain.</p><p>After the war, the barrio was the frequent meeting place of Monsignor Gregorio Aglipay and other Filipino priests. It was here where he and other priests met and made a decision to separate from the authority of the Roman Catholic Church on May 8, 1902.</p>","title":"Kul-labeng Historical Site","subtitle":"Pinili, Ilocos Norte"}}},"address":"Brgy. Aglipay, Pinili, Ilocos Norte","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Kul-labeng Historical Site"},"Q54151815":{"wikipedia":{"San Bartolome de Malabon Church":"San Bartolome Church (Malabon)"},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.95165,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Simbahan ng San Bartolome","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Rizal Avenue Extension, Malabon, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng San Bartolome","inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang bisita ng Tondo, 21 Mayo 1599. Naging parokya sa patronato ni San Bartolome de Tambobong (ngayo’y Malabon), 17 Mayo 1614. Ipinatayo ang simbahan ni Padre Diego de Robles yari sa bato, 1622. Ipinagawa ang harapan ng simbahan at ang dalawang kampanaryo ayon sa disenyo ni Luciano Oliver, 1861. Noong 1896, kasunod ng Sigaw sa Pugadlawin (23 Agosto), itinaon ni Andres Bonifacio sa pista ni San Bartolome (24 Agosto) ang isang lihim at malaking pulong ng Katipunan sa Balintawak upang makaiwas sa pagdakip ng mga guwardya sibil ang mga Katipunero at makarating sa pulong na nagpapanggap na sila'y mga peregrino. Nasunog ang kanang bahagi ng simbahan, 1898. Ipinaayos, 1906. Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Ipinaayos ang harapang bahagi ng simbahan, 1951, at ang kampanaryo at interiyor, 1958.</p>"}}},"macroAddress":"Malabon, Metro Manila","date":"2015-08-27","lat":14.65858},"Q51452915":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.69172,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José María Panganiban":true},"date":"1985-02-01","macroAddress":"Jose Panganiban, Camarines Norte","lat":14.29029,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":1600,"hash":"2b","width":1200,"file":"Jose Maria Panganiban historical marker in Jose Panganiban, Camarines Norte.jpg","credit":"Jrr irang soulfinder {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"title":"Jose Ma. Panganiban y Enverga","subtitle":"(1863–1890)","inscription":"<p>Manunulat, siyentipiko, orador at propagandista. Isinilang noong Pebrero 1, 1863, sa Mambulao (ngayo’y Jose Panganiban) Camarines Norte. Nag-aral, mababang paaralan sa seminaryo ng Nueva Caceres (ngayo’y Naga), mataas na paaralan sa San Juan de Letran, Maynila. Kung saan nakamit ang A.B., at Medisina sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas at Pamantasan ng Barcelona, Espanya. Mananalaysay at tagasalingwika ng La Solidaridad. Namatay sa Barcelona noong Agosto 19, 1890.</p><p>Bilang alaal, sinulat ni Jose Rizal: “Namatay siyang hindi naisakatuparan ang isang dakilang adhikain na inilaan sa kanya ng kanyang talinong hindi-mapantayan. Hindi luha ang kanyang pinakamimithing kasaysayan kundi ang nakikitang gawa: Hindi para sa kanyang sarili, kundi para sa kanyang bayan.”</p>"}}},"address":"Jose Panganiban, Camarines Norte","name":"Jose Ma. Panganiban y Enverga","region":"Bicol Region"},"Q52811192":{"locPhoto":{"width":1280,"file":"Gota de Leche 09.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":1920,"hash":"e0"},"lon":120.9884,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of the building, to the left and slightly behind the La Proteccion de la Infancia, Inc. historical marker.","wikipedia":{"Natividad Almeda-López":true},"date":"1992-09-08","macroAddress":"Sampaloc, Manila","lat":14.60278,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1892–1977)","title":"Natividad Almeda Lopez","inscription":"<p>Nangunang Filipinang nanungkulan bilang abogado; unang Filipinang hukom at mahistrado ng Hukuman sa Paghahabol. Ipinanganak, Seytembre 8, 1892. Nagkamit ng mga titulong Bachelor of Arts, Liceo de Manila, 1909; Licentiate in Jurisprudence, Escuela de Direcho de Manila, 1913; Master of Laws, 1937, at Doctor of Civil Law, 1938, kapwa buhat sa Pamantasan ng Santo Tomas. Tinanggap sa Bar, 1914. Nagsimulang maglingkod sa pamahalaan bilang special attorney, Kawanihan ng Katarungan, 1919. Nangulo sa iba’t ibang hukuman ng katarungan, 1931–1962. Humawak sa iba’t ibang katungkulan sa mga kilalang samahan at institusyong pansibiko at pangkawanggawa. Pangulo, La Proteccion de la Infancia, (Kagota de Leche), 1936–1977. Tagapagtatag, Manila Children’s and Lying-in Hospital. Kinatawan sa maraming mahahalagang kapulungang pangdaigdig. Tumanggap ng mga Gawad Pampangulo dahil sa kanyang pangunguna sa mga kilusang pangkababaihan, 1955; para sa kanyang pakikibaka para sa kilusan sa pagboto ng mga kababaihan sa bansa, 1966; dahil sa kanyang napakabisang pangunguna tungo sa pagkilala sa mga karapatan ng mga Filipina, 1968. Namatay, Enero 23, 1977.</p>"}}},"address":"Gota de Leche Building, 859 Sergio H. Loyola Street, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Natividad Almeda Lopez","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q24243017":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the monument dedicated to the Fifteen Martyrs of Bicol.","wikipedia":{"Fifteen Martyrs of Bicol":true},"locPhoto":{"width":768,"file":"Plaza Quince Martires.jpg","credit":"Melandriaromero {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"6f","height":1024},"lon":123.18593,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2000,"file":"Labinlimang Martir ng Bikol historical marker 2.jpg","credit":"Photo: Jblaza; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"d5","height":2591},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Mga ilustrado ng Bikol na dinakip at nilitis ng Komisyong Militar noong 29 Disyembre 1896 sa bintang na balak na pagpatay sa lahat ng Kastila sa iba't ibang dako ng Kabikulan. Walang kasalanan sa krimeng ibinibintang sa kanila. Sila ay binaril sa Luneta, Maynila, noong 4 Enero 1897. </p><p> Mga binaril: Domingo Abella, Manuel Abella, P. Severino Diaz, P. Inocencio Herrera, Camilo Jacob, Florencio Lerma, Mariano Melgarejo, Cornelio Mercado, P. Gabriel Prieto, Tomas Prieto at Macario Valentin. Namatay sa bilangguan: Leon Hernandez at Mariano Ordenanza. Namatay samantalang tapon: Ramon Abella at Mariano Araña. </p><p> Ang bangkay ng mga martir na ito ay inilagak sa iisang hukay na hindi natunton kailanman.</p>","title":"Labinlimang Martir ng Bikol","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Plaza Quince Martires, Peñafrancia Avenue, Naga, Camarines Sur","region":"Bicol Region","name":"Labinlimang Martir ng Bikol","lat":13.62445,"macroAddress":"Naga, Camarines Sur","date":"1982"},"Q24705272":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.525,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Gala–Rodriguez House":"Gala–Rodriguez Ancestral House"},"macroAddress":"Sariaya, Quezon","date":"2008","lat":13.96194,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a heritage house by the National Historical Institute 14 May 2008</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Gala–Rodriguez House"},"photo":{"hash":"55","height":1353,"file":"Historical Marker Gala-Rodriguez House.jpg","credit":"Zernan2014 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1508}}},"address":"Gala–Rodriguez House, Rizal Street cor. Gomez Street, Sariaya, Quezon","name":"Gala–Rodriguez House","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q41082784":{"address":"Sta. Lucia Street cor. Real Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pintong Sta. Lucia","inscription":"<p>Ito ang ikalawang pintong nakaharap sa Look ng Maynila na nasa panulukan ng Daang Real at Daang Sta. Lucia. Muling ginawa noong 1781 ni inhinyero ng hukbo na si Thomas Sanz noong panahon ni Gobernador Heneral Jose Basco at Vargas, sa dating pook na kinaroroonan ng unang pinto. Nasira noong 1945 dahil sa digmaan. Ang bahagi ay muling ginawa ng Intramuros Restoration Committee sa tulong ng abuloy ng Marinduque Mining and Industrial Corporation, ng pambansang pamahalaan, at ng Lungsod ng Maynila.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres; perspective correction: Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Pintong Sta. Lucia.jpg","width":349,"height":535,"hash":"ea"}}},"name":"Pintong Sta. Lucia","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1968","lat":14.58845,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Gates of Intramuros":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97365},"Q25068837":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.94012,"address":"Imus Arsenal, Imus, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Arsenal ng Imus","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito, noong 1896, itinatag ng Tsinong panday na si Jose Ignacio Paua, na naging Heneral noong Himagsikang Pilipino laban sa Espanya at Labanang Pilipino - Amerikano, ang isang Arsenal sa utos ni Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo. Dito ginawa at kinumpuni ang mga baril at lantaka ng mga manghihimagsik sa tulong ng iba pa niyang kapwa Tsino at Rebolusyonaryo.</p>"},"photo":{"width":480,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Imus Arsenal 03.JPG","hash":"b1","height":640}}},"name":"Arsenal ng Imus","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Imus, Cavite","date":"1990","lat":14.42967},"Q55833851":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>This is a Heritage House pursuant to Board Resolution No. 3 dated April 6, 1993 of the National Historical Institute of the Republic of the Philippines.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Cesar Lacson Locsin Ancestral House"},"photo":{"width":4124,"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker Cesar Lacson Locsin Ancestral House.JPG","height":2742,"hash":"9c"}}},"address":"Cesar Lacson Locsin Ancestral House, Rizal Street, Silay, Negros Occidental","name":"Cesar Lacson Locsin Ancestral House","region":"Western Visayas","date":"1995","macroAddress":"Silay, Negros Occidental","lat":10.79831,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the center of the building facade.","wikipedia":{"Cesar Lacson Locsin Ancestral House":true},"locPhoto":{"file":"El Ideal 6.JPG","credit":"ClaireMRA {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1936,"height":1288,"hash":"ad"},"lon":122.97535},"Q46996468":{"lat":14.3988,"date":"1957-04-04","macroAddress":"Tanza, Cavite","address":"Felipe G. Calderon Elementary School, San Agustin Street, Tanza, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Guro, manananggol, manunulat, pantas, at makabayan. Bumalangkas ng Saligang-Batas ng Kaunaunahang Republika ng Pilipinas. Nagtatag ng Colegio de Abogados de Filipinas at ng Escuela de Derecho de Manila, 1899. Kaunaunahang Pangulo ng Asociacion de Tagalistas, 1904. Tagapagtatag, Asociacion Historica de Filipinas, 1905. Anak nina Jose Gonzales Calderon at Manuela Roca; ipinanganak sa Tanza (Santa Cruz de Malabon), Kabite, 4 Abril 1868. Nanirahan sa purok ng Santa Ana. Namatay sa Maynila, 6 Hunyo 1908.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Felipe G. Calderon"},"photo":null}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Felipe G. Calderon","lon":120.85523,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Felipe Calderón":"Felipe Calderón (Filipino politician)"}},"Q54505642":{"date":"1984","macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","lat":14.66459,"name":"Ang Sigaw ng Pugad Lawin","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":1920,"hash":"bf","file":"Cry of Pugad Lawin 01.jpg","credit":"MIKELAAGAN {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1280},"text":{"subtitle":"(1896)","title":"Ang Sigaw ng Pugad Lawin","inscription":"<p>Sa paligid ng pook na ito, si Andres Bonifacio at mga isang libong Katipunero ay nagpulong noong umaga ng ika-23 Agosto 1896, at ipinasyang maghimagsik laban sa pamahalaang Kastila sa Pilipinas. Bilang patunay ay pinagpunit-punit ang kanilang mga sedula na naging tanda ng pagkaalipin ng mga Pilipino. Ito ang kauna-unahang sigaw ng bayang api laban sa bansang Espanya na pinatibayan sa pamamagitan ng paggamit ng sandata.</p>"}}},"address":"Seminary Road, Brgy. Bahay Toro, Project 8, Quezon City, Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.01756,"wikipedia":{"Cry of Pugad Lawin":true},"locDesc":null},"Q54810346":{"wikipedia":{"Candon Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located below the left niche on the church facade.","lon":120.44888,"locPhoto":{"width":2048,"file":"Candon church facade.jpg","credit":"Danny b11 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"f0","height":1536},"region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Simbahan ng Candon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":2100,"hash":"81","width":1775,"file":"Simbahan ng Candon historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng Candon","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga misyonerong Agustino, 1591. Itinayo, 1695. Nasira ng lindol, 1707 at isinaayos, 1709–1713. Muling isinaayos, 1865. Kinubkob ng mga Rebolusyonaryo sa pamumuno ni Isabelo Abaya ang kumbento ng simbahan, 25 Marso 1898. Naligtas ang simbahan sa pagsunog ng mga Hapon sa bayan ng Candon, 1942.</p>"}}},"address":"San Juan Street, Candon, Ilocos Sur","lat":17.19344,"macroAddress":"Candon, Ilocos Sur","date":"2016-03-29"},"Q28912601":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Liwasan ng Dapitan historical marker 08.jpg","width":924,"hash":"88","height":1369},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinaayos ayon sa plano ni Jose Rizal habang nakadistiyero sa Dapitan, 1892-1896. May limang landas patungo sa kiyoskong kinatatayuan ngayon ng bantayog ng pambansang bayani. Itinanim ni Rizal ang mga punong akasya sa liwasan. Ipinagkaoob niya ang sistemang pangliwanag na gumagamit ng langis ng niyog mula sa bayao ng isang pasyenteng Ingles. Binuo ni Rizal at ng kanyang dating guro P. Francisco de Padua Sanchez, S.J., ang mapa ng Mindanao, sa tulong ng mga tauhan ng simbahan at ng mga mag-aaral ng paaralang parokyal ng Dapitan, 1892. Inayos ang mapa noong panahon ni Jose Aseniero, dating mag-aaral ni Rizal, Gobernador ng Zamboanga, 1925-1928. Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan, 13 Marso 2002 at ang mapa ng Mindanao bilang isang Yamang Pangkalinangan ng Pambansang Museo, 20 Hunyo 2005.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Liwasan ng Dapitan"}}},"address":"Dapitan Park, City Hall Drive, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","name":"Liwasan ng Dapitan","lat":8.65493,"macroAddress":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","date":"2003","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete pedestal at the western portion of the park.","wikipedia":null,"lon":123.42409,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Liwasan ng Dapitan Marker.JPG","width":2848,"height":4288,"hash":"d4"}},"Q41757852":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96996,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Rizal Shrine":"Rizal Shrine (Intramuros)"},"lat":14.59441,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"2013","address":"Rizal Shrine, Santa Clara Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang ladrilyong guho ay bahagi ng isa sa pinakamatandang gusali sa Fort Santiago. Itinayo bilang kuwartel para sa mga sundalong Espanyol, 1593. Dito ikinulong si Jose Rizal, 3 Nobyembre–29 Disyembre 1896, bago ang pagbaril sa kanya sa Bagumbayan, ngayo’y Liwasang Rizal, noong 30 Disyembre 1896. </p><p> Bahagi ng deklarasyon ng Fort Santiago bilang pambansang dambana sa bisa ng RA 597, 6 Marso 1951. Muling ipinatayo, 1953. Ipinahayag bilang sagradong pook sa bisa ng PD 105, 24 Enero 1973.</p><p>Pinangasiwaan ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan, 19 Hunyo 1965, hanggang sa kasalukuyan.</p>","title":"Dambanang Rizal sa Fort Santiago","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":326,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Dambanang Rizal sa Fort Santiago.jpg","height":448,"hash":"01"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Dambanang Rizal sa Fort Santiago"},"Q54806489":{"lat":17.57557,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":2959,"file":"Historical Marker Birthplace of Father Burgos (cropped).jpg","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":3158,"hash":"54"},"text":{"title":"Birthplace of Father Burgos","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>At this place, town of Vigan, capital of the province of Ilocos Sur, Jose Apolonio Burgos, priest and martyr, was born February 9, 1837. His parents were Jose Burgos, an army lieutenant, and Dona Florencia Garcia. Father Burgos graduated from the University of Santo Tomas and held very high positions in the Cathedral of Manila. Throughout his ecclesiastical career he was a staunch advocate of the uplift of the secular clergy. He was executed in Bagumbayan field February 17, 1872, together with the Rev. Mariano Gomez and the Rev. Jacinto Zamora, for supposed implication in the military revolt of Cavite, January 20, 1872.</p>"}}},"address":"Calle Burgos, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Birthplace of Father Burgos","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.38581,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Burgos":true}},"Q53629298":{"date":"2001","macroAddress":"Palanan, Isabela","lat":17.05911,"name":"Ang Pagdakip kay Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo","region":"Cagayan Valley","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bahay na nakatayo sa pook na ito nadakip si Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo ng isang pangkat ng Iskawt Macabebe kasama ang dating opisyal ng Hukbo ni Aguinaldo na sina Hilario Tal Placido at Lazaro Segovia at apat na Amerikano sa pamumuno ni Brigadyer Heneral Frederick Funston noong hapon ng Marso 23, 1901. </p><p>Inilagay ang panandang pangkasaysayan noong ipagdiwang ang ika-100 taon ng makasaysayang pangyayaring ito.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Pagdakip kay Heneral Emilio Aguinaldo"}}},"address":"Poblacion, Palanan, Isabela","lon":122.42908,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Emilio Aguinaldo":true,"First Philippine Republic":true},"locDesc":null},"Q45206250":{"lat":14.43802,"macroAddress":"Bacoor, Cavite","date":"2017-12-01","region":"Calabarzon","name":"San Ezekiel Moreno","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Paring Agustino Rekoleto at santo. Isinilang sa La Rioja, Espanya, 9 Abril 1848. Dumating sa Maynila, 10 Pebrero 1870. Naordenahang pari sa Katedral ng Maynila, 2 Hunyo 1871. Kabilang sa mga nagtatag ng bayan ng Puerto Princesa bilang unang misyonero, kapelyan ng mga militar at ng colonya penal, 4 Marso 1872. Mula 1873 hanggang 1885, naging kura paroko ng Calapan (Mindoro), Las Piñas, Santo Tomas (Batangas), Sta. Cruz (Maynila) at tagapamahala ng Hacienda ng Imus. Yumao sa Espanya sa sakit na kanser, 19 Agosto 1906. Idineklarang santo ni Papa Juan Pablo II dahil sa ipinakitang kabanalan, kapuri-puring halimbawa, at taospusong pagsilbi sa mga kapuspalad at mga maysakit sa Pilipinas, Espanya at Colombia, 11 Oktubre 1992. Itinuturing na santo at patron ng mga may kanser.</p>","title":"San Ezekiel Moreno","subtitle":"1848–1906"},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"San Ezekiel Moreno historical marker (Bacoor).jpg","width":2466,"height":3673,"hash":"b9"}}},"address":"Bacoor, Cavite","locPhoto":{"hash":"0f","height":3000,"file":"Saint Ezekiel Moreno y Diaz Park (Bacoor) - 3.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4000},"lon":120.97537,"wikipedia":{"Ezequiél Moreno y Díaz":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a pedestal just to the west of the statue of the saint."},"Q55392314":{"details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Lingayen Beach historical marker.JPG","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1890,"hash":"f2","height":3123},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Lingayen Beach","inscription":"<p>On this beach, General Lloyd Wheaton landed his troops on 7 November 1898 to cut off the retreat of General Emilio Aguinaldo; and General of the army Douglas Macarthur began his campaign on 9 January 1945 for the liberation of Luzon from the Japanese invaders.</p>"}}},"address":"Pangasinan Provincial Capitol, Lingayen, Pangasinan","name":"Lingayen Beach","region":"Ilocos Region","date":"1948","macroAddress":"Lingayen, Pangasinan","lat":16.03444,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the north side of a simple concrete war memorial near the World War II memorabilia site.","wikipedia":{"Philippine–American War":true,"Battle of Luzon":true},"lon":120.23122,"locPhoto":{"credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"IJVLingayenBeach2.jpg","width":3872,"height":2592,"hash":"9f"}},"Q55365118":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Teodoro Yangco Monument & Marker in front of the San Antonio Town Hall in Zambales.jpg","width":3456,"hash":"e6","height":4608},"lon":120.08965,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the monument pedestal in front the municipal hall.","wikipedia":{"Teodoro R. Yangco":true},"date":"2005","macroAddress":"San Antonio, Zambales","lat":14.94829,"address":"San Antonio Municipal Hall, T.R. Yangco Street, San Antonio, Zambales","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":2582,"hash":"95","width":1816,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Teodoro Yangco Monument & Marker in front of the San Antonio Town Hall in Zambales (cropped).jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pilantropo at mangangalakal. Isinilang sa San Antonio, Zambales, 9 Nobyembre 1861. Nagtapos sa Ateneo ng Rachiller en Artes at abogasya sa Universidad de Santo Tomas. Nagtapos ng komersyo sa Ealing College, London, 1886. Nagtatag ng sariling kumpanya at pagawaan ng mga barkong pampasahero. May-ari ng Bazaar Siglo XX na bumibili at nagtitinda ng pangkalahatang kalakal. Nanungkulan bilang Filipino Resident Commissioner sa Washington, D.C. 1917–1920, kung saan nakatulong siya sa pagpasa ng batas sa taripang katig sa mga produktong galing sa Pilipinas. Aktibo sa pagsulong sa mga proyektong pangkawang gawa. Presidente ng ilang institusyong pangsibiko tulad ng Young Men’s Christian Association, Kapisanang Laban sa Tuberkolosis, at Gota de Leche. Tinaguriang Ama ng Y.M.C.A. Namatay, 20 Abril 1939.</p>","title":"Teodoro R. Yangco","subtitle":"(1861–1939)"}}},"name":"Teodoro R. Yangco","region":"Central Luzon"},"Q37784067":{"lon":120.59758,"locPhoto":{"height":2000,"hash":"9e","file":"Cape Bojeador Lighthouse, Burgos, Ilocos Norte.JPG","credit":"Ma. Isabel Sheila Solidum {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3008},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the entrance of the first floor pavilion of the lighthouse complex.","wikipedia":{"Cape Bojeador Lighthouse":true},"macroAddress":"Burgos, Ilocos Sur","date":"2005","lat":18.51211,"address":"Cape Bojeador Lighthouse, Burgos, Ilocos Sur","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Idinisenyo ni Inhenyero Magin Pers y Pers, 1887. Isinaayos at natapos ng Servicio de Faros sa ilalim ni Inhenyero Guillermo Brockman, 1890. Itinayo bilang Faro de Primera Orden na may tore at mga pabelyon sa burol na Vigia de Nagparitan ng bayan ng Burgos. Nagsilbing gabay-tanglaw sa mga sasakyang pandagat mula 1892 hanggang sa kasalukuyan. Natatanging halimbawa ng parola at arkitektura ng ikalabinsiyam na dantaon. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandang Pangkasaysayan ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan, 13 Agosto 2004, at Pambansang Yamang Pangkalinangan ng Pambansang Museo, 20 Hunyo 2005.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Parola ng Cape Bojeador"},"photo":{"width":1158,"file":"Cape Bojeador Lighthouse Historical Marker (cropped).jpg","credit":"Popodiaz {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"30","height":1443}}},"name":"Ang Parola ng Cape Bojeador","region":"Ilocos Region"},"Q24033363":{"name":"Catholic Church of Sarrat","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Catholic Church of Sarrat","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Formerly named Church of San Miguel in commemoration of the arrival at Sarrat of the first missionaries on the feast of San Miguel, 29 September 1725; Now named Sarrat by the Philippine legislature in 1916, restored the original name of the town, Sarrat. First convent constructed 1769 served as temporary church; Destroyed by fire 16 March 1816; Church and tower were constructed 1779; Another convent was built under the supervision of Father Vicente Berragro and finished May 1817; Burned again 18 October 1882; A third convent was built and completed June 1896.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Sarrat Church, Sarrat, Ilocos Norte","date":"1959","macroAddress":"Sarrat, Ilocos Norte","lat":18.1558,"wikipedia":{"Sarrat Church":"Santa Monica Parish Church (Sarrat)"},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.6445,"locPhoto":null},"Q31997939":{"macroAddress":"Bacoor, Cavite","date":"2015-03-10","lat":14.46395,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa lugar na ito lumaban ang mga rebolusyonaryong Pilipino sa dalawang labanan upang mabawi ang Cavite sa mga Espanyol at pigilan ang tuluyang pagsakop ng mga Amerikano: una, sa pangunguna ni Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo laban sa mga Espanyol, 17 Pebrero 1897, na pinagwagian ng mga Pilipino ngunit ikinasawi ni Hen. Edilberto Evangelista; at ang huli, sa pangunguna nina Hen. Artemio Ricarte at Mariano Noriel laban sa mga Amerikano, 13 Hunyo 1899.</p><p>Ipinahayag bilang Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan sa bisa ng Resolusyon Blg. 11 ng Pambansang Komisyong Pangkasaysayan ng Pilipinas, 9 Setyembre 2013.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Zapote","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":3433,"hash":"6f","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Labanan sa Zapote historical marker.jpg","width":2342}}},"address":"Zapote Bridge, Aguinaldo Highway, Las Piñas, Metro Manila / Zapote Bridge, Aguinaldo Highway, Bacoor, Cavite","name":"Labanan sa Zapote","region":["Metro Manila","Calabarzon"],"lon":120.96636,"locPhoto":{"hash":"cd","height":3000,"width":4000,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Zapote Bridge looking southward.jpg"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the middle of the southeastern side of the bridge.","wikipedia":{"Battle of Zapote River":true,"Battle of Zapote Bridge":"Battle of Zapote Bridge (1897)"}},"Q54555325":{"wikipedia":{"Andres Bonifacio":"Andrés Bonifacio"},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.97254,"locPhoto":null,"name":"Andres Bonifacio","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"1e","height":526,"file":"Andres Bonifacio 1863 - 1897.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":352},"text":{"subtitle":"1863–1897","title":"Andres Bonifacio","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa pook na ito nong ika-30 ng Nobyembre, 1863. Lumaki sa pagdaralita ngunit natuto sa sariling pagsisikap at likas na katalinuhan. Lumabas sa mga dulang Tagalog sa pamamahala ng <u>Teatro Porvenir</u> sa Trozo. Itinatag ang mapanghimagsik na <u>Katipunan nang manga Anak nang Bayan</u> noong ika-7 ng Hulyo, 1892 na ang layo’y makamtan ang kasarinlan ng bayan. Namuno sa paghihimagsik laban sa mga Kastila noong 1896 na humantong sa Republika ng Pilipinas noong 1899. </p><p>Namatay sa Kabite noong ika-10 ng Mayo, 1897.</p>"}}},"address":"Claro M. Recto Avenue, Tutuban, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1974","macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","lat":14.60664},"Q44558486":{"locPhoto":{"width":3869,"file":"Plaza Cuartel Entrance.jpg","credit":"Daxster16 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"ec","height":2281},"lon":118.72965,"locDesc":"The historical markers are located on either side of the main entrance gate; the Tagalog marker on the left and the English marker on the right.","wikipedia":{"Palawan massacre":true},"date":true,"macroAddress":"Puerto Princesa","lat":9.74014,"address":"Plaza Cuartel, Taft Street, Puerto Princesa","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>On this site, once a military base during the Second World War, some 150 American prisoners of war were burned to death by Japanese soldiers, 14 December 1944. A few survivors swam to Iwahig. The remains of those who died were brought and interred in a common grave at the Jefferson Barracks National Cemetery, St. Louis County, Missouri, United States of America, 1952.</p>","title":"Plaza Cuartel","subtitle":null},"photo":null,"date":"2016-04-22"},"tl":{"date":"2005-03-05","photo":{"width":3000,"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker at the Plaza Cuartel.JPG","hash":"e5","height":4512},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito na dating tanggulang militar noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig naganap ang pagsunog ng mga sundalong Hapon sa humigit kumulang 150 Amerikanong bihag ng digma noong 14 Disyembre 1944. Ilang nakaligtas ay lumangoy sa dagat patungong Iwahig. Ang mga labi ng mga nasawi ay dinala at inilibing sa St. Louis County sa isang panlahatang libingan sa Jefferson Barracks National Cemetery, Missouri, Estados Unidos, 1952.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Plaza Cuartel"}}},"name":"Plaza Cuartel","region":"Mimaropa"},"Q28937532":{"lon":125.6255,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":7.07532,"date":"2003","macroAddress":"Davao City","region":"Davao Region","name":"Port Sta. Ana","address":"Magsaysay Park, Leon Garcia Street cor. Monteverde Avenue, Davao City","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dinaungan ng mga unang manggagawang agrikultural na Hapon sa Davao, Mayo 1903 na nanguna sa pagpapaunlad ng industriya ng abaka dito.</p>","title":"Port Sta. Ana","subtitle":null},"photo":null}}},"Q55110971":{"date":"1966-04-16","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Laguna","lat":14.25114,"address":"Santa Cruz, Laguna","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":704,"file":"Hm burialEmilioJacito.jpg","credit":"Tabunon {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":960,"hash":"40"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pook na Pinaglibingan kay Emilio Jacinto","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito inilibing si Emilio Jacinto na namatay noong ika-16 ng Abril, 1899. Si Jacinto ay sumapi sa Kataas-taasang Katipunan ng mga Anak ng Bayan (KKK) o Katipunan noong 1894 na may sagisag na “Pingkian”. Naging kalihim ng samahan at kanang-kamay ni Andres Bonifacio. May akda ng “Kartilya”, “Liwanag at Dilim”, at iba pa. Kasamang nagtatag ng pahayagang Kalayaan at sumulat sa sagisag na “Dimas-Ilaw”. Ang kanyang mga labi ay inilipat sa Mausoleo de los Veteranos de la Revolucion sa Manila noong 18 ng Disyembre 1921, at noong Disyembre 1976 sa Dambanang Emilio Jacinto sa Himlayang Pilipino, Lungsod ng Quezon.</p>"}}},"name":"Pook na Pinaglibingan kay Emilio Jacinto","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.408,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Emilio Jacinto":true}},"Q48123589":{"name":"Insular Life","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Insular Life Corporate Centre, Insular Life Drive, Alabang, Muntinlupa, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Insular Life historical marker.jpg","width":2011,"hash":"ca","height":3000},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang kumpanyang Filipino sa pagseseguro sa Pilipinas, itinatag bilang Insular Life Assurance Co., Ltd. sa Maynila, 25 Nobyembre 1910. Antonio Ma. Barretto, unang pangulo. Unang opisina, Lack & Davis Bldg., Echague, Santa Cruz, Maynila. Nagkaroon ng sariling gusali, Plaza Moraga, Binondo, 1931. Nagbukas ng sangay, Honolulu, 1934, Lungsod ng Cebu, unang tanggapang pangdistrito nito, 1938. Sinakop ang Filipinas Life Assurance Co., 1943. Nagpatuloy ang operasyon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1941–1945. Sinakop ang Occidental Life Insurance Co. of California sa Pilipinas, 1954. Unang nagbigay ng segurong pang-industriyal, 1958. Lumipat ang opisina sa Makati, 1963; sa Muntinlupa, 2001.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Insular Life"}}},"date":"2010-11-25","macroAddress":"Muntinlupa, Metro Manila","lat":14.41909,"wikipedia":{"Insular Life":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a wall to the right of the main entrance of Insular Life Corporate Centre.","locPhoto":{"height":4000,"hash":"ed","width":3000,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Insular Life historical marker vicinity - 2.jpg"},"lon":121.03838},"Q55345233":{"lat":14.23436,"macroAddress":"Pila, Laguna","date":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":1024,"hash":"e6","file":"Marker of the Historic Town of Pila.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph M. Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":768},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating naluklok sa Pinagbayanan at inilipat sa Pagalangan. Pinagkalooban ng mga Kastila ng titulong La Noble Villa de Pila noong simula ng ika-17 dantaon dahil sa kadalisayan ng kaugalian at tradisyon ng mga mamamayan nito. Inilipat sa Sitio ng Santa Clara na bahagi ng asyendang pag-aari ng magkakakpatid na sina Felizardo, Miguel at Rafael de Rivera bago matapos ang ika-18 dantaon. Ginawa ang balangkas ng bayan ni Felizardo de Rivera na makikita pa hanggang sa kasalukuyan bilang isang halimbawa ng pagpaplanong bayan noong panahon ng mga Kastila. Ipinahayag ang makasaysayang pook ng bayan na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 17 Mayo 2000.</p>","title":"Pila","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Pila, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Pila","lon":121.36414,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Pila":"Pila, Laguna"}},"Q28927514":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Sakahan ni Rizal 1.jpg","width":1287,"height":824,"hash":"24"},"lon":123.29666,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the Jose Rizal monument.","wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true,"Jose Rizal Farm":"José Rizal Farm"},"macroAddress":"Katipunan, Zamboanga del Norte","date":"2011-07-17","lat":8.50128,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Sakahan ni Jose Rizal","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Binili at nilinang ni Rizal ang sakahan na dating pag-aari ni Calixto Carreon na naging pasyente niya habang nasa Dapitan. Inatasan ang kapatid na si Trinidad Rizal na pangasiwaan ang pangangalaga nito, at lumaon namang inilipat kay Fernando Eguia, mag-aaral ni Rizal at naging katiwala sa sakahan. Ipinagbili ni Trinidad kay Crisostomo Eguia Sr. Saksi ang ibang mga kapatid ni Rizal sa kasunduang panatilihan ang sakahan sa pangalan ni Jose Rizal, 1949.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"cc","height":541,"file":"Rizal Farm historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":409}}},"address":"Jose Rizal Farm, Katipunan, Zamboanga del Norte","name":"Sakahan ni Jose Rizal","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula"},"Q35004190":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":124.40502,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Rekoleto sa ilalim ng patronato ni Santa Filomena, 1863. Ipinatayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan at kumbento yari sa kahoy, 1874. Ginamit ang kumbento bilang himpilan ng puwersang Amerikano sa kanilang kampanya laban sa mga Boholano, Hulyo 1901. Nakaligtas sa pagsunog ng mga Amerikano sa bayan ng Duero, Oktubre 1901. Ipingalan sa Nuestra Señora Inmaculada Concepcion, 1969. Isa sa mga nananatiling sinaunang simbahang yari sa kahoy.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Duero"},"photo":null}},"address":"Immaculate Conception Parish Church, Duero, Bohol","name":"Simbahan ng Duero","region":"Central Visayas","date":"2015","macroAddress":"Duero, Bohol","lat":9.70773},"Q55298469":{"date":"1984","macroAddress":"Mauban, Quezon","lat":14.18997,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Pransiskano noong 1583 sa Pinagbayanan (ngayo’y Luya-Luya). Inilipat sa Balay-Balay upang makaiwas sa mga piratang Moro. Muling inilipat noong 1678 sa Sulida, ang kasalukuyang pook. Pinangalanang Mauban susog kay Gat Uban, ang tagapagtanggol ng bayan sa mga Moro. Itinatag ang sangay ng Katipunan sa nayon ng San Miguel, 1896; ang deposito ng tubig, 1810; ang pantalan, 1930; at ang seawall, 1935. Nilusob ng Hukbong Hapon, Disyembre 24, 1941, at napalaya ng Hukbong Amerikano, 1945.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Bayan ng Mauban"},"photo":null}},"address":"Mauban Municipal Hall, San Buenaventura Street, Mauban, Quezon","name":"Ang Bayan ng Mauban","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.73165,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Mauban":true}},"Q43302115":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.09193,"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Unang Misa sa Baryo ng Jesus de la Peña","address":"P. Zamora Street, Marikina, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa dating kinatatayuan ng isang bodega na kinatitirikan ngayon ng simbahang ito ay ginanap ang unang misa noong Abril 16, 1630, sa kapahintulutan ni Padre Pedro de Arce, Obispo ng Maynila. Ang misa ay ginanap ng mga misyonerong Heswita na nakatuklas sa imahen ni Cristo sa isang talampas at sinamba sa buong bayan ng Jesus de la Peña na ngayon ay isang baryo ng Marikina.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Unang Misa sa Baryo ng Jesus de la Peña"},"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Unang Misa sa Baryo ng Jesus de la Peña.jpg","width":377,"hash":"ca","height":514}}},"lat":14.6342,"macroAddress":"Marikina, Metro Manila","date":"1970-04-16"},"Q28942552":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Makhdum Karim":true,"Sheik Karimol Makhdum Mosque":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":119.84925,"address":"Sheik Karimol Makhdum Mosque, Brgy. Tubig Indangan, Simunul, Tawi-Tawi","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"b1","height":1600,"width":1116,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Sheik Makhdum Mosque historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Sheik Makhdum Mosque","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sinasabi ng mga mananalaysay na ang Islam ay pinalakas sa Pilipinas ni Sheik Makhdum, isang misyonerong Arabe, unang lumunsad sa Tubig-Indangan, Simunul sa pulo ng Tawi-Tawi noong 1380. Dito niya ipinatayo ang kauna-unahang simbahang Muslim sa kapuluan ng Pilipinas na hangang sa kasalukuyan ay nakatayo bilang bahagi ng muling ipinagawang “Tahanan ni Allah.” Pinaniniwalaang ang orihinal na simbahan ay nagtagal ng humigit-kumulan sa 500 taon. Ang orihinal na haligi ay yari sa ipil at pinangangalagaan hanggang sa kasalukuyan.</p>"}}},"name":"Sheik Makhdum Mosque","region":"Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao","macroAddress":"Simunul, Tawi-Tawi","date":"1980-11-07","lat":4.89805},"Q37621078":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Labanan sa Kalero","address":"Manila–Cavite Road, Noveleta, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":2856,"file":"BattleofNoveletajf3101 04.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"c9","height":4284},"text":{"title":"Labanan sa Kalero","subtitle":"Nobeleta, Kabite","inscription":"<p>Sa tulay na ito naganap ang isang mahigpit na labanan noong ika-10 ng Nobyembre, 1896. Mahigit sa 400 na kawal ni Heneral Diego de Los Rios ng pamahalaang Kastila ang napatay ng mga magigiting na manghihimagsik ng sangguniang Magdiwang sa pamumuno ni Koronel Luciano San Miguel at sa tulong ng matibay na Tanggulang Blg. 2.</p><p>Nagtagumpay ang mga Magdiwang sa pamomook na ito.</p>"}}},"lat":14.44147,"date":"1983","macroAddress":"Noveleta, Cavite","wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the southern end of the northbound side of Soriano Bridge along the Manila–Cavite Road.","lon":120.87907,"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"d6","width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"BattleofNoveletajf3112 02.JPG"}},"Q22340926":{"lat":14.21373,"date":"1951","macroAddress":"Calamba, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Birthplace of Jose Rizal","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Restored by Executive Order No. 145 of President Elpidio Quirino with funds mainly contributed by school children of the Philippines. Inaugurated, 1950. Architect: Juan F. Nakpil.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Birthplace of Jose Rizal"},"photo":{"height":3442,"hash":"7d","width":2500,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Birthplace of Jose Rizal historical marker.jpg"}}},"address":"Rizal Shrine, Jose Rizal Street, Calamba, Laguna","locPhoto":{"file":"Calambajf2779 13.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608,"hash":"be","height":3456},"lon":121.16669,"wikipedia":{"Rizal Shrine":"Rizal Shrine (Calamba)","José Rizal":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main door of the house."},"Q46883970":{"macroAddress":"Murcia, Negros Occidental","date":"2006-04-29","lat":10.51222,"name":"Ishiwata Bath House","region":"Western Visayas","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3000,"credit":"Photo: Jblaza; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Ishiwata Bath House historical marker.jpg","height":2909,"hash":"da"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ishiwata Bath House","inscription":"<p>Itinayo bilang bahagi ng Mambukal Resort na may disenyong neo-classical ni Kokichi Paul Ishiwata, 1927. Mula sa Bundok Kanlaon ang tubig na dumaloy sa anim na kubol na may paliguan, mga tanging nalalabing orihinal na istruktura.</p>"}}},"address":"Mambukal, Murcia, Negros Occidental","lon":123.10353,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q46868165":{"lon":123.6418,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":10.10387,"date":"2010-05-29","macroAddress":"Carcar, Cebu","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Ang Dakong Balay","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical Institute 04 September 2009</p>","title":"Ang Dakong Balay","subtitle":"(Don Florencio Noel House)"},"photo":null}},"address":"Don Florencio Noel House, Santa Catalina Street, Carcar, Cebu"},"Q24764362":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ang Bayan ng Taal","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"d1","height":2808,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Ang Bayan ng Taal historical marker.jpg","width":1901},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang itinatag sa pook ng Balangon noong 1572. Dahil sa madalas na pagputok ng bulkan ay inilipat ang bayan sa kasalukuyang pook. Naging kabisera noong 1732 kaya't taal ang ipinangalan sa buong lalawigan. Nang muling masira ang bayan dahil sa pagputok ng bulkan noong 1754, ang kabisera ay inilipat sa batangan at isinunod dito ang pangalan ng lalawigan. Ang bulkan ng Taal, na pinakamaliit sa buong daigdig, at nasa gitna ng lawa ng Bonbon at sa bunganga ng bulkan ay may isang pulong nasa isa pang maliit na lawa. Pumutok ang bulkan noong 1634, 1635, 1641, 1709, 1718, 1723, 1731, 1749, 1754, 1867, 1874, 1880, 1911 at 1965. Ang ngayo'y mga bayan ng Lemery, San Luis, Agoncillo, San Nicolas, at Sta. Teresita ay dating sakop ng Taal.</p>","title":"Ang Bayan ng Taal","subtitle":"(1572)"}}},"address":"Taal Municipal Hall, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas","lat":13.88014,"date":"1972","macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","wikipedia":{"Taal":"Taal, Batangas"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main entrance of the municipal hall.","lon":120.92292,"locPhoto":{"hash":"79","height":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Taaljf2280 01.JPG","width":4608}},"Q24237251":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":4160,"file":"University of Nueva Caceres historical marker.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":3120,"hash":"54"},"text":{"title":"University of Nueva Caceres","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa daang Burgos, lungsod ng Naga sa pamumuno ni Dr. Jaime Hernandez, unang pangulo, 1948. Pinagtibay ng Securities and Exchange Commission bilang Nueva Caceres Colleges, 18 Mayo 1948. Binuksan ang sekondarya at mga kursong pangkolehiyo, 1 Hulyo 1948; elementarya at ROTC, 1949. Inilipat sa daang J. Hernandez, 1952. Unang paaralan sa Kabikulan na ginawaran ng katayuang unibersidad, 15 Disyembre 1954.</p>"}}},"address":"University of Nueva Caceres, J. Hernandez Avenue, Naga, Camarines Sur","name":"University of Nueva Caceres","region":"Bicol Region","macroAddress":"Naga, Camarines Sur","date":"2008","lat":13.62465,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"University of Nueva Caceres":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.1842},"Q43302082":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating Escuela de Niños, ang pinakamatandang paaralan ng Katoliko Romano sa Marinduque. Ginamit ang bahagi bilang carcel nang masunog ang Casa Real, 1856. Ginawa ang isa sa mga silid para sa cuadrillos, 1887. Ipinaayos bilang sangay ng Casa Real, 1891. Tribunal ng pamahalaang Kastila at Presidencia ng Himagsikang Pilipino. Muling ipinatayo bilang museo at aklatan, 1987.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Museo at Aklatan ng Boac"},"photo":null}},"address":"Mercader Street cor. 1 de Noviembre Street, Boac, Marinduque","name":"Museo at Aklatan ng Boac","region":"Mimaropa","macroAddress":"Boac, Marinduque","date":"1987-11-30","lat":13.44767,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.84006},"Q55364934":{"date":"2011-09-10","macroAddress":"Concepcion, Tarlac","lat":15.3243,"name":"Ang Tahanan ng Pamilyang Aquino","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Aquino Family Ancestral House historical marker in Concepcion, Tarlac.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"56"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito nanirahan ang tatlong henerasyon ng mga tanyag na Filipino: Heneral Servillano Aquino (1874–1959), lumahok sa Rebolusyong Filipino at Digmaang Filipino–Amerikano; Benigno Aquino, Sr. (1894–1947), Ispiker ng Pambansang Asamblea, kinatawan ng Tarlac, senador, at Kalihim ng Agrikultura at Komersyo; at Benigno Aquino, Jr. (1932–1983), punong lalawigan ng Tarlac, senador at lumaban sa rehimeng Marcos. </p><p>Ang tahanang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan sa bisa ng Board Resolution Blg. 1, s. 1987.</p>","title":"Ang Tahanan ng Pamilyang Aquino","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Aquino Ancestral House, F. Timbol Street cor. A. Luna Street, Concepcion, Tarlac","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.65708,"wikipedia":{"Servillano Aquino":true,"Benigno Aquino, Sr.":"Benigno Aquino Sr.","Benigno Aquino, Jr.":"Benigno Aquino Jr."},"locDesc":null},"Q52144885":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.55541,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"date":"1995-04-08","macroAddress":"Lucban, Quezon","lat":14.11405,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ipinatayo ng mag-asawang Pedro Nepomuceno y Villaseñor at Ana Maria Herrera y de la Concepcion ang isang malaking bahay na bato sa estilong neo-classical ilang taon makaraan ang kanilang kasal noong 1842. Nag-iisang yari sa ganitong estilo sa buong bayan ng Lucban ang bahay ay paboritong tuluyan ng mga kilalang panauhin mula sa Maynila at mga karatig bayan. Lalong kilala sa tawag na La Casa de Doña Ana bilang parangal sa butihing maybahay ng nagtatag ng Hospicio de Pobres de Lucban. Isang institusyong kanyang itinaguyod sa pamamagitan ng kanyang personal na pagkalinga sa mahihirap at mga maysakit. Binili ng mag-asawang Marcelo Dealo at Eduviges Veloso, 1946. Muling ipinagawa ng mga tagapagmanang sina Antonio at Milada Dealo-Valde, 1994 at pinanganlang La Doña Ana.</p>","title":"La Casa de Doña Ana","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"La Doña Ana, Quezon Avenue, Lucban, Quezon","name":"La Casa de Doña Ana","region":"Calabarzon"},"Q54552995":{"name":"Leoncio Asuncion","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"2e","height":575,"width":662,"file":"LeoncioAsuncion HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1813–1888)","title":"Leoncio Asuncion","inscription":"<p>Ama ng makabagong iskulturang panreliyon. Ipinanganak noong Setyembre 12, 1813 sa Sta. Cruz, Maynila. Nagtrabaho sa bantog na “Taller de Esculturas” noong 1830 at naging isa sa pinakamahusay na tagasalin ng garing at kahoy ng mga sining na panreliyon noong ika-19 na siglo. Lumilok ng bantong na “La Tercera Caida” ang kanyang mga obramaestra ay kilala dahil sa nakahahabag na anyo at sa pagkakatugma-tugma ng mga linyang anatomikal na isinagawa sa mga imaheng garing ng Pinagpalang Birheng Maria, Santo Cristo at marami pang iba. Namatay noong 1888.</p>"}}},"address":"Santa Cruz Church, Plaza Santa Cruz, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","date":"1983-09-12","lat":14.59943,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98022},"Q54567846":{"lat":14.50043,"date":"1984-03-04","macroAddress":"Parañaque, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Padre Pedro Dandan y Masangkay","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Padre Pedro Dandan y Masangkay","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Pari ng mga naghihimagsik at isa sa mga kampeon sa Pilipinismo. Isinilang sa Palanyag, Rizal (ngayon’y Parañaque, Metro Manila). Kagawad ng Orden ng mga Sekular, nasangkot sa Cavite Mutiny. Kasama nina Padre Jose Burgos, Mariano Gomes, Jacinto Zamora at iba pa noong Enero 20, 1872. Ipinatapon sa Pulo ng Marianas lulan ng Flores de Maria, Marso 14, 1872. Bumalik sa Pilipinas at naging pangalawang punong kantor (kinatawan ng punong kantor) pre-bendado at coadjutor ng arsobispo sa Katedral ng Maynila, 1895–1896. Sumapi sa pangkat ni Hen. Licerio Geronimo sa Bundok Buray, Montalban. Nahalal na pangulo ng kapulungan ng Pamahalaang Pangkagawaran ng Gitnang Luzon. Sumapi rin sa pangkat ni Hen. Emiliano Riego de Dios at Hen. Crispulo Aguinaldo. Namatay noong 1897.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"05","height":532,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Padre Pedro Dandan y Masangkay marker.jpg","width":384}}},"address":"Parañaque Cathedral, Quirino Avenue, La Huerta, Parañaque, Metro Manila","lon":120.99156,"locPhoto":{"file":"Fr. Pedro Dandan historical marker at the Parañaque Cathedral.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"hash":"47","height":4608},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting beside the statue of Fr. Pedro Dandan at the right side of the church belfry."},"Q54543728":{"lat":14.6043,"macroAddress":"Sampaloc, Manila","date":"1964","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Disyembre 8, 1964","inscription":"<p>Matamis na alaala ng mga anak-pawis sa Ama ng Kilusan sa Paggawa, Isabelo de los Reyes. Nagtatag ng unang kapisanan sa paggawa noong Pebrero 2, 1902, sa Sine Variadades sa Daang Sulukan, Sampalok, Maynila. Naging Konsehal, at Senador. Anak ng makatang si Leona Florentino, si Isabelo de los Reyes, ay ipinanganak sa Vigan, Ilocos Sur, noong Hulyo 7, 1864. Namatay noong Oktubre 10, 1938.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"04","height":2464,"file":"Disyembre 9, 1964 NHCP Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1500}}},"address":"Plaza Santa Teresita, P. Guevara Street, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Disyembre 8, 1964","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.99677,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Isabelo de los Reyes":true,"Union Obrera Democratica Filipina":"Unión Obrera Democrática Filipina"}},"Q35009205":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Santa Cruz Parish Church":"Maribojoc Church"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.84351,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":1095,"hash":"94","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Maribojoc Church historical marker.jpg","width":812},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga paring Heswita bilang misyon at parokya sa patronato ng Santa Cruz, 1767. Inilipat sa mga paring Recoletos, 1768. Inumpisahang ipatayo ni Padre Manuel Plaza, O.A.R. ang kasalukuyang simbahan na yari sa korales at bato, 1852. Natapos sa pamumuno ni Padre Fernando Rubio Lucas Martinez, O.A.R., 1872; ang kumbento at kampanaryo na may orasan, 1877-1898. Isinagawa ni Ray Francia ang mga pintadong obra sa loob ng simbahan, mga taong 1930. Ipinaayos ng Comite de Obras ang mga retablo, 1934. Nailigtas nang sunugin ang bayan ng Maribojoc noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1942-1945. Itinalaga bilang Diocesan Shrine of San Vicente Ferrer, 2005. Halimbawa ng arkitekturang kolonyal noong panahon ng mga Espanyol.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Maribojoc","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Santa Cruz Parish Church, Maribojoc, Bohol","name":"Simbahan ng Maribojoc","region":"Central Visayas","date":"2009","macroAddress":"Maribojoc, Bohol","lat":9.74045},"Q50426643":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Silliman University":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.30892,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Silliman University","inscription":"<p>Originally an elementary school founded in 1901 by Dr. and Mrs. David S. Hibbard under the terms of a gift by philanthropist, Dr. Horace B. Silliman, it was converted into a college in 1910 and a university in 1938. Its buildings were occupied by the Japanese forces from 1942 to 1945. It was reopened after the Second World War. The first Filipino president, Dr. Leopoldo T. Ruiz, was elected in 1952.</p>"}}},"address":"Silliman University, Rizal Avenue, Dumaguete, Negros Oriental","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Silliman University","lat":9.31123,"macroAddress":"Dumaguete, Negros Oriental","date":"1966"},"Q54073268":{"lon":121.16778,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Vicente Manansala":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"1984","macroAddress":"Binangonan, Rizal","lat":14.51586,"name":"Ang Bahay ni Vicente S. Manansala","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Bahay ni Vicente S. Manansala","inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, 1 Agosto 1973, na sinusugan ng mga Kautusan Bilang 375, 14 Enero 1974, at Bilang 1515, 11 Hunyo 1978, ang bahay na ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"73 Gloria Street cor. Aristorenas Street, Brgy. San Carlos, Binangonan, Rizal"},"Q37948341":{"lat":14.58319,"date":"1955","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Plaza Olivia Salamanca","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":1097,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Plaza Olivia Salamanca historical marker.jpg","hash":"f4","height":1755},"text":{"inscription":"<p>In memory of Olivia Salamanca, M.D., pioneer woman physician of the Philippines. Born in San Roque, Cavite on 1 July 1889; appointed government scholar in 1905; studied in Drexel Institute, Philadelphia. Died on 11 July 1913. A devoted and competent practitioner, she was a credit to the medical profession and an inspiration to her fellow women.</p>","title":"Plaza Olivia Salamanca","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Plaza Olivia Salamanca, Taft Avenue cor. T.M. Kalaw Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98389,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q27043938":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Manunulat at pantas ng kilusang propaganda. Isinilang, 1 Pebrero 1863, Mambulao (ngayo'y Jose Panganiban), Camarines Norte. Nag-aral sa ilalim ng mga pari ng La Congregacion de La Mision de San Vicente de Paul sa Seminario Conciliar de Nueva Caceres (ngayo'y Holy Rosary Minor Seminary), Nueva Caceres (ngayo'y Lungsod ng Naga), Camarines Sur. Nag-aral ng medisina sa Barcelona, Espanya, 1888, at naging aktibo sa Kilusang Propaganda sa pamamagitan ng pagsulat ng mga artikulo sa La Solidaridad na uminog sa kalayaan sa pamamahayag at reporma sa sistema ng edukasyon sa Pilipinas. Yumao sa Barcelona, 19 Agosto 1890, na ipinagluksa ng komunidad ng mga Pilipino sa Europa.</p>","subtitle":"1863–1890","title":"Jose Ma. Panganiban y Enverga"},"photo":{"height":4160,"hash":"c6","width":3120,"file":"Jose Ma. Panganiban historical marker.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"address":"Naga Central Road, Naga, Camarines Sur","name":"Jose Ma. Panganiban y Enverga","region":"Bicol Region","macroAddress":"Naga, Camarines Sur","date":"2016-02-01","lat":13.63154,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting beside the monument dedicated to Jose Ma. Panganiban.","wikipedia":{"José María Panganiban":true},"lon":123.18955,"locPhoto":{"width":3120,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jose Maria Panganiban Monument.jpg","height":4160,"hash":"92"}},"Q43223320":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.27756,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lat":13.46861,"macroAddress":"Bula, Camarines Sur","date":"1939","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"1b","height":2464,"credit":"Yawrei {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Church of Bula signage WTR.JPG","width":1632},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The town dates from 1578. The first church was destroyed by fire in 1676. The second church, built in 1688, was destroyed by a typhoon in 1700. The present Church was completed in 1706 and repaired in 1876 and 1885.</p>","title":"Church of Bula","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Bula, Camarines Sur","region":"Bicol Region","name":"Church of Bula"},"Q38226290":{"details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"JfBirthplaceGregorioSanciangcoMemorialfvf 09.JPG","hash":"c8","height":4608},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Birthplace of Gregorio Sanciangco","inscription":"<p>Lawyer, economist and writer. Born 7 March 1852, Malabon, Rizal, son of Eladio Sanciangco and Regina Gozon. Educated in the Philippines and Spain. Author of the first treatise on economics entitled “El Progreso de Filipinas.” Joined the reform movement led by Rizal. Became justice of the peace in Cabanatuan. Deported to Lingayen for sedition, 1888. Died 17 November 1897, Santo Domingo, Nueva Ecija.</p>"}}},"address":"Sanciangco Street, Tonsuya, Malabon, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Birthplace of Gregorio Sanciangco","lat":14.66213,"macroAddress":"Malabon, Metro Manila","date":"1952","locDesc":"The historical marker is located beneath the bust of Sanciangco.","wikipedia":{"Gregorio Sancianco":true},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"JfBirthplaceGregorioSanciangcoMemorialfvf 08.JPG","width":3456,"hash":"ee","height":4608},"lon":120.9563},"Q53709293":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Patrocinio Gamboa":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.56017,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Patrocinio Gamboa","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa pook na ito kina Fermin Gamboa at Leonarda Villareal, 30 Abril 1865. Sumapi sa Kilusang Rebolusyonaryo sa Iloilo, Marso 1898. Ipinagsapalaran ang kanyang buhay sa pagdadala ng bandila ng Pilipinas mula Jaro hanggang Santa Barbara, kung saan itinataas ito ni Heneral Martin Delgado nang pasinayaan ang pansamantalang Pamahalaang Rebolusyonaryo, 17 Nobyembre 1898. Inalagaan at inaruga ang mga nasugatan at maysakit sa panahon ng digmaan laban sa mga Amerikano. Yumao, 24 Nobyembre 1953 sa Molo, Iloilo.</p>"}}},"address":"Commission Civil Street cor. Jaime Street, Jaro, Iloilo City","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Patrocinio Gamboa","lat":10.72217,"date":"2015-04-30","macroAddress":"Iloilo City"},"Q53826179":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.57358,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"date":"2006-05-17","macroAddress":"Iloilo City","lat":10.69252,"name":"Plaza Libertad","region":"Western Visayas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Plaza Libertad","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Bantayog ng Kagitingan ng mga bayani ng Panay. Dito nagtipon at nagtaas ng watawat ng Pilipinas ang Puwersang Mapanghimagsik sa pamumuno ni Hen. Martin Delgado, tanda ng pagtatapos ng pamamahala ng mga Kastila sa Panay, 25 Disyembre 1898. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Pangkasaysayan, 17 Nobyembre 2003.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Plaza Libertad historical marker.JPG","credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","width":2304,"hash":"6d","height":3456}}},"address":"Plaza Libertad, J.M. Basa Street cor. Zamora Street, City Proper, Iloilo City"},"Q24061618":{"lat":14.59961,"macroAddress":"Quiapo, Manila","date":"1976","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng San Sebastian","inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ang simbahang ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"},"photo":{"height":3294,"hash":"59","file":"Historical marker of declaration of San Sebastian Church as a National Historical Landmark (corrected).jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":3628}}},"address":"San Sebastian Church, Pasaje del Carmen Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Simbahan ng San Sebastian","locPhoto":{"width":3000,"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"San Sebastian Basilica main entrance.jpg","hash":"12","height":1424},"lon":120.98927,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main entrance of the church.","wikipedia":{"San Sebastian Church":"San Sebastian Church (Manila)"}},"Q24882639":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":121.34511,"locPhoto":null,"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Don Placido Escudero Dam","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Don Placido Escudero Dam","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Don Ciriaco Nadres, duly authorized by the Spanish government, constructed here in 1872 a dam of adobe stone and lime mortar for irrigating his land on this side of the brook. Don Hermenegildo, his son, sold the property in 1890 to Don Placido Escudero and his wife, Doña Claudia Marasigan, who in 1904 reconstructed this dam with hard stone and cement mortar. Their only son Don Arsenio and Doña Rosario Adap, his wife, rebuilt this dam in 1937 for irrigation, and for the hydro-electric plant, supplying power and light to the “Cooperative Coconut Products, Inc.”, and to “Villa Escudero”.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Villa Escudero, Kilometer 91, Pan-Philippine Highway, Tiaong, Quezon","lat":13.99422,"date":"1938","macroAddress":"Tiaong, Quezon"},"Q54990751":{"lat":10.85552,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Cuyo, Palawan","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Fort of Cuyo was built about 1680 by the Recollect Agustinians, according to the plans and under the supervision of Rev. Juan de San Severo, A.R. The fort, made of stone and mortar, was square in form, with four bastions.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Fort Cuyo"},"photo":null}},"address":"Fort Cuyo, Rizal Street, Cuyo, Palawan","region":"Mimaropa","name":"Fort Cuyo","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.00832,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Fort Cuyo":"Cuyo Fort"}},"Q24837637":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Apolinario Mabini":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.09922,"address":"Tanauan, Batangas","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Patriot, statesman, lawyer, political writer, educator. Son of Inocencio Mabini and Dionisia Maranan. Rose from poverty. Joined the revolution becoming chief adviser of General Emilio Aguinaldo. Struck with paralysis, January 1896. Imprisoned by the Spaniards, following October; by the Americans, 1899. Exiled to Guam, January 15, 1901; returned February 26, 1903; Died in Manila, May 13, 1903.</p>","title":"On This Site was Born 23 July 1864 Apolinario Mabini","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"ae","height":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Apolinario Mabini Birthplace historical marker.jpg","width":3456}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"On This Site was Born 23 July 1864 Apolinario Mabini","lat":14.10089,"date":"1952","macroAddress":"Tanauan, Batangas"},"Q53620838":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.8888,"region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Fernando M. Maramag","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Fernando M. Maramag","subtitle":"(1893–1936)","inscription":"<p>Kinilalang isa sa mga pangunahing mananalaysay ng kanyang panahon at dalubhasang editoryalista. Ipinanganak noong Enero 21, 1893 sa Ilagan, Isabela, ang bayang itinatag ng kanyang ninuno na kapangalan niya. Isa sa mga unang Pilipinong naging dalubhasa sa wikang Ingles. Ang kanyang mga sanaysay at tula ay nabantog dahil sa dingal, kawastuan at kagandahan ng mga pangungusap. Ang kanyang mga editoryal sa <u>The Tribune</u> na kanyang pinamatnugutan hanggang sa kanyang kamatayan noong Oktubre 23, 1936, ay naglalaman ng matatalim na puna tungkol sa mga pambansang suliranin at pangyayari.</p>"}}},"address":"Rizal Park, Rizal Street, Ilagan, Isabela","lat":17.14876,"date":"1983-01-21","macroAddress":"Ilagan, Isabela"},"Q28874593":{"lon":4.34736,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"El Filibusterismo":"El filibusterismo","José Rizal":true},"lat":50.8433,"date":"2007","macroAddress":"Brussels, Belgium","details":{"fr":{"text":{"subtitle":"1861–1896","title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Heros National des Philippines</p><p>Habitait dan cette maison lorsqu’il ecrivit son roman ‘El Filibusterismo’ en 1890–1891</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Jose Rizal historical marker in Brussels, Belgium.jpg","credit":"Michel wal {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1966,"hash":"df","height":1687}}},"address":"42 Rue Philippe de Champagne, Midi-Lemonnier Quarter, Pentagon, Brussels, Belgium","region":"Overseas","name":"Jose Rizal"},"Q46542087":{"macroAddress":"Bulusan, Sorsogon","date":"2015-02-07","lat":12.75175,"name":"Mga Moog ng Bulusan","region":"Bicol Region","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Mga Moog ng Bulusan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinayo upang depensahan ang mga mamamayan ng Bulusan at ang Punta de Bulusan, na mahalagang daungan para sa mga manlalayag at sa mga barkong galyon sa Embocadero mula sa pagsalakay ng mga Moro, ika-18 hanggang ika-19 na siglo. Bahagi ng mga istrukturang ito ang mga moog sa Macabari, Busaingan at Gate na ngayo’y sakop na ng mga bayan ng Barcelona, Sta. Magdalena at Bulan, Sorsogon.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Gov. Juan Reyes Street, Poblacion, Bulusan, Sorsogon","lon":124.13698,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Manila galleon":true},"locDesc":null},"Q28912809":{"date":"1949","macroAddress":"Tanauan, Leyte","lat":11.11273,"name":"Church of Tanauan, Leyte","region":"Eastern Visayas","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":687,"hash":"a6","file":"Tanauan Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":455},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Constructed by the Jesuit Missionaries, 1704, and turned over to the Augustinians, 1768-1843. Repaired and enlarged 1850-1860 by Fr. Francisco de Paula Marquez who added a transept and surrounded the premises with thick rock-wall having a watch tower on each four corners for defense against pirates. Withstood hurricane and tidal wave of 1897.</p>","title":"Church of Tanauan, Leyte","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Tanauan Church, Tanauan, Leyte","lon":125.01739,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q55752994":{"locPhoto":{"width":3456,"file":"OraniChurchjf3063 06.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"c9","height":4608},"lon":120.53563,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the left column of a concrete arch holding the Orani Church Bell, by the base of the church bell tower.","wikipedia":{"Orani Church":true},"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Orani, Bataan","lat":14.80099,"address":"Orani Church, National Road, Orani, Bataan","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"71","height":3872,"width":3422,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Orani Church historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Orani became an independent missionary center in 1714. The Church and the Convent of Orani, repaired in 1792 and 1838, were badly damaged by the earthquake of September 16, 1852. They were rebuilt and improved under the supervision of the Rev. Bartolome Alvarez del Manzano, O.P., in 1868, and of the Rev. Fermin Perez San Julian, O.P., in 1891, and were destroyed on March 16, 1938, by fire which razed about three fourths of Orani, including the town hall, the tercena -- former Bataan High School and later Orani Elementary School building. The Church was reconstructed in September, 1938.</p>","title":"Church of Orani","subtitle":null}}},"name":"Church of Orani","region":"Central Luzon"},"Q23779734":{"name":"Jose Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","address":"Rizal Monument, Chipeco Avenue Extension, Calamba, Laguna","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pambansang Bayani ng Pilipinas. Doktor, agrimensor, dalubwika, manunulat, makata, eskultor at pintor. Isinilang sa Calamba, Laguna, 19 Hunyo 1861. May-akda ng Noli me Tangere (1887) at El Filibusterismo (1891), mga nobelang higit pang nagpaalab sa mga Filipino na maghimagsik laban sa Espanya. Dinakip at ipinatapon sa Dapitan, Hilagang Mindanao, 6 Hulyo, 1892. Nagboluntaryo bilang manggagamot ng puwersang Espanyol sa Cuba, 1896, ngunit muling dinakip habang patungong Espanya sa bintang na rebelyon. Binaril sa Bagumbayan (ngayo’y Liwasang Rizal), Maynila, 30 Disyembre 1896. Patuloy na inspirasyon para sa kalayan at pagkabansang Filipino.</p>","subtitle":"(1861–1896)","title":"Jose Rizal"},"photo":{"hash":"b9","height":3535,"credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Jose Rizal historical marker (Calamba monument).jpg","width":2500}}},"macroAddress":"Calamba, Laguna","date":"2011-06-19","lat":14.19586,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the front side of the monument’s pedestal.","lon":121.15976,"locPhoto":{"width":730,"file":"Largest Rizal Monument (cropped).jpg","credit":"Jtcueno {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":1056,"hash":"d0"}},"Q53638186":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1448,"file":"Union Theological Seminary historical marker.jpg","credit":"Patnubaypatnugot {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":1436,"hash":"37"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa Daang Tennessee ngayo’y Malvar, Malate, Maynila ng pinagsanib na Ellinwood Bible Training School (Presbyterian) at Florence B. Nicholson Seminary (Methodist) para magsanay ng mga Filipinong naghahangad na maging pastor at tagapagturo ng ebanghelyo, 1907. Naging kasapi nito ang United Brethren, 1911; Disciples 1916; at Congregationalist, 1920. Naging korporasyon, 7 Enero 1920. Rev. George W. Wright, unang pangulo, 1920. Inilipat sa Taft Avenue, 1926. Rev. Dr. Benjamin I. Guansing, unang Filipinong Pangulo, 1952, at itinalaga, 22 Hunyo 1954. Inilipat sa Dasmariñas, Cavite, 1962. Nakipag-isa sa Phlippine Christian University, 1978. Itinataguyod ng United Church of Christ in the Philippines (UCCP) at United Methodist Church (UMC).</p>","title":"Union Theological Seminary","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Union Theological Seminary, Dasmariñas, Cavite","name":"Union Theological Seminary","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Dasmariñas, Cavite","date":"2007","lat":14.29294,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Union Theological Seminary":"Union Theological Seminary (Philippines)"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96179},"Q43301980":{"wikipedia":{"National University":"National University (Philippines)"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.99469,"name":"National University","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":1442,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"National University NHCP Historical Marker.jpg","height":2481,"hash":"4f"},"text":{"title":"National University","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The first private non-sectarian university in the Philippines. Founded, August 1, 1900, as Colegio Filipino by Mariano F. Jhocson. Renamed Colegio Mercantil, 1905; National Academy, 1916. Converted into a university, 1921. Camilo Osias, first president.</p>"}}},"address":"National University, M. F. Jhocson Street, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","date":"1952","macroAddress":"Sampaloc, Manila","lat":14.60431},"Q24702097":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang parokya ng San Fernando noong 1 Marso 1881. Si Fr. Mariano Granja ang unang paroko. Ipinagawa ang simbahang ito noong Mayo 1882 at natapos noong Hulyo 1884. Nasunog noong 24 Mayo 1887. Muling ipinagawa noong Nobyembre 1887. Ang Diyosesis ng Lucena ay itinatag noong 8 Setyembre 1950.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Lucena"},"photo":{"hash":"bc","height":3997,"file":"San Fernando Cathedral Lucena City Marker.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2428}}},"address":"Lucena","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Simbahan ng Lucena","lat":13.93592,"date":"1953","macroAddress":"Lucena","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.61258},"Q46993504":{"lon":122.95433,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lat":14.11352,"macroAddress":"Daet, Camarines Norte","date":"1992","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3648,"hash":"b9","file":"Martyrs of Camarines Norte historical marker in Daet.jpg","credit":"User:Alhorin {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2736},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Alaala sa mga Katipuneros at mga dakilang anak ng Daet at mga karatig bayan na nag-alay ng buhay para sa Inang Bayan noong 1898: Ildefonso Moreno, Tomas Zaldua, Telesforo Zaldua, Marianito Zaldua, Jose Abaño, Jacinto Rada, Vicente Salveria, Isidro Avila, Gavino Saavedra, Domingo Lozada, Angel Zaleta, Gregorio del Valle at Florante Bacerdo at marami pang iba.</p>","title":"Martir ng Camarines Norte","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Rizal Park, Magallanes Iraya Street cor. Justo Lukban Street, Daet, Camarines Norte","region":"Bicol Region","name":"Martir ng Camarines Norte"},"Q28923507":{"lon":125.49334,"locPhoto":{"file":"Surigao City Hall and Flagpole.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4000,"height":3000,"hash":"d1"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the flagpole in front of the Surigao City Hall.","wikipedia":{"flag of the Philippines":"Flag of the Philippines"},"lat":9.79104,"macroAddress":"Surigao, Surigao del Norte","date":"2000","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"8d","height":3652,"width":2532,"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Unang Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao Marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa Casa Real ng bayan ng Surigao, ang kabisera ng lalawigan ng Surigao (dating Caraga), si Alejandro \"Jantoy\" Gonzalez, pangulo ng Panlalawigang Hunta ng Surigao, at ang iba pang mga pinuno ng Ikatlong Distrito ng Mindanao, ay opisal na itinaas sa kauna-unahang pagkakataon, noong umaga ng Disyembre 26, 1898, ang watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao. Ay opisyal na itinaas sa kauna unahang pagkakataon noong umaga ng Disyembre 26, 1898 ang watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao.</p>","title":"Pook ng Unang Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Surigao City Hall, Borromeo Street, Surigao, Surigao del Norte","region":"Caraga","name":"Pook ng Unang Pagtataas ng Watawat ng Pilipinas sa Mindanao"},"Q55100634":{"address":"St. Paul University Philippines, Mabini Street, Tuguegarao, Cagayan","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"St. Paul University Philippines NHCP Marker.jpg","credit":"Tabunon {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1366,"height":2048,"hash":"f4"},"text":{"subtitle":"Tuguegarao City","title":"St. Paul University Philippines","inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng Sisters of St. Paul of Chartres bilang Colegio de San Pablo, Kalye Rizal, 1907. Naging Colegio del Sagrado Corazon de Jesus, 1909. Binuksan ang antas ng sekundarya, 1911. Pinangalanang Sacred Heart of Jesus Institution, 1925. Lumipat sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan, 1934. Nanguna sa pagbukas ng mga kursong pagtuturo sa Cagayan Valley, 1939. Ginamit na hospital at garison ng mga Hapon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1941–1945. Ipinagpatuloy ang pagtuturo, 1941-1944. Binomba ng Amerikano, 1945. Naging St. Paul College of Tuguegarao, 1949. Itinalaga bilang pamantasan, 1982.</p>"}}},"region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"St. Paul University Philippines","lat":17.61687,"date":"2014-02-11","macroAddress":"Tuguegarao, Cagayan","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"St. Paul University Philippines":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.72498},"Q50413489":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.20291,"wikipedia":{"World War II":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Zamboanguita, Negros Oriental","date":"2007-09-22","lat":9.11136,"name":"Ang Pagsuko ng mga Puwersang Hapones sa Negros Oriental","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Pagsuko ng mga Puwersang Hapones sa Negros Oriental","inscription":"<p>Naitaboy ng mga gerilyang Filipino ng 73<sup>rd</sup> Division (Provisional), sa ilalim ng pamumuno ni Maj. Ceferino Galvez, ang mga tropang Hapones mula sa iba't ibang bayan sa katimugan, kasama na ang Zamboanguita, 6 Mayo 1944. Di kalaunan, napalaya ang buong Negros ng magkasanib na puwersang Filipino at Amerikano, na siyang nagbigay daan sa pormal na pagsuko sa pook na ito, 9:00 ng umaga ng 22 Setyembre 1945, ng mga puwersang Hapones sa ilalim ni Kol. Satosi Oie sa 503<sup>rd</sup> Airborne Regiment ng Hukbong Amerikano. Ibinigay ni Kol. Oie ang kanyang espadang samurai kay Kol. F. Wilson bilang tanda ng kanyang pagsuko. Dinala ang mga sumukong Hapones sa lumang trade school sa Dumaguete.</p>"}}},"address":"Guinsuan Bridge, Km. 26 National Highway, Brgy. Basak, Zamboanguita, Negros Oriental"},"Q24710143":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.39658,"wikipedia":{"San Juan":"San Juan, Batangas"},"locDesc":null,"lat":13.82501,"macroAddress":"San Juan, Batangas","date":"1990-12-12","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Bayan ng San Juan","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating nasa Pinagbayanan. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang pook sa kahilingan ng mamamayan dahil sa madalas na pagbaha ng mga ilog Bancoro at Bangbang at tuluyang paglubog sa tubig ng dating kabayanan noong taong 1883. Ang paglipat ay pinagtibay ng Gobernador Heneral noong Disyembre 12, 1890 sa panahon ng panunungkulan ng Gobernadorsilyo Benedicto de Villa. Naging San Juan de Bolboc sa bisa ng Batas Lehislatibo bilang 2390, Pebrero 28, 1914; San Juan de Nepomuceno bilang parangal sa patron ng bayan, nang mga unang taon ng 1920; at ngayon ay bayan ng San Juan.</p>","title":"Bayan ng San Juan","subtitle":"(San Juan de Bocboc)"},"photo":{"width":3456,"file":"Municipality of San Juan historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"e7","height":4608}}},"address":"San Juan, Batangas"},"Q54810935":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating Pideg at ginawang Diego–Gabriela Silang noong 1976. Ipinagawa ng mga Pransiskano noong 1600. Ginamit noong 1660 sa pag-aalsa nina Andres Malong at nina Diego at Gabriela, noong 1762. Pagkamatay ni Diego noong Mayo 28, 1763, ang pag-aalsa ay pinamunuan ni Gabriela, pagkaraan ng ilang sagupaan ay sinalakay ng mga Kastila ang pasong ito. Nadakip si Gabriela at ipinabitay noong Seytembre 20, 1763.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Pasong Diego–Gabriela Silang"}}},"address":"Km. 383 Manila North Road, Brgy. Quezon District, Santa, Ilocos Sur","name":"Pasong Diego–Gabriela Silang","region":"Ilocos Region","macroAddress":"Santa, Ilocos Sur","date":"1976-09-20","lat":17.46447,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Diego Silang":true,"Gabriela Silang":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.43505},"Q54818645":{"lat":17.57635,"macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","date":"1949","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Gregoria M. Rivera","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Gregoria M. Rivera","subtitle":"Memorial Library","inscription":"<p>This building was constructed to house the Municipal Jail, 1657; made provincial jail when Ilocos Sur became a province, 1818; repaired, 1855; seized by the Revolutionists under Col. Juan Villamor, 1898; taken over by the American forces who detained in it the political leaders, Mena Crisologo, Estanislao Reyes and Enrique Quema, 1899. President Elpidio Quirino was born in this building 16 November 1890, when his father was the warden. Converted into a library, 27 October 1948, in honor of President Quirino’s mother, Gregoria Rivera Mendoza de Quirino.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2112,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Gregoria M. Rivera Memorial Library NHCP Historical Marker.jpg","height":2816,"hash":"49"}}},"address":"Calle Burgos, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.38595,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q37726263":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Lider Sibika at pangunang unang ginang ng bansa sa ilalim ng malasariling pamahalaan ng Pilipinas. Ipinanganak noong ika-19 ng Pebrero 1888 sa Baler, Tayabas (ngayo’y sakop ng lalawigan ng Aurora). Nag-aral sa Paaralang Normal ng Pilipinas. Ikinasal sa Hongkong kay Manuel Luis Quezon, Pangulo ng Senado noong 1918. Mga anak: Maria Aurora, Maria Zeneida, Luisa Corazon Paz at Manuel L., Jr.</p><p>Nagtatag at nagsagawa ng iba’t-ibang batayan ng kaalaman para sa mamamayan, lalo na ng kabataan, sa Baler upang mapaunlad ang karunungang bumasa’t sumulat at maitaguyod ang mga tungkuling pambayan. Makaraang mamatay ang Pangulong Quezon (1944) nagtaguyod ng mga gawaing panlipunan at panrelihiyon para mapabuti ang pamantayan ng pamumuhay at pagbibigay ng karunungan at biyaya sa mga kapuspalad. Namuno para makilalang isang pambansang samahan ang Krus na Pula at naging unang babaeng pangulo nito. Tinangkilik ang pagtatayong-muli ng makasaysayang simbahan ng Baler.</p><p>Habang pauwi ng Baler, tinambangan ng isang pangkat ng Hukbalahap sa Nueva Ecija at kasamang napatay si Maria Aurora, manugang na Felipe Buencamino III at ilang kaibigan noong ika-28 ng Abril 1949.</p><p>Bilang parangal sa kanya, itinatag ang sub-lalawigan ng Aurora noong 1951 sa pamamagitan ng Batas ng Republika Blg. 648 at ginawang lalawigan ito sa bisa ng Batas Pambansa Blg. 7 noong 1978.</p>","title":"Aurora Aragon Quezon","subtitle":"(1888–1949)"},"photo":{"width":1547,"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Aurora Aragon Quezon Historical Marker.jpg","height":2063,"hash":"c3"}}},"address":"Rizal Street cor. San Luis Street, Baler, Aurora","name":"Aurora Aragon Quezon","region":"Central Luzon","macroAddress":"Baler, Aurora","date":"1985-02-19","lat":15.75868,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting outside Aurora Aragon’s replica house.","wikipedia":{"Aurora Quezon":true},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Aurorahousejf.JPG","width":3264,"hash":"31","height":2448},"lon":121.56261},"Q54961086":{"date":"2007","macroAddress":"Alcantara, Romblon","lat":12.26172,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Labanan sa Karagatan ng Sibuyan historical marker 2.jpg","width":1200,"height":1600,"hash":"7d"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isa sa mga makasaysayang labanang naganap sa karagatan noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 24 Oktubre 1944. Binomba ng mga eroplano mula sa aircraft carriers ng mga Amerikano ang puwersang Hapon na kinabibilangan ng mga barkong pandigmang Musashi, Yamato, Haruna at Nagato at ilang kasatorpedero habang patungong San Bernardino Strait. Napalubog ang 68,000 toneladong Musashi kasama ang 989 marinong Hapon at 39 na opisyal. Ang pagkatalo ng mga Hapon sa Karagatan ng Sibuyan ay nakatulong sa tagumpay ng mga Amerikano sa Labanan sa Leyte Gulf.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Karagatan ng Sibuyan","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Battle of Sibuyan Sea Road, Alcantara, Romblon","name":"Labanan sa Karagatan ng Sibuyan","region":"Mimaropa","lon":122.057,"locPhoto":{"height":1200,"hash":"f7","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines","file":"Labanan sa Karagatan ng Sibuyan historical marker 1.jpg","width":1600},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting.","wikipedia":{"Battle of the Sibuyan Sea":true}},"Q54877699":{"wikipedia":{"Wenceslao Vinzons":true,"Philippines Campaign":"Philippines Campaign (1941–42)"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.95421,"region":"Bicol Region","name":"Bantayog para sa Kapayapaan","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","title":"Bantayog para sa Kapayapaan","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Laniton Bridge, Km. 348 Pan-Philippine Highway, Basud, Camarines Norte","lat":14.06256,"macroAddress":"Basud, Camarines Norte","date":"1980"},"Q30097970":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96395,"wikipedia":{"Antonio Luna":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Cabanatuan, Nueva Ecija","date":"1966","lat":15.48919,"name":"Death Place of General Antonio Luna","region":"Central Luzon","address":"College of the Immaculate Conception, Del Pilar Street, Cabanatuan, Nueva Ecija","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":4128,"hash":"93","width":3096,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Death Place of General Antonio Luna Historical Marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>On the plaza, in front of this building, formerly the Presidential Headquarters of the First Philippine Republic, General Antonio Luna and his aide Colonel Francisco Roman were assasinated in the afternoon of 5 June 1899, by members of General Emilio Aguinaldo's presidential guard.</p>","title":"Death Place of General Antonio Luna","subtitle":null}}}},"Q55283424":{"lon":121.14556,"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"cb","credit":"Judgefloro","file":"752Rodriguez, Rizal Barangays Roads Landmarks 30.jpg","width":3456},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the house facade, to the left of entryway facing J.P. Rizal Street.","wikipedia":{"Eulogio Rodriguez":true},"lat":14.73286,"date":"1983","macroAddress":"Rodriguez, Rizal","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"3d","height":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Eulogio Rodriguez y Adona historical marker.jpg","width":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Anak ng mahirap na mag-asawang Petronilo Rodriguez at Monica Adona, si Eulogio ay ipinanganak noong Enero 21, 1883 sa Montalban, Rizal. Dahil sa kanyang sipag, tiyaga at pagsisikap ay umigpaw siya mula sa pagiging sakatero hanggang manging Pangulo ng Montalban, Gobernador ng Lalawigang Rizal, Alkalde ng Maynila, Kinatawan ng Nuweba Biskaya at ng ikalawang purok ng Rizal sa lehislatura, Kalihim ng Pagsasaka at Likas na Kayamanan, Senador, Pangulo ng Senado, at Pangulo ng Lapiang Nacionalista. Ikinulong ng mga Hapon sa Kutang Santiago dahil sa hindi niya pakikiisa sa kanila. Matapat sa tungkulin, maawain, at matulungin sa kapwa. Ang kanyang pagkamatay noong Disyembre 9, 1964 ay iniluha ng buong bansa.</p>","title":"Eulogio Rodriguez y Adona","subtitle":"(1883–1964)"}}},"address":"Eulogio Rodriguez Ancestral House, J.P. Rizal Street, Rodriguez, Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Eulogio Rodriguez y Adona"},"Q53823438":{"locPhoto":{"credit":"KisekiLacroix {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Basco Cathedral 10.JPG","width":2592,"hash":"36","height":4608},"lon":121.96933,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the middle left buttress of church facade.","wikipedia":{"Santo Domingo Cathedral":"Santo Domingo Cathedral (Basco)"},"date":"2008-03-27","macroAddress":"Basco, Batanes","lat":20.45075,"address":"Santo Domingo Cathedral, National Road, Basco, Batanes","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang itinayo nina P. Baltazar Calderon, O.P. at P. Bartolome Artiguez, O.P. sa patronahe ni Santo Domingo de Guzman, 1783. Ginawa sa bato ni P. Francisco de Paula Esteban O.P., 1795. Pinaikli ang nabe at itinayo ang fachada ni P. Nicolas Castaño, 1812. Nasunog, 1860; muling itinayo ni P. Antonio Vicente, O.P., 1863; pinalitan ng yerong bubong ni P. Mariano Gomez, O.P., 1891; nailigtas noong Digmaang Filipino–Amerikano, 1899–1901, at Pangalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1941–1945; isinaayos ni Obispo Peregrin de la Fuente, O.P., D.D., noong mga taong 1950. Nasira ng lindol ang kampanaryo, 2000. Muling isinaayos ni Obispo Jose Salazar, O.P., D.D. at P. Henry Romero, S.O.L.T., 2002. Kilala rin bilang Katedral ng Inmaculada Concepcion na Patrona ng lalawigan ng Batanes.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Basco","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"name":"Simbahan ng Basco","region":"Cagayan Valley"},"Q54663244":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located in the niche to the right of the side entrance of the church.","wikipedia":null,"lon":120.99802,"locPhoto":{"hash":"90","height":3456,"width":4608,"file":"Peñafrancia de Manila Church side entrance.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ginawang una sa pawid at kawayan noong 1697 nang ang Peñafrancia ay sityo ng dating bayan ng Dilao na noon ay nasa karatig pook ng city hall ng Lungsod ng Maynila. Naitayo ito sa pagsusumikap ni Padre Miguel Robles de Covarrubias, dahilan sa kanyang panata sa Birhen ng Peña de Francia sa Salamanca sa Espanya noong siya ay bata pang sakitin. Ang imahen na pinangalanang “Nuestra Señora del Rosario ng Ilog Pasig,” ay idinambana rito noong 1712.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Birhen ng Peñafrancia","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":225,"file":"Peñafrancia de Manila Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":400,"hash":"82"}}},"address":"Church of Our Lady of Peñafrancia, 1343 Gomez Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Simbahan ng Birhen ng Peñafrancia","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","date":"1979-07-04","lat":14.58507},"Q51920412":{"lon":122.56277,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"West Visayas State University":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":10.71334,"macroAddress":"Iloilo City","date":"2007","region":"Western Visayas","name":"West Visayas State University","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"West Visayas State University","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang Iloilo Normal School, 16 Hunyo 1902. Natapos ang gusali ng paaralan, 1924. Naging West Visayas State College, 4 Mayo 1965. Naging West Visayas State University, 27 Enero 1986. Hinirang bilang Center of Excellence for Teacher Education ng Commission on Higher Education, 1995.</p>"},"photo":{"width":1944,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"WVSU historical marker.JPG","height":2592,"hash":"83"}}},"address":"West Visayas State University, Luna Street, La Paz, Iloilo City"},"Q54810487":{"lon":120.38629,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Pedro Bucaneg":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":17.57547,"date":"1983-07-05","macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Pedro Bukaneg","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ama ng Panitikang Iloko. Isinilang noong 1591. Natuto ng mga wikang Latin at Kastila sa mga paring Agustino ng Simbahan ng Bantay. Naging guro at tagasalin ng dalawang wikang ito sa wikang Iloko. Isinalin, Doctrina Cristiana, 1606, at mga dalangin sa mga wikang Latin at Kastila. Tumulong sa mga prayle sa pagpapalaganap ng ebanghelyo mula sa Aringay hanggang Laoag. Pinakadakilang akda: Biag ni Lam-ang. Namatay noong 1626.</p>","subtitle":"(1591–1626)","title":"Pedro Bukaneg"},"photo":{"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker Pedro Bukaneg.JPG","width":4771,"height":3172,"hash":"eb"}}},"address":"Plaza Vicente Singson Encarnacion, Calle Burgos, Vigan, Ilocos Sur"},"Q28928184":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Bank of the Philippine Islands Zamboanga","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ang bahay na ito ay nagsilbing unang gusali ng sangay ng BPI sa Zamboanga, 1912, na dating pagmamay-ari ni Don Francisco Barrios. Naging opisyal na tahanan ni Hen. John Pershing, gobernador militar ng Lalawigan ng Moro, 1909–1913. Inilunsad ang ikalawang palapang bilang BPI Museum Zamboanga, 2012.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"26 N.S. Valderrosa Street, Zamboanga City","name":"Bank of the Philippine Islands Zamboanga","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","date":"2012","macroAddress":"Zamboanga City","lat":6.90359,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Bank of the Philippine Islands":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.07713},"Q47141910":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Pampanga Provincial Jail":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.68599,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ayon sa disenyo ni William E. Parsons, 1909. Nanatiling bilangguan hanggang inokupahan ng mga puwersang Hapones, 1942–1945. Ibinigay ng Estados Unidos sa pamahalaan ng Republika ng Pilipinas bilang bahagi ng pagtatapos ng Pamahalaang Commonwealth at ipinagpatuloy bilang bilangguan, 1946. Ginamit ang pangalawang palapag bilang tanggapan ng Court of Agrarian Reform at ng Court of First Instance, 1960’s–1970’s; nanatili ang archives section ng Court of First Instance (ngayo’y Regional Trial Court) hanggang 1995. Halimbawa ng arkitektura ng mga panlalawigang bilangguan noong panahon ng mga Amerikano.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Pampanga Provincial Jail"},"photo":{"file":"SF (62) Pampanga Jail NHCP Historical Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":2332,"hash":"e9","height":3238}}},"address":"Pampanga Provincial Jail, San Fernando, Pampanga","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Pampanga Provincial Jail","lat":15.02342,"macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","date":"2009"},"Q42931929":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Casa Narvas","inscription":"<p>Declared a Heritage House by the National Historical [Institute] 26 April 2007</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Casa Narvas, Governor D. Reyes Street cor. Del Mundo Street, Boac, Marinduque","region":"Mimaropa","name":"Casa Narvas","lat":13.44844,"date":"2007","macroAddress":"Boac, Marinduque","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":121.83949,"locPhoto":null},"Q53399116":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Gusaling Roman R. Santos","address":"Don Roman Santos Building, Plaza Sta. Cruz Street cor. Escolta Street, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Roman S. Santos Building in Santa Cruz historical marker.jpg","hash":"15","height":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito itinayo ang gusali na inokupahan ng <u>Caja Ahorros y Monte de Piedad</u> mula noong 1894 hanggang 1937. Nabili at pinalaki ng <u>Consolidated Investments Corporation</u> at muling ipinagbili sa Asyenda Magdalena noong 1944. Naging pagamutan ng Krus na Pula ng Amerika, 1945–1947.</p><p>Binili ni Ramon R. Santos noong 1955 at inokupahan ng <u>Prudential Bank and Trust Company</u> at mga tanggapang pangkalakal. Ang muling pagsasaayos ay natapos noong 1957.</p>","title":"Gusaling Roman R. Santos","subtitle":null}}},"lat":14.59896,"macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","date":"1977","wikipedia":{"Don Roman Santos Building":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98005},"Q37713611":{"lon":122.1377,"locPhoto":{"hash":"d1","height":4000,"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Cape Engano Lighthouse Facade.jpg","width":3000},"wikipedia":{"Cape Engaño Lighthouse":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the lighthouse facing the southern entrance to the compound.","lat":18.57977,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"Santa Ana, Cagayan","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Parola ng Cape Engaño","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Idinisenyo ni Inhenyero Magin Pers y Pers ayon sa plano ng mga parola sa Cape Bojeador, Faro de Punta Capones at Faro de la Isla de Cabra na may tore at mga pabelyon, 1 Hunyo 1887. Ipinatayo, 21 Setyembre 1888. Natapos, 31 Disyembre 1892. Isa sa mga natatanging halimbawa ng arkitektura at nalalabing parolang itinayo noong panahon ng mga Espanyol.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Parola ng Cape Engaño"},"photo":{"width":1588,"file":"Cape Engano Lighthouse Historical Marker (cropped).jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"56","height":1870}}},"address":"Cape Engaño Lighthouse, Palaui Island, Santa Ana, Cagayan"},"Q24763827":{"address":"Leon Apacible Museum, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"9f","height":1576,"width":1180,"file":"Leon Apacible historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Balayan, Batangas, noong 25 Octubre 1861. Abogado at Hukom pamayapa. Nagtatag ng masonerya sa kanyang lalawigan. Naglingkod bilang kanang kamay ng Heneral Miguel Malvar; naging katulong sa pagtatatag ng lalawigan ng Batangas noong panahon ng himagsikan. Nahirang na kinatawan ng Lepanto sa Kongreso ng Malolos. Nakaisang dibdib si Matilde Martinez; namatay noong 1901. Ang bahay na ito ay naaging tananan niya at naging tagpuan din nina dr. Jose Rizal, Mariano Ponce, at iba pang mga bayani.</p>","title":"Leon Apacible","subtitle":"(1861–1901)"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Leon Apacible","lat":13.87944,"date":"1973","macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.91975},"Q55230161":{"locPhoto":{"file":"Licerio Geronimo Monument at Camp Geronimo, Taytay, Rizal.jpg","credit":"Roel Balingit {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":3120,"height":4160,"hash":"fd"},"lon":121.14959,"wikipedia":{"Licerio Gerónimo":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the monument pedestal of Gen. Licerio Geronimo at the right wing of the Rizal Police Provincial Office inside Camp Geronimo.","lat":14.57385,"date":"2017","macroAddress":"Taytay, Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Licerio L. Geronimo","address":"Camp Geronimo, Cabrera Road, Brgy. Dolores, Taytay, Rizal","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Bayani ng Labanan ng San Mateo. Ipinanganak Agosto 27, 1855, Sampaloc, Maynila. Puno, Kapulungang Katipunan ng Wawa, Montalban; tagapagtatag, Katipunan sa San Mateo at Marikina. Napaurong ang mga Kastila na sumalakay sa puwersa ni Heneral Aguinaldo sa Bundok Puray. Nahirang na medyor heneral ng dibisyon nakatalaga sa San Mateo, 1898; komandante heneral ng Ikatlong Sona Militar ng Lalawigan ng Maynila, 1899. Buong tapang na nakipaglaban kasama ang kanyang mga Tiradores de la Muerte sa Labanan ng San Mateo kung saan napatay niya si Heneral Henry Lawton at iba pang opisyal na Amerikano. Sinundan ito ng mga pagsalakay sa iba’t-ibang himpilan ng mga Amerikano sa Bulakan, Rizal at mga karatig bayan ng Maynila. Sumuko sa mga Amerikano, 1901. Nagtrabaho sa Konstabularyo ng Pilipinas bilang 4th Class Inspector, Hunyo 1, 1902. Naging 3rd Lieutenant at Inspector Disyembre 23, 1902. Namatay, Enero 16, 1924.</p>","title":"Licerio L. Geronimo","subtitle":"(1855–1924)"},"photo":{"height":4160,"hash":"64","credit":"Roel Balingit {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Licerio Geronimo historical marker (Taytay, Rizal).jpg","width":3120}}}},"Q46487777":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Imus","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Imus","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Formed part of the Hacienda de Imus owned by the Recollect Fathers, 1686. Organized into a municipality, 1795. Occupied by the Revolutionists, September 1, 1896. Seat of the Revolutionary Assembly, January, 1897. Retaken by the Spaniards, March 28, 1897. Reoccupied by the Filipinos, May 28, 1898, until the establishment of civil government under the Americans, June 11, 1901. Taken by the Japanese, January 1, 1942. Liberated by the Americans, February 4, 1945.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"ImusCavitejf0433 04.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"24"}}},"address":"Imus Plaza, Castañeda Street cor. Maestro G. Tirona Street, Imus, Cavite","lat":14.42895,"macroAddress":"Imus, Cavite","date":"1954","wikipedia":{"Imus":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":120.9362,"locPhoto":null},"Q24836055":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"e4","height":4608,"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Miguel Malvar historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa baryo ng San Miguel, Santo Tomas, Batangas, noong Setyembre 27, 1865 sa mag-asawang Maximo Malvar at Tiburcia Carpio. Unang nag-aral sa paaralan ni Padre Valerio Malabanan. Naging Gobernadorsilyo ng Sto. Tomas noong 1892. Isa sa kauna-unahang sumapi sa Himagsikang Filipino laban sa mga Kastila noong 1896. Kahuli-hulihang Pilipinong Heneral na sumuko sa mga Amerikano noong Abril 18, 1902. Namatay noong Oktubre 13, 1911.</p>","subtitle":"1865–1911","title":"Miguel Malvar"}}},"address":"Santo Tomas, Batangas","name":"Miguel Malvar","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Santo Tomas, Batangas","date":"1973-09-27","lat":14.11027,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Miguel Malvar":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.1427},"Q34131366":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dinisenyo ni William E. Parsons noong 1907 para sa Manila Lodge of The Elks, isang samahang makabayan, pangkapatiran at pangkawanggawa ng mga Amerikanong mangangalakal na itinatag noong 1902. Ipinatayo, 1910. Pinasinayaan, 1911. Bahagi ng Balangkas Burnham–Anderson para sa Maynila at isang halimbawa ng arkitekturang Amerikano noong panahng iyon. Naging Museum of Philippine Art; pagkaraan, punong tanggapan ng Manila Overseas Press Club; at sa kasalukuyan, Museo Pambata ng Maynila.</p>","title":"Gusali ng Elks Club","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":2500,"file":"Gusali ng Elks Club historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","height":2993,"hash":"0f"}}},"address":"Elks Club Building, Roxas Boulevard cor. South Drive, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Gusali ng Elks Club","lat":14.57911,"date":"2002","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main entrance of the museum.","wikipedia":{"Manila Elks Club":true,"Museo Pambata":true,"Elks Club Building":"Elks Club Building (Manila)"},"lon":120.97718,"locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"14","width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"MuseoPambatajf0260 23.JPG"}},"Q22236841":{"lon":120.97864,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"León María Guerrero III":true},"locDesc":null,"date":"1983","macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","lat":14.57828,"name":"Leon Ma. Guerrero","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1915–1982)","title":"Leon Ma. Guerrero","inscription":"<p>Diplomatiko, manunulat, mamamahayag, abogado, at makabayan. Ipinanganak noong Marso 24, 1915 sa Ermita, Maynila. Nagtapos ng A.B., summa cum laude, Ateneo de Manila, 1935; at LL.B., summa cum laude, Philippine Law School, 1939. Pangalawang Kalihim ng Kagawaran ng Suliraning Panlabas, 1954. Embahador sa Great Britain, Denmark, Sweden, Norway, Finland, Germany, Spain, India, Nepal, Afghanistan, Mexico, Guatemala, Nicaragua, Costa Rica, Honduras, Panama, El Salvador, Ecuador, Venezuela, Columbia, Cuba at Yugoslavia, 1954–1980. May-akda ng nagwaging talambuhay ni Rizal, The First Filipino. Nagsalin sa Ingles ng Noli Me Tangere at El Filibusterismo. Tumanggap ng gawad, Doctor of Humanities, honoris causa, Lyceum of the Philippines, 1971, at Gawad Mabini, 1982. Namatay noong Hunyo 24, 1982.</p>"},"photo":{"width":432,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Leon Ma. Guerrero (1915–1982).jpg","hash":"18","height":348}}},"address":"Roxas Boulevard cor. Plaza Nuestra Señora de Guia Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q54956877":{"wikipedia":{"Magalang":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal holding a sculpture of a book and an eagle at the western side of the town plaza.","locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"e6","width":4608,"file":"3513jfSan Nicolas Town Patio Magalang Pampangafvf 03.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"lon":120.66086,"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Magalang","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Magalang historical marker.jpg","width":3552,"height":3000,"hash":"92"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Established by the Augustinians at Macapsa in 1605. Scene of the encounter between the followers of Andres Malong led by Melchor de Vera and the Spanish troops in 1660. Moved to San Bartolome in 1734. Swept by the Parua River in the flood of 1863. Re-established in barrio San Pedro on 13 December 1863 by Gobernadorcillo Pablo M. Luciano. The Revolutionary Government took over, 12 June 1898 until 5 November 1899 when the Americans succeeded. Occupied by the Japanese, 3 January 1942. Liberated by the Americans, 24 January 1945. Turned over to the Republic of the Philippines, 4 July 1946.</p>","title":"Magalang","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Magalang–Arayat Road, Magalang, Pampanga","lat":15.21433,"date":"1954","macroAddress":"Magalang, Pampanga"},"Q41758337":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Paciano Rizal","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"07","height":1404,"width":1056,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Paciano Rizal historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"1851–1930","title":"Paciano Rizal","inscription":"<p>Nakatatandang kapatid ni Jose Rizal. Ipinanganak sa Calamba, Laguna, noong Marso 9, 1851. Nangilak ng abuloy para sa kilusan sa pagpapalaganap laban sa Espanya at nangilak ng suskrisyon para sa Diariong Tagalog. Nakumisyong heneral ng Hukbong Mapanghimagsik. Inihalal na Kalihim ng Pananalapi sa Pamahalaang Pangkagawaran ng Gitnang Luson sa Bundok Puray, Montalban, at itinalagang Punong Militar ng mga manghihimagsik sa Laguna. Lumahok sa Digmaang Pilipino–Amerikano at nadakip ng mga kaaway noong 1900. Namatay sa bahay na ito noong Abril 13, 1930.</p>"}}},"address":"General Paciano Rizal Shrine, Villegas Street cor. Juan Luna Street, Los Baños, Laguna","lat":14.1817,"macroAddress":"Los Baños, Laguna","date":"1983-04-13","wikipedia":{"Paciano Rizal":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.22399},"Q28913899":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Leyte Landing","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this spot, Palo, Leyte, General Douglas MacArthur returned to the Philippines on 20 October 1944 and personally led the swift drive against the Japanese forces in the Philippines. President Sergio Osmeña and some members of the government-in-exile arrived with General MacArthur and proceeded to reorganize, restore, and administer the government of the Commonwealth of the Philippines. Declared a National Historical Landmark, 2004.</p>"},"photo":{"width":396,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Leyte landing historical marker.jpg","hash":"c9","height":409}},"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Paglunsad sa Leyte historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":382,"height":482,"hash":"ae"},"text":{"title":"Paglunsad sa Leyte","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito sa Palo, Leyte, nagbalik sa Pilipinas si Heneral Douglas MacArthur noong 20 Oktubre 1944 at personal na nanguna sa mabilisang pagtataboy sa hukbong Hapones na nasa Pilipinas and pangulong Sergio Osmeña at ilang kagawad ng nagdestiyepong pamahalaan ay dumating kasama ni Hen. MacArthur at kumilos para sa muling pagtatatag, pagpapanumbalik, at pangangasiwa sa pamahalaang Komonwelt ng Pilipinas. Ipinahayag ng Pambansang Tandang Pangkasaysayan, 2004.</p>"}}},"address":"MacArthur Landing Memorial National Park, Palo, Leyte","region":"Eastern Visayas","name":"Leyte Landing","lat":11.17213,"date":"2004","macroAddress":"Palo, Leyte","locDesc":"The historical markers in Filipino and English are located on a concrete mounting in front of the memorial sculpture of the landing.","wikipedia":{"Douglas MacArthur":true,"Battle of Leyte":true},"locPhoto":{"height":2112,"hash":"fb","credit":"Ryme26 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Phils Leyte MacArthur Landing Memorial Palo.JPG","width":2816},"lon":125.01217},"Q54810760":{"macroAddress":"Narvacan, Ilocos Sur","date":"1950","lat":17.41859,"name":"Church of Narvacan","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Narvacan","inscription":"<p>On this site, chapel and convent were constructed under the direction of the Agustinian Fathers, 1587. Both were destroyed by fire, 1611, rebuilt later. To the convent were brought from Vigan Bishop Fray Rodrigo Cardenas and his priests by Filipino Revolutionists, 20 January 1661. Belfry was erected by Fray Jose B. Reosendo, 1864. The church was rebuilt and enlarged, 1883, by Fray Angel Corrugedo, who added a transept. Destroyed by bombs, 1945; reconstructed with the aid of the United States War Damage Commission, the Diocese of Nueva Segovia and generous citizens, 1949.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Narvacan, Ilocos Sur","lon":120.47632,"locPhoto":{"file":"Narvacan Church.JPG","credit":"Danny b11 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1024,"height":768,"hash":"c7"},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade to the left of the main entrance."},"Q54803203":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Lal-lo":"Lal-lo, Cagayan","Archdiocese of Nueva Segovia":"Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Nueva Segovia"},"lon":121.66124,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Lalloc–Nueva Segovia","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>The town of Lalloc, named Nueva Segovia by Juan Pablo Carrion in 1581, was visited by Juan Salcedo in 1572 and by Luis Perez Dasmariñas in 1592. Lalloc was the seat of the Diocese of Nueva Segovia, created by Pope Clement VIII on August 15, 1595, and continued to be so up to 1755, when it was transferred to Vigan. It was the capital of Cagayan up to 1839, when the provincial government was moved to Tuguegarao.</p>"}}},"address":"Lal-lo Church, Real Street, Lal-lo, Cagayan","name":"Lalloc–Nueva Segovia","region":"Cagayan Valley","date":"1939","macroAddress":"Lal-lo, Cagayan","lat":18.1994},"Q35006081":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Heswita sa ilalim ng patronato ni San Pablo Apostol, 1724. Winasak ng mga nag-alsang tagasunod ni Francisco Dagohoy ang simbahang yari sa bato, ika-18 siglo. Inilipat ang parokya sa pangangasiwa ng mga Rekoleto, 1768-1898. Sinimulang ipaayos ang apsis, 1889. Pinangasiwaan ng mga paring sekular, 1899. Sinunog ng mga sundalong Amerikano, Enero 1902. Ipinagawa ang harapang bahagi ng simbahan sa panunungkulan ni Padre Quiterio Sarigumba, 1931; at ni Padre Valeriano Cabantan ang kampanaryo, 1940. Pinalitan ng bakal at tisa ang bubong, 2002. Nasira ng lindol, 15 Oktubre 2013.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Inabanga"}}},"address":"Inabanga Church, Inabanga, Bohol","name":"Simbahan ng Inabanga","region":"Central Visayas","macroAddress":"Inabanga, Bohol","date":"2015","lat":10.02882,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.0683},"Q28944715":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Philippine–American War":true},"lon":125.43306,"locPhoto":null,"address":"Borongan, Eastern Samar","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1899 Himagsikang Pilipino–Amerikano)","title":"Ang Labanan sa Borongan","inscription":"<p>Dito nagwagi ang mga rebolusyonaryong Pilipino ng Samar sa pamumuno ni Kapitan Ramon Serrano matapos nilang salakayin ang mga sundalong Amerikanong nakabase dito, 16 Marso 1900. Ang mga sumunod na matagumpay na labanan ay naganap sa pamumuno ni Kapitan Andres Lobrio noong 10 Hulyo, 13 Hulyo at 16 Hulyo, 1901.</p>"},"photo":null}},"name":"Ang Labanan sa Borongan","region":"Eastern Visayas","date":"2012","macroAddress":"Borongan, Eastern Samar","lat":11.6078},"Q44353315":{"wikipedia":{"Roman Ongpin":"Román Ongpin"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a granite mounting to the left of the statue of Ramon Ongpin.","locPhoto":{"hash":"85","height":4608,"file":"Ramon Ongpin statue and historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456},"lon":120.97485,"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Roman Ongpin","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"78","width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Ramon Ongpin historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1847–1912)","title":"Roman Ongpin","inscription":"<p>Makabayan at pilantropo. Isinilang sa Binondo, Maynila, 28 Pebrero 1847. Nahalal bilang teniente primero de mestizos ng Binondo, 1883–1885. Itinatag ang El '82, unang tindahang gumamit ng paraang fixed price sa Kalye Colon ngayo'y bahagi ng Kalye San Fernando, 1882. Tumulong sa Kilusang Propaganda. Ipiniit ng mga Espanyol dahil sa kanyang pagtulong sa mga rebolusyonaryo, 1896. Ikinulong muli ng mga Amerikano, 6 Disyembre 1900 hanggang 23 Marso 1901. Naglingkod bilang ingat-yaman ng Union Obrera Democratica, 1902. Naging pangulo ng mga samahang sibiko tulad ng Casa Asilo de Invalidos Filipinos por la Guerra, La Proteccion de la Infancia at Gota de Leche. Yumao, 10 Disyembre 1912. Ipinangalan sa kanya ang Daang Sacristia ng Lupong Munisipal ng Maynila bilang pagkilala sa kanyang mga nagawa, 1915.</p>"}}},"address":"Don Roman Ongpin Monument, Ongpin Street, Binondo, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59974,"macroAddress":"Binondo, Manila","date":"2008"},"Q28861697":{"macroAddress":"Sampaloc, Manila","date":"1961","lat":14.60844,"details":{"es":{"text":{"title":"Manuel L. Quezon","subtitle":"1878–1944","inscription":"<p>Primer Presidente de la Mancomunidad de Filipinas. Alumno de la Real y Pontificia Universidad de Santo Tomas, Manila, Filipinas, 1894–1898.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2448,"file":"Manuel Quezon historical marker at the Arch of the Centuries UST.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":3264,"hash":"3b"}}},"address":"Arch of the Centuries, España Boulevard, Sampaloc, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Manuel L. Quezon","region":"Metro Manila","lon":120.99086,"locPhoto":{"file":"Arch of the Centuries- University of Santo Tomas.jpg","credit":"Ms.popsie21 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":640,"hash":"5d","height":426},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the right post of the arch looking from España Boulevard.","wikipedia":{"Manuel L. Quezon":true}},"Q23665520":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Fort of San Pedro","inscription":"<p>The Fort of San Pedro, described in an official report of 1739, is triangular in shape and made of stone and mortar. The three bastions are La Concepcion, San Ignacio de Loyola, and San Miguel–Powder Magazine.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"3d","height":2800,"width":2708,"file":"Fort of San Pedro historical marker (perspective corrected).jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)"}}},"address":"Fort San Pedro, Cebu City","name":"Fort of San Pedro","region":"Central Visayas","macroAddress":"Cebu City","date":"1939","lat":10.29264,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of Fort San Pedro.","wikipedia":{"Fort San Pedro":true},"lon":123.90563,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Fort of San Pedro historical marker context.jpg","width":1488,"hash":"d4","height":1119}},"Q24727895":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.52321,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Fort Stotsenburg":true,"Clark Air Base":true,"Clark Freeport Zone":"Clark Freeport and Special Economic Zone"},"lat":15.17983,"date":"2003","macroAddress":"Angeles","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"e2","height":3456,"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"0520jfFort Stotsenburg Parkfvf 23.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":"(Fort Stotsenburg)","title":"Clark Field","inscription":"<p>Dating pati o pamayanan ng mga Aeta. Naging Camp Stotsenburg bilang paggunita kay Col. John Miller Stotsenburg ng 1st Nebraska Regiment, 1902. Lupang-laan para sa hukbo ng Estados Unidos, 1 Setyembre 1903. Nagtayo ng paliparan at tinawag na Clark Field bilang paggunita sa pilotong si Maj. Harold Merville Clar, 1919. Sinalakay ng mga Hapon, 8 Disyembre 1941. Pook ng labanan ng mga sundalong Amerikano, Pilipino at Hapon. 1945, nanatili sa pamamahala ng Estados Unidos ayon sa kasunduang base militar ng RP-US, 1947. Clark Air Force Base, 1949. Isinara, 1991. Naging Clark Special Economic Zone, 1992.</p>"}}},"address":"Angeles","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Clark Field"},"Q37703111":{"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Labanan sa Imus","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3602,"hash":"c7","width":2500,"file":"Labanan sa Imus historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sinalakay ng puwersa nina Hen. Emilio Aguinaldo at Kor. Jose Tagle ang mga prayle at guardia civil na nanganlong sa Casa Hacienda 1 Setyembre 1896. Samantalong nakikipaglaban sa Bacoor si Hen. Aguinaldo at kanyang mga tauhan. Muling sinalakay ng mga rebolusyonaryong pinamumunuan ni Kor. Tagle ang Casa Hacienda 2 Setyembre 1896. Nagapi ang karagdagang puwersang Espanyol na pinamumunuan ni Hen. Ernesto de Aguirre, 3 Setyembre 1896. Sa labanang ito nahulog ang sable de mando ni Hen. de Aguirre na nakuha ng mga rebolusyonaryo. Nagsilbing inspirasyon ang tagumpay na ito sa mga rebolusyonaryo sa pakikipaglaban para sa kalayaan.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa Imus"}}},"address":"Battle of Imus, Imus, Cavite","lat":14.42996,"macroAddress":"Imus, Cavite","date":"2006","wikipedia":{"Battle of Imus":true,"Emilio Aguinaldo":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of an elongated monument of 8 soldiers charging in battle led by General Emilio Aguinaldo with the flag of the Philippines as backdrop.","locPhoto":{"width":2048,"file":"Battle of Imus Monument.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":1536,"hash":"54"},"lon":120.94027},"Q44488084":{"lat":10.72375,"macroAddress":"Iloilo City","date":"1976","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"c5","height":2083,"width":1738,"file":"Ang Katedral ng Jaro, Iloilo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Josh Lim (Sky Harbor); perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo noong 1874 sa utos ng Kgg. Mariano Cuartero, O. P., unang Obispo ng Jaro; napinsala ng lindol noong Enero, 1948 at ipinaayos sa utos ng Kgg. Jose Ma. Cuenco, unang Arsobispo ng Jaro, 1956. Dito bininyagan si Graciano Lopez Jaena, makabayan at mananalumpati, noong Disyembre 20, 1856.</p>","title":"Ang Katedral ng Jaro, Iloilo","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Jaro Cathedral, Jaro, Iloilo City","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Ang Katedral ng Jaro, Iloilo","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.55649,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Jaro Cathedral":true}},"Q54803536":{"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Lal-lo, Cagayan","lat":18.19933,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Site of the former Church of Tocolana. In former times Lalloc had three parishes: The parish of the Cathedral was served by the secular clergy up to 1788, the parish of Bagumbayan was entrusted to the Dominicans by Bishop Diego de Soria in 1613, and the parish of Tocolana was completely administered by the Dominicans. In the Dominican Hospital of Tocolana, the Rev. Francisco de Capillas, O.P. ministered to the spiritual and corporal needs of the natives of Cagayan.</p>","title":"Lalloc–Tocolana","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Lal-lo Church, Real Street, Lal-lo, Cagayan","name":"Lalloc–Tocolana","region":"Cagayan Valley","lon":121.66126,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q28927475":{"date":"1998","macroAddress":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","lat":8.66691,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"8d","height":1600,"width":1082,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Where Rizal Left for Manila historical marker.jpg"},"text":{"subtitle":"(1861–1896)","title":"Dr. Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Sa dalampasigang ito noong dapithapon ng Hulyo 31, 1896, ang pambansang bayani ng Pilipinas at dangal ng lahing Malayo ay umalis patungong Maynila kasama ang kanyang pamilya at mga kaibigan, na nagbigay wakas sa mahigit na apat na mabungang taon ng pagkakatapon niya sa Dapitan.</p>"}}},"address":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","name":"Dr. Jose Rizal","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.4164,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true}},"Q55097220":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.41559,"name":"Labanan sa Sta. Cruz, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito nakipaglaban ang mga Gerilyang Wha-Chi (Philippine-Chinese Anti Japanese Guerilla Force) sa mga puwersang Hapon upang mapalaya ang bayan ng Sta. Cruz, Laguna, 26 Enero 1945. Sa tulong ng mga gerilyang HUKBALAHAP at HUNTERS ROTC, matagumpay na nakubkob ang simbahang pinagkukutaan ng mga Hapon. Sa labanang ito lubos na nakilala ang mga Gerilyang Wha-Chi sa kanilang tapang sa pakikipaglaban noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig.</p>","title":"Labanan sa Sta. Cruz, Laguna","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Battle of Santa Cruz, Laguna historical marker.jpg","height":4608,"hash":"7d"}}},"address":"M. H. del Pilar Street, Santa Cruz, Laguna","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Laguna","date":"2010","lat":14.28179},"Q56033739":{"lon":122.55689,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Saint Vincent Ferrer Seminary":"St. Vincent Ferrer Seminary"},"locDesc":null,"lat":10.72218,"date":"1990","macroAddress":"Iloilo City","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Seminaryo ng San Vicente Ferrer","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1051,"file":"San Vicente Ferrer Iloilo historical marker seminario.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"23","height":1528},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag upang pagsanayan ng mga klerikong diyosesano, 1869. Dating nasa palasyo ng obispo, sa ilalim ng pangangalaga ng mga pari sa Kongregasyon ng San Vicente de Paul. Itinayo ang unang gusali, 1871; itinatag at binuksan ang klase sa kolehiyo ng seminaryo ng San Vicente de Paul, 1872. Ginawang tirahan ng mga Amerikano, 1899, ngunit pagkaraan ay muling ibinalik sa mga paring Vincentian. Nasunog, 1906; muling itinayo, 1912. Nasira noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Muling binuksan ng paaralan, 1946. Ang kasalukuyang gusali ay ganap na natapos, Hunyo 19, 1954 at pinasinayaan, Agosto 15, 1954. Ilang sa mga kilalang nagsipagtapos sa seminaryong ito ay sina Graciano Lopez Jaena, Martin Delgado, Quintin Salas, Ramon Avanceña, Delfin Jaranilla, ang kanyang kabunyian Jaime Cardinal Sin at iba pa.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Seminaryo ng San Vicente Ferrer"}}},"address":"Saint Vincent Ferrer Seminary, Seminario Street cor. Burgos Street, Jaro, Iloilo City"},"Q24025942":{"lat":14.5809,"macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","date":"1998-02-17","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Memorare","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Photo: Carlo Joseph Moskito; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Gomburza burial Memorare historical marker.jpg","width":2300,"hash":"c2","height":3053},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The mortal remains of the three martyred priests, Fathers Jose A. Burgos, Mariano C. Gomes and Jacinto R. Zamora, were buried in this hallowed ground after their execution on 17 February 1872 for complicity in the Cavite Mutiny.</p><p>This marker was unveiled by His Excellency Fidel V. Ramos, President, Republic of the Philippines, February 17, 1998 on the occasion of the martyrdom of the three priests.</p>","title":"Memorare","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Paco Park, Gen. Luna Street cor. Padre Faura Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"hash":"c4","height":2448,"width":3264,"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"GOMBURZA Burial Site.JPG"},"lon":120.9887,"wikipedia":{"Jacinto Zamora":true,"José Burgos":true,"Mariano Gómez":true,"Gomburza":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of a cross memorial."},"Q45153368":{"lat":10.38327,"macroAddress":"Liloan, Cebu","date":"2006","address":"Bagacay Point Lighthouse, Liloan, Cebu","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Parola ng Bagacay Point","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinayo sa lupaing inilaan ni Gobernador Heneral William Howard Taft, 1904. May taas na 72 talampakan at nagbibigay liwanag na umaabot ng may 17 milyang-dagat. Nagsisilbing gabay sa mga sasakyang dagat na naglalayag sa bukana ng hilagang-silangan ng Cebu Harbor. Isa sa mga nalalabing parolang may mahalagang halimbawa ng arkitekturang Amerikano sa bansa. Ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan, 13 Agosto 2004.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"bc","height":917,"width":749,"file":"Bagacay Point Lighthouse historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines"}}},"region":"Central Visayas","name":"Parola ng Bagacay Point","locPhoto":null,"lon":124.01854,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Bagacay Point Lighthouse":true}},"Q29018419":{"macroAddress":"Catarman, Northern Samar","date":"2014","lat":12.50977,"name":"University of Eastern Philippines","region":"Eastern Visayas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nagsimula bilang paaralang panlalawigan sa pangalang Catarman Farm School, 1918. Naging paaralang bayan dahil sa insular aid ng Pamunuang Pambansa at tinawag na Catarman Agricultural School, 1919; Kalaunan, Catarman Agricultural High School. Tumulong sa mga karatig na pamayanang pang-agrikultura. Nagsilbing lugar para sa pagsasanay-militar ng puwersang gerilya at pansamantalang himpilan ng mga Hapon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Pinangalanang Catarman National Agricultural High School, 1951. Naging Samar Institute of Technology, 1956. Itinalaga bilang unibersidad at tinawag na University of Eastern Philippines, 1964.</p>","title":"University of Eastern Philippines","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"University of Eastern Philippines, Catarman, Northern Samar","lon":124.66689,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"University of Eastern Philippines":true},"locDesc":null},"Q23835528":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Casas Consistoriales","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Casas Consistoriales","subtitle":"(Ayuntamiento)","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayong tahanan ng Cabildo at iba pang pinuno ng pamahalaan ng lungsod ng Maynila. Inilagay ang panukulang bato, 1735; natapos, 1738. Nasira ng lindol, 1863; muling ipinatayo, 1879. Naging luklukan ng pamahalaang kolonyal na Kastila at Amerikano at ng unang Asamblea ng Pilipinas. Sa Salón de Marmol ng gusaling ito pinasinayaan si Sergio Osmeña bilang ispiker noong Oktubre 16, 1907, katungkulang kanyang hinawakan hanggang 1922. Nasira nang bombahin ng hukbong Hapon at Amerikano noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2500,"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Casas Consistoriales historical marker.jpg","height":3616,"hash":"32"}}},"address":"Ayuntamiento de Manila, Cabildo, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.59248,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1989","wikipedia":{"Ayuntamiento de Manila":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall between the northernmost and the second-to-the-northernmost main doors of the building.","lon":120.97331,"locPhoto":{"width":4015,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Casas Consistoriales historical marker vicinity.jpg","height":3016,"hash":"5d"}},"Q22341049":{"wikipedia":{"Calamba Church":"Saint John the Baptist Parish Church (Calamba)"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.16747,"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Pabinyagan ng Simbahan Katoliko ng Kalamba","address":"Calamba Church, Jose Rizal Street, Calamba, Laguna","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Historical marker of the baptistery of Calamba Church.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":384,"hash":"7a","height":481},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pabinyagan ng Simbahan Katoliko ng Kalamba","inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Resolusyon bilang 2, Agosto 19, 1976, ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan na binigyan ng karapatan ng Seksyon 4 ng Kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ang bahaging ito ng Simbahan ng Kalamba ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palantandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"}}},"lat":14.21375,"macroAddress":"Calamba, Laguna","date":"1976"},"Q24763481":{"lon":120.91964,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"date":"1977-10-25","macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas","lat":13.87953,"name":"Bahay ni Apacible","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng resolusyon noong Hunyo 29, 1976 ng Pambansang Suriang Pangkasaysayan na binigyan ng karapatan ng Seksyon 4 ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1, 1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974 ang gusaling ito ay ipinahahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>","title":"Bahay ni Apacible","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"08","height":2325,"file":"Bahay ni Apacible historical marker.jpg","credit":"IJVelas {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1937}}},"address":"Leon Apacible Museum, Calle Marcela Mariño Agoncillo, Taal, Batangas"},"Q54077592":{"lon":120.52049,"locPhoto":null,"wikipedia":{"Valentín Díaz":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":18.06246,"macroAddress":"Paoay, Ilocos Norte","date":"1951","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Birthplace of Valentin Diaz","address":"Roosevelt Avenue, Pannaratan, Paoay, Ilocos Norte","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Here was born, 1 November 1849, Philippine revolutionary hero, Valentin Diaz, son of Geronimo Diaz and Maria Villanueva. Moved to Tayug, Pangasinan, 1857, later became Gobernadorcillo Member of La Liga Filipina, 3 July 1892; Treasurer of the Katipunan, 7 July 1892; Major in the Army of the Revolution, 1895; exiled to Hong Kong, 1897; Colonel in the Philippine Army during the Filipino–American War 1899–1902. Died in Manila, 1916.</p>","title":"Birthplace of Valentin Diaz","subtitle":null},"photo":{"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker Birthplace Valentin Diaz.jpg","width":2189,"hash":"c8","height":3292}}}},"Q24068225":{"locPhoto":{"width":2064,"file":"Agoo Basilica entrance.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","hash":"97","height":2736},"lon":120.36743,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the right-side wall of the recessed main entrance of the basilica.","wikipedia":{"Agoo Basilica":"Basilica Minore of Our Lady of Charity"},"lat":16.32294,"macroAddress":"Agoo, La Union","date":"1982","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"54","height":2853,"credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Basilica of Our Lady of Charity historical marker.jpg","width":2500},"text":{"title":"Basilica of Our Lady of Charity","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Located in La Union's oldest town, Agoo. Parish and town founded in 1578 by Franciscan Frs. Juan Bautista Lucarelli and Sebastian de Baeza. Original church in Barangay Nagrugcan. Improved by Augustinian Fr. Saturnino Franco; Belfry built by Frs. Casimiro Melgosa and Aquilino Garcia. All destroyed by 1892 earthquake. </p><p> Built on this site was the next church where the long-venerated image of Our Lady of Charity was canonically crowned by Apostolic Nuncio Salvatore Sinno on 1 May 1971 by rescript of Pope Paul VI. Demolished in 1975 for a new shrine. Cornerstone laid on 8 Sept. 1975, feast of Our Lady's Nativity, by Archbishop Mariano A. Madriaga, native of the town. Construction started 8 Jan. 1976 from donations by the faithful led by a son of the town, Tourism minister Jose D. Aspiras and his family and encouragement of Bishop Victorino Ligot of San Fernando de La Union Diocese.</p><p>Consecrated Marian shrine on 8 Dec. 1978, feast of the Immaculate Conception by Sebastiano Cardinal Baggio, Prefect of the Sacred Congregation of Bishops, with President Ferdinand E. Marcos and first lady Imelda Romualdez Marcos in Attendance. </p><p>Elevated to rank of Basilica Minore by Pope John Paul II, on 15 July 1982, on petition of Bishop Salvador Lazo through Archbishop Bruno Torpigliani, Apostolic Nuncio to the Philipines. Dedicated as such by Sebastiano Cardinal Baggio on 8 Dec. 1982. </p><p>Msgr. Benito P. Sison, first rector; Msgr. Jose G. Tongson, present rector; Tomas M. Asprer, provincial governor; Jose Luis M. Aspiras, municipal mayor; Ignacio Palma Bautista, architect; Bernardo M. Vergara, Edmundo Tolentino, Jose Manantan and Bernabe Corpuz, supervising engineers.</p>"}}},"address":"Agoo Basilica, Manila North Road cor. Cases Boulevard, Agoo, La Union","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Basilica of Our Lady of Charity"},"Q54943262":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.55509,"wikipedia":{"Graciano López Jaena":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":10.72714,"macroAddress":"Iloilo City","date":"1970-02-15","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Graciano Lopez Jaena","address":"Fajardo Street, Jaro, Iloilo City","details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Graciano Lopez Jaena","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak noong 18 Disyembre 1856. Anak nina Placido Lopez at Maria Jacobe Jaena. Tumungo sa Espanya noong 1880 at naging tagapagtatag at unang patnugot ng La Solidaridad noong 15 Pebrero 1889. Sumulat sa Europa at nangtatanggol sa mga karapatang Pilipino. Nakiisa kina Rizal, del Pilar at ibang Pilipino sa Kilusang Pagpapalaganap noong 1882. Mananalumpati at mamamahayag. Namatay sa Barselona, Espanya, 20 Enero 1896.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"95","height":1762,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Lopez Jaena historical marker.JPG","width":1301}}}},"Q24702672":{"macroAddress":"Mauban, Quezon","date":"2011","lat":14.18917,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nakilala sa tawag na Calvario, dating bahagi ng bulubundukin ng Sierra Madre na nang malaon ay nahiwalay sa pagtatabas ng lupa upang gawing kalsada. Pinakamataas na bahagi ng kabayanan na ginamit bilang bantayan at sa mga gawaing panrelihiyon noong panahon ng Espanyol. Naging punong himpilan ng mga sundalong Amerikano at bantayan ng Philippine Constabulary noong panahon ng Amerikano, at ng civilian emergency administration noong panahon ng Hapon. Itinayo ang bantayog para kay Jose Rizal, Disyembre 1925.</p>","title":"Rizal Hill Park","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"26","credit":"Lawrence Ruiz (Epi Fabonan III) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Rizal Hill Park 4.jpg","width":3456}}},"address":"Mauban, Quezon","name":"Rizal Hill Park","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":{"hash":"ff","height":4608,"width":3456,"file":"Rizal Hill Park 5.jpg","credit":"Lawrence Ruiz (Epi Fabonan III) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"lon":121.73097,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the pedestal for the statue of José Rizal.","wikipedia":null},"Q52145038":{"address":"Hermano Pule Shrine, Lucban–Luisiana Road, Lucban, Quezon","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Lalong kilala sa pangalang “Hermano Puli”. Isinilang noong Hulyo 22, 1815 dito sa Sitio Pandak ng bayan ng Lucban, (Tayabas) Quezon, kung saan niya natamo ang pangunahing pag-aaral ng pananampalataya natanggap na hermano sa <u>San Juan de Dios</u>.</p><p>Kabilang sa labinsiyam na dating hermano na nagtatag ng <u>Cofradia de San Jose</u>, na naging tagapagtanggol ng kalayaan sa pananampalataya at ng karapatang panlipunan.</p><p>Namatay noong Nobyembre 4, 1841 sa isang sagupaan ng mga Pilipino at mga Kastila.</p>","title":"Apolinario de la Cruz","subtitle":"(1815–1841)"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Apolinario de la Cruz","lat":14.14415,"date":"1977","macroAddress":"Lucban, Quezon","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Hermano Pule":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.54566},"Q56049577":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.94155,"wikipedia":{"Evelio Javier":true},"locDesc":null,"lat":10.74397,"date":"2006-02-11","macroAddress":"San Jose de Buenavista, Antique","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Evelio B. Javier","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Evelio B. Javier","inscription":"<p>Isinilang kina Everardo Javier at Felisa Bellaflor sa Lanag, Hamtik, Antique, 31 Oktubre 1942. Nagtapos ng Bachelor of Arts, 1963; Bachelor of Laws, 1968, sa Ateneo de Manila University; at ng Masters in Public Administration, Harvard University, 1982. Nagsilbing gobernador ng Antique, 1972–1980. Naging inspirasyon ng mga Antiqueño ang kanyang masigasig na panunungkulan at mabuting pamamalakad ng lalawigan.</p><p> Pinaslang sa pook na ito noong 11 Pebrero 1986 habang binabantayan ang bilangan ng mga boto sa naganap na Snap Presidential Elections. Bilang paggunita sa kanyang kabayanihan, ipinahayag ang araw na ito bilang taunang pistang pambayan sa pulo ng Panay.</p>"}}},"address":"Evelio B. Javier Freedom Park, Governor Villavert Street, San Jose de Buenavista, Antique"},"Q31440525":{"date":"1953","macroAddress":"Balilihan, Bohol","lat":9.75589,"name":"Balilihan Belfry","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":937,"file":"Balilihan Belfry historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","height":1301,"hash":"e2"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Constructed of materials taken near Baclayon, 1844, by Recollect Fr. Antonio Cortes. Withstood the 1863 storm which destroyed the church, utilized as guard post by the Spanish, Filipino, American and Japanese forces.</p>","title":"Balilihan Belfry","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Balilihan Belfry, Balilihan, Bohol","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.97368,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q23854678":{"region":"Overseas","name":"Dr. Jose Rizal","details":{"de":{"text":{"title":"Dr. Jose Rizal","subtitle":"(1861–1896)","inscription":"<p>Nationalheld der Philippinen, war Arzt und Dichter. Als Reformer und Kritiker der Kolonialregierung Spanien stand Rizal für den gewaltlosen Widerstand und vollendete in diesem Haus seinen stark autobiographisch geprägten Roman, Noli me tangere.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"6f","height":2576,"file":"José Rizal historical marker in Berlin.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2500}}},"address":"Jägerstraße 71 cor. Glinkastraße, Mitte, Berlin, Germany","lat":52.5138,"date":"2003","macroAddress":"Berlin, Germany","wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true,"Noli Me Tángere":"Noli Me Tángere (novel)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the building’s entrance.","lon":13.38659,"locPhoto":{"width":4128,"file":"Building where Jose Rizal marker in Berlin is located 03.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","height":3096,"hash":"91"}},"Q51901440":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the right of the main door of the lighthouse building.","wikipedia":{"Cape Santiago Lighthouse":true},"locPhoto":{"file":"Cape Santiago Lighthouse Facade.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4000,"height":3000,"hash":"4e"},"lon":120.65303,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":4000,"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Cape Santiago Lighthouse Historical Marker.jpg","height":3000,"hash":"a3"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Kilala bilang Faro de Cabo Santiago. Unang siniyasat at ipinanukala ni Margin Pers y Pers, 1887. Itinayo ng Aldecoa y Cia na yari sa ladrilyo batay sa disenyo ni Guillermo Brockman, 1890. Nagsilbing gabay ng mga naglalayag sa daungan ng Maynila</p>","title":"Parola ng Cape Santiago","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Cape Santiago Lighthouse, Calatagan, Batangas","name":"Parola ng Cape Santiago","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Calatagan, Batangas","date":"2018","lat":13.77206},"Q40176820":{"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1869–1964)","title":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy","inscription":"<p>First President of the Republic of the Philippines, 1899–1901, and leader of the Filipino People in the revolution against Spanish rule, 1896–1898 and the Filipino–American War, 1899–1901. Born March 22, 1869, Kawit, Cavite. Became Municipal Captain of Kawit. Inducted into Masonry and initiated into the Katipunan under his chosen name, Magdalo, 1895. Led in the capture of Kawit, Imus, Bacoor and other towns in Cavite during the outbreak of the Philippine Revolution in 1896. His military victories provided prestige which led to his election, in absentia, as president of the First Revolutionary Government during the Tejeros Convention on March 22, 1897. Went to self-exile in Hongkong in accordance with the Pact of Biak-na-Bato and forged an alliance with the United States of America to overthrow Spanish rule in the Philippines. Returned from Hongkong, May 19, 1898 and resumed the struggle for freedom. Proclaimed Philippine independence on June 12, 1898 at Kawit. On this occasion the Philippine national flag made in Hongkong by Dona Marcela de Agoncillo was officially unfurled and the Marcha Nacional which became the Philippine National Anthem was played publicly for the first time. Convened the Revolutionary Congress in Malolos, Bulacan, September 15, 1898. Led the Filipino forces during the Filipino–American War and was captured in Palanan, Isabela on March 23, 1901.</p><p>Died at the Veterans Memorial Hospital, Quezon City, February 6, 1964.</p>"},"photo":{"height":3966,"hash":"b8","width":2500,"file":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"}}},"address":"Aguinaldo Shrine, Kawit Loop Road, Kawit, Cavite","name":"Emilio Aguinaldo y Famy","region":"Calabarzon","date":"1998","macroAddress":"Kawit, Cavite","lat":14.44532,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Emilio Aguinaldo":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.90689},"Q24004133":{"address":"Paco Park, Gen. Luna Street cor. Padre Faura Street, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Jose Rizal","inscription":"<p>Executed 30 December 1896; interred secretly in this spot by the authorities on the same day; guarded for fifteen days by the Guardia Civil Veterana. Remains exhumed 17 August 1898, placed in an urn made by Teodoro Romualdo de Jesus, deposited in the house of his mother in Estraude Street, Binondo, and on 30 December 1912 laid beneath his monument at the Luneta.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Jose Rizal Marker on Paco Cemetery.JPG","width":2448,"height":3264,"hash":"85"}}},"name":"Jose Rizal","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","date":"1957","lat":14.5817,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the ground, in front of a cross monument dedicated to José Rizal.","wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"lon":120.98873,"locPhoto":{"height":1536,"hash":"39","width":2048,"file":"Paco Park - José Rizal memorial.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}},"Q46540162":{"date":"1973-04-27","macroAddress":"Bato, Catanduanes","lat":13.58815,"name":"Dambana sa Batalay","region":"Bicol Region","address":"Batalay Shrine, Brgy. Batalay, Bato, Catanduanes","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Dambana sa Batalay","inscription":"<p>Bilang pagpapahalaga sa mga kaugaliang katutubo na nagpasalin-salin sa mga henerasyon ng mga taga-Katandungan at upang gunitain ang Agustinong si Padre Diego de Herrera, ang unang misyonerong Kristiyano ng ekspedisyong Legazpi–Urdaneta na inilibing sa pook na ito noong 1576. Dinadalaw ng mga manlalakbay pangrelihiyon sa buong lalawigan ng Catanduanes. </p><p>Inihayag ng obispo ng Lungsod ng Legazpi na isang <u>Diocesan Shrine</u> ng Banal na Krus noong Abril 1, 1973.</p>"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.31532,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q56158571":{"macroAddress":"Cebu City","date":"1980","lat":10.31157,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"","subtitle":null,"title":"Colegio de la Inmaculada Concepcion"}}},"address":"Colegio de la Inmaculada Concepcion, Gorordo Avenue, Cebu City","name":"Colegio de la Inmaculada Concepcion","region":"Central Visayas","lon":123.90399,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Colegio de la Inmaculada Concepcion":true}},"Q54395488":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Oton":"Oton, Iloilo"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.47783,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isa sa mga sentro ng kalakalan at komersiyo sa Kabisayaan mula ika-12 siglo hanggang dumating ang mga Espanyol. Dating kabisera ng probinsya ng Ogtong (ngayo’y lalawigan ng Iloilo), 1570–1581. Nagsilbing daungan, pagawaan ng mga sasakyang pandagat at pinagkukunan ng mga pangangailangan sa mga kampo ng mga sundalong Espanyol sa Moluccas at Mindanao, ika-16 na siglo. Tinanggap bilang pangatlong misyon ng mga Agustino sa labas ng Maynila at Cebu, 3 Mayo 1572. Lubhang nasalanta sa pakikidigma ng mga Espanyol laban sa mga Ingles (1593), pananalakay at panununog ng mga Olandes (1630), at paglusob ng mga Moro na tutol sa pananakop ng mga Espanyol sa Mindanao (1662).</p>","title":"Bayan ng Oton","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Oton Municipal Hall, Rizal Street cor. Bonifacio Street, Oton, Iloilo","name":"Bayan ng Oton","region":"Western Visayas","macroAddress":"Oton, Iloilo","date":"2013-05-03","lat":10.69218},"Q24702093":{"lat":13.96347,"macroAddress":"Sariaya, Quezon","date":"1938","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Sariaya Church Historical Marker.jpg","width":2992,"height":2730,"hash":"6d"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The first church dates from 1599. The second church, built in 1605, was replaced by a third in 1641. In 1703 the town was transferred to Lumangbayan, but the earthquakes and floods of 1743 destroyed the church and the town and caused the people to transfer to the present site. The present church was built in 1748.</p>","title":"Church of Sariaya","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Sariaya Church, General Luna Street, Sariaya, Quezon","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Church of Sariaya","lon":121.52397,"locPhoto":{"height":1856,"hash":"a0","width":2439,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Church of Sariaya historical marker vicinity.jpg"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the right of the main entrance of the church at the base of the bell tower.","wikipedia":{"Sariaya Church":"Saint Francis of Assisi Parish Church"}},"Q40501131":{"name":"Rizal Fountain","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Rizal Park, Roxas Boulevard, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Rizal fountain.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":344,"hash":"02","height":415},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating nasa tahanan ni Pastor Karl Ullmer sa Wilhelmsfeld, Alemanya kung saan nanirahan si Jose Rizal nang tapusin niya ang mga huling kabanata ng nobelang Noli me Tangere, 1886. Ipinagkaloob ng pamahalaan ng Alemanya sa Pilipinas bilang tanda ng makasaysayang relasyon ng dalawang bansa at inilagay sa Rizal Park, 30 Disyembre 1964. Isinaayos, 1994. Muling isinaayos bilang bahagi ng ika-150 taong pagdiriwang ng kapanganakan ni Rizal, 2011.</p>","title":"Rizal Fountain","subtitle":null}}},"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"2011-12-30","lat":14.58082,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97761},"Q52542570":{"wikipedia":{"Gregorio Aglipay":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.56173,"name":"Birthplace of Gregorio Aglipay","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Site where Archbishop Gregorio Aglipay, soldier, religious reformer and patriot, was born, 8 May 1860. Son of Pedro Aglipay and Victoria Labayan. Ordained Catholic priest, 1889; first military chaplain of the Philippine Revolution, 1896; member of the Malolos Congress and Vicar General of the Revolution, 1898; and founder of the Philippine Independent Church, 1902. Died, 1 September 1940.</p>","title":"Birthplace of Gregorio Aglipay","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"62","height":3107,"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker at the Birthplace of Gregorio Aglipay.jpg","width":2066}}},"address":"Gregorio Aglipay National Shrine, Msgr. Aglipay Street cor. Najera Street, Batac, Ilocos Norte","macroAddress":"Batac, Ilocos Norte","date":"1949","lat":18.05253},"Q29018404":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.18232,"wikipedia":{"Capul Church":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"Capul, Northern Samar","date":"2011","lat":12.4228,"name":"Simbahan ng Capul","region":"Eastern Visayas","address":"Capul Church, Capul, Northern Samar","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Paring Heswita bilang Misyon, 1596. Ipinatayo yari sa nipa at kahoy ang unang simbahan sa patronato ni San Ignacio de Loyola; muling ipinatayo kasabay ang kuta na yari sa bato bilang tanggulan laban sa mga mandirigmang Moro ca. 1600. Isinailalim sa pamamahala ng mga paring Pransiskano, 1768. Ipinaayos ni Padre Mariano Valero ang simbahan at ipinatayo ang kampanaryo, 1781. Itinalaga ng obispo ng Cebu bilang parokya, 8 Nobyembre 1864. Isinagawa ang lagusan ng kuta sa kanang bahagi ng simbahan, 1898. Pangunahing halimbawa ng simbahang tanggulan noong panahon ng mga Espanyol.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Capul","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"b5","height":1051,"file":"Historical Marker of Capul Church, Northern Samar.JPG","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":710}}}},"Q43264019":{"lat":13.43554,"macroAddress":"Boac, Marinduque","date":"2015-06-04","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Nagsilbing pangunahing daungan ng bayan ng Boac mula noong ika-19 na dantaon. Ginamit na pantalan ng mga bapor na naghahatid ng mga pasahero, kargada, at lokal na produkto ng Marinduque papuntang Maynila at mga karatig pook. Ginamit na daungan ng mga rebolusyonaryong Pilipino, 1896 at 1898. Itinayo ang kongkretong daungan noong ika-20 dantaon.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Puwerto ng Laylay, Boac"},"photo":null}},"address":"Circumferential Road, Boac, Marinduque","region":"Mimaropa","name":"Puwerto ng Laylay, Boac","lon":121.81892,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q29018396":{"address":"Palapag Church, Palapag, Northern Samar","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Heswita bilang Misyon ng Cabo de Espiritu Santo sa Hilagang Samar sa patronato ng Nuestra Señora de la Asuncion, 1605. Ipinatayo ang unang simbahan na yari sa kahoy at nipa. Dito nagsimula ang himagsikan ni Agustin Sumuroy na lumaganap sa ibang bahagi ng Samar at Leyte, 1 Hunyo 1649. Tinapos ni Ignacio Alcina, S.J. ang simbahang may hugis krus, kumbento at kuta na yari sa korales at bato bilang tanggulan sa mga pirata, 1663. Dito tumuloy ang mga Heswita, Pransiskano, at Dominikano na lulan ng galyong \"Concepcion\" na dumaong sa Palapag, 1666. Isinailalim sa pamamahala ng mga paring Pransiskano, 1768-1941. Huling ginamit nang matapos ang bagong simbahan, mga taong 1970. Ipinatayo sa harapan nito ang malaking krus bilang alaala sa ika-400 na taong pagkakatatag ng Kristyanismo sa Hilagang Samar, 1995.</p>","title":"Lumang Simbahan ng Palapag","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":922,"hash":"12","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Palapag Church Ruins historical marker.jpg","width":654}}},"name":"Lumang Simbahan ng Palapag","region":"Eastern Visayas","macroAddress":"Palapag, Northern Samar","date":"2010","lat":12.54536,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":125.11556},"Q54841701":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Bessang Pass":true},"lon":120.44882,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"The Bitalag Road Junction","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This road junction which served as vital Japanese outpost, was assaulted by elements of the 121st Infantry, USAFIP NL, on 8 January 1945 and was captured four days later. The siege of Bitalag was the initial action in the great battle for Bessang Pass, farther to the east, whose capture on 14 June 1945 hastened the surrender of the Japanese Imperial Forces in the Philippines.</p>"}}},"address":"Bitalag Park, Km. 320 Manila North Road cor. Tagudin–Cervantes–Sabangan Road, Brgy. Bitalag, Tagudin, Ilocos Sur","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"The Bitalag Road Junction","lat":16.96841,"date":"1958","macroAddress":"Tagudin, Ilocos Sur"},"Q54666420":{"macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","date":"2007-11-23","lat":14.57413,"name":"Chapel of the Crucified Christ","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"St. Paul University Manila","title":"Chapel of the Crucified Christ","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ayon sa disenyo ni Arkitekto Andres Luna de San Pedro sa pamumuno ni Reverend Mother Saint Xavier Vermeersch, SPC at pinasinayaan ni Apostolic Nuncio Guglielmo Piani, 1927. Ginamit ng puwersang Hapones noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig, 1944–1945. Nasunog ang simbahan maliban sa harapan na may disenyo ng krusipiho noong Labanan sa Maynila na ikinasawi ng maraming sibilyan na nagkanlong dito, 1945. Muling ipinatayo ayon sa orihinal na disenyo at pinasinayaan ni Arsobispo Michael J. O’Doherty ng Maynila, 1948.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Chapel of the Crucified Christ (St. Paul Manila) historical marker.jpg","width":2969,"hash":"9e","height":3988}}},"address":"Chapel of the Crucified Christ, St. Paul University Manila, 680 Pedro Gil Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","lon":120.98614,"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"c0","file":"FvfStPaulChapeljdg8959 03.JPG","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the left column on the church facade."},"Q55717576":{"lat":14.8186,"macroAddress":"Balagtas, Bulacan","date":"1949","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito sa nayon ng Pañginay, bayan ng Bigaá, Bulakán, isinilang si Francisco <i>Balagtas</i> Baltazar, noóng iká-2 ng Abril, 1788. Anák nina Juan Baltazar at Juana de la Cruz. Siya ang kinikilalang Amá ng wikang Tagalog na maykatha ng waláng kamatayang awit na <i>Florante at Laura</i>. Siná José Burgos, José Rizal, Marcelo H. del Pilar, Mariano Ponce, Macario Adriatico, Epifanio de los Santos, Rafael Palma, at ibá pang pantás at bayani ng bansá, ay nagsikilala sa kadakilaan ng nasabing awit ni Balagtas. Namatay siya sa bayan ng Udyong, Bataan, noong iká-20 ng Pebrero, 1862.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Pook na Sinilangan ni Balagtas"},"photo":{"width":3456,"file":"Balagtas birth place historical marker in Panginay, Balagtas, Bulacan.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"aa","height":4608}}},"address":"Francisco Balagtas Memorial School, Bigaa–Plaridel Road, Brgy. Panginay, Balagtas, Bulacan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Pook na Sinilangan ni Balagtas","locPhoto":{"height":3456,"hash":"00","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Balagtas,Bulacanjf9650 33.JPG","width":4608},"lon":120.89557,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting by the entrance to house replica in the school grounds.","wikipedia":{"Francisco Balagtas":true}},"Q54718604":{"address":"Plaza Zamora, Teodoro San Luis Street, Pandacan, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"file":"Zamora Marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":278,"height":440,"hash":"51"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito ng Pandakan, Maynila, isinilang noong ika-14 ng Agosto, 1835 si Pari Jacinto Zamora. Magiting na anak nina Venancio Zamora at Hilaria del Rosario. Binitay na kasama ng mga paring sina Jose Burgos at Mariano Gomez noong ika-17 ng Pebrero, 1872, dahilan sa kanilang pagtatanggol sa mga karapatan ng mga paring Pilipino.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Pari Jacinto Zamora"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Pari Jacinto Zamora","lat":14.59112,"date":"1954","macroAddress":"Pandacan, Manila","locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the monument pedestal of Jacinto Zamora.","wikipedia":{"Jacinto Zamora":true},"lon":121.0028,"locPhoto":{"height":640,"hash":"be","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Zamora Monument.jpg","width":480}},"Q53085102":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.03722,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"ABS-CBN Corporation":"ABS-CBN","Television in the Philippines":true},"lat":14.63981,"date":"2003","macroAddress":"Quezon City, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Unang Brodkast sa Telebisyon sa Pilipinas","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Inilunsad ng Alto Broadcasting System (ABS) sa DZAQ Channel 3 ang unang brodkast sa telebisyon sa Pilipinas, 23 Oktubre 1953. Itinatag ni Eugene J. Lopez ang Chronicle Broadcasting Network, 1955. Nabili ang ABS, 1957, at ang dalawang network ay nakilala bilang ABS-CBN, 1963. Naging ABS-CBN Corporation, 1967. Ipinatayo itong sentro ng pagbobrodkast ng network ng radyo't telebisyon sa Bohol Avenue, 24 Pebrero 1967. Pinasinayaan, 18 Disyembre 1968.</p>"}}},"address":"ABS-CBN Broadcasting Center, Sergeant Esguerra Avenue, Brgy. South Triangle, Diliman, Quezon City, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Unang Brodkast sa Telebisyon sa Pilipinas"},"Q52984027":{"address":"Asan Beach Unit, War in the Pacific National Historical Park, Marine Corps Drive, Asan, Asan-Maina, Guam, United States of America","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":"(1854–1903)","title":"Apolinario Mabini","inscription":"<p>Filipino patriot, nationalist, statesman, and political scientist, Prime Minister and Secretary of Foreign Affairs of the First Philippine Republic. Banished to Guam as “the most prominent irreconcilable among the Filipinos.” He lived in a building on this site of Asan, from February 1901 to February 1903. With him were revolutionary General Artemio Recarte, Pio del Pilar, Maximino Hizon, and 54 other Filipino political prisoners.</p>"}}},"name":"Apolinario Mabini","region":"Overseas","date":"1964","macroAddress":"Guam, United States","lat":13.47462,"locDesc":"The historical marker is attached to a vertical concrete pedestal at Asan Beach.","wikipedia":{"Apolinario Mabini":true},"locPhoto":{"height":3240,"hash":"ac","width":4320,"credit":"Daderot","file":"Apolinario Mabini memorial - War in the Pacific National Historical Park (Asan Beach Unit) - DSC00847.JPG"},"lon":144.70899},"Q50086781":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.65474,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"macroAddress":"Camalig, Albay","date":"2014-12-15","lat":13.18209,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinayo ng mga Fransiskano ang unang simbahan yari sa kahoy at nipa sa patronato ni San Juan Bautista, 1579–1580. Itinayo ng mga bilanggo ang pangalawang simbahan yari sa bato, 1605. Nasira nang pumutok ang Bulkang Mayon, 1766 at 1814. Muling ipinatayo nina Padre Francisco Latoba at Padre Manuel Brihuega, 1837. Ipinagawa ang harapan ng simbahan, kampanaryo at Escuela Catolica ni Padre Miguel Barcela, 1845. Pinamunuan ng mga Fransiskano sa mahigit na apat na dantaon, 1579–1983.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Camalig"},"photo":null}},"address":"Camalig Church, R. Nasol Street cor. B. Buena Street, Camalig, Albay","name":"Simbahan ng Camalig","region":"Bicol Region"},"Q52030144":{"lat":14.56624,"macroAddress":"Makati, Metro Manila","date":"1937","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Church and Monastery of Guadalupe","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"85","file":"Our Lady of Grace Church in Makati. Marker.JPG","credit":"Ronaldbunag {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3072},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The foundations of this Church and Monastery of the Augustinian Order were laid in 1601 and construction work was finished in 1629. Nuestra Señora de Guadalupe was chosen titular patroness in 1603. After the Chinese uprising of 1639 this sanctuary served as a seat of devotion for the Chinese. The buildings withstood the earthquakes of 1645, 1658, 1754 and 1863; the masonry roof of the church collapsed in the earthquakes of 1880 and the structure was rebuilt in 1882 by Rev. Jose Corujedo, O.S.A. Site of an orphan asylum and trade school administered by the Augustinian Order for the benefit of the children of the victims of the cholera of 1882. Both church and monastery were gutted by fire in February, 1899, during the early skirmishes between Americans and Filipinos.</p>","title":"Church and Monastery of Guadalupe","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Nuestra Señora de Gracia Church, 7440 Bernardino Street, Guadalupe Viejo, Makati, Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"hash":"d2","height":3456,"file":"02516jfChurch and Monastery of Guadalupe Makati Cityfvf 01.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4608},"lon":121.0431,"wikipedia":{"Nuestra Señora de Gracia Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the right side of the church facade."},"Q55283241":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.14545,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Rodriguez":"Rodriguez, Rizal"},"lat":14.73249,"date":"2009","macroAddress":"Rodriguez, Rizal","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Bayan ng Rodriguez","inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang bayan ng Montalban mula sa apat na baryo ng bayan ng San Mateo, 27 Abril 1871. Sa yungib ng Pamitinan naganap ang mga lihim na pagpupulong ng Katipunan. Lumahok sa himagsikan laban sa mga Espanyol, 1898. Dito naganap ang labanan sa pagitan ng mga Filipino at Amerikano sa pamumuno ni Hen. Licerio Geronimo, 1899. Isinama sa San Mateo, Oktubre 1903–1908. Naging nagsasariling bayan, 1 Enero 1909. Pinangalanang Rodriguez bilang parangal kay Eulogio “Amang” Rodriguez, Sr. na dating punong lalawigan ng Rizal (1916–1922), 27 Hunyo 1982.</p>"}}},"address":"Rodriguez Municipal Hall, J.P. Rizal Street, Rodriguez, Rizal","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Bayan ng Rodriguez"},"Q56052532":{"macroAddress":"Cebu City","date":"2010","lat":10.30034,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3264,"hash":"c1","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"University of San Carlos historical marker.jpg","width":2448},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Established at the instance of Bishop Mateo Joaquin Rubio de Arevalo as Seminario de San Carlos at the former site of Colegio San Ildefonso of the Jesuits, 1779. Became Seminario Conciliar de San Carlos, 1825. Administered by the Vincentians and renamed Seminario–Colegio de San Carlos, 1867. Sergio Osmeña, fourth President of the Philippines, one of the first graduates conferred a bachelor’s degree, 1894. Formed as a corporation under Rector Jacinto Villalain, 1911. Separated from the Seminary, 1922. Transferred to this site, 1930. Placed under the Society of the Divine Word (SVD), 1935. Reopened after the Second World War, 1945. Became university, 1948. Fr. Amante Castillo, first Filipino president, 1970.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"University of San Carlos"}}},"address":"University of San Carlos, P. del Rosario Street, Cebu City","name":"University of San Carlos","region":"Central Visayas","locPhoto":null,"lon":123.89853,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"University of San Carlos":true}},"Q55088581":{"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"f6","width":3456,"file":"CaviteCityjf5302 07.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"lon":120.8877,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal on which a bust of Julian Felipe stands.","wikipedia":{"Julián Felipe":true},"lat":14.47247,"macroAddress":"Cavite City, Cavite","date":"1955","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Here in the City of Cavite was Born on 28 January, 1861 Julian Felipe","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Patriot, composer and professor of music. Son of Justo Felipe and Victoria Reyes. Arrested with the Thirteen Martyrs of Cavite and imprisoned in Fort San Felipe, Septermber, 1896. Composed the “Philippine National Anthem,” 1898. Imprisoned in Fort Santiago by the Americans, 1899. Taught piano lessons, 1903–1942. Died in Sampaloc, Manila, 2 October, 1944.</p>"},"photo":{"height":4608,"hash":"d3","width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Julian Felipe historical marker in Cavite City.jpg"}}},"address":"Julian Felipe Boulevard cor. Miranda Street, Cavite City, Cavite","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Here in the City of Cavite was Born on 28 January, 1861 Julian Felipe"},"Q28919992":{"lat":7.09397,"macroAddress":"Davao City","date":"2003","region":"Davao Region","name":"Ohta Kyozaburo","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Hyogo, Japan, Pebrero 1876. Nagtatag, Ohta Development Company. Ang unang taniman ng abaka ng mga Hapon sa Pilipinas, 3 Mayo 1907. Nagtatag ng iba pang mga kumpanya tulad ng Mintal Plantation Company, Riverside Plantation Company, Talomo River Plantation Company at Guianga Plantation Company. Tumulong sa paglago ng negosyong Hapones sa Davao. Namatay sa Kyoto, Japan, 31 Oktubre 1917.</p>","title":"Ohta Kyozaburo","subtitle":"(1876–1917)"},"photo":{"file":"Ohta Kyozaburo historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","width":1096,"hash":"c5","height":1600}}},"address":"Mintal Elementary School, Brgy. Mintal, Tugbok, Davao City","locPhoto":null,"lon":125.50026,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q22295396":{"macroAddress":"Lipa, Batangas","date":"2011-04-12","lat":13.94092,"name":"Arsobispado ng Lipa","region":"Calabarzon","address":"Lipa Cathedral, Lipa, Batangas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinahayag ng mga Agustino ang ebanghelyo sa ngayo'y lalawigan ng Batangas, 1572. Naging bahagi ng Obispado ng Maynila, 1579 at Arsobispado ng Maynila, 1595. Itinatag ang Obispado sa pamamagitan ng dekretong konsistoryal “Novas Erigere Ecclesias” ni Papa San Pio X, sakop ang lalawigan ng Batangas, Laguna, Tayabas, at Mindoro, 10 Abril 1910. Naging katedra ang Lipa. Giuseppe Petrelli, D.D., unang obispo, Abril 1910–Marso 1916. Alfredo Verzosa, unang Filipinong obispo, 1916–1950. Naging arsobispado na binubuo ng lalawigan ng Batangas, 20 Hunyo 1972. Alejandro Olalia, unang arsobispo.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Arsobispado ng Lipa"},"photo":{"height":4750,"hash":"76","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction and retouching: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Arsobispado ng Lipa historical marker.jpg","width":3377}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.16374,"wikipedia":{"Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Lipa":true},"locDesc":null},"Q28868870":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Baker Memorial Hall":true,"Raid at Los Baños":"Raid on Los Baños"},"lon":121.24247,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ginamit ng mga Hapones bilang bilangguang kampo para sa mga bihag na Amerikano at ibang banyaga noong 1943. Nilusob ng pinagsanib na pangkat ng mga gerilyang Filipino mula sa mga kasapi ng ROTC Hunters, HUKBALAHAP ika-48 iskwadrong Tsino, sariling pangkat ni Pangulong Quezon, Pangkat Marking, at iba pang di-regular na tropa noong 23 Pebrero 1945. Ang pinagsanib na puwersa ay inorganisa ni Tinyente Koronel Gustavo Ingles na kasapi ng Hunters at kinatawan ng puwersang Amerikanong nangangasiwa sa mga gerilya ng Katimugang Luzon. Pinamunuan ni Tinyente Koronel Honorio Guerrero at ng ROTC Hunters ang unang salakay. Matagumpay nilang nakontrol ang paligi ng kampo at sa tulong ng mga Amerikanong miyembro ng Company B 511th Paratroop Infantry ay napalaya ang 2,147 bilanggo.</p>","title":"Pook ng Bilangguang Kampo sa Los Baños","subtitle":null},"photo":{"width":654,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Baker Hall historical marker.jpg","height":900,"hash":"53"}}},"address":"Baker Memorial Hall, Mariano M. Mondoñedo Avenue, Los Baños, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Pook ng Bilangguang Kampo sa Los Baños","lat":14.16179,"macroAddress":"Los Baños, Laguna","date":"2005"},"Q36164177":{"name":"International Rice Research Institute","region":"Calabarzon","address":"International Rice Research Institute, Pili Drive, Los Baños, Laguna","details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"b3","height":1408,"width":1029,"file":"IRRI historical marker 2.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Established through the cooperation of Ford and Rockefeller Foundations and the Philippine Government to launch an intensive research and development for new methods of rice production, 1960. Dr. Robert F. Chandler, First Director General, 1960–1971. Played a major role in initiating the green revolution in Asia. Successfully bred a new type of rice, IR 8 or Miracle Rice that improved the production of rice in the Philippines, 29 November 1966. It is a major world center of scientific research on rice.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"International Rice Research Institute"}},"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"International Rice Research Institute","inscription":"<p>Naitatag mula sa pagtutulungan ng Ford at Rockefeller Foundation at ng Pamahalaan ng Pilipinas upang maglunsad ng malawakang pananaliksik at pagpapaunlad ng makabagong pamamaraan sa produksyon ng palay, 1960. Dr. Robert F. Chandler, Jr., unang direktor heneral, 1960–1971. Kabalikat sa paglulunsad ng Green Revolution sa Asya. Matagumpay na nakapaglikha ng bagong uri ng palay, IR8 o Miracle Rice, na nakapagpataas ng produksyon ng palay sa Pilipinas, 29 Nobyembre 1966. Pandaigdigang sentro ng pag-aaral sa agham ng pagtatanim ng palay.</p>"},"photo":{"height":1412,"hash":"91","width":1023,"file":"IRRI historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"macroAddress":"Los Baños, Laguna","date":"2010-04-14","lat":14.16883,"wikipedia":{"International Rice Research Institute":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":121.25524,"locPhoto":null},"Q54757703":{"address":"San Miguel Church, 1000 J.P. Laurel Street cor. General Solano Street, San Miguel, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":623,"hash":"33","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"SanMiguelChurch HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg","width":472},"text":{"title":"Simbahan ng San Miguel","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinayo ng mga Hesuwita ang unang simbahang yari sa bato sa tabi ng Tripa de Gallina, 1603. Naging simbahang pangparokya, 1603. Sentro ng misyong Hapon, 1615. Ibinigay sa pamamahala ng mga paring sekular, 1768, at sa mga Pransiskano, 1777. Inilipat sa pinagkakatayuan ngayon at pinasailalim sa Parokya ng Quiapo, 1783. Ibinalik sa mga Pransiskano, 1797. Pinangasiwaan ng mga paring sekular, 1899. Itinayo ang kasalukuyang simbahan, 1913. Hinirang na Pro-Katedral ng Maynila, 1946–1958. Ginawang Pambansang Dambana ni San Miguel at ng mga Arkanghel, 1986.</p>"}}},"name":"Simbahan ng San Miguel","region":"Metro Manila","date":"2003-09-28","macroAddress":"San Miguel, Manila","lat":14.59224,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade below the window to the right of the main entrance.","wikipedia":{"San Miguel Church":"San Miguel Church (Manila)"},"lon":120.99157,"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"fb","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Facade of San Miguel Church Manila.jpg","width":3456}},"Q24702362":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.61317,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lat":13.9285,"macroAddress":"Lucena","date":"1987-08-17","address":"Lucena","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"width":1944,"file":"Quezon Provincial Capitol Marker.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":2592,"hash":"b9"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Quezon Provincial Capitol","inscription":"<p>Dating Tayabas capitol na ipinatayo sa loteng ipinagkaloob ni abogado Filemon E. Perez noong 1908. Ginawang kongkreto batay sa balangkas at detalye ng kasangguning arkitekto ayon sa itinakda ng Public Act 1637, April 30, 1907. Binago at pinalaki noong 1930 sa panunungkulan ni Governador Leon G. Guinto at tinapos noong 1935 sa panunungkulan ni Governador Maximo Rodriguez. Nasira noong ikalawang digmaang pandaigdig at ipinaayos sa pamamagitan ng U.S. Philippine Rehabilitation (Tydings) Act, April 30, 1946. Pinangalanang Quezon Provincial Capitol sa bisa ng Republic Act No. 14 September 7, 1946, na nagpalit sa pangalan ng lalawigang Tayabas ng Quezon.</p>"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Quezon Provincial Capitol"},"Q23848781":{"wikipedia":{"Lumban Church":"San Sebastian Parish Church (Lumban)"},"locDesc":null,"lon":121.45922,"locPhoto":null,"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Church of Lumbang","details":{"en":{"text":{"title":"Church of Lumbang","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Lumbang was for a time the center of all missionary activities in Laguna. Rev. Juan de Plasencia, O.F.M., ministered here in 1578. The original Church, of wood and thatch, was destroyed by fire, being replaced by the first stone Church to be built in Laguna, completed here in 1600. A solemn Eucharistic procession was held here on October 9, 1600. The Church was seriously damed by the earthquakes of 1880. A rest-house for sick Franciscan missionaries was maintained here from 1606 to 1618. Rev. Juan de Santa Maria, O.F.M., conducted here in 1606 a regional school, where 400 boys were taught liturgical hymns and the use of musical instruments.</p>"},"photo":{"width":4608,"file":"Historical marker of St. Sebastian Church in Lumban, Laguna.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":3456,"hash":"41"}}},"address":"Lumban Church, Lumban, Laguna","lat":14.29734,"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Lumban, Laguna"},"Q24705458":{"date":"2006-11-13","macroAddress":"Imus, Cavite","lat":14.42956,"name":"Katedral ng Imus","region":"Calabarzon","address":"Imus Cathedral, Imus, Cavite","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang simbahang parokyal ng mga paring Rekoletos sa patronato ni Nuestra Señora Del Pilar at San Juan Bautista at sa pamamahala ni Francisco de Santiago, Orsa, bilang unang kura paroko, 1795. Mula sa Toclong inilipat sa Balangon, ang kasalukuyang kinatatayuan nito, 1823. Ipinatayo ang simbahang gawa sa bato at ladrilyo sa ilalim ni Nicolas Becerra, Orsa, na nagsibli mula 1821 - 1840. Pinangasiwaan ng mga paring sekular, 1897. Naging katedral at luklukan ng Diyosesis ng Imus, 1961.</p>","title":"Katedral ng Imus","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Katedral ng Imus historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":2500,"height":3366,"hash":"e7"}}},"lon":120.93608,"locPhoto":{"hash":"33","height":1239,"width":1783,"file":"Imus Cathedral historical marker location.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"wikipedia":{"Imus Cathedral":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the western front entrance of the cathedral."},"Q55097315":{"wikipedia":{"Immaculate Conception Parish Church":"Immaculate Conception Parish Church (Santa Cruz)"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.41477,"name":"Church of Santa Cruz","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Santa Cruz Church of Laguna historical marker.jpg","height":4608,"hash":"02"},"text":{"title":"Church of Santa Cruz","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This church, dedicated to Our Lady of the Immaculate Concepcion, was originally constructed of stone in 1608 under the direction of Franciscan Fr. Antonio de la Llave, the first parish priest. Enlarged in 1672 by Fr. Miguel Perciva with the addition of two wings, giving the church the form of a cross. In 1850 Fr. Juan Antonio Marzo built the principal nave and the convent, and remodelled the five altars. Destroyed by fire on 26 January 1945 during the liberation. Reconstructed in 1948 under the auspices of the 10th Postwar Executive Planning Council of Santa Cruz through the initiative of Rev. Fr. Mariano O. Limjuco.</p>"}}},"address":"Immaculate Conception Parish Church, Lopez Jaena Street, Santa Cruz, Laguna","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Laguna","date":"1955-12-07","lat":14.28269},"Q28878285":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.42488,"details":{"photo":{"file":"Casa Real Marker.jpg","credit":"Iamjepoi {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1600,"height":2464,"hash":"9d"},"text":{"tl":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Casa Real","inscription":"<p>Ito ang pook na kinatatayuan ng Casa Real, ang opisyal na tahanan at gusaling pampangasiwaan ng gobernador pulitiko-militar ng purok. Dito nanahanan si Jose Rizal bilang tapon mula noong 17 Hulyo 1892 hangang Marso 1893 nang ilipat siya sa Talisay, na ngayo’y Dapitan Rizal Shrine.</p>"},"en":{"title":"Casa Real","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>This is the site of the Casa Real, official residence and administration building of the politico-military governor of the district. Here, Jose Rizal lived as an exile from July 17, 1892 to March, 1893 when he was transferred to Talisay, now the Rizal Dapitan Shrine.</p>"}}},"address":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","name":"Casa Real","lat":8.65524,"date":"1989","macroAddress":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte"},"Q55279735":{"name":"Lt. Gilmore Rescue Party","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"en":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Lt.GilmoreRescueParty HistoricalMarker Baler.jpg","width":729,"hash":"0f","height":707},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Lieutenant-Commander James C. Gilmore, U.S.N., commanding the U.S.S. Gunboat Yorktown was captured, together with all his command, save two, who were instantly killed and two mortally wounded, by insurgent forces, when he came to Baler in April 1899 to relieve the half-famished Spanish garrison that had been besieged in the town church for nearly a year. Lt. Gilmore and the survivors were taken to Nueva Ecija, and then to Northern Luzon. They were later rescued by American forces and taken to Manila.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Lt. Gilmore Rescue Party"}}},"address":"Rizal Street cor. San Luis Street, Poblacion, Baler, Aurora","macroAddress":"Baler, Aurora","date":"1939","lat":15.75878,"wikipedia":{"Siege of Baler":true},"locDesc":null,"lon":121.56271,"locPhoto":null},"Q28923203":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of the statue of Paulino Santos facing Pioneer Avenue.","wikipedia":{"Paulino Santos":true},"locPhoto":{"credit":"Thecl2499 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Monument of Gen. Paulino Santos.jpg","width":4314,"hash":"17","height":2880},"lon":125.17171,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Hen. Paulino Santos","subtitle":"(1890–1945)","inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Camiling, Tarlac, noong Hunyo 22, 1890 kina Remigio Santos at Rosa Torres. Nagtapos bilang balidiktoryan sa Akademya Militar ng Pilipinas noong 1914. Itinalaga bilang pangatlong tenyente ng Konstabularya ng Pilipinas. </p><p> Bilang komandanteng panlalawigan at gobernador, napaunlad niya ang edukasyon, agrikultura at komunikasyon sa Lanao. </p><p> Naging Direktor ng mga Bilangguan; Nagtatag ng Davao Penal Colony at nagsagawa ng madaliang paglilipat ng New Bilibid Prison sa Muntinlupa. </p><p> Naging unang puno ng Estado Mayor ng Hukbong Pilipino. Patnugot ng National Land Settlement Adminsitration. Sa kanyang masigasig at mabisang panunungkulan, anim na pamayanan ang itinatag sa South Cotabato. </p><p> Namatay sa Kiangan, Mt. Province noong Agosto 29, 1945. Bilang parangal sa kanya, ang bayan ng Buayan (dati’y Dadiangas) at pinangalanang Heneral Santos na pagkaraan ay ginawang lungsod.</p>"}}},"address":"Plaza Heneral Santos, Pres. Sergio Osmeña Avenue, General Santos","name":"Hen. Paulino Santos","region":"Soccsksargen","date":"1981","macroAddress":"General Santos","lat":6.11178},"Q53708180":{"lat":10.72455,"macroAddress":"Iloilo City","date":"1980","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1865–1953)","title":"Patrocinio Gamboa","inscription":"<p>Ipinanganak sa Jaro, Iloilo noong ika-30 ng Abril 1865 kina Fermin Gamboa at Leonarda Villareal.</p><p>May kaisipang makabayan na pinasigla ng <u>Noli</u> at <u>Fili</u> ni Rizal. Siya ay umanib sa pangkat panghimagsikan sa Iloilo. Ipinakipagsapalaran niya ang kanyang buhay sa paghahatid ng watawat ng Pilipinas na kanyang ginawa buhat sa Jaro patungong Sta. Barbara kung saan itinataas ito nang pasinayaan ang pansamantalang Pamahalaang Panghimagsikan noong ika-17 ng Nobyembre 1898.</p><p>Tumulong siya sa pag-aalaga sa mga sugatan at maysakit noong panahon ng digmaan laban sa mga Amerikano.</p><p>Siya ay namatay noong ika-24 ng Nobyembre 1953 sa Molo, Iloilo.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"9c","height":2944,"file":"Patrocinio Gamboa historical marker.JPG","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1976}}},"address":"Graciano Lopez Jaena Park, E. Lopez Street cor. El 98 Street, Jaro, Iloilo City","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Patrocinio Gamboa","locPhoto":null,"lon":122.55718,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Patrocinio Gamboa":true}},"Q54666744":{"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"39","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"OurLadyoftheAbandonedParishjf9827 07.JPG","width":3456},"lon":121.09628,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade to the left of the main entrance.","wikipedia":{"Our Lady of the Abandoned Church":"Our Lady of the Abandoned Parish Church (Marikina)"},"lat":14.63036,"date":"1990-05-13","macroAddress":"Marikina, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Unang ipinatayong yari sa pawid at kawayan ng mga paring Agustino sa Chorillo (ngayo’y Barangka), 1572. Inilipat sa Jesus de la Peña nang ang visita ay nalipat sa ilalim ng pangangasiwa ng mga paring Heswita, 1630; pinasinayaaan at ginanap ang unang misa, Abril 16, 1630. Muling inilipat at ipinagawa ang simbahang bato sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan nito, 1687; ganap na natapos at naging isang parokya, 1690. Nasunog ang malaking bahagi ng noong Digmaang Pilipino laban sa Kastila at Pilipino laban sa Amerikano. Nasira ang kampanaryo noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Pinasimulang ayusin at pagandahin simula pa noong 1951 ng kura paroko sa tulong ng mga samahang panrelihiyon, sibiko at mamamayan.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Nuestra Señora de los Desemparados","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"03","height":4608,"file":"Our Lady of the Abandoned Church in Marikina, Metro Manila.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456}}},"address":"Our Lady of the Abandoned Church, J.P. Rizal Street cor. V. Gomez Street, Sta. Elena, Marikina, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Simbahan ng Nuestra Señora de los Desemparados"},"Q52539178":{"region":"Western Visayas","name":"Miagao Church","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":1800,"hash":"85","width":1170,"file":"Miagao Church NHCP historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Nickrds09; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Construction of this church began in 1787 while Fray Francisco M. Gonzales, O.S.A. was Parish Priest of this town and Domingo Libo-on was Gobernadorcillo. The Church was completed in 1797. It served as fortress against Muslim raiders. In 1898, during the Revolution, the Church was destroyed. Subsequently rebuilt, it was damaged by file in 1910. It was badly damaged by earthquake in 1948. Restoration work began in 1960 and completed in 1962, during the term of office of Most Rev. Dr. Jose Ma. Cuenco, D.D. Metropolitan Archbishop of Jaro, of Msgr. Fernando S. Javillo, O.P., Parish Priest of this town and Dioscoro Mueda, Municipal Mayor.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Miagao Church"}}},"address":"Miagao Church, Zulueta Avenue cor. Noble Street, Miagao, Iloilo","lat":10.64202,"macroAddress":"Miagao, Iloilo","date":"1963-02-16","wikipedia":{"Miagao Church":true},"locDesc":"This historical marker is located at the base of the south bell tower at the left side of the church facade.","lon":122.23584,"locPhoto":{"hash":"78","height":1350,"file":"Miagao Church south bell tower.jpg","credit":"Rabosajr {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1000}},"Q46518566":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the southwestern corner of the ruined church tower.","wikipedia":{"Cagsawa Ruins":true},"lon":123.70104,"locPhoto":{"height":2848,"hash":"3d","file":"Cagsawa Church Ruins.jpg","credit":"Wijo08 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4288},"details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Cagsaua","inscription":"<p>The spiritual administration of Cagsaua from 1587 to 1595 was under the parish of Camalig. An early church was burned, 25 July 1636, by the Dutch who ransacked the towns bordering Legaspi Bay. This Church built after 1724 by Fray Francisco Blanco, O. F. M., was buried by rocks and lava during the eruption of Mayon Volcano, 1 February 1814. The authorities of Cagsaua meeting at Ligao, 6 July 1814, decided to incorporate their town as part of Daraga. The first centenary of the destruction of the church was commemorated, 1 February 1914, with a huge pilgrimage to the ruins where high mass was celebrated.</p>"},"photo":{"width":4000,"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical Marker at the Church of Cagsaua.JPG","hash":"e5","height":6016}}},"address":"Cagsawa Ruins, Pan-Philippine Highway, Daraga, Albay","name":"Church of Cagsaua","region":"Bicol Region","date":"1954","macroAddress":"Daraga, Albay","lat":13.16601},"Q55374226":{"lon":120.58761,"locPhoto":{"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"FvfTarlacMacabulos9370 02.JPG","height":4608,"hash":"47"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the Francisco Makabulos monument.","wikipedia":{"Francisco Macabulos":true},"lat":15.48159,"macroAddress":"Tarlac City, Tarlac","date":"2008","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Heneral ng Rebolusyon at manunulat. Isinilang sa La Paz, Tarlac, 17 Setyembre, 1871. Nagtatag at nagpalaganap ng Katipunan sa lalawigan ng Tarlac, 1895. Namuno sa Sigaw sa Tarlac, 4 Enero 1897; at pansamantalang pamahalaan sa Gitnang Luzon, 17 Abril 1898. Itinalagang gobernador politico–militar ng lalawigan ng Tarlac matapos palayain ang bayan ng Tarlac, 10 Hulyo 1898. Nanguna sa pagpapalaya sa mga karatig bayan, hinirang na Kumandante Militar ng Tarlac at Pangasinan, 8 Oktubre 1898. Lumaban sa mga Amerikano, 1899; Pangulo ng La Paz, Tarlac, 1908; Pangalawang Pangulo ng Tarlac, Tarlac, 1918. Yumao, 20 Abril 1922.</p>","subtitle":"(1871–1922)","title":"Francisco Makabulos"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Francisco Makabulos historical marker in Tarlac City.jpg","hash":"ba","height":4608}}},"address":"Maria Cristina Park, Romulo Boulevard, Tarlac City, Tarlac","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Francisco Makabulos"},"Q56048366":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito unang iwinagayway ang bandilang Pilipino sa Kabisayaan at Mindanaw nang pasinayaan ang Pamahalaang Mapanghimagsik ng Kabisayaan noong Nobyembre 17, 1898, sa pamamahala ni Heneral Martin Teofilo Delgado. Nahirang na mga pinuno ng nasabing pamahalaan sina Roque Lopez, Pangulo; Vicente Franco, Pangalawang Pangulo at Kalihim Panloob; Venancio Concepcion, Kalihim ng Pananalapi; Ramon Avanceña, Kalihim ng Estado; Jovito Yusay, Kalihim ng Katarungan; Julio Hernandez, Kalihim Pandigma; Fernando Salas, Kalihim–Panlahat; Martin Delgado, Kataas-taasang Heneral; at Perfecto Poblador at Pascual Magbanua, mga heneral ng dibisyon.</p>","subtitle":"(1898)","title":"Pamahalaang Mapanghimagsik ng Kabisayaan"}}},"address":"General Martin Teofilo Delgado Street cor. Merlo Street, Santa Barbara, Iloilo","name":"Pamahalaang Mapanghimagsik ng Kabisayaan","region":"Western Visayas","macroAddress":"Santa Barbara, Iloilo","date":"1973","lat":10.82623,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Federal State of the Visayas":true},"lon":122.53358,"locPhoto":null},"Q41962281":{"locPhoto":{"height":2048,"hash":"df","width":1365,"file":"20161015 Titopao Gomburza Martyrdom Site.jpg","credit":"Titopao {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"lon":120.97732,"locDesc":"The historical markers are located on opposite sides of the monument marking the execution site with the English marker on the western side and the Spanish marker on the eastern side.","wikipedia":{"José Burgos":true,"Mariano Gómez":true,"Jacinto Zamora":true,"Gomburza":true},"lat":14.58243,"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":true,"details":{"es":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Supuestos complicados en motin militar de Cavite, 20 Enero 1872, Padre Jose A. Burgos, Padre Mariano Gomez, Padre Jacinto Zamora Martires de la libertad de Filipinas, ejecutados en garrote vil en este lugar, 17 Febrero 1872.</p>","title":null,"subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":4087,"hash":"38","file":"Gomburza execution site historical marker (Spanish).jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3000},"date":"1953"},"en":{"photo":{"height":736,"hash":"f9","credit":"Titopao {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Gomburza execution site historical marker (English).jpg","width":1068},"date":"1998","text":{"inscription":"<p>On this spot, on February 17, 1872, Fathers Jose G. Burgos, Mariano C. Gomes and Jacinto R. Zamora, were executed by strangulation for alleged complicity with the military uprising in Cavite on January 20, 1872.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":null}}},"address":"Rizal Park, Roxas Boulevard cor. Padre Burgos Avenue, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Gomburza execution site"},"Q56069465":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":123.30731,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dating visita ng Tanjay, Negros; naging parokya ng Diyosesis ng Cebu sa patronato ni San Miguel Arkanghel, 1780. Ipinatayo sa pamumuno ni Padre Romualdo Avila ang simbahan at kumbento yari sa sagay (korales) at kahoy, 1842. Ang bantayang nagsilbi sa pagmamasid ng Kipot Tañon sa pagitan ng Cebu at Negros ay ipinagawa yari sa sagay sa panahon ni Padre Toribio Gerzon, paring sekular ng Diyosesis ng Cebu, 1878. Sa ibabaw ng gulod na may 157 na baitang mula tore pababa ng dalampasigan ay ang tinatawag na Escala de Jacob.</p>","title":"Simbahan ng Samboan","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Samboan Church, Samboan, Cebu","region":"Central Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Samboan","lat":9.52947,"date":"2016","macroAddress":"Samboan, Cebu"},"Q24033382":{"lat":17.575,"macroAddress":"Vigan, Ilocos Sur","date":"1949","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Cathedral of Vigan","address":"Vigan Cathedral, Plaza Salcedo, Vigan, Ilocos Sur","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Built in 1641, this church became a cathedral when the seat of the Diocese of Nueva Segovia was transferred from Lal-lo, Cagayan, to Vigan, 1758. Occupied by the revolutionists under Col. Juan Villamor, 1896, and by the American forces under Lt. Col. James Parker, 1899. A chapel of wood and thatch erected on this site, 1574, by order of Juan de Salcedo, the conquistador and founder of Villa Fernandina, after which Vigan was first called, was damaged by earthquake in 1619 and 1627, and by fire in 1739.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Cathedral of Vigan"},"photo":{"file":"Historical Marker Cathedral of Vigan.jpg","credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1976,"height":2971,"hash":"60"}}},"locPhoto":{"width":2592,"credit":"Captaincid {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"St. Paul's Cathedral, Vigan Ilocos Sur.JPG","hash":"31","height":1944},"lon":120.38855,"wikipedia":{"Vigan Cathedral":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade between the entrance to the nave and the right aisle."},"Q53449322":{"wikipedia":{"José Fabella":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the main entrance of the main building.","locPhoto":{"height":1029,"hash":"16","width":863,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Department of Health Central Office - main entrance of main building.jpg"},"lon":120.98207,"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Jose F. Fabella","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"35","height":514,"width":373,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Jose F. Fabella 1888 - 1945.jpg"},"text":{"title":"Jose F. Fabella","subtitle":"1888–1945","inscription":"<p>Ama ng kalusugang pambayan. Ipinanganak kina Juan Fabella at Damiana Fernandez, Pagsanjan, Laguna, 16 Oktubre 1888. Nagtapos ng medisina, Rush Medical College, 1912. Kalihim, Anti-Tuberculosis Society, 1914–1916, at Public Welfare Board, 1916–1921. Nanungkulan sa pamahalaan at mga pribadong samahan na kaugnay ng kalusugan at kagalingang bayan. Nanguna sa pagtatatag ng Santol Tuberculosis Society (ngayo’y Quezon Institute), Welfareville, Maternity and Children’s Hospital, Paco Settlement House at mga klinika sa panganganak, mga sanggunian sa wastong pag-aalaga ng mga bata at mga hukumang pangkabataan sa bansa. Yumao, 16 Enero 1945.</p>"}}},"address":"Department of Health Central Office, Rizal Avenue cor. Tayuman Street, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.61551,"date":"2002","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila"},"Q37785797":{"wikipedia":{"San Agustin Church":"San Agustin Church (Lubao)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the main entrance of the church.","locPhoto":{"credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"JC Lubao 3.jpg","width":3744,"hash":"93","height":1938},"lon":120.60177,"name":"Church of Lubao","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Founded 1572 in Barrio Santa Catalina. Moved to this site thirty years later due to yearly floods. Architect Fr. Antonio Herrera, Augustinian, constructed this church 1614–1630 out of locally-made brick and sand mixed in egg albumen contributed by the people of Lubao. Occupied 1898 by the revolutionists. Used as hospital 1899 by American forces. Destroyed 1942 by Japanese shelling. Repaired 1949-1952, under the direction of Fr. Melencio Garcia and other priests.</p>","title":"Church of Lubao","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":2880,"hash":"74","width":1920,"credit":"JJ Carpio {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"JC Lubao 19.jpg"}}},"address":"San Agustin Church, Lubao, Pampanga","date":"1957","macroAddress":"Lubao, Pampanga","lat":14.93833},"Q24813571":{"macroAddress":"San Jose, Batangas","date":"1939","lat":13.8795,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"14","height":3456,"file":"San Jose, Batangas Church historical marker.jpg","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The foundation of this town, known formerly as Malaquing Tubig, dates from 1765. The church was built by the famous botanist, The Rev. Manuel Blanco, O.S.A., in 1812. The stone bridge over Malaquing Tubig was constructed by the Rev. Bruno Laredo, O.S.A.</p>","title":"Church of San Jose","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Saint Joseph the Patriarch Church, San Jose, Batangas","name":"Church of San Jose","region":"Calabarzon","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.1042,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Saint Joseph the Patriarch Church":"Saint Joseph the Patriarch Church (Batangas)"}},"Q48649068":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lon":120.58669,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang Easter School ni Charles Henry Brent, obispo ng Simbahang Episkopal upang mabigyan ng pormal ma edukasyon ang mga batang lalaki mula sa Mountain Province, 1906. Tumanggap ng mga babaeng mag-aaral, 1909. Sa pagsisikap ni Dyakonesa Anne Hargreaves itinatag ang pagsasanay sa paghahabi ng tela para sa mga babaeng mag-aaral. Nagsilbing himpilan ng mga Hapon noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Idinagdag ang sekondaryang edukasyon, 1963. Naging Easter College, 1995.</p>","title":"Easter College","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Easter College, Baguio","region":"Cordillera Administrative Region","name":"Easter College","lat":16.4245,"date":"2017-12-12","macroAddress":"Baguio"},"Q54858369":{"macroAddress":"Luna, La Union","date":"1958","lat":16.82102,"name":"Camp Spencer","region":"Ilocos Region","details":{"en":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Named in honor of Private Grafton Spencer, AUS, killed in action early 1943. This camp in Darigayos, site of the GHQ, was center and base of operations of the USAFIP, NL, during the liberation campaign of Luzon, from January to September 1945 when 52,033 enemy troops were killed and 32,001 captured. This camp was deactivated on orders of the Philippine Army, December 1946.</p><p>Darigayos cove was the landing scene of American submarine landings for vital war materiel and supplies from the south-west Pacific Area, command of Gen. Douglas MacArthur, late 1944.</p>","title":"Camp Spencer","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Bacnotan–Luna–Balaoan Road, Brgy. Darigayos, Luna, La Union","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.33592,"wikipedia":{"United States Army Forces in the Philippines - Northern Luzon":true},"locDesc":null},"Q41214132":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Luzon":true,"511th Parachute Infantry Regiment":"511th Parachute Infantry Regiment (United States)"},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.96197,"details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":791,"hash":"1f","width":498,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"TagaytayRidge HistoricalMarker TagaytayCity.jpg"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Site of the first parachute landing in the Philippines executed by the 511th Parachute Infantry Regiment, 11th Airborne Division, 8th Army, USA, under Lt. Gen. Robert Eichelberger, with Maj. John P. M. Swing, CG., 3 February 1945.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Tagaytay Ridge Landing"}}},"address":"Tagaytay Rotonda, Emilio Aguinaldo Highway, Tagaytay, Cavite","name":"Tagaytay Ridge Landing","region":"Calabarzon","macroAddress":"Tagaytay, Cavite","date":"1951","lat":14.11533},"Q42919921":{"wikipedia":{"Battle of Mindoro":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":121.043,"name":"Pagdaong sa Mindoro","region":"Mimaropa","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Pagdaong sa Mindoro","inscription":"<p>Sa dalampasigan ng San Jose dumaong ang dating Visayan Attack Force na nahati bilang Mindoro Attack Group sa ilalim ni Admiral Arthur D. Struble, Close Covering Group ni Rear Admiral Russell S. Berkey; at Motor Torpedo Boat Group ni Lt. Com. N. Burt Davis, 15 Disyembre 1944. Kasama dito ang 11,878 combat troops; 9,578 Army Air Force; at 5,901 service troops sa pamumuno ni General William C. Dunckel na nagsagawa ng mga paliparan ng pwersang panghimpapawid para sa gagawing pagdaong sa Lingayen, Pangasinan at pagpapalaya sa Luzon. Kaugnay nito ang pagkilala sa mga grupo ng Filipino gerilya nina Major Ramon Ruffy, Major Sofronio Untalan at Captain Lawrence Cooper upang maging kaagapay sa pakikipaglaban sa mga pwersang Hapones sa Mindoro.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Bubog Road, Brgy. San Roque, San Jose, Occidental Mindoro","date":"2010","macroAddress":"San Jose, Occidental Mindoro","lat":12.35939},"Q28877420":{"lat":6.90148,"macroAddress":"Zamboanga City","date":"1949","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula","name":"Fort Pilar","address":"Fort Pilar, N.S. Valderrosa Street, Zamboanga City","details":{"en":{"photo":{"width":2696,"credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Fort Pilar Historical Marker.jpg","hash":"dd","height":2816},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Founded as southern outpost of Spanish domain under the supervision of Melchor de Vera, 1635; Attacked by the Dutch, 1646; Deserted when troops were concentrated in Manila to drive away Chinese pirates, 1663; Reconstructed by the Society of Jesus, 1666; Rebuilt the management of Juan Sicarra, 1719; Stormed by Dalasi, King Bulig, with 3,000 moros, 1720; Cannonaded by the British, 1798; Witnessed the mutiny of seventy prisoners, 1872; Abandoned by the Spaniards, 1898; Occupied by the Americans under General J.C. Bates 1899; Seized by the Japanese, 1942; Taken over by the Republic of the Philippines, July 1946.</p>","title":"Fort Pilar","subtitle":null}}},"locPhoto":{"width":4032,"file":"Fort Pilar Entrance.jpg","credit":"Ervin Malicdem {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"5e","height":3024},"lon":122.08212,"wikipedia":{"Fort Pilar":true},"locDesc":"This historical marker is located on the wall (previously a pedestal) just to the right of the main entrance of the fort."},"Q55111177":{"region":"Cordillera Administrative Region","name":"United Church of Christ in the Philippines","address":"Otek Street cor. Fernando G. Bautista Drive, Baguio","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"United Church of Christ in the Philippines","subtitle":"(UCCP Baguio)","inscription":"<p>Itinatag sa pangunguna nina Maximino Nebres at Pastor Juan Abuan Leones sa tulong ng misyonerong Amerikano na si Rev. Howard Widdoes, ang United Brethren Church sa Baguio, isa sa mga unang simbahang Protestante sa Hilagang Luzon, 11 Pebrero 1911. Naging Baguio United Evangelical Church, 1930. Nagsilbing pansamantalang kanlungan ng mga mamamayan ang simbahan nito sa panahon ng digmaan, Marso 1945. Kasamang bumuo sa United Church of Christ in the Philippines, 1948. Pinangalanang UCCP Baguio, 1950.</p>"}}},"lat":16.41286,"date":"2012-02-11","macroAddress":"Baguio","wikipedia":{"United Church of Christ in the Philippines":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.59279},"Q43267173":{"lat":13.56019,"macroAddress":"Mogpog, Marinduque","date":"2011-08-09","region":"Mimaropa","name":"Station Balanacan","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Dito itinatag (Latitud: 13° 33′ 41″.000 N; Longhitud: 121° 52′ 03″.000 E; Clarke Spheroid 1866) ni O.W. Ferguson, United States Coast and Geodetic Survey (USCGS) na pangunahing geodetic station para sa triangulation network ng Pilipinas, 1906. Itinalagang origin ng Luzon Datum na itinatag ni E.R. Frisby sa pamamagitan ng batong muhon sa mismong punto ng orihen, 1911. Naging batayan ng mga sumunod na kwenta ng eksaktong latitud at longhitud ng mga posisyon sa lahat ng panig ng Pilipinas. Inangkop ang dato nito ng United States Coast Guard and Geodetic Survey (USCGS), 1911; ng Bureau of Coast and Geodetic Survey (BCGS) ng Pilipinas, 1950; at ng National Mapping and Resource Information Authority (NAMRIA), 1987. Patuloy na nagsisilbing datum origin sa kabila ng pagtaas sa antas ng Philippine Reference System of 1992 (PRS92).</p>","title":"Station Balanacan","subtitle":"Datum Origin of the Luzon Datum of 1911"},"photo":null}},"address":"Station Balanacan, Mt. Mataas, Brgy. Hinanggayon, Mogpog, Marinduque","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.86897,"wikipedia":{"Luzon Datum of 1911":true},"locDesc":null},"Q54811304":{"lat":16.96042,"macroAddress":"Cervantes, Ilocos Sur","date":"1954","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Began with the assault on the Japanese line at Bitalag, Tagudin, Ilocos Sur, by the United States Army Forces in the Philippines, North Luzon (USAFIP, NL), 8 January 1945, followed by the seizure of enemy strongholds along Highway 4 and the defeat of the Japanese Defenders of the Pass, 14 June 1945. The battle spearheaded by the 121st Infantry, USAFIP, NL, was conceded by American military authorities as “one of the most terrible and incredibly difficult battle of the entire war.” Hastened the surrender of the Japanese Imperal Forces under General Tomoyuki Yamashita. </p><p><small><i>This monument is erected in honor of the 3,400 men killed and wounded who fought gallantly for freedom and peace.</i></small></p>","title":"The Battle of Bessang Pass","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Bessang Pass Natural Monument, Km. 364 Tagudin–Cervantes–Sabangan Road, Brgy. Malaya, Cervantes, Ilocos Sur","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"The Battle of Bessang Pass","locPhoto":{"width":4128,"file":"Bessang Pass Monument.jpg","credit":"Warrendering {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"eb","height":2322},"lon":120.65785,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the monument.","wikipedia":{"Battle of Bessang Pass":true}},"Q44640888":{"wikipedia":{"Turtle Islands":"Turtle Islands, Tawi-Tawi"},"locDesc":null,"lon":118.31266,"locPhoto":null,"region":"Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao","name":"Turtle Islands","address":"Turtle Islands Municipal Hall, Taganak Island, Turtle Islands, Tawi-Tawi","details":{"photo":null,"text":{"en":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Turtle Islands","inscription":"<p>These islets were leased by the Sultan of Sulu on 22 January 1878 to the British North Borneo Company. Became part of the Philippines by virtue of the Treaty of Paris, 10 December 1898, between Spain and the United States. Lessee continued administering them under the 1932 United States–Great Britain treaty to be relinquished to owner upon a year’s notice. Transferred to the Republic of the Philippines, 16 October 1947.</p>"},"tl":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Turtle Islands","inscription":"<p>Ang mga pulong ito ay pinaupahan ng Sultan ng Sulu sa British North Borneo Company noong 22 Enero 1878. Naging bahagi ng Pilipinas noong 10 Disyembre 1898 ayon sa Kasunduan ng Paris na nilagdaan ng Espanya at Estados Unidos. Patuloy na pinamahalaan ng British North Borneo Company ayon sa kasunduang nilagdaan noong 1932 ng Estados Unidos at Gran Bretanya. Pinagkayarian ding ibabalik sa may-ari pagkatapos mapagpatalastasan ang nangungupahan sa loob ng isang taon. Inilipat sa Republika ng Pilipinas noong 16 Oktubre 1947.</p>"}}},"lat":6.07322,"date":"1969","macroAddress":"Turtle Islands, Tawi-Tawi"},"Q54943881":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lon":120.59394,"locPhoto":null,"region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Bahay Pamahalaan ng San Nicolas","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo bilang Casa Tribunal at nang matapos ginamit na paaralan bilang tugon sa Batas Pang-Edukasyon ng pamahalaang kolonyal, 1863. Ginamit bilang Casa Tribunal, mga taong 1890’s. Naging sentro sa pagtataguyod sa San Nicolas bilang nagsasariling bayan sa pamumuno ni Marcelo Barba, unang presidente municipal, 1909. Pinalaki ang gusali, 1919–1921. Idinagdag dito ang tanggapan ng Justice of the Peace, Police Force, Post Office, Session Hall, Treasury at Municipal Jail. Naging garison ng mga Hapon, 1942–1945. Muling ginamit na tanggapan ng lokal na pamahalaan pagkatapos ng Digmaan. Pinalawak ang gusali, tinanggal ang Municipal Jail at inilipat ang Post Office, 1972–1986. Muling ipinaayos ang gusali ayon sa orihinal na disenyo, 2004–2009. Halimbawa ng “Bahay na Tisa” sa Rehiyon ng Ilocos.</p>","title":"Bahay Pamahalaan ng San Nicolas","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"a8","height":5974,"credit":"Jblaza {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Historical Marker Bahay Pamahalaan San Nicolas.jpg","width":3972}}},"address":"Manila North Road cor. Madamba Street, Poblacion, San Nicolas, Ilocos Norte","lat":18.17288,"macroAddress":"San Nicolas, Ilocos Norte","date":"2009-12-30"},"Q24817360":{"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall immediately to the right of the main entrance of the house.","locPhoto":{"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Ylagan–de la Rosa Ancestral House main entrance.jpg","hash":"d9","height":3456},"lon":120.92475,"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ylagan–de la Rosa Ancestral House","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Ylagan-de la Rosa Ancestral House historical marker.jpg","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","width":2644,"hash":"d3","height":2456},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ylagan–de la Rosa Ancestral House","inscription":"<p>This heritage house of the Ylagan–de la Rosa family is registered with the National Historical Institute, pursuant to NHI Board Resolution No. 9 S. 1998.</p>"}}},"address":"Ylagan–de la Rosa Ancestral House, 3 Calle Jose P. Rizal, Taal, Batangas","lat":13.87814,"date":"1999-05-30","macroAddress":"Taal, Batangas"},"Q41337041":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Church of Santa Ana","address":"Santa Ana Church, Pedro Gil Street cor. New Panaderos Street, Santa Ana, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>First Franciscan Mission established outside Manila, in 1578. Present Church built under the supervision of Vicente Ingles, O.F.M. Cornerstone laid on September 12, 1720, by Francisco De la Cuesta, Archbishop of Manila and acting Governor of the Philippines.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Santa Ana"},"photo":{"height":1100,"hash":"59","file":"Church of Santa Ana (Manila) historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":1231}}},"lat":14.5821,"date":"1936","macroAddress":"Santa Ana, Manila","wikipedia":{"Santa Ana Church":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the western wall at the base of the church’s bell tower.","lon":121.01362,"locPhoto":{"file":"0819jfSanta Ana Church Main Right Facade Statue Exterior Patio Manilafvf 14.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4608,"hash":"cd","height":3456}},"Q43305624":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal where the statue of Licerio Gerónimo stands.","wikipedia":{"Licerio Gerónimo":true},"locPhoto":{"hash":"cb","height":4608,"file":"SanMaeojf5812 07.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456},"lon":121.14521,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Licerio I. Geronimo","subtitle":"(1855–1924)","inscription":"<p>Bayani ng Labanan ng San Mateo. Ipinanganak Agosto 27, 1855, Sampaloc, Maynila. Puno, Kapulungang Katipunan ng Wawa, Montalban, tagapagtatag, Katipunan sa San Mateo at Marikina. Napaurong ang mga Kastila na sumalakay sa puwersa ni Heneral Aguinaldo sa Bundok Puray. Nahirang na medyor heneral ng dibisyon nakatalaga sa San Mateo, 1898; komandante heneral ng Ikatlong Sona Militar ng lalawigan ng Maynila, 1899. Buong tapang na nakipaglaban kasama ang kanyang mga Tiradores de la Muerte sa Labanan ng San Mateo kung saan napatay niya si Heneral Henry Lawton at iba pang opsiyal na Amerikano. Sinundan ito ng mga pagsalakay sa iba’t-ibang himpilan ng mga Amerikano sa Bulakan, Rizal at mga karatig bayan ng Maynila. Sumuko sa mga Amerikano, 1901. Nagtrabaho sa Konstabularyo ng Pilipinas bilang 4th class inspector, Hunyo 1, 1902. Naging 3rd lieutenant at inspector, Disyembre 23, 1902. Namatay, Enero 16, 1924.</p>"},"photo":{"width":3456,"file":"SanMaeojf5812 04.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","height":4608,"hash":"70"}}},"address":"J. P. Rizal Street cor. A. Bonifacio Street, Rodriguez, Rizal","name":"Licerio I. Geronimo","region":"Calabarzon","date":"1992","macroAddress":"Rodriguez, Rizal","lat":14.73248},"Q40313447":{"locPhoto":{"hash":"8d","height":3456,"width":4608,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"02342jfManila Intramuros Streets Buildings Churches Landmarksfvf 15.jpg"},"lon":120.97522,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall of the northeastern side of the church facade.","wikipedia":{"San Agustin Church":"San Agustin Church (Manila)"},"lat":14.58922,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"1998","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Oldest stone church in the Philippines. Plans were approved in 1586. Construction started in 1587 and completed in 1607 under the supervision successively of Augustinian Fathers Francisco de Bustos, Ildefonso Perez, Diego de Avila and Brother Alonso de Perea. Its architect was Juan Macias. It has withstood many earthquakes from 1645 up to the present and survived the British invasion in 1762, the Spanish–American War in 1898 and the Japanese invasion in 1942. The church choir has 68 carved molave seats with narra inlaids, an artistic lectern and parchment cantorals of the 17th and 18th centuries. The church and its graves were profaned during the British occupation of Manila in 1762. The ashes of early Spanish conquistadores Legazpi, Salcedo, Lavezares, and blessed Pedro de Zuniga and others now rest in the easternmost chapel of the transept. Terms for the American occupation of Manila were prepared in the vestry of the church in 1898. The First Philippine Plenary Council was held here in 1953. Chosen as a World Heritage Site by UNESCO in 1993.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of San Agustin"},"photo":{"width":2000,"file":"Church of San Agustin historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Judgefloro; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","height":2960,"hash":"13"}}},"address":"San Agustin Church, Gen. Luna Street cor. Real Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Church of San Agustin"},"Q52862417":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.9921,"wikipedia":{"San Beda University":true},"locDesc":null,"macroAddress":"San Miguel, Manila","date":"2001-07-22","lat":14.59956,"name":"Kolehiyo ng San Beda","region":"Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"94","height":685,"width":457,"file":"KolehiyoNgSanBeda HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ng mga Kastilang paring Benediktino sa Kalye Arlegui noong 1901 bilang El Colegio de San Beda. Opisyal na binuksan para sa mga mag-aaral sa mababa at mataas na paaralan at sa komersyo noong Hunyo 17, 1901. Kinilala ng Pontipikal na Unibersidad ng Santo Tomas, Enero 24, 1906. Kinilala ng pamahalaan at binigyan ng karapatang magkaloob ng diploma para sa mababa at mataas na paaralan at ng titulong batsilyer, Mayo 12, 1910. Nakilala bilang Kolehiyo ng San Beda, 1918. Inilipat sa kasalukuyang kinatatayuan noong 1926. Naging tirahan ng kor ng komisaryo ng Hukbo ng Estados Unidos, 1941 at ng Hukbong Imperyal ng Hapon sa buong panahon ng pananankop nito. Nagsilbing pagamutan ng Hukbo ng Estados Unidos, 1945. Binuksan ang kurso para sa batas, 1948, at pag-aaral na gradwado, 1988.</p><p>Inilagay ang panandang pangkasaysayan noong ipagdiwang ang ika-100 taon ng pagkatatatag ng Kolehiyo.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Kolehiyo ng San Beda"}}},"address":"San Beda University, Mendiola Street, San Miguel, Manila, Metro Manila"},"Q24188864":{"name":"Church of Nuestra Señora de Peña de Francia","region":"Bicol Region","address":"Our Lady of Peñafrancia Shrine, Peñafrancia Avenue, Naga, Camarines Sur","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3120,"hash":"8a","width":4160,"file":"Historical Marker of Peñafrancia Shrine.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The early church dedicated to \"Nuestra Señora de Peña de Francia \" was built about 1711 trough the generosity of the Rev. Miguel de Covarrubias as a vow-offering for blessings he received in his youth. The present church was built about 1750 by Bishop Isidoro de Arevalo and repaired and improved in 1876-1877 by Bishop Francisco Gainza. The image was solemnly crowned by the Rt. Rev. Guillermo Piani on September 20, 1924.</p>","title":"Church of Nuestra Señora de Peña de Francia","subtitle":null}}},"date":"1940","macroAddress":"Naga, Camarines Sur","lat":13.6342,"wikipedia":{"Our Lady of Peñafrancia Shrine":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.19545},"Q41658841":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located by the eastern corner of the council building beside the side entrance facing the Manila Cathedral.","wikipedia":{"Knights of Columbus":true},"lon":120.97352,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"FvfIntramuros0485 15.JPG","width":4608,"height":3456,"hash":"dd"},"address":"General Luna Street cor. Beaterio Street, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"78","height":3322,"credit":"Josh Lim (Sky Harbor) {CC BY‑SA 3.0 ph}","file":"Knights of Columbus Manila Council historical marker.JPG","width":2165},"text":{"title":"Knights of Columbus Manila Council No. 1000","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang unang orden ng Knights of Columbus sa Maynila at tinawag na Manila Council No. 1000, 1905. Grand Knight Richard Campbell, unang pinuno. Antonio Opisso at Anastacio Quijano, unang mga Pilipino sa orden, 1907. Itinatag ng kasaping si Dr. Jose Ma. Delgado ang San Pablo Council No. 1900 sa Laguna, 1918. Sinimulan ng Manila Council No. 1000 ang pagbuo ng mga sangay sa lungsod ng Cebu, Albay, Laoag, Baguio, Lingayen, at Tacloban, dekada 1920. Lumaban para sa kalayaan at nasawi ang mga kasaping sina Benito Soliven, Manuel Colayco at Enrique Albert noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Itinuon ang mga gawaing pampamayanan sa pamumuno ni Rev. Fr. George Willmann S.J, 1947–1953 at ipinagtibay ang ganitong layunin nang mabuo ang “Patriotic Degree” ng orden, 1949. Binuo ang Columbian Farmers’ Aid Association, 1951. Ipinalaganap ang Credit Unions – Consumers’ Cooperatives Movement, 1963. Inilunsad ang Barrio Uplift Program, 1967.</p>"}}},"name":"Knights of Columbus Manila Council No. 1000","region":"Metro Manila","date":"2013","macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","lat":14.59102},"Q56219227":{"lon":120.98733,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"lat":14.61333,"date":"1972","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","address":"Maria Clara Church, 1320 Concepcion Street, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"2a","height":3264,"credit":"Urbanroamer {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Maria Clara Parish church marker.JPG","width":2448},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Obispo Maximo Isabelo de los Reyes, Anak","inscription":"<p>Sa simbahang ito inordenan at unang nagmisa. Isinilang sa Madrid, Espanya, noong Pebrero 14, 1900. Naging Kataas-taasang Obispo ng Iglesia Filipina Independiente at masugid na tagapagtaguyod ng Kilusang Ekumenismo sa Pilipinas. Namatay noong Oktubre 10, 1971 sa sa simbahang ito samantalang nagkakasal.</p>"}}},"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Obispo Maximo Isabelo de los Reyes, Anak"},"Q54569998":{"locPhoto":{"hash":"65","height":4608,"width":3456,"file":"4331United Methodist Episcopal Church Memorial 03.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"},"lon":120.99629,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the right most portion of the church facade.","wikipedia":null,"macroAddress":"Parañaque, Metro Manila","date":"1991-03-19","lat":14.51633,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3060,"hash":"c0","credit":"Judgefloro","file":"United Methodist Episcopal Church (Tambo, Parañaque) historical marker (cropped).jpg","width":2098},"text":{"title":"Simbahang Metodistang Episkopal","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Unang Simbahang Metodista sa timog Maynila na itinatag ng mga misyonaryong Metodistang Amerikano sa Mabong, Pasay, 1901. Inilipat sa Pildira, Pasay 1915; sa kasalukuyang pook, 1917. Di-sinasadyang tinamaan ng bomba noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig na kumitil sa buhay ng 77 Pilipinong mananampalataya. Pinanganlang Martyrs Memorial United Methodist, 1948. Muling ipinatayo sa tulong ng Philippine War Damaged Commission at ng Simbahang Trinity ng Estados Unidos, 1950.</p>"}}},"address":"Martyrs' Memorial United Methodist Church, 199 Quirino Avenue, Tambo, Parañaque, Metro Manila","name":"Simbahang Metodistang Episkopal","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q24262125":{"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3700,"hash":"89","credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Miguel Zaragoza y Aranquizna historical marker.jpg","width":2516},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pintor, manunulat, mambabatas at makabayan. Ipinanganak sa San Isidro, Nueva Ecija noong Setyembre 29, 1847. Nag-aral sa Ateneo Municipal de Manila at Academia de Dibujo y Pintura, 1859. Isa sa mga pensyonado ng pamahalaan sa larangan ng sining na pinag-aral sa Academia de San Fernando, Madrid, Espanya, 1879 at sa Roma, 1882. Sumapi sa Kilusang Propaganda sa Roma at bumalik sa Espanya, 1885. Umuwi sa Pilipinas at muling binuhay ang magasing, La Ilustracion Filipina, 1891. Ilan sa kanyang mga pintura: A Roman Laborer; The Death of St. Francis Xavier at St. Peter Chavez; Highway Men; at 'El Violencellista.' Ang dalawa sa labingdalawa niyang lahok ay nagwagi ng ginto at pilak na medalya sa Eksposisyon sa St. Louis, 1904. Naging propesor: Ateneo Municipal, 1891; Escuela Superior de Pintura, Esculturo y Grabado, 1893; Liceo de Manila, 1900; at isa sa unang tatlong propesor ng U.P. School of Fine Arts, 1909. Nahirang na kagawad sa Kongreso ng Malolos, 1898 at isa sa lumagda ng Saligang Batas ng Unang Republika ng Pilipinas. Namatay noong Marso, 1923.</p>","subtitle":"(1847–1923)","title":"Miguel Zaragoza y Aranquizna"}}},"address":"Nazarene Catholic School, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"Miguel Zaragoza y Aranquizna","region":"Metro Manila","macroAddress":"Quiapo, Manila","date":"1989","lat":14.59892,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.9874},"Q47037925":{"date":"2004","macroAddress":"San Fernando, Pampanga","lat":15.02682,"name":"Himpilang Daang-bakal ng San Fernando","region":"Central Luzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"San Fernando Pampanga train station historical marker.jpg","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"7d"},"text":{"title":"Himpilang Daang-bakal ng San Fernando","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Itinayo noong 1892 bilang bahagi ng linyang Manila–Dagupan ng Manila Railroad Company. Dito bumaba si Jose Rizal nang dalawin niya ang San Fernando. Sa himpilang daang-bakal ding ito, noong Abril 1942, isinakay sa tren ang mga bihag na sundalong kasama sa Death March patungo sa Kampo O'Donnell, Capas, Tarlac, upang doon ikulong.</p>"}}},"address":"San Fernando railway station, San Fernando, Pampanga","locPhoto":{"hash":"0c","height":3456,"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"San Fernando Pampanga train station.jpg"},"lon":120.68666,"wikipedia":{"San Fernando railway station":"San Fernando railway station (Pampanga)"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the facade to the left of the street entrance of the station."},"Q24185746":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.48847,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Manaoag Church":true},"date":"1937","macroAddress":"Manaoag, Pangasinan","lat":16.04405,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Administered since 1605 by the Dominicans, the first church of wood lasted a century. The second one, which was of stone, was built through the generosity of Gaspar de Gamboa and Agata Yangta, and inaugrated in 1720. In 1733 it was donated to the Dominican corporation, but was destroyed by the earthquake of 1892. The provisional church, built of wood, was burned during the insurrection of 1898. The reconstruction of the present church began in 1901 with the return of the Dominicans. The image of Nuestra Señora de Manaoag is famous throughout Pangasinan. It was preserved in Dagupan during the revolution, then taken back to the sanctuary by the people of Manaoag where it was solemnly crowned on April 21, 1926, in the presence of thousands of the faithful, by Mons. Guillermo Piano, Apostolic Delegate to the Philippines.</p>","title":"Church of Nuestra Señora de Manaoag","subtitle":null},"photo":{"hash":"f9","height":2500,"file":"Church of Nuestra Señora de Manaoag historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Jblaza; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY 3.0}","width":2114}}},"address":"Manaoag Church, M. Garcia Street, Manaoag, Pangasinan","name":"Church of Nuestra Señora de Manaoag","region":"Ilocos Region"},"Q22340895":{"lat":14.38083,"date":"1988","macroAddress":"Pakil, Laguna","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ang Simbahan ng Pakil","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":3011,"hash":"1a","width":2000,"file":"Ang Simbahan ng Pakil historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ramon FVelasquez; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Simbahan ng Pakil","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayong yari sa kawayan at nipa ni Padre Francisco Barajas sa patronato ni San Pedro de Alcantara nang ang Pakil ay mahiwalay sa Paete, 1676. Ipinagawa ang kumbento at simbahang bato ni Padre Fernando Haro, 1732. Dinugtungan ang tore, 1777; Idinambana ang Birhen ng Turumba, 1788; Nasunog na muli, 1851 at ipinaayos ni Padre Juan de Llarena. Nasira ng lindol ang tore at bubong ng simbahan, 1881 at pinaayos ni Padre Juan de Dios de Villayos. Inilagay ang kisame at pinadorado ang altar ni Padre Paulino Camba, 1883. Sinirang muli ng lindol, 1937 at pinaayos ni Padre Federico Diaz Pines sa tulong ng Kapisanang Unidad Catolica. Ginawang marmol ang altar ni Padre Joseph Reagan at kinonsagrahan ang altar ni Obispo Alejandro Olaila, 1959. Pinaayos ang tore at kisame sa pamamahala ng Parish Council of the Laity, 1980-84.</p>"}}},"address":"Pakil Church, Pakil, Laguna","locPhoto":{"file":"TurumbaChurchjf6544 18.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":4608,"height":3456,"hash":"83"},"lon":121.47891,"wikipedia":{"Pakil Church":"Saint Peter of Alcantara Parish Church"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located at the base of the bell tower which is to the left of the main entrance of the church."},"Q54566617":{"date":"1939","macroAddress":"Parañaque, Metro Manila","lat":14.50054,"address":"Parañaque Cathedral, Quirino Avenue, La Huerta, Parañaque, Metro Manila","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Parañaque","inscription":"<p>The first Catholic Missionary of Parañaque was the Rev. Diego de Espinal, O.S.A., companion of Salcedo in the reconnoissance of Camarines. The veneration for Nuestra Señora del Buen Suceso at Parañaque dates from 1625. The Church and the Convent were built by the Rev. Dionisio Suarez, O.S.A., parish priest from 1638 to 1650. This Church was administered by the eminent historian, the Rev. Joaquin Martinez de Zuñiga, O.S.A., from 1801 to 1806. Parañaque is the birthplace of the Filipino botanist, the Rev. Ignacio Mercado, O.S.A.</p>"},"photo":{"height":2982,"hash":"30","width":2805,"file":"Parañaque Cathedral historical marker (cropped).jpg","credit":"Judgefloro"}}},"name":"Church of Parañaque","region":"Metro Manila","lon":120.99164,"locPhoto":{"hash":"21","height":3456,"file":"432Saint Andrew's School Cathedral Market Parañaque City 33.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":4608},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade, to the right of the main entrance.","wikipedia":{"Parañaque Cathedral":true}},"Q37807353":{"region":"Metro Manila","name":"Asilo of San Vicente de Paul","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":1071,"hash":"4f","width":1142,"file":"Asilo of San Vicente de Paul historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The ground and college were donated to the Sisters of Charity for the education of poor girls by Sor Asuncion Ventura, a native of Pampanga, herself a Sister of Charity. The institution was inaugurated on July 26, 1885 and gained great distinction for the design and excellence of its embroidery and needlework.</p>","title":"Asilo of San Vicente de Paul","subtitle":null}}},"address":"Asilo de San Vicente de Paul, 1148 United Nations Avenue, Paco, Manila, Metro Manila","lat":14.58426,"macroAddress":"Paco, Manila","date":"1935","wikipedia":{"Asilo de San Vicente de Paul":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located above the eastern pedestrian gate.","lon":120.99046,"locPhoto":{"hash":"f2","height":1500,"width":1865,"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Asilo de San Vicente de Paul main gate.jpg"}},"Q55752357":{"region":"Central Luzon","name":"Mariveles","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Originally known as village of Kamaya belonging to the “Corregimiento” of Mariveles. Served as checking point for ships entering or leaving Manila Bay. Invaded by the Dutch in 1600 and 1609. Assumed its present name when the province of Bataan was created in 1754. Witnessed the surrender of Maj. Manuel L. Quezon, 1901; Gen. Artemio Ricarte, 1904; and Maj. Gen. Edward P. King, Jr., 1942. Starting point of the Death March, 9 April 1942.</p>","title":"Mariveles","subtitle":null},"photo":{"file":"Mariveles historical marker (cropped).JPG","credit":"Judgefloro","width":2439,"hash":"56","height":3293}}},"address":"Mariveles Municipal Hall, National Road, Brgy. Poblacion, Mariveles, Bataan","lat":14.43559,"date":"1950","macroAddress":"Mariveles, Bataan","wikipedia":{"Mariveles":"Mariveles, Bataan"},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.49033},"Q51221948":{"macroAddress":"Ermita, Manila","date":"1993-02-03","lat":14.58801,"name":"Sa mga Bayani ng Lungsod ng Maynila","region":"Metro Manila","address":"Manila City Hall, Taft Avenue cor. Antonio Villegas Street, Ermita, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":551,"hash":"08","width":396,"file":"SaMgaBayaniNgLungsodNgMaynila HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Na nag-iwan sa amin ng isang dakilang pamana na may karangalan dahil sa ginawa nilang pagtulong sa mga kulang-palad na walang kakayahan, sa pagtatanggol ng mga naaapi, sa pagsasanggalang ng patrimonyo ng lungsod at sa walang-takot ninyong pagbubuwis ng buhay para sa isang banal at kagalang-galang na pamamaraan. Kaya, kami sa ngayon ay binubuhay ang inyong kadakilaan sa pamamagitan ng panandang pangkasaysayang ito. Isang buhay na alaala at sagisag ng aming walang-hanggang pagpapahalaga at paggalang sa inyong kabayanihan at pagmakabayan.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Sa mga Bayani ng Lungsod ng Maynila"}}},"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.9819,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null},"Q43282748":{"lat":13.44778,"date":"1975-12-06","macroAddress":"Boac, Marinduque","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"title":"Liwasan ng Kalayaan","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>Dating kinatatayuan ng Casa Real noong panahon ng mga Kastila at pagkatapos ay naging Presidencia, sa pook na ito pinatay ang mga rebolusyonaryong kinabibilangan nina Kapitan Hermenegildo Flores at Remigio Medina noong 1897. Dito rin nilagdaan ni Koronel Maximo Abad at Kapitan H.H. Bandholtz noong ika-25 ng Abril 1901 ang kasunduang nagwakas sa Digmaang Pilipino–Amerikano sa Marinduque.</p>"}}},"address":"Mercader Street cor. 1 de Noviembre Street, Boac, Marinduque","region":"Mimaropa","name":"Liwasan ng Kalayaan","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.83987,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q46509859":{"wikipedia":{"Lapu-Lapu":true,"Battle of Mactan":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the front side of the pedestal inside an open building on the eastern side of the Mactan Shrine.","locPhoto":{"file":"Targa in ricordo di Lapu Lapu (Mactan).jpg","credit":"Paolobon140 {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4296,"height":2864,"hash":"bd"},"lon":124.01551,"name":"Lapulapu","region":"Central Visayas","details":{"en":{"photo":{"file":"Lapulapu-beschreibung.jpg","credit":"TrapperFrank {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":534,"height":687,"hash":"8a"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Here, on 27 April 1521, Lapulapu and his men repulsed the Spanish Invaders, killing their leader, Ferdinand Magellan. Thus Lapulapu became the first Filipino to have repelled European aggression.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Lapulapu"}}},"address":"Mactan Shrine, Punta Engaño Road, Lapu-Lapu","macroAddress":"Lapu-Lapu","date":"1951","lat":10.31081},"Q30127147":{"date":"1959","macroAddress":"Ghent, Belgium","lat":51.05221,"name":"José Rizal","region":"Overseas","details":{"fr":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>[Rizal] vivait dans cette maison quand il publia son roman “El Filibusterismo” en 1891.</p>","title":"José Rizal","subtitle":"1861–1896<br>Héros National des Philippines"},"photo":{"height":1332,"hash":"c1","credit":"Paul Drieghe {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"José Rizal gedenkplaat Henegouwenstraat Gent.png","width":972}}},"address":"Henegouwenstraat 9, Ghent, East Flanders, Flemish Region, Belgium","locPhoto":null,"lon":3.72602,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true,"El Filibusterismo":"El filibusterismo"},"locDesc":null},"Q52347797":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal on which a statue of Diego Silang stands.","wikipedia":{"Diego Silang":true},"lon":120.34476,"locPhoto":{"height":4608,"hash":"b2","width":3456,"file":"CabaLaUnionjf709.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}"},"address":"Caba Town Plaza, MacArthur Highway cor. Diego Silang Avenue, Caba, La Union","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>In this town, Caba, La Union, Diego Silang was born on December 16, 1739. At the time Caba was a barrio of Aringay then a part of Pangasinan province. Famed leader of the Ilocos Revolt (1762–1763), Silang was assassinated in Vigan on May 28, 1763. After his death the revolt was continued by his wife, Maria Josefa Gabriela whose execution on September 20, 1763, ended the uprising.</p>","title":"Diego Silang","subtitle":"(1730–1763)"},"photo":{"hash":"f1","height":4608,"file":"CabaLaUnionjf708.JPG","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":3456}}},"name":"Diego Silang","region":"Ilocos Region","macroAddress":"Caba, La Union","date":"1963","lat":16.43094},"Q54554216":{"lat":14.60982,"date":"2010","macroAddress":"Tondo, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Honorio Lopez","address":"Plaza Moriones, Moriones Street cor. Nicolas Zamora Street, Tondo, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"height":640,"hash":"36","file":"Honorio Lopez (1875 - 1958).jpg","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":480},"text":{"subtitle":"(1875–1958)","title":"Honorio Lopez","inscription":"<p>Mandudula at rebolusyonaryo. Isinilang sa Sta. Cruz, Maynila, 30 Disyembre 1875 at lumaki sa Tondo. Nagtapos ng bachiller en artes sa Colegio de San Juan de Letran. Sumapi sa Himagsikang Filipino. Naging tinyente kolonel at hepe ng rehimyento impanteriya Raxa Matanda “Vibora”, sa ilalim ng pamumuno ni Hen. Artemio Ricarte. Nagpatuloy ng pakikibaka laban sa mga Amerikano, 1899. May-akda ng Calendariong Filipino “Dimasalang”. Kasama ni Juan Abad na nagtatag ng La Juventud Filipina, isang kumpanya na nagtatanghal ng mga dulang makabayan. Naging patnugot ng pahayagang Libre, La Patria at La Consolidacion noong panahon ng mga Amerikano. Propesor ng agrimensura at segunda enseñanza; direktor ng kolehiyo, Instituto Patrio, ca. 1907–09. Asesor tecnico, Comite Central ng Union Agraria de Filipinas. Nahalal na konsehal ng Maynila, 1916–1919. Hinirang na kasapi ng Veterans Pension Board, 1954. Katulong na teknikal nina Pangulong Ramon Magsaysay at Carlos P. Garcia. Yumao, 3 Hulyo 1958. Ipinangalan sa kanya ang North Bay Boulevard sa Tondo ng pamahalaang Lungsod ng Maynila, bilang parangal sa kanyang legado, 1 Pebrero 1967.</p>"}}},"lon":120.968,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Honorio Lopez monument at Moriones, Tondo.jpg","width":3456,"hash":"73","height":4608},"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on a concrete mounting beside the Honorio Lopez Monument."},"Q54803613":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Malaueg Church":"Saint Raymond of Peñafort Parish Church (Malaueg)"},"lon":121.34531,"locPhoto":null,"details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>The ecclesiastical administration of this town was accepted by the Dominicans on April 26, 1608. The cornerstone of the early Church was laid on November 21, 1617. The Church and the Convent had been destroyed and rebuilt four times.</p>","title":"Church of Malaueg","subtitle":null},"photo":null}},"address":"Malaueg Church, Poblacion, Rizal, Cagayan","region":"Cagayan Valley","name":"Church of Malaueg","lat":17.84529,"macroAddress":"Rizal, Cagayan","date":"1939"},"Q28933344":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":124.73852,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Battle of Agusan Hill":true},"date":"2000-05-14","macroAddress":"Cagayan de Oro","lat":8.48813,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa Burol Agusan","inscription":"<p>Sa pook na ito, Mayo 14, 1900, ang unang kumpanya ng lakas panghimagsikan ng batalyong Mindanao sa pangunguna ni Kapitan Vicente Roa y Racines at mga kabalyeriya sa pamumuno ni Sarhento Uldarico Akut kasama ang mga macheteros, ay madugong nakipaglaban sa mga sundalong Amerikano ng ika-40 rehimyento ng boluntaryong impanterya ng Estados Unidos na pinangunahan ni Kapitan Walter B. Elliot. Si Kapitan Roa, kasama ang iba pang makabayang Pilipino ay buong kabayanihang namatay sa labanang ito.</p><p>Sa mga dakilang tagapagtanggol ng kalayaan ng dating lalawigan ng Misamis, lalung-lalo na yaong mga namatay sa Labanan sa Burol Agusan, ang panandang pangkasaysayang ito ay iniaalay ng sambayanang Pilipino bilang paggunita sa ikasandaang taon ng makasaysayang labanang ito.</p>"},"photo":null}},"address":"Cagayan de Oro","name":"Labanan sa Burol Agusan","region":"Northern Mindanao"},"Q55194866":{"details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":"(1907–1995)","title":"Angela Manalang Gloria","inscription":"<p>Makata at manunulat. Isinilang sa Guagua, Pampanga, 2 Agosto 1907. Nagtapos ng Bachelor of Arts major in Philosophy, summa cum laude, sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas, 1929. Ikinasal kay Celedonio Gloria, 1929. Naging patnugot ng Philippine Herald Magazine, 1929. Kauna-unahang Filipinang makata na nagsulat at naglimbag ng koleksyon ng mga tula sa wikang Ingles na pinamagatang Poems, 1940. Yumao sa Tabaco, Albay, 19 Agosto 1995.</p>"},"photo":{"height":960,"hash":"29","credit":"Tabunon {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Hm angelaManalangGloria.jpg","width":717}}},"address":"Smith, Bell and Company House, Rizal Street cor. J. B. Berces Street, Tabaco, Albay","region":"Bicol Region","name":"Angela Manalang Gloria","lat":13.35985,"date":"2007","macroAddress":"Tabaco, Albay","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Angela Manalang-Gloria":true},"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.73171},"Q28933113":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.82117,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Ozámiz":true},"lat":8.41615,"macroAddress":"Aloran, Misamis Occidental","date":"2014","address":"Town Plaza, Aloran, Misamis Occidental","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Isinilang sa Banisilon, Aloran, Misamis Occidental, 5 Mayo 1898. Nagtapos ng abogasya sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas, 1921. Gobernador ng Misamis Occidental, 1929-1931; kinatawan sa Lehislatura ng Pilipinas, 1931-1935; Kombensyon Konstitusyonal, 1934-1935; Pambansang Asambleya, 1935-1938. Naihalal muli sa asambleya ngunit tumanggi sa posisyon upang umanib sa kilusang gerilya at hukbong Amerikano sa Australia noong Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig. Dinakip ng mga Hapon at ipiniit sa Fort Santiago at Bilibid. Dinala sa Manila Chinese Cemetery kung saan siya at ang iba pang kasama ay pinugutan ng ulo at itinapon ang kanilang mga bangkay sa isang hukay lamang sa loob ng sementeryo, 30 Agosto 1944. Natagpuan ang mga labi, 1946. Inilipat ang mga labi at binigyan ng marangal na libing sa Cementerio del Norte sa Maynila, 9 Marso 1947.</p>","title":"Jose F. Ozamiz","subtitle":"(1898–1944)"}}},"region":"Northern Mindanao","name":"Jose F. Ozamiz"},"Q28927536":{"lon":123.4192,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"José Rizal":true},"date":"1989","macroAddress":"Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","lat":8.65627,"details":{"photo":{"width":958,"credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)","file":"Dito Lumunsad si Rizal historical marker.jpg","hash":"7e","height":1600},"text":{"en":{"title":"Site Where Rizal Landed","subtitle":null,"inscription":"<p>On this beach of Sta. Cruz, Jose Rizal landed at 7:00 o’clock PM on July 17, 1892 to begin the life an exile in Dapitan. With Captain Delgras and three artillery men, they walked through Sta. Cruz street with a “Farol de Combate” to the Casa Real where he was presented to Don Ricardo Carnicero, Spanish military governor of the district.</p>"},"tl":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Dito Lumunsad si Rizal","inscription":"<p>Sa dalampasigang ito ng Sta. Cruz, lumunsad si Jose Rizal noong ika-7 ng gabi, ika-17 ng Hulyo, 1892 upang simulan ang buhay-tapon sa Dapitan. Kasama ni Kapitan Delgras ang tatlong kawal ng artilyerya ay naglakad sina Rizal sa daang patungo sa Casa Real. Dito siya ipinakilala kay Don Ricardo Carnicero, ang Kastilang Gobernador Militar ng purok.</p>"}}},"address":"Sunset Boulevard, Dapitan, Zamboanga del Norte","name":"Site Where Rizal Landed","region":"Zamboanga Peninsula"},"Q35090763":{"details":{"en":{"photo":{"hash":"1c","height":707,"width":472,"file":"Historical Marker of Abolition of Tobacco Monopoly Monument.jpg","credit":"Carlo Joseph Moskito {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"},"text":{"inscription":"<p>Government tobacco monopoly formally established March 1782 by Governor Jose Basco y Vargas by virtue of the Royal Decree of 9 February 1780. </p><p> While this monopoly increased government revenue and stimulated the tobacco industry, it led to many abuses by the government officials. </p><p> Abolished in 1882 by the Royal Decree of 25 June 1881 during the incumbency of Governor Fernando Primo de Rivera.</p><p> Erected by the people as an expression of joy over the abolition of the tobacco monopoly.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Abolition of Tobacco Monopoly"}}},"address":"Abolition of Tobacco Monopoly Monument, Laoag, Ilocos Norte","region":"Ilocos Region","name":"Abolition of Tobacco Monopoly","lat":18.19524,"date":"1958","macroAddress":"Laoag, Ilocos Norte","locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.59263},"Q54153208":{"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.7153,"address":"Macabebe Municipal Hall, Poblacion, Macabebe, Pampanga","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Sinalakay ng mga rebolusyonaryo sa pamumuno ni Hen. Isidoro Torres ang umatras na puwersang Espanyol sa Macabebe, 25 Hunyo 1898. Nakuha ang artileriya ng mga Espanyol, 28 Hunyo 1898.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Labanan sa Macabebe"},"photo":{"credit":"Judgefloro","file":"Battle of Macabebe historical marker upclose.jpg","width":4608,"hash":"cb","height":3456}}},"name":"Labanan sa Macabebe","region":"Central Luzon","date":"2013-06-25","macroAddress":"Macabebe, Pampanga","lat":14.90835},"Q40317563":{"lon":120.97733,"locPhoto":null,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null,"macroAddress":"Intramuros, Manila","date":"2006","lat":14.59485,"details":{"tl":{"photo":{"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"NatPressClub HistoricalMarker Manila.jpg","width":617,"height":812,"hash":"3c"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"National Press Club","inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang samahan ng mga peryodista, 1952. Ipinatayo ang gusaling idinisenyo ni Angel Nakpil, 1955. Sa ikatlong palapag ipininta ni Vicente Manansala, Pambansang Alagad ng Sining, ang “Freedom of the Press” mural, Oktubre 1955. Kinilala sa pagpapalaganap ng pagkakaisa at pagkakaunawaan ng peryodista, pagtatanggol sa kalayaan sa pamamamhayag at pagtataguyod ng mga tuntunin at etika tungo sa pagsulong ng propesyon gayundin sa pakikipag-ugnayan sa iba’t ibang samahang lokal at internasyonal sa pagpapabuti ng kasanayan at kakayahan ng mga nasa propesyon.</p>"}}},"address":"Magallanes Drive, Intramuros, Manila, Metro Manila","name":"National Press Club","region":"Metro Manila"},"Q28871785":{"lon":122.23566,"locPhoto":{"hash":"43","height":1323,"file":"Miagao Church north bell tower.jpg","credit":"Rabosajr {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1000},"wikipedia":{"Miagao Church":true},"locDesc":"This historical marker is located at the base of the north bell tower at the right side of the church facade.","lat":10.6422,"date":"1977-04-14","macroAddress":"Miagao, Iloilo","region":"Western Visayas","name":"Simbahan ng Miag-ao","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Simbahan ng Miag-ao","inscription":"<p>Sa bisa ng Kautusan ng Pangulo Bilang 260, Agosto 1,1973 na sinusugan ng Kautusan Bilang 375, Enero 14, 1974, ito ay ipinahayag na Pambansang Palatandaang Makasaysayan.</p>"},"photo":{"width":2794,"file":"Simbahan ng Miag-ao historical marker.jpg","credit":"Photo: Ryomaandres; perspective correction: Eugene Alvin Villar (seav) {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","hash":"5b","height":2500}}},"address":"Miagao Church, Zulueta Avenue cor. Noble Street, Miagao, Iloilo"},"Q55753123":{"lon":120.54205,"locPhoto":{"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"ParishChurchofSt.CatherineofSienajf3477 06.JPG","width":3456,"height":4608,"hash":"34"},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the church facade, to the left of the main entrance.","wikipedia":null,"lat":14.77003,"macroAddress":"Samal, Bataan","date":"1939","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":3352,"hash":"27","credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Historical marker of Samal Church in Samal, Bataan.jpg","width":3175},"text":{"inscription":"<p>The spiritual ministration of Samal was entrusted to the Dominicans in 1596. The town was attacked by Dutch invaders in April, 1647, but the local garrison of Pampangos under the command of Alejo Aguas compelled the Dutch forces to retreat. The church and the convent built by the Rev. Jeronimo Belen, O.P., were ruined during the Dutch invasions. In 1898 the Church was burned by the Katipuneros to drive out their enemies in the Convent. The Rev. Justo Quesada rebuilt the Church and Convent in 1905.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Samal"}}},"address":"Samal Church, Guttieres Street, Brgy. San Roque, Samal, Bataan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Church of Samal"},"Q24702663":{"lat":13.93525,"date":"1982","macroAddress":"Gumaca, Quezon","details":{"tl":{"photo":{"hash":"23","height":3000,"width":4000,"credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Marker San Diego de Alcala Park Gumaca, Quezon.JPG"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ika-400 Taong Pagdiriwang ng Pagiging Kristiyano ng Bayan ng Gumaca","inscription":null}}},"address":"Km. 193 Maharlika Highway, Brgy. Rosario, Gumaca, Quezon","region":"Calabarzon","name":"Ika-400 Taong Pagdiriwang ng Pagiging Kristiyano ng Bayan ng Gumaca","locPhoto":{"width":2154,"file":"San Diego de Alcala Park Gumaca, Quezon.JPG","credit":"Nickrds09 {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","hash":"e6","height":4000},"lon":122.08428,"locDesc":"The marker is located on the pedestal of a statue of St. Didacus of Alcalá.","wikipedia":{"Gumaca":true}},"Q38406106":{"lat":14.56112,"date":"1991-06-11","macroAddress":"Malate, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Pablo Ocampo","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Abogado, editor, estadista at makabayan. Isinilang, Enero 25, 1853, Sta. Cruz, Maynila. Hinirang na Relator Audencia ng Maynila, 1888; promotor fiscal, Hukumang Unang Dulugan ng Tondo, 1889; Defensor de Oficio at Kalihim, Colegio de Abogado, 1890. Kagawad at isa sa kalihim ng Kongreso ng Malolos at Kagawad ng komiteng bumabalangkas sa Konstitusyon ng Malolos. Editor ng La Patria, kung saan nalathala ang mahahalagang suliranin at mga isyung pambayan kasama ang kanyang mga kuro-kurong makabayan. Ipinatapon sa Guam kasama ng ibang makabayang Filipino, 1901. Bumalik sa Pilipinas pagkaraang makapanumpa ng katapatan sa Estaods Unidos, 1902. Nahalal na Naninirahang Komisyonado sa E.U. 1907 at kasama ng delegasyong Amerikano sa Interparliamentary Union Conference sa Berlin, Alemanya, 1902. Nahalal na kinatawan ng Maynila sa Ikalawang Legislatura ng Pilipinas, 1919. Namatay Pebrero 5, 1925.</p>","subtitle":"(1853–1925)","title":"Pablo Ocampo"},"photo":{"file":"Pablo Ocampo historical marker.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro","width":1399,"hash":"79","height":2163}}},"address":"Pablo Ocampo Street cor. Adriatico Street, Malate, Manila, Metro Manila","locPhoto":{"hash":"d1","height":2736,"width":3648,"credit":"Theodore Uy {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Pablo Ocampo-B.JPG"},"lon":120.99229,"wikipedia":{"Pablo Ocampo":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the pedestal of a statue of Pablo Ocampo on the center island at the junction of Pablo Ocampo Street and Adriatico Street."},"Q54552791":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":120.98022,"wikipedia":null,"locDesc":null,"lat":14.59946,"date":"1983-09-12","macroAddress":"Santa Cruz, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Justiniano Asuncion","address":"Santa Cruz Church, Plaza Santa Cruz, Santa Cruz, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Pangunahing pintor na kilalang-kilala sa “Capitan Ting.” Ipinanganak noong Setyembre 26, 1816 sa Sta. Cruz, Maynila. Nag-aral sa Escuela de Dibujo, 1834. Capitan municipal ng Sta. Cruz, gumuhit ng bantog na Koronasyon ng Birhen, Birhen ng Antipolo, Filomena Asuncion at Romana A. Carillo. Gumuhit din ng sinlaki ng taong larawan nina San Agustin, San Geronimo, San Ambrosio at San Gregorio Magno na dating nasa Simbahan ng Sta. Cruz, itinanghal ang mga ito sa Pambansang Museo at inilipat sa pag-iingat ng \"Kayamanan\" ng Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas. Namatay noong 1896.</p>","title":"Justiniano Asuncion","subtitle":"(1816–1896)"},"photo":{"hash":"12","height":3456,"width":4608,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Justiniano Asuncion historical marker at the Santa Cruz Church, Manila.jpg"}}}},"Q46123869":{"macroAddress":"Magdalena, Laguna","date":"2017-12-14","lat":14.19995,"name":"Emilio Jacinto","region":"Calabarzon","details":{"tl":{"photo":null,"text":{"inscription":"<p>Rebolusyonaryo at bayani. Isinilang sa Tondo, Maynila, 15 Disyembre 1875. Nag-aral sa Kolehiyo ng San Juan de Letran at Unibersidad ng Sto. Tomas. Umanib sa Katipunan na may pangalang pandigma na Pingkian at naging Kalihim ng Samahan, 1894. Sumulat ng “Kartilya,” “Katipunan nang manga A.N.B. – Sa may nasang makisanib sa Katipunang ito.” Isa sa mga nagtatag ng “Kalayaan,” ang pahayagan ng Katipunan, 1896. Kasamang sumalakay sa San Juan del Monte upang kubkubin ang El Polvorin bilang pagsisimula ng malawakang paghihimagsik laban sa mga Espanyol, 30 Agosto 1896. Hinirang ni Bonifacio bilang punong hukbo sa hilaga. Pinamunuan ang Labanan sa Maimpis, Magdalena, Laguna kung saan malubha siyang nasugatan, 27 Pebrero 1898. May akda ng “Gising na, mga Tagalog!” (1895); “Sa Bayang Tinubuan” (1896); “A la Patria” (1897); “Liwanag at Dilim” at iba pa. Yumao sa Sta. Cruz, Laguna, 16 Abril 1899.</p>","title":"Emilio Jacinto","subtitle":"1875–1899"}}},"address":"Magdalena, Laguna","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.4296,"wikipedia":{"Emilio Jacinto":true},"locDesc":null},"Q53862524":{"locPhoto":null,"lon":122.3754,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":{"Tigbauan":true},"macroAddress":"Tigbauan, Iloilo","date":"1975-12-07","lat":10.67443,"details":{"tl":{"text":{"title":"Tigbauan","subtitle":"(1575–1975)","inscription":"<p>Itinatag bilang bisita ng Oton noong 1575 at naging parokya noong 1580. Naging lunan ng kaunaunahang paaralan at dormitoryo sa Pilipinas na itinatag ni Pedro Chirino, S.J. noong 1592. Lumahok sa himagsikan laban sa mga Kasila noong 1898 at sa pakikidigma laban sa mga Amerikano noong 1899–1901. Itinatag ang pamahalaang sibil noong 1901. Lumunsad ang mga Amerikano sa nayon ng Parara noong ika-18 ng Marso, 1945 bilang unang hakbang sa pagpapalaya sa Panay. Piniling maging lunan ng Southeast Asian Fisheries Development Center noong 1973.</p>"},"photo":{"hash":"78","height":2217,"width":1557,"file":"Tigbauan historical marker.JPG","credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}"}}},"address":"Tigbauan Church, Allera Street, Tigbauan, Iloilo","name":"Tigbauan","region":"Western Visayas"},"Q28933475":{"lat":8.19101,"macroAddress":"Iligan","date":"2002","details":{"en":{"photo":{"height":579,"hash":"68","width":648,"file":"Macapagal-Macaraeg House historical marker.jpg","credit":"National Historical Commission of the Philippines (NHCP)"},"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Macapagal-Macaraeg Ancestral House","inscription":"<p>Declared a heritage house by the National Historical Institute, 14 August 2002.</p>"}}},"address":"Macapagal-Macaraeg House, National Highway, Sitio Timoga, Brgy. Buru-un, Iligan","region":"Northern Mindanao","name":"Macapagal-Macaraeg Ancestral House","locPhoto":null,"lon":124.17882,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q45161681":{"wikipedia":{"Colon Street":true},"locDesc":null,"locPhoto":null,"lon":123.90367,"name":"Daang Colon","region":"Central Visayas","address":"Colon Street cor. Mabini Street, Cebu City","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Ang daang Colon, kilala rin bilang Parian, ang pinakamatandang daan sa Pilipinas. Ipinatayo ng mga Kastila na dumating sa Cebu noong 1565 lulan ng plotang binubuo ng mga sasakyang-dagat na San Pedro, San Pablo at San Juan sa pamumuno ni Miguel Lopez de Legazpi.</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Daang Colon"},"photo":{"credit":"Joannerfabregas {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Colon Street Historical Marker.JPG","width":2976,"height":3968,"hash":"5b"}}},"date":"1961-10-16","macroAddress":"Cebu City","lat":10.29797},"Q24715649":{"lat":13.96331,"macroAddress":"Sariaya, Quezon","date":"2008-05-14","address":"Gen. Luna Street cor. Rizal Street, Sariaya, Quezon","details":{"en":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Declared a heritage house by the National Historical Institute 14 May 2008</p>","subtitle":null,"title":"Natalio Enriquez House"},"photo":{"width":3456,"credit":"Ramon FVelasquez {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","file":"Sariaya,Mansion,TownCenterjf0265 15.JPG","height":4608,"hash":"df"}}},"region":"Calabarzon","name":"Natalio Enriquez House","locPhoto":null,"lon":121.52454,"locDesc":null,"wikipedia":null},"Q41643044":{"lon":120.81257,"locPhoto":{"height":603,"hash":"9d","width":877,"credit":"Shubert Ciencia {CC BY 2.0}","file":"Historical markers on the facade of Barasoain Church.jpg"},"wikipedia":{"Malolos Congress":true,"Barasoain Church":true,"Malolos Constitution":true},"locDesc":"The historical marker is located on the wall to the left of the central main door of the church.","lat":14.84628,"date":"1940","macroAddress":"Malolos, Bulacan","region":"Central Luzon","name":"Church of Barasoain","details":{"en":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Church of Barasoain","inscription":"<p>Barasoain was originally part of Malolos until its official separation on August 31, 1859. In 1903 it became part of Malolos again. The old Church constructed by Rev. Francisco Royo, O.S.A., was destroyed by fire in May, 1884, but rebuilt by Rev. Juan Giron, O.S.A., in 1885. This Church was the seat of the Revolutionary Congress which convened from the middle of September, 1898, to the last week of February, 1899, under the presidency of Pedro A. Paterno. Among the important measures passed by the Congress was the Malolos Constitution, drafted chiefly by Felipe G. Calderon.</p>"},"photo":{"file":"Philippines Historical Committee Marker for Barasoain Church.JPG","credit":"Cool2compute {CC BY‑SA 3.0}","width":1989,"height":2000,"hash":"da"}}},"address":"Barasoain Church, Paseo del Congreso cor. Don Antonio Bautista Street, Malolos, Bulacan"},"Q54617934":{"lat":14.60387,"date":"2013-06-14","macroAddress":"Binondo, Manila","region":"Metro Manila","name":"Tiong Se Academy","details":{"tl":{"text":{"inscription":"<p>Itinatag ang Anglo Chinese School ni Engracio Palanca (Tankang), unang Tsinong Konsul–Heneral sa bansa, upang tugunan ang pangangailangang pang-edukasyon ng mga Tsino sa Pilipinas sa pamamagitan ng paglikom ng pondo mula sa Comunidad de Chino. Pormal na nagbukas ng klase sa bakuran ng Imperial Chinese Consulate General, 15 Abril 1899. Inilipat ang paaralan sa Kalye San Fernando, 1899; Kalye Salazar, 1909; Kalye Sacristia (ngayo’y Kalye Ongpin), 1910 at Kalye Sta. Elena, 1912. Isinara noong pananakop ng Hapon, 1942 at muling binuksan, 1945. Naging Tiong Se Academy alinsunod sa Pilipinasasyon ng mga paaralang banyaga sa bansa, 24 Pebrero 1975. Nagsilbing huwaran ng sistemang pang-edukasyon ng mga Tsino at Tsinong Pilipino sa Pilipinas.</p>","title":"Tiong Se Academy","subtitle":null},"photo":{"height":871,"hash":"d2","width":601,"credit":"Ryomaandres {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","file":"Tiong Se Academy Historical Marker.jpg"}}},"address":"Philippine Tiong Se Academy, 708 Sta. Elena Street, Binondo, Manila, Metro Manila","locPhoto":null,"lon":120.97254,"wikipedia":{"Philippine Tiong Se Academy":"Tiong Se Academy"},"locDesc":null},"Q24058217":{"locDesc":"The historical marker is located to the left of the main entrance of the house.","wikipedia":{"Nakpil–Bautista House":"Bahay Nakpil-Bautista"},"locPhoto":{"file":"09626jfBautista Street Bahay Nakpil Bautista Ancestral House Quiapo Manilafvf 06.jpg","credit":"Judgefloro {CC BY‑SA 4.0}","width":4608,"height":3456,"hash":"2d"},"lon":120.98465,"address":"Nakpil–Bautista House, 432 Ariston Bautista Street, Quiapo, Manila, Metro Manila","details":{"tl":{"text":{"subtitle":null,"title":"Ang Bahay ng mga Nakpil at Bautista","inscription":"<p>Ipinatayo ni Ariston Bautista Lin (1863–1928) at ng kanyang maybahay na si Petrona Nakpil sa pamamagitan ng kilalang arkitektong si Arcadio Arellano noong 1914.</p><p>Si Dr. Bautista ay isang manggagamot, pilantropo at imbentor ng isang gamot na panlaban sa kolera. Nanirahan din dito sina Julio Nakpil (1877–1960), rebolusyonaryo at konpositor ng mga awit ng Katipunan; kanyang asawang si Gregoria de Jesus (1876–1943), lakambini ng Katipunan at biyuda ni Andres Bonifacio; kanilang anak na si Juan (1899–1986) at pinsang buo nitong si Angel (1914–1979), na pawang mga tanyag na arkitekto.</p><p>Sa bahay ding ito ay dating katatagpuan ng Plateria Nakpil na dinadayo dahil sa mga masusing panindang mga alahas.</p>"},"photo":{"credit":"Eugene Alvin Villar (seav)","file":"Ang Bahay ng mga Nakpil at Bautista historical marker.jpg","width":2138,"height":3500,"hash":"aa"}}},"name":"Ang Bahay ng mga Nakpil at Bautista","region":"Metro Manila","date":"1995","macroAddress":"Quiapo, Manila","lat":14.59846}}